{"title":"Wikinews interviews Christopher Hill, U.S. Republican Party presidential candidate","wikiTitle":"Wikinews_interviews_Christopher_Hill,_U.S._Republican_Party_presidential_candidate","wid":1837952,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-08T00:53:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, William S. Saturn] What qualifications do you have that will assist you in executing the duties of president?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Why run for president? Why not run for a lower office that you would be more likely to win and effect change?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Why did you choose to run in the Republican Party?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WS] How do you plan to get into the Republican debates and make an impact on polls?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] If you do not receive the Republican nomination, would you consider running as a TEMPLATE[w, Third party (United States), third party candidate]?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Other than yourself, which candidates have you supported for president in previous primary campaigns?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] What are your thoughts on the job Barack Obama has done as president?  Specifically, what would you have done differently?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] If elected, what would constitute a successful presidency for you?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Which individuals would you like to see in a Hill administration?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Anything else you would like to add?"],["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMitt Romney wins the 2012 New Hampshire Republican primary, date\u003dJanuary 12, 2012]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dWikinews interviews Buddy Roemer, U.S. Republican Party presidential candidate, date\u003dOctober 30, 2011]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.campaignon.com/presidential/about.php, title\u003dChris Hill for President, author\u003d, pub\u003dCampaignON, date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015 (accessed)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://results.enr.clarityelections.com/AZ/36496/75798/en/summary.html, title\u003dAZ - Election Results, author\u003d, pub\u003dState of Arizona, date\u003dMarch 19, 2012 (last updated)]"],["Hill campaign Twitter account","Supplementary links for interview responses:"]],"links":[{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"New_Hampshire","description":"New Hampshire"},{"id":"Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"U.S. Republican Party"},{"id":"United_States_presidential_election,_2016","description":"2016 presidential nomination"},{"id":"Arizona","description":"Arizona"},{"id":"Massachusetts","description":"Massachusetts"},{"id":"Mitt_Romney","description":"Mitt Romney"},{"id":"Barack_Obama","description":"Barack Obama"},{"id":"NATO","description":"NATO"},{"id":"Buddy_Roemer","description":"Buddy Roemer"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"https://twitter.com/hill4president","description":"Hill campaign Twitter account"},{"id":"http://www.campaignon.com/presidential/presidentialqualifications.php","description":"Presidential qualifications"},{"id":"http://www.livefreeordiealliance.org/VoterResources/2016_Presidential_Candidates/tabid/3290/Default.aspx","description":"Listing as a 2014 Presidential contender"},{"id":"http://www.campaignon.com/presidential/termlimits.php","description":"Term Limits"},{"id":"http://www.campaignon.com/presidential/taxes.php","description":"Tax System"},{"id":"http://www.campaignon.com/presidential/livingwage.php","description":"Living Wage"},{"id":"http://www.campaignon.com/presidential/peaceforamerica.php","description":"Peace and Security"}],"sections":["Interview","Related news","Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 6, 2015] TEMPLATE[2016_US_Presidential_Election] TEMPLATE[image, Hill for President] U.S. TEMPLATE[w, United States Air Force, Air Force] veteran and airline pilot Christopher V. Hill of New Hampshire took some time to talk with Wikinews about his campaign for the U.S. Republican Party\u0027s 2016 presidential nomination.","Hill served in TEMPLATE[w, Operation Desert Storm], flying about fifty combat missions.  Shortly after the war, he returned to civilian life, working as a loader and then a pilot for the TEMPLATE[w, United Parcel Service].  In 2010, he organized the \"Pilots and Patriots Defending the Constitution\" ahead of the that year\u0027s midterm elections.  Hill ran his first campaign for president in 2012, seeking the Republican nomination.  In that cycle, he appeared on the primary ballot in two states, receiving 108 votes in the TEMPLATE[w, New Hampshire primary] and 139 in the Arizona primary.  Former Massachusetts governor Mitt Romney ultimately received the nomination and lost to incumbent president Barack Obama.","With Wikinews reporter William S. Saturnâ, Hill discusses his 2016 campaign, his political background, and his policy proposals.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Christopher Hill] My Presidential qualifications are rooted in my service as an Officer in the United States Air Force.  I took the Oath to our TEMPLATE[w, United States Constitution, Constitution] at 22 years old. I understood it was an Oath to America and ALL of our people.  Politicians profess an Oath to this nation but once in office pursue their party agenda and reward their voters.  As President, I will serve ALL of the people in America, guided by the Constitution.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] When I was a young man in Air Force TEMPLATE[w, Reserve Officers\u0027 Training Corps, ROTC] I was chosen to attend a unique Pilot Training Program called Euro-NATO Joint Jet Pilot Training.  The Air Force only selected 180 Officers a year from the Academy, Squadron Officer School and ROTC to attend.  I volunteered for that program because I knew I wanted to be a Fighter Pilot and at the \"Tip of the Spear.\"  In those days it was all or nothing.  If you graduated you were assigned a fighter, if you were not quite fighter pilot material you had no recourse to fly another aircraft, you were washed out.  Congress has proven itself ineffective as a body.  To make a difference in America you must have the \"TEMPLATE[wikt, bully pulpit, Bully Pulpit]\" and speak to the People. The President has that pulpit.  All or nothing.  I never wanted to make politics a career.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] My ties to the Republican party date back to 1979 when I volunteered for TEMPLATE[w, Ronald Reagan] and his campaign in New Hampshire. In those days I believed there was a difference in the parties.  Today, like many Americans, I am skeptical.  I understand third party candidates have no success.  I hope to lead the Republican party in a new direction for working middle class Americans.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] In order to be invited to the debates, we must raise money and poll nationally.  This is an effort that is underway.  Recently we were listed in New Hampshire and nationally with Politics1.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] No, I will back the nominee of the Republican party in 2016.  After that, I may reconsider.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] Reagan in 80 and 84, TEMPLATE[w, George H. W. Bush, [George H. W.] Bush] in 88 and 92, TEMPLATE[w, Phil Gramm, [Phil] Gramm] in 96, TEMPLATE[w, George W. Bush, [George W.] Bush] in 2000 and 04, Romney in 08.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] President Obama has an agenda that represents the far left wing of his party.  His use of the Presidency to further this agenda has in many ways been unconstitutional.  Specifically, altering law once it is passed to accommodate his voting blocs.  His direction to TEMPLATE[w, Eric Holder] to enforce some laws and not others is another example.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] Achieving four goals:",":::#Term Limits for Congress and the Courts returning government to the People.",":::#Implementing a Tax System that allows working Americans making under $250,000 to keep all of their money.   Closing Loopholes and putting in place a system that is transparent and works.",":::#Passing a Living Wage program lifting people out of poverty.",":::#Returning America to a state of Peace and Security.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] I would like to bring People from the TEMPLATE[w, Heartland (United States), heartland of America] that make this nation work.  We have had too many decades of TEMPLATE[w, Ivy League] elites and Professors immersed in theory.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Hill] A final thought.  America is a nation that will endure.  I believe it is our responsibility to pass on the same opportunities to future generations that were promised to us.  As President, I intend to keep that promise!","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[interview]","* Presidential qualifications","* Listing as a 2014 Presidential contender","* Goals",":* Term Limits",":* Tax System",":* Living Wage",":* Peace and Security","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:New_Hampshire","description":"Category:New Hampshire"},{"id":"Category:Barack_Obama","description":"Category:Barack Obama"},{"id":"Category:Mitt_Romney","description":"Category:Mitt Romney"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:2016_United_States_presidential_election","description":"Category:2016 United States presidential election"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 6, 2015"]},{"name":"2016_US_Presidential_Election","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Hill for President"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Air Force","Air Force"]},{"name":"w","description":["Operation Desert Storm"]},{"name":"w","description":["United Parcel Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["New Hampshire primary"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["William S. Saturn"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Christopher Hill"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Constitution","Constitution"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reserve Officers\u0027 Training Corps","ROTC"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["bully pulpit","Bully Pulpit"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ronald Reagan"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"w","description":["Third party (United States)","third party candidate"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"w","description":["George H. W. Bush","[George H. W.] Bush"]},{"name":"w","description":["Phil Gramm","[Phil] Gramm"]},{"name":"w","description":["George W. Bush","[George W.] Bush"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eric Holder"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Heartland (United States)","heartland of America"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ivy League"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Hill"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMitt Romney wins the 2012 New Hampshire Republican primary","date\u003dJanuary 12, 2012"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dWikinews interviews Buddy Roemer, U.S. Republican Party presidential candidate","date\u003dOctober 30, 2011"]},{"name":"interview","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.campaignon.com/presidential/about.php","title\u003dChris Hill for President","author\u003d","pub\u003dCampaignON","date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015 (accessed)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://results.enr.clarityelections.com/AZ/36496/75798/en/summary.html","title\u003dAZ - Election Results","author\u003d","pub\u003dState of Arizona","date\u003dMarch 19, 2012 (last updated)"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Wikinews","Wikinews"]}
{"title":"French campaigning film director RenÃ© Vautier dies","wikiTitle":"French_campaigning_film_director_RenÃ©_Vautier_dies","wid":1838502,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-08T00:52:10Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.english.rfi.fr/africa/20150105-french-anti-colonial-film-maker-vautier-dies, title\u003dFrench anti-colonial film-maker Vautier dies, author\u003d, pub\u003dRadio France Internationale, date\u003dJanuary 5, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dw.de/anti-censorship-film-maker-vautier-dies/a-18170366, title\u003dAnti-censorship film-maker Vautier dies, author\u003dIan P. Johnson, pub\u003dDeutsche Welle, date\u003dJanuary 4, 2014]"]],"links":[{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"Algeria","description":"Algeria"},{"id":"Burkina_Faso","description":"Burkina Faso"},{"id":"Zimbabwe","description":"Zimbabwe"},{"id":"South_Africa","description":"South Africa"},{"id":"French_Resistance","description":"French Resistance"},{"id":"World_War_II","description":"World War II"},{"id":"Paris","description":"Paris"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 5, 2015] TEMPLATE[France] TEMPLATE[w, RenÃ© Vautier], the self-described \"most censored director in France\", died yesterday aged 86. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[:fr:w:Utilisateur:Vivre la rue, Vivre la Rue]]] Vautier focused on French colonies. He made over 150 films and targeted what he described as \"lack of teachers and doctors, the crimes committed by the French Army in the name of France, the instrumentalization of the colonized peoples\". One topic of particular focus was the war in Algeria. Between 1954 and 1962 Algerians fought for, and won, their independence from France.","His work on the conflict included Algeria in Flames in 1958 and TEMPLATE[w, Avoir 20 ans dans les AurÃ¨s, 20 Years in Aures], which also investigated post-conflict Algeria and won 1972\u0027s international critics\u0027 award at the TEMPLATE[w, Cannes Film Festival]. That film looked at killings by young French conscripts.","In 1950 he was imprisoned in France for a year for, amongst other things, unauthorised filming in Upper Volta, a colonial region that became Burkina Faso. His footage was seized but he salvaged sufficient material to make TEMPLATE[w, Afrique 50], a seventeen-minute work that was banned in France until 1990.","His work in the 60s and 70s looked at racism in former Rhodesia, which is now Zimbabwe, and in South Africa. He compared his investigative footage with the official position of local authorities. In 1974 he co-directed TEMPLATE[w, Humain, trop humain, Human, Too Human], an almost-unspoken film depicting TEMPLATE[w, Citroen] car manufacture in France.","Other topics he covered include pollution, TEMPLATE[w, women\u0027s rights], and the French far-right.","Vautier\u0027s achievements outside of directing include a TEMPLATE[w, hunger strike] in 1973 against what he viewed as political censorship. French law was changed. His activism went back to age 15 when he joined the French Resistance during World War II. He documented himself in a 1998 book. In the 1960s he headed back to newly-independent Algeria to teach film directing.","Vautier himself was trained at the TEMPLATE[w, Institut des hautes Ã©tudes cinÃ©matographiques, Advanced Institute for Cinemagraphic Studies], in Paris.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Algeria","description":"Category:Algeria"},{"id":"Category:Burkina_Faso","description":"Category:Burkina Faso"},{"id":"Category:Zimbabwe","description":"Category:Zimbabwe"},{"id":"Category:South_Africa","description":"Category:South Africa"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Film","description":"Category:Film"},{"id":"Category:Free_speech","description":"Category:Free speech"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Journalism","description":"Category:Journalism"},{"id":"Category:French_Resistance","description":"Category:French Resistance"},{"id":"Category:World_War_II","description":"Category:World War II"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 5, 2015"]},{"name":"France","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["RenÃ© Vautier"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[:fr:w:Utilisateur:Vivre la rue","Vivre la Rue]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Avoir 20 ans dans les AurÃ¨s","20 Years in Aures"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cannes Film Festival"]},{"name":"w","description":["Afrique 50"]},{"name":"w","description":["Humain, trop humain","Human, Too Human"]},{"name":"w","description":["Citroen"]},{"name":"w","description":["women\u0027s rights"]},{"name":"w","description":["hunger strike"]},{"name":"w","description":["Institut des hautes Ã©tudes cinÃ©matographiques","Advanced Institute for Cinemagraphic Studies"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.english.rfi.fr/africa/20150105-french-anti-colonial-film-maker-vautier-dies","title\u003dFrench anti-colonial film-maker Vautier dies","author\u003d","pub\u003dRadio France Internationale","date\u003dJanuary 5, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dw.de/anti-censorship-film-maker-vautier-dies/a-18170366","title\u003dAnti-censorship film-maker Vautier dies","author\u003dIan P. Johnson","pub\u003dDeutsche Welle","date\u003dJanuary 4, 2014"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Algeria in Flames","TEMPLATE[w, Avoir 20 ans dans les AurÃ¨s, 20 Years in Aures]","TEMPLATE[w, Afrique 50]","TEMPLATE[w, Humain, trop humain, Human, Too Human]"]}
{"title":"FBI investigating explosion near NAACP office in Colorado Springs","wikiTitle":"FBI_investigating_explosion_near_NAACP_office_in_Colorado_Springs","wid":1842757,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-08T00:56:14Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://gazette.com/possible-explosion-heard-outside-colorado-springs-barbershop/article/1544124, title\u003dFBI looking for man regarding explosion near Colorado Springs NAACP office, author\u003d Kassondra Cloos and Lisa Walton, pub\u003dThe Gazette (Colorado Springs), date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/jan/07/fbi-explosion-naacp-office-colorado, title\u003dFBI hunts Colorado man in connection with explosion near NAACP office, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_27267521/colorado-springs-police-responding-explosion-reports-at-naacp, title\u003d\u0027Improvised explosive device\u0027 set off near Colorado Springs NAACP office, author\u003dJesse Paul, pub\u003dThe Denver Post, date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Colorado_Springs,_Colorado","description":"Colorado Springs"},{"id":"Colorado","description":"Colorado"},{"id":"National_Association_for_the_Advancement_of_Colored_People","description":"National Association for the Advancement of Colored People"},{"id":"Federal_Bureau_of_Investigation","description":"FBI"},{"id":"Bureau_of_Alcohol,_Tobacco,_Firearms_and_Explosives","description":"Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] An explosion that took place in a barber shop next door to the Colorado Springs, Colorado office of the National Association for the Advancement of Colored People (NAACP) yesterday is currently being investigated by the FBI\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Joint Terrorism Task Force], as well as the Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives. Officials said the explosive device was placed next to a can of gasoline but the gasoline did not ignite after the device detonated.","The FBI are seeking a balding white male, aged about 40 years old, as a \"person of interest\" connected to the case. The FBI statement continued: \"He may be driving a 2000 or older model dirty, white pick-up truck with paneling, a dark colored bed liner, open tailgate, and a missing or covered license plate\".","FBI Special Agent Amy Sanders said: \"The investigation is ongoing and it is not known at this time if the NAACP or a business in the vicinity was the intended target\".","Gene Southerland, owner of Mr. G\u0027s Hair Design Studios, said: \"I was cutting somebody\u0027s hair and I heard the explosion [...] It was such a loud explosion that some plastic containers fell off the shelf.\" Southerland continued: \"Some neighbors came out and said they saw a Caucasian gentleman get into a white truck [...] It was such a beautiful day and everything, sunny. And in broad daylight, you hear this explosion. It\u0027s frightening\".","Henry Allen Jr, the president of the Colorado Springs branch of the NAACP, told reporters: \"We\u0027ll move on. This won\u0027t deter us from doing the job we want to do in the community.\" The NAACP national office put out a statement stating that the group \"looks forward to a full and thorough investigation into this matter by federal agents and local law enforcement\".","TEMPLATE[w, US House of Representatives, US Congressman] TEMPLATE[w, Doug Lamborn] told Colorado Springs newspaper TEMPLATE[w, The Gazette (Colorado Springs), The Gazette] by email: \"I\u0027m thankful that none of the volunteers or employees of the Colorado Springs NAACP were injured in today\u0027s apparent bombing [...] I hope that the FBI investigation is able to swiftly apprehend the people responsible for this act of violence and intimidation.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Colorado","description":"Category:Colorado"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:FBI","description":"Category:FBI"},{"id":"Category:Bureau_of_Alcohol,_Tobacco,_Firearms_and_Explosivesâ","description":"Category:Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosivesâ"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Colorado_Springs,_Colorado","description":"Category:Colorado Springs, Colorado"},{"id":"Category:National_Association_for_the_Advancement_of_Colored_People","description":"Category:National Association for the Advancement of Colored People"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 7, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Joint Terrorism Task Force"]},{"name":"w","description":["US House of Representatives","US Congressman"]},{"name":"w","description":["Doug Lamborn"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Gazette (Colorado Springs)","The Gazette"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://gazette.com/possible-explosion-heard-outside-colorado-springs-barbershop/article/1544124","title\u003dFBI looking for man regarding explosion near Colorado Springs NAACP office","author\u003d Kassondra Cloos and Lisa Walton","pub\u003dThe Gazette (Colorado Springs)","date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/jan/07/fbi-explosion-naacp-office-colorado","title\u003dFBI hunts Colorado man in connection with explosion near NAACP office","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.denverpost.com/news/ci_27267521/colorado-springs-police-responding-explosion-reports-at-naacp","title\u003d\u0027Improvised explosive device\u0027 set off near Colorado Springs NAACP office","author\u003dJesse Paul","pub\u003dThe Denver Post","date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Gazette (Colorado Springs), The Gazette]"]}
{"title":"John Boehner re-elected as US House Speaker despite conservative challenge","wikiTitle":"John_Boehner_re-elected_as_US_House_Speaker_despite_conservative_challenge","wid":1843528,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-06T01:33:18Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2015-01-07/boehner-pays-back-republicans-for-voting-against-him-for-speaker, title\u003dBoehner Takes His Revenge on Republicans Opposing Him for Speaker, author\u003dJonathan Allen, David Weigel, pub\u003dBloomberg Politics, date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-fix/wp/2015/01/06/here-are-the-republicans-who-voted-against-john-boehner-for-speaker/, title\u003dHere are the Republicans who voted against John Boehner for speaker, author\u003dAaron Blake, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/boehner-faces-leadership-challenge-from-conservative-members/2015/01/06/1c047668-95c1-11e4-aabd-d0b93ff613d5_story.html, title\u003dBoehner survives leadership challenge from conservative members, author\u003dRobert Costa, David A. Fahrenthold, Sean Sullivan, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/jan/06/john-boehner-house-speaker-leadership-challenge, title\u003dBoehner maintains House Speaker post despite biggest revolt in a century, author\u003dAmanda Holpuch and Paul Lewis, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] TEMPLATE[Image, US House of Representatives] Representative TEMPLATE[w, John Boehner] was re-elected as Speaker of the TEMPLATE[w, US] TEMPLATE[w, US House of Representatives, House of Representatives] on Tuesday despite a right-wing rebellion of 25 members. Boehner\u0027s appointment as Speaker passed with 216 of the 408 votes. TEMPLATE[w, Republican Party (US), Republican] Senator TEMPLATE[w, Mitch McConnell] was also sworn in on Tuesday as the TEMPLATE[w, US Senate, Senate] majority leader, marking the first time in eight years when Republicans have controlled both the House and Senate.","The challengers to Boehner came primarily from the libertarian and hard right wing of the party, sometimes associated with the TEMPLATE[w, Tea Party movement].  One â TEMPLATE[w, Brian Babin] â simply voted \u0027present\u0027 while the remaining twenty four voted for a variety of other candidates. Twelve voted for Representative TEMPLATE[w, Daniel Webster], three voted for Representative TEMPLATE[w, Louis Gohmert], two voted for Representative TEMPLATE[w, Ted Yoho], and two for Representative TEMPLATE[w, Jim Jordan]. There were also votes for Representatives TEMPLATE[w, Jeff Duncan], TEMPLATE[w, Kevin McCarthy] and TEMPLATE[w, Trey Gowdy], as well as votes for Senators TEMPLATE[w, Rand Paul] and TEMPLATE[w, Jeff Sessions].","Two of those voting against Boehner, Daniel Webster and TEMPLATE[w, Richard B. Nugent], were not reappointed to the TEMPLATE[w, House Rules Committee]. Speaking to reporters, Boehner said the House Republicans were \"going to have a family conversation, which we had this morning, about bringing our team together\".","Reacting to his removal from the Rules Committee, Richard Nugent stated: \"Iâm not on Rules, I will tell you that [...] But it\u0027s not really clear that I couldn\u0027t get back on it. I carried a lot of water on the Rules Committee, took a lot of tough votes.\" Webster said he was less interested in being on the Committee: \"Do you see people running to get on it?\"","Following the election of Boehner and McConnell, the White House announced President TEMPLATE[w, Barack Obama] would veto planned legislation by Republicans to start the construction of the TEMPLATE[w, Keystone XL] oil pipeline. White House press secretary Josh Earnest told reporters: \"If this bill passes this Congress, the president wouldn\u0027t sign it\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:John_Boehner","description":"Category:John Boehner"},{"id":"Category:Tea_Party_movement","description":"Category:Tea Party movement"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:US_Congress","description":"Category:US Congress"},{"id":"Category:US_House_of_Representatives","description":"Category:US House of Representatives"},{"id":"Category:US_Senate","description":"Category:US Senate"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Mitch_McConnell","description":"Category:Mitch McConnell"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 8, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"Image","description":["US House of Representatives"]},{"name":"w","description":["John Boehner"]},{"name":"w","description":["US"]},{"name":"w","description":["US House of Representatives","House of Representatives"]},{"name":"w","description":["Republican Party (US)","Republican"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mitch McConnell"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Senate","Senate"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tea Party movement"]},{"name":"w","description":["Brian Babin"]},{"name":"w","description":["Daniel Webster"]},{"name":"w","description":["Louis Gohmert"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ted Yoho"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jim Jordan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jeff Duncan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kevin McCarthy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Trey Gowdy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rand Paul"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jeff Sessions"]},{"name":"w","description":["Richard B. Nugent"]},{"name":"w","description":["House Rules Committee"]},{"name":"w","description":["Barack Obama"]},{"name":"w","description":["Keystone XL"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bloomberg.com/politics/articles/2015-01-07/boehner-pays-back-republicans-for-voting-against-him-for-speaker","title\u003dBoehner Takes His Revenge on Republicans Opposing Him for Speaker","author\u003dJonathan Allen, David Weigel","pub\u003dBloomberg Politics","date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/blogs/the-fix/wp/2015/01/06/here-are-the-republicans-who-voted-against-john-boehner-for-speaker/","title\u003dHere are the Republicans who voted against John Boehner for speaker","author\u003dAaron Blake","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/boehner-faces-leadership-challenge-from-conservative-members/2015/01/06/1c047668-95c1-11e4-aabd-d0b93ff613d5_story.html","title\u003dBoehner survives leadership challenge from conservative members","author\u003dRobert Costa, David A. Fahrenthold, Sean Sullivan","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/jan/06/john-boehner-house-speaker-leadership-challenge","title\u003dBoehner maintains House Speaker post despite biggest revolt in a century","author\u003dAmanda Holpuch and Paul Lewis","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dJanuary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Researchers say light signal from space suggests merging black holes","wikiTitle":"Researchers_say_light_signal_from_space_suggests_merging_black_holes","wid":1843534,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-01-22T22:29:03Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.caltech.edu/news/unusual-light-signal-yields-clues-about-elusive-black-hole-merger-45188, title\u003dUnusual Light Signal Yields Clues About Elusive Black Hole Merger, author\u003dKer Than, pub\u003dCaltech, date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nasa.gov/jpl/unusual-light-signal-hints-at-distant-black-hole-merger/index.html#.VK2wEsm4Jpt, title\u003dUnusual Light Signal Hints at Distant Black Hole Merger, author\u003dWhitney Clavin, pub\u003dNASA, date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nature.com/nature/journal/vaop/ncurrent/full/nature14143.html, title\u003dA possible close supermassive black-hole binary in a quasar with optical periodicity, author\u003d Matthew J. Graham, S. G. Djorgovski, Daniel Stern, Eilat Glikman, Andrew J. Drake, Ashish A. Mahabal, Ciro Donalek, Steve Larson, and Eric Christensen, pub\u003dNature (journal), date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"supermassive_black_holes","description":"supermassive black holes"},{"id":"black_holes","description":"black holes"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 10, 2015] TEMPLATE[space] TEMPLATE[image, [[NASA]]] On Wednesday, TEMPLATE[w, Stanislav George Djorgovski, George Djorgovski] and collaborators reported in the journal TEMPLATE[w, Nature (journal), Nature] on an unusual light signal they say suggests two supermassive black holes are merging, a phenomenon never seen before, though theorized.","The discovery could clarify how black holes merge and TEMPLATE[w, galaxies] evolve, and could also provide a better understanding of the so-called \"final parsec problem\" \u0026mdash; the inability of theories to predict how, or even how quickly, the final phases of black hole mergers happen.","The team discovered the light coming from quasar PG 1302-102 in data from the TEMPLATE[w, Catalina Real-time Transient Survey] (CTRS), which is able to study light sources from four fifths of the night sky using three ground-based US and Australian telescopes.","Coauthor and TEMPLATE[w, Caltech] computational scientist Matthew Graham emphasized the final stages of these black hole mergers are not well understood.  CTRS has so far identified 20 quasars with similar signals, but Graham said this one is the best example because it has a clear signal that recurs about every five years, similar to a TEMPLATE[w, sine wave] (see the 2D graph shown on the left).","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Space","description":"Category:Space"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Supermassive_black_holes","description":"Category:Supermassive black holes"},{"id":"Category:Black_holes","description":"Category:Black holes"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Physics","description":"Category:Physics"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 10, 2015"]},{"name":"space","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[NASA]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stanislav George Djorgovski","George Djorgovski"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nature (journal)","Nature"]},{"name":"w","description":["galaxies"]},{"name":"w","description":["Catalina Real-time Transient Survey"]},{"name":"w","description":["Caltech"]},{"name":"w","description":["sine wave"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.caltech.edu/news/unusual-light-signal-yields-clues-about-elusive-black-hole-merger-45188","title\u003dUnusual Light Signal Yields Clues About Elusive Black Hole Merger","author\u003dKer Than","pub\u003dCaltech","date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nasa.gov/jpl/unusual-light-signal-hints-at-distant-black-hole-merger/index.html#.VK2wEsm4Jpt","title\u003dUnusual Light Signal Hints at Distant Black Hole Merger","author\u003dWhitney Clavin","pub\u003dNASA","date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nature.com/nature/journal/vaop/ncurrent/full/nature14143.html","title\u003dA possible close supermassive black-hole binary in a quasar with optical periodicity","author\u003d Matthew J. Graham, S. G. Djorgovski, Daniel Stern, Eilat Glikman, Andrew J. Drake, Ashish A. Mahabal, Ciro Donalek, Steve Larson, and Eric Christensen","pub\u003dNature (journal)","date\u003dJanuary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Nature (journal), Nature]"]}
{"title":"SpaceX launches fifth resupply rocket to International Space Station","wikiTitle":"SpaceX_launches_fifth_resupply_rocket_to_International_Space_Station","wid":1849477,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-01-24T02:45:51Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dLaunch failure occurs at Virginia spaceport, date\u003dOctober 30, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://arstechnica.com/science/2015/01/spacex-launch-successful-landing-not-so-much/, title\u003dSpaceX: launch successful, landing not so much, author\u003dJohn Timmer, pub\u003dArs Technica, date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.spacex.com/news/2015/01/10/spacex-launches-fifth-official-mission-resupply-international-space-station, title\u003dSpaceX launched fith official mission to ressuply the International Space Station, pub\u003dSpaceX, date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/elonmusk, title\u003d@elonmusk, pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015 (date of access)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/daring-spacex-rocket-landing-test-crashes-successful-cargo-104322044.html, title\u003dDaring SpaceX Rocket Landing Test Crashes After Successful Cargo Launch for NASA, author\u003dMike Wall, pub\u003dYahoo! News, date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"SpaceX","description":"SpaceX"},{"id":"International_Space_Station","description":"International Space Station"},{"id":"Falcon_9","description":"Falcon 9"},{"id":"Atlantic","description":"Atlantic"},{"id":"Elon_Musk","description":"Elon Musk"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Space] Space transport services company SpaceX launched their TEMPLATE[w, SpaceX CRS-5, fifth Dragon resupply vehicle] to the International Space Station  yesterday. The spacecraft \u0026mdash; containing more than 2,200TEMPLATE[w, kilogram, kg] (5,000 TEMPLATE[w, pound (mass), pounds]) of food, experiments, and spare parts \u0026mdash; successfully decoupled from the launch rocket and should reach the station early tomorrow. TEMPLATE[image, Bruno Sanchez-Andrade NuÃ±o] The launch was postponed from Tuesday because of a technical issue on the second stage of the rocket. The shipment includes replacements for cargo aboard the spaceship Cygnus, destroyed during a failed launch in October. Cygnus belonged to the rival TEMPLATE[w, Orbital Sciences Corporation].","SpaceX tried unsuccessfully to land the Falcon 9 delivery rocket for reuse. The rocket reached an unmanned  barge in the Atlantic, but landed too hard. SpaceX CEO Elon Musk said the landing \"bodes well for the future, though\". The attempted salvage of the rocket was experimental, using new retractable fins. Next time they will add extra hydraulic fluid, Musk said.","The ship\u0027s support equipment was damaged but, according to Musk, the barge is intact. Last year saw two successful SpaceX splashdowns but landing on such a small target as a ship is unique.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:International_Space_Station","description":"Category:International Space Station"},{"id":"Category:SpaceX","description":"Category:SpaceX"},{"id":"Category:Space","description":"Category:Space"},{"id":"Category:Merchant_shipping","description":"Category:Merchant shipping"},{"id":"Category:Robotics","description":"Category:Robotics"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Elon_Musk","description":"Category:Elon Musk"},{"id":"Category:Falcon_9","description":"Category:Falcon 9"},{"id":"Category:Dragon_(spacecraft)","description":"Category:Dragon (spacecraft)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Space","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["SpaceX CRS-5","fifth Dragon resupply vehicle"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilogram","kg"]},{"name":"w","description":["pound (mass)","pounds"]},{"name":"image","description":["Bruno Sanchez-Andrade NuÃ±o"]},{"name":"w","description":["Orbital Sciences Corporation"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dLaunch failure occurs at Virginia spaceport","date\u003dOctober 30, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://arstechnica.com/science/2015/01/spacex-launch-successful-landing-not-so-much/","title\u003dSpaceX: launch successful, landing not so much","author\u003dJohn Timmer","pub\u003dArs Technica","date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.spacex.com/news/2015/01/10/spacex-launches-fifth-official-mission-resupply-international-space-station","title\u003dSpaceX launched fith official mission to ressuply the International Space Station","pub\u003dSpaceX","date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/elonmusk","title\u003d@elonmusk","pub\u003dTwitter","date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015 (date of access)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/daring-spacex-rocket-landing-test-crashes-successful-cargo-104322044.html","title\u003dDaring SpaceX Rocket Landing Test Crashes After Successful Cargo Launch for NASA","author\u003dMike Wall","pub\u003dYahoo! News","date\u003dJanuary 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","pub","date","url","title","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
