{"title":"Tom Wolf inaugurated as Pennsylvania Governor","wikiTitle":"Tom_Wolf_inaugurated_as_Pennsylvania_Governor","wid":1870077,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-01-31T17:15:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.mcall.com/news/nationworld/pennsylvania/mc-pa-gov-tom-wolf-inauguration-20150120-story.html#page\u003d1, title\u003dDemocrat Tom Wolf sworn in as Pennsylvania\u0027s 47th governor, author\u003dSteve Esack and Emily Opilo, pub\u003dThe Morning Call, date\u003dJanuary 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.pennlive.com/politics/index.ssf/2015/01/read_the_full_text_of_gov_tom.html, title\u003dRead the full text of Gov. Tom Wolf\u0027s inaugural address, author\u003dTeresa Bonner, pub\u003dThe Patriot-News, date\u003dJanuary 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.pottsmerc.com/general-news/20150119/tom-wolf-poised-to-take-inaugural-oath-as-47th-pa-governor, title\u003dTom Wolf poised to take inaugural oath as 47th Pa. governor, author\u003dPeter Jackson ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003dThe Mercury (Pennsylvania), date\u003dJanuary 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://web.archive.org/web/20070810212052/www.revenue.state.pa.us/revenue/cwp/view.asp?A\u003d6\u0026Q\u003d67924, title\u003dAbout Us - Thomas W. Wolf, Secretary, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dInternet Archive, date\u003dAugust 10, 2007 (date archived)]"]],"links":[{"id":"Democratic_Party_(United_States)","description":"Democrat"},{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"Pennsylvania","description":"Pennsylvania"},{"id":"Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Republican"},{"id":"Tom_Corbett","description":"Tom Corbett"},{"id":"Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology","description":"Massachusetts Institute of Technology"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Pennsylvania_infobox] TEMPLATE[date, January 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[image_credit, Tom Wolf for Governor] Democrat TEMPLATE[w, Tom Wolf (politician), Tom Wolf] was inaugurated yesterday as the 47th Governor of the U.S. commonwealth of Pennsylvania. He succeeds Republican Tom Corbett, whom he defeated in the election last November. The inauguration took place in front of the TEMPLATE[w, Pennsylvania State Capitol] in TEMPLATE[w, Harrisburg, Pennsylvania, Harrisburg].","Wolf, 66, and his running mate, newly sworn-in Lieutenant Governor TEMPLATE[w, Michael J. Stack III, Mike Stack], defeated Corbett and former Lieutenant Governor TEMPLATE[w, Jim Cawley] by nearly ten percentage points in last November\u0027s general election. As a result, Corbett became the first Pennsylvania Governor in modern times to lose a re-election bid.","In his TEMPLATE[w, inaugural address] to a crowd of roughly 4,000, Wolf focused on his belief in the need for change, labeling himself an \"unconventional\" and \"different kind of governor.\" He touched on a number of issues including education, over which he and Corbett clashed during last year\u0027s campaign, in addition to the economy and government reform.","\"As your Governor, I will do everything in my power to make Pennsylvania a place where jobs pay, schools teach, government works ... and where all Pennsylvanians can believe in the fundamental notion that our democracy still works\", Wolf said. \"Because I know that if we come together with a sense of shared purpose, we can build the better future that Pennsylvania deserves.\"","Items on Wolf\u0027s gubernatorial agenda include raising the minimum wage, a five percent extraction tax on TEMPLATE[w, Marcellus Shale, natural gas drillers] and an increase in public school funding, among others. He is slated to propose his first budget to the TEMPLATE[w, Pennsylvania General Assembly] on March 3 for the fiscal year beginning July 1.","Wolf, a native of TEMPLATE[w, York, Pennsylvania, York], Pennsylvania, previously served as secretary of the TEMPLATE[w, Pennsylvania Department of Revenue] in the cabinet of former Governor TEMPLATE[w, Ed Rendell] from 2007 to 2008. He was also chairman and president of his family\u0027s building materials business, The Wolf Organization Inc. He holds a doctorate from the Massachusetts Institute of Technology, a master\u0027s degree from the TEMPLATE[w, University of London] and a bachelor\u0027s degree from TEMPLATE[w, Dartmouth University].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, Pennsylvania gubernatorial election, 2014, List of Governors of Pennsylvania]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Democratic_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Democratic Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:Pennsylvania","description":"Category:Pennsylvania"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Corbett","description":"Category:Tom Corbett"}],"templates":[{"name":"Pennsylvania_infobox","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["January 21, 2015"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Tom Wolf for Governor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tom Wolf (politician)","Tom Wolf"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pennsylvania State Capitol"]},{"name":"w","description":["Harrisburg, Pennsylvania","Harrisburg"]},{"name":"w","description":["Michael J. Stack III","Mike Stack"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jim Cawley"]},{"name":"w","description":["inaugural address"]},{"name":"w","description":["Marcellus Shale","natural gas drillers"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pennsylvania General Assembly"]},{"name":"w","description":["York, Pennsylvania","York"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pennsylvania Department of Revenue"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ed Rendell"]},{"name":"w","description":["University of London"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dartmouth University"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["Pennsylvania gubernatorial election, 2014","List of Governors of Pennsylvania"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.mcall.com/news/nationworld/pennsylvania/mc-pa-gov-tom-wolf-inauguration-20150120-story.html#page\u003d1","title\u003dDemocrat Tom Wolf sworn in as Pennsylvania\u0027s 47th governor","author\u003dSteve Esack and Emily Opilo","pub\u003dThe Morning Call","date\u003dJanuary 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.pennlive.com/politics/index.ssf/2015/01/read_the_full_text_of_gov_tom.html","title\u003dRead the full text of Gov. Tom Wolf\u0027s inaugural address","author\u003dTeresa Bonner","pub\u003dThe Patriot-News","date\u003dJanuary 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.pottsmerc.com/general-news/20150119/tom-wolf-poised-to-take-inaugural-oath-as-47th-pa-governor","title\u003dTom Wolf poised to take inaugural oath as 47th Pa. governor","author\u003dPeter Jackson ((TEMPLATE))","pub\u003dThe Mercury (Pennsylvania)","date\u003dJanuary 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://web.archive.org/web/20070810212052/www.revenue.state.pa.us/revenue/cwp/view.asp?A\u003d6\u0026Q\u003d67924","title\u003dAbout Us - Thomas W. Wolf, Secretary","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dInternet Archive","date\u003dAugust 10, 2007 (date archived)"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Priests beaten in Forecariah, Guinea over Ebola fears","wikiTitle":"Priests_beaten_in_Forecariah,_Guinea_over_Ebola_fears","wid":1871332,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-01-31T22:59:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.christiantoday.com/article/guinea.three.priests.beaten.and.held.hostage.for.spreading.ebola/46425.htm, title\u003dGuinea: Three priests beaten and held hostage for \u0027spreading Ebola\u0027, author\u003dCarey Lodge, pub\u003dChristian Today, date\u003dJanuary 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-30900917, title\u003dEbola crisis: Guinean priests beaten up over health fears, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJanuary 20, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Guinea","description":"Guinea"},{"id":"Ebola","description":"Ebola"},{"id":"World_Health_Organisation","description":"World Health Organisation"},{"id":"Red_Cross","description":"Red Cross"},{"id":"Liberia","description":"Liberia"},{"id":"Sierra_Leone","description":"Sierra Leone"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[Guinea] Three Baptist priests in Guinea were assaulted and held hostage yesterday by local villagers after being mistaken for campaigners promoting awareness about Ebola, the TEMPLATE[w, BBC] has reported. They were visiting TEMPLATE[w, Kaback, Kabac], a village in the sub-prefecture of TEMPLATE[w, ForÃ©cariah], to spray insecticide for the treatment of wells and pit latrines. Locals reportedly thought they were bringing Ebola and attacked the priests. After the assault they were held hostage and had their vehicle set alight. TEMPLATE[image, [[Centers for Disease Control]] / Dr. Frederick Murphy] Following the attack on the priests, town council workers were forced to evacuate as their building came under assault and was set fire to. A local report, not been independently verified, alleged a council worker was killed during the incident. Police intervened to arrest a number of the local villagers involved in the attacks but were met with hostility from those trying to stop the arrested being taken away.","Such incidents have been noted by the World Health Organisation (WHO). A recent WHO report said \"community resistance\" is a \"major barrier to control\" in the countries Ebola has worst hit.","ForÃ©cariah has seen incidents like this before. In one incident, on September 23, two Red Cross volunteers buried an Ebola victim, and were then attacked. Villagers removed the corpse from the grave and hid it. This then grew into an attack on a team of TEMPLATE[w, epidemiology, epidemiologists] by a mob of about 3000 armed youths. This attack had undone \"weeks of persistent and effective efforts to slow the outbreak\" according to the WHO, who were overseeing the team.","Although not the worst affected country, Guinea has seen 1,876 deaths from 2,871 cases of Ebola, according to WHO. This is compared to Liberia and Sierra Leone with 3,605 and 3,145 deaths each from the effects of the Ebola virus.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Ebola_virus","description":"Category:Ebola virus"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:World_Health_Organisation","description":"Category:World Health Organisation"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Christianity","description":"Category:Christianity"},{"id":"Category:Infectious_disease","description":"Category:Infectious disease"},{"id":"Category:Disease","description":"Category:Disease"},{"id":"Category:Guinea","description":"Category:Guinea"},{"id":"Category:BBC","description":"Category:BBC"},{"id":"Category:Red_Cross_and_Red_Crescent","description":"Category:Red Cross and Red Crescent"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Guinea","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaback","Kabac"]},{"name":"w","description":["ForÃ©cariah"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Centers for Disease Control]] / Dr. Frederick Murphy"]},{"name":"w","description":["epidemiology","epidemiologists"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.christiantoday.com/article/guinea.three.priests.beaten.and.held.hostage.for.spreading.ebola/46425.htm","title\u003dGuinea: Three priests beaten and held hostage for \u0027spreading Ebola\u0027","author\u003dCarey Lodge","pub\u003dChristian Today","date\u003dJanuary 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-30900917","title\u003dEbola crisis: Guinean priests beaten up over health fears","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJanuary 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"UN Security Council heads to Haiti amid political instability","wikiTitle":"UN_Security_Council_heads_to_Haiti_amid_political_instability","wid":1876406,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-22T13:31:22Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dLaurent Lamothe resigns as Haitian PM, date\u003dDecember 15, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/world/americas/article8009664.html, title\u003dHaiti installs new electoral board hours before U.N. Security Council delegation arrives, author\u003dJacqueline Charles, pub\u003dThe Miami Herald, date\u003dJanuary 23, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/security-council-members-arrive-haiti-day-visit-28429977, title\u003dUN Security Council Members Arrive in Haiti for 3-Day Visit, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dJanuary 23, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2015/1/23/international-community-battles-perception-of-bias-in-haiti.html, title\u003dInternational leaders battle perception of bias in Haiti, author\u003dBenedict Moran, pub\u003dal-Jazeera America, date\u003dJanuary 23, 2014]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_Nations","description":"United Nations"},{"id":"United_Nations_Security_Council","description":"Security Council"},{"id":"Haiti","description":"Haiti"},{"id":"Michel_Martelly","description":"Michel Martelly"},{"id":"Brazil","description":"Brazil"},{"id":"Canada","description":"Canada"},{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"Spain","description":"Spain"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"European_Union","description":"European Union"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 24, 2015] TEMPLATE[Haiti] Representatives of the United Nations Security Council\u0027s (UNSC) fifteen member states flew to Haiti yesterday. The nation is moving to hold new elections with President Michel Martelly presently ruling by decree. TEMPLATE[image, [[World Economic Forum]]] Martelly swore in a new Provisional Electoral Council (CEP) of nine members yesterday. It is Martelly\u0027s fifth CEP in four years. Last month a presidential commission recommended the prior CEP\u0027s resignation as part of a package of measures to move the country towards new elections. The commission was Martelly\u0027s response to widespread anti-regime protests that started in October. The sometimes-violent protests were triggered by failure to hold elections, some due since 2011.","On January 12 the TEMPLATE[w, Haitian Senate, Senate] was reduced to a defunct ten members, with sixteen  required for a quorum. Amendments to electoral law were required by the Senate before elections due in 2011 could be held. Rival political factions were unable to resolve disagreements. The lower level of parliament, the Chamber of Deputies, also saw all 99 seats vacated.","Also due are municipal elections, with 4,000 local posts needing refilled. A presidential election is due this year and the constitution forbids a consecutive term for Martelly. CEP members were sworn in yesterday at the TEMPLATE[w, Supreme Court of Haiti, Supreme Court]; the presidential commission also recommended a new head for the court.","This month Martelly installed a new cabinet including opposition members, amongst them appointing TEMPLATE[w, Evans Paul] as Prime Minister. Paul replaces TEMPLATE[w, Laurent Lamothe] who resigned last month at the request of Martelly\u0027s commission. Paul was yesterday joined by foreign diplomats to welcome the new CEP in TEMPLATE[w, Petionville], the CEP headquarters.","Protests continued around the nation yesterday, with anger directed at foreign leaders who have supported Martelly as well as the local regime. Brazil, Canada, France, Spain, the United States, the European Union, and the TEMPLATE[w, Organization of American States] expressed in a joint statement \"support to the president of the republic in the exercise of his constitutional duty to ensure the regular functioning of institutions and the continuity of the state\" as parliament\u0027s terms lapsed and power passed to Martelly alone.","The UN is unpopular in Haiti where many blame their peacekeeping force for a 2010 TEMPLATE[w, cholera] outbreak, which is ongoing with 9,000 deaths. The UN has extended the peacekeeping mission for another year but does plan to reduce troops from around 5,000 to around 2,400. Anti-peacekeeper protests have also focussed on sexual abuse allegations.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Caribbean","description":"Category:Caribbean"},{"id":"Category:Haiti","description":"Category:Haiti"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Protests","description":"Category:Protests"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:United_Nations","description":"Category:United Nations"},{"id":"Category:United_Nations_Security_Council","description":"Category:United Nations Security Council"},{"id":"Category:2010_Haitian_cholera_outbreak","description":"Category:2010 Haitian cholera outbreak"},{"id":"Category:Michel_Martelly","description":"Category:Michel Martelly"},{"id":"Category:Haitian_Constitution","description":"Category:Haitian Constitution"},{"id":"Category:Haitian_Supreme_Court","description":"Category:Haitian Supreme Court"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Haiti","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[World Economic Forum]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Haitian Senate","Senate"]},{"name":"w","description":["Supreme Court of Haiti","Supreme Court"]},{"name":"w","description":["Evans Paul"]},{"name":"w","description":["Laurent Lamothe"]},{"name":"w","description":["Petionville"]},{"name":"w","description":["Organization of American States"]},{"name":"w","description":["cholera"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dLaurent Lamothe resigns as Haitian PM","date\u003dDecember 15, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.miamiherald.com/news/nation-world/world/americas/article8009664.html","title\u003dHaiti installs new electoral board hours before U.N. Security Council delegation arrives","author\u003dJacqueline Charles","pub\u003dThe Miami Herald","date\u003dJanuary 23, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/security-council-members-arrive-haiti-day-visit-28429977","title\u003dUN Security Council Members Arrive in Haiti for 3-Day Visit","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dABC News","date\u003dJanuary 23, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://america.aljazeera.com/articles/2015/1/23/international-community-battles-perception-of-bias-in-haiti.html","title\u003dInternational leaders battle perception of bias in Haiti","author\u003dBenedict Moran","pub\u003dal-Jazeera America","date\u003dJanuary 23, 2014"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Greek singer Demis Roussos dies aged 68","wikiTitle":"Greek_singer_Demis_Roussos_dies_aged_68","wid":1882772,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-07T13:15:53Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/11369568/Demis-Roussos-singer-dies.html, title\u003dDemis Roussos, the celebrated Greek singer, dies aged 68, author\u003dMartin Chilton, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/jan/26/demis-roussos-dies-aged-69-greek-singer-forever-and-ever, title\u003dDemis Roussos, Greek singer of Forever and Ever, dies aged 68, author\u003dPeter Walker, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-30984851, title\u003dGreek singer Demis Roussos dies aged 68, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/renowned-greek-singer-demis-roussos-dead-68-28483359, title\u003dRenowned Greek Singer Demis Roussos Dead at 68, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Greece","description":"Greek"},{"id":"Athens","description":"Athens"},{"id":"Egypt","description":"Egypt"},{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"England","description":"England"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[Greece] TEMPLATE[w, Baku]TEMPLATE[image, Urek Meniashvili] Greek singer TEMPLATE[w, Demis Roussos] died on Sunday in Athens.  The 68-year-old Roussos, born in Egypt, died in a private hospital. No official cause of death has been announced but the hospital said he had been there for some time. Roussos reached international fame in the 1960s and 70s. His hits included TEMPLATE[w, The Roussos Phenomenon EP, Forever and Ever], Quand je t\u0027aime, and Goodbye.","Roussos, whose musical career started with work in TEMPLATE[w, cabaret], had success both as a solo artist and as part of a group. He belonged to progressive rock group TEMPLATE[w, Aphrodite\u0027s Child]. After a successful career with Aphrodite\u0027s Child, Roussos went solo. His single Forever and Ever reached number one in several Single charts in 1973 and topped the TEMPLATE[w, UK Singles chart] in 1976.","He and his family left Egypt in 1961, when he was a teenager, in the aftermath of the TEMPLATE[w, Suez crisis]. Before the move he had studied and performed music in a Greek church. He was 17 when he joined group The Idols; while with The Idols he met TEMPLATE[w, Vangelis], who he would go on to form Aphrodite\u0027s Child with.","Vangelis released a statement about the death of his former bandmate Roussos. He said  \"Demis my friend. I have just arrived in London and I\u0027ve been told that you decide to take the long voyage, I\u0027m shocked because I can\u0027t believe that this happened so soon. Nature gave you this magic voice of yours which made millions of people around the world very happy. [...] As for me, I keep those special memories that we share together those early days and I wish you to be happy wherever you are. [...] Goodbye my friend goodbye. Love Vangelis.\"","Another tribute came from fellow Greek singer TEMPLATE[w, Nana Mouskouri]. Speaking to French radio station TEMPLATE[w, RTL (French radio), RTL], she said \"He had a superb voice, he travelled in the world [...] he loved what he was doing. He was an artist, a friend. I hope he is in a better world.\"","In 1985 he was a captive in the TEMPLATE[w, TWA Flight 847] hijacking.  He was held for five days, one of which was his 39th birthday.","During his later life Roussos lived in several countries including France, United States and England. In 2013 he was awarded the TEMPLATE[w, French Legion of Honour] during a ceremony in Athens.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Greece","description":"Category:Greece"},{"id":"Category:Egypt","description":"Category:Egypt"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Greece","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Baku"]},{"name":"image","description":["Urek Meniashvili"]},{"name":"w","description":["Demis Roussos"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Roussos Phenomenon EP","Forever and Ever"]},{"name":"w","description":["cabaret"]},{"name":"w","description":["Aphrodite\u0027s Child"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK Singles chart"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suez crisis"]},{"name":"w","description":["Vangelis"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nana Mouskouri"]},{"name":"w","description":["RTL (French radio)","RTL"]},{"name":"w","description":["TWA Flight 847"]},{"name":"w","description":["French Legion of Honour"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/music/music-news/11369568/Demis-Roussos-singer-dies.html","title\u003dDemis Roussos, the celebrated Greek singer, dies aged 68","author\u003dMartin Chilton","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/jan/26/demis-roussos-dies-aged-69-greek-singer-forever-and-ever","title\u003dDemis Roussos, Greek singer of Forever and Ever, dies aged 68","author\u003dPeter Walker","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-30984851","title\u003dGreek singer Demis Roussos dies aged 68","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Entertainment/wireStory/renowned-greek-singer-demis-roussos-dead-68-28483359","title\u003dRenowned Greek Singer Demis Roussos Dead at 68","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dABC News","date\u003dJanuary 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Roussos Phenomenon EP, Forever and Ever]","Quand je t\u0027aime","Goodbye","Forever and Ever"]}
{"title":"Scientists find ancient solar system in Milky Way galaxy","wikiTitle":"Scientists_find_ancient_solar_system_in_Milky_Way_galaxy","wid":1890866,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-07T15:21:20Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/5-rocky-planets-found-in-very-ancient-solar-system-1.2934538, title\u003d5 rocky planets found in very ancient \u0027solar system\u0027, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dCBC News, date\u003dJanuary 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Technology/astronomers-discover-ancient-solar-system-earth-planets/story?id\u003d28514140, title\u003dAstronomers Discover Ancient Solar System With 5 Earth-Like Planets, author\u003dAlyssa Newcomb, pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dJanuary 27, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://iopscience.iop.org/0004-637X/799/2/170/article, title\u003dAn Ancient Extrasolar System with Five Sub-Earth-size Planets, author\u003dT. L. Campante \u0027\u0027et al\u0027\u0027, pub\u003dThe Astrophysical Journal, date\u003dJanuary 27, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"The_Astrophysical_Journal","description":"The Astrophysical Journal"},{"id":"NASA","description":"NASA"},{"id":"Kepler_telescope","description":"Kepler telescope"},{"id":"University_of_Sydney","description":"University of Sydney"},{"id":"Venus","description":"Venus"},{"id":"exoplanets","description":"exoplanets"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 30, 2015] TEMPLATE[space] Astronomers reported on Tuesday in The Astrophysical Journal they have found an ancient solar system with several Earth-like TEMPLATE[w, planets]. TEMPLATE[w, Kepler-37b] They said the system dates roughly to the formation of the TEMPLATE[w, Milky Way] galaxy. They found the planets orbiting around TEMPLATE[w, Kepler-444], about 117 TEMPLATE[wikt, light year, light years] from TEMPLATE[w, Earth]. Researchers investigated Kepler-444 with NASA\u0027s Kepler telescope using a method called TEMPLATE[w, astroseismology].","Scientists explain they studied the TEMPLATE[w, star] and noticed planets passing in front of it because it created a dimming effect in which the star seems less bright for a short period of time, when there are actually planets passing between the observer and the star.","Because these planets are older than Earth, this suggests life might have existed in the early universe, the researchers say.","According to Daniel Huber, part of the research team at the University of Sydney, it takes under ten days for these five planets to orbit the star and all of them are too close to it to sustain life. These planets are smaller than Earth, with the largest compared to Venus.","This month, the number of exoplanets found using the Kepler telescope passed 1,000. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Space","description":"Category:Space"},{"id":"Category:Exoplanets","description":"Category:Exoplanets"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:The_Astrophysical_Journal","description":"Category:The Astrophysical Journal"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:University_of_Sydney","description":"Category:University of Sydney"},{"id":"Category:Physics","description":"Category:Physics"},{"id":"Category:Kepler_telescope","description":"Category:Kepler telescope"},{"id":"Category:NASA","description":"Category:NASA"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 30, 2015"]},{"name":"space","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["planets"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kepler-37b"]},{"name":"w","description":["Milky Way"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kepler-444"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["light year","light years"]},{"name":"w","description":["Earth"]},{"name":"w","description":["astroseismology"]},{"name":"w","description":["star"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/technology/5-rocky-planets-found-in-very-ancient-solar-system-1.2934538","title\u003d5 rocky planets found in very ancient \u0027solar system\u0027","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dCBC News","date\u003dJanuary 28, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Technology/astronomers-discover-ancient-solar-system-earth-planets/story?id\u003d28514140","title\u003dAstronomers Discover Ancient Solar System With 5 Earth-Like Planets","author\u003dAlyssa Newcomb","pub\u003dABC News","date\u003dJanuary 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://iopscience.iop.org/0004-637X/799/2/170/article","title\u003dAn Ancient Extrasolar System with Five Sub-Earth-size Planets","author\u003dT. L. Campante \u0027\u0027et al\u0027\u0027","pub\u003dThe Astrophysical Journal","date\u003dJanuary 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["The Astrophysical Journal"]}
{"title":"Conductor Israel Yinon dies after collapsing on stage","wikiTitle":"Conductor_Israel_Yinon_dies_after_collapsing_on_stage","wid":1893549,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-07T19:55:21Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.timesofisrael.com/renowned-israeli-conductor-dies-on-stage-during-concert/, title\u003dRenowned Israeli conductor dies on stage during concert, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Times of Israel, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2932877/Israeli-conductor-collapses-Swiss-concert-dies.html, title\u003dInternationally renowned conductor drops dead in front of screaming audience and musicians during a symphony in Switzerland, author\u003dTim McFarlan, pub\u003dMail Online, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/11379995/Israel-Yinon-composer-obituary.html, title\u003dIsrael Yinon, composer - obituary, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Switzerland","description":"Switzerland"},{"id":"Israel","description":"Israel"},{"id":"Germany","description":"German"},{"id":"Second_World_War","description":"Second World War"},{"id":"Austria","description":"Austria"},{"id":"Czech_Republic","description":"Czech Republic"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[Music] TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Etan J. Tal, Etan J. Tal]]] Conductor Israel Yinon died yesterday after collapsing during a performance in Switzerland. The Israeli conductor was directing an orchestra in the city of TEMPLATE[w, Lucerne] when he suddenly collapsed and fell head first off of the platform. No official cause of death has been announced. He was 59 years old.","Yinon collapsed during the performance of German composer TEMPLATE[w, Richard Strauss]\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, An Alpine Symphony]. An audience member attended to him while others were asked to leave the TEMPLATE[w, Lucerne Culture and Congress Centre, Lucerne Culture and Convention Centre] and musicians exited. Yinon\u0027s girlfriend was playing in the orchestra when he collapsed.","Yinnon was known for showcasing the works of composers killed in the TEMPLATE[w, The Holocaust, Holocaust]. He highlighted symphonies from those such as TEMPLATE[w, Pavel Haas] and TEMPLATE[w, Viktor Ullmann]. Through this he gained international recognition including his award of the German criticsâ recording prize in 1993. He went on to conduct the TEMPLATE[w, BBC Symphony Orchestra] and the TEMPLATE[w, Berlin Symphony Orchestra].","Speaking about the work of those composers who became victims of the Holocaust, Yinnon was quoted as saying \"Without the Second World War, new music would have sounded quite different.\"","Despite his international success he never achieved similar critical acclaim in his home country of Israel. Speaking to the TEMPLATE[w, Ynet] news website his cousin Yisrael Ganor said \"In Germany, Austria, and the Czech Republic he was very successful with this material, whereas in Israel he was rarely invited [to conduct]. Once someone famous told him â I donât remember if it was a musician or journalist â that they would only invite him if there was no one else, or if the budgetary constraints couldn\u0027t cover someone well known.\"","Tributes have been paid to the conductor including one from the Jungen Philharmonie Zentralschweiz student orchestra. They said they lost \"not only a highly regarded musical colleague and sensitive educator, but a big-hearted friend.\" Yinnon had conducted them in 2009 and 2012 concerts.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Israel","description":"Category:Israel"},{"id":"Category:Switzerland","description":"Category:Switzerland"},{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:World_War_II","description":"Category:World War II"},{"id":"Category:Classical_music","description":"Category:Classical music"},{"id":"Category:Lucerne","description":"Category:Lucerne"},{"id":"Category:The_Holocaust","description":"Category:The Holocaust"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Music","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Etan J. Tal","Etan J. Tal]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lucerne"]},{"name":"w","description":["Richard Strauss"]},{"name":"w","description":["An Alpine Symphony"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lucerne Culture and Congress Centre","Lucerne Culture and Convention Centre"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Holocaust","Holocaust"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pavel Haas"]},{"name":"w","description":["Viktor Ullmann"]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC Symphony Orchestra"]},{"name":"w","description":["Berlin Symphony Orchestra"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ynet"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.timesofisrael.com/renowned-israeli-conductor-dies-on-stage-during-concert/","title\u003dRenowned Israeli conductor dies on stage during concert","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Times of Israel","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2932877/Israeli-conductor-collapses-Swiss-concert-dies.html","title\u003dInternationally renowned conductor drops dead in front of screaming audience and musicians during a symphony in Switzerland","author\u003dTim McFarlan","pub\u003dMail Online","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/11379995/Israel-Yinon-composer-obituary.html","title\u003dIsrael Yinon, composer - obituary","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, An Alpine Symphony]","TEMPLATE[w, Ynet]"]}
{"title":"Gas explosion flattens Mexico City maternity hospital","wikiTitle":"Gas_explosion_flattens_Mexico_City_maternity_hospital","wid":1894746,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-26T19:54:27Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/01/30/world/mexico-explosion/, title\u003d3 arrested in connection with deadly Mexico hospital blast, author\u003dCatherine E. Shoichet, Mariano Castillo, Rafael Romo, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/30/us-mexico-blast-idUSKBN0L21TT20150130, title\u003dBabies found alive in rubble after truck blast rips through Mexico hospital, author\u003dLizbeth Diaz, Joanna Zuckerman Bernstein, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-31039921, title\u003dMexico City gas truck explodes near maternity hospital, author\u003dKaty Watson, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Mexico_City","description":"Mexico City"},{"id":"Mexico","description":"Mexico"},{"id":"Pope_Francis","description":"Pope Francis"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[Mexico] An explosion on Thursday morning destroyed a state maternity hospital in Mexico City, Mexico. A nurse and two babies are dead. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, I feel grateful to have another chance to keep living, to keep working as a nurse, 4\u003dIvonne Lugo Durantes, injured survvor] Initially reports placed the fatalities at seven. Local officials including Mexico City Health Secretary Armando Ahued and Mayor Miguel Angel Mancera have since revised the figure downwards. Over 70 people including 20 infants are wounded. Around 100 people were in the building at the time.","The explosion occurred as a truck was resupplying the hospital\u0027s gas tanks, and a leak developed in the supply hose. Driver Julio CÃ©sar MartÃ­nez and assistants Carlos Chavez and Salvador Alatorre have been arrested. Chavez and Alatorre spent around fifteen minutes attempting to stem the leak, to no avail. All three are amongst the injured.","Firefighters and federal police entered the ruins to recover trapped survivors. Victims\u0027 relatives, and other bystanders, gathered at police cordons around the scene. \"I am still a little bit in shock. It was a nightmare,\" said nurse Ivonne Lugo Durantes.","Durantes was rescued after ten minutes trapped beneath debris. She has first degree burns but is \"grateful to have another chance to keep living, to keep working as a nurse.\" She witnessed other staff rescuing babies amid a conflagration.","New father Jose Eduardo told reporters his wife ran barefoot with their baby to escape. Eduardo said some escaped nude. Witnesses around the hospital reported a strong smell of gas, a large explosion, and flying debris. Ambulances and helicopters were used to evacuate casualties.","President TEMPLATE[w, Enrique Pena Nieto] and Pope Francis both took to Twitter to express support for the victims.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Mexico","description":"Category:Mexico"},{"id":"Category:Mexico_City","description":"Category:Mexico City"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Pope_Francis","description":"Category:Pope Francis"},{"id":"Category:Enrique_PeÃ±a_Nieto","description":"Category:Enrique PeÃ±a Nieto"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Mexico","description":[]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["I feel grateful to have another chance to keep living, to keep working as a nurse","4\u003dIvonne Lugo Durantes, injured survvor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Enrique Pena Nieto"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/01/30/world/mexico-explosion/","title\u003d3 arrested in connection with deadly Mexico hospital blast","author\u003dCatherine E. Shoichet, Mariano Castillo, Rafael Romo","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/01/30/us-mexico-blast-idUSKBN0L21TT20150130","title\u003dBabies found alive in rubble after truck blast rips through Mexico hospital","author\u003dLizbeth Diaz, Joanna Zuckerman Bernstein","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-31039921","title\u003dMexico City gas truck explodes near maternity hospital","author\u003dKaty Watson","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Rare megamouth shark found dead in Pio Duran, Philippines","wikiTitle":"Rare_megamouth_shark_found_dead_in_Pio_Duran,_Philippines","wid":1894879,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-07T20:48:28Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/420469/news/regions/rare-megamouth-shark-dies-in-albay-shore, title\u003dRare megamouth shark dies in Albay shore, author\u003d, pub\u003dGMA Network, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/01/29/mysterious-megamouth-shark-washes-ashore-in-the-philippines/, title\u003dMysterious megamouth shark washes ashore in the Philippines, author\u003dAbby Phillip, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/rare-megamouth-shark-washes-up-onshore-in-the-philippines-10010763.html, title\u003dRare megamouth shark washes up onshore in the Philippines, author\u003dHeather Saul, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://mashable.com/2015/01/29/megamouth-shark-philippines/, title\u003dA rare 15-foot megamouth shark washed up on a Philippines beach, author\u003dMax Knoblauch, pub\u003dMashable, date\u003dJaunary 29, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Philippines","description":"Philippines"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"Taiwan","description":"Taiwan"},{"id":"Japan","description":"Japan"},{"id":"Hawaii","description":"Hawaii"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[biology] A TEMPLATE[w, megamouth shark] was found dead in the Philippines on Wednesday.  There have been only fifteen confirmed sightings in the nation and around 60 worldwide.  TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[w:User:saberwyn, \"saberwyn\"]]] The fifteen-foot male was found after reportedly becoming entangled with a fishing net near the Barangay Marigondon neighborhood of TEMPLATE[w, Pio Duran], TEMPLATE[w, Albay] province. Its body was encased with ice pending a necropsy. The cause of death was not immediately clear.","Locals have nicknamed the dead shark \u0027toothless\u0027, a TEMPLATE[w, How to Train Your Dragon] movie reference.  In truth megamouths can have up to fifty rows of teeth.","Megamouths reach up to eighteen feet. Their name refers to its large head and mouth, used to filter TEMPLATE[w, plankton] and other small food from the ocean. Occasionally the prey of other sharks and whales, megamouths are thought to live in the TEMPLATE[w, Pacific Ocean, Pacific] around Taiwan, the Philippines, and Japan based on previous sightings. Its true range and population size are however unknown. The first such shark identified was accidentally discovered by the TEMPLATE[w, US Navy] off the coast of Hawaii when it became stuck in a ship\u0027s anchor. Researchers theorise a white strip on the shark\u0027s head TEMPLATE[w, bioluminescence, illuminates] to attract prey.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Philippines","description":"Category:Philippines"},{"id":"Category:Biology","description":"Category:Biology"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Marine_science","description":"Category:Marine science"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Species_endangerment","description":"Category:Species endangerment"},{"id":"Category:Albay","description":"Category:Albay"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 31, 2015"]},{"name":"biology","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["megamouth shark"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[w:User:saberwyn","\"saberwyn\"]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pio Duran"]},{"name":"w","description":["Albay"]},{"name":"w","description":["How to Train Your Dragon"]},{"name":"w","description":["plankton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pacific Ocean","Pacific"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Navy"]},{"name":"w","description":["bioluminescence","illuminates"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.gmanetwork.com/news/story/420469/news/regions/rare-megamouth-shark-dies-in-albay-shore","title\u003dRare megamouth shark dies in Albay shore","author\u003d","pub\u003dGMA Network","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/speaking-of-science/wp/2015/01/29/mysterious-megamouth-shark-washes-ashore-in-the-philippines/","title\u003dMysterious megamouth shark washes ashore in the Philippines","author\u003dAbby Phillip","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/rare-megamouth-shark-washes-up-onshore-in-the-philippines-10010763.html","title\u003dRare megamouth shark washes up onshore in the Philippines","author\u003dHeather Saul","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dJanuary 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://mashable.com/2015/01/29/megamouth-shark-philippines/","title\u003dA rare 15-foot megamouth shark washed up on a Philippines beach","author\u003dMax Knoblauch","pub\u003dMashable","date\u003dJaunary 29, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, How to Train Your Dragon]"]}
{"title":"South African apartheid assassin Eugene de Kock granted parole","wikiTitle":"South_African_apartheid_assassin_Eugene_de_Kock_granted_parole","wid":1895169,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-08T17:31:45Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/southafrica/11378913/Prime-Evil-apartheid-killer-Eugene-de-Kock-gets-parole.html, title\u003d\u0027Prime Evil\u0027 apartheid killer Eugene de Kock gets parole, author\u003dAislinn Laing, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31054912, title\u003dSouth Africa apartheid assassin De Kock given parole, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/prime-evil-apartheid-death-squad-commander-eugene-de-kock-granted-parole-in-south-africa-10013499.html, title\u003d\u0027Prime Evil\u0027 apartheid death squad commander Eugene de Kock granted parole in South Africa, author\u003dLizzie Dearden, (TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2014]"]],"links":[{"id":"South_Africa","description":"South Africa"},{"id":"human_rights","description":"human rights"},{"id":"Nelson_Mandela","description":"Nelson Mandela"},{"id":"BBC","description":"BBC"},{"id":"The_Associated_Press","description":"The Associated Press"},{"id":"Lesotho","description":"Lesotho"},{"id":"missing","description":"missing"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, January 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[South_Africa] South African Justice Minister TEMPLATE[w, Michael Masutha] yesterday announced he is granting parole to TEMPLATE[w, Eugene de Kock], an TEMPLATE[w, apartheid]-era assassin who has spent twenty years in prison. TEMPLATE[w, Jann Turner]TEMPLATE[Image_credit, George Hallett] After South Africa\u0027s first democratic elections in 1994 de Kock was arrested and subsequently detailed his actions to the nation\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Truth and Reconciliation Commission] (TRC). As head of a TEMPLATE[w, South African Police, police] \u0027counter-insurgency\u0027 unit de Kock took responsibility for murdering and torturing dissidents opposed to white-only rule. His methods included bombings, shootings, and stabbings and he operated internationally and at home. His revelations earned him the nickname \"Prime Evil\".","The TRC granted de Kock immunity for most crimes in exchange for his testimony. He was charged with remaining offences, not covered due to limits in TRC power, and in 1996 jailed for life for six murders. Additional convictions include kidnap and attempted murder. He received an additional 212-year term for those crimes. The TRC could only grant immunity where the offence was a human rights violation and the offender gave a full confession.","During his TRC testimony de Kock accused police commanders of ordering murders including those of TEMPLATE[w, African National Council] (ANC) members. In a 2007 prison interview he said TEMPLATE[w, FW de Klerk], the last white President, had hands \"soaked in blood\". De Klerk denies de Kock\u0027s allegations he ordered individual murders. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, It\u0027s mixed feelings, which is something we\u0027ve gotten used to as South Africans, 4\u003dEddie Makue] In the early nineties de Kock teamed up with anti-ANC party TEMPLATE[w, Inkatha] to arrange violence within black communities. Internal conflict killed 12,000 in the wake of future President Nelson Mandela\u0027s release. Mandela wrote of fearing \"a hidden hand behind the violence[...] attempting to disrupt the negotiations\", by orchestrating the clashes in TEMPLATE[w, Natal] and TEMPLATE[w, Transvaal]. He was referring to upcoming elections and a transfer of power away from white rule and apartheid.","Masutha said de Kock was being released \"in the interest of reconciliation and nation building\". The date, location, and terms are to remain secret.","Reaction from his victims is varied.","Murder victim Glenack Mama\u0027s widow Sandra welcomed the release. She said to a BBC reporter \"I think it will actually close a chapter in our history because we\u0027ve come a long way and I think his release will just once again help with the reconciliation process because there\u0027s still a lot of things that we need to do as a country\". She said \"He got the instructions from the top and they [more senior officials] got away with it[...] they\u0027re amongst us today and one man is taking the fall\". TEMPLATE[QuoteRight, I pray that those whom he hurt, those from whom he took loved ones, will find the power within them to forgive him, 4\u003dDesmond Tutu] Eddie Makue said to The Associated Press the release stirred up \"mixed feelings, which is something we\u0027ve gotten used to as South Africans\". He was a TEMPLATE[w, South African Council of Churches] employee in 1988 when de Kock bombed their headquarters. Jane Quin said she was \"terribly disappointed\" and he should never be released.  Her sister Jacqui Quin was murdered in Lesotho in 1985 by de Kock.","TRC chairman Archbishop TEMPLATE[w, Desmond Tutu] said \"I pray that those whom he hurt, those from whom he took loved ones, will find the power within them to forgive him.\" He said the release would not be universally welcome but is nonetheless \"to our collective credit, as people and as a nation.\" Tutu called it \"an indictment on our government\" that apartheid officials who did not co-operate with the TRC had evaded prosecution.","Whilst in prison de Kock has assisted the recovery of his missing victims\u0027 remains. Remorse and his help to the TEMPLATE[w, Missing Persons Task Team] were cited by Masutha as reasons to release him, which was initially decided against last July. \"[H]is key role has been to introduce us to other former security police who can assist with finding others,\" said Task Team leader Madeleine Fullard. Fullard said de Kock had also directly assisted in retrieving two bodies. \"He certainly feels lives were wasted for no reason\", she added, describing a meeting with him at one ANC victim\u0027s grave. \"He seemed to be quite stressed.\"","Masutha also announced yesterday the rejection of a parole application by apartheid killer TEMPLATE[w, Clive Derby-Lewis], an ex-MP. Derby-Lewis is serving life for murdering popular TEMPLATE[w, South African Communist Party] leader TEMPLATE[w, Chris Hani]. Hani also led the ANC\u0027s militant division. His killing in 1993 sparked rioting. Derby-Lewis sought parole because he has TEMPLATE[w, lung cancer]. Masutha said in rejecting the application that Derby-Lewis was remorseless.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:South_Africa","description":"Category:South Africa"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Serial_killers","description":"Category:Serial killers"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:BBC","description":"Category:BBC"},{"id":"Category:Associated_Press","description":"Category:Associated Press"},{"id":"Category:Missing_persons","description":"Category:Missing persons"},{"id":"Category:Lesotho","description":"Category:Lesotho"},{"id":"Category:Nelson_Mandela","description":"Category:Nelson Mandela"},{"id":"Category:Desmond_Tutu","description":"Category:Desmond Tutu"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["January 31, 2015"]},{"name":"South_Africa","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Michael Masutha"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eugene de Kock"]},{"name":"w","description":["apartheid"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jann Turner"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["George Hallett"]},{"name":"w","description":["Truth and Reconciliation Commission"]},{"name":"w","description":["South African Police","police"]},{"name":"w","description":["African National Council"]},{"name":"w","description":["FW de Klerk"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["It\u0027s mixed feelings, which is something we\u0027ve gotten used to as South Africans","4\u003dEddie Makue"]},{"name":"w","description":["Inkatha"]},{"name":"w","description":["Natal"]},{"name":"w","description":["Transvaal"]},{"name":"QuoteRight","description":["I pray that those whom he hurt, those from whom he took loved ones, will find the power within them to forgive him","4\u003dDesmond Tutu"]},{"name":"w","description":["South African Council of Churches"]},{"name":"w","description":["Desmond Tutu"]},{"name":"w","description":["Missing Persons Task Team"]},{"name":"w","description":["Clive Derby-Lewis"]},{"name":"w","description":["South African Communist Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Chris Hani"]},{"name":"w","description":["lung cancer"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/southafrica/11378913/Prime-Evil-apartheid-killer-Eugene-de-Kock-gets-parole.html","title\u003d\u0027Prime Evil\u0027 apartheid killer Eugene de Kock gets parole","author\u003dAislinn Laing","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31054912","title\u003dSouth Africa apartheid assassin De Kock given parole","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/prime-evil-apartheid-death-squad-commander-eugene-de-kock-granted-parole-in-south-africa-10013499.html","title\u003d\u0027Prime Evil\u0027 apartheid death squad commander Eugene de Kock granted parole in South Africa","author\u003dLizzie Dearden, (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2014"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["BBC","The Associated Press"]}
{"title":"Fire ravages large academic library in Moscow","wikiTitle":"Fire_ravages_large_academic_library_in_Moscow","wid":1895857,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-30T03:34:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-31074938, title\u003dFire rages through library in Russian capital, Moscow, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wsj.com/articles/fire-at-moscow-library-housing-rare-texts-1422724422, title\u003dFire at Moscow Library Damages Rare Texts, author\u003dOlga Razumovskaya, pub\u003dThe Wall Street Journal, date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/huge-library-containing-historic-texts-and-14-million-books-goes-up-in-flames-moscow-10015455.html, title\u003dHuge library containing historic texts and 14 million books goes up in flames Moscow, author\u003dJon Stone, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://rt.com/news/228075-moscow-fire-unique-library/, title\u003dMassive blaze devastates Russian library housing unique documents, ancient texts (PHOTOS, VIDEO), author\u003d, pub\u003dRT (TV network), date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Moscow","description":"Moscow"},{"id":"Russia","description":"Russia"},{"id":"United_Nations","description":"United Nations"},{"id":"Italy","description":"Italian"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"UK","description":"UK"},{"id":"Arson","description":"Arson"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[Russia] TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Putnik, Sergey Leschina]]] A fire Friday night and Saturday morning caused major damage to the TEMPLATE[w, Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences of the Russian Academy of Sciences, Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences] in Moscow, Russia. It is among the nation\u0027s largest academic libraries.","The fire began at 10p.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC+3, local time] on the third floor, damaging much of one wing.  TEMPLATE[w, Russian Academy of Sciences] boss Vladimir Fortov called it \"a great loss to science\". He said around 15% of the library\u0027s 14.2 million books and other documents are likely damaged.","TEMPLATE[w, RT (TV network), Russia Today] said 147 personnel battled the blaze with 38 vehicles. The emergency ministry puts the number of firefighters at over 200. The blaze left no injuries and was contained by around midnight. TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Putnik, Sergey Leschina]]] Thought to have escaped the fire are the library\u0027s collection of rare and ancient Slavic manuscripts. Other documents housed include Russia\u0027s largest repository of articles from the United Nations and TEMPLATE[w, UNESCO] in particular, and UN precursor the TEMPLATE[w, League of Nations]. Large numbers of other documents in old and modern languages from across Asia and Europe are on-site, as are reports from national legislatures. Parliamentary documents held include Italian documents from 1897, US documents from 1789, and UK documents from 1803.","Founded in 1918 and boasting 49,000 readers served by 330 staff, the library has lost around 2,000 square metres. The roof has partially collapsed. Arson has been ruled out with an official telling TEMPLATE[w, Ria Novosti] an electrical fault is considered likely.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, commons, Category:Fire in the Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences of Russian Academy of Sciences (31 January 2015)]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Russia","description":"Category:Russia"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Fires","description":"Category:Fires"},{"id":"Category:Moscow","description":"Category:Moscow"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Arson","description":"Category:Arson"},{"id":"Category:Books","description":"Category:Books"},{"id":"Category:Literature","description":"Category:Literature"},{"id":"Category:Russian_Academy_of_Sciences","description":"Category:Russian Academy of Sciences"},{"id":"Category:History","description":"Category:History"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Russia","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Putnik","Sergey Leschina]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences of the Russian Academy of Sciences","Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+3","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Russian Academy of Sciences"]},{"name":"w","description":["RT (TV network)","Russia Today"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Putnik","Sergey Leschina]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["UNESCO"]},{"name":"w","description":["League of Nations"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ria Novosti"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["commons","Category:Fire in the Institute of Scientific Information on Social Sciences of Russian Academy of Sciences (31 January 2015)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-31074938","title\u003dFire rages through library in Russian capital, Moscow","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wsj.com/articles/fire-at-moscow-library-housing-rare-texts-1422724422","title\u003dFire at Moscow Library Damages Rare Texts","author\u003dOlga Razumovskaya","pub\u003dThe Wall Street Journal","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/huge-library-containing-historic-texts-and-14-million-books-goes-up-in-flames-moscow-10015455.html","title\u003dHuge library containing historic texts and 14 million books goes up in flames Moscow","author\u003dJon Stone","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://rt.com/news/228075-moscow-fire-unique-library/","title\u003dMassive blaze devastates Russian library housing unique documents, ancient texts (PHOTOS, VIDEO)","author\u003d","pub\u003dRT (TV network)","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, RT (TV network), Russia Today]","TEMPLATE[w, Ria Novosti]"]}
{"title":"Richard von WeizsÃ¤cker, former President of Germany, dies","wikiTitle":"Richard_von_WeizsÃ¤cker,_former_President_of_Germany,_dies","wid":1897929,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-12T21:58:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-31073517, title\u003dGerman ex-President Richard von Weizsaecker dies at 94, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/europe/2015/01/german-president-weizsaecker-dies-94-150131132345021.html, title\u003dGerman ex-president Weizsaecker dies at 94, author\u003d, pub\u003dal-Jazeera, date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Germany","description":"German"},{"id":"World_War_II","description":"World War II"},{"id":"UK","description":"UK"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[Germany] TEMPLATE[w, Richard von WeizsÃ¤cker], the President who oversaw German reunification in 1990, was announced to have died yesterday. He was 94. TEMPLATE[w, German Federal Archives] von WeizsÃ¤cker served as a Nazi soldier during World War II, earning promotions and an TEMPLATE[w, Iron Cross]. He would later describe Germany\u0027s defeat as a liberation and encouraged his countrymen to acknowledge their collective past, including the TEMPLATE[w, Holocaust]. Following a business and law career he turned to politics. He joined the TEMPLATE[w, Christian Democratic Union (Germany), Christian Democratic Union] and served as mayor of TEMPLATE[w, West Berlin] before his 1984 election as President.","The year after, he made a famed speech before TEMPLATE[w, West Germany]\u0027s parliament marking the 40th anniversary of German defeat in the war. \"All of us, whether guilty or not, whether young or old, must accept the past. We are all affected by its consequences and liable for it. Anyone who closes his eyes to the past is blind to the present.\" He also said Allied forces \"freed us all from the system of National Socialist tyranny.\" TEMPLATE[QuoteRight, Guilt, like innocence, is always a matter for the individual, 4\u003dRichard von WeizsÃ¤cker] Born in TEMPLATE[w, Stuttgart] in 1920, von WeizsÃ¤cker oversaw reunification of West and TEMPLATE[w, East Germany] in 1990, eleven months after the TEMPLATE[w, Berlin Wall] fell. In 1989 he was reelected unopposed.  In 1986 he became the first German to address the UK parliament.","Present President TEMPLATE[w, Joachim Gauck] said von WeizsÃ¤cker \"stood worldwide for a Germany that had found its way to centre of the democratic family of peoples.\"","With his father TEMPLATE[w, Ernst von WeizsÃ¤cker, Ernst] a defendant at the TEMPLATE[w, Nuremberg trials], Richard von WeizsÃ¤cker appeared before the court as a lawyer for his father\u0027s defence. Ernst von WeizsÃ¤cker was a member of the TEMPLATE[w, Schutzstaffel], better known simply as the SS, and also worked for the foreign ministry.","\"Guilt,\" according to Richard von WeizsÃ¤cker, \"like innocence, is always a matter for the individual.\" He claimed as a military officer he refused to obey \"inhumane\" orders from more senior Nazis.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:World_War_II","description":"Category:World War II"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:The_Holocaust","description":"Category:The Holocaust"},{"id":"Category:Joachim_Gauck","description":"Category:Joachim Gauck"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Germany","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Richard von WeizsÃ¤cker"]},{"name":"w","description":["German Federal Archives"]},{"name":"w","description":["Iron Cross"]},{"name":"w","description":["Holocaust"]},{"name":"w","description":["Christian Democratic Union (Germany)","Christian Democratic Union"]},{"name":"w","description":["West Berlin"]},{"name":"w","description":["West Germany"]},{"name":"QuoteRight","description":["Guilt, like innocence, is always a matter for the individual","4\u003dRichard von WeizsÃ¤cker"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stuttgart"]},{"name":"w","description":["East Germany"]},{"name":"w","description":["Berlin Wall"]},{"name":"w","description":["Joachim Gauck"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ernst von WeizsÃ¤cker","Ernst"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nuremberg trials"]},{"name":"w","description":["Schutzstaffel"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-31073517","title\u003dGerman ex-President Richard von Weizsaecker dies at 94","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/europe/2015/01/german-president-weizsaecker-dies-94-150131132345021.html","title\u003dGerman ex-president Weizsaecker dies at 94","author\u003d","pub\u003dal-Jazeera","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Connecticut ex-death row inmate Robert Courchesne dies","wikiTitle":"Connecticut_ex-death_row_inmate_Robert_Courchesne_dies","wid":1902570,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-09T19:56:07Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://wtnh.com/2015/02/03/expectant-moms-killer-once-condemned-collapses-and-dies/, title\u003dExpectant momâs killer, once condemned, collapses and dies, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dWTNH, date\u003dFebruary 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.corrections.com/news/article/38772-former-death-row-inmate-s-death-under-investigation, title\u003dFormer Death Row Inmateâs Death Under Investigation, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dCorrections.com, date\u003dFebruary 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.660news.com/2015/02/02/ex-connecticut-death-row-inmate-convicted-of-killing-pregnant-woman-collapses-in-prison-dies/, title\u003dEx-Connecticut death row inmate convicted of killing pregnant woman collapses in prison, dies, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003d660 News, date\u003dFebruary 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Connecticut","description":"Connecticut"},{"id":"capital_punishment","description":"death sentence"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 3, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] Connecticut murder convict Robert Courchesne, who had a death sentence overturned by the TEMPLATE[w, Connecticut Supreme Court, state Supreme Court], collapsed in prison yesterday. He died in hospital an hour later. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[commons:User:Faolin42, John Phelan]]] Courchesne, now 57, stabbed heavily pregnant Demetris Rodgers to death in 1998. In 2004 he was convicted of her murder and that of her unborn baby, delivered minutes after the murder by TEMPLATE[w, cesarean section]. Baby Antonia Rodgers spent over a month on life support before death was confirmed. Using legislation that provided the death penalty to multiple murderers the court sentenced Courchesne to death.","Courchesne reached the Connecticut Supreme Court in 2010 and had the Antonia murder conviction overturned. The court ruled it was not proved the baby was alive at the time of the cesarean delivery. The death penalty was substituted with a 60-year sentence which prosecutors accepted instead of opting for a retrial.","Yesterday\u0027s death at TEMPLATE[w, Danbury Hospital] is being probed by police and prison officials, but is not considered suspicious. Courchesne collapsed while walking in the TEMPLATE[w, Garner Correctional Center], TEMPLATE[w, Newtown, Connecticut, Newtown] at around 10:35 a.m. TEMPLATE[w, Eastern Standard Time (North America), local time].","Connecticut abolished the death penalty in 2012, but those already on death row remained sentenced to die. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Connecticut","description":"Category:Connecticut"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Newtown,_Connecticut","description":"Category:Newtown, Connecticut"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 3, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Connecticut Supreme Court","state Supreme Court"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[commons:User:Faolin42","John Phelan]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["cesarean section"]},{"name":"w","description":["Danbury Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["Garner Correctional Center"]},{"name":"w","description":["Newtown, Connecticut","Newtown"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eastern Standard Time (North America)","local time"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://wtnh.com/2015/02/03/expectant-moms-killer-once-condemned-collapses-and-dies/","title\u003dExpectant momâs killer, once condemned, collapses and dies","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dWTNH","date\u003dFebruary 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.corrections.com/news/article/38772-former-death-row-inmate-s-death-under-investigation","title\u003dFormer Death Row Inmateâs Death Under Investigation","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dCorrections.com","date\u003dFebruary 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.660news.com/2015/02/02/ex-connecticut-death-row-inmate-convicted-of-killing-pregnant-woman-collapses-in-prison-dies/","title\u003dEx-Connecticut death row inmate convicted of killing pregnant woman collapses in prison, dies","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003d660 News","date\u003dFebruary 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Scottish university football club under investigation over \u0027blackface\u0027 event","wikiTitle":"Scottish_university_football_club_under_investigation_over_\u0027blackface\u0027_event","wid":1908838,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-04T03:29:51Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.stir.ac.uk/statement/, title\u003dUniversity and Students\u0027 Union response to serious incidents, author\u003dProfessor John Gardner and Amy McDermott, pub\u003dUniversity of Stirling, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://stirling.tab.co.uk/2015/02/06/watch-the-blackface-footballers-angrily-confront-locals-outside-cape/, title\u003dWatch the blackface footballers angrily confront locals outside Cape, author\u003dPaul Connolly, pub\u003dThe Tab, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://stirling.tab.co.uk/2015/02/06/racist-uni-football-team-blacks-up-for-african-cup-of-nations-social/, title\u003dâRacistâ uni football team blacks up for African Cup of Nations social, author\u003dPaul Connolly, pub\u003dThe Tab, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.stirlingstudentsunion.com/news/article/6013/University-and-Students-Union-response-to-serious-incidents/, title\u003dUniversity and Students\u0027 Union response to serious incidents, author\u003dProfessor John Gardner and Amy McDermott, pub\u003dUniversity of Stirling, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/TheTabStirling/posts/830195840380860, title\u003dIt\u0027s so cringe, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dFacebook, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.srtrc.org/news/news-and-events?news\u003d5388, title\u003dIntention to offend is not relevant when considering the practice of \u0027blackface\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dShow Racism the Red Card, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015 (date of access)]"]],"links":[{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scottish"},{"id":"Association_football","description":"football"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 6, 2015] TEMPLATE[Education] A Scottish university is investigating after several dozen members of its football club reportedly used TEMPLATE[w, Blackface, blackface] as part of costuming for a social event yesterday. Representatives from the TEMPLATE[w, University of Stirling], located in central Scotland, has said it has \"zero-tolerance\" for racism and is \"disappointed that the actions of a few are tarnishing the [university\u0027s] reputation\". TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, The university and the Students\u0027 Union have a zero-tolerance approach to racism and will respond robustly to any behaviour that does not meet with our values and expectations, source\u003d\u0027\u0027Professor John Gardner and Amy McDermott, University of Stirling\u0027\u0027]","TEMPLATE[w, Stirling University F.C.] yesterday tweeted about its intention to hold what it called an \"TEMPLATE[w, Africa Cup of Nations, African cup of nations]\" themed event that evening, although the tweet was later deleted. That evening, a group of people said to be from the team reportedly arrived at Cape, a bar in Stirling, wearing football kits, their faces and limbs covered black. Website TEMPLATE[w, The Tab] accompanies its report with pictures of several men who appear to be covered in black makeup and quotes one man, Jim MacIvor, describing witnessing \"30\u0026ndash;40 blacked up footballers having a drink\", socialising, \"being quite boisterous [...] [and] quite drunk \u0026mdash; and some of them were taking their tops off and stuff like that.\" The website also shared video of members of the public confronting some of the men in the group and accusing them of racism.","The Tab, which in publicising its article described the incident as \"so cringe\", has prompted debate among Facebook users as to whether or not the football club members\u0027 actions amount to racism. A spokesperson for TEMPLATE[w, Show Racism the Red Card], a charity advocating for anti-racism education, said: \"The practice of blacking up was usually as part of a show by white entertainers for white audiences which relied on mocking black peopleâs skin colour and culture; the practice is racist and should definitely be avoided in our more enlightened times.\" Previously, the same charity has said \"it is the consequences of the practice rather than the intention that is relevant; what does black-face say to people, and young people particularly about the acceptance and normality of different skin colours in society? Show Racism the Red Card would argue that these practices caricature and exoticise differences which could lead to discrimination.\"","The university has suspended four of its football teams from any football-related activities as the investigation continues. In a joint statement, Professor John Gardner, Deputy Principal for Education and Students, and student union president Amy McDermott, said the university is investigating the incident. \"The university and the Studentsâ Union have a zero-tolerance approach to racism and will respond robustly to any behaviour that does not meet with our values and expectations\", their statement said. \"We are committed to promoting equality and diversity so that all students, staff and members of society can be confident that they will be treated with dignity and respect.  We promote equality and diversity through a variety of policies and initiatives, including the âOne Stirlingâ campaign, which outlines our commitment to these values. We are disappointed that the actions of a few are tarnishing the reputation of the University of Stirling, and we wish to reassure students that a full investigation is underway and disciplinary action will be taken against any student found to have engaged in racist behaviour.\"","Upon contacting Gardner and McDermott, as well as Sports President Chris Priddle, to enquire further about the incident, the university reiterated to Wikinews the comments made in the above statement.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Education","description":"Category:Education"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Education","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Blackface","blackface"]},{"name":"w","description":["University of Stirling"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["The university and the Students\u0027 Union have a zero-tolerance approach to racism and will respond robustly to any behaviour that does not meet with our values and expectations","source\u003d\u0027\u0027Professor John Gardner and Amy McDermott, University of Stirling\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stirling University F.C."]},{"name":"w","description":["Africa Cup of Nations","African cup of nations"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Tab"]},{"name":"w","description":["Show Racism the Red Card"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.stir.ac.uk/statement/","title\u003dUniversity and Students\u0027 Union response to serious incidents","author\u003dProfessor John Gardner and Amy McDermott","pub\u003dUniversity of Stirling","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://stirling.tab.co.uk/2015/02/06/watch-the-blackface-footballers-angrily-confront-locals-outside-cape/","title\u003dWatch the blackface footballers angrily confront locals outside Cape","author\u003dPaul Connolly","pub\u003dThe Tab","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://stirling.tab.co.uk/2015/02/06/racist-uni-football-team-blacks-up-for-african-cup-of-nations-social/","title\u003dâRacistâ uni football team blacks up for African Cup of Nations social","author\u003dPaul Connolly","pub\u003dThe Tab","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.stirlingstudentsunion.com/news/article/6013/University-and-Students-Union-response-to-serious-incidents/","title\u003dUniversity and Students\u0027 Union response to serious incidents","author\u003dProfessor John Gardner and Amy McDermott","pub\u003dUniversity of Stirling","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/TheTabStirling/posts/830195840380860","title\u003dIt\u0027s so cringe","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dFacebook","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.srtrc.org/news/news-and-events?news\u003d5388","title\u003dIntention to offend is not relevant when considering the practice of \u0027blackface\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dShow Racism the Red Card","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015 (date of access)"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["source","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Tab]","The Tab","Wikinews"]}
{"title":"Man steals dying lorry crash victim\u0027s purse in Greater Manchester, England","wikiTitle":"Man_steals_dying_lorry_crash_victim\u0027s_purse_in_Greater_Manchester,_England","wid":1909652,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-09T20:04:33Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.gmp.police.uk/Content/WebsitePages/0D156311CAA35A4F80257DE40060CED8?OpenDocument, title\u003dPolice investigate after purse stolen, author\u003d, pub\u003dGreater Manchester Police, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wigantoday.net/news/local/purse-stolen-as-pensioner-lay-dying-1-7092877, title\u003dPurse stolen as pensioner lay dying, author\u003d, pub\u003dWigan Today, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.leighjournal.co.uk/news/11770574.UPDATED__Woman_dies_after_being_hit_by_lorry/, title\u003dWoman dies after being hit by lorry in Leigh, author\u003dSophie Arnold, pub\u003dLeigh Journal, date\u003dFebruary 4, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"England","description":"England"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] England\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Greater Manchester Police] yesterday appealed to the public for information to track down a man who stole a woman\u0027s purse after she was fatally injured by a lorry. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, This is one of the most disgusting crimes I have ever investigated and I find it hard to believe someone could stoop so low to commit such a horrific offence, source\u003dSergeant Neil Lawless]","Police were alerted to the collision between the truck and the 82-year-old woman, in the town of TEMPLATE[w, Leigh, Greater Manchester, Leigh], at approximately 1145 TEMPLATE[w, Coordinated Universal Time, UTC] on Wednesday. The woman died at the scene, in what one nearby resident called \"a horrible thing to have happened\". Witnesses subsequently told police a man stole the victim\u0027s purse in the aftermath of the crash.","\"This is one of the most disgusting crimes I have ever investigated and I find it hard to believe someone could stoop so low to commit such a horrific offence,\" said detective Sergeant Neil Lawless. \"This man has taken what he sees as an easy opportunity by stealing a purse from a dying woman.  I am sure the community will be equally disgusted and I appeal to anyone who may have seen this man take the purse and walk off on Leigh Road. There are a number of rumours circulating on social media at the moment but I would like to reassure residents we are doing all we can to find out who is responsible.\" Meanwhile, website Wigan Today has claimed witnesses and an unnamed Greater Manchester Police source informed it some nearby pedestrians took pictures of her body following the crash, although the official police statement does not directly address these claims.","Sergeant Lawless has asked members of the public to contact police with any information that may be relevant to the investigation. Greater Manchester Police describe the thief as white, of medium build, aged between 30 and 40, and six feet in height. The police force say he \"had a dark brown beard, [and] wore a light grey hooded top with the hood pulled over his head, light blue jeans and black boot style training shoes.\"","TEMPLATE[PhoneContact, Anyone with any information about this incident is asked to contact: Greater Manchester Police: 101  (TEMPLATE) (anonymous): 0800 555 111]","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Greater_Manchester","description":"Category:Greater Manchester"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Greater_Manchester_Police","description":"Category:Greater Manchester Police"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Greater Manchester Police"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["This is one of the most disgusting crimes I have ever investigated and I find it hard to believe someone could stoop so low to commit such a horrific offence","source\u003dSergeant Neil Lawless"]},{"name":"w","description":["Leigh, Greater Manchester","Leigh"]},{"name":"w","description":["Coordinated Universal Time","UTC"]},{"name":"PhoneContact","description":["Anyone with any information about this incident is asked to contact:\nGreater Manchester Police: 101\n\n(TEMPLATE) (anonymous): 0800 555 111"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.gmp.police.uk/Content/WebsitePages/0D156311CAA35A4F80257DE40060CED8?OpenDocument","title\u003dPolice investigate after purse stolen","author\u003d","pub\u003dGreater Manchester Police","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wigantoday.net/news/local/purse-stolen-as-pensioner-lay-dying-1-7092877","title\u003dPurse stolen as pensioner lay dying","author\u003d","pub\u003dWigan Today","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.leighjournal.co.uk/news/11770574.UPDATED__Woman_dies_after_being_hit_by_lorry/","title\u003dWoman dies after being hit by lorry in Leigh","author\u003dSophie Arnold","pub\u003dLeigh Journal","date\u003dFebruary 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["source","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Wigan Today"]}
{"title":"Chinese market fire kills seventeen, child detained","wikiTitle":"Chinese_market_fire_kills_seventeen,_child_detained","wid":1910371,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-09T20:24:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1704301/least-17-people-killed-raging-fire-sweeps-through-china-shopping-mall, title\u003dHong Kong girl, 14, feared among 17 killed in blaze at Guangdong shopping mall, author\u003dHe Huifeng, pub\u003dSouth China Morning Post, date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.tribuneindia.com/news/world/china-mall-fire-kills-17/38931.html, title\u003dChina mall fire kills 17, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Tribune (Chandigarh), date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-31159879, title\u003dChina\u0027s deadly shopping blaze \u0027started by boy, nine\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/feb/06/china-shopping-mall-fire-kills-at-least-17-guangdong, title\u003dChina shopping mall fire kills at least 17, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"China","description":"China"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[China] Police detained a nine-year-old after a blaze started in a wholesale market in TEMPLATE[w, Huizhou], TEMPLATE[w, Guangdong], southern China on Thursday afternoon. Seventeen died. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:é¿å¤æ é£, User:é¿å¤æ é£]]] According to police the child was playing with matches in a warehouse on the top-floor of the four-storey Yiwu Commodity Mall. Soon the entire floor was engulfed, leading to an eighteen-hour TEMPLATE[w, search and rescue, rescue] mission involving 270 firefighters with 45 vehicles. Nine market managers have also been detained.","The complex includes restaurants and a cinema. The cinema\u0027s bathroom, on the top floor, became a trap for ten of the victims. Firefighter Wan Jie told reporters \"Our firemen tried several times to approach the fourth floor where the cinema was located, without success. It was too dark to see anything and the temperature was extremely high. We carried oxygen bottles as we crawled forward.\"","He described how he and another firefighter almost ran out of oxygen while rescuing one girl. Around 300 people were evacuated. Photos at the scene showed medical personnel, some with stretchers, waiting en masse to treat casualties.","Firefighters came from TEMPLATE[w, Shenzhen], TEMPLATE[w, Dongguan], and TEMPLATE[w, Shanwei] to augment local forces. Four, including Wan Jie, were injured. \"It was the worst and most dangerous fire I have ever attended,\" he said. The fire service said the entire building, which passed a safety inspection last month, was at risk of collapse. The fire was extinguished around 8a.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC+8, local time] yesterday.","TEMPLATE[w, Southern Metropolis News] released a list of suspected victims. Among them are a family of four and a fourteen-year-old girl from TEMPLATE[w, Hong Kong].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:China","description":"Category:China"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Fires","description":"Category:Fires"},{"id":"Category:Arson","description":"Category:Arson"},{"id":"Category:Hong_Kong","description":"Category:Hong Kong"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Guangdong","description":"Category:Guangdong"},{"id":"Category:Shenzhen","description":"Category:Shenzhen"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 7, 2015"]},{"name":"China","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Huizhou"]},{"name":"w","description":["Guangdong"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:é¿å¤æ é£","User:é¿å¤æ é£]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["search and rescue","rescue"]},{"name":"w","description":["Shenzhen"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dongguan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Shanwei"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+8","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Southern Metropolis News"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hong Kong"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1704301/least-17-people-killed-raging-fire-sweeps-through-china-shopping-mall","title\u003dHong Kong girl, 14, feared among 17 killed in blaze at Guangdong shopping mall","author\u003dHe Huifeng","pub\u003dSouth China Morning Post","date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.tribuneindia.com/news/world/china-mall-fire-kills-17/38931.html","title\u003dChina mall fire kills 17","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Tribune (Chandigarh)","date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-31159879","title\u003dChina\u0027s deadly shopping blaze \u0027started by boy, nine\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/feb/06/china-shopping-mall-fire-kills-at-least-17-guangdong","title\u003dChina shopping mall fire kills at least 17","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub",