{"title":"Taipei plane crash toll reaches 40","wikiTitle":"Taipei_plane_crash_toll_reaches_40","wid":1910958,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-16T13:49:40Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thenewstribune.com/2015/02/07/3627356/transasia-pilots-undergo-proficiency.html, title\u003dTransAsia pilots undergo proficiency tests following crash, author\u003dRalph Jennings ([[Associated Press, AP]]), pub\u003dThe News Tribune, date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/02/07/asia/taiwan-transasia-plane-crash/index.html, title\u003dTransAsia plane had engine trouble before crash; death toll rises to 40, author\u003dDavid Molko, Jethro Mullen, Faith Karimi, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/transasia-crash-hero-pilots-died-clutching-joystick-after-steering-plane-through-skyscrapers-10027701.html, title\u003dTransAsia crash: Hero pilots died clutching joystick after steering plane through skyscrapers, author\u003dLizzie Dearden, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Taiwan","description":"Taiwan"},{"id":"aerodynamic_stall","description":"stall"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[w:zh:User:M940504, M940504]]] The death toll from Wednesday\u0027s plane crash in TEMPLATE[w, Taipei], Taiwan reached 40 today with the recovery of five more bodies.","There were 58 on board when TEMPLATE[w, TransAsia Airways] TEMPLATE[w, TransAsia Airways Flight 235, Flight 235] crashed into the city\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Keelung River]. Fifteen survived and three more remain missing. TEMPLATE[w, Tzu Chi Foundation] volunteer Lee Hung Shu-ying said today cold weather meant the families of the missing believe their loved ones are dead.","The Aviation Safety Council is investigating. The plane was in the air for minutes before banking steeply, hitting an elevated road, and crashing into the river. The domestic flight from TEMPLATE[w, Taipei Songshan Airport] was headed to the island of TEMPLATE[w, Kinmen].","Investigators are focusing on the TEMPLATE[w, ATR 72, ATR 72-600]\u0027s engines. One engine automatically \u0027feathered\u0027 itself. Feathering involves the TEMPLATE[w, turboprop]\u0027s propeller rotating its blades to reduce drag.","Engines autofeather when they fail (\u0027flaming out\u0027). By reducing drag on the non-working engine, a twin turboprop plane can fly safely using only its other engine. A feathered engine will not provide any thrust. The reason for autofeathering is presently unclear; what is known is the flight crew subsequently shut off the wrong engine. A series of stall warnings went off in the cockpit as the aircraft headed to disaster.","Aviation Safety Council managing director Thomas Wang confirmed an automated \"number two engine flameout\" message should have alerted the crew to the engine trouble, leading them to follow \"the corresponding checklist\". \"There are procedures that pilots go through â safeguards â when you\u0027re going to shut down an engine, particularly close to the ground,\" said John M. Cox, former commercial pilot and boss of a safety consultant. \"Why that didn\u0027t occur here, I don\u0027t know.\" TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[commons:User:çå²ç, çå²ç]]] Stephen Fredrick, a former pilot of similar aircraft, told TEMPLATE[w, CNN] video showing the final seconds is consistent with dual flameout. He said the wings-level, nose-down position suggested gliding.","Wang, however, cautions it is too early to blame any particular factor. \"At this moment we just release the numbers, the parameter we\u0027ve confirmed, we did not release any judgment who did what at this time\". The Aviation Safety Council has teamed up with engine manufacturer TEMPLATE[w, Pratt and Whitney, Pratt \u0026 Whitney Canada] to examine the engines.","Also being prioritised is finalising a TEMPLATE[w, cockpit voice recorder] transcript and cockpit examination. The aircraft was near-new.","Local prosecutors are investigating potential \"professional error\", and the TEMPLATE[w, Civil Aeronautics Administration] has ordered TransAsia retest all ATR pilots. 90 flights over three days are cancelled to allow the proficiency checks. TransAsia and TEMPLATE[w, Uni Air] have also been ordered to check their collective 22 ATRs for engine and fuel system problems.","Pilot Liao Chien-tsung and his co-pilot, not publicly identified, were initially hailed as heroes by prosecutors, mayor Ko Wen-je, international press, and at least one relative of a survivor. After declaring \"Mayday Mayday, engine flameout\" to TEMPLATE[w, air traffic control] the pair grappled with their struggling plane, avoiding buildings in its path.","They have been credited with reducing the death toll. Their bodies were found in the cockpit, with leg fractures. Both were still holding the wrecked plane\u0027s controls.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, TransAsia Airways Flight 235] TEMPLATE[sisters, commons, Category:TransAsia Airways Flight 235]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Taiwan","description":"Category:Taiwan"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Missing_persons","description":"Category:Missing persons"},{"id":"Category:Aerodynamic_stalls","description":"Category:Aerodynamic stalls"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[w:zh:User:M940504","M940504]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Taipei"]},{"name":"w","description":["TransAsia Airways"]},{"name":"w","description":["TransAsia Airways Flight 235","Flight 235"]},{"name":"w","description":["Keelung River"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tzu Chi Foundation"]},{"name":"w","description":["Taipei Songshan Airport"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kinmen"]},{"name":"w","description":["ATR 72","ATR 72-600"]},{"name":"w","description":["turboprop"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[commons:User:çå²ç","çå²ç]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["CNN"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pratt and Whitney","Pratt \u0026 Whitney Canada"]},{"name":"w","description":["cockpit voice recorder"]},{"name":"w","description":["Civil Aeronautics Administration"]},{"name":"w","description":["Uni Air"]},{"name":"w","description":["air traffic control"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","TransAsia Airways Flight 235"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["commons","Category:TransAsia Airways Flight 235"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thenewstribune.com/2015/02/07/3627356/transasia-pilots-undergo-proficiency.html","title\u003dTransAsia pilots undergo proficiency tests following crash","author\u003dRalph Jennings ([[Associated Press","AP]])","pub\u003dThe News Tribune","date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/02/07/asia/taiwan-transasia-plane-crash/index.html","title\u003dTransAsia plane had engine trouble before crash; death toll rises to 40","author\u003dDavid Molko, Jethro Mullen, Faith Karimi","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/transasia-crash-hero-pilots-died-clutching-joystick-after-steering-plane-through-skyscrapers-10027701.html","title\u003dTransAsia crash: Hero pilots died clutching joystick after steering plane through skyscrapers","author\u003dLizzie Dearden","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dFebruary 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Cancer kills Niki Quasney, Indiana gay marriage pioneer","wikiTitle":"Cancer_kills_Niki_Quasney,_Indiana_gay_marriage_pioneer","wid":1912885,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-05T01:24:09Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.indystar.com/story/news/2015/02/08/munster-woman-indianas-st-sex-marriage-dies/23050723/, title\u003dMunster woman in Indianaâs 1st same-sex marriage dies, author\u003dJill Disis, pub\u003dThe Indianapolis Star, date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://wishtv.com/2015/02/08/indiana-woman-who-fought-gay-marriage-ban-dies-of-cancer/, title\u003dIndiana woman who fought gay-marriage ban dies of cancer, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dWISH-TV, date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"gay_marriage","description":"married gay couple"},{"id":"Indiana","description":"Indiana"},{"id":"cancer","description":"cancer"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Massachusetts","description":"Massachusetts"},{"id":"Illinois","description":"Illinois"},{"id":"Chicago","description":"Chicago"},{"id":"US_Supreme_Court","description":"national Supreme Court"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[LGBT] Niki Quasney, who together with wife Amy Sandler became the first married gay couple in Indiana, died of cancer on Thursday. She was 38. The death was announced today by the law firm that assisted her. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, They knew that by coming forward they could help accelerate equality for all same-sex couples in Indiana by demonstrating the urgency of their need for equal dignity, 4\u003dThe couple\u0027s lawyer] Indiana, US had only recognised their marriage last year after a TEMPLATE[w, US federal law, federal] judge granted their emergency request. They wed in 2013 in Massachusetts, two years after an Illinois civil union.","Quasney was diagnosed with TEMPLATE[w, ovarian cancer] in 2009 and sought the intervention to ensure eligibility for her daughters and wife to receive state and national assistance after her death. Also sought was a death certificate recognising her marriage.","The same judge ultimately struck down the state gay marriage ban. An appeals court in Chicago upheld the decision, as did the national Supreme Court. The case was one of a national slew following an earlier Supreme Court ruling in favor of gay marriage.","\"If my life is cut short because of ovarian cancer,\" Quasney told one court \"I want our children to know that their parents were treated like other married couples in their home state, and to be proud of this. I want to know what it feels like to be a legally recognized family in our community, together with Amy and our daughters.\" Their lawyer Paul Castillo said today the couple \"knew that by coming forward they could help accelerate equality for all same-sex couples in Indiana by demonstrating the urgency of their need for equal dignity.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Indiana","description":"Category:Indiana"},{"id":"Category:Massachusetts","description":"Category:Massachusetts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:US_Supreme_Court","description":"Category:US Supreme Court"},{"id":"Category:Cancer","description":"Category:Cancer"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Same-sex_marriage","description":"Category:Same-sex marriage"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 8, 2015"]},{"name":"LGBT","description":[]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["They knew that by coming forward they could help accelerate equality for all same-sex couples in Indiana by demonstrating the urgency of their need for equal dignity","4\u003dThe couple\u0027s lawyer"]},{"name":"w","description":["US federal law","federal"]},{"name":"w","description":["ovarian cancer"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.indystar.com/story/news/2015/02/08/munster-woman-indianas-st-sex-marriage-dies/23050723/","title\u003dMunster woman in Indianaâs 1st same-sex marriage dies","author\u003dJill Disis","pub\u003dThe Indianapolis Star","date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://wishtv.com/2015/02/08/indiana-woman-who-fought-gay-marriage-ban-dies-of-cancer/","title\u003dIndiana woman who fought gay-marriage ban dies of cancer","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dWISH-TV","date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Divers retrieve 100th corpse from Java Sea jet crash","wikiTitle":"Divers_retrieve_100th_corpse_from_Java_Sea_jet_crash","wid":1912987,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-20T21:12:05Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAirAsia disaster: Bodies, wreckage found, date\u003dDecember 30, 2014]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAirAsia jet vanishes over Indonesia, 162 missing, date\u003dDecember 28, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://globalnews.ca/news/1817576/divers-recover-more-bodies-from-airasia-crash-raising-number-retrieved-to-100/, title\u003dDivers recover more bodies from AirAsia crash, raising number retrieved to 100, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dThe Canadian Press, date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.presstv.ir/Detail/2015/02/07/396611/7-bodies-retrieved-from-AirAsia-plane, title\u003dSeven more bodies retrieved from doomed AirAsia plane, author\u003dMFB/HJL/SS, pub\u003dPress TV, date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jan/30/airasia-pilots-turned-off-planes-computer-system-before-crash-report, title\u003dAirAsia pilots may have turned off plane computer system before crash, report claims, author\u003dTania Branigan, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Java_Sea","description":"Java Sea"},{"id":"AirAsia","description":"AirAsia"},{"id":"Indonesia_AirAsia_Flight_8501","description":"Flight 8501"},{"id":"Juanda_International_Airport","description":"Juanda International Airport"},{"id":"Singapore","description":"Singapore"},{"id":"Changi_International_Airport","description":"Changi International Airport"},{"id":"Indonesia","description":"Indonesia"},{"id":"South_Korea","description":"South Korea"},{"id":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysia"},{"id":"UK","description":"Brit"},{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"Sulawesi","description":"Sulawesi"},{"id":"National_Transportation_Safety_Committee","description":"National Transportation Safety Committee"},{"id":"aerodynamic_stall","description":"stalling"},{"id":"weather","description":"weather"},{"id":"National_Search_and_Rescue_Agency","description":"National Search and Rescue Agency"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[Indonesia] Divers yesterday recovered three bodies from December\u0027s air disaster in the Java Sea. Added to four retrieved on Friday, they bring the total to 100. An additional 62 victims remain to be recovered. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:Sabung.hamster, Oka Sudiatmika]]] There were no survivors when Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501 crashed on December 28. The six-year-old TEMPLATE[w, Airbus A320-200] was 40 minutes from Juanda International Airport with 155 passengers and seven crew, bound for Singapore\u0027s Changi International Airport. Most were Indonesians, with three South Koreans, one Malaysian, one Brit and one French person on board.","One of the latest bodies was a uniformed man strapped into a cockpit seat, and presumed to be either Indonesian Pilot Iriyanto or French co-pilot Remi Emmanuel Plesel. Underwater currents have complicated recovery of the other body from the cockpit. Efforts to retrieve the entire aircraft last month were abandoned. Some bodies have been found roughly 1,000 TEMPLATE[w, kilometre, kilometres] (600 TEMPLATE[w, mile, miles]) from the crash site, floating near Sulawesi.","Iriyanto and Plessel had over 8,000 hours experience between them. Iriyanto has a decade of experience training other pilots, and previous employers include the air force. Their actions have come under scrutiny as the National Transportation Safety Committee (NTSC) investigates. TEMPLATE[image_credit, Antonio P. Turretto Ramos, (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, US Navy] The aircraft entered an excessively steep climb before stalling, the NTSC said last month. It took three minutes for the plane to reach the water, during which time the flight crew tried to regain control. TEMPLATE[w, Bloomberg] claims the flight crew switched off computers designed to aid them after they issued alerts. AirAsia has declined to comment pending the NTSC investigation, which is expected to continue for several months.","The TEMPLATE[w, Agency for Meteorology, Climatology and Geophysics] suggests weather caused the disaster, suggesting ice led to engine failure. NTSC head investigator Marjono Siswosuwarno last month reported satellite data showed storms as high as 44,000ft. The plane was attempting to avoid storms in the minutes before contact was lost.","The National Search and Rescue Agency has over 60 divers working to retrieve the bodies.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501] TEMPLATE[sisters, commons, Category:Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia","description":"Category:Indonesia"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia_AirAsia_Flight_8501","description":"Category:Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501"},{"id":"Category:Java_Sea","description":"Category:Java Sea"},{"id":"Category:National_Search_and_Rescue_Agency","description":"Category:National Search and Rescue Agency"},{"id":"Category:National_Transportation_Safety_Committee","description":"Category:National Transportation Safety Committee"},{"id":"Category:Weather","description":"Category:Weather"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Sulawesi","description":"Category:Sulawesi"},{"id":"Category:Singapore","description":"Category:Singapore"},{"id":"Category:Juanda_International_Airport","description":"Category:Juanda International Airport"},{"id":"Category:Changi_International_Airport","description":"Category:Changi International Airport"},{"id":"Category:South_Korea","description":"Category:South Korea"},{"id":"Category:Korean_Peninsula","description":"Category:Korean Peninsula"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Aerodynamic_stalls","description":"Category:Aerodynamic stalls"},{"id":"Category:AirAsia","description":"Category:AirAsia"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Indonesia","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:Sabung.hamster","Oka Sudiatmika]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Airbus A320-200"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometre","kilometres"]},{"name":"w","description":["mile","miles"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Antonio P. Turretto Ramos, (TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Navy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bloomberg"]},{"name":"w","description":["Agency for Meteorology, Climatology and Geophysics"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dAirAsia disaster: Bodies, wreckage found","date\u003dDecember 30, 2014"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dAirAsia jet vanishes over Indonesia, 162 missing","date\u003dDecember 28, 2014"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["commons","Category:Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://globalnews.ca/news/1817576/divers-recover-more-bodies-from-airasia-crash-raising-number-retrieved-to-100/","title\u003dDivers recover more bodies from AirAsia crash, raising number retrieved to 100","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dThe Canadian Press","date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.presstv.ir/Detail/2015/02/07/396611/7-bodies-retrieved-from-AirAsia-plane","title\u003dSeven more bodies retrieved from doomed AirAsia plane","author\u003dMFB/HJL/SS","pub\u003dPress TV","date\u003dFebruary 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jan/30/airasia-pilots-turned-off-planes-computer-system-before-crash-report","title\u003dAirAsia pilots may have turned off plane computer system before crash, report claims","author\u003dTania Branigan","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dJanuary 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Bloomberg]"]}
{"title":"Four die in dump truck crash in Bath, England","wikiTitle":"Four_die_in_dump_truck_crash_in_Bath,_England","wid":1915694,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-19T14:53:52Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMultiple fatalities in bin lorry crash in Glasgow, Scotland, date\u003dDecember 22, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.avonandsomerset.police.uk/newsroom/investigation-launched-into-fatal-collision-in-bath/, title\u003dInvestigation launched into fatal collision in Bath, author\u003d, pub\u003dAvon and Somerset Constabulary, date\u003dFebruary 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.itv.com/news/west/story/2015-02-09/breaking-four-dead-after-serious-collision-in-bath/, title\u003dBREAKING: four dead after serious collision in Bath, author\u003d, pub\u003dITV News West Country, date\u003dFebruary 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-bristol-31321186, title\u003dBath tipper truck crash kills child and three adults, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dFebruary 9, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"England","description":"England"},{"id":"Bristol","description":"Bristol"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 10, 2015] TEMPLATE[Disasters_and_accidents] Four people have died and at least four more have been seriously injured after a TEMPLATE[w, Dump truck, dump truck] hit multiple vehicles and two pedestrians in TEMPLATE[w, Bath, Somerset, Bath] in TEMPLATE[w, South West England, South West] England. The incident occurred at around 1600 TEMPLATE[w, Coordinated Universal Time, UTC] yesterday when the truck rolled down a hill on Lansdown Lane in the city\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Weston, Bath, Upper Weston] district in what witness accounts given to police suggest was an accident avoidance attempt.","The four fatalities died at the scene of the crash, on a steep hill close to Weston All Saints Primary School. Three people injured were taken to TEMPLATE[w, Royal United Hospital] in Bath; one was critically injured and transported to Bristol\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Southmead Hospital] by air ambulance. A number of others also received minor injuries, leading to the primary school being turned into a temporary hospital. Eyewitness accounts reported by TEMPLATE[w, ITV News West Country] indicated the truck driver repeatedly beeped his horn in the seconds before the collision, at a time when a number of children would have been leaving the school.","Police closed off the road to allow for investigative work. Speaking on behalf of TEMPLATE[w, Avon and Somerset Constabulary], Chief Superintendent Caroline Peters, who described the collision scene as \"one of carnage\", explained: \"We have a collision team of investigators who are trying to assess the cause of this accident and we are working very closely with the fire service and South West Ambulance\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Somerset","description":"Category:Somerset"},{"id":"Category:Bristol","description":"Category:Bristol"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Dump truck","dump truck"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bath, Somerset","Bath"]},{"name":"w","description":["South West England","South West"]},{"name":"w","description":["Coordinated Universal Time","UTC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Weston, Bath","Upper Weston"]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal United Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["Southmead Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["ITV News West Country"]},{"name":"w","description":["Avon and Somerset Constabulary"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMultiple fatalities in bin lorry crash in Glasgow, Scotland","date\u003dDecember 22, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.avonandsomerset.police.uk/newsroom/investigation-launched-into-fatal-collision-in-bath/","title\u003dInvestigation launched into fatal collision in Bath","author\u003d","pub\u003dAvon and Somerset Constabulary","date\u003dFebruary 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.itv.com/news/west/story/2015-02-09/breaking-four-dead-after-serious-collision-in-bath/","title\u003dBREAKING: four dead after serious collision in Bath","author\u003d","pub\u003dITV News West Country","date\u003dFebruary 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-bristol-31321186","title\u003dBath tipper truck crash kills child and three adults","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dFebruary 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, ITV News West Country]"]}
{"title":"Two men shot during robbery in Houston, Texas","wikiTitle":"Two_men_shot_during_robbery_in_Houston,_Texas","wid":1919766,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-22T14:55:16Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.khou.com/story/news/crime/2015/02/11/robbers-on-the-run-after-killing-stereo-shop-worker-in-nw-houston/23220759/, title\u003dRobbers on the run after killing stereo shop worker in NW Houston, author\u003d, pub\u003dKHOU, date\u003dFebruary 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.click2houston.com/news/two-men-shot-during-robbery-in-northwest-houston/31204492, title\u003dTwo men shot during robbery in Northwest Houston, author\u003dRobert Arnold, pub\u003dKPRC-TV, date\u003dFebruary 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Houston,_Texas","description":"Houston"},{"id":"Texas","description":"Texas"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Texas] Two men were shot during a robbery at a car stereo and alarm business in the city of Houston, Texas yesterday evening, according to police. One of the men, Abdullah Shakur, 65, later died at a local hospital.  The other man, Samer Salam, 32, was reportedly in critical condition late Tuesday evening.  TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Rama, User:Rama]]] Police said three robbers carried out the attack, each wearing masks,  Reportedly, the store employees resisted. No suspects had been named as of 1:30pm local time Wednesday.","It is unclear if the suspects left with any property, but early reports indicate one suspect was injured during the robbery. Police noted a blood trail was found outside the business. Police said the men may have arrived at the business driving a light blue or silver TEMPLATE[w, Ford Mustang].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Texas","description":"Category:Texas"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Houston","description":"Category:Houston"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Texas","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Rama","User:Rama]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ford Mustang"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.khou.com/story/news/crime/2015/02/11/robbers-on-the-run-after-killing-stereo-shop-worker-in-nw-houston/23220759/","title\u003dRobbers on the run after killing stereo shop worker in NW Houston","author\u003d","pub\u003dKHOU","date\u003dFebruary 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.click2houston.com/news/two-men-shot-during-robbery-in-northwest-houston/31204492","title\u003dTwo men shot during robbery in Northwest Houston","author\u003dRobert Arnold","pub\u003dKPRC-TV","date\u003dFebruary 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Indian army helicopter crash kills two in Jammu and Kashmir","wikiTitle":"Indian_army_helicopter_crash_kills_two_in_Jammu_and_Kashmir","wid":1920217,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-22T14:55:19Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/army-chopper-crash-laman-forests-bandipora-district-jammu-and-kashmir-police/1/418391.html, title\u003dPilot and co-pilot killed in Army helicopter crash in Kashmir, author\u003d, pub\u003dIndia Today, date\u003dFebruary 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Two-officers-killed-in-Army-helicopter-crash-in-JK/articleshow/46203714.cms, title\u003dTwo officers killed in Army helicopter crash in J\u0026K, author\u003dRajat Pandit ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003dThe Times of India, date\u003dFebruary 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Jammu_and_Kashmir","description":"Jammu and Kashmir"},{"id":"Ecuador","description":"Ecuador"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[India] A military helicopter crashed in Jammu and Kashmir today. Two people, believed to be the pilots, are dead. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:ILA-boy, ILA-boy]]] Both bodies are too burned for immediate identification. The TEMPLATE[w, HAL Dhruv, Dhruv] caught fire after going down in a forest in TEMPLATE[w, Bandipora district, Bandipora]. The crash at around 7:43p.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC+05:30, local time] was during night training over TEMPLATE[w, Ganderbal]. TEMPLATE[w, Search and rescue] personnel reached the wreckage in the Laman/TEMPLATE[w, Safapora] forest at around 9:00p.m.","The army, police, and fire service all attended. Night flights have been a routine fixture in the area, according to locals. \"There was a huge noise which was followed by smoke and flames,\" according to witnesses. Rescuers were due to check for further victims.","Manufactured by TEMPLATE[w, Hindustan Aeronautics, PSU Hindustan Aeronautics] in India, more than 140 Dhruvs are in service nationally. They have suffered a string of setbacks, with four previous crashes across the country since 2011 killing a total of fourteen. The army says their weight is too high and their engines too underpowered for some roles. Ecuador has seven Dhruvs which are on reduced duties following accidents.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:India","description":"Category:India"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Jammu_and_Kashmir","description":"Category:Jammu and Kashmir"},{"id":"Category:Fires","description":"Category:Fires"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 11, 2015"]},{"name":"India","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:ILA-boy","ILA-boy]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["HAL Dhruv","Dhruv"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bandipora district","Bandipora"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+05:30","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ganderbal"]},{"name":"w","description":["Search and rescue"]},{"name":"w","description":["Safapora"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hindustan Aeronautics","PSU Hindustan Aeronautics"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/army-chopper-crash-laman-forests-bandipora-district-jammu-and-kashmir-police/1/418391.html","title\u003dPilot and co-pilot killed in Army helicopter crash in Kashmir","author\u003d","pub\u003dIndia Today","date\u003dFebruary 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Two-officers-killed-in-Army-helicopter-crash-in-JK/articleshow/46203714.cms","title\u003dTwo officers killed in Army helicopter crash in J\u0026K","author\u003dRajat Pandit ((TEMPLATE))","pub\u003dThe Times of India","date\u003dFebruary 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Dominican murder draws light to anti-Haitian sentiment","wikiTitle":"Dominican_murder_draws_light_to_anti-Haitian_sentiment","wid":1922425,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-02-26T19:05:37Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-13166-haiti-social-haitian-assassinated-found-dead-hanged-on-a-tree-in-dr.html, title\u003dHaiti - Social : Haitian assassinated, found dead hanged on a tree in DR, author\u003dSL, pub\u003dHaiti Libre, date\u003dFebruary 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/feb/12/dominican-republic-lynching-haiti-fears-human-rights, title\u003dDominican Republic lynching raises fears of humanitarian crisis, author\u003dSibylla Brodzinsky, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dFebruary 12, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Haiti","description":"Haiti"},{"id":"Dominican_Republic","description":"Dominican Republic"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[Dominican_Republic] TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, They shouldn\u0027t have to apply for residency. They are Dominicans., 4\u003d[[Human rights]] advocate Santiago Canton] Yesterday\u0027s  discovery of a bound man, believed to be of Haitian ancestry, hanged from a tree in TEMPLATE[w, Santiago, Dominican Republic, Santiago], Dominican Republic has drawn attention to anti-Hatian sentiments in the nation.","The Dominican Republic and Haiti between them make up the island of TEMPLATE[w, Hispaniola] and Dominicans have grown concerned by Haitian immigration in recent years. Police say they believe the man, known to his friends as Tulile, was murdered during a robbery. Police officers anonymously told reporters a winning lottery ticket may have been the motive.","Aged around 23, Tulile made his living shining shoes and taking commissions from money lending in the area he was murdered. Bound hand and foot, his body was found at dawn in Ercilia PepÃ­n park, Sabana Larga street. The scene is close to the University Hospital Jose Maria Cabral y BÃ¡e, around which Tulile worked.","This week saw the public burning of Haiti\u0027s flag in Santiago by local residents, saying it symbolised their rejection of Haitian immigration. The issue is a hot topic, with a court ruling two years ago retrospectively stripping Dominicans born to unregistered Haitian parents from 1930 onwards of their citizenship. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[w:de:Benutzer:Greifen, \"Greifen\"]]] Only 7,000 of an estimated 200,000 eligible residents have signed up for residency cards, a scheme instigated by the government in the face of international pressure. The deadline to apply for the permits, which allow citizenship after two years, has passed.","\"They shouldn\u0027t have to apply for residency,\" said Santiago Canton of the TEMPLATE[w, Robert F Kennedy Center for Human Rights] in a TEMPLATE[w, The Guardian, Guardian] interview. \"They are Dominicans.\" Canton said the murder should be viewed \"in the context of constant discrimination and violence against Haitians\". TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Dominican_Republic","description":"Category:Dominican Republic"},{"id":"Category:Haiti","description":"Category:Haiti"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Dominican_Republic","description":[]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["They shouldn\u0027t have to apply for residency. They are Dominicans.","4\u003d[[Human rights]] advocate Santiago Canton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Santiago, Dominican Republic","Santiago"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hispaniola"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[w:de:Benutzer:Greifen","\"Greifen\"]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Robert F Kennedy Center for Human Rights"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Guardian","Guardian"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.haitilibre.com/en/news-13166-haiti-social-haitian-assassinated-found-dead-hanged-on-a-tree-in-dr.html","title\u003dHaiti - Social : Haitian assassinated, found dead hanged on a tree in DR","author\u003dSL","pub\u003dHaiti Libre","date\u003dFebruary 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/feb/12/dominican-republic-lynching-haiti-fears-human-rights","title\u003dDominican Republic lynching raises fears of humanitarian crisis","author\u003dSibylla Brodzinsky","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dFebruary 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Guardian, Guardian]"]}
{"title":"University of Utah study finds suicide may be linked to air pollution","wikiTitle":"University_of_Utah_study_finds_suicide_may_be_linked_to_air_pollution","wid":1925900,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-03T00:16:49Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://psychcentral.com/news/2015/02/14/polluted-air-tied-to-hike-in-suicide-risk/81230.html, title\u003dPolluted Air Tied to Hike in Suicide Risk, author\u003dTraci Pedersen, pub\u003dPsych Central, date\u003dFebruary 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/289436.php, title\u003dAir pollution linked to increased risk of suicide, author\u003dHonor Whiteman, pub\u003dMedical News Today, date\u003dFebruary 13, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[Source, url\u003dhttp://aje.oxfordjournals.org/content/early/2015/02/10/aje.kwu341.abstract?sid\u003dba2fdeb3-d7f8-475a-b05c-4b89770c91ee, title\u003dAcute Air Pollution Exposure and Risk of Suicide Completion, author\u003dAmanda V. Bakian, Rebekah S. Huber, Hilary Coon, Douglas Gray, Phillip Wilson, William M. McMahon, and Perry F. Renshaw, pub\u003dAmerican Journal of Epidemiology, date\u003dFebruary 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Utah","description":"Utah"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[science_and_technology] A TEMPLATE[w, University of Utah, University of] Utah study published on Tuesday in TEMPLATE[w, American Journal of Epidemiology, The American Journal of Epidemiology] suggests TEMPLATE[w, air pollution] may increase TEMPLATE[w, suicide] rates. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:Greenhorn1, \"Greenhorn1\"]]] The team analysed suicide records for over 1,500 people from TEMPLATE[w, Salt Lake County], Utah from 2000 through 2010. Comparing to air pollution exposure in the three days prior to death the scientists noticed an increase of 20% for deaths amongst those exposed to high TEMPLATE[w, nitrogen dioxide].","High exposure to fine particulates in the three days prior to death led to a 5% increase. For men, the rates when exposed to nitrogen dioxide were 25% higher than average. Middle-aged men were particularly affected.","The scientists believe air pollution combines with other factors to increase suicides, rather than triggering them itself. Doctor Amanda Bakian, one of the researchers, said \"As suicide risk was found to differ by age and gender, this suggests that vulnerability to suicide following air pollution exposure is not uniform across Salt Lake County residents and that some Salt Lake County residents are more vulnerable than others.\"","Bakian said research to identify what made individuals susceptible to increased suicide risk after air pollution exposure is planned.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Utah","description":"Category:Utah"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Mental_health","description":"Category:Mental health"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Environment","description":"Category:Environment"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 14, 2015"]},{"name":"science_and_technology","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["University of Utah","University of"]},{"name":"w","description":["American Journal of Epidemiology","The American Journal of Epidemiology"]},{"name":"w","description":["air pollution"]},{"name":"w","description":["suicide"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:Greenhorn1","\"Greenhorn1\"]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Salt Lake County"]},{"name":"w","description":["nitrogen dioxide"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://psychcentral.com/news/2015/02/14/polluted-air-tied-to-hike-in-suicide-risk/81230.html","title\u003dPolluted Air Tied to Hike in Suicide Risk","author\u003dTraci Pedersen","pub\u003dPsych Central","date\u003dFebruary 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.medicalnewstoday.com/articles/289436.php","title\u003dAir pollution linked to increased risk of suicide","author\u003dHonor Whiteman","pub\u003dMedical News Today","date\u003dFebruary 13, 2015"]},{"name":"Source","description":["url\u003dhttp://aje.oxfordjournals.org/content/early/2015/02/10/aje.kwu341.abstract?sid\u003dba2fdeb3-d7f8-475a-b05c-4b89770c91ee","title\u003dAcute Air Pollution Exposure and Risk of Suicide Completion","author\u003dAmanda V. Bakian, Rebekah S. Huber, Hilary Coon, Douglas Gray, Phillip Wilson, William M. McMahon, and Perry F. Renshaw","pub\u003dAmerican Journal of Epidemiology","date\u003dFebruary 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, American Journal of Epidemiology, The American Journal of Epidemiology]"]}
{"title":"Police shoot dead suspect in Copenhagen attacks","wikiTitle":"Police_shoot_dead_suspect_in_Copenhagen_attacks","wid":1927456,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-04T03:15:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-02-15/danish-police-kill-man-in-copenhagen-close-to-earlier-attacks/6107034, title\u003dCopenhagen shootings: Police kill man close to scene of deadly synagogue and cafe attacks, author\u003d(TEMPLATE)/(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dABC Online, date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/copenhagen-shootings-police-shoot-dead-man-they-believe-was-responsible-for-two-deadly-attacks-on-a-cafe-and-synagogue-10046859.html, title\u003dCopenhagen shootings: Police shoot dead suspect after two deadly attacks on a cafe and synagogue, author\u003dLoulla-Mae Eleftheriou-Smith, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/reports-shots-fired-at-copenhagen-cafe-free-speech-event/2015/02/14/e34f4d5c-b460-11e4-bf39-5560f3918d4b_story.html, title\u003dGunman kills 1 in attack on free speech event in Denmark, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dFebruary 14, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Denmark","description":"Denmark"},{"id":"Charlie_Hebdo","description":"Charlie Hebdo"},{"id":"Paris","description":"Paris"},{"id":"Associated_Press","description":"Associated Press"},{"id":"FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"FranÃ§ois Hollande"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"},{"id":"Nick_Clegg","description":"Nick Clegg"},{"id":"Tony_Abbott","description":"Tony Abbott"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 15, 2015] TEMPLATE[Denmark] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, [[Commons:User:Kim Bach, Kim Bach]]] Police in Denmark have shot dead a man they believe was responsible for two gun attacks that killed two people in TEMPLATE[w, Copenhagen] yesterday. Police had kept a property in the TEMPLATE[w, NÃ¸rrebro] district of the city under surveillance. When the man returned to the property, they confronted him and shot him in the ensuing fire fight.","Jorgen Skov, a police investigator, said \"nothing at this point suggests there were other perpetrators\" than the man shot today. Yesterday, he was allegedly involved in two shooting incidents in the city.","The first shooting took place in a cafÃ© at the Krudttoenden cultural center which was hosting a discussion about blasphemy and free speech, relating to the attacks on the Charlie Hebdo magazine in Paris. Swedish artist TEMPLATE[w, Lars Vilks], who organised the meeting, was subjected to death threats following publication of a number of drawings of the Prophet Muhammad. Vilks\u0027 website says the event was timed to coincide with the fatwa placed on the British novelist TEMPLATE[w, Salman Rushdie]. The event also hosted Inna Shevchenko, an activist with the feminist protest group TEMPLATE[w, FEMEN].","TEMPLATE[w, FranÃ§ois Zimeray], France\u0027s ambassador to Denmark, attended the event.  He told reporters: \"They shot from the outside [and] had the same intention as Charlie Hebdo, only they didn\u0027t manage to get in[...] Intuitively I would say there were at least 50 gunshots, and the police here are saying 200. Bullets went through the doors and everyone threw themselves to the floor.\"","The second attack yesterday took place outside a synagogue in the TEMPLATE[w, Krystalgade] area of Copenhagen. The attacker shot and killed, according to the local Jewish community, Dan Uzan, a 37-year-old Jewish man who was volunteering as a security guard outside the synagogue while a TEMPLATE[w, bat mitzvah] service was held inside. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:Kim Bach, Kim Bach]]] Following the attacks, police released a description and photo of the suspect: he was depicted wearing a black puffer jacket, carrying a black bag, wearing a maroon balaclava, aged between 25 and 30 with a black automatic weapon. The chief police inspector Torben Molgaard Jensen told reporters: \"We assume that it\u0027s the same culprit behind both incidents.\"","TEMPLATE[w, Helle Thorning-Schmidt], the Danish Prime Minister, said yesterday: \"We feel certain now that it\u0027s a politically motivated attack, and thereby it is a terrorist attack.\"","Lars Vilks in a statement to Associated Press said he believed the first attack was directed at him: \"What other motive could there be? It\u0027s possible it was inspired by Charlie Hebdo\".","World leaders have condemned the shooting. French President FranÃ§ois Hollande described the attacks as \"deplorable\" and promised the Danish \"full solidarity of France in this trial\". British Prime Minister David Cameron tweeted: \"I condemn the shootings in Copenhagen. Free speech must always be protected.\" British Deputy Prime Minister Nick Clegg said: \"Sickened by shooting at free speech event in Copenhagen. My thoughts are with the people of the city and country.\"","Australian Prime Minister Tony Abbott said the Australian government \"condemns the shooting at a free speech event in Copenhagen overnight\" and \"[t]he thoughts of all Australians are with the people of Denmark and, in particular, the family of the victim who lost his life and the police officers injured in this brutal act of terror. As with the Charlie Hebdo atrocity in Paris, the Copenhagen attack is an affront to one of our most fundamental values \u0026mdash; freedom of speech. We stand with the people and government of Denmark in confronting this cynical attempt to undermine that fundamental right.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, 2015 Copenhagen shootings, commons, Category:2015 Copenhagen attacks]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Free_speech","description":"Category:Free speech"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Paris","description":"Category:Paris"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Charlie_Hebdo","description":"Category:Charlie Hebdo"},{"id":"Category:Jyllands-Posten","description":"Category:Jyllands-Posten"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Nick_Clegg","description":"Category:Nick Clegg"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Abbott","description":"Category:Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Category:FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"Category:FranÃ§ois Hollande"},{"id":"Category:Depictions_of_Muhammed","description":"Category:Depictions of Muhammed"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Denmark","description":"Category:Denmark"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Denmark","description":[]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:Kim Bach","Kim Bach]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Copenhagen"]},{"name":"w","description":["NÃ¸rrebro"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lars Vilks"]},{"name":"w","description":["Salman Rushdie"]},{"name":"w","description":["FEMEN"]},{"name":"w","description":["FranÃ§ois Zimeray"]},{"name":"w","description":["Krystalgade"]},{"name":"w","description":["bat mitzvah"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:Kim Bach","Kim Bach]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Helle Thorning-Schmidt"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","2015 Copenhagen shootings","commons","Category:2015 Copenhagen attacks"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-02-15/danish-police-kill-man-in-copenhagen-close-to-earlier-attacks/6107034","title\u003dCopenhagen shootings: Police kill man close to scene of deadly synagogue and cafe attacks","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)/(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dABC Online","date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/copenhagen-shootings-police-shoot-dead-man-they-believe-was-responsible-for-two-deadly-attacks-on-a-cafe-and-synagogue-10046859.html","title\u003dCopenhagen shootings: Police shoot dead suspect after two deadly attacks on a cafe and synagogue","author\u003dLoulla-Mae Eleftheriou-Smith","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/world/europe/reports-shots-fired-at-copenhagen-cafe-free-speech-event/2015/02/14/e34f4d5c-b460-11e4-bf39-5560f3918d4b_story.html","title\u003dGunman kills 1 in attack on free speech event in Denmark","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dFebruary 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Charlie Hebdo","fatwa"]}
{"title":"Netanyahu calls for European Jews to move to Israel","wikiTitle":"Netanyahu_calls_for_European_Jews_to_move_to_Israel","wid":1927841,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-04T16:30:26Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dPolice shoot dead suspect in Copenhagen attacks, date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4626738,00.html, title\u003dNetanyahu calls for \u0027massive immigration\u0027 of European Jews to Israel, author\u003dMoran Azulay, Attila Somfalvi, pub\u003dYNetNews, date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/israel/11414029/Danish-rabbi-criticises-Benjamin-Netanyahus-Jewish-emigration-call.html, title\u003dDanish rabbi criticises Benjamin Netanyahu\u0027s Jewish emigration call, author\u003dRobert Tait, pub\u003dThe Telegraph, pubtarget\u003dTelegraph Media Group, date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/copenhagen-shootings-benjamin-netanyahu-calls-for-massive-immigration-of-european-jews-to-israel-in-wake-of-attack-10047271.html, title\u003dCopenhagen shootings: Benjamin Netanyahu calls for \u0027massive immigration\u0027 of European Jews to Israel in wake of attack, author\u003dJamie Campbell, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Benjamin_Netanyahu","description":"Benjamin Netanyahu"},{"id":"Judaism","description":"Jews"},{"id":"Israel","description":"Israel"},{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"Belgium","description":"Belgium"},{"id":"Ukraine","description":"Ukraine"},{"id":"Denmark","description":"Denmark"},{"id":"Charlie_Hebdo","description":"Charlie Hebdo"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 15, 2015] TEMPLATE[Israel] TEMPLATE[Image, US State Department] Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu has today called for European Jews to emigrate to Israel following the attack on a synagogue in TEMPLATE[w, Copenhagen] yesterday. The Israeli government is to discuss a plan to allocate TEMPLATE[w, United States dollar, $]46 million (TEMPLATE[w, euro, \u0026euro;]40 million) of funds to aid immigration by Jews in France, Belgium and Ukraine.","Meeting with the Israeli Cabinet, Netanyahu said: \"Jews have been murdered again on European soil only because they were Jews and this wave of terrorist attacks â including murderous anti-Semitic attacks â is expected to continue[...] Jews deserve protection in every country but we say to Jews: Israel is your home. We are preparing and calling for the absorption of mass immigration from Europe. I would like to tell all European Jews and all Jews wherever they are: \u0027Israel is the home of every Jew.\u0027 [...] Israel is waiting for you with open arms.\"","The Israeli economy minister TEMPLATE[w, Naftali Bennett] backed up Netanyahu\u0027s statement: \"Israel is always waiting for them. This will never change. Jews can and should have the right to live anywhere, but if there are Jews who are concerned about their future, we are certainly waiting for them.\"","Israeli foreign minister TEMPLATE[w, Avigdor Lieberman] stated the Danish attacks \"prove what we have said over the years â that Israel and the Jews are affected by this terrorism before anyone else because they are on the frontline in the war terror is waging against the West and the entire free world.\" He also said the international community needed \"to ask for more than declarations and demonstrations against this terrorism, but also shake off the rules of political correctness and fight a real all-out war against Islamic terror and its roots.\"","Denmark\u0027s chief rabbi Jair Melchior said Netanyahu\u0027s comments \"disappointed\" him, and argued: \"Terror is not a reason to move to Israel. [...] People from Denmark move to Israel because they love Israel, because of Zionism. If the way we deal with terror is to run somewhere else, we should all run to a deserted island.\"","Netanyahu offered a similar statement following the attacks in Paris last month against the offices of Charlie Hebdo and a kosher supermarket.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Israel","description":"Category:Israel"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Belgium","description":"Category:Belgium"},{"id":"Category:Ukraine","description":"Category:Ukraine"},{"id":"Category:Denmark","description":"Category:Denmark"},{"id":"Category:Judaism","description":"Category:Judaism"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Benjamin_Netanyahu","description":"Category:Benjamin Netanyahu"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Israel","description":[]},{"name":"Image","description":["US State Department"]},{"name":"w","description":["Copenhagen"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States dollar","$"]},{"name":"w","description":["euro","\u0026euro;"]},{"name":"w","description":["Naftali Bennett"]},{"name":"w","description":["Avigdor Lieberman"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dPolice shoot dead suspect in Copenhagen attacks","date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ynetnews.com/articles/0,7340,L-4626738,00.html","title\u003dNetanyahu calls for \u0027massive immigration\u0027 of European Jews to Israel","author\u003dMoran Azulay, Attila Somfalvi","pub\u003dYNetNews","date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/middleeast/israel/11414029/Danish-rabbi-criticises-Benjamin-Netanyahus-Jewish-emigration-call.html","title\u003dDanish rabbi criticises Benjamin Netanyahu\u0027s Jewish emigration call","author\u003dRobert Tait","pub\u003dThe Telegraph","pubtarget\u003dTelegraph Media Group","date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/copenhagen-shootings-benjamin-netanyahu-calls-for-massive-immigration-of-european-jews-to-israel-in-wake-of-attack-10047271.html","title\u003dCopenhagen shootings: Benjamin Netanyahu calls for \u0027massive immigration\u0027 of European Jews to Israel in wake of attack","author\u003dJamie Campbell","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dFebruary 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","pubtarget","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Pakistan releases 173 Indian prisoners at Wagah border","wikiTitle":"Pakistan_releases_173_Indian_prisoners_at_Wagah_border","wid":1930076,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-19T20:52:23Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailytimes.com.pk/national/17-Feb-2015/173-indian-inmates-released-by-pakistan, title\u003d173 Indian inmates released by Pakistan, author\u003d, pub\u003dDaily Times (Pakistan), date\u003dFebruary 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-pakistan-hands-over-173-prisoners-to-india-2061497, title\u003dPakistan hands over 173 prisoners to India, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dDaily News and Analysis, date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thehindu.com/news/international/south-asia/pakistan-releases-172-indian-fishermen/article6898959.ece, title\u003dPakistan releases 172 Indian fishermen, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Hindu, date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Pakistan-releases-172-Indian-fishermen/articleshow/46253896.cms, title\u003dPakistan releases 172 Indian fishermen, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Times of India, date\u003dFeb 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/asia/2014/11/pakistan-detains-dozens-indian-fishermen-20141121152026423248.html, title\u003dPakistan detains dozens of Indian fishermen, author\u003d, pub\u003dAl Jazeera, date\u003dNovember 21, 2014]"]],"links":[{"id":"Pakistan","description":"Pakistan"},{"id":"India","description":"India"},{"id":"Karachi","description":"Karachi"},{"id":"Arabian_Sea","description":"Arabian Sea"},{"id":"Narendra_Modi","description":"Narendra Modi"},{"id":"Nawaz_Sharif","description":"Nawaz Sharif"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister Links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[India] Pakistan released 173 inmates to Indian authorities at the Wagah border on Monday, out of which 172 were fishermen. The Pakistani Government ordered the fishermen released from two Karachi jails on Sunday. Alleged violation of the Arabian Sea maritime boundary of Karachi]] led the fishermen to imprisonment in the Malir and Landhi District Jail. TEMPLATE[image, Mxshanii] Earlier during the week Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi provided his warm greeting to Pakistan Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif and leaders of other nations in the TEMPLATE[w, South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation] who are taking part in the 2015 TEMPLATE[w, Cricket World Cup]. The Indian fishermen reportedly had completed the terms of their imprisonment sentences last year; Pakistan\u0027s Foreign Ministry released a statement on Monday expressing hope for release of Pakistanis whose sentences in India are complete.","India and Pakistan often imprison each other\u0027s fisherman for violating the maritime border. There are still about 350 prisoners in Pakistan\u0027s jail as of now. Pakistan arrested another 38 fishermen last month.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, IndiaâPakistan maritime trespassing]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:India","description":"Category:India"},{"id":"Category:Pakistan","description":"Category:Pakistan"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Karachi","description":"Category:Karachi"},{"id":"Category:Arabian_Sea","description":"Category:Arabian Sea"},{"id":"Category:Narendra_Modi","description":"Category:Narendra Modi"},{"id":"Category:Nawaz_Sharif","description":"Category:Nawaz Sharif"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 18, 2015"]},{"name":"India","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Mxshanii"]},{"name":"w","description":["South Asian Association for Regional Cooperation"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cricket World Cup"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","IndiaâPakistan maritime trespassing"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailytimes.com.pk/national/17-Feb-2015/173-indian-inmates-released-by-pakistan","title\u003d173 Indian inmates released by Pakistan","author\u003d","pub\u003dDaily Times (Pakistan)","date\u003dFebruary 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dnaindia.com/india/report-pakistan-hands-over-173-prisoners-to-india-2061497","title\u003dPakistan hands over 173 prisoners to India","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dDaily News and Analysis","date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thehindu.com/news/international/south-asia/pakistan-releases-172-indian-fishermen/article6898959.ece","title\u003dPakistan releases 172 Indian fishermen","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Hindu","date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Pakistan-releases-172-Indian-fishermen/articleshow/46253896.cms","title\u003dPakistan releases 172 Indian fishermen","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Times of India","date\u003dFeb 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/asia/2014/11/pakistan-detains-dozens-indian-fishermen-20141121152026423248.html","title\u003dPakistan detains dozens of Indian fishermen","author\u003d","pub\u003dAl Jazeera","date\u003dNovember 21, 2014"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Welsh historian John Davies dies aged 76","wikiTitle":"Welsh_historian_John_Davies_dies_aged_76","wid":1930287,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-30T03:23:17Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-31484879, title\u003dHistorian and BBC commentator John Davies dies aged 76, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/influential-historian-dr-john-davies-8657404, title\u003dInfluential historian Dr John Davies dies aged 76, author\u003dRobin Turner, pub\u003dWestern Mail (Wales), date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Wales","description":"Welsh"},{"id":"BBC","description":"British Broadcasting Corporation"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 16, 2015] TEMPLATE[Wales] TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:FÃ¦, FÃ¦]]] TEMPLATE[w, John Davies (historian), John Davies], highly regarded Welsh historian, has died at the age of 76. Davies worked closely with the British Broadcasting Corporation (BBC) during his career, often as a commentator on TEMPLATE[w, BBC Wales]. As well as his work as a broadcaster he was also an author and a teacher at several universities across Wales.","As an author he won the TEMPLATE[w, Glyndwr Award], an award that recognizes an outstanding contribution to the arts in Wales, and the TEMPLATE[w, Wales Book of the Year] in 2010. He won the later award for his work Cymru: Y 100 Lle I\u0027w Gweld Cyn Marw (Wales: 100 Places to See Before Dying). He also wrote A History of Wales, a book regarded, according to the BBC, by many as definitive on Welsh history.","Tributes have been paid to Davies from many people including politicians and broadcasters. Welsh TEMPLATE[w, First Minister of Wales, First Minister] TEMPLATE[w, Carwyn Jones] said \"He\u0027ll be remembered as one of our great historians [...] of Wales\u0027 past which he gladly and passionately shared through his teaching, writing and broadcasting.\"","Current BBC presenter TEMPLATE[w, Huw Edwards (journalist), Huw Edwards] said \"He had an extraordinary way of sharing his message in an engaging and lively way \u0026mdash; in both languages \u0026mdash; and that was incontrovertibly proved in his excellent and comprehensive work A History of Wales[...] He was a colourful character and great company.\" Another BBC tribute came from TEMPLATE[w, Rhodri Talfan Davies], the director of BBC Cymru Wales. He said \"He didn\u0027t just bring the story of Wales and its people to life \u0026mdash; he did so in technicolor.\"","Davies, who lived in TEMPLATE[w, Grangetown, Cardiff, Grangetown], TEMPLATE[w, Cardiff], would go on to share his knowledge of Welsh history by teaching at both TEMPLATE[w, Swansea University, Swansea] and TEMPLATE[w, Aberystwyth university, Aberystwyth] universities. He also held the position of warden at Aberystwyth, monitoring a student residence hall.","He is survived by his wife Janet and four children.  TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Wales","description":"Category:Wales"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:History","description":"Category:History"},{"id":"Category:Literature","description":"Category:Literature"},{"id":"Category:BBC","description":"Category:BBC"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Aberystwyth_University","description":"Category:Aberystwyth University"},{"id":"Category:Books","description":"Category:Books"},{"id":"Category:Cardiff,_Wales","description":"Category:Cardiff, Wales"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Wales","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:FÃ¦","FÃ¦]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["John Davies (historian)","John Davies"]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC Wales"]},{"name":"w","description":["Glyndwr Award"]},{"name":"w","description":["Wales Book of the Year"]},{"name":"w","description":["First Minister of Wales","First Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["Carwyn Jones"]},{"name":"w","description":["Huw Edwards (journalist)","Huw Edwards"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rhodri Talfan Davies"]},{"name":"w","description":["Grangetown, Cardiff","Grangetown"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cardiff"]},{"name":"w","description":["Swansea University","Swansea"]},{"name":"w","description":["Aberystwyth university","Aberystwyth"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-wales-31484879","title\u003dHistorian and BBC commentator John Davies dies aged 76","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/influential-historian-dr-john-davies-8657404","title\u003dInfluential historian Dr John Davies dies aged 76","author\u003dRobin Turner","pub\u003dWestern Mail (Wales)","date\u003dFebruary 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Cymru: Y 100 Lle I\u0027w Gweld Cyn Marw","A History of Wales"]}
{"title":"Harris Wittels, Parks and Recreation executive producer, found dead aged 30","wikiTitle":"Harris_Wittels,_Parks_and_Recreation_executive_producer,_found_dead_aged_30","wid":1938726,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-08T22:07:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPaul Schneider leaving NBC\u0027s Parks and Recreation; Rob Lowe, Adam Scott to appear in series, date\u003dMarch 15, 2010]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/02/20/harris-wittels-parks-and-recreation-co-executive-producer-dies-at-30/, title\u003dHarris Wittels, \u0027Parks and Recreation\u0027 co-executive producer, dies at 30, author\u003d, pub\u003dFox News, date\u003dFebruary 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31549699, title\u003dParks and Recreation producer found dead at LA home, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dFebruary 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/culturenews/11424455/Harris-Wittels-tributes-made-to-the-Parks-and-Recreation-writer.html, title\u003dHarris Wittels: tributes made to the Parks and Recreation writer, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dFebruary 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.tmz.com/2015/02/19/harris-wittels-dead-parks-and-recreation-producer-dies-drugs-overdose/, title\u003d\u0027Parks and Rec\u0027 Exec Harris Wittels Found Dead; Signs of Overdose, author\u003d, pub\u003dTMZ, date\u003dFebruary 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.avclub.com/article/rip-harris-wittels-comedian-and-parks-and-rec-exec-215531#comment-1865070624, title\u003dR.I.P. Harris Wittels, comedian and \u0027\u0027Parks And Rec\u0027\u0027 executive producer, author\u003dErik Adams, pub\u003dThe A.V. Club, date\u003dFebruary 19, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Los_Angeles","description":"Los Angeles"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[Television] TEMPLATE[w, Harris Wittels], an executive producer on the comedy television series TEMPLATE[w, Parks and Recreation], has been found dead. The 30-year-old was found unresponsive at his home in Los Angeles by his assistant on Thursday. He was pronounced dead at the scene. Police have announced they are investigating the possibility of a drug overdose.","Wittels had a history of drug abuse and spoke openly about his addiction and treatment in drug rehabilitation centers. As well as working as a producer he was also a writer, musician, and stand-up comedian. He performed a stand-up set in TEMPLATE[w, Hollywood] the night before his death.","Wittels, from TEMPLATE[w, Texas], started work on Parks and Recreation as a writer before being promoted to producer and eventually executive producer. Parks and Recreation is in its seventh and final season. The last episode is due to be broadcast on TEMPLATE[w, NBC] next week.","His other working credits include work on TEMPLATE[w, The Sarah Silverman Show] and TEMPLATE[w, Eastbound and Down]. He authored a book, Humblebrag: The Art of False Modesty, which came from a phrase he coined on Twitter. #humblebrag was used as a term to describe the art of false modesty.","Tributes have come from across the world of television and comedy. TEMPLATE[w, Sarah Silverman] called Wittels her \"baby\". She said on Twitter \"You should know that Harris was brilliant beyond compare. That his imagination was without limit. That he loved comedy more than anything\".","Parks and Recreation actress TEMPLATE[w, Amy Poehler] said at a TEMPLATE[w, Variety (magazine), Variety] event where she was being honored \"I don\u0027t really feel like telling any jokes. Today, I lost a friend. I lost a dear, young friend in my life who was struggling with addiction.\"","Fans of Wittels also paid tribute to him. Posting on culture website TEMPLATE[w, The AV Club], one fan wrote \"I don\u0027t mean to belittle what those who knew him are going through at all, I know how I feel is nothing compared to what they\u0027re dealing with, but it does feel like I lost a friend.\" Another posted \"Been sitting here crying since I found out an hour ago. Just unbelievably awful. Said this elsewhere but I genuinely feel like I lost a friend, don\u0027t care how lame that sounds. RIP Harris.\"","An official cause of death will not be known until results are released by the Los Angeles County coronerâs office.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Comedy","description":"Category:Comedy"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Twitter","description":"Category:Twitter"},{"id":"Category:California","description":"Category:California"},{"id":"Category:Los_Angeles,_California","description":"Category:Los Angeles, California"},{"id":"Category:NBC","description":"Category:NBC"},{"id":"Category:Drugs","description":"Category:Drugs"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Television","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Harris Wittels"]},{"name":"w","description":["Parks and Recreation"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hollywood"]},{"name":"w","description":["Texas"]},{"name":"w","description":["NBC"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Sarah Silverman Show"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eastbound and Down"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sarah Silverman"]},{"name":"w","description":["Amy Poehler"]},{"name":"w","description":["Variety (magazine)","Variety"]},{"name":"w","description":["The AV Club"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPaul Schneider leaving NBC\u0027s Parks and Recreation; Rob Lowe, Adam Scott to appear in series","date\u003dMarch 15, 2010"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.foxnews.com/entertainment/2015/02/20/harris-wittels-parks-and-recreation-co-executive-producer-dies-at-30/","title\u003dHarris Wittels, \u0027Parks and Recreation\u0027 co-executive producer, dies at 30","author\u003d","pub\u003dFox News","date\u003dFebruary 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31549699","title\u003dParks and Recreation producer found dead at LA home","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dFebruary 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/culture/culturenews/11424455/Harris-Wittels-tributes-made-to-the-Parks-and-Recreation-writer.html","title\u003dHarris Wittels: tributes made to the Parks and Recreation writer","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dFebruary 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.tmz.com/2015/02/19/harris-wittels-dead-parks-and-recreation-producer-dies-drugs-overdose/","title\u003d\u0027Parks and Rec\u0027 Exec Harris Wittels Found Dead; Signs of Overdose","author\u003d","pub\u003dTMZ","date\u003dFebruary 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.avclub.com/article/rip-harris-wittels-comedian-and-parks-and-rec-exec-215531#comment-1865070624","title\u003dR.I.P. Harris Wittels, comedian and \u0027\u0027Parks And Rec\u0027\u0027 executive producer","author\u003dErik Adams","pub\u003dThe A.V. Club","date\u003dFebruary 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Parks and Recreation]","Parks and Recreation","Parks and Recreation","TEMPLATE[w, The Sarah Silverman Show]","TEMPLATE[w, Eastbound and Down]","Humblebrag: The Art of False Modesty"]}
{"title":"Southwest Airlines grounds 128 uninspected planes","wikiTitle":"Southwest_Airlines_grounds_128_uninspected_planes","wid":1953770,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-09T13:48:25Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/southwest-airlines-grounds-128-planes-due-to-missed-inspections/, title\u003dSouthwest Airlines grounds 128 planes due to missed inspections, author\u003dCBS/(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dCBS News, date\u003dFebruary 25, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/business-31629480, title\u003dSouthwest Airlines forced to ground uninspected planes, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dFebruary 25, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Southwest_Airlines","description":"Southwest Airlines"},{"id":"Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Federal Aviation Administration"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, February 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation] The US carrier Southwest Airlines, the world\u0027s largest low-cost carrier, announced grounding 128 planes on Tuesday because the planes had not be adequately inspected.","Company spokesperson Brandy King explained backup hydraulic systems of 128 of the company\u0027s Boeing 737-700s should have been inspected sooner. The systems overdue for inspection back up the main rudder control systems.","King said the the incident is inadvertent and emphasised the airline\u0027s commitment to safety. The airline decided to ground the planes involved in the missed inspections and notified the authorities.","As of last year, Southwest Airlines\u0027 fleet had around 665 TEMPLATE[w, Boeing 737]s. The uninspected planes incident involves about twenty percent of its fleet, and caused the airline to cancel about 80 flights on Tuesday, with possibly another 19 cancellations yesterday.","Following the airline\u0027s actions, the Federal Aviation Administration ruled grounding of the planes is not mandatory provided inspections are completed within five days.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Flight control surfaces]","TEMPLATE[translated_Wikinews, wiki\u003dfr, title\u003dSouthwest Airlines suspend l\u0027exploitation de 128 appareils pour problÃ¨mes de maintenance, language\u003dFrench]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Economy_and_business","description":"Category:Economy and business"},{"id":"Category:Southwest_Airlines","description":"Category:Southwest Airlines"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Category:Federal Aviation Administration"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["February 26, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Boeing 737"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","Flight control surfaces"]},{"name":"translated_Wikinews","description":["wiki\u003dfr","title\u003dSouthwest Airlines suspend l\u0027exploitation de 128 appareils pour problÃ¨mes de maintenance","language\u003dFrench"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/southwest-airlines-grounds-128-planes-due-to-missed-inspections/","title\u003dSouthwest Airlines grounds 128 planes due to missed inspections","author\u003dCBS/(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dCBS News","date\u003dFebruary 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/business-31629480","title\u003dSouthwest Airlines forced to ground uninspected planes","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dFebruary 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["wiki","title","language","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Footballer Adam Johnson arrested on suspicion of sex with under-age girl","wikiTitle":"Footballer_Adam_Johnson_arrested_on_suspicion_of_sex_with_under-age_girl","wid":1964089,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-10T04:04:38Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11695/9740539/adam-johnson-arrested, title\u003dAdam Johnson bailed, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky Sports, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-31702374, title\u003dAdam Johnson arrested on suspicion of sex with girl, 15, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-2975953/Adam-Johnson-arrested-suspicion-having-sex-15-year-old-girl.html, title\u003dAdam Johnson released on bail after arrest on suspicion of having sex with 15-year-old girl as Sunderland suspend England star, author\u003dCraig Hope, Christian Gysin, and Mario Ledwith, pub\u003dMail Online, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.sunderlandecho.com/news/local/all-news/sunderland-footballer-adam-johnson-arrested-over-sex-allegation-involving-under-age-girl-1-7134547, title\u003dSunderland footballer Adam Johnson arrested over sex allegation involving under-age girl, author\u003dGary Welford, pub\u003dSunderland Echo, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11695/9740557/adam-johnson-biography, title\u003dAdam Johnson biography, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky Sports, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"England","description":"English"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 3, 2015] TEMPLATE[football] TEMPLATE[w, Manchester City F.C., Manchester City]TEMPLATE[image, Roger GorÄczniak] English footballer TEMPLATE[w, Adam Johnson (footballer), Adam Johnson] has been arrested on suspicion of having sex with a girl under the age of 16. Johnson, who currently plays for TEMPLATE[w, Sunderland A.F.C.] , was arrested yesterday morning at his home. TEMPLATE[w, Durham, England, Durham] Police confirmed they had arrested a \"27-year-old man [...] on suspicion of sexual activity with a girl under 16.\"","A neighbour of Johnson\u0027s spoke to TEMPLATE[w, The Sun (United Kingdom), The Sun] newspaper about the arrest. They said \"All the main activity was between 9.15am and 9.35am. Three undercover cars and a scenes of crime van arrived. As far as I know he lives there with his girlfriend\".","He was due to travel with his club to face TEMPLATE[w, Hull City A.F.C., Hull] on Tuesday night in the TEMPLATE[w, English Premier League]. However since the news of his arrest broke Sunderland AFC have released a statement confirming his suspension. The club said \"Sunderland AFC has confirmed Adam Johnson has been suspended from the club, pending the outcome of a police investigation.\"","Johnson has made 105 appearances for Sunderland having previously played for TEMPLATE[w, Middlesbrough F.C., Middlesbrough], TEMPLATE[w, Leeds United F.C., Leeds United], and TEMPLATE[w, Manchester City F.C., Manchester City]. He has represented TEMPLATE[w, England national football team, England] on 12 occasions and scored two goals for the national team. He last played for the England National Team in 2012.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Sex_crimes","description":"Category:Sex crimes"},{"id":"Category:Newcastle_upon_Tyn