er-adam-johnson-arrested-over-sex-allegation-involving-under-age-girl-1-7134547","title\u003dSunderland footballer Adam Johnson arrested over sex allegation involving under-age girl","author\u003dGary Welford","pub\u003dSunderland Echo","date\u003dMarch 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www1.skysports.com/football/news/11695/9740557/adam-johnson-biography","title\u003dAdam Johnson biography","author\u003d","pub\u003dSky Sports","date\u003dMarch 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Sun (United Kingdom), The Sun]"]}
{"title":"Beverly Hall, indicted public school superintendent, dies aged 68","wikiTitle":"Beverly_Hall,_indicted_public_school_superintendent,_dies_aged_68","wid":1966857,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-11T13:23:46Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ajc.com/news/news/breaking-news/hall-dies-criminal-case-and-her-legacy-unresolved/nkMKf/, title\u003dBeverly Hall dies; criminal case â and her legacy â unresolved, author\u003dAlan Judd, pub\u003dThe Atlanta Journal-Constitution, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wsbtv.com/news/news/local/former-aps-superintendent-beverly-hall-dies/nkMJq/, title\u003dFormer APS Superintendent Beverly Hall dies, author\u003d, pub\u003dWSB-TV, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Georgia_(US_state)","description":"Georgia"},{"id":"New_Jersey","description":"New Jersey"},{"id":"Jamaica","description":"Jamaica"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[education] TEMPLATE[w, Beverly Hall, Dr. Beverly Hall], a central figure in an TEMPLATE[w, Atlanta, Georgia, Atlanta], Georgia public schools cheating scandal since 2009, died at the age of 68 on Monday. The cause of death was reported as TEMPLATE[w, breast cancer], a disease she had been suffering from since 2004. At the time of her death Hall was still facing criminal charges relating to the cheating scandal.","No official statement was released by Hall\u0027s family or her legal team regarding the circumstances of her death however her lawyers stated that Hall maintained her innocence \"to her dying breath.\" Should she have been convicted of several offences, including TEMPLATE[w, racketeering], Hall could have been sentenced to up to 45 years imprisonment.","Current TEMPLATE[w, Atlanta Public Schools, Atlanta Public School] Superintendent, Meria Carstarphen commented on Hall\u0027s death: \"We offer our condolences to the family of Dr. Hall. Our thoughts and prayers are with her family and friends during this difficult time.\" Hall became the Atlanta Public School Superintendent in 1999. She previously held the position of Superintendent in TEMPLATE[w, Newark, New Jersey, Newark], New Jersey. During her time as Newark\u0027s Superintendent test scores only increased mildly and the school had financial problems; Newark\u0027s mayor, TEMPLATE[w, Sharpe James], criticised at the time, \"[Hall] is getting out of here before you realize she hasn\u0027t done anything.\"","She gained critical acclaim during her time in Atlanta and was recognized for innovative urban education. In 2009 she was awarded the title of National Superintendent of the Year. At the time of the award, Atlanta schools had seen a large improvement on test scores. Shortly after, TEMPLATE[w, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution] published a report showing problems with test results. The report showed test scores had increased implausibly fast, and alleged the school internally detected problems but didn\u0027t act on the findings.  Evidence thereafter indicated test papers were tampered with. Hall, along with 34 other education officials, was indicted in 2013.","In total twenty-one people pleaded guilty to charges relating to the cheating scandal while several others remain on trial. Hall became too ill to stand trail after the cancer spread to other parts of her body.","Hall was born in Jamaica, and later moved to the United States. She is survived by her husband and a son.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, Atlanta Public Schools cheating scandal]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Education","description":"Category:Education"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Jamaica","description":"Category:Jamaica"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Georgia_(U.S._state)","description":"Category:Georgia (U.S. state)"},{"id":"Category:New_Jersey","description":"Category:New Jersey"},{"id":"Category:Cancer","description":"Category:Cancer"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 4, 2015"]},{"name":"education","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Beverly Hall","Dr. Beverly Hall"]},{"name":"w","description":["Atlanta, Georgia","Atlanta"]},{"name":"w","description":["breast cancer"]},{"name":"w","description":["racketeering"]},{"name":"w","description":["Atlanta Public Schools","Atlanta Public School"]},{"name":"w","description":["Newark, New Jersey","Newark"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sharpe James"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Atlanta Journal-Constitution"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["Atlanta Public Schools cheating scandal"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ajc.com/news/news/breaking-news/hall-dies-criminal-case-and-her-legacy-unresolved/nkMKf/","title\u003dBeverly Hall dies; criminal case â and her legacy â unresolved","author\u003dAlan Judd","pub\u003dThe Atlanta Journal-Constitution","date\u003dMarch 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wsbtv.com/news/news/local/former-aps-superintendent-beverly-hall-dies/nkMJq/","title\u003dFormer APS Superintendent Beverly Hall dies","author\u003d","pub\u003dWSB-TV","date\u003dMarch 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Atlanta Journal-Constitution]"]}
{"title":"Edward Snowden in talks to return to United States","wikiTitle":"Edward_Snowden_in_talks_to_return_to_United_States","wid":1967652,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-11T13:23:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/world/edward-snowden-would-go-back-to-u-s-if-guaranteed-fair-trial-lawyer-1.2980385, title\u003dEdward Snowden would go back to U.S. if guaranteed fair trial: lawyer, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dCanadian Broadcasting Corporation, date\u003dMarch 3 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.pcworld.com/article/2892512/snowden-willing-to-face-trial-in-us-if-its-fair.html, title\u003dSnowden willing to face trial in US, if it\u0027s fair, author\u003dGrant Gross, pub\u003dPC World, date\u003dMarch 3 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/edward-snowden-talks-return-united-states-lawyer-article-1.2135651, title\u003dEdward Snowden in talks to return to United States from Russian exile: lawyer, author\u003dBill Hutchinson, pub\u003dDaily News (New York), date\u003dMarch 3 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/03/us-russia-usa-snowden-idUSKBN0LZ1U020150303, title\u003dFugitive ex-NSA contractor Snowden seeks to come home: lawyer, author\u003d, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dMarch 3 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Edward_Snowden","description":"Edward Snowden"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"Germany","description":"Germany"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] Edward Snowden, a TEMPLATE[w, US] TEMPLATE[w, National Security Agency] (NSA) whistle-blower who has been in exile since 2013, would like to return to the United States providing he is guaranteed a \"fair and impartial trial\", said Anatoly Kucherena, his Russian lawyer, yesterday. TEMPLATE[image_credit, Praxis Films] The TEMPLATE[w, US Attorney General] has promised Snowden he will not be TEMPLATE[w, death penalty, executed] if he is convicted under the TEMPLATE[w, Espionage Act of 1917, Espionage Act], however, Kucherena says, he has not been promised the fair trial he seeks. Kucherena also said the US Attorney General does not have legal power to enforce the promise of no execution. Reportedly, \"fair\", to Snowden\u0027s lawyers, requires he would not be tried under the Espionage Act. Snowden has been on the run since leaking classified information regarding the NSA\u0027s mass electronic surveillance of the US population to the mainstream media.","Upon returning to the US, Snowden would still have to face trial on two counts of theft of government property. If he were found guilty on both counts he would serve an up to 30-year prison sentence.","Spokesman for the TEMPLATE[w, United States Department of Justice, US Justice Department] Marc Raimondi, in remarks to TEMPLATE[w, Reuters], reiterated the position of the US on the case, saying, \"Snowden is not a whistle-blower. He is accused of leaking classified information and there is no question his actions have inflicted serious harms on our national security\".","Kucherena said he is working alongside lawyers from both Germany and the US in order to ensure that a fair trial can be negotiated.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Russia","description":"Category:Russia"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Edward_Snowden","description":"Category:Edward Snowden"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Right_to_a_fair_trial","description":"Category:Right to a fair trial"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 4, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["US"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Security Agency"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Praxis Films"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Attorney General"]},{"name":"w","description":["death penalty","executed"]},{"name":"w","description":["Espionage Act of 1917","Espionage Act"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Department of Justice","US Justice Department"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reuters"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/world/edward-snowden-would-go-back-to-u-s-if-guaranteed-fair-trial-lawyer-1.2980385","title\u003dEdward Snowden would go back to U.S. if guaranteed fair trial: lawyer","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dCanadian Broadcasting Corporation","date\u003dMarch 3 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.pcworld.com/article/2892512/snowden-willing-to-face-trial-in-us-if-its-fair.html","title\u003dSnowden willing to face trial in US, if it\u0027s fair","author\u003dGrant Gross","pub\u003dPC World","date\u003dMarch 3 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nydailynews.com/news/national/edward-snowden-talks-return-united-states-lawyer-article-1.2135651","title\u003dEdward Snowden in talks to return to United States from Russian exile: lawyer","author\u003dBill Hutchinson","pub\u003dDaily News (New York)","date\u003dMarch 3 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/03/us-russia-usa-snowden-idUSKBN0LZ1U020150303","title\u003dFugitive ex-NSA contractor Snowden seeks to come home: lawyer","author\u003d","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dMarch 3 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Explorers find shipwreck thought to be massive WWII battleship Musashi","wikiTitle":"Explorers_find_shipwreck_thought_to_be_massive_WWII_battleship_Musashi","wid":1968436,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-11T13:23:54Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-31724995, title\u003dJapan\u0027s WW2 \u0027Musashi battleship wreck found\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://ajw.asahi.com/article/behind_news/social_affairs/AJ201503040050, title\u003dWreck of battleship Musashi said found off Philippines, author\u003dManabu Sasaki, pub\u003dAsahi Shimbun, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Brunei","description":"Brunei"},{"id":"Microsoft","description":"Microsoft"},{"id":"Japan","description":"Japan"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"World_War_Two","description":"World War Two"},{"id":"Philippines","description":"Filipino"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"remotely_operated_underwater_vehicles","description":"ROV"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[image_credit, Tobei Shiraishi] Billionaire Microsoft co-founder TEMPLATE[w, Paul Allen] yesterday announced his ocean exploration team has found a wreck thought to be the TEMPLATE[w, Japanese battleship Musashi, Musashi], one of the largest warships ever built. The Musashi was a Japanese battleship sunk by US forces during World War Two.","The wreck was discovered yesterday local time under a TEMPLATE[w, kilometre] of water in the TEMPLATE[w, Sibuyan Sea], off the Filipino coast. Together with TEMPLATE[w, Yamato-class battleship, sister ship] TEMPLATE[w, Japanese battleship Yamato, \u0027\u0027Yamato\u0027\u0027] the Musashi fought in the TEMPLATE[w, Battle of Leyte Gulf], one of the war\u0027s biggest sea fights. TEMPLATE[w, Isokaze-class destroyer, Isokaze]TEMPLATE[image_credit, Tobei Shiraishi] Musashi sank on October 24, 1944, during the battle and two years after commissioning. Over 1,000 crew died. Well-armed with 18-inch guns, the 263TEMPLATE[w, metre, m] (862TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), ft]) ship struggled to defend itself against waves of aircraft launched from US carriers. Musashi fired into the water, creating large geysers to knock incoming bombers out of the sky. Eighteen planes were downed.","The battle was won by the US and Australia, defeating Japan. Yamato escaped with damage but was sunk the following year, also by US forces. The two battleships were the TEMPLATE[w, Japanese Imperial Navy]\u0027s centrepieces. Musashi boasted a 22-TEMPLATE[w, mile] reach with its nine main guns, and seven aircraft.","If confirmed, the find completes Allen\u0027s eight-year search for the Musashi. Following seabed mapping the wreck was found using an ROV. One of the world\u0027s richest people, Allen has reportedly invested much of his wealth in marine exploration and began his quest to find the Musashi out of a lifelong interest in the war.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive] TEMPLATE[DISPLAYTITLE:Explorers_find_shipwreck_thought_to_be_massive_WWII_battleship_\u0027\u0027Musashi\u0027\u0027]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:History","description":"Category:History"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:World_War_II","description":"Category:World War II"},{"id":"Category:Microsoft","description":"Category:Microsoft"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Japan","description":"Category:Japan"},{"id":"Category:Philippines","description":"Category:Philippines"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Remotely_operated_underwater_vehicles","description":"Category:Remotely operated underwater vehicles"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 4, 2015"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Tobei Shiraishi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Paul Allen"]},{"name":"w","description":["Japanese battleship Musashi","Musashi"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometre"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sibuyan Sea"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yamato-class battleship","sister ship"]},{"name":"w","description":["Japanese battleship Yamato","\u0027\u0027Yamato\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["Battle of Leyte Gulf"]},{"name":"w","description":["Isokaze-class destroyer","Isokaze"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Tobei Shiraishi"]},{"name":"w","description":["metre","m"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","ft"]},{"name":"w","description":["Japanese Imperial Navy"]},{"name":"w","description":["mile"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-31724995","title\u003dJapan\u0027s WW2 \u0027Musashi battleship wreck found\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://ajw.asahi.com/article/behind_news/social_affairs/AJ201503040050","title\u003dWreck of battleship Musashi said found off Philippines","author\u003dManabu Sasaki","pub\u003dAsahi Shimbun","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]},{"name":"DISPLAYTITLE:Explorers_find_shipwreck_thought_to_be_massive_WWII_battleship_\u0027\u0027Musashi\u0027\u0027","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["","TEMPLATE[w, Japanese battleship Musashi, Musashi]","Musashi","Musashi","","Musashi","Musashi","Yamato","Musashi","Musashi","Musashi"]}
{"title":"Scottish footballer Dave Mackay dies aged 80","wikiTitle":"Scottish_footballer_Dave_Mackay_dies_aged_80","wid":1968775,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-12T17:41:53Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/31704507, title\u003dDave Mackay: Scotland and Tottenham legend dies aged 80, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/02/dave-mackay-scotland-tottenham-hearts, title\u003dDave Mackay of Scotland, Hearts, Tottenham and Derby, dies aged 80, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scottish"},{"id":"England","description":"English"},{"id":"Manchester_United","description":"Manchester United"},{"id":"Northern_Ireland","description":"Northern Ireland"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 5, 2015] TEMPLATE[Scotland] TEMPLATE[image_credit, \"[[w:User:TuborgLight, TuborgLight]]\"] Scottish footballer TEMPLATE[w, Dave Mackay] died in an English hospital on Monday. He was 80.","\"Dave was one of the most influential players of his era[...] a superb player who possessed all the technique, passing ability and talent to be the complete footballer\", said TEMPLATE[w, Tottenham Hotspur], an English team Mackay played for in the late fifties and early sixties.","Mackay\u0027s career took him to England after competitive success at Scottish team TEMPLATE[w, Heart of Midlothian FC, Hearts], where he was captain. With Hearts he won the TEMPLATE[w, Scottish Cup] and twice won the TEMPLATE[w, Scottish League Cup]. He won three TEMPLATE[w, FA Cup]s, one being a \u0027Double\u0027 won in the same year as the English league, with Tottenham Hotspur. He also appeared 22 times playing for the Scottish national side.","In the early seventies Mackay turned his attention to managing, taking the top job at various English and Middle Eastern sides. TEMPLATE[w, Derby County FC, Derby County] won the league under him in 1975. Mackay\u0027s management career continued until 1995. He has held the title Footballer of the Year in both Scotland and England.","Late Manchester United player TEMPLATE[w, George Best] has previously called Mackay the \"hardest man I have ever played against\". A minute\u0027s applause is planned as tribute when Scotland takes on Northern Ireland at home  on March 25.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_national_football_team","description":"Category:Scottish national football team"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 5, 2015"]},{"name":"Scotland","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["\"[[w:User:TuborgLight","TuborgLight]]\""]},{"name":"w","description":["Dave Mackay"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tottenham Hotspur"]},{"name":"w","description":["Heart of Midlothian FC","Hearts"]},{"name":"w","description":["Scottish Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["Scottish League Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["FA Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["Derby County FC","Derby County"]},{"name":"w","description":["George Best"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/31704507","title\u003dDave Mackay: Scotland and Tottenham legend dies aged 80","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/02/dave-mackay-scotland-tottenham-hearts","title\u003dDave Mackay of Scotland, Hearts, Tottenham and Derby, dies aged 80","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Alabama Supreme Court orders judges to stop issuing same-sex marriage licences","wikiTitle":"Alabama_Supreme_Court_orders_judges_to_stop_issuing_same-sex_marriage_licences","wid":1968946,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-11T16:18:01Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/04/in-defiant-ruling-alabama-supreme-court-stops-same-sex-marriage-in-state/, title\u003dIn defiant ruling, Alabama Supreme Court stops same-sex marriage in state, author\u003dFred Barbash, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-31727556, title\u003dAlabama Supreme Court orders halt to same-sex marriage licences, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.al.com/news/index.ssf/2015/03/alabama_supreme_court_orders_h.html#incart_std, title\u003dAlabama Supreme Court orders halt to same-sex marriages, author\u003dKyle Whitmire, Brendad Kirby, Kent Faulk, pub\u003dThe Birmingham News, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"same-sex_marriage","description":"same-sex marriage"},{"id":"United_States_Supreme_Court","description":"United States Supreme Court"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[LGBT] TEMPLATE[image, Chris Pruitt] The TEMPLATE[w, Supreme Court of Alabama] yesterday ordered all judges to halt in issuing same-sex marriage licenses in the state. The ruling goes against an earlier order by the United States Supreme Court, allowing judges to issue same-sex couples a marriage license.","The ruling said \"As it has done for approximately two centuries, Alabama law allows for âmarriageâ between only one man and one woman. Alabama[...] judges have a[...] duty not to issue any marriage license contrary to this law. Nothing in the TEMPLATE[w, United States Constitution] alters or overrides this duty.\"","David Kennedy, a lawyer who represented an Alabama couple who fought an earlier court ruling, said \"I don\u0027t really think that they can do that. I\u0027m not surprised, but I\u0027m somewhat appalled. The Supreme Court of the United States ruled that the stay (on the order striking down the gay marriage ban) would expire on Feb. 9. On Feb. 9, same-sex marriage effectively became legal in Alabama\". He added \"Whenever state law conflicts with federal law, federal law wins\".","The issue of same-sex marriage has been contested over recent months. Alabama Chief Justice TEMPLATE[w, Roy Moore] had told judges not to issue licenses. The national Supreme Court intervened in January, deeming Moore\u0027s decision unconstitutional. Moore was not among the judges behind the latest decision. Of the 67 state counties, only a third of them began to issue same-sex marriage licences.","The status of the licenses that have already been issued in Alabama hasn\u0027t been made clear. The Alabama Supreme Court said that the pre-issued licenses were \"purported\". On this issue, Kennedy said \"These people are married. There\u0027s nothing the Alabama Supreme Court can do to overturn that.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Same-sex_marriage","description":"Category:Same-sex marriage"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Alabama","description":"Category:Alabama"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:US_Supreme_Court","description":"Category:US Supreme Court"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 4, 2015"]},{"name":"LGBT","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Chris Pruitt"]},{"name":"w","description":["Supreme Court of Alabama"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Constitution"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roy Moore"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/04/in-defiant-ruling-alabama-supreme-court-stops-same-sex-marriage-in-state/","title\u003dIn defiant ruling, Alabama Supreme Court stops same-sex marriage in state","author\u003dFred Barbash","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-31727556","title\u003dAlabama Supreme Court orders halt to same-sex marriage licences","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.al.com/news/index.ssf/2015/03/alabama_supreme_court_orders_h.html#incart_std","title\u003dAlabama Supreme Court orders halt to same-sex marriages","author\u003dKyle Whitmire, Brendad Kirby, Kent Faulk","pub\u003dThe Birmingham News","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Spanish authorities arrest Yuriy Kolobov, former Ukrainian finance minister","wikiTitle":"Spanish_authorities_arrest_Yuriy_Kolobov,_former_Ukrainian_finance_minister","wid":1969228,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-12T17:41:55Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/business/spain-arrests-ukraines-ex-finance-minister-yuri-kolobov/articleshow/46461652.cms, title\u003dSpain arrests Ukraine\u0027s ex-finance minister Yuri Kolobov, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Economic Times, date\u003dMarch 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-31738293, title\u003dUkraine\u0027s former finance minister arrested in Spain, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://uk.news.yahoo.com/former-ukraine-finance-minister-arrested-spanish-coast-174521935.html#9taKqXk, title\u003dFormer Ukraine Finance Minister arrested on Spanish coast, author\u003dSonya Dowsett, Elisabeth O\u0027Leary, pub\u003dYahoo! News, date\u003dMarch 4, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Viktor_Yanukovich","description":"Viktor Yanukovich"},{"id":"Ukraine","description":"Ukraine"},{"id":"Spain","description":"Spain"},{"id":"Viktor_Yanukovych","description":"Viktor Yanukovych"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 5, 2015] TEMPLATE[Ukraine] TEMPLATE[image_credit, \"[https://www.youtube.com/user/spravedlive Ð¡Ð¿ÑÐ°Ð²ÐµÐ´Ð»Ð¸Ð²ÑÑÑÑ. ÐÐ½Ð½Ð° ÐÐµÐ·ÑÐ»Ð¸Ðº]\"] TEMPLATE[w, Yuriy Kolobov], the former TEMPLATE[w, Ministry of Finance (Ukraine), finance minister] of Ukraine has been arrested in Spain on charges of fraud and embezzlement. Kolobov was wanted, along with former President Viktor Yanukovych, accused of fraud which cost Ukraine billions of dollars in assets. The Spanish civil guard arrested him on Wednesday, at a flat in TEMPLATE[w, Altea], in the TEMPLATE[w, Province of Alicante].","A brief statement from the Ukrainian interior ministry said: \"We confirm the information that [Mr Kolobov] has been detained.\" No comment was made by Spain\u0027s interior ministry. A judge at Spain\u0027s High Court will question Kolobov, before dealing with the extradition process. Kolobov, 41, is the first member of Yanukovich\u0027s administration to be arrested on charges relating to fraud. The current Ukrainian government continue efforts to recover lost assets. The Interim Prime Minister, TEMPLATE[w, Arseniy Yatsenyuk], told parliament that Yanukovich has left Ukraine with $75 billion of debt.","Interpol issued warrants for Yanukovich, Kolobov, and former Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Mykola Azarov]. It is doubtful Yanukovich, who is now in Russia, could be extradited back to Ukraine. Kolobov previously held the position of deputy head of Ukraine\u0027s central bank, before being selected as Finance minister in 2012.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Ukraine","description":"Category:Ukraine"},{"id":"Category:Spain","description":"Category:Spain"},{"id":"Category:Russia","description":"Category:Russia"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Viktor_Yanukovych","description":"Category:Viktor Yanukovych"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Economy_and_business","description":"Category:Economy and business"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 5, 2015"]},{"name":"Ukraine","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["\"[https://www.youtube.com/user/spravedlive Ð¡Ð¿ÑÐ°Ð²ÐµÐ´Ð»Ð¸Ð²ÑÑÑÑ. ÐÐ½Ð½Ð° ÐÐµÐ·ÑÐ»Ð¸Ðº]\""]},{"name":"w","description":["Yuriy Kolobov"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ministry of Finance (Ukraine)","finance minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["Altea"]},{"name":"w","description":["Province of Alicante"]},{"name":"w","description":["Arseniy Yatsenyuk"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mykola Azarov"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/international/business/spain-arrests-ukraines-ex-finance-minister-yuri-kolobov/articleshow/46461652.cms","title\u003dSpain arrests Ukraine\u0027s ex-finance minister Yuri Kolobov","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Economic Times","date\u003dMarch 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-31738293","title\u003dUkraine\u0027s former finance minister arrested in Spain","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://uk.news.yahoo.com/former-ukraine-finance-minister-arrested-spanish-coast-174521935.html#9taKqXk","title\u003dFormer Ukraine Finance Minister arrested on Spanish coast","author\u003dSonya Dowsett, Elisabeth O\u0027Leary","pub\u003dYahoo! News","date\u003dMarch 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Delta Air Lines jetliner skids off New York airport\u0027s runway","wikiTitle":"Delta_Air_Lines_jetliner_skids_off_New_York_airport\u0027s_runway","wid":1974065,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-16T11:25:12Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnbc.com/id/102413682, title\u003dOne LaGuardia runway reopened after plane accident shut down airport, author\u003dEverett Rosenfeld, pub\u003dCNBC, date\u003dMarch 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/delta-airlines-plane-skids-off-runway-laguardia-airport/story?id\u003d29411627, title\u003dDelta Airlines Plane Skids Off Runway at LaGuardia Airport in New York, author\u003dGillian Mohny, pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dMarch 5, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Delta_Air_Lines","description":"Delta Air Lines"},{"id":"New_York_City","description":"New York City"},{"id":"LaGuardia_Airport","description":"LaGuardia Airport"},{"id":"Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Federal Aviation Administration"},{"id":"National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"National Transportation Safety Board"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation] TEMPLATE[w, Aircraft Rescue and Firefighting, emergency vehicle]TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[w:User:FieldMarine, Leonard J. DeFrancisci]]] A Delta Air Lines passenger jet skidded off the runway at New York City\u0027s LaGuardia Airport in snowy weather on Thursday, causing a shutdown of the airport, according to officials.  The jetliner was carrying 127 passengers and five crew.","The MD-88, operating as flight 1086, was flying in from TEMPLATE[w, Atlanta, Georgia, Atlanta] when it lost control after landing. There were a few minor injuries while the passengers were evacuated. The plane was significantly damaged and the airport was shut down. One of the runways reopened around 2 p.m., although an earlier Federal Aviation Administration statement had put reopening at 6:59 p.m.","The city fire department said five out of at least 28 passengers with minor injuries were hospitalized.","TEMPLATE[w, Pat Foye], executive director of the port authority, said the plane was two thirds of the way along the 7,000-TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), foot] runway when it began a leftward skid that nearly sent it into the water.","The National Transportation Safety Board sent an investigator for the TEMPLATE[w, flight data recorders]. Delta stated they would work with authorities to investigate.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Delta_Air_Lines","description":"Category:Delta Air Lines"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:New_York","description":"Category:New York"},{"id":"Category:New_York,_New_York","description":"Category:New York, New York"},{"id":"Category:LaGuardia_Airport","description":"Category:LaGuardia Airport"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Category:Federal Aviation Administration"},{"id":"Category:National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"Category:National Transportation Safety Board"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 8, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Aircraft Rescue and Firefighting","emergency vehicle"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[w:User:FieldMarine","Leonard J. DeFrancisci]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Atlanta, Georgia","Atlanta"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pat Foye"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","foot"]},{"name":"w","description":["flight data recorders"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnbc.com/id/102413682","title\u003dOne LaGuardia runway reopened after plane accident shut down airport","author\u003dEverett Rosenfeld","pub\u003dCNBC","date\u003dMarch 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/delta-airlines-plane-skids-off-runway-laguardia-airport/story?id\u003d29411627","title\u003dDelta Airlines Plane Skids Off Runway at LaGuardia Airport in New York","author\u003dGillian Mohny","pub\u003dABC News","date\u003dMarch 5, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Five dead after bar attack in Bamako, Mali","wikiTitle":"Five_dead_after_bar_attack_in_Bamako,_Mali","wid":1978009,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-18T22:30:10Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/03/07/africa/mali-bar-shooting/, title\u003dReport: Jihadist group says it carried out attack that killed five at Mali bar, author\u003dFaith Karimi, Katarina Hoije, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMarch 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31775679, title\u003dMali bar attack kills five in Bamako, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/mali/11353315/Five-dead-including-Frenchman-and-Belgian-in-Mali-restaurant-terror-attack.html, title\u003dFive dead including Frenchman and Belgian in Mali restaurant terror attack, author\u003dDavid Chazan, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dMarch 7. 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Mali","description":"Mali"},{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"Belgium","description":"Belgian"},{"id":"European_Union","description":"European Union"},{"id":"Switzerland","description":"Swiss"},{"id":"FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"FranÃ§ois Hollande"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[Mali] TEMPLATE[image, Arensond] Five people, including two Europeans, have been killed by gunmen during an attack on a bar in TEMPLATE[w, Bamako], the capital city of Mali, early on Sunday morning. At least nine others were injured during the attack in which the assailants used machine guns and grenades.","Three Malians, a French national, and a Belgian security official who was working for the European Union were killed. At least three Swiss nationals, including soldiers, are amongst the wounded. Local newspaper al-Akhbar reported TEMPLATE[w, al-Murabitun], an Islamic extremist group, say they are behind the shooting.","Gunmen attacked the La Terrasse bar shortly at around 1:00a.m. French soldiers were on-scene soon after the attack had started.","Commenting for the BBC, Alex Duval-Smith said \"When I arrived there about an hour after the attack, there was a white body bag on the floor. A dozen Malian police were at the scene, including an inspector who used tables and stools to cordon off the bar. A witness said the attackers had sped off in a vehicle and on a motorbike and that one had shouted \u0027TEMPLATE[w, Takbir, \u0027\u0027Allahu Akbar\u0027\u0027]\u0027\".","al-Murabitun hold territory in Northern Mali. According to the TEMPLATE[w, U.S State Department] they are \"newly-formed\".","French President FranÃ§ois Hollande said the shooting was \"cowardly\" and spoke to TEMPLATE[w, Ibrahim Boubakar Keita], the President of Mali. During the conversation he offered Mali \"the aid of France\" to fight extremism. The French Embassy in Bamako has warned its citizens living in the city to be on high alert.","This is believed to be the first attack by a Islamist group in the capital city. In 2013 French troops aided in displacing Islamist forces from towns in Northern Mali. Mali still has around 1,000 serving French soldiers stationed in the country.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Mali","description":"Category:Mali"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Belgium","description":"Category:Belgium"},{"id":"Category:Switzerland","description":"Category:Switzerland"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"Category:FranÃ§ois Hollande"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:European_Union","description":"Category:European Union"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Islam","description":"Category:Islam"},{"id":"Category:Ibrahim_Boubacar_Keita","description":"Category:Ibrahim Boubacar Keita"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Mali","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Arensond"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bamako"]},{"name":"w","description":["al-Murabitun"]},{"name":"w","description":["Takbir","\u0027\u0027Allahu Akbar\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["U.S State Department"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ibrahim Boubakar Keita"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/03/07/africa/mali-bar-shooting/","title\u003dReport: Jihadist group says it carried out attack that killed five at Mali bar","author\u003dFaith Karimi, Katarina Hoije","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMarch 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31775679","title\u003dMali bar attack kills five in Bamako","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/africaandindianocean/mali/11353315/Five-dead-including-Frenchman-and-Belgian-in-Mali-restaurant-terror-attack.html","title\u003dFive dead including Frenchman and Belgian in Mali restaurant terror attack","author\u003dDavid Chazan","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dMarch 7. 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["al-Akhbar"]}
{"title":"Nigeria allies join fight against Boko Haram","wikiTitle":"Nigeria_allies_join_fight_against_Boko_Haram","wid":1978129,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-16T11:25:14Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/03/08/uk-nigeria-violence-niger-idUKKBN0M40LF20150308, title\u003dChad, Niger launch joint offensive against Boko Haram in Nigeria, author\u003dMadjiasra Nako and Abdoulaye Massalaki, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dMarch 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31789412, title\u003dBoko Haram conflict: Nigerian allies launch offensive, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2985034/Niger-Chad-launch-offensive-against-Boko-Haram-Niger-government.html, title\u003dNiger, Chad attack Boko Haram after IS pledge of allegiance, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dDaily Mail, date\u003dMarch 8, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Chad","description":"Chad"},{"id":"Niger","description":"Niger"},{"id":"Boko_Haram","description":"Boko Haram"},{"id":"Nigeria","description":"Nigeria"},{"id":"African_Union","description":"African Union"},{"id":"Cameroon","description":"Cameroon"},{"id":"Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Islamic State"},{"id":"BBC","description":"BBC"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[Nigeria] Military forces from Chad and Niger yesterday engaged Boko Haram militants within the borders of Nigeria. This follows African Union endorsement on Friday of the creation of an 8,000-plus strong regional force to combat the threat posed by the militant group.","Along with Cameroon, both Chad and Niger have previously engaged Boko Haram forces who have crossed their borders from the territory they hold in northern Nigeria. While all three countries have previously aided Nigeria against Boko Haram, the new attacks are Niger\u0027s first push into foreign territory.","The new attacks against Boko Haram follow its leader pledging allegiance on Saturday to Islamic State, as other groups have done. A Nigerian military spokesman, speaking to the BBC, dismissed this as a \"plea for help\"; Nigerian spokesmen cited recent military defeats inflicted upon Boko Haram as the reason for the militants\u0027 announcement.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:African_Union","description":"Category:African Union"},{"id":"Category:Boko_Haram","description":"Category:Boko Haram"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Cameroon","description":"Category:Cameroon"},{"id":"Category:Chad","description":"Category:Chad"},{"id":"Category:Niger","description":"Category:Niger"},{"id":"Category:Nigeria","description":"Category:Nigeria"},{"id":"Category:CSJJ104_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:CSJJ104 (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Nigeria","description":[]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/03/08/uk-nigeria-violence-niger-idUKKBN0M40LF20150308","title\u003dChad, Niger launch joint offensive against Boko Haram in Nigeria","author\u003dMadjiasra Nako and Abdoulaye Massalaki","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dMarch 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31789412","title\u003dBoko Haram conflict: Nigerian allies launch offensive","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/wires/afp/article-2985034/Niger-Chad-launch-offensive-against-Boko-Haram-Niger-government.html","title\u003dNiger, Chad attack Boko Haram after IS pledge of allegiance","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dDaily Mail","date\u003dMarch 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Zambian President Edgar Lungu to undergo treatment abroad after collapse","wikiTitle":"Zambian_President_Edgar_Lungu_to_undergo_treatment_abroad_after_collapse","wid":1980102,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-18T21:53:03Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPresident Levy Mwanawasa of Zambia dies at age 59 following stroke, date\u003dAugust 20, 2008]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://mgafrica.com/article/2015-03-09-new-president-lungu-collapses-why-its-bad-politics-for-zambias-presidents-to-be-taken-ill/, title\u003dNo job for ordinary men: New Zambian president to have treatment abroad after collapsing, author\u003d, pub\u003dMail and Guardian Africa, date\u003dMarch 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31795526, title\u003dEdgar Lungu collapse: Zambian president \u0027needs treatment abroad\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 9, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Zambia","description":"Zambia"},{"id":"International_Women\u0027s_Day","description":"International Women\u0027s Day"},{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"England","description":"England"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 10, 2015] TEMPLATE[Zambia] TEMPLATE[image, US Embassy Addisababa] TEMPLATE[w, Edgar Lungu], the current President of Zambia, is to undergo medical treatment aboard after collapsing while on stage in TEMPLATE[w, Lusaka] on Sunday during a ceremony for International Women\u0027s Day. The Presidency announced yesterday that Lungu will have throat surgery abroad.","Doctors on Sunday diagnosed him with TEMPLATE[w, malaria]. Lungu spoke to the press from hospital on Sunday saying \"I am looking forward to going home. Doctors have done their tests and they have found traces of malaria, but they are doing further tests and they will let me know what next after before the end of the day\".","A later announcement identified his condition instead as a narrowing of the TEMPLATE[wikt, oesophagus], which he had previously received treatment for three decades ago. Despite not announcing where Lungu would head to be treated the Presidency did say he would undergo a \"high-tech medical procedure which is currently unavailable in Zambia\".","Lungu, who only became the Zambian President in January, has previously dispelled rumours of his health. During the election he fought back against comments about his health calling it a  \"smear\" campaign against him.","Some in Zambia have claimed the presidency is \"jinxed\". Lungu\u0027s predecessor TEMPLATE[w, Michael Sata] died in October of last year at the age of 77 in London, England. Sata died only six years after serving President TEMPLATE[w, Levy Mwanawasa] died following a stroke.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Zambia","description":"Category:Zambia"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:International_Women\u0027s_Day","description":"Category:International Women\u0027s Day"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Zambia","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["US Embassy Addisababa"]},{"name":"w","description":["Edgar Lungu"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lusaka"]},{"name":"w","description":["malaria"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["oesophagus"]},{"name":"w","description":["Michael Sata"]},{"name":"w","description":["Levy Mwanawasa"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPresident Levy Mwanawasa of Zambia dies at age 59 following stroke","date\u003dAugust 20, 2008"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://mgafrica.com/article/2015-03-09-new-president-lungu-collapses-why-its-bad-politics-for-zambias-presidents-to-be-taken-ill/","title\u003dNo job for ordinary men: New Zambian president to have treatment abroad after collapsing","author\u003d","pub\u003dMail and Guardian Africa","date\u003dMarch 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31795526","title\u003dEdgar Lungu collapse: Zambian president \u0027needs treatment abroad\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Sam Simon, \u0027The Simpsons\u0027 co-creator, dies aged 59","wikiTitle":"Sam_Simon,_\u0027The_Simpsons\u0027_co-creator,_dies_aged_59","wid":1980223,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-24T19:58:17Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://variety.com/2015/tv/news/sam-simon-co-creator-of-the-simpsons-dies-at-59-1201448945/, title\u003dSam Simon, Co-Creator of âThe Simpsons,â Dies at 59, author\u003dCarmel Dagan, pub\u003dVariety (magazine), date\u003dMarch 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2986891/Simpsons-creator-Sam-Simon-gave-away-100million-fortune-animal-charities-dies-colon-cancer-aged-59.html, title\u003dSimpsons co-creator Sam Simon who gave away his $100million fortune to animal charities dies of colon cancer aged 59, author\u003dDavid McCormack, James Nye, pub\u003dMail Online, date\u003dMarch 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/sam-simon-dead-the-simpsons-cocreator-dies-aged-59-10096742.html, title\u003dSimpsons co-creator Sam Simon dies aged 59, author\u003dLoulla-Mae Eleftheriou-Smith, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMarch 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-31801198, title\u003dSam Simon, co-creator of The Simpsons, dies at 59, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 9, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"cancer","description":"cancer"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 10, 2015] TEMPLATE[television] TEMPLATE[w, 2008 World Series of Poker]TEMPLATE[image, Matt Waldron] TEMPLATE[w, Sam Simon] died, at the age of 59, on Sunday of TEMPLATE[w, colon cancer, colon] cancer, a disease he was diagnosed with in 2012. One of the co-creators of the television series TEMPLATE[w, The Simpsons], Simon helped create the hugely successful series in 1989 alongside TEMPLATE[w, Matt Groening] and TEMPLATE[w, James L. Brooks]. He left the show in 1993 after roles as writer and character developer among others.","Before The Simpsons Simon had worked on several shows in various positions. During the 1980s he worked on shows such as TEMPLATE[w, Taxi (TV series), Taxi], TEMPLATE[w, Cheers], and TEMPLATE[w, The Tracy Ullman Show]. In 1989 he helped create The Simpsons with Brooks and Groening, and was responsible for hiring the show\u0027s first writing team. Despite leaving the show in 1993 he kept the title of executive producer, and continued to receive tens of millions of dollars every season in royalties.","After his diagnosis he began to donate his fortune to charity, estimated at around TEMPLATE[w, US$]100 million . He donated to and was an active voice for charities focusing on animal rights including TEMPLATE[w, PETA]. The Sam Simon Foundation, an organization he founded in 2002, released a statement to TEMPLATE[w, TMZ] after his death: \"For those of us who knew him, his voice will forever echo in our minds; his sense of humor will continue to make us laugh; and his compassion and generosity will continue to impact our lives[...] Sam, you will be missed by many, but there is a particular sadness among our clinic staff. We have been together for so long, and your absence will forever leave a void in our lives.\"","Speaking to TEMPLATE[w, NBC] in November 2014, Simon said \"Cancer has been a fight, a journey, an adventure and the most amazing experience of my life.\"","Simon had no children and was twice divorced. His first wife was actress TEMPLATE[w, Jennifer Tilly], to whom he was married from 1984 until their split in 1991. He married Playboy Playmate TEMPLATE[w, Jami Ferrell] in 2000; the pair divorced not long after.","Current executive producer of The Simpsons, TEMPLATE[w, Al Jean] paid tribute to Simon via Twitter, tweeting \"Just heard terrible news of death of @simonsam. A great man; I owe him everything.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Cancer","description":"Category:Cancer"},{"id":"Category:The_Simpsons","description":"Category:The Simpsons"},{"id":"Category:Animal_rights","description":"Category:Animal rights"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 10, 2015"]},{"name":"television","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["2008 World Series of Poker"]},{"name":"image","description":["Matt Waldron"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sam Simon"]},{"name":"w","description":["colon cancer","colon"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Simpsons"]},{"name":"w","description":["Matt Groening"]},{"name":"w","description":["James L. Brooks"]},{"name":"w","description":["Taxi (TV series)","Taxi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cheers"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Tracy Ullman Show"]},{"name":"w","description":["US$"]},{"name":"w","description":["PETA"]},{"name":"w","description":["TMZ"]},{"name":"w","description":["NBC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jennifer Tilly"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jami Ferrell"]},{"name":"w","description":["Al Jean"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://variety.com/2015/tv/news/sam-simon-co-creator-of-the-simpsons-dies-at-59-1201448945/","title\u003dSam Simon, Co-Creator of âThe Simpsons,â Dies at 59","author\u003dCarmel Dagan","pub\u003dVariety (magazine)","date\u003dMarch 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-2986891/Simpsons-creator-Sam-Simon-gave-away-100million-fortune-animal-charities-dies-colon-cancer-aged-59.html","title\u003dSimpsons co-creator Sam Simon who gave away his $100million fortune to animal charities dies of colon cancer aged 59","author\u003dDavid McCormack, James Nye","pub\u003dMail Online","date\u003dMarch 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/sam-simon-dead-the-simpsons-cocreator-dies-aged-59-10096742.html","title\u003dSimpsons co-creator Sam Simon dies aged 59","author\u003dLoulla-Mae Eleftheriou-Smith","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dMarch 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-31801198","title\u003dSam Simon, co-creator of The Simpsons, dies at 59","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Simpsons]","The Simpsons","TEMPLATE[w, Taxi (TV series), Taxi]","TEMPLATE[w, Cheers]","TEMPLATE[w, The Tracy Ullman Show]","The Simpsons","The Simpsons"]}
{"title":"U.S. Secret Service conducts drone exercise","wikiTitle":"U.S._Secret_Service_conducts_drone_exercise","wid":1982440,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-20T16:56:11Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://bigstory.ap.org/article/b201597fe2dc4f5e9fe8241516e35e07/secret-service-testing-drones-how-disrupt-their-flying, title\u003dSecret Service testing drones, how to disrupt their flying, author\u003d Alicia A. Caldwell, Josh Ledermam, pub\u003dAssociated Press, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://gizmodo.com/the-secret-service-is-flying-drones-over-dc-in-the-midd-1690504073, title\u003dThe Secret Service Is Flying Drones Over DC Late at Night, author\u003dAdam Clarke Estes, pub\u003dGizmodo, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://rt.com/usa/239349-drones-washington-secret-service/, title\u003dSecret Service to carry out drone tests over Washington, author\u003d, pub\u003dRT (TV network), date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/retrieveECFR?gp\u003d\u0026SID\u003d01104537a81a7a5ee958dee7bb087ed4\u0026n\u003dpt14.2.93\u0026r\u003dPART\u0026ty\u003dHTML#se14.2.93_1335, title\u003dTitle 14 CFR Chapter I, Subchapter F, Part 93, author\u003d, pub\u003dUnited States Government Publishing Office, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Associated_Press","description":"Associated Press"},{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"Washington,_D.C.","description":"Washington, D.C."},{"id":"Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Federal Aviation Administration"},{"id":"Paris,_France","description":"Paris"},{"id":"France","description":"France"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation]  The Associated Press (AP) reported on Tuesday the U.S. TEMPLATE[w, U.S. Secret Service, Secret Service] is conducting drone exercises over Washington, D.C. to defend against TEMPLATE[w, unmanned aerial vehicles] being flown over the area.","The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) approved the Secret Service to conduct these flying exercises. The exercises are to be over parts of D.C. airspace which is normally off-limits below 18,000 TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), feet], also called a no-fly aone or the TEMPLATE[w, Washington, DC Metropolitan Area Special Flight Rules Area#Flight Restricted Zone, D.C. flight restricted zone]. The exercises are to take place in the very early morning hours over the next several weeks.","According to AP, a U.S. official speaking under condition of anonymity said the agency is testing these drones for law enforcement and to defend against potentially dangerous drones, but declined to comment on the specific details because they\u0027re classified. However, they sought to prevent concerns by possible witnesses by publicizing their intent to conduct tests. The agency is cautious of witnesses of unmanned aerial vehicles flying over D.C. because of a drone sighting incident several weeks ago. Witnesses saw several unidentified drones flying over Paris, France, which caused concerns.","AP said techniques to be tested include signal jamming. Most drones use TEMPLATE[w, radio-frequency] signals for remote control. Intercepting these signals might allow tracking the drones. Jamming, though, could interrupt TEMPLATE[w, Wi-Fi] of people in the vicinity.","The FAA last month announced preliminary guidelines requiring UAVs be operated within sight of the operator, prohibiting night flying, and requiring TEMPLATE[w, airspeed, speeds] below 100 TEMPLATE[w, miles per hour] (about 160 TEMPLATE[w, kilometres per hour, kph]) and altitudes below 500 feet.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:aviation","description":"Category:aviation"},{"id":"Category:Washington,_D.C.","description":"Category:Washington, D.C."},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 12, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["U.S. Secret Service","Secret Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["unmanned aerial vehicles"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","feet"]},{"name":"w","description":["Washington, DC Metropolitan Area Special Flight Rules Area#Flight Restricted Zone","D.C. flight restricted zone"]},{"name":"w","description":["radio-frequency"]},{"name":"w","description":["Wi-Fi"]},{"name":"w","description":["airspeed","speeds"]},{"name":"w","description":["miles per hour"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometres per hour","kph"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://bigstory.ap.org/article/b201597fe2dc4f5e9fe8241516e35e07/secret-service-testing-drones-how-disrupt-their-flying","title\u003dSecret Service testing drones, how to disrupt their flying","author\u003d Alicia A. Caldwell, Josh Ledermam","pub\u003dAssociated Press","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://gizmodo.com/the-secret-service-is-flying-drones-over-dc-in-the-midd-1690504073","title\u003dThe Secret Service Is Flying Drones Over DC Late at Night","author\u003dAdam Clarke Estes","pub\u003dGizmodo","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://rt.com/usa/239349-drones-washington-secret-service/","title\u003dSecret Service to carry out drone tests over Washington","author\u003d","pub\u003dRT (TV network)","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/retrieveECFR?gp\u003d\u0026SID\u003d01104537a81a7a5ee958dee7bb087ed4\u0026n\u003dpt14.2.93\u0026r\u003dPART\u0026ty\u003dHTML#se14.2.93_1335","title\u003dTitle 14 CFR Chapter I, Subchapter F, Part 93","author\u003d","pub\u003dUnited States Government Publishing Office","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Ten killed in helicopter crash in Argentina, French Olympians among the dead","wikiTitle":"Ten_killed_in_helicopter_crash_in_Argentina,_French_Olympians_among_the_dead","wid":1982805,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-20T16:56:10Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/03/10/uk-argentina-crash-idUKKBN0M52EN20150310, title\u003dFrance mourns sports stars killed in Argentina helicopter crash, author\u003dEliana Raszewski, Mark John, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/southamerica/argentina/11460541/French-Olympians-filming-reality-TV-survival-show-killed-in-helicopter-crash-in-Argentina.html, title\u003dFrench Olympians filming reality TV survival show killed in helicopter crash in Argentina, author\u003dJosie Ensor, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-31819952, title\u003dStunned France probes deadly Argentina helicopter crash, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1441788/video-emerges-of-reality-tv-helicopter-crash, title\u003dVideo Emerges Of Reality TV Helicopter Crash, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"Argentina","description":"Argentina"},{"id":"Francois_Hollande","description":"Francois Hollande"},{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"England","description":"England"},{"id":"China","description":"China"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[Argentina] TEMPLATE[image, Elisabeth Klimesch] Three French sport stars are among the dead following a TEMPLATE[w, Villa Castelli helicopter crash, helicopter crash] on Monday in TEMPLATE[w, Villa Castelli, Argentina, Villa Castelli], Argentina. In total, ten people died after the crash, which involved two helicopters. The dead included passengers and both pilots in the mid-air collision. The victims were taking part in the French reality television show \u0027TEMPLATE[w, Dropped (TV series), Dropped]\u0027 when the accident happened.","The victims included TEMPLATE[w, Summer Olympic Games, Olympic] swimmer TEMPLATE[w, Camille Muffat], Olympic boxer TEMPLATE[w, Alexis Vastine] and TEMPLATE[w, Florence Arthaud], a yachtswoman. Both pilots were Argentinian, the remainder of the victims were French and worked as part of the television shows production team. Bodies of all ten of the victims have been retrieved and taken to the morgue.","The accident occurred while both helicopters were flying at a low altitude in tandem. Amateur camera footage shows the helicopters colliding when one appears to fly into the path of the other. It remains unclear what caused actions which lead to the crash. Cesar Angulo, Secretary of Security for TEMPLATE[w, La Rioja], the province in which the accident happened released an update. He said \"An explosion occurred and it\u0027s believed that they must have collided. Aeronautical experts will have to determine that.\"","French President Francois Hollande paid tribute to the victims. Speaking about the sport stars who lost their lives he said \"They are dead because they wanted to push the boundaries. They wanted to make new exploits known to the world, make people aware of new countries and regions.\" An involuntary manslaughter investigation has been opened by French officials. The procedure occurred automatically due to the fact the French citizens died abroad.","The television show involves contestants taking part in survival style activities in remote locations. Other contestants taking part included figure skater TEMPLATE[w, Philippe Candeloro], footballer TEMPLATE[w, Sylvain Wiltord], snowboarder TEMPLATE[w, Anne-Flore Marxer], swimmer TEMPLATE[w, Alain Bernard] and TEMPLATE[w, Jeannie Longo], a cyclist. All the other contestants were uninjured during the accident.","The show, which was to be shown on TEMPLATE[w, TF1] in France started filming in February. The channel released a statement after the accident. They said \"We learn with immense sadness of the accident that occurred during the filming of the show \u0027Dropped.\u0027 [Staff] come together in this terrible time with the pain of the families and those close to the victims\". French media announced that all contestants and crew are returning home and that filming had been suspended.","Muffat became the Olympic champion in the 400m freestyle event at the TEMPLATE[w, 2012 Summer Olympics] in London, England. The 25-year-old also won a silver and bronze medal at the same games in different events. Vastine, 28, also competed at the 2012 games, being eliminated from the Light Welterweight category in the quarter finals. He won a gold medal in the TEMPLATE[w, 2008 Summer Olympics, 2008 games] in TEMPLATE[w, Beijing], China. Arthaud, 57, was a yachtswoman who won the 1990 TEMPLATE[w, Route du Rhum].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Argentina","description":"Category:Argentina"},{"id":"Category:South_America","description":"Category:South America"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Midair_collisions","description":"Category:Midair collisions"},{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Swimming","description":"Category:Swimming"},{"id":"Category:Boxing","description":"Category:Boxing"},{"id":"Category:Sailing","description":"Category:Sailing"},{"id":"Category:Olympics","description":"Category:Olympics"},{"id":"Category:2012_Summer_Olympics","description":"Category:2012 Summer Olympics"},{"id":"Category:Beijing_2008_Olympic_and_Paralympic_Summer_Games","description":"Category:Beijing 2008 Olympic and Paralympic Summer Games"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Argentina","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Elisabeth Klimesch"]},{"name":"w","description":["Villa Castelli helicopter crash","helicopter crash"]},{"name":"w","description":["Villa Castelli, Argentina","Villa Castelli"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dropped (TV series)","Dropped"]},{"name":"w","description":["Summer Olympic Games","Olympic"]},{"name":"w","description":["Camille Muffat"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alexis Vastine"]},{"name":"w","description":["Florence Arthaud"]},{"name":"w","description":["La Rioja"]},{"name":"w","description":["Philippe Candeloro"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sylvain Wiltord"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anne-Flore Marxer"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alain Bernard"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jeannie Longo"]},{"name":"w","description":["TF1"]},{"name":"w","description":["2012 Summer Olympics"]},{"name":"w","description":["2008 Summer Olympics","2008 games"]},{"name":"w","description":["Beijing"]},{"name":"w","description":["Route du Rhum"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/03/10/uk-argentina-crash-idUKKBN0M52EN20150310","title\u003dFrance mourns sports stars killed in Argentina helicopter crash","author\u003dEliana Raszewski, Mark John","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/southamerica/argentina/11460541/French-Olympians-filming-reality-TV-survival-show-killed-in-helicopter-crash-in-Argentina.html","title\u003dFrench Olympians filming reality TV survival show killed in helicopter crash in Argentina","author\u003dJosie Ensor","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-latin-america-31819952","title\u003dStunned France probes deadly Argentina helicopter crash","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1441788/video-emerges-of-reality-tv-helicopter-crash","title\u003dVideo Emerges Of Reality TV Helicopter Crash","author\u003d","pub\u003dSky News","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Hard drugs temporarily legal in Ireland due to constitutional loophole","wikiTitle":"Hard_drugs_temporarily_legal_in_Ireland_due_to_constitutional_loophole","wid":1983470,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-03T15:42:25Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/10/irish-es-are-smiling-ecstasy-drugs-temporarily-legal-in-ireland, title\u003dIrish Es are smiling â ecstasy and other drugs temporarily legal in Ireland, author\u003dHenry McDonald, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/ireland-mistakenly-legalises-drugs-twitter-reacts-to-bizarre-loophole-allowing-ecstasy-ketamine-and-magic-mushrooms-for-one-night-only-10099278.html, title\u003dIreland mistakenly legalises drugs: Twitter reacts to bizarre loophole allowing ecstasy, ketamine and magic mushrooms for one night only, author\u003dKashmira Gander, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/31822842, title\u003dIreland has mistakenly legalised ecstasy and ketamine for one day, author\u003dLaura Wignall, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/ireland-just-accidentally-legalised-ecstasy-ketamine-and-crystal-meth-10098612.html, title\u003dIreland just accidentally legalised ecstasy, ketamine and magic mushrooms, author\u003dChristopher Hooton, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]"],["Leo Varadkar, Irish Health Minister, personal website","Misuse of Drugs Act, 1977, Irish Statute Book"]],"links":[{"id":"Ireland","description":"Ireland"},{"id":"Dublin","description":"Dublin"},{"id":"ecstasy_(drug)","description":"ecstasy"},{"id":"magic_mushrooms","description":"magic mushrooms"},{"id":"Oireachtas","description":"Oireachtas"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"http://leovaradkar.ie/","description":"Leo Varadkar"},{"id":"http://www.irishstatutebook.ie/1977/en/act/pub/0012/","description":"Misuse of Drugs Act, 1977"}],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Ireland] TEMPLATE[w, Leo Varadkar], Ireland\u0027s Health Minister, introduced emergency legislation in the lower house of the Irish parliament yesterday evening, to negate the legal loophole created by a decision from Dublin\u0027s Court of Appeal that morning. Various hard drugs \u0026mdash; including TEMPLATE[w, ketamine], ecstasy, and magic mushrooms \u0026mdash; were rendered legal, following the law governing their prohibition being found to be unconstitutional.","The drug possession case of Stanislav Bederev led to the legal loophole; his lawyers arguing the 2010 addition of several drugs to the country\u0027s controlled substances list, governed by the TEMPLATE[w, Misuse of Drugs Act (Ireland), Misuse of Drugs Act, 1977], was unlawful. They contended it was unconstitutional to add these substances to the list without consulting the Oireachtas \u0026mdash; i.e., parliament.","The Irish government is stressing the urgency of parliamentary legislation to rectify the situation. \"It is now important from both a public health and criminal justice perspective that the legislation be enacted as soon as possible\", said a government spokesperson. The Health Minister expressed concern both for the welfare of individuals taking advantage of the temporary legality of the substances involved, and for drug-related convictions handed down since the now-unconstitutional changes came into effect.","\"The emergency legislation I am introducing today will re-instate the status quo ante and re-control all drugs that were controlled prior to this judgment\", said Mr Varadkar.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Ireland","description":"Category:Ireland"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Drugs","description":"Category:Drugs"},{"id":"Category:MDMA","description":"Category:MDMA"},{"id":"Category:Psilocybin","description":"Category:Psilocybin"},{"id":"Category:Oireachtas","description":"Category:Oireachtas"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Ireland","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Leo Varadkar"]},{"name":"w","description":["ketamine"]},{"name":"w","description":["Misuse of Drugs Act (Ireland)","Misuse of Drugs Act, 1977"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/10/irish-es-are-smiling-ecstasy-drugs-temporarily-legal-in-ireland","title\u003dIrish Es are smiling â ecstasy and other drugs temporarily legal in Ireland","author\u003dHenry McDonald","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/ireland-mistakenly-legalises-drugs-twitter-reacts-to-bizarre-loophole-allowing-ecstasy-ketamine-and-magic-mushrooms-for-one-night-only-10099278.html","title\u003dIreland mistakenly legalises drugs: Twitter reacts to bizarre loophole allowing ecstasy, ketamine and magic mushrooms for one night only","author\u003dKashmira Gander","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/31822842","title\u003dIreland has mistakenly legalised ecstasy and ketamine for one day","author\u003dLaura Wignall","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/ireland-just-accidentally-legalised-ecstasy-ketamine-and-crystal-meth-10098612.html","title\u003dIreland just accidentally legalised ecstasy, ketamine and magic mushrooms","author\u003dChristopher Hooton","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dMarch 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Misuse of Drugs Act (Ireland), Misuse of Drugs Act, 1977]"]}
{"title":"BBC suspend presenter Jeremy Clarkson over \u0027fracas\u0027 with producer","wikiTitle":"BBC_suspend_presenter_Jeremy_Clarkson_over_\u0027fracas\u0027_with_producer","wid":1983793,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-03T15:42:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003d\u0027Have them all shot\u0027: BBC gets 21,000+ complaints over Jeremy Clarkson\u0027s public sector striker comments, date\u003dDecember 3, 2011]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/mar/10/top-gear-jeremy-clarkson-suspended-bbc-producer, title\u003dJeremy Clarkson suspended by BBC over \u0027fracas\u0027 with Top Gear producer, author\u003dJane Martinson, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11463383/Jeremy-Clarkson-suspended-after-punching-Top-Gear-producer-in-row-over-catering.html, title\u003dJeremy Clarkson suspended after \u0027punching Top Gear producer in row over catering\u0027, author\u003dGordon Rayner, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dMarch 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31828184, title\u003dJeremy Clarkson \u0027punch\u0027: Top Gear episodes to be dropped, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Jeremy_Clarkson","description":"Jeremy Clarkson"},{"id":"BBC","description":"BBC"},{"id":"India","description":"India"},{"id":"Mexico","description":"Mexico"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[BBC] TEMPLATE[w, Top Gear (2002 TV series), Top Gear]TEMPLATE[image, Ed Perchick] Jeremy Clarkson, one of the presenters on the BBC\u0027s motoring programme \u0027TEMPLATE[w, Top Gear (2002 TV series), Top Gear]\u0027 has been suspended by the corporation. Clarkson, responsible for several prior controversies, was suspended Tuesday, after allegedly \u0027punching\u0027 a producer last week. The next two episodes of \u0027Top Gear\u0027 have been pulled from broadcast, with a third \u0026mdash; the season finale \u0026mdash; also unlikely to be shown.","The incident leading to Clarkson\u0027s suspension reportedly occurred after an argument with a producer. After filming had finished in TEMPLATE[w, Newcastle], it is believed Clarkson, 54 punched 36-year-old producer Oisin Tymon over a lack of catering availability. The incident was reported to the BBC on Monday. A source spoke to the British newspaper The TEMPLATE[w, Daily Mirror] about the incident. They said, \"They came to the end of filming after a long day and Jeremy discovered that no food had been laid on. He just saw red and hit the assistant producer, who he blamed for not having organised the food. He snapped.\"","However a source close to the suspended presenter defended him saying \"he didn\u0027t punch anyone\".","The BBC released a short statement clarifying the situation. It said \"Following a fracas with a BBC producer, Jeremy Clarkson has been suspended pending an investigation. No one else has been suspended. Top Gear will not be broadcast this Sunday. The BBC will be making no further comment at this time.\"","Previously Clarkson had been given a \"final warning\" by BBC bosses over comments he had made. In 2014 it appeared that the presenter used a racist term while singing a nursery rhyme, he apologised after the incident came to light. He also caused offence with comments he made about India and Mexico as well as comments about people with special needs.","\u0027Top Gear\u0027 is a motoring programme shown on BBC Two in the United Kingdom. Clarkson has presented the show since 2002, co-hosting alongside TEMPLATE[w, Richard Hammond] and TEMPLATE[w, James May]. He is one of the BBC\u0027s highest paid stars.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:BBC","description":"Category:BBC"},{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Jeremy_Clarkson","description":"Category:Jeremy Clarkson"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 11, 2015"]},{"name":"BBC","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Top Gear (2002 TV series)","Top Gear"]},{"name":"image","description":["Ed Perchick"]},{"name":"w","description":["Top Gear (2002 TV series)","Top Gear"]},{"name":"w","description":["Newcastle"]},{"name":"w","description":["Daily Mirror"]},{"name":"w","description":["Richard Hammond"]},{"name":"w","description":["James May"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003d\u0027Have them all shot\u0027: BBC gets 21,000+ complaints over Jeremy Clarkson\u0027s public sector striker comments","date\u003dDecember 3, 2011"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/media/2015/mar/10/top-gear-jeremy-clarkson-suspended-bbc-producer","title\u003dJeremy Clarkson suspended by BBC over \u0027fracas\u0027 with Top Gear producer","author\u003dJane Martinson","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11463383/Jeremy-Clarkson-suspended-after-punching-Top-Gear-producer-in-row-over-catering.html","title\u003dJeremy Clarkson suspended after \u0027punching Top Gear producer in row over catering\u0027","author\u003dGordon Rayner","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dMarch 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31828184","title\u003dJeremy Clarkson \u0027punch\u0027: Top Gear episodes to be dropped","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"South African TV journalist mugged while preparing for live broadcast","wikiTitle":"South_African_TV_journalist_mugged_while_preparing_for_live_broadcast","wid":1983903,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-21T13:53:15Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31831824, title\u003dSouth Africa TV presenter Vuyo Mvoko mugged on camera, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://mg.co.za/article/2015-03-10-sabcs-vuyo-mvoko-and-crew-mugged-seconds-before-live-crossing, title\u003dSABC\u0027s Vuyo Mvoko and crew mugged on camera, author\u003d, pub\u003dMail and Guardian Africa, date\u003dMarch 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Johannesburg","description":"Johannesburg"},{"id":"South_Africa","description":"South Africa"},{"id":"Zambia","description":"Zambian"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 13, 2015] TEMPLATE[South_Africa] TEMPLATE[w, South African Broadcasting Corporation, SABC]TEMPLATE[image, Zaian] On Wednesday, Vuyo Mvoko, a television journalist, was mugged moments before he was due to start a live broadcast in Johannesburg, South Africa. During the incident, two men approached Mvoko and demanded his mobile phone while he stood near the TEMPLATE[w, Milpark hospital]. When Mvoko refused to hand over the phone he was reportedly threatened with a gun. Video footage caught the mugging and has been publicly released.","In the video, the perpetrators never appeared to look at the camera. The assailants escaped with mobile phones and laptops. Police have announced that officers are investigating the mugging. During a later interview, Mvoko spoke about the incident. He said, \"It was like seconds to air and then the commotion started... I couldn\u0027t understand why they\u0027d walk right in front of the camera because the light is on and they could see that - and our car is branded, so they could see that this is a live broadcast -- because I wasn\u0027t giving him the phone, he then called the other one who had a gun, and said: \u0027Dubula le nja.\u0027 [Shoot this dog].\"","The TEMPLATE[w, South African National Editors\u0027 Forum] released a statement relating to the mugging, saying \"Every South African lives with the reality of crime, but to see thugs brazenly ignoring television cameras and robbing media workers in the course of their work, yet again brings home the level of criminality in our society.\" The broadcast was taking place to report the arrival of TEMPLATE[w, Edgar Lungu], the Zambian President who arrived in South Africa for medical tests after he collapsed last week.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:South_Africa","description":"Category:South Africa"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Johannesburg","description":"Category:Johannesburg"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:Zambia","description":"Category:Zambia"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 13, 2015"]},{"name":"South_Africa","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["South African Broadcasting Corporation","SABC"]},{"name":"image","description":["Zaian"]},{"name":"w","description":["Milpark hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["South African National Editors\u0027 Forum"]},{"name":"w","description":["Edgar Lungu"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-31831824","title\u003dSouth Africa TV presenter Vuyo Mvoko mugged on camera","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://mg.co.za/article/2015-03-10-sabcs-vuyo-mvoko-and-crew-mugged-seconds-before-live-crossing","title\u003dSABC\u0027s Vuyo Mvoko and crew mugged on camera","author\u003d","pub\u003dMail and Guardian Africa","date\u003dMarch 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Ian Holloway sacked as manager of Millwall F.C.","wikiTitle":"Ian_Holloway_sacked_as_manager_of_Millwall_F.C.","wid":1984595,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-22T20:41:49Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/31833672, title\u003dMillwall: Ian Holloway sacking \u0027no surprise\u0027, says Matt Lawrence, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC Sport, date\u003dMarch 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www1.skysports.com/football/news/30964/9752487/millwall-have-sacked-manager-ian-holloway, title\u003dMillwall sack manager Ian Holloway, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky Sports, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/mar/10/millwall-ian-holloway-neil-harris, title\u003dMillwall sack Ian Holloway and install Neil Harris until end of season, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.millwallfc.co.uk/news/article/millwall-ian-holloway-neil-harris-2325508.aspx, title\u003dClub statement - Lions part company with Ian Holloway, author\u003d, pub\u003dMillwall Football Club, date\u003dMarch 10, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[football] TEMPLATE[image, Brian Minkoff] TEMPLATE[w, Ian Holloway] has been sacked as manager of TEMPLATE[w, Millwall F.C., Millwall football club]. His sacking, announced on Tuesday, has come after a 1\u0026ndash;4 defeat to TEMPLATE[w, Norwich City F.C]. on March 7. He had managed Millwall since January 2014. Former player TEMPLATE[w, Neil Harris (footballer, born 1977), Neil Harris] has been placed in charge until season\u0027s end.","An official statement was released by club chairman TEMPLATE[w, John Berylson]. He said \"This was a hard decision to take because we very much hoped that Ollie would prove to be the man to take us forward and on to the next level. I would like to thank him for his efforts, and in particular for keeping us in the Championship last May.\" He added \"Ian Holloway remains a fine manager and it was his impressive track record which led us to appoint him some 14 months ago. However, our view is that the decision to part company at this stage is in the best interests of the football club going forward.\"","At the time of Holloway\u0027s departure Millwall sat in 23rd position of the TEMPLATE[w, Football League Championship], the second tier of English football. They were eight points away from TEMPLATE[w, Promotion and relegation, safety]. Holloway, 51, was in charge of Millwall for 62 games; during his tenure they won only 14 times, losing 29 and drawing the remaining 19.","Former Millwall player TEMPLATE[w, Matthew Lawrence (footballer), Matt Lawrence] spoke to TEMPLATE[w, BBC London 94.9] about Holloway\u0027s sacking and offered his opinion. He said \"I think everybody knew this was coming. Most people are surprised it has taken this long[...] The fans completely turned and the minute you lose the fans your time is up and it is time to move on.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 14, 2015"]},{"name":"football","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Brian Minkoff"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ian Holloway"]},{"name":"w","description":["Millwall F.C.","Millwall football club"]},{"name":"w","description":["Norwich City 