{"title":"Best selling British author Sir Terry Pratchett dies, aged 66","wikiTitle":"Best_selling_British_author_Sir_Terry_Pratchett_dies,_aged_66","wid":1987211,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-23T13:35:31Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dGood Omens to be made into BBC radio drama, date\u003dSeptember 7, 2014]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dDiscworld author films his battle with Alzheimer\u0027s, date\u003dJanuary 31, 2009]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31858156, title\u003dSir Terry Pratchett, renowned fantasy author, dies aged 66, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/books/2015/mar/12/terry-pratchett-author-of-the-discworld-series-dies-aged-66, title\u003dTerry Pratchett, author of the Discworld series, dies aged 66, author\u003dCaroline Davies, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 12, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] TEMPLATE[image, [https://www.flickr.com/people/firepile/ Robin Zebrowski]] British author TEMPLATE[w, Terry Pratchett], best known for the TEMPLATE[w, Discworld] series of TEMPLATE[w, Fantasy literature, fantasy novels], has died at the age of 66. Pratchett was diagnosed with a rare form of TEMPLATE[w, Alzheimer\u0027s] in 2007, following his diagnosis he donated to Alzheimer\u0027s charities and became a public face of the disease","Pratchett spoke out for the right of an individual to TEMPLATE[w, euthanasia, assisted suicide]. However, Larry Finlay, of Pratchett\u0027s publisher Transworld, said that the author did not die of suicide but of natural causes at home \"with his cat sleeping on his bed, surrounded by his family,\"","British Prime Minister David Cameron paid tribute to Pratchett. He said \"Sad to hear of Sir Terry Pratchett\u0027s death, his books fired the imagination of millions and he fearlessly campaigned for dementia awareness.\"","A writer since his teens, Pratchett first came to prominence with the Discworld novel TEMPLATE[w, The Colour of Magic] in 1983, and at his peak was publishing three books a year, writing over 70 in total. Alzheimer\u0027s slowed but did not end his writing, with a final novel, the fourth book in the TEMPLATE[w, Long Earth] series due in the summer of 2015. He was knighted for services to literature in 2009.","News of Pratchett\u0027s death was made via his official Twitter account in the persona of TEMPLATE[w, Death (Discworld), Death], a character in many of his novels, with the tweet: \"AT LAST, SIR TERRY, WE MUST WALK TOGETHER.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Literature","description":"Category:Literature"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 14, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[https://www.flickr.com/people/firepile/ Robin Zebrowski]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Terry Pratchett"]},{"name":"w","description":["Discworld"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fantasy literature","fantasy novels"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alzheimer\u0027s"]},{"name":"w","description":["euthanasia","assisted suicide"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Colour of Magic"]},{"name":"w","description":["Long Earth"]},{"name":"w","description":["Death (Discworld)","Death"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dGood Omens to be made into BBC radio drama","date\u003dSeptember 7, 2014"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dDiscworld author films his battle with Alzheimer\u0027s","date\u003dJanuary 31, 2009"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-31858156","title\u003dSir Terry Pratchett, renowned fantasy author, dies aged 66","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/books/2015/mar/12/terry-pratchett-author-of-the-discworld-series-dies-aged-66","title\u003dTerry Pratchett, author of the Discworld series, dies aged 66","author\u003dCaroline Davies","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Convicted murderer J.C.X. Simon dies in prison, aged 69","wikiTitle":"Convicted_murderer_J.C.X._Simon_dies_in_prison,_aged_69","wid":1990932,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-24T03:43:06Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/zebra-killer-j-c-x-simon-found-dead-prison-cell-n323401, title\u003d\u0027Zebra Killer\u0027 J.C.X. Simon Found Dead in Prison Cell, author\u003dJillian Sederholm, pub\u003dNBC News, date\u003dMarch 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-zebra-killer-jcx-simon-dead-20150313-story.html, title\u003d\u0027Zebra Killer\u0027 J.C.X. Simon found dead in San Quentin prison cell, author\u003dLee Romney, pub\u003dLos Angeles Times, date\u003dMarch 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.mercurynews.com/breaking-news/ci_27707926/zebra-killer-inmate-jcx-simon-found-dead-san, title\u003d\u0027Zebra killer\u0027 inmate JCX Simon found dead in San Quentin prison cell, author\u003d, pub\u003dSan Jose Mercury News, date\u003dMarch 13, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"San_Francisco","description":"San Francisco"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] TEMPLATE[w, San Quentin State Prison]TEMPLATE[image, Jjz3d83] J.C.X Simon, one of the convicted \u0027TEMPLATE[w, Zebra murders, Zebra Killers]\u0027, has died at the age of 69 in TEMPLATE[w, San Quentin State Prison]. His death came shortly before midnight on Thursday, with the cause remaining unknown. Simon was convicted alongside three others for the killing spree known as the \u0027Zebra Killings\u0027 in San Francisco in the 1970s.","A statement released by prison officials said \"The cause of death is unknown pending the results of an autopsy.\" Simon was found unresponsive in his single person cell.","In total fourteen people were killed by Simon and three other assailants, all of whom were black. The murders took place in 1973 and 1974, with all of the victims being white and targeted purely on race. At least seven more victims were injured in the shootings, including future San Francisco mayor TEMPLATE[w, Art Agnos]. According to Anthony C. Harris, the suspects were part of the \u0027Death Angels\u0027, an offshoot of the TEMPLATE[w, Nation of Islam]. Harris was a key witness in the trial, who was alleged to have taken part in the hunt for white victims.","Simon was convicted, and sentenced to life without TEMPLATE[w, parole], in 1976. The charges consisted of two counts of first-degree murder, conspiracy to commit first-degree murder, and assault with a deadly weapon. The other men convicted for the murders were Larry Green, Manuel Moore, and Jessie Lee Cooks. The three remaining convicts remain incarcerated without possibility of parole.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Serial_killers","description":"Category:Serial killers"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:San_Francisco,_California","description":"Category:San Francisco, California"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:California","description":"Category:California"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["San Quentin State Prison"]},{"name":"image","description":["Jjz3d83"]},{"name":"w","description":["Zebra murders","Zebra Killers"]},{"name":"w","description":["San Quentin State Prison"]},{"name":"w","description":["Art Agnos"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nation of Islam"]},{"name":"w","description":["parole"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/zebra-killer-j-c-x-simon-found-dead-prison-cell-n323401","title\u003d\u0027Zebra Killer\u0027 J.C.X. Simon Found Dead in Prison Cell","author\u003dJillian Sederholm","pub\u003dNBC News","date\u003dMarch 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.latimes.com/local/lanow/la-me-ln-zebra-killer-jcx-simon-dead-20150313-story.html","title\u003d\u0027Zebra Killer\u0027 J.C.X. Simon found dead in San Quentin prison cell","author\u003dLee Romney","pub\u003dLos Angeles Times","date\u003dMarch 13, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.mercurynews.com/breaking-news/ci_27707926/zebra-killer-inmate-jcx-simon-found-dead-san","title\u003d\u0027Zebra killer\u0027 inmate JCX Simon found dead in San Quentin prison cell","author\u003d","pub\u003dSan Jose Mercury News","date\u003dMarch 13, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Xu Caihou, former Chinese general, dies aged 71","wikiTitle":"Xu_Caihou,_former_Chinese_general,_dies_aged_71","wid":1993465,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-27T19:52:16Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1738760/former-chinese-general-xu-caihou-dies-cancer, title\u003dChina\u0027s former PLA number 2 Xu Caihou dies of cancer amid graft probe, author\u003d, pub\u003dSouth China Morning Post, date\u003dMarch 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/15/us-china-corruption-idUSKBN0MB0TX20150315, title\u003dDisgraced former top Chinese officer dies of cancer: Xinhua, author\u003dBen Blanchard, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dMarch 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.startribune.com/world/296369371.html, title\u003dFormer top Chinese military official Xu Caihou, facing bribery investigation, dies of cancer, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dStar Tribune, date\u003dMarch 15, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"China","description":"Chinese"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 16, 2015] TEMPLATE[China] TEMPLATE[image, R. D. Ward] TEMPLATE[w, Xu Caihou], a former Chinese general who was once the second in command within the TEMPLATE[w, People\u0027s Liberation Army], died yesterday, according to Chinese state news agency TEMPLATE[w, Xinhua]. Xu, 71, was due to be prosecuted over TEMPLATE[w, bribery] charges. The cause of death was announced as TEMPLATE[w, bladder cancer, bladder] TEMPLATE[w, cancer].","In 2012 Xu resigned from the executive committee of the TEMPLATE[w, Communist Party of China, Communist Party].  In 2013 he retired from the position of TEMPLATE[w, Central Military Commission (China), Central Military Commission] Vice Chairman.  In June last year, despite no charges announced against Xu at the time, his general\u0027s rank was revoked.","The government said they started investigating Xu last March over claims of corruption and in October he admitted to accepting \"massive\" bribes as payment in assisting people to gain promotions. Due to his death the charges against him are to be dropped but anything gained illegally by Xu is to be dealt with under Chinese law.","Military officials have been investigated more regularly in recent years as the Chinese government try to crack down on army corruption.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:China","description":"Category:China"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Cancer","description":"Category:Cancer"},{"id":"Category:Disease","description":"Category:Disease"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 16, 2015"]},{"name":"China","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["R. D. Ward"]},{"name":"w","description":["Xu Caihou"]},{"name":"w","description":["People\u0027s Liberation Army"]},{"name":"w","description":["Xinhua"]},{"name":"w","description":["bribery"]},{"name":"w","description":["bladder cancer","bladder"]},{"name":"w","description":["cancer"]},{"name":"w","description":["Communist Party of China","Communist Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Central Military Commission (China)","Central Military Commission"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1738760/former-chinese-general-xu-caihou-dies-cancer","title\u003dChina\u0027s former PLA number 2 Xu Caihou dies of cancer amid graft probe","author\u003d","pub\u003dSouth China Morning Post","date\u003dMarch 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/15/us-china-corruption-idUSKBN0MB0TX20150315","title\u003dDisgraced former top Chinese officer dies of cancer: Xinhua","author\u003dBen Blanchard","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dMarch 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.startribune.com/world/296369371.html","title\u003dFormer top Chinese military official Xu Caihou, facing bribery investigation, dies of cancer","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dStar Tribune","date\u003dMarch 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"54 dead after bus crash in southern Brazil","wikiTitle":"54_dead_after_bus_crash_in_southern_Brazil","wid":1993819,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-07-09T01:34:16Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-31899506, title\u003dBrazil bus crash: At least 49 killed on way to religious event, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0315/687193-brazil/, title\u003dDeath toll in Brazil bus crash rises to 54, author\u003d, pub\u003dRTE News, date\u003dMarch 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://rt.com/news/240837-brazil-tourist-bus-accident/, title\u003d54 dead as tourist bus plunges into ravine in Brazil, author\u003d, pub\u003dRussia Today, date\u003dMarch 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/03/15/americas/brazil-deadly-bus-crash/, title\u003d50 die after bus plunges off road in southern Brazil, author\u003dBrian Walker and Ben Brumfield, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMarch 15, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Brazil","description":"Brazil"},{"id":"Dilma_Rousseff","description":"Dilma Rousseff"},{"id":"World_Health_Organisation","description":"World Health Organisation"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 16, 2015] TEMPLATE[Brazil] TEMPLATE[correction, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015, explanation\u003dThis article accurately reflects what was at the time believed to be the correct death toll. That has since been revised downwards to 51.] A bus carrying 60 passengers to a religious event in the TEMPLATE[w, Santa Catarina (state), Santa Catarina] state of Brazil plunged over a cliff on Saturday evening. The driver reportedly lost control whilst approaching a curve, leading the bus to fall 400 metres into a wooded area just ten kilometres away from TEMPLATE[w, Joinville], the final destination. Whilst the cause of the accident is not yet confirmed, police believe that the brakes on the vehicle may have failed.","Approximately 100 rescue workers, plus fifteen ambulances and a helicopter were on the scene; although, the accident happened at nightfall making access to the area difficult. President Dilma Rousseff expressed her condolences upon hearing the news, saying: \"In this hour of pain of suffering, I want to extend my sympathies to the families and friends who have lost their dear ones.\"","The roads that wind through the Dona Francisca mountain range are notoriously dangerous, with 110 fatalities on these roads in the past five years, according to police. Throughout the nation, with the World Health Organisation stating 43,000 people die annually in accidents on the congested and poorly maintained roads.","The first funerals for the recovered victims are to take place Monday.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Brazil","description":"Category:Brazil"},{"id":"Category:South_America","description":"Category:South America"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Dilma_Rousseff","description":"Category:Dilma Rousseff"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Brazil","description":[]},{"name":"correction","description":["date\u003dAugust 24, 2015","explanation\u003dThis article accurately reflects what was at the time believed to be the correct death toll. That has since been revised downwards to 51."]},{"name":"w","description":["Santa Catarina (state)","Santa Catarina"]},{"name":"w","description":["Joinville"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-latin-america-31899506","title\u003dBrazil bus crash: At least 49 killed on way to religious event","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.rte.ie/news/2015/0315/687193-brazil/","title\u003dDeath toll in Brazil bus crash rises to 54","author\u003d","pub\u003dRTE News","date\u003dMarch 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://rt.com/news/240837-brazil-tourist-bus-accident/","title\u003d54 dead as tourist bus plunges into ravine in Brazil","author\u003d","pub\u003dRussia Today","date\u003dMarch 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/03/15/americas/brazil-deadly-bus-crash/","title\u003d50 die after bus plunges off road in southern Brazil","author\u003dBrian Walker and Ben Brumfield","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMarch 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["date","explanation","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Lindt cafe in Sydney reopens after siege","wikiTitle":"Lindt_cafe_in_Sydney_reopens_after_siege","wid":2010199,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-05-14T21:28:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-20/lindt-cafe-in-martin-place-reopens-after-deadly-siege/6334154, title\u003d Lindt cafe in Sydney\u0027s Martin Place reopens after deadly siege, author\u003d Johanna Nicholson, pub\u003d ABC News (Australia), date\u003d March 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://globalnews.ca/news/1893306/sydney-cafe-reopens-3-months-after-deadly-siege/, title\u003d Sydney cafe reopens 3 months after deadly siege, author\u003d (TEMPLATE), pub\u003d Global News, date\u003d March 19, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Sydney","description":"Sydney"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"New_South_Wales","description":"New South Wales"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] The TEMPLATE[w, Lindt \u0026 SprÃ¼ngli, Lindt] cafe in Sydney, Australia reopened on Friday, after a siege at the cafe three months ago killed one of its employees, Tori Johnson, and a customer, Katrina Dawson.","On December 15, the cafe was taken hostage by a gunman, TEMPLATE[w, Man Haron Monis]. The siege lasted for over sixteen hours until the gunman was taken down. On Friday the cafe had its reopening with Joel Herat, one of the survivors of the siege, back at work.","Two plaques, in the honor of the employee and customer who died, were put up at the front door entrance. The CEO of Lindt Australia, Steve Loane, praised the reopening. A note on a flower bouquet outside the entrance read, \"The light shines in the darkness and darkness has never put it out.\" Herat said \"It was extremely important for me to be here and support Lindt and support the people I work with.\"","Herat also notes of Tori Johnson, the manager of the cafe who was killed during the hostage situation, \"He was the first person who\u0027d come and greet me at the door, so that\u0027ll take a long time to adjust to\". The premier of New South Wales, TEMPLATE[w, Mike Baird], attended the reopening too. He said, \"They [cafe staff] are there because they believe in those who went through what they did\". The premier also praised Herat.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:_Australia","description":"Category: Australia"},{"id":"Category:_Sydney","description":"Category: Sydney"},{"id":"Category:_Oceania","description":"Category: Oceania"},{"id":"Category:_Crime_and_law","description":"Category: Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:_Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category: Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:New_South_Wales","description":"Category:New South Wales"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Baird","description":"Category:Mike Baird"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 22, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Lindt \u0026 SprÃ¼ngli","Lindt"]},{"name":"w","description":["Man Haron Monis"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mike Baird"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-03-20/lindt-cafe-in-martin-place-reopens-after-deadly-siege/6334154","title\u003d Lindt cafe in Sydney\u0027s Martin Place reopens after deadly siege","author\u003d Johanna Nicholson","pub\u003d ABC News (Australia)","date\u003d March 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://globalnews.ca/news/1893306/sydney-cafe-reopens-3-months-after-deadly-siege/","title\u003d Sydney cafe reopens 3 months after deadly siege","author\u003d (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003d Global News","date\u003d March 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Singapore\u0027s \u0027founding father\u0027 Lee Kuan Yew dies aged 91","wikiTitle":"Singapore\u0027s_\u0027founding_father\u0027_Lee_Kuan_Yew_dies_aged_91","wid":2018130,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-03-31T15:00:12Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/23/us-singapore-leekuanyew-idUSKBN0MI08Y20150323, title\u003dLee Kuan Yew, founding father of modern Singapore, dies at 91, author\u003dRujun Shen, Lee Rou Urn, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dMarch 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-32014307, title\u003dSingapore mourns founding father Lee Kuan Yew, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/lee-kuan-yew-dead-founder-of-modern-singapore-dies-age-91-10126515.html, title\u003dLee Kuan Yew dead: Founder of modern Singapore dies aged 91, author\u003dIan Johnston, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMarch 22, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Lee_Kuan_Yew","description":"Lee Kuan Yew"},{"id":"Singapore","description":"Singapore"},{"id":"Lee_Hsien_Loong","description":"Lee Hsien Loong"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"Barack_Obama","description":"Barack Obama"},{"id":"Xi_Jinping","description":"Xi Jinping"},{"id":"China","description":"Chinese"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 24, 2015] TEMPLATE[Singapore] TEMPLATE[image, Robert D. Ward] Lee Kuan Yew, the first TEMPLATE[w, Prime Minister of Singapore, Prime Minister] of Singapore, has died at the age of 91. Considered the \"founding father\" of Singapore, Lee led Singapore through the aftermath of independence to become one of the world\u0027s richest nations. He died yesterday under treatment for TEMPLATE[w, pneumonia] at the TEMPLATE[w, Singapore General Hospital].","The current Prime Minister of Singapore, Lee Hsien Loong, announced the former Prime Minister\u0027s death in a televised statement. Prime Minister Lee, who is the eldest son of Lee Kuan Yew, said \"The first of our founding fathers is no more. He inspired us, gave us courage, and brought us here[...]  To many Singaporeans, and indeed others too, Lee Kuan Yew was Singapore.\"","More tributes came from within Singapore and around the world. The TEMPLATE[w, President of the United States, President] of the United States, Barack Obama, called Lee \"a true giant of history.\" Xi Jinping, the Chinese TEMPLATE[w, President of the People\u0027s Republic of China, President], said \"Lee Kwan Yew\u0027s passing is as much a loss for the international community as it is for Singapore\".","Lee, co-founder of the TEMPLATE[w, People\u0027s Action Party], was the nation\u0027s first Prime Minister from 1959 continuously to 1990. Despite no longer holding the office he remained highly involved within Singaporean politics until his death. He was both admired and criticized throughout the world during his rule.","He was condemned by opponents over many of his strict home policies. During his tenure the press and media was strictly controlled and TEMPLATE[w, chewing gum] was banned. He was however highly regarded for his financial tact, leading Singapore to vast financial success through his economic policies.","Lee defended his tough stance in a 2010 TEMPLATE[w, New York Times] interview, saying \"I\u0027m not saying everything I did was right[...] But everything I did was for an honourable purpose.\" He admitted to ordering \"nasty things\" such as âlocking fellows up without trial.\"","A period of national mourning has begun and his body is to lie in state from Wednesday until Saturday. A state funeral for Lee is to take place on Sunday, followed by private services on Monday and Tuesday. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Singapore","description":"Category:Singapore"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Lee_Hsien_Loong","description":"Category:Lee Hsien Loong"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Lee_Kuan_Yew","description":"Category:Lee Kuan Yew"},{"id":"Category:Xi_Jinping","description":"Category:Xi Jinping"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Singapore","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Robert D. Ward"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prime Minister of Singapore","Prime Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["pneumonia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Singapore General Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["President of the United States","President"]},{"name":"w","description":["President of the People\u0027s Republic of China","President"]},{"name":"w","description":["People\u0027s Action Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["chewing gum"]},{"name":"w","description":["New York Times"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/03/23/us-singapore-leekuanyew-idUSKBN0MI08Y20150323","title\u003dLee Kuan Yew, founding father of modern Singapore, dies at 91","author\u003dRujun Shen, Lee Rou Urn","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dMarch 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-32014307","title\u003dSingapore mourns founding father Lee Kuan Yew","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/news/lee-kuan-yew-dead-founder-of-modern-singapore-dies-age-91-10126515.html","title\u003dLee Kuan Yew dead: Founder of modern Singapore dies aged 91","author\u003dIan Johnston","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dMarch 22, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Germanwings Flight 9525 crashes into French Alps, 150 on board","wikiTitle":"Germanwings_Flight_9525_crashes_into_French_Alps,_150_on_board","wid":2020214,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-10T00:13:20Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-32030270, title\u003dGermanwings plane 4U 9525 crashes in French Alps - no survivors, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/24/germanwings-plane-black-box-found-as-investigators-reach-crash-site, title\u003dGermanwings plane black box found as mystery surrounds Alps crash, author\u003dKim Willsher, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.express.co.uk/news/world/566001/Plane-crash-horror-two-babies-among-150-dead-in-Germanwings-Alps-crash, title\u003dLATEST: Britons \u0027likely\u0027 to be among 150 dead on stricken Germanwings plane, author\u003dAlix Culbertson, pub\u003dDaily Express, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Airbus","description":"Airbus"},{"id":"Germany","description":"Germany"},{"id":"Spain","description":"Spain"},{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"FranÃ§ois Hollande"},{"id":"Angela_Merkel","description":"Angela Merkel"},{"id":"Germanwings","description":"Germanwings"},{"id":"Lufthansa","description":"Lufthansa"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 25, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] TEMPLATE[w, BarcelonaâEl Prat Airport, Barcelona Airport]TEMPLATE[image, Sebastian Mortier] TEMPLATE[w, Germanwings Flight 9525], an Airbus TEMPLATE[w, Airbus A320, A320] carrying 150 passengers and crew, crashed into the TEMPLATE[w, French Alps] yesterday between TEMPLATE[w, Digne] and TEMPLATE[w, Barcelonnette]. Officials said there were no survivors. The plane was flying to TEMPLATE[w, Duesseldorf], Germany from TEMPLATE[w, Barcelona], Spain. An emergency recovery team made its way to the crash site and reportedly recovered one of the plane\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, flight recorder, flight recorders].","According to French authorities, 144 passengers were aboard the plane, reportedly including sixteen school children who were travelling on a German exchange project. A further six crew were present, including the two pilots. The flight was predominately made up of Spanish and German citizens.","The pilots did not send a distress signal. Various officials described the crash as an accident; the TEMPLATE[w, White House] stated terrorism is not believed to be a factor. The weather reportedly was clear when the crash occurred. The plane descended for eight minutes before impact falling, by various reports, more than 30,000 TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), feet].","French President FranÃ§ois Hollande said regarding the accident \"I would like to send all our solidarity to the family of the victims[...] It\u0027s a new air tragedy; we must know all the causes. We are in mourning because this accident happened on our territory\". He said he has been in contact with both German Chancellor Angela Merkel and King TEMPLATE[w, Felipe VI of Spain], the later of whom cancelled the remainder of his state visit to France.","According to French prosecutor Bruce Robin the plane was completely destroyed. He said \"The body of the plane is in a state of destruction, there is not one intact piece of wing or fuselage\". He made the comments to TEMPLATE[w, Reuters] news agency describing his view of the crash site from a helicopter.","Germanwings is owned by Lufthansa. CEO of Lufthansa TEMPLATE[w, Carsten Spohr] said  \"We do not yet know what has happened to flight 4U 9525. My deepest sympathy goes to the families and friends of our passengers and crew on 4U 9525. If our fears are confirmed, this is a dark day for Lufthansa. We hope to find survivors.\"","The plane, registered as D-AIPX, had been in service for nearly 25 years. It first flew on November 29, 1990 and had been last checked earlier this month.  TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Lufthansa","description":"Category:Lufthansa"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Spain","description":"Category:Spain"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"Category:FranÃ§ois Hollande"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Angela_Merkel","description":"Category:Angela Merkel"},{"id":"Category:Germanwings","description":"Category:Germanwings"},{"id":"Category:Germanwings_Flight_9525","description":"Category:Germanwings Flight 9525"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["BarcelonaâEl Prat Airport","Barcelona Airport"]},{"name":"image","description":["Sebastian Mortier"]},{"name":"w","description":["Germanwings Flight 9525"]},{"name":"w","description":["Airbus A320","A320"]},{"name":"w","description":["French Alps"]},{"name":"w","description":["Digne"]},{"name":"w","description":["Barcelonnette"]},{"name":"w","description":["Duesseldorf"]},{"name":"w","description":["Barcelona"]},{"name":"w","description":["flight recorder","flight recorders"]},{"name":"w","description":["White House"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","feet"]},{"name":"w","description":["Felipe VI of Spain"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reuters"]},{"name":"w","description":["Carsten Spohr"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-32030270","title\u003dGermanwings plane 4U 9525 crashes in French Alps - no survivors","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/24/germanwings-plane-black-box-found-as-investigators-reach-crash-site","title\u003dGermanwings plane black box found as mystery surrounds Alps crash","author\u003dKim Willsher","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.express.co.uk/news/world/566001/Plane-crash-horror-two-babies-among-150-dead-in-Germanwings-Alps-crash","title\u003dLATEST: Britons \u0027likely\u0027 to be among 150 dead on stricken Germanwings plane","author\u003dAlix Culbertson","pub\u003dDaily Express","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"British singer Lil\u0027 Chris found dead aged 24","wikiTitle":"British_singer_Lil\u0027_Chris_found_dead_aged_24","wid":2020487,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-04T18:28:17Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3009454/Channel-4-s-Rock-School-star-Lil-Chris-dies-aged-24.html, title\u003dTragedy as Lil\u0027 Chris - star of Channel 4 reality show Rock School - is found dead aged 24, author\u003dHanna Flint, Steph Cockroft, pub\u003dMail Online, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-suffolk-32038895, title\u003dRock School star Lil\u0027 Chris found dead in Lowestoft, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"England","description":"English"},{"id":"Channel_4","description":"Channel 4"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 25, 2015] TEMPLATE[Music] TEMPLATE[w, Lil\u0027 Chris], an English singer and television personality, died on Monday, police reported that day. The 24-year-old Chris Hardman was found dead at an address in TEMPLATE[w, Lowestoft], TEMPLATE[w, Suffolk]. TEMPLATE[w, Suffolk Constabulary, Suffolk Police] said they were not treating it as a suspicious death. Hardman came to fame as Lil\u0027 Chris after appearing on the Channel 4 reality television show TEMPLATE[w, Rock School].","Rock School in 2006 featured a student rock band that TEMPLATE[w, KISS (band), KISS] frontman TEMPLATE[w, Gene Simmons] created. Hardman was chosen to be the bands lead singer by Simmons. Speaking to TEMPLATE[w, The Daily Mirror], Simmons paid tribute to Hardman. He said \"Lil Chris was a kind, little soul. I will greatly miss his smile and his spirit. I knew there was something special about him as soon as I met him\".","More tributes came from other celebrities. TEMPLATE[w, McFly] band member TEMPLATE[w, Dougie Poynter] paid tribute to Hardman on TEMPLATE[w, Instagram]; he posted alongside a photograph of him, \"So sad to hear about Lil Chris. He was such a genuinely sweet and funny guy, we had some awesome times. Our thoughts go out to his family and friends.\" Boxer TEMPLATE[w, Anthony Ogogo] praised him as a \"super-talented kid\"; Ogogo and Hardman both went to Kirkley High School.","Hardman\u0027s most successful hit was TEMPLATE[w, Checkin\u0027 It Out], his debut single in 2006, which made it to number three on the TEMPLATE[w, UK Singles Chart]. He released his last album in 2008 but had recently announced plans of a musical comeback on Twitter.","Prior to his death Hardman had spoken about his battle with depression on Twitter. He once tweeted \"Depression really sucks. Learning how to notice it can save lives and your own feelings at times. Take time to understand it, for everybody.\" Since his death has been announced the suicide helpline charity TEMPLATE[w, Samaritans (charity), The Samaritans] have released a statement. They said \"If anyone has been affected by this news, or is struggling to cope, we would like to let people know that Samaritans is here for them if they need to talk.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Mental_health","description":"Category:Mental health"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Music","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Lil\u0027 Chris"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lowestoft"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suffolk"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suffolk Constabulary","Suffolk Police"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rock School"]},{"name":"w","description":["KISS (band)","KISS"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gene Simmons"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Daily Mirror"]},{"name":"w","description":["McFly"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dougie Poynter"]},{"name":"w","description":["Instagram"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anthony Ogogo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Checkin\u0027 It Out"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK Singles Chart"]},{"name":"w","description":["Samaritans (charity)","The Samaritans"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/tvshowbiz/article-3009454/Channel-4-s-Rock-School-star-Lil-Chris-dies-aged-24.html","title\u003dTragedy as Lil\u0027 Chris - star of Channel 4 reality show Rock School - is found dead aged 24","author\u003dHanna Flint, Steph Cockroft","pub\u003dMail Online","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-suffolk-32038895","title\u003dRock School star Lil\u0027 Chris found dead in Lowestoft","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Rock School]","TEMPLATE[w, The Daily Mirror]","TEMPLATE[w, Checkin\u0027 It Out]"]}
{"title":"Utah reinstates firing squad for death penalty","wikiTitle":"Utah_reinstates_firing_squad_for_death_penalty","wid":2021162,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-10T14:25:00Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/24/utah-reinstates-firing-squad-capital-punishment, title\u003dHuman rights groups call Utah firing squad decision \u0027backward â and backwoods\u0027, author\u003dJoanna Walters and Lauren Gambino, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2015/03/24/official-firing-squads-utah-allowed/70366174/, title\u003dIt\u0027s official: Firing squads in Utah allowed, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dUSA Today, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/24/why-utahs-gruesome-firing-squads-might-not-be-such-a-bad-alternative/?tid\u003dhp_mm\u0026hpid\u003dz3\u0026tid\u003dptv_rellink, title\u003dWhy Utahâs âgruesomeâ firing squads might not be such a bad alternative, author\u003dTerrence McCoy, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dMarch 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-32027751, title\u003dUtah to resume use of firing squad for executions, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 23, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Utah","description":"Utah"},{"id":"death_penalty","description":"execution"},{"id":"capital_punishment","description":"capital punishment"},{"id":"American_Civil_Liberties_Union","description":"American Civil Liberties Union"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] The US state of Utah has reinstated the use of the TEMPLATE[w, firing squad] as the method of execution for prisoners on TEMPLATE[w, sister\u003dwikt, death row], eleven years after it was abolished. On Monday TEMPLATE[w, Gary Herbert], the state\u0027s governor, signed into law legislation approving the firing squad as an alternative means of capital punishment if lethal injections are unavailable.","The new law follows the refusal of European manufacturers of drugs used in lethal injections to sell their products to US prisons, in opposition to capital punishment. It states the decision to use the firing squad could be made thirty days before the scheduled date if lethal injections were not available.","Human rights activists have called the move \"backward\" and \"brutalizing\". Karen McCreary, executive director of the American Civil Liberties Union of Utah said, \"We believe all current methods of capital punishment violate the eighth amendment to the US constitution that outlaws cruel and unusual punishment, but this particular method, firing squad, seems very barbaric and something more associated with war\".","Last July, TEMPLATE[w, U.S Court of Appeals] judge, Alex Kozinski, wrote, \"The firing squad strikes me as the most promising. Eight or ten large-caliber rifle bullets fired at close range can inflict massive damage, causing instant death every time.\" TEMPLATE[w, Jay Chapman], the man who developed the protocol for lethal injections still used today, said in 2007 remarks to TEMPLATE[w, CNN] that lethal injection \"works if it\u0027s administered competently\", but added it does require skill to perform.","The passing of the law on Monday does not grant prisoners a choice on the method of execution they will face, and lethal injections are to remain the primary method of execution.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Utah","description":"Category:Utah"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"},{"id":"Category:ACLU","description":"Category:ACLU"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["firing squad"]},{"name":"w","description":["sister\u003dwikt","death row"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gary Herbert"]},{"name":"w","description":["U.S Court of Appeals"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jay Chapman"]},{"name":"w","description":["CNN"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/24/utah-reinstates-firing-squad-capital-punishment","title\u003dHuman rights groups call Utah firing squad decision \u0027backward â and backwoods\u0027","author\u003dJoanna Walters and Lauren Gambino","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.usatoday.com/story/news/nation-now/2015/03/24/official-firing-squads-utah-allowed/70366174/","title\u003dIt\u0027s official: Firing squads in Utah allowed","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dUSA Today","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/03/24/why-utahs-gruesome-firing-squads-might-not-be-such-a-bad-alternative/?tid\u003dhp_mm\u0026hpid\u003dz3\u0026tid\u003dptv_rellink","title\u003dWhy Utahâs âgruesomeâ firing squads might not be such a bad alternative","author\u003dTerrence McCoy","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dMarch 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-us-canada-32027751","title\u003dUtah to resume use of firing squad for executions","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["sister","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Zayn Malik leaves pop band One Direction after five years","wikiTitle":"Zayn_Malik_leaves_pop_band_One_Direction_after_five_years","wid":2024286,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-05T16:18:51Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/03/25/entertainment/feat-zayn-malik-leaving-one-direction/index.html, title\u003dZayn Malik leaving One Direction, author\u003dTodd Leopold, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMarch 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/business/zayn-malik-leaves-one-direction-8923943, title\u003dZayn Malik leaves One Direction: Hundreds ask for compassionate leave after star quits band, author\u003dAlex Bell, pub\u003dManchester Evening News, date\u003dMarch 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/32057401, title\u003dZayn Malik is leaving One Direction but group continues as four-piece, author\u003dDel Crooks, pub\u003dBBC Newsbeat, date\u003dMarch 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11494944/Zayn-Malik-leaves-One-Direction.html, title\u003dZayn Malik leaves One Direction - as it happened, March 25, 2015, author\u003dCamilla Turner, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dMarch 25, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"UK","description":"British"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[Music] TEMPLATE[image, Eva Rinaldi] TEMPLATE[w, Zayn Malik], one of the members of British pop boy-band TEMPLATE[w, One Direction], has left the group after five years. The band confirmed yesterday that Malik has left the group with a statement on Facebook. They also announced they would continue with the remaining four members and their fifth album would be recorded later this year.","The statement posted on One Direction\u0027s Facebook page said \"After five incredible years Zayn Malik has decided to leave One Direction. TEMPLATE[w, Niall Horan, Niall], TEMPLATE[w, Harry Styles, Harry], TEMPLATE[w, Liam Payne, Liam] and TEMPLATE[w, Louis Tomlinson, Louis] will continue as a four-piece and look forward to the forthcoming concerts of their world tour and recording their fifth album, due to be released later this year\".","Malik, 22, also released a statement through Facebook confirming his departure. He said \"My life with One Direction has been more than I could ever have imagined. But, after five years, I feel like it is now the right time for me to leave the band. I\u0027d like to apologise to the fans if I\u0027ve let anyone down, but I have to do what feels right.\"","After news of Malik\u0027s departure spread fans took to social media to share their disappointment. On Twitter the hashtag #AlwaysInOurHeartsZaynMalik was created and 48,000 comments were left on the statement posted by the band on Facebook. The Employer Advice Service, based at Manchester company Peninsula, said 220 people had called overnight regarding TEMPLATE[wikt, compassionate leave] relating to the news. Speaking to the TEMPLATE[w, Manchester Evening News], employment law director Alan Price said âWhile I sympathise with One Direction fans, I hardly think this qualified as compassionate leave\".","One Direction formed as a group in 2010 after competing as single artists on the British reality music competition TEMPLATE[w, The X Factor (UK series 7), The X Factor]. The band was signed by TEMPLATE[w, Simon Cowell]\u0027s record label after the show, which they finished third on. The remaining members of the group are Harry Styles, Niall Horan, Liam Payne and Louis Tomlinson.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:Television","description":"Category:Television"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Music","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Eva Rinaldi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Zayn Malik"]},{"name":"w","description":["One Direction"]},{"name":"w","description":["Niall Horan","Niall"]},{"name":"w","description":["Harry Styles","Harry"]},{"name":"w","description":["Liam Payne","Liam"]},{"name":"w","description":["Louis Tomlinson","Louis"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["compassionate leave"]},{"name":"w","description":["Manchester Evening News"]},{"name":"w","description":["The X Factor (UK series 7)","The X Factor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Simon Cowell"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/03/25/entertainment/feat-zayn-malik-leaving-one-direction/index.html","title\u003dZayn Malik leaving One Direction","author\u003dTodd Leopold","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMarch 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.manchestereveningnews.co.uk/business/zayn-malik-leaves-one-direction-8923943","title\u003dZayn Malik leaves One Direction: Hundreds ask for compassionate leave after star quits band","author\u003dAlex Bell","pub\u003dManchester Evening News","date\u003dMarch 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/newsbeat/32057401","title\u003dZayn Malik is leaving One Direction but group continues as four-piece","author\u003dDel Crooks","pub\u003dBBC Newsbeat","date\u003dMarch 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11494944/Zayn-Malik-leaves-One-Direction.html","title\u003dZayn Malik leaves One Direction - as it happened, March 25, 2015","author\u003dCamilla Turner","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dMarch 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Manchester Evening News]"]}
{"title":"Officials say co-pilot intentionally crashed Germanwings Airbus","wikiTitle":"Officials_say_co-pilot_intentionally_crashed_Germanwings_Airbus","wid":2025426,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-10T00:12:55Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32081681, title\u003dGermanwings crash: Co-pilot \u0027treated for depression\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/03/26/europe/france-germanwings-plane-crash-main/, title\u003dGermanwings Flight 9525 co-pilot deliberately crashed plane, officials say, author\u003dJosh Levs, Laura Smith-Spark, Holly Yan, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMarch 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Germanwings","description":"Germanwings"},{"id":"airbus","description":"airbus"},{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"Lufthansa","description":"Lufthansa"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 29, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation]  Officials said on Thursday, after analyzing data from the Germanwings TEMPLATE[w, Germanwings Flight 9525, Flight 9525] TEMPLATE[w, cockpit voice recorder], that the airbus crashed into the French TEMPLATE[w, Alps] because its co-pilot deliberately crashed it.","On the TEMPLATE[w, cockpit] voice recorder, the captain can be heard trying to get back into the cockpit.  Transponder data indicates the autopilot was told to descend form 38,000 TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), feet] to 100 feet.  The last part of the recording contains screaming during the sudden decent.","Investigators are still searching for the plane\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, flight data recorder].","The co-pilot started training in 2008, and was diagnosed in 2009 with serious depression according to TEMPLATE[w, BBC News]. Later he completed his training and passed all his tests to pilot, according to Lufthansa chief executive TEMPLATE[w, Carsten Spohr].","In light of this incident, several airlines announced a ban on leaving any one person alone in the cockpit.","The flight path and altitude chart can be seen in the images below.","TEMPLATE[clr]TEMPLATE[Picture_select, width\u003d720px, 1\u003d[[File:4U9525 flight path v1.svg, 4U9525 flight path, 700px, center]] 4U9525 flight path\u003cp\u003eImage: Andrew Heneen\u003cbr /\u003e, 2\u003d[[File:Absturzstelle.png, 4U9525 flight path, 700px, center]] 4U9525 flight path \u003cp\u003e Image: Kopiersperre\u003cbr /\u003e, 3\u003d[[File:Altitude Chart for Flight 4U9525 register D-AIPX.png, Altitude Chart for Flight 4U9525 register D-AIPX, 700px, center]] Altitude Chart for Flight 4U9525 register D-AIPX\u003cp\u003eImage: LÃ¤mpel\u003cbr /\u003e]","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Lufthansa","description":"Category:Lufthansa"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Mental_health","description":"Category:Mental health"},{"id":"Category:Germanwings","description":"Category:Germanwings"},{"id":"Category:Germanwings_Flight_9525","description":"Category:Germanwings Flight 9525"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 29, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Germanwings Flight 9525","Flight 9525"]},{"name":"w","description":["cockpit voice recorder"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alps"]},{"name":"w","description":["cockpit"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","feet"]},{"name":"w","description":["flight data recorder"]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC News"]},{"name":"w","description":["Carsten Spohr"]},{"name":"clr","description":[]},{"name":"Picture_select","description":["width\u003d720px","1\u003d[[File:4U9525 flight path v1.svg","4U9525 flight path","700px","center]]\n4U9525 flight path\u003cp\u003eImage: Andrew Heneen\u003cbr /\u003e","2\u003d[[File:Absturzstelle.png","4U9525 flight path","700px","center]]\n4U9525 flight path \u003cp\u003e Image: Kopiersperre\u003cbr /\u003e","3\u003d[[File:Altitude Chart for Flight 4U9525 register D-AIPX.png","Altitude Chart for Flight 4U9525 register D-AIPX","700px","center]]\nAltitude Chart for Flight 4U9525 register D-AIPX\u003cp\u003eImage: LÃ¤mpel\u003cbr /\u003e"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32081681","title\u003dGermanwings crash: Co-pilot \u0027treated for depression\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/03/26/europe/france-germanwings-plane-crash-main/","title\u003dGermanwings Flight 9525 co-pilot deliberately crashed plane, officials say","author\u003dJosh Levs, Laura Smith-Spark, Holly Yan","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMarch 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["width","1","2","3","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"UK Supreme Court require government to release Prince Charles \u0027black spider\u0027 letters","wikiTitle":"UK_Supreme_Court_require_government_to_release_Prince_Charles_\u0027black_spider\u0027_letters","wid":2025951,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-09T22:47:27Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAttorney General vetos release of Prince Charles correspondence, date\u003dOctober 18, 2012]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/mar/26/supreme-court-clears-way-release-secret-prince-charles-letters-black-spider-memos, title\u003dSupreme court clears way for release of secret Prince Charles letters, author\u003d Rob Evans, Robert Booth and Rowena Mason, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/prince-charles-black-spider-letters-to-be-published-within-weeks-10136889.html, title\u003dPrince Charles\u0027 \u0027black spider\u0027 letters to be published \u0027within weeks\u0027, author\u003dChris Green, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMarch 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evans-v-1-information-commissioner-2-seven-government-departments-2012-ukut-313-aac, title\u003dEvans v (1) Information Commissioner (2) seven Government Departments \u0026#91;2012\u0026#93; UKUT 313 (AAC), author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dGOV.UK, date\u003dOctober 16, 2012]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] TEMPLATE[Image, [http://www.flickr.com/photos/30692593@N07/7597030944 Dan Marsh]] The TEMPLATE[w, Supreme Court of the United Kingdom, Supreme Court] of the TEMPLATE[w, United Kingdom] have concluded yesterday that the government must release a series of 27 letters sent by TEMPLATE[w, Charles, Prince of Wales, Prince Charles] to government ministers and that attempts to prevent their publication under the TEMPLATE[w, Freedom of Information Act 2000] have been unlawful.","The letters were sent to ministers of the previous TEMPLATE[w, Labour Party (UK), Labour] government in the years of 2004 and 2005 and contain advocacy that has been described as \"particularly frank\". TEMPLATE[w, The Guardian] newspaper have been attempting to have these letters released using freedom of information legislation for ten years.","In 2012, the Attorney General TEMPLATE[w, Dominic Grieve] blocked the publication of the letters despite a ruling from the TEMPLATE[w, Upper Tribunal, information tribunal] that the release of the letters is in the public interest. Grieve\u0027s statement at the time argued Prince Charles\u0027 correspondence was \"of very considerable practical benefit\" to his \"preparations for kingship\" as \"such correspondence and dialogue will assist him in fulfilling his duties\". Grieve went on to argue correspondence of this nature \"must be under conditions of confidentiality\" otherwise both the Prince and government ministers \"will feel seriously inhibited from exchanging views candidly and frankly\". The statement from Grieve asserts \"The Prince of Wales is party-political neutral\" and \"it is highly important that he is not considered by the public to favour one political party or another\", but that if the letters were released there would be the risk he would be \"viewed by others as disagreeing with government policy\" and \"such perception would be seriously damaging to his role as future Monarch, because if he forfeits his position of political neutrality as heir to the Throne, he cannot easily recover it when he is King.\"","TEMPLATE[w, David Neuberger, Baron Neuberger of Abbotsbury, Lord Neuberger], in giving the majority decision of the court, stated the Attorney General could not veto the release \"merely because he, a member of the executive, considering the same facts and arguments, takes a different view from that taken by the tribunal or court\". Neuberger said the legislation\u0027s veto power did not go so far as to \"enable a member of the executive to over-ride a judicial decision\" and that the Attorney General \"proceeded on the basis of findings which differed radically from those made by the upper tribunal without real or adequate explanation.\"","Appeal judges had subsequently ruled this veto on the part of the Attorney General to be unlawful, and the further appeal by the government to the Supreme Court has been unsuccessful. The government is required to release the documents within 30 days, although it is possible some of the contents may be redacted.","A spokeswoman for the Prince of Wales stated the ruling is \"a matter for the Government\" but that the Prince is \"disappointed the principle of privacy has not been upheld.\"","Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, David Cameron] said the decision was \"disappointing\": \"This is about the principle that senior members of the Royal Family are able to express their views to government confidentially. I think most people would agree this is fair enough.\"","A spokeswoman for Cameron elaborated: \"The prime minister has been very clear this morning it is a deeply disappointing judgment. He doesn\u0027t agree with it. He thinks whatâs at stake here is an important principle about the ability of senior members of the royal family to express their views to government confidentially. He thinks thatâs a principle that we should uphold. So while we have taken steps in this TEMPLATE[w, UK Parliament, parliament] to strengthen the ability to do that through the FOI act, if there needs to be more done to make that clear, then the prime minister is clear those steps should happen in the next parliament.\"","The legislation was already amended in 2010 to make it so that correspondence and other matters related to the Royal family are exempt from further freedom of information requests. Graham Smith, from TEMPLATE[w, Republic (political organisation), Republic], which campaigns for an elected head of state, argues there needs to be greater transparency over the Royal Family\u0027s affairs: \"The court has defended democratic principles over the interests of the royal family and that needs to be enshrined in law. David Cameronâs response is worrying because he says he wants to tighten up the veto.\"","The Labour MP TEMPLATE[w, Paul Flynn (politician), Paul Flynn] raised the possibility the ruling might have consequences for Charles\u0027 suitability to be King: \"If there are serious questions about the suitability of Prince Charles as a monarch there could be a question in the public mind about whether to skip a generation. The attorney general already said the main justification for keeping the letters secret was they would hinder Charles\u0027s ability to be a successful monarch.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Royalty","description":"Category:Royalty"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Journalism","description":"Category:Journalism"},{"id":"Category:Free_speech","description":"Category:Free speech"},{"id":"Category:Dominic_Grieve","description":"Category:Dominic Grieve"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 27, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"Image","description":["[http://www.flickr.com/photos/30692593@N07/7597030944 Dan Marsh]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Supreme Court of the United Kingdom","Supreme Court"]},{"name":"w","description":["United Kingdom"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles, Prince of Wales","Prince Charles"]},{"name":"w","description":["Freedom of Information Act 2000"]},{"name":"w","description":["Labour Party (UK)","Labour"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Guardian"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dominic Grieve"]},{"name":"w","description":["Upper Tribunal","information tribunal"]},{"name":"w","description":["David Neuberger, Baron Neuberger of Abbotsbury","Lord Neuberger"]},{"name":"w","description":["David Cameron"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK Parliament","parliament"]},{"name":"w","description":["Republic (political organisation)","Republic"]},{"name":"w","description":["Paul Flynn (politician)","Paul Flynn"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dAttorney General vetos release of Prince Charles correspondence","date\u003dOctober 18, 2012"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/mar/26/supreme-court-clears-way-release-secret-prince-charles-letters-black-spider-memos","title\u003dSupreme court clears way for release of secret Prince Charles letters","author\u003d Rob Evans, Robert Booth and Rowena Mason","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/prince-charles-black-spider-letters-to-be-published-within-weeks-10136889.html","title\u003dPrince Charles\u0027 \u0027black spider\u0027 letters to be published \u0027within weeks\u0027","author\u003dChris Green","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dMarch 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.gov.uk/government/publications/evans-v-1-information-commissioner-2-seven-government-departments-2012-ukut-313-aac","title\u003dEvans v (1) Information Commissioner (2) seven Government Departments \u0026#91;2012\u0026#93; UKUT 313 (AAC)","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dGOV.UK","date\u003dOctober 16, 2012"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Guardian]"]}
{"title":"UEFA Euro 2016 qualification match abandoned after brawl in Montenegro","wikiTitle":"UEFA_Euro_2016_qualification_match_abandoned_after_brawl_in_Montenegro","wid":2029217,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-12T19:30:09Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.goal.com/en/news/7157/euro-2016-qualifiers/2015/03/28/10254392/we-look-like-barbarians-montenegro-chief-slams-fans, title\u003d\u0027We look like barbarians\u0027 - Montenegro chief slams fans, author\u003dEnis Koylu, pub\u003dGoal.com, date\u003dMarch 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32096292, title\u003dRussia keeper Akinfeev hit by flare in abandoned Montenegro match, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC Sport, date\u003dMarch 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/russia/11500830/Goalkeeper-hit-by-flare-in-Montenegro-v-Russia.html, title\u003dGoalkeeper Igor Akinfeev hit by flare in Montenegro v Russia, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dMarch 27, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Montenegro","description":"Montenegro"},{"id":"Russia","description":"Russia"},{"id":"Sweden","description":"Sweden"},{"id":"Austria","description":"Austria"},{"id":"Moldova","description":"Moldova"},{"id":"Liechtenstein","description":"Liechtenstein"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 30, 2015] TEMPLATE[Football] TEMPLATE[image, Steindy] The TEMPLATE[w, UEFA Euro 2016] qualification match between Montenegro and Russia on Friday was abandoned after players and coaching staff got involved in a brawl. The match, at Montenegrin capital TEMPLATE[w, Podgorica]\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Podgorica City Stadium, Gradski Stadion], was suspended within the first minute after the Russian goalkeeper was hit with a TEMPLATE[w, flare]. The match re-started after a delay but was called off around the 66th minute when a brawl started.","The flare, thrown from the crowd, hit 28-year-old Russian goalkeeper TEMPLATE[w, Igor Akinfeev] on the back of the head less than 30 seconds after the game had started. The game was suspended and play delayed for 35 minutes after the incident. Akinfeev was substituted with TEMPLATE[w, Yuri Lodygin] coming on in his place. Akinfeev, who plays his domestic football for TEMPLATE[w, CSKA Moscow], suffered a neck injury and minor burns and was taken to a Podgorica hospital.","Disturbances caused a further 18-minute delay in starting the second half. Play resumed and Russia were awarded a penalty on the 66th minute. TEMPLATE[w, Roman Shirokov] saw his penalty saved by TEMPLATE[w, Vukasin Poleksic] and the score remained 0\u0026ndash;0. In the moments after the penalty players and officials from both teams started a brawl on the pitch. The players were led off the TEMPLATE[w, pitch (sports field), pitch], and the crowd was told the game had been called off.","TEMPLATE[w, Football Association of Montenegro, Montenegrin Football Association] general secretary Momir Djurdjevac gave his reaction the the events. He said to TEMPLATE[w, Reuters], \"These fans sing \u0027Montenegro we love you\u0027 but throw flares, insult rivals and cause all sorts of incidents every time they turn up and that\u0027s outright hypocrisy[...] We have left the impression of barbarians and this is a complete disaster. It seems we don\u0027t deserve to have a nation, a football team or a berth in a major tournament. As far as I am concerned the game should not have continued after the first-minute incident. We can only thank God that no one was seriously hurt\".","He also spoke about his fear of the repercussions it could have on Montenegro\u0027s hopes to qualify for Euro 2016. He said \"We will in all likelihood pay a hefty fine and say goodbye to a major tournament but what scares me is that this can happen again.\"","Russia and Montenegro are competing in Group G of the qualification process. They are in the group along side Sweden, Austria, Moldova, and Liechtenstein.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:UEFA_Euro_2016","description":"Category:UEFA Euro 2016"},{"id":"Category:Russia","description":"Category:Russia"},{"id":"Category:Montenegro","description":"Category:Montenegro"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Football","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Steindy"]},{"name":"w","description":["UEFA Euro 2016"]},{"name":"w","description":["Podgorica"]},{"name":"w","description":["Podgorica City Stadium","Gradski Stadion"]},{"name":"w","description":["flare"]},{"name":"w","description":["Igor Akinfeev"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yuri Lodygin"]},{"name":"w","description":["CSKA Moscow"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roman Shirokov"]},{"name":"w","description":["Vukasin Poleksic"]},{"name":"w","description":["pitch (sports field)","pitch"]},{"name":"w","description":["Football Association of Montenegro","Montenegrin Football Association"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reuters"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.goal.com/en/news/7157/euro-2016-qualifiers/2015/03/28/10254392/we-look-like-barbarians-montenegro-chief-slams-fans","title\u003d\u0027We look like barbarians\u0027 - Montenegro chief slams fans","author\u003dEnis Koylu","pub\u003dGoal.com","date\u003dMarch 28, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/32096292","title\u003dRussia keeper Akinfeev hit by flare in abandoned Montenegro match","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC Sport","date\u003dMarch 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/russia/11500830/Goalkeeper-hit-by-flare-in-Montenegro-v-Russia.html","title\u003dGoalkeeper Igor Akinfeev hit by flare in Montenegro v Russia","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dMarch 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Small plane with one pilot crashes near Virginia airport","wikiTitle":"Small_plane_with_one_pilot_crashes_near_Virginia_airport","wid":2033650,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-14T15:13:06Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nbc29.com/story/28649757/orange-county-plane-crash-investigation-continues, title\u003dOrange County Plane Crash Investigation Continues, author\u003d, pub\u003dWVIR-TV, date\u003dMarch 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wusa9.com/story/news/local/virginia/2015/03/29/va-fatal-plane-crash-1-dead/70634572/, title\u003dTeen killed in Va. plane crash, investigation ongoing, author\u003d, pub\u003dWUSA (TV), date\u003dMarch 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://wtvr.com/2015/03/30/ryan-mccall-plane-crash/, title\u003dTeenage pilot Ryan McCall died doing what he loved, friends say, author\u003dLaura French, pub\u003dWTVR-TV, date\u003dMarch 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Virginia","description":"Virginia"},{"id":"Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Federal Aviation Administration"},{"id":"National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"National Transportation Safety Board"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation]  A small plane, piloted by sixteen-year-old Ryan McCall, crashed near TEMPLATE[w, Orange County Airport (Virginia), Orange County Airport] in Virginia, at about 9:45 a.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC-04, local time] Sunday morning, police said. He was killed in the accident.","The boy, Ryan McCall, a sophomore at Riverbend High School in TEMPLATE[w, Spotsylvania County, Virginia, Spotsylvania County], was alone on the plane. The plane, a 1974 Piper, model PA28140, crashed in a field just east of the airport. The plane belonged to TEMPLATE[w, Springfield, Virginia, Springfield], Virginia resident William Rushing III.","Flying instructors suggested birds might have contributed to the crash. The Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) and the National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB) are continuing their investigation as to what actually happened. Sixteen-year-old pilots are common, according to Virginia Aviation Board President Johnny Meza. He said a sixteen-year-old flying either alone or with a certified pilot is allowed. The NTSB predicted five to ten business days for a preliminary report.","The Spotsylvania County school district sent out a memorandum saying the school\u0027s administration is working with counsellors to help students cope with the loss of their classmate. The statement said in part, \"We were very saddened to hear the news about the death of Riverbend High Sophomore Ryan McCall.\" Grief counsellors were available at the school to provide support to students.","The boy\u0027s remains were sent to a medical examiner\u0027s office for TEMPLATE[w, autopsy].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Virginia","description":"Category:Virginia"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 1, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Orange County Airport (Virginia)","Orange County Airport"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC-04","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Spotsylvania County, Virginia","Spotsylvania County"]},{"name":"w","description":["Springfield, Virginia","Springfield"]},{"name":"w","description":["autopsy"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nbc29.com/story/28649757/orange-county-plane-crash-investigation-continues","title\u003dOrange County Plane Crash Investigation Continues","author\u003d","pub\u003dWVIR-TV","date\u003dMarch 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wusa9.com/story/news/local/virginia/2015/03/29/va-fatal-plane-crash-1-dead/70634572/","title\u003dTeen killed in Va. plane crash, investigation ongoing","author\u003d","pub\u003dWUSA (TV)","date\u003dMarch 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://wtvr.com/2015/03/30/ryan-mccall-plane-crash/","title\u003dTeenage pilot Ryan McCall died doing what he loved, friends say","author\u003dLaura French","pub\u003dWTVR-TV","date\u003dMarch 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Four found dead at flat in Gibraltar","wikiTitle":"Four_found_dead_at_flat_in_Gibraltar","wid":2033651,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-27T18:25:46Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-32121743, title\u003dFamily of four found dead in Gibraltar flat, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMarch 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/30/gibraltar-couple-and-two-children-found-stabbed-to-death, title\u003dGibraltar couple and two children found stabbed to death, author\u003dStephen Burgen, Rebecca Ratcliffe, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/british-family-of-four-found-dead-in-gibraltar-10144490.html, title\u003dGibraltar stabbing: British man found dead alongside Spanish partner and two children, author\u003dKashmira Gander, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMarch 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Gibraltar","description":"Gibraltar"},{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"British"},{"id":"Spain","description":"Spanish"},{"id":"Foreign_and_Commonwealth_Office","description":"Foreign and Commonwealth Office"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, March 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] TEMPLATE[image, Steve] The bodies of two adults and two children were found yesterday at a flat in Gibraltar in a possible murder-suicide. Two young girls, one aged four and the other only six weeks, were found stabbed alongside a British 31-year-old male and a Spanish 37-year-old female. TEMPLATE[w, Royal Gibraltar Police] said despite opening up a crime investigation on the deaths they do not currently believe anyone else was involved.","Police said an apartment letting agency staff member notified them about the property where the bodies were discovered. Police responded to the flat, in the Boschetti\u0027s Steps area, at around 11:35 local time. Police said \"They got no answer from within but noticed that the house was locked from inside and that sent a few alarm bells ringing and they decided to call the police[...] At the moment what we are doing is trying to get as much background information from both the Spanish and the UK sides of the family.\"","Police also said the family were not permanent residents in Gibraltar and had entered the British overseas territory only days ago. The Foreign and Commonwealth Office said they too were looking into the incident.","According to the Spanish newspaper TEMPLATE[w, El Mundo], police sources believe the older girl is the woman\u0027s daughter but not the man\u0027s. Police confirmed âIt is believed that all the deceased belong to the same family\". As relatives of the deceased are being sought, the names of the victims have not yet been released.","TEMPLATE[w, Fabian Picardo], the TEMPLATE[w, Gibraltar Chief Minister], spoke of his shock after hearing about the deaths. \"As a husband and father, I \u0026mdash; like no doubt all Gibraltarians and residents of Gibraltar \u0026mdash; am in total shock to hear about this terrible crime[...] Gibraltarians are not accustomed to witness this type of incident in our peaceful and law abiding community. Words will fail us all at a moment like this and all we can do is keep the victims and their families in our thoughts.\" Due to the incident he ordered TEMPLATE[w, Gibraltar Parliament, parliament] be adjourned until Wednesday.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Gibraltar","description":"Category:Gibraltar"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Spain","description":"Category:Spain"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Foreign_and_Commonwealth_Office","description":"Category:Foreign and Commonwealth Office"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Royal_Gibraltar_Police","description":"Category:Royal Gibraltar Police"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["March 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Steve"]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal Gibraltar Police"]},{"name":"w","description":["El Mundo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fabian Picardo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gibraltar Chief Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gibraltar Parliament","parliament"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-32121743","title\u003dFamily of four found dead in Gibraltar flat","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMarch 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/30/gibraltar-couple-and-two-children-found-stabbed-to-death","title\u003dGibraltar couple and two children found stabbed to death","author\u003dStephen Burgen, Rebecca Ratcliffe","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMarch 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/british-family-of-four-found-dead-in-gibraltar-10144490.html","title\u003dGibraltar stabbing: British man found dead alongside Spanish partner and two children","author\u003dKashmira Gander","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dMarch 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Musician Joni Mitchell hospitalised after found unconscious in home","wikiTitle":"Musician_Joni_Mitchell_hospitalised_after_found_unconscious_in_home","wid":2036735,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-17T18:44:29Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://jonimitchell.com, title\u003dUpdate on Joni\u0027s Health, author\u003d, pub\u003dJoni Mitchell  - Official Website, date\u003dApril 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/joni-mitchells-battle-with-morgellons-disease-20150403-1mdtnz.html, title\u003dJoni Mitchell\u0027s battle with Morgellons Disease, author\u003dSu-Lin Tan, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dApril 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.maxtv.com.au/news/breaking-joni-mitchell-found-unconscious-rushed-to-hospital.aspx, title\u003dUpdate Regarding Joni Mitchell\u0027s Condition, author\u003d, pub\u003dMax (channel), date\u003dApril 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/joni-mitchell-in-good-spirits-after-being-rushed-to-los-angeles-hospital-20150401-1mcwiq.html, title\u003dJoni Mitchell \u0027in good spirits\u0027 after being rushed to Los Angeles Hospital, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dApril 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/joni-mitchell-hospitalized-in-los-angeles-20150331, title\u003dJoni Mitchell Hospitalized in Los Angeles, author\u003dKori Grow, pub\u003dRolling Stone, date\u003dMarch 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.tmz.com/2015/03/31/joni-mitchell-hospitalized-ambulance-911/, title\u003dJoni Mitchell Legendary Singer Hospitalised, author\u003d, pub\u003dTMZ, date\u003dMarch 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/LeslieCBC/status/583101436243902464, author\u003dLeslie Stojsic, title\u003d@LeslieCBC, pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dMarch 31, 2015]"],["We love you Joni \u0026mdash; created by Joni Mitchell official Website"]],"links":[{"id":"Los_Angeles,_California","description":"Los Angeles"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"http://weloveyoujoni.com","description":"We love you Joni"}],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[music] Well-known TEMPLATE[w, Canada, Canadian] singer-songwriter TEMPLATE[w, Joni Mitchell] was found unconscious on Tuesday at her Los Angeles home, and immediately taken to hospital, according to reports. An update on her condition appeared yesterday on her website.","The update yesterday on her website said, \"Joni remains under observation in the hospital and is resting comfortably. We are encouraged by her progress and she continues to improve and get stronger each day.\" Webpage \u0027We love you Joni\u0027 was also created for fans on Facebook and Twitter to send Mitchell messages to get well soon.","A previous statement left on Mitchell\u0027s website on Tuesday said, \"Joni was found unconscious in her home this afternoon. She regained consciousness on the ambulance ride to an L.A. area hospital. She is currently in intensive care undergoing tests and is awake and in good spirits.\" They added, \"More updates to come when we hear them. Light a candle and sing a song, let\u0027s all send good wishes her way.\"","According to an early report by TEMPLATE[w, TMZ], the seventy-one year old musician\u0027s condition was serious, and a TEMPLATE[w, 9-1-1, 911] phone call was made from her home around 2:30 p.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC-7, local time].","TEMPLATE[w, Rolling Stone], also claims that a Los Angeles Fire Department spokesperson explained to them that, though they could not reveal who was taken to the hospital at the time, paramedics were sent to Mitchell\u0027s house.","On her twitter account, CBC news producer Leslie Stojsic gave a conflicting statement to other reports on Mitchell\u0027s condition, saying, \"Source tells me she\u0027s in hospital recovering after \u0027minor medical emergency,\u0027 was *not* found unconscious.\"  She also added, \"I\u0027m told now she\u0027s resting in hospital and is among friends. A good sign.\"","It did not take long for her condition in hospital to spread through the social media. Many tweeted prayers and well wishes; one of them being rocker TEMPLATE[w, Billy Idol]. He tweeted, \"Sorry to hear todays news about Joni Mitchell. I sang on her \u0027Dancing Clown\u0027 single many moons ago, all the best 4 her recovery.\"","Mitchell also reportedly suffers from TEMPLATE[w, Morgellons, Morgellons disease]; a skin condition where people claim they have fibres coming out of their skin, along with tingling sensations. In her memoir, \u0027Joni Mitchell: In her own words,\u0027 released last year, the folk artist describes her experiences with the disease saying, \"All the time it felt like I was being eaten alive by parasites living under my skin. I couldn\u0027t leave my house for several years.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:music","description":"category:music"},{"id":"category:Los_Angeles,_California","description":"category:Los Angeles, California"},{"id":"category:United_States","description":"category:United States"},{"id":"Category:California","description":"Category:California"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 4, 2015"]},{"name":"music","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Canada","Canadian"]},{"name":"w","description":["Joni Mitchell"]},{"name":"w","description":["TMZ"]},{"name":"w","description":["9-1-1","911"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC-7","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rolling Stone"]},{"name":"w","description":["Billy Idol"]},{"name":"w","description":["Morgellons","Morgellons disease"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://jonimitchell.com","title\u003dUpdate on Joni\u0027s Health","author\u003d","pub\u003dJoni Mitchell  - Official Website","date\u003dApril 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/joni-mitchells-battle-with-morgellons-disease-20150403-1mdtnz.html","title\u003dJoni Mitchell\u0027s battle with Morgellons Disease","author\u003dSu-Lin Tan","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dApril 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.maxtv.com.au/news/breaking-joni-mitchell-found-unconscious-rushed-to-hospital.aspx","title\u003dUpdate Regarding Joni Mitchell\u0027s Condition","author\u003d","pub\u003dMax (channel)","date\u003dApril 1, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/entertainment/music/joni-mitchell-in-good-spirits-after-being-rushed-to-los-angeles-hospital-20150401-1mcwiq.html","title\u003dJoni Mitchell \u0027in good spirits\u0027 after being rushed to Los Angeles Hospital","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dApril 1, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.rollingstone.com/music/news/joni-mitchell-hospitalized-in-los-angeles-20150331","title\u003dJoni Mitchell Hospitalized in Los Angeles","author\u003dKori Grow","pub\u003dRolling Stone","date\u003dMarch 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.tmz.com/2015/03/31/joni-mitchell-hospitalized-ambulance-911/","title\u003dJoni Mitchell Legendary Singer Hospitalised","author\u003d","pub\u003dTMZ","date\u003dMarch 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/LeslieCBC/status/583101436243902464","author\u003dLeslie Stojsic","title\u003d@LeslieCBC","pub\u003dTwitter","date\u003dMarch 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","author","title","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Gun control campaigner Sarah Brady dies aged 73","wikiTitle":"Gun_control_campaigner_Sarah_Brady_dies_aged_73","wid":2043604,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-13T13:41:57Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dJames Brady, former White House press secretary, gun control advocate, dies at 73, date\u003dAugust 5, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/apr/04/gun-control-activist-sarah-brady-dies-aged-73, title\u003dGun control activist Sarah Brady dies aged 73, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dApril 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.latimes.com/local/obituaries/la-me-sarah-brady-20150403-story.html#page\u003d1, title\u003dSarah Brady, gun control advocate and widow of James Brady, dies at 73, author\u003dElaine Woo, pub\u003dLos Angeles Times, date\u003dApril 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/sarah-brady-wife-white-house-secretary-jim-brady/story?id\u003d30091174, title\u003dSarah Brady, Wife of Former White House Secretary Jim Brady, Dies, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dApril 3, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"},{"id":"Bill_Clinton","description":"Bill Clinton"},{"id":"US_House_of_Representatives","description":"Congresswoman"},{"id":"Gabrielle_Giffords","description":"Gabrielle Giffords"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 5, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] TEMPLATE[image, White House] TEMPLATE[w, Sarah Brady], gun control campaigner and widow of former US TEMPLATE[w, Executive Office of the President of the United States, White House] TEMPLATE[w, White House Press Secretary, Press Secretary] TEMPLATE[w, James Brady], has died at the age of 73. Her death was announced by the TEMPLATE[w, Brady Campaign, Brady Campaign and Center to Prevent Gun Violence]. Brady died on Friday after a battle with TEMPLATE[w, pneumonia] according to e-mails sent by her family.","A statement by the Brady Campaign and Center to Prevent Gun Violence was posted on Facebook. It said \"We are heartbroken over the loss of Sarah Brady, our dear friend and Chairperson of the Brady Campaign and Center to Prevent Gun Violence. Sarah was a champion for gun violence prevention and her commitment and fiery compassion will live on.\"","On March 30, 1981 , Sarah Brady\u0027s husband, James, was injured in a shooting attempted assassination of US President TEMPLATE[w, Ronald Reagan]. A bullet entered his head and lodged in his brain. He suffered severe injuries and was partially paralyzed for the remainder of his life. The attack by TEMPLATE[w, John W. Hinckley Jr]. also injured three more people, including President Reagan.","In the years after the shooting, Sarah Brady became an advocate for gun control laws, and in 1989 vice chair of Handgun Control, Inc. In 2001 Handgun Control, Inc. became known as the Brady Campaign in tribute of both Sarah and James\u0027 efforts in fighting for tougher gun control. Brady said \"the proudest moment of our lives\" was in 1993 when President Bill Clinton signed into effect the TEMPLATE[w, Brady Bill], tightening gun law legislation.","Former First Lady TEMPLATE[w, Nancy Reagan] released a statement regarding the death of her \"dear friend\" Sarah Brady. She said \"Over the years, I found her to be a woman of immense courage, strength and optimism. I will miss Sarah very much, but take comfort in knowing that she joined Jim on Good Friday and is now at peace.\"","Another tribute came from former Congresswoman Gabrielle Giffords. Giffords, who was was shot in the head and nearly killed in 2011, said \"We know Sarah will be missed by all those whose lives she touched and who were so inspired by her commitment to her late husband Jim and to the cause of reducing gun violence in our country[...] Sarah Brady showed us not only what a tireless fight for common sense looks like, but also what it means to be a loving spouse and caretaker in the wake of a senseless tragedy. Our prayers are with her son Scott, her daughter Missy, and the entire Brady Campaign family as they mourn this devastating loss\".","Brady\u0027s death has come less than a year after the death of her husband. James Brady also died at the age of 73 last August. She is survived by son James and stepdaughter Melissa.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Gun_politics","description":"Category:Gun politics"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Bill_Clinton","description":"Category:Bill Clinton"},{"id":"Category:Gabrielle_Giffords","description":"Category:Gabrielle Giffords"},{"id":"Category:Ronald_Reagan","description":"Category:Ronald Reagan"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 5, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["White House"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sarah Brady"]},{"name":"w","description":["Executive Office of the President of the United States","White House"]},{"name":"w","description":["White House Press Secretary","Press Secretary"]},{"name":"w","description":["James Brady"]},{"name":"w","description":["Brady Campaign","Brady Campaign and Center to Prevent Gun Violence"]},{"name":"w","description":["pneumonia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ronald Reagan"]},{"name":"w","description":["John W. Hinckley Jr"]},{"name":"w","description":["Brady Bill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nancy Reagan"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dJames Brady, former White House press secretary, gun control advocate, dies at 73","date\u003dAugust 5, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/apr/04/gun-control-activist-sarah-brady-dies-aged-73","title\u003dGun control activist Sarah Brady dies aged 73","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dApril 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.latimes.com/local/obituaries/la-me-sarah-brady-20150403-story.html#page\u003d1","title\u003dSarah Brady, gun control advocate and widow of James Brady, dies at 73","author\u003dElaine Woo","pub\u003dLos Angeles Times","date\u003dApril 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/sarah-brady-wife-white-house-secretary-jim-brady/story?id\u003d30091174","title\u003dSarah Brady, Wife of Former White House Secretary Jim Brady, Dies","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News","date\u003dApril 3, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Plane crash in Illinois kills seven","wikiTitle":"Plane_crash_in_Illinois_kills_seven","wid":2050520,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-19T03:12:15Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nbc12.com/story/28738329/father-in-law-5-dead-after-small-plane-crashes-in-illinois, title\u003dIllinois State athletic staffers among 7 dead in plane crash, author\u003dDavid Mercer and Jason Keyser ([[Associated Press]]), pub\u003dWWBT, date\u003dApril 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.foxnews.com/sports/2015/04/07/illinois-state-staffers-among-7-dead-in-plane-crash/, title\u003dIllinois State staffers among 7 dead in plane crash, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dFox News, date\u003dApril 7, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Illinois","description":"Illinois"},{"id":"NCAA","description":"NCAA"},{"id":"basketball","description":"basketball"},{"id":"National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"National Transportation Safety Board"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation] TEMPLATE[image, AirSafetyGuy] A TEMPLATE[w, Cessna 414] twin engine aircraft crashed in an Illinois field on Tuesday while returning from an TEMPLATE[w, Indianapolis] NCAA basketball tournament.  All seven people on the plane were killed.","The plane took off from an airport in Indianapolis. It crashed very early Tuesday morning. According to the TEMPLATE[w, McLean County] sheriff, rescuers found all seven people dead. Coroner Kathleen Davis said they were killed by blunt force trauma.","An associate head coach of basketball and a deputy athletic director were among the dead in the crash, according to an email sent out by TEMPLATE[w, Illinois State University] President Larry Dietz to students, staff, and faculty. Both of these people were a part of Illinois State University\u0027s athletic department, where, Dietz said, they were highly esteemed.","A National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB) investigator said he didn\u0027t know yet why the plane turned away from its approach to a runway in TEMPLATE[w, Bloomington, Illinois, Bloomington], Ilinois, though he noted conditions of rain and fog. The NTSB is investigating the crash. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Illinois","description":"Category:Illinois"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:NCAA","description":"Category:NCAA"},{"id":"Category:Basketball","description":"Category:Basketball"},{"id":"Category:National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"Category:National Transportation Safety Board"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 9, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["AirSafetyGuy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cessna 414"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indianapolis"]},{"name":"w","description":["McLean County"]},{"name":"w","description":["Illinois State University"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bloomington, Illinois","Bloomington"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nbc12.com/story/28738329/father-in-law-5-dead-after-small-plane-crashes-in-illinois","title\u003dIllinois State athletic staffers among 7 dead in plane crash","author\u003dDavid Mercer and Jason Keyser ([[Associated Press]])","pub\u003dWWBT","date\u003dApril 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.foxnews.com/sports/2015/04/07/illinois-state-staffers-among-7-dead-in-plane-crash/","title\u003dIllinois State staffers among 7 dead in plane crash","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dFox News","date\u003dApril 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Dzhokhar Tsarnaev found guilty in Boston Marathon bombing trial","wikiTitle":"Dzhokhar_Tsarnaev_found_guilty_in_Boston_Marathon_bombing_trial","wid":2055057,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-22T02:09:39Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMultiple explosions hit Boston Marathon, date\u003dApril 15, 2013]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dTwo people confirmed dead in Boston Marathon bombing, date\u003dApril 15, 2013]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1461154/boston-marathon-bomber-convicted-on-all-counts, title\u003dBoston Marathon Bomber Convicted On All Counts, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dApril 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/boston-marathon-bomber-dzhokhar-tsarnaev-guilty-of-multiple-counts/, title\u003dTsarnaev convicted on all charges in Boston Marathon bombing, author\u003dCBS/(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dCBS News, date\u003dApril 8, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Boston_Marathon","description":"Boston Marathon"},{"id":"Massachusetts_Institute_of_Technology","description":"MIT"},{"id":"death_penalty","description":"death penalty"},{"id":"Massachusetts","description":"Massachusetts"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] TEMPLATE[Image, Aaron Tang] Jurors in the US federal criminal trial of TEMPLATE[w, Dzhokhar Tsarnaev] found him guilty yesterday of all 30 charges for the bombing of the Boston Marathon which occurred on April 15, 2013. The bombings killed three people and injured a further 264 people. Tsarnaev was also found guilty of shooting dead Sean Collier, an MIT police officer. The jury took eleven hours across two days to find Tsarnaev guilty.","During the fifteen days of the trial, the prosecutors called 92 witnesses to testify as to the chaotic scenes following the bombing. The father of Martin Richard, an eight-year-old boy killed in the bombing, said he had to make the difficult choice to leave his wounded son to die so he could get help for his six-year-old daughter whose leg had been destroyed in the blast. Footage presented in court showed Tsarnaev placing a backpack containing the bomb close to the location of Martin Richard.","Tsarnaev was represented by TEMPLATE[w, Judy Clarke], a death penalty specialist who previously represented TEMPLATE[w, Ted Kaczynski], the \"Unabomber\". The defence focused on averting the death penalty, and called only four witnesses, seeking to present Tsarnaev\u0027s older brother Tamerlan as the guiding force in the attack. They said that Tamerlan searched online for terms like \"detonator\" and that while Tamerlan\u0027s fingerprints were found on the bombs, Dzhokhar\u0027s were not.","Though Massachusetts does not have the death penalty, as the case is being heard in federal court the prosecutors are able to seek the death penalty. The second phase of the trial is to decide whether or not Tsarnaev will be executed or sentenced to life in prison.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Boston_Marathon","description":"Category:Boston Marathon"},{"id":"Category:Boston,_Massachusetts","description":"Category:Boston, Massachusetts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Massachusetts","description":"Category:Massachusetts"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 9, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"Image","description":["Aaron Tang"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dzhokhar Tsarnaev"]},{"name":"w","description":["Judy Clarke"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ted Kaczynski"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMultiple explosions hit Boston Marathon","date\u003dApril 15, 2013"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dTwo people confirmed dead in Boston Marathon bombing","date\u003dApril 15, 2013"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1461154/boston-marathon-bomber-convicted-on-all-counts","title\u003dBoston Marathon Bomber Convicted On All Counts","pub\u003dSky News","date\u003dApril 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/boston-marathon-bomber-dzhokhar-tsarnaev-guilty-of-multiple-counts/","title\u003dTsarnaev convicted on all charges in Boston Marathon bombing","author\u003dCBS/(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dCBS News","date\u003dApril 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Foreigners evacuated from Yemen by India","wikiTitle":"Foreigners_evacuated_from_Yemen_by_India","wid":2056981,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-02-16T16:54:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, Suicide bombers attack mosques in Sanaa, Yemen, date\u003dMarch 21, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://in.reuters.com/article/2015/04/10/yemen-india-idINKBN0N10PV20150410, title\u003dIndia ends Yemen evacuation, rescues people from 41 countries, author\u003dDouglas Busvine, Katharine Houreld, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dApril 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://indianexpress.com/article/explained/explained-leaving-yemen/, title\u003dExplained: How India evacuated 5000 stranded in Yemen, author\u003dPranav Kulkarni, Shubhajit Roy, Sushant Singh, pub\u003dThe Indian Express, date\u003dApril 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"India","description":"India"},{"id":"Yemen","description":"Yemen"},{"id":"Africa","description":"Africa"},{"id":"Djibouti","description":"Djibouti"},{"id":"Aden","description":"Aden"},{"id":"Sanaa","description":"Sanaa"},{"id":"UK","description":"Britain"},{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"Narendra_Modi","description":"Narendra Modi"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Yemen] India\u0027s Ministry of External affairs yesterday announced the end of an evacuation effort which has rescued about 5,600 people from more than 40 countries from the conflict in Yemen.","To avoid a no-fly zone over parts of Yemen, India transported people via the African state of Djibouti. This was achieved using ships of the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Navy] as transport from Aden across the TEMPLATE[w, Bab-el-Mandeb] strait to Djibouti, and TEMPLATE[w, Air India] planes flying from Sanaa to Djibouti, and from there onward to India.","4,600 of those evacuated in this way were Indian, with citizens of Western countries rescued, including Britain, France, and the United States among others. Three TEMPLATE[w, Pakistan, Pakistanis] were also amongst those rescued by the Indian effort. The TEMPLATE[w, Pakistani navy] rescued eleven Indians, for which Indian Prime Minister Narendra Modi gave a vote of thanks.","Along with ending the evacuation, India also announced the closing of its embassy in Sanaa. TEMPLATE[w, Saudi Arabia] has begun air strikes in the area against the TEMPLATE[w, Houthi] rebels who have taken control of the city, in apparent support of previous President TEMPLATE[w, Ali Abdullah Saleh].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Yemen","description":"Category:Yemen"},{"id":"Category:India","description":"Category:India"},{"id":"Category:Djibouti","description":"Category:Djibouti"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Narendra_Modi","description":"Category:Narendra Modi"},{"id":"Category:Ali_Abdullah_Saleh","description":"Category:Ali Abdullah Saleh"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:CSJJ104_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:CSJJ104 (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Aden,_Yemen","description":"Category:Aden, Yemen"},{"id":"Category:Sana\u0027a","description":"Category:Sana\u0027a"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Yemen","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Navy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bab-el-Mandeb"]},{"name":"w","description":["Air India"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pakistan","Pakistanis"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pakistani navy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Saudi Arabia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Houthi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ali Abdullah Saleh"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["Suicide bombers attack mosques in Sanaa, Yemen","date\u003dMarch 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://in.reuters.com/article/2015/04/10/yemen-india-idINKBN0N10PV20150410","title\u003dIndia ends Yemen evacuation, rescues people from 41 countries","author\u003dDouglas Busvine, Katharine Houreld","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dApril 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://indianexpress.com/article/explained/explained-leaving-yemen/","title\u003dExplained: How India evacuated 5000 stranded in Yemen","author\u003dPranav Kulkarni, Shubhajit Roy, Sushant Singh","pub\u003dThe Indian Express","date\u003dApril 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"US Capitol lockdown lifted after shooting","wikiTitle":"US_Capitol_lockdown_lifted_after_shooting","wid":2058800,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-25T15:48:15Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.foxnews.com/us/2015/04/11/us-capitol-building-on-lockdown-after-reports-shots-fired/, title\u003dUS Capitol Building reopens after shooting suicide on western steps, author\u003d(TEMPLATE) and Chad Pergram, pub\u003dFoxNews, date\u003dApril 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.myfoxdc.com/story/28778149/us-capitol-on-lock-down-following-shooting, title\u003dMan commits suicide at the US Capitol, author\u003d, pub\u003dWTTG, date\u003dApril 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_CAPITOL_SHOOTING?SITE\u003dAP\u0026SECTION\u003dHOME\u0026TEMPLATE\u003dDEFAULT\u0026CTIME\u003d2015-04-11-14-57-46, title\u003dUS Capitol lockdown lifted after man fatally shoots himself, author\u003dKevin Freking, pub\u003dAssociated Press, date\u003dApril 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Washington_D.C.","description":"Washington D.C."},{"id":"U.S._Capitol_building","description":"U.S. Capitol building"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] In Washington D.C., the U.S. Capitol building has reopened after shots were fired in front of it. For safety, no entry or exit was permitted from the building after a man committed suicide just before 2pm TEMPLATE[w, UTC-4, local time] yesterday. The lockdown lasted until around 3:50pm while members of the bomb squad investigated the man\u0027s backpack, suitcase, and the surrounding area.","A witness estimated 60 other persons were in the area at the time of death. Witnesses reported the man had a sign of protest about taxation and social justice.","The shooting occurred during the annual TEMPLATE[w, National Cherry Blossom Festival, Cherry Blossom Festival], a busy Washington tourist season. TEMPLATE[w, US Congress, Congress] was not in session during the attack but are returning from recess tomorrow.","TEMPLATE[Haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Washington,_D.C.","description":"Category:Washington, D.C."},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:US_Capitol","description":"Category:US Capitol"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 12, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC-4","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Cherry Blossom Festival","Cherry Blossom Festival"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Congress","Congress"]},{"name":"Haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.foxnews.com/us/2015/04/11/us-capitol-building-on-lockdown-after-reports-shots-fired/","title\u003dUS Capitol Building reopens after shooting suicide on western steps","author\u003d(TEMPLATE) and Chad Pergram","pub\u003dFoxNews","date\u003dApril 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.myfoxdc.com/story/28778149/us-capitol-on-lock-down-following-shooting","title\u003dMan commits suicide at the US Capitol","author\u003d","pub\u003dWTTG","date\u003dApril 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://hosted.ap.org/dynamic/stories/U/US_CAPITOL_SHOOTING?SITE\u003dAP\u0026SECTION\u003dHOME\u0026TEMPLATE\u003dDEFAULT\u0026CTIME\u003d2015-04-11-14-57-46","title\u003dUS Capitol lockdown lifted after man fatally shoots himself","author\u003dKevin Freking","pub\u003dAssociated Press","date\u003dApril 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url",