{"title":"US soccer: Sounders 2 maintain win streak with 2-1 victory over Timbers 2","wikiTitle":"US_soccer:_Sounders_2_maintain_win_streak_with_2-1_victory_over_Timbers_2","wid":2059950,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-24T19:58:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.oregonlive.com/timbers/index.ssf/2015/04/t2_loses_for_first_time_in_201.html, title\u003dT2 loses for first time in 2015 season, 2-1 to Sounders FC 2, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Oregonian, date\u003dApril 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.soundersfc.com/post/2015/04/11/undefeated-s2-rolls-last-minute-victory-over-cascadia-rivals, title\u003dUndefeated S2 rolls on with last-minute victory over Cascadia rivals, author\u003d, pub\u003dSeattle Sounders FC, date\u003dApril 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.uslsoccer.com//ViewContent.dbml?DB_OEM_ID\u003d32800\u0026CONTENT_ID\u003d1268863, title\u003dPortland Timbers 2 vs Seattle Sounders 2 (Apr 11, 2015) Soccer Box Score (Final), author\u003d, pub\u003dUnited Soccer League, date\u003dApril 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"association_football","description":"association football"},{"id":"Washington","description":"Washington"},{"id":"Seattle","description":"Seattle"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[Football_(soccer)] TEMPLATE[w, Seattle Sounders FC 2] (S2) association football club have maintained a streak with their third home win at TEMPLATE[w, Starfire Stadium] in TEMPLATE[w, Tukwila, Washington, Tukwila], Washington last night, this time against TEMPLATE[w, Portland Timbers 2] (T2).","T2 struck first when defender TEMPLATE[w, Harrison Delbridge] headed the ball in from a free kick in the 30th minute. Seattle responded with TEMPLATE[w, Pablo Rossi] converting a penalty kick in the 47th minute and TEMPLATE[w, Giuliano Frano] tapping a lobbed pass into the net in the 88th minute. Final score, 2\u0026ndash;1 Seattle.","In the 30th minute, T2 midfielder TEMPLATE[w, Blair Gavin] placed the ball nicely for Delbridge who connected cleanly with the ball to head it past S2 goalkeeper TEMPLATE[w, Charlie Lyon]. At half, the game still stood with TEMPLATE[w, Portland, Oregon, Portland] in the lead 1\u0026ndash;0. In the first minutes of the second half, S2 TEMPLATE[w, Andy Craven] was pulled down in the penalty box by T2 TEMPLATE[w, Andy Thoma]. Rossi was able to convert the penalty with a strong strike to the top left corner. T2 keeper TEMPLATE[w, Jake Gleeson] was unable to stop the shot. Frano\u0027s goal came in the 88th minute as he was able to chip the ball into the net after nice build up play by the Sounders. The Timbers did look dangerous on corners having earned 8 to Seattle\u0027s 3.","The Timbers suffered their first loss of their season while the Sounders experienced their first ever comeback victory. This was also the first match between the two TEMPLATE[w, Cascadia Cup, Cascadia rivals]. T2 now stand at 7 points with a record of 2\u0026ndash;1\u0026ndash;1. S2 and TEMPLATE[w, Arizona United SC] are now the only TEMPLATE[w, Western Conference (MLS), Western Conference] teams still undefeated. Portland next faces defending champions TEMPLATE[w, Sacramento Republic FC] away on Saturday, April 18 while Seattle hits the road to battle TEMPLATE[w, Tulsa Roughnecks FC] on Thursday, April 16.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Seattle,_Washington","description":"Category:Seattle, Washington"},{"id":"Category:Seattle_Sounders_FC","description":"Category:Seattle Sounders FC"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Washington","description":"Category:Washington"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Football_(soccer)","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Seattle Sounders FC 2"]},{"name":"w","description":["Starfire Stadium"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tukwila, Washington","Tukwila"]},{"name":"w","description":["Portland Timbers 2"]},{"name":"w","description":["Harrison Delbridge"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pablo Rossi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Giuliano Frano"]},{"name":"w","description":["Blair Gavin"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charlie Lyon"]},{"name":"w","description":["Portland, Oregon","Portland"]},{"name":"w","description":["Andy Craven"]},{"name":"w","description":["Andy Thoma"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jake Gleeson"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cascadia Cup","Cascadia rivals"]},{"name":"w","description":["Arizona United SC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Western Conference (MLS)","Western Conference"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sacramento Republic FC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tulsa Roughnecks FC"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.oregonlive.com/timbers/index.ssf/2015/04/t2_loses_for_first_time_in_201.html","title\u003dT2 loses for first time in 2015 season, 2-1 to Sounders FC 2","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Oregonian","date\u003dApril 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.soundersfc.com/post/2015/04/11/undefeated-s2-rolls-last-minute-victory-over-cascadia-rivals","title\u003dUndefeated S2 rolls on with last-minute victory over Cascadia rivals","author\u003d","pub\u003dSeattle Sounders FC","date\u003dApril 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.uslsoccer.com//ViewContent.dbml?DB_OEM_ID\u003d32800\u0026CONTENT_ID\u003d1268863","title\u003dPortland Timbers 2 vs Seattle Sounders 2 (Apr 11, 2015) Soccer Box Score (Final)","author\u003d","pub\u003dUnited Soccer League","date\u003dApril 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Australian charged with murder of two after 24 years","wikiTitle":"Australian_charged_with_murder_of_two_after_24_years","wid":2064031,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-29T17:35:40Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theage.com.au/victoria/robert-penny-charged-with-murder-of-wife-and-hairdresser-in-portland-salon-20150413-1mjt86.html, title\u003dRobert Penny charged with murder of wife and hairdresser in Portland salon, author\u003dMark Russell, Adam Cooper, Nino Bucci, pub\u003dThe Age, date\u003dApril 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-04-13/man-arrested-over-brutal-1991-portland-double-murder/6388050, title\u003dRobert Penny charged with murder of Margaret Penny and Claire Acocks at Portland hairdressing salon in 1991, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dApril 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/law-order/bail-for-husband-charged-over-1991-portland-hairdresser-shop-killings-of-margaret-penny-claire-acocks/story-fni0fee2-1227301417838, title\u003dBail for husband charged over 1991 Portland hairdresser shop killings of Margaret Penny, Claire Acocks, author\u003dShannon Deery, Mark Butler, James Dowling, pub\u003dThe Herald Sun, date\u003dApril 13, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Victoria","description":"Victoria"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[crime_and_law] Robert Penny, 83, yesterday was charged with the murder of his wife Margaret Penny and hairdresser Claire Acocks, twenty four years after their deaths at the Old London Coiffure hair salon in TEMPLATE[w, Portland, Victoria, Portland], Victoria in Australia.","Mr Penny was charged by homicide detectives after a revived investigation found Penny had disclosed details of the women\u0027s deaths to various people, that he could only have known firsthand. He allegedly told Mrs Acocks\u0027s husband the morning after her death that she was killed with a comb, and \"died very quickly\"; police found no weapon at the scene in 1991.","The prosecution also alleges Mr Penny revealed details of the murders in phone calls to both his son and daughter in the hours following the attack, again referring to the use of a TEMPLATE[w, sister\u003dcommons, foreign\u003dforce, File:Hair Braiding Equipment.JPG, tail-comb] as the weapon. Investigators at the time initially believed there may have been two weapons, and Homicide Detective Senior Constable Tom Hogan told the court \"it would have been impossible for him or any of the police to understand the Â­nature of the injuries\" before an autopsy was carried out.","The court also heard evidence of a covertly recorded phone conversation between Mr Penny and his granddaughter in February 2014, in which he said \"Would a hitman pick up a comb and kill two women?\".","Mr Penny was released on bail due to poor health, under conditions including surrender of his passport. He is due to face court again in July.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Victoria","description":"Category:Victoria"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 14, 2015"]},{"name":"crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Portland, Victoria","Portland"]},{"name":"w","description":["sister\u003dcommons","foreign\u003dforce","File:Hair Braiding Equipment.JPG","tail-comb"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theage.com.au/victoria/robert-penny-charged-with-murder-of-wife-and-hairdresser-in-portland-salon-20150413-1mjt86.html","title\u003dRobert Penny charged with murder of wife and hairdresser in Portland salon","author\u003dMark Russell, Adam Cooper, Nino Bucci","pub\u003dThe Age","date\u003dApril 13, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-04-13/man-arrested-over-brutal-1991-portland-double-murder/6388050","title\u003dRobert Penny charged with murder of Margaret Penny and Claire Acocks at Portland hairdressing salon in 1991","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dApril 13, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/law-order/bail-for-husband-charged-over-1991-portland-hairdresser-shop-killings-of-margaret-penny-claire-acocks/story-fni0fee2-1227301417838","title\u003dBail for husband charged over 1991 Portland hairdresser shop killings of Margaret Penny, Claire Acocks","author\u003dShannon Deery, Mark Butler, James Dowling","pub\u003dThe Herald Sun","date\u003dApril 13, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["sister","foreign","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Mississippi medical board allows embattled physician to keep license","wikiTitle":"Mississippi_medical_board_allows_embattled_physician_to_keep_license","wid":2067610,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-29T20:13:33Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.clarionledger.com/story/news/2015/04/15/carroll-frazier-landrum-goldwater-license/25826701/, title\u003dEdwards doctor will keep medical license, author\u003dClay Chandler, pub\u003dThe Clarion-Ledger, date\u003dApril 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wlox.com/story/28801936/89-year-old-edwards-doctor-continues-to-fight-for-his-medical-license, title\u003d89-year-old Edwards doctor gains national media attention, author\u003dJessica Bowman, pub\u003dWLOX, date\u003dApril 14, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Mississippi","description":"Mississippi"},{"id":"Toyota","description":"Toyota"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"drug","description":"drug"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[Health] TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:Special:Contributions/Sprinno, Sprinno]]] On Wednesday, the Mississippi State Board of Medical Licensure chose to let Doctor Carroll Frazier Landrum keep his physician\u0027s license, following an investigation sparked by an anonymous complaint. Media reported the Mississippi doctor has been working out of his Toyota TEMPLATE[w, Toyota Camry, Camry] for about two years, making house calls to see patients.","The investigation, started earlier this year, reportedly centered around Dr. Landrum having no physical office thus possibly being unable to properly store patient records.","Volunteers are presently renovating the former post office in the town of TEMPLATE[w, Edwards, Mississippi, Edwards], Mississippi, United States for the doctor to have an office. Estimations indicate the new office should be ready by early next month. Landrum, 89, closed his Edwards office two years ago. Landrum has routinely seen three or four patients per day since that time. Reportedly, illegal drug activity in the vicinity of his office placed him in danger. The doctor stated he was told his physical safety was in jeopardy.","Becoming tearful, Dr. Landrum told reporters he\u0027s glad he\u0027s been able to help so many people and \"give them some hope and relief, and help them survive.\" Landrum has assured the medical board he will refresh his training with a medical record-keeping course. According to Landrum\u0027s attorneys, at first the board were unwilling to release their investigative records, although ultimately they did release some of the documents.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Mississippi","description":"Category:Mississippi"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Health","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:Special:Contributions/Sprinno","Sprinno]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Toyota Camry","Camry"]},{"name":"w","description":["Edwards, Mississippi","Edwards"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.clarionledger.com/story/news/2015/04/15/carroll-frazier-landrum-goldwater-license/25826701/","title\u003dEdwards doctor will keep medical license","author\u003dClay Chandler","pub\u003dThe Clarion-Ledger","date\u003dApril 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wlox.com/story/28801936/89-year-old-edwards-doctor-continues-to-fight-for-his-medical-license","title\u003d89-year-old Edwards doctor gains national media attention","author\u003dJessica Bowman","pub\u003dWLOX","date\u003dApril 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Gyrocopter lands on US Capitol\u0027s west lawn","wikiTitle":"Gyrocopter_lands_on_US_Capitol\u0027s_west_lawn","wid":2070183,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-04-30T13:51:59Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dU.S. Secret Service conducts drone exercise, date\u003dMarch 12, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/04/16/politics/gyrocopter-pilot-washington-capitol-court/, title\u003dGyrocopter pilot who shut down Capitol released from jail, author\u003dKristen Holmes, Wes Bruer, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dApril 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.faa.gov/news/updates/?newsId\u003d82565, title\u003dFAA Statement, author\u003d, pub\u003dFederal Aviation Administration, date\u003dApril 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.politico.com/story/2015/04/gyrocopter-landing-us-capitol-117002.html, title\u003dFlorida mailman detained after landing gyrocopter on Capitol lawn, author\u003dLauren French, pub\u003dPolitico, date\u003dApril 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID\u003de81a6268c1de501429283bd2fb0fd115\u0026mc\u003dtrue\u0026node\u003dsp14.2.93.v\u0026rgn\u003ddiv6#se14.2.93_1337, title\u003dTitle 14 Code of Federal Regulations, Part 93, author\u003d, pub\u003dU.S. Government Publishing Office, date\u003dApril 15, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"US_Capitol","description":"US Capitol"},{"id":"United_States_Capitol_Police","description":"United States Capitol Police"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[aviation] Douglas Mark Hughes, a mailman for the United States TEMPLATE[w, United States Postal Service, Postal Service], landed his TEMPLATE[w, gyrocopter] on the west lawn of the US Capitol on Wednesday. He told his friends he was going to do this.","The mailman was flying his aircraft into restricted airspace when he landed on the lawn. He was immediately arrested. His stated intention was to deliver letters to all members of TEMPLATE[w, Congress] concerning campaign finance statutes. As a protective measure, the Capitol complex went on lockdown for a time.","Hughes told the TEMPLATE[w, Tampa Bay Times] of his intentions to fly the light-weight aircraft. The paper said they alerted the Secret Service and the United States Capitol Police, but TEMPLATE[w, FOX News] reported some disagreement about this from Capitol Police. Hughes had no contact with TEMPLATE[w, air traffic controllers] during the incident.","The mailman said his intention was non-violent, but he wanted to spread the word about his cause. The Secret Service questioned him some months before the incident.","Hughes was charged under TEMPLATE[w, United States Code] Title 49, concerning transportation. He was released from jail under conditions including that he must not visit the US Capitol. He is currently under house arrest.","Besides this low-flying aircraft incident, a government employee crashed a drone onto the White House property a few months ago. Also, the Secret Service conducted drone exercises to combat against possibly rogue light-weight aircraft last month.","The airspace above the Washington D.C. region is protected below 18,000 feet MSL (Mean Sea Level) with the roughly fifteen-nautical-mile-radius TEMPLATE[w, Washington, DC Metropolitan Area Special Flight Rules Area, anchor\u003dFlight Restricted Zone, Flight Restricted Zone] which surrounds the TEMPLATE[w, VHF omnidirectional range] located at TEMPLATE[w, Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport, Washington National Airport], which handles regularly scheduled commercial flights. Pilots are not allowed to fly in the Washington, DC Metropolitan Area Special Flight Rules Area, which includes the Flight Restricted Zone, unless they have TEMPLATE[w, FAA] authorization and are able to maintain effective communication with air traffic control with a two-way radio. Pilots must obtain a transponder code when flying under TEMPLATE[w, visual flight rules] in this area. Law enforcement and air ambulance operations are exempted from the FAA authorization requirement if they can maintain communications with air traffic control.","The FAA was investigating this incident, along with law enforcement agencies. Police found no explosives in the aircraft.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:US_Capitol","description":"Category:US Capitol"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Washington,_D.C.","description":"Category:Washington, D.C."},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 18, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Postal Service","Postal Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["gyrocopter"]},{"name":"w","description":["Congress"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tampa Bay Times"]},{"name":"w","description":["FOX News"]},{"name":"w","description":["air traffic controllers"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Code"]},{"name":"w","description":["Washington, DC Metropolitan Area Special Flight Rules Area","anchor\u003dFlight Restricted Zone","Flight Restricted Zone"]},{"name":"w","description":["VHF omnidirectional range"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ronald Reagan Washington National Airport","Washington National Airport"]},{"name":"w","description":["FAA"]},{"name":"w","description":["visual flight rules"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dU.S. Secret Service conducts drone exercise","date\u003dMarch 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/04/16/politics/gyrocopter-pilot-washington-capitol-court/","title\u003dGyrocopter pilot who shut down Capitol released from jail","author\u003dKristen Holmes, Wes Bruer","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dApril 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.faa.gov/news/updates/?newsId\u003d82565","title\u003dFAA Statement","author\u003d","pub\u003dFederal Aviation Administration","date\u003dApril 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.politico.com/story/2015/04/gyrocopter-landing-us-capitol-117002.html","title\u003dFlorida mailman detained after landing gyrocopter on Capitol lawn","author\u003dLauren French","pub\u003dPolitico","date\u003dApril 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ecfr.gov/cgi-bin/text-idx?SID\u003de81a6268c1de501429283bd2fb0fd115\u0026mc\u003dtrue\u0026node\u003dsp14.2.93.v\u0026rgn\u003ddiv6#se14.2.93_1337","title\u003dTitle 14 Code of Federal Regulations, Part 93","author\u003d","pub\u003dU.S. Government Publishing Office","date\u003dApril 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["anchor","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"ISIS attacks United States consulate in Irbil, Iraq","wikiTitle":"ISIS_attacks_United_States_consulate_in_Irbil,_Iraq","wid":2073872,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-29T01:15:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.cnn.com/2015/04/17/middleeast/iraq-violence/index.html, title\u003d ISIS claims blast near U.S. Consulate in Iraq, author\u003d Hamdi Alkhshali, pub\u003d CNN, date\u003d April 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/04/17/us-mideast-crisis-us-consulate-idUSKBN0N81RF20150417, title\u003d Car bomb kills three outside U.S. consulate in Iraq\u0027s Kurdish capital, author\u003d Isabel Coles, pub\u003d Reuters, date\u003d April 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://abcnews.go.com/International/car-bomb-explodes-us-consulate-erbil-iraq/story?id\u003d30392969, title\u003d Car Bomb Explodes Outside US Consulate in Erbil, Iraq, author\u003d Justin Fishel, pub\u003d ABC News, date\u003d April 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/car-bomb-explodes-outside-u-s-consulate-iraq-state-department-n343536, title\u003d Erbil Blast: Car Bomb Explodes Outside U.S. Consulate in Iraq, Official Says, author\u003d Richard Engel and Erin McClam, pub\u003d NBC News, date\u003d April 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/170420151, title\u003d 3 killed in suicide car bombing near US Consulate in Erbil, author\u003d, pub\u003d Rudaw Media Network, date\u003d April 17, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_Syria","description":"Islamic State of Iraq and Syria"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Iraq","description":"Iraq"},{"id":"Christian","description":"Christian"},{"id":"Afghanistan","description":"Afghanistan"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 19, 2015] TEMPLATE[Iraq] On Friday a car bomb, claimed by Islamic State of Iraq and Syria (ISIS), killed, by varying reports, at least three people and injured at least five others, possibly including a US national, outside of the United States Consulate in TEMPLATE[w, Irbil, Iraq, Irbil], Iraq. According to the TEMPLATE[w, US Department of State] there were no injuries to consulate personnel. TEMPLATE[w, Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve] According to police, following a small improvised explosion, a car approached the consulate, but exploded short of the consulate when fired on by security personnel. They said the explosives seem to have been triggered by the people inside the car, not the gunfire.","According to TEMPLATE[w, Reuters], until this incident there had been little ISIS aggression in Irbil since November.  Ainkawa, the consulate\u0027s neighborhood, is mainly Christian. Reportedly the primary blast took place at approximately 5:40 p.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC+3, local time], when the neighborhood is busy.","On Saturday, an attack claimed by ISIS in Afghanistan killed reportedly at least thirty-three people outside of a major bank which had a long line of people outside of it waiting to collect their pay checks.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Islam","description":"Category:Islam"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Iraq","description":"Category:Iraq"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Iraq","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Irbil, Iraq","Irbil"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Department of State"]},{"name":"w","description":["Combined Joint Task Force - Operation Inherent Resolve"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reuters"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+3","local time"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.cnn.com/2015/04/17/middleeast/iraq-violence/index.html","title\u003d ISIS claims blast near U.S. Consulate in Iraq","author\u003d Hamdi Alkhshali","pub\u003d CNN","date\u003d April 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.reuters.com/article/2015/04/17/us-mideast-crisis-us-consulate-idUSKBN0N81RF20150417","title\u003d Car bomb kills three outside U.S. consulate in Iraq\u0027s Kurdish capital","author\u003d Isabel Coles","pub\u003d Reuters","date\u003d April 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://abcnews.go.com/International/car-bomb-explodes-us-consulate-erbil-iraq/story?id\u003d30392969","title\u003d Car Bomb Explodes Outside US Consulate in Erbil, Iraq","author\u003d Justin Fishel","pub\u003d ABC News","date\u003d April 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.nbcnews.com/news/world/car-bomb-explodes-outside-u-s-consulate-iraq-state-department-n343536","title\u003d Erbil Blast: Car Bomb Explodes Outside U.S. Consulate in Iraq, Official Says","author\u003d Richard Engel and Erin McClam","pub\u003d NBC News","date\u003d April 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://rudaw.net/english/kurdistan/170420151","title\u003d 3 killed in suicide car bombing near US Consulate in Erbil","author\u003d","pub\u003d Rudaw Media Network","date\u003d April 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Reuters]"]}
{"title":"Student kills teacher in Barcelona","wikiTitle":"Student_kills_teacher_in_Barcelona","wid":2080226,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-03T15:37:20Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/04/20/europe/spain-teacher-killed/index.html, title\u003dSchool attack in Spain leaves teacher dead, four others injured, author\u003dCNN staff, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dApril 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32380705, title\u003dSpain pupil with \u0027crossbow\u0027 kills teacher in Barcelona, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dApril 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/youth-detained-deadly-school-attack-spain-084819827.html, title\u003dSpain: Student armed with crossbow, machete kills teacher, author\u003dCiaran Giles and Hernan Munzo ([[Associated Press]]), pub\u003dYahoo! News, date\u003dApril 20, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Barcelona","description":"Barcelona"},{"id":"Spain","description":"Spain"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] A student killed a school teacher at the Instituto Joan Fuster in Barcelona, Spain on Monday.  Reports indicate the student was thirteen years old; police said he was under fourteen.","The student reportedly had a TEMPLATE[wikt, crossbow] and knife; however police have not yet confirmed the cause of death. Two other teachers and two students received non-life-threatening injuries in the attack. One teacher was treated for minor injuries on scene, while the other three injured were treated at Barcelona hospitals.","Police said the motive for the attack has not been established.  The attack happened on the sixteenth anniversary of the TEMPLATE[w, Columbine High School massacre] in the United States.","According to Spanish law, the boy, because he is under fourteen years of age, cannot be held criminally responsible. As a result he cannot be jailed, but can be institutionalized in a mental health facility and was sent for psychiatric examinations following the attack.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Spain","description":"category:Spain"},{"id":"Category:Barcelona","description":"Category:Barcelona"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Education","description":"Category:Education"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 22, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"wikt","description":["crossbow"]},{"name":"w","description":["Columbine High School massacre"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/04/20/europe/spain-teacher-killed/index.html","title\u003dSchool attack in Spain leaves teacher dead, four others injured","author\u003dCNN staff","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dApril 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32380705","title\u003dSpain pupil with \u0027crossbow\u0027 kills teacher in Barcelona","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dApril 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/youth-detained-deadly-school-attack-spain-084819827.html","title\u003dSpain: Student armed with crossbow, machete kills teacher","author\u003dCiaran Giles and Hernan Munzo ([[Associated Press]])","pub\u003dYahoo! News","date\u003dApril 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Three people die in New South Wales storms","wikiTitle":"Three_people_die_in_New_South_Wales_storms","wid":2082005,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-05-14T21:27:41Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/sydney-storms-thousands-without-power-as-rain-continues-to-lash-nsw/story-fnl2dlu7-1227312880811, title\u003dStormageddon: Dungog awash with pain and devastation, author\u003dNeil Keene, Samantha Townsend, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (Australia), date\u003dApril 22, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://m.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/wild-weather-lashes-nsw-leaving-100000-homes-without-power/story-e6frg6nf-1227312955107, title\u003dWild weather lashes NSW, leaving 100,000 homes without power, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Australian, date\u003dApril 21, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/apr/21/three-die-as-once-in-a-decade-storms-lash-sydney-and-surrounding-regions, title\u003dThree die as \u0027once-in-a-decade\u0027 storms lash Sydney and surrounding regions, author\u003dBridie Jabour, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dApril 21, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"New_South_Wales","description":"New South Wales"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"Sydney","description":"Sydney"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[disasters_and_accidents] In New South Wales (NSW), Australia, two men and a woman died yesterday after search-and-rescue operations failed to rescue them from TEMPLATE[w, flood, floods] in TEMPLATE[w, Dungog, New South Wales, Dungog], roughly 200 TEMPLATE[w, kilometre, km] (125 TEMPLATE[w, mile, miles]) north of the state\u0027s capital, Sydney.","Storms hit communites along the east coast of Australia including TEMPLATE[w, Newcastle, New South Wales, Newcastle], the TEMPLATE[w, Hunter Region], the TEMPLATE[w, Central Coast (New South Wales), Central Coast], the TEMPLATE[w, Illawarra] region, and Sydney. The TEMPLATE[w, Bureau of Meteorology] reported a deep low-pressure system has caused heavy rainfall and strong winds which reached 130TEMPLATE[w, kilometres per hour, kph] (80TEMPLATE[w, miles per hour, mph]). Winds were predicted to ease today.","There have been blackouts throughout the region and severe flooding which has caused roads, bridges and houses to be washed away.  More than 500 volunteers were working with the TEMPLATE[w, State Emergency Service] to assist with operations and protect individuals, with firefighters from the Rural Fire Service and Fire Rescue according to State Emergency Service deputy commissioner Steven Pearce. They issued a warning that residents in Newcastle and surrounding areas might experience flash flooding.","The Insurance Council of Australia reported already during the day yesterday more than 5500 policyholder claims due to the storms.  New South Wales premier TEMPLATE[w, Mike Baird] said people should leave work early and arrive home before dark, as storms were predicted to intensify.","NSW transport authorities said 300 sets of traffic lights in Syndey were out and motorists should be cautious or preferably not drive. Authorities advised residents to stay away from flood-waters and from areas exposed to surf, where heavy surf can lead to coastal damage and erosion.","The New South Wales Emergency Services Minister David Elliot said it was a \"once-in-a-decade storm\". TEMPLATE[Haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Weather","description":"category:Weather"},{"id":"category:Australia","description":"category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:New_South_Wales","description":"Category:New South Wales"},{"id":"Category:Sydney","description":"Category:Sydney"},{"id":"Category:Floods","description":"Category:Floods"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Baird","description":"Category:Mike Baird"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 22, 2015"]},{"name":"disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["flood","floods"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dungog, New South Wales","Dungog"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometre","km"]},{"name":"w","description":["mile","miles"]},{"name":"w","description":["Newcastle, New South Wales","Newcastle"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hunter Region"]},{"name":"w","description":["Central Coast (New South Wales)","Central Coast"]},{"name":"w","description":["Illawarra"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bureau of Meteorology"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometres per hour","kph"]},{"name":"w","description":["miles per hour","mph"]},{"name":"w","description":["State Emergency Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mike Baird"]},{"name":"Haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailytelegraph.com.au/news/nsw/sydney-storms-thousands-without-power-as-rain-continues-to-lash-nsw/story-fnl2dlu7-1227312880811","title\u003dStormageddon: Dungog awash with pain and devastation","author\u003dNeil Keene, Samantha Townsend","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (Australia)","date\u003dApril 22, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://m.theaustralian.com.au/news/nation/wild-weather-lashes-nsw-leaving-100000-homes-without-power/story-e6frg6nf-1227312955107","title\u003dWild weather lashes NSW, leaving 100,000 homes without power","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Australian","date\u003dApril 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/apr/21/three-die-as-once-in-a-decade-storms-lash-sydney-and-surrounding-regions","title\u003dThree die as \u0027once-in-a-decade\u0027 storms lash Sydney and surrounding regions","author\u003dBridie Jabour","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dApril 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
