id":"Kentucky","description":"Kentucky"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[football_(soccer)] Seattle based soccer club TEMPLATE[w, Seattle Sounders FC 2] (S2) lost their initial two away games of the season despite having entered the road trip undefeated with three wins. First, they played the Tulsa TEMPLATE[w, Tulsa Roughnecks, Roughnecks] who won 4\u0026ndash;3 on Thursday. Next, S2 traveled to nearby TEMPLATE[w, Oklahoma City] to battle TEMPLATE[w, Energy FC] on Saturday but lost 2\u0026ndash;1.","The first half of the game against Tulsa was very exciting with five goals within the first twenty five minutes. Gibson Bardley scored immediately (2\u0027) for the Roughnecks. This prompted two quick goals from TEMPLATE[w, Qudus Lawal] who scored two along (9\u0027, 10\u0027) to put the Sounders back in the lead. TEMPLATE[w, Eli Galbraith-Knapp] scored for the opposition in the 19th minute to bring the teams level but Jimmy Ockford (25\u0027) notched one shortly after to give the Sounders three goals before the half. After the break, the Roughnecks were able to keep the Sounders from scoring but pulled ahead with two goals of their own from TEMPLATE[w, Steven Miller (soccer), Steven Miller] (69\u0027) and Lucas Cordeiro (77\u0027).","The Sounders struck first in the game against the Energy with a goal from TEMPLATE[w, Darwin Jones (soccer), Darwin Jones] in the 33rd minute. This was a short-lived lead, however, with Oklahoma City scoring five minutes later with a goal from TEMPLATE[w, Chuy Sanchez]. Energy FC might have led going into the half when they were awarded a penalty kick but TEMPLATE[w, Michael Thomas (soccer), Michael Thomas] was unable to convert. The Sounders almost held on for a draw but TEMPLATE[w, Danni KÃ¶nig] scored in the 86th minute.","S2 next faces the TEMPLATE[w, Whitecaps FC 2, Vancouver Whitecaps 2] away while the Roughnecks are to travel to Kentucky to face TEMPLATE[w, Louisville City FC]. The Energy are to host TEMPLATE[w, Saint Louis FC].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Tulsa,_Oklahoma","description":"Category:Tulsa, Oklahoma"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Seattle_Sounders_FC","description":"Category:Seattle Sounders FC"},{"id":"Category:Oklahoma","description":"Category:Oklahoma"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Seattle,_Washington","description":"Category:Seattle, Washington"},{"id":"Category:Washington","description":"Category:Washington"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 22, 2015"]},{"name":"football_(soccer)","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Seattle Sounders FC 2"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tulsa Roughnecks","Roughnecks"]},{"name":"w","description":["Oklahoma City"]},{"name":"w","description":["Energy FC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Qudus Lawal"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eli Galbraith-Knapp"]},{"name":"w","description":["Steven Miller (soccer)","Steven Miller"]},{"name":"w","description":["Darwin Jones (soccer)","Darwin Jones"]},{"name":"w","description":["Chuy Sanchez"]},{"name":"w","description":["Michael Thomas (soccer)","Michael Thomas"]},{"name":"w","description":["Danni KÃ¶nig"]},{"name":"w","description":["Whitecaps FC 2","Vancouver Whitecaps 2"]},{"name":"w","description":["Louisville City FC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Saint Louis FC"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.sounderatheart.com/2015/4/19/8455113/sounders-2-fall-in-oklahoma-again","title\u003dSounders 2 fall in Oklahoma, again","author\u003dJacob Landsberg","pub\u003dSounder At Heart","date\u003dApril 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp:/