{"title":"Holocaust survivor publicly forgives 93-year-old Auschwitz guard during his trial","wikiTitle":"Holocaust_survivor_publicly_forgives_93-year-old_Auschwitz_guard_during_his_trial","wid":2083571,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-07T19:52:46Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://globalnews.ca/news/1965291/auschwitz-says-witnessing-trial-of-ex-nazi-guard-is-a-kind-of-satisfaction/, title\u003dAuschwitz survivor says trial of ex-Nazi guard is âa kind of satisfactionâ, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dGlobal News, date\u003dApril 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/27/nazi-guard-kiss-holocaust-survivor-eva-mozes-kor_n_7149364.html, title\u003dFormer Nazi Guard Oskar Groening Kisses Holocaust Survivor Eva Kor During His Trial, author\u003dDominique Mosbergen, pub\u003dThe Huffington Post, date\u003dApril 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/04/27/the-radical-forgiveness-of-an-auschwitz-survivor-who-hugged-a-nazi-guard/, title\u003dAn Auschwitz survivorâs radical forgiveness as she hugs Nazi guard, author\u003dSarah Kaplan, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dApril 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.timescolonist.com/auschwitz-guard-tells-court-he-shares-moral-guilt-witnessed-how-jews-were-led-to-gas-chambers-1.1829563, title\u003dAuschwitz guard tells court he shares moral guilt, witnessed how Jews were led to gas chambers, author\u003dDavid Rising ([[Associated Press, AP]]), pub\u003dTimes Colonist, date\u003dApril 21, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Germany","description":"Germany"},{"id":"Judaism","description":"Jews"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 30, 2015] TEMPLATE[crime_and_law] On Friday, Eva Mozes Kor, a 81-year-old TEMPLATE[w, Auschwitz concentration camp] survivor, publicly forgave and embraced 93-year-old former TEMPLATE[w, Schutzstaffel, SS] guard Oskar GrÃ¶ning, who is currently on trial in Germany as an accessory to 300,000 murders of Jews at Auschwitz.","Kor, who was among many Jews medically experimented on at Auschwitz, has thanked Mr GrÃ¶ning for answering to the crimes he aided during his time as an Auschwitz guard.","Kor is amongst a number of Auschwitz survivors attending the trial who have joined the prosecutors as co-plaintiffs in the case against Mr GrÃ¶ning. While Kor has forgiven Mr GrÃ¶ning, she still holds him liable for his involvement during TEMPLATE[w, the Holocaust], as she did last week when she testified against him. Other survivors have recently spoken out about the trial; survivor Eva Pusztai-Fahidi said on Tuesday the trial itself against a former SS guard matters more than the end punishment.","During the first day of Mr GrÃ¶ning\u0027s trial, he denied any direct role in the killings, though he did admit to having witnessed them. Mr GrÃ¶ning said he shared \"moral guilt\" for the crimes, regardless of whether his actions make him criminally guilty.","The prosecutors have argued that serving as a concentration camp guard is legally accessory to the act of murder. Mr GrÃ¶ning is reportedly one of three remaining former SS guards that have been identified for trial. If found guilty, the former SS Guard could reportedly face up to fifteen years in prison.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:germany","description":"category:germany"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:World_War_II","description":"Category:World War II"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Judaism","description":"Category:Judaism"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:History","description":"Category:History"},{"id":"Category:The_Holocaust","description":"Category:The Holocaust"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 30, 2015"]},{"name":"crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Auschwitz concentration camp"]},{"name":"w","description":["Schutzstaffel","SS"]},{"name":"w","description":["the Holocaust"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://globalnews.ca/news/1965291/auschwitz-says-witnessing-trial-of-ex-nazi-guard-is-a-kind-of-satisfaction/","title\u003dAuschwitz survivor says trial of ex-Nazi guard is âa kind of satisfactionâ","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dGlobal News","date\u003dApril 28, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.huffingtonpost.com/2015/04/27/nazi-guard-kiss-holocaust-survivor-eva-mozes-kor_n_7149364.html","title\u003dFormer Nazi Guard Oskar Groening Kisses Holocaust Survivor Eva Kor During His Trial","author\u003dDominique Mosbergen","pub\u003dThe Huffington Post","date\u003dApril 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/morning-mix/wp/2015/04/27/the-radical-forgiveness-of-an-auschwitz-survivor-who-hugged-a-nazi-guard/","title\u003dAn Auschwitz survivorâs radical forgiveness as she hugs Nazi guard","author\u003dSarah Kaplan","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dApril 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.timescolonist.com/auschwitz-guard-tells-court-he-shares-moral-guilt-witnessed-how-jews-were-led-to-gas-chambers-1.1829563","title\u003dAuschwitz guard tells court he shares moral guilt, witnessed how Jews were led to gas chambers","author\u003dDavid Rising ([[Associated Press","AP]])","pub\u003dTimes Colonist","date\u003dApril 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Power outage at Fukushima poses radioactive risk","wikiTitle":"Power_outage_at_Fukushima_poses_radioactive_risk","wid":2084174,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-07T15:32:38Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dExplosion at earthquake-damaged Fukushima nuclear power plant, date\u003dMarch 12, 2011]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://rt.com/news/251637-fukushima-plant-toxic-water/, title\u003dPumps at Fukushima plant halted, toxic water leaking into ocean - TEPCO, author\u003d, pub\u003dRT (TV network), date\u003dApril 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/04/21/national/outage-hits-pumps-fukushima-plant-toxic-water-leaks-ocean/, title\u003dOutage hits pumps at Fukushima plant; toxic water leaks into ocean, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Japan Times, date\u003dApril 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.statesmanjournal.com/story/tech/science/environment/2015/04/06/fukushima-radiation-reached-north-american-shores/25322871/, title\u003dFukushima radiation has reached North American shores, author\u003dTracy Loew, pub\u003dStatesman Journal, date\u003dApril 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://rt.com/news/fukushima-new-leak-toxic-832/, title\u003d100 tons of toxic water leaked at Fukushima plant, author\u003d, pub\u003dRT (TV network), date\u003dFebruary 20, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2011/mar/12/fukushima-nuclear-blast-japan-alert, title\u003dFukushima nuclear plant blast puts Japan on high alert, author\u003dIan Sample and Tania Branigan, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMarch 12, 2011]"]],"links":[{"id":"Japan","description":"Japan"},{"id":"Fukushima_1_Nuclear_Power_Plant","description":"Fukushima 1 nuclear plant"},{"id":"Tokyo_Electric_Power_Company","description":"Tokyo Electric Power Company"},{"id":"Fukushima_Daiichi_nuclear_disaster","description":"Fukushima Daiichi nuclear disaster"},{"id":"earthquake","description":"earthquake"},{"id":"tsunami","description":"tsunami"},{"id":"North_America","description":"North America"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 24, 2015] TEMPLATE[Japan] A power outage at Japan\u0027s Fukushima 1 nuclear plant on Tuesday has seen eight water transfer pumps shut down, hindering efforts to collect leaked radioactive water before it can reach the sea.","Tokyo Electric Power Company (TEPCO), which runs the plant, said the affected pumps pull radioactive water out of a drainage channel, sending it through another channel to an enclosed artificial bay. This transfer began on April 17, following an official report released in February by TEPCO, revealing high concentration of radioactive materials found in the plant\u0027s drainage water.","This latest news from the nuclear plant, which sits on the eastern edge of the island nation, alongside the North Pacific Ocean, comes four years after the Fukushima Daiichi nuclear disaster, on March 12, 2011. This disaster saw the nuclear plant subjected to the combined force of an earthquake and tsunami, which caused an explosion at the plant. Since then, the site has remained unstable.","The TEMPLATE[w, Woods Hole Oceanographic Institution] found small amounts of radioactive TEMPLATE[W, Caesium, caesium] isotopes along the coast of North America, reported early this month. Along with these caesium substances, TEPCO reports indicate up to 10 trillion TEMPLATE[wikt, becquerel, becquerels] of TEMPLATE[W, Strontium, strontium]-90 and 40 trillion becquerels of TEMPLATE[W, Tritium, tritium] have contaminated sea water as a result of, and in the aftermath of, the 2011 disaster.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Japan","description":"Category:Japan"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and 