{"title":"Over 10,000 attend Gallipoli dawn service for ANZAC Day centenary","wikiTitle":"Over_10,000_attend_Gallipoli_dawn_service_for_ANZAC_Day_centenary","wid":2092557,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-09T20:47:04Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/travel/world-travel/aussies-gather-for-historic-centenary-services-at-gallipoli/story-e6frfqbr-1227319869409, title\u003dAussies gather for historic centenary services at Gallipoli, author\u003d, pub\u003dNews.com.au, date\u003dApril 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-04-25/anzac-day-2015-live-blog/6418912, title\u003dAnzac Day 2015: Hundreds of thousands attend dawn services to mark 100th anniversary of Gallipoli landings, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dApril 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32459375, title\u003dGallipoli centenary: Australia and New Zealand mark Anzac Day, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dApril 25, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, April 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[infobox, history] A crowd of over 10,000 people attended the TEMPLATE[w, Anzac day, anchor\u003dDawn service, dawn service] on Saturday at TEMPLATE[w, Gallipoli], TEMPLATE[w, Turkey] for the 100th anniversary of the landing of TEMPLATE[w, Australia, Australian] and TEMPLATE[w, New Zealand] troops there in 1915. The solemn remembrance ceremony was held at the site of the original Gallipoli landings, now known as TEMPLATE[w, Anzac Cove].  TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Gnangarra, Gnangarra]]] The Gallipoli Campaign of the TEMPLATE[w, First World War] is remembered as a failed attack in which thousands of lives were lost for little to no gain for either side. The campaign killed 45,000 TEMPLATE[w, Allies of World War I, Allied] and 86,000 Turkish troops.","Attendees at the dawn service included TEMPLATE[w, Charles, Prince of Wales, Prince Charles], the Prime Minister of Australia, and the Prime Minister of New Zealand.","Australian Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Tony Abbott]\u0027s speech later in the day emphasised the importance of the day to Australians.  \"Like every generation since, we are here on Gallipoli because we believe the Anzacs represented Australians at their best. Because they rose to their challenges, we believe it is a little easier for us to rise to ours. Their example helps us to be better than we would otherwise be\", he said.","New Zealand Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, John Key] at dawn described Gallipoli as a symbol of the highest ideals of Australians and New Zealanders \"especially when they work side by side in the face of adversity\".","Prince Charles stirred emotions by reading extracts from a serviceman\u0027s diary. The diary entry, by Company Quartermaster Sergeant Benjamin Leane, was addressed to his wife and was written hours before the first Gallipoli landing.","The centenary milestone of TEMPLATE[w, Anzac Day] also drew a Turkish security force of 3700, both police and paramilitary. Attendees entered past six security checkpoints.","A record 120,000 people also attended services at the TEMPLATE[w, Australian War Memorial] in TEMPLATE[w, Canberra] to commemorate the centenary.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:World_War_I","description":"Category:World War I"},{"id":"Category:History","description":"Category:History"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Turkey","description":"Category:Turkey"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:New_Zealand","description":"Category:New Zealand"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Royalty","description":"Category:Royalty"},{"id":"Category:Canberra","description":"Category:Canberra"},{"id":"Category:Australian_Capital_Territory","description":"Category:Australian Capital Territory"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["April 27, 2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anzac day","anchor\u003dDawn service","dawn service"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gallipoli"]},{"name":"w","description":["Turkey"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australia","Australian"]},{"name":"w","description":["New Zealand"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anzac Cove"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Gnangarra","Gnangarra]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["First World War"]},{"name":"w","description":["Allies of World War I","Allied"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles, Prince of Wales","Prince Charles"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tony Abbott"]},{"name":"w","description":["John Key"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anzac Day"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australian War Memorial"]},{"name":"w","description":["Canberra"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/travel/world-travel/aussies-gather-for-historic-centenary-services-at-gallipoli/story-e6frfqbr-1227319869409","title\u003dAussies gather for historic centenary services at Gallipoli","author\u003d","pub\u003dNews.com.au","date\u003dApril 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-04-25/anzac-day-2015-live-blog/6418912","title\u003dAnzac Day 2015: Hundreds of thousands attend dawn services to mark 100th anniversary of Gallipoli landings","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dApril 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-europe-32459375","title\u003dGallipoli centenary: Australia and New Zealand mark Anzac Day","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dApril 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["anchor","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[],"infobox":{"name":"infobox","description":["history"]}}
{"title":"Two Australians executed in Indonesia over 2005 drug smuggling case","wikiTitle":"Two_Australians_executed_in_Indonesia_over_2005_drug_smuggling_case","wid":2101987,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-12T16:34:58Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/world/asia/the-executions-of-bali-nine-duo-andrew-chan-and-myuran-sukumaran/story-fnh81fz8-1227325701195, title\u003dThe executions of Bali Nine duo Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran, author\u003dCindy Wockner, pub\u003dNews.com.au, date\u003dApril 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/queensland/andrew-chan-and-myuran-sukumaran-executions-a-black-day-for-afp-bob-myers-20150429-1mvo24.html?\u0026utm_source\u003dfacebook\u0026utm_medium\u003dcpc\u0026utm_campaign\u003dsocial\u0026eid\u003dsocialn%3Afac-14omn0012-optim-nnn%3Apaid-25%2F06%2F2014-social_traffic-all-postprom-nnn-smh-o\u0026campaign_code\u003dnocode\u0026promote_channel\u003dsocial_facebook, title\u003dAndrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran executions a \u0027black day\u0027 for AFP: Bob Myers, author\u003dKim Stephens, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dApril 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/bali-9-executions-andrew-chan-and-myuran-sukumaran-shot-dead-in-indonesia-20150428-1mvjj8.html, title\u003dBali 9 executions: Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran shot dead in Indonesia, author\u003dJewel Topsfield, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dApril 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/04/29/07/11/live-stream-julie-bishop-press-conference-bali-nine, title\u003dLong road ahead to rebuilding Australia and Indonesia relationship, author\u003d, pub\u003dninemsn, date\u003dApril 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/bali-9-execution-australia-reacts-to-the-deaths-of-chan-and-sukumaran/story-fn59niix-1227325398207, title\u003dBali 9 execution: Australia reacts to the deaths of Chan and Sukumaran, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Australian, date\u003dApril 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ibtimes.co.uk/bali-9-andrew-chan-myuran-sukumaran-faced-firing-squad-strength-dignity-1499021, title\u003dBali 9: Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran faced firing squad with \u0027strength and dignity\u0027, author\u003dPriya Joshi, pub\u003dInternational Business Times, date\u003dApril 29, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"heroin","description":"heroin"},{"id":"death_penalty","description":"executed"},{"id":"Indonesia","description":"Indonesia"},{"id":"Tony_Abbott","description":"Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Julie_Bishop","description":"Julie Bishop"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[Indonesia] At 12:35 am TEMPLATE[w, UTC+7, local time] Wednesday morning, TEMPLATE[W, Andrew Chan], 31, and TEMPLATE[W, Myuran Sukumaran], 33, leaders of the so-called \"TEMPLATE[W, Bali Nine]\" heroin drug smugglers group, were executed on the Indonesian island of TEMPLATE[W, Nusa Kambangan].","The execution came nearly ten years after their 2006 conviction, in which time both men had become fully rehabilitated, said Australian Prime Minister Tony Abbott. Chan had become a TEMPLATE[w, Christianity, Christian] minister and Sukumaran turned to painting to help other prisoners at TEMPLATE[W, Kerobokan Prison] to rehabilitate.","The two Australian men as well as the other six men executed were confirmed dead 27 minutes after they faced a firing squad, said Indonesian officials. They refused blindfolds when they stood before the firing squad, and sang \"TEMPLATE[w, Amazing Grace]\", according to witnesses.","Australian officials condemned the executions, with Prime Minister Tony Abbott saying the relationship between the neighbouring countries has reached a \"dark moment\". The Prime Minister, as well as the Foreign Minister, Julie Bishop, agreed to withdraw the Australian ambassador to Indonesia \"once all the courtesies have been extended to the Chan and Sukumaran families\", who were staying in the TEMPLATE[w, Cilacap] region. Mr Abbott said, \"We respect Indonesia\u0027s sovereignty but we do deplore what\u0027s been done and this cannot be simply business as usual.\"","Australian authorities are coming under question, with lawyer Bob Myers saying \"this is a black day for the AFP [TEMPLATE[W, Australian Federal Police]], a day they deliberately exposed nine Australians to the death penalty\". Myers was contacted by the father of Bali Nine member TEMPLATE[W, Scott Rush] after the father suspected his son\u0027s involvement in the operation, which aimed to import 8.3 kilograms of heroin into Australia, with an estimated street value of about TEMPLATE[w, Australian dollar, A$]4 million. Myers said the AFP knew of the plans of every member of the Bali Nine, excluding Sukumaran, \"and they didn\u0027t want to stop these people.\" He said the AFP had the opportunity to arrest the Australians before they left for Indonesia, meaning they would face a prison sentence in Australia, and avoid the death penalty. In not doing so, Myers said, they now have \"blood on their hands\".","Tributes have flowed in on social media using hashtag #IStandForMercy. Many Australians have also said they will boycott future plans to travel to the island nation, using hashtags #boycottindonesia and #boycottbali.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia","description":"Category:Indonesia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Drugs","description":"Category:Drugs"},{"id":"Category:Heroin","description":"Category:Heroin"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Abbott","description":"Category:Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Category:Julie_Bishop","description":"Category:Julie Bishop"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Indonesia","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+7","local time"]},{"name":"W","description":["Andrew Chan"]},{"name":"W","description":["Myuran Sukumaran"]},{"name":"W","description":["Bali Nine"]},{"name":"W","description":["Nusa Kambangan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Christianity","Christian"]},{"name":"W","description":["Kerobokan Prison"]},{"name":"w","description":["Amazing Grace"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cilacap"]},{"name":"W","description":["Australian Federal Police"]},{"name":"W","description":["Scott Rush"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australian dollar","A$"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/world/asia/the-executions-of-bali-nine-duo-andrew-chan-and-myuran-sukumaran/story-fnh81fz8-1227325701195","title\u003dThe executions of Bali Nine duo Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran","author\u003dCindy Wockner","pub\u003dNews.com.au","date\u003dApril 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/queensland/andrew-chan-and-myuran-sukumaran-executions-a-black-day-for-afp-bob-myers-20150429-1mvo24.html?\u0026utm_source\u003dfacebook\u0026utm_medium\u003dcpc\u0026utm_campaign\u003dsocial\u0026eid\u003dsocialn%3Afac-14omn0012-optim-nnn%3Apaid-25%2F06%2F2014-social_traffic-all-postprom-nnn-smh-o\u0026campaign_code\u003dnocode\u0026promote_channel\u003dsocial_facebook","title\u003dAndrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran executions a \u0027black day\u0027 for AFP: Bob Myers","author\u003dKim Stephens","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dApril 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/bali-9-executions-andrew-chan-and-myuran-sukumaran-shot-dead-in-indonesia-20150428-1mvjj8.html","title\u003dBali 9 executions: Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran shot dead in Indonesia","author\u003dJewel Topsfield","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dApril 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/04/29/07/11/live-stream-julie-bishop-press-conference-bali-nine","title\u003dLong road ahead to rebuilding Australia and Indonesia relationship","author\u003d","pub\u003dninemsn","date\u003dApril 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theaustralian.com.au/national-affairs/bali-9-execution-australia-reacts-to-the-deaths-of-chan-and-sukumaran/story-fn59niix-1227325398207","title\u003dBali 9 execution: Australia reacts to the deaths of Chan and Sukumaran","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Australian","date\u003dApril 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ibtimes.co.uk/bali-9-andrew-chan-myuran-sukumaran-faced-firing-squad-strength-dignity-1499021","title\u003dBali 9: Andrew Chan and Myuran Sukumaran faced firing squad with \u0027strength and dignity\u0027","author\u003dPriya Joshi","pub\u003dInternational Business Times","date\u003dApril 29, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Indiana Governor signs needle exchange program","wikiTitle":"Indiana_Governor_signs_needle_exchange_program","wid":2108202,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-22T21:21:45Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.indystar.com/story/news/politics/2015/05/05/pence-signs-bill-facilitate-needle-exchange-programs/26946043/, title\u003dPence signs law to facilitate needle exchange programs, author\u003dLesley Weidenbener (TheStatehouseFile.com), pub\u003dThe Indianapolis Star, date\u003dMay 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/pence-signs-needle-exchange-bill-hiv-outbreak-cases-30827836, title\u003dPence Signs Needle-Exchange Bill as HIV Outbreak Cases Grow, author\u003dTom Davies ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dMay 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://wishtv.com/2015/04/29/gov-pence-says-he-will-support-needle-exchange-bill/, title\u003dGov. Pence says he will âsupportâ needle exchange bill, author\u003dBennett Haeberle, pub\u003dWISH-TV, date\u003dMay 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.chicagotribune.com/news/local/breaking/chi-indiana-hiv-needle-exchange-20150429-story.html, title\u003dFaced with HIV outbreak, Indiana lawmakers OK needle exchange programs, author\u003d, pub\u003dChicago Tribune, date\u003dApril 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.indystar.com/story/news/2015/04/27/needle-exchange-can-help-stop-hiv-spread-experts-say/26387435/, title\u003dNeedle exchange can help stop HIV spread, experts say, author\u003dShari Rudavsky, pub\u003dThe Indianapolis Star, date\u003dApril 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.southbendtribune.com/news/local/deadline-nears-for-indiana-needle-exchange-bill/article_8a6ff914-5c63-51ba-a73b-2de1a6beb3f8.html, title\u003dDeadline nears for Indiana needle-exchange bill, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dSouth Bend Tribune, date\u003dApril 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/metro-government/2015/04/23/louisville-metro-council-vote-needle-exchange/26234243/, title\u003dMetro Council approves needle exchange, author\u003dPhillip M. Bailey, pub\u003dLouisville Courier-Journal, date\u003dApril 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://iga.in.gov/legislative/2015/committees/, title\u003dIndiana General Assembly 2015 Session Committees, pub\u003dIndiana General Assembly, date\u003dMay 7, 2015 (date of access)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://iga.in.gov/legislative/2015/bills/senate/461, title\u003dIndiana General Assembly 2015 Session Senate Bill 461, author\u003dSenator Patricia Miller, Senator Vaneta Becker, pub\u003dIndiana General Assembly, date\u003dMay 7, 2015 (date of access)]"]],"links":[{"id":"Indiana","description":"Indiana"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[Indiana] TEMPLATE[image_credit, United States Congress] Indiana Governor TEMPLATE[w, Mike Pence] dropped his former opposition to needle exchange programs and on Tuesday signed legislation passed by lawmakers on April 29 \u0026mdash; the last day of the state\u0027s legislative session \u0026mdash; that would allow local health departments, municipalities, counties, or nonprofit organizations to implement needle exchange programs. The debate about the controversial programs came on the heels of an TEMPLATE[w, HIV] outbreak in Southern Indiana.","TEMPLATE[w, Austin, Indiana, Austin], in TEMPLATE[w, Scott County, Indiana, Scott County], Indiana, was the epicenter of the outbreak.  The number of new HIV positive cases in Scott County in this outbreak rose past 140. Governor Pence declared the outbreak a public health emergency on March 26, and at the same time approved a 30-day needle exchange program. Pence since offered a 30-day extension as the number of HIV positive cases continued to rise.","Needle exchange programs provide clean needles in exchange for dirty needles. The sharing of dirty needles has been linked to the outbreak. Experts like Chris Beyrer, president of the TEMPLATE[w, International AIDS Society], support needle exchange programs. Beyrer told the TEMPLATE[w, Indianapolis Star], however, that temporary measures, like the one Pence implemented on March 26, don\u0027t solve the long-term problem. The TEMPLATE[w, World Health Organization] and the TEMPLATE[w, Centers for Disease Control and Prevention] also recommend needle exchange programs. But experts say long-term needle exchange programs are needed.","The HIV epidemic in Southern Indiana has been linked to a drug problem in Scott County. HIV and Hepatitis C are blood-borne viruses that spread by way of bodily fluids and bloodstream injections, especially when more than one person is using the same needle.","Legislators on the committee responsible for Senate Bill 461 heard testimony last week before voting. Representative TEMPLATE[w, Thomas Washburne], TEMPLATE[w, Republican Party (US), Republican], TEMPLATE[w, Evansville, Indiana, Evansville], told Wikinews on April 27 that he was involved in conversations pertaining to needle exchange programs. \"I am inclined to follow the recommendations of the Centers for Disease Control in implementing needle exchanges,\" Washburne said in an interview with Wikinews. \"My vote against Senate Bill 461 was not due to the needle exchanges, but other issues involved in the bill.\"","House members passed the bill 80\u0026ndash;19, senators 38\u0026ndash;11.","After legislators passed the bill, Pence told TEMPLATE[w, WISH-TV]: \"From my perspective, the focus needs to be on health emergencies. I have throughout my career not supported needle exchanges as anti-drug policies. But with regard to addressing an epidemic, which is what weâve seen in Scott County, which is unprecedented in any rural part of the country. I was prepared to support that through executive action.\"","TEMPLATE[w, Louisville], TEMPLATE[w, Kentucky], about 35 miles south of Austin, was the first Kentucky municipal government to approve a needle exchange program. The Louisvile Metro Council voted 22\u0026ndash;0 to approve the program on April 23. That approval requires reconsulting the council before actually implementing such a program. About 195 cities in the TEMPLATE[w, United States] have adopted similar programs.","Dr. William Shaffner, a doctor and chair of the Department of Preventative Medicine at TEMPLATE[w, Vanderbilt University] in TEMPLATE[w, Nashville], TEMPLATE[w, Tennessee], told Wikinews reporters March 25 at the TEMPLATE[w, University of Southern Indiana] in Evansville, the day before Pence declared the public health emergency, such a program would make sense. He said the best course of action would be to \"block and tackle.\"","\"Needle exchange programs ought to be used,\" Shaffner said. \"They have been proven to work and do not cause an increase in drug use.\"","TEMPLATE[clear]TEMPLATE[Picture_select, width\u003d720px, 1\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 03.jpg, 400px, center]]\u003cbr /\u003e Dr. William Schaffner presents March 25, 2015 at the 2015 Shaw Lecture at the University of Southern Indiana about emerging infectious diseases. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e, 2\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 01.jpg, 400px, center]]\u003cbr /\u003e USI Biology Professor Marlene Shaw welcomes a full house to the 2015 Shaw Lecture on March 25, 2015 at the University of Southern Indiana. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e, 3\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 02.jpg, 400px, center]]\u003cbr /\u003e A crowd of students, faculty and healthcare professionals gather during the 2015 Shaw Lecture on March 25, 2015 in Mitchell Auditorium at the University of Southern Indiana to hear Dr. William Shaffner present. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e, 4\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 04.jpg, 400px, center]]\u003cbr /\u003e Dr. William Shaffner answers questions from students on March 25, 2015 during the 2015 Shaw Lecture at the University of Southern Indiana. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e]","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay, Should the state of Indiana emphasize drug reduction and not have a needle exchange program or emphasize preventative health measures and continue the needle exchange?, Comment!]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Drugs","description":"Category:Drugs"},{"id":"Category:AIDS","description":"Category:AIDS"},{"id":"Category:Infectious_disease","description":"Category:Infectious disease"},{"id":"Category:Disease","description":"Category:Disease"},{"id":"Category:Indiana","description":"Category:Indiana"},{"id":"Category:Kentucky","description":"Category:Kentucky"},{"id":"Category:Tennessee","description":"Category:Tennessee"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Jrlvaughn_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Jrlvaughn (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Crtew_(Wikinewsie)â","description":"Category:Crtew (Wikinewsie)â"},{"id":"Category:Gkstylianides_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Gkstylianides (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Pence","description":"Category:Mike Pence"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Indiana","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["United States Congress"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mike Pence"]},{"name":"w","description":["HIV"]},{"name":"w","description":["Austin, Indiana","Austin"]},{"name":"w","description":["Scott County, Indiana","Scott County"]},{"name":"w","description":["International AIDS Society"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indianapolis Star"]},{"name":"w","description":["World Health Organization"]},{"name":"w","description":["Centers for Disease Control and Prevention"]},{"name":"w","description":["Thomas Washburne"]},{"name":"w","description":["Republican Party (US)","Republican"]},{"name":"w","description":["Evansville, Indiana","Evansville"]},{"name":"w","description":["WISH-TV"]},{"name":"w","description":["Louisville"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kentucky"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States"]},{"name":"w","description":["Vanderbilt University"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nashville"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tennessee"]},{"name":"w","description":["University of Southern Indiana"]},{"name":"clear","description":[]},{"name":"Picture_select","description":["width\u003d720px","1\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 03.jpg","400px","center]]\u003cbr /\u003e\nDr. William Schaffner presents March 25, 2015 at the 2015 Shaw Lecture at the University of Southern Indiana about emerging infectious diseases. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e","2\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 01.jpg","400px","center]]\u003cbr /\u003e\nUSI Biology Professor Marlene Shaw welcomes a full house to the 2015 Shaw Lecture on March 25, 2015 at the University of Southern Indiana. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e","3\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 02.jpg","400px","center]]\u003cbr /\u003e\nA crowd of students, faculty and healthcare professionals gather during the 2015 Shaw Lecture on March 25, 2015 in Mitchell Auditorium at the University of Southern Indiana to hear Dr. William Shaffner present. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e","4\u003d[[File:USI Shaw Lecture 04.jpg","400px","center]]\u003cbr /\u003e\nDr. William Shaffner answers questions from students on March 25, 2015 during the 2015 Shaw Lecture at the University of Southern Indiana. (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr /\u003e"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[User:Gkstylianides","Gkstylianides]]"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[User:Gkstylianides","Gkstylianides]]"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[User:Gkstylianides","Gkstylianides]]"]},{"name":"im