-5c63-51ba-a73b-2de1a6beb3f8.html","title\u003dDeadline nears for Indiana needle-exchange bill","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dSouth Bend Tribune","date\u003dApril 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.courier-journal.com/story/news/politics/metro-government/2015/04/23/louisville-metro-council-vote-needle-exchange/26234243/","title\u003dMetro Council approves needle exchange","author\u003dPhillip M. Bailey","pub\u003dLouisville Courier-Journal","date\u003dApril 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://iga.in.gov/legislative/2015/committees/","title\u003dIndiana General Assembly 2015 Session Committees","pub\u003dIndiana General Assembly","date\u003dMay 7, 2015 (date of access)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://iga.in.gov/legislative/2015/bills/senate/461","title\u003dIndiana General Assembly 2015 Session Senate Bill 461","author\u003dSenator Patricia Miller, Senator Vaneta Becker","pub\u003dIndiana General Assembly","date\u003dMay 7, 2015 (date of access)"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["width","1","2","3","4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Stand by me: Music legend Ben E King dies at 76","wikiTitle":"Stand_by_me:_Music_legend_Ben_E_King_dies_at_76","wid":2109457,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-17T15:34:35Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/entertainment/2015/05/02/08/47/soul-singer-ben-e-king-dead-at-76, title\u003d\u0027Stand by Me\u0027 singer and soul legend Ben E King dies aged 76, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dNine News, date\u003dMay 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-32547474, title\u003dBen E King: R\u0026B legend dies at 76, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003d May 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11577200/Stand-By-Me-singer-Ben-E-King-dies-at-76.html, title\u003dStand by Me singer Ben E King Dies at 76, author\u003dHannah Furness, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003d May 1, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"New_Jersey","description":"New Jersey"},{"id":"Boston","description":"Boston"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 3, 2015] TEMPLATE[music] TEMPLATE[image_source, annulla] TEMPLATE[w, Ben E King], the TEMPLATE[w, soul music, soul] singer recognised for memorable track \"TEMPLATE[w, Stand by Me (song), Stand by Me]\", died on Thursday at the age of 76.","According to publicist Phil Brown, King died in New Jersey of natural causes.","King was best known for being a part of TEMPLATE[w, The Drifters] in the 1950s who had hits such as \"TEMPLATE[w, Save the Last Dance for Me]\", and \"TEMPLATE[w, There Goes My Baby (The Drifters song), There Goes my Baby]\". Later on when he left the band and embarked on a solo career, he took on the name \"Ben E King\" and brought out notable tracks \"TEMPLATE[w, Spanish Harlem (song), Spanish Harlem]\" and \"TEMPLATE[w, Supernatural Thing (song), Supernatural Thing] \u0026mdash; Part One\".  In 1961 he released the song \"Stand by Me\".  It was later the title track for the 1986 film TEMPLATE[w, Stand by Me (film), Stand by Me] directed by TEMPLATE[w, Rob Reiner].","In an interview with Boston public television station TEMPLATE[w, WGBH-TV, WGBH], King recalled writing track \"Stand by Me\", saying, \"when I wrote \u0027Stand by Me\u0027 as a song, and to know that the song will probably be here for hundreds and hundreds of years to come, it\u0027s great\".","At the news of King\u0027s death, many sent their condolences and paid tribute online through social media. On Twitter, novelist TEMPLATE[w, Salman Rushdie] linked King\u0027s \"Stand by Me\", tweeting \"Thanks Ben E King\", and musician TEMPLATE[w, Gary U.S. Bonds] wrote about his friendship with King on Facebook, saying, \"With an extremely heavy heart, I must say goodbye to one of the sweetest, gentlest and gifted souls that I have had the privilege of knowing and calling my friend for more than 50 years \u0026mdash; Mr. Ben E. King [...] Our sincere condolences go out to Betty and the entire family.\"","Survived by his wife Betty, along with three children and six grandchildren, King, originally known as Benjamin Earl Nelson, started in a TEMPLATE[w, doo-wop] band, The Five Crowns, who eventually became The Drifters.  According to TEMPLATE[w, BBC News], the tracks \"Stand by Me\", \"Spanish Harlem\", and \"There Goes my Baby\" are on the TEMPLATE[w, Rock and Roll Hall of Fame]\u0027s list of 500 songs that Shaped Rock and Roll.  Talking to TEMPLATE[w, The Guardian] in 2013, King spoke about his voice in \"Stand by Me\". He said, \"In my vocal I think you can hear something of my earlier times when I\u0027d sing in subway halls for the echo, and perform doo-wop on street corners\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:New_Jersey","description":"Category:New Jersey"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 3, 2015"]},{"name":"music","description":[]},{"name":"image_source","description":["annulla"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ben E King"]},{"name":"w","description":["soul music","soul"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stand by Me (song)","Stand by Me"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Drifters"]},{"name":"w","description":["Save the Last Dance for Me"]},{"name":"w","description":["There Goes My Baby (The Drifters song)","There Goes my Baby"]},{"name":"w","description":["Spanish Harlem (song)","Spanish Harlem"]},{"name":"w","description":["Supernatural Thing (song)","Supernatural Thing"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stand by Me (film)","Stand by Me"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rob Reiner"]},{"name":"w","description":["WGBH-TV","WGBH"]},{"name":"w","description":["Salman Rushdie"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gary U.S. Bonds"]},{"name":"w","description":["doo-wop"]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC News"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rock and Roll Hall of Fame"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Guardian"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/entertainment/2015/05/02/08/47/soul-singer-ben-e-king-dead-at-76","title\u003d\u0027Stand by Me\u0027 singer and soul legend Ben E King dies aged 76","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dNine News","date\u003dMay 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/entertainment-arts-32547474","title\u003dBen E King: R\u0026B legend dies at 76","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003d May 1, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/celebritynews/11577200/Stand-By-Me-singer-Ben-E-King-dies-at-76.html","title\u003dStand by Me singer Ben E King Dies at 76","author\u003dHannah Furness","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003d May 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Royal Birth: Duchess of Cambridge gives birth to baby girl","wikiTitle":"Royal_Birth:_Duchess_of_Cambridge_gives_birth_to_baby_girl","wid":2109647,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-15T19:11:52Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/royal-baby-kate-middleton-duchess-of-cambridge-gives-birth-to-baby-girl-20150502-1mym0o.html, title\u003dRoyal Baby: Kate Middleton, Duchess of Cambridge, gives birth to baby girl, author\u003dNick Miller, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dMay 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/uk-32562117, title\u003dRoyal baby: Duchess of Cambridge gives birth to daughter, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-02/duchess-of-cambridge-taken-to-london-hospital-in-labour/6440060, title\u003dRoyal Baby: Catherine Duchess of Cambridge, take to London hospital in labour, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dMay 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.skynews.com.au/news/top-stories/2015/05/02/duchess-of-cambridge-in-labour.html, title\u003dRoyal Baby: Duchess of Cambridge in Labour, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dMay 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"UK","description":"UK"},{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"Tony_Abbott","description":"Tony Abbott"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"Queen_Elizabeth_II","description":"Queen Elizabeth II"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 3, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] The UK\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge] gave birth yesterday to a baby girl, and TEMPLATE[w, Kensington Palace] announced, \"Her Royal Highness the Duchess of Cambridge was safely delivered of a daughter at 8:34 am.\" TEMPLATE[image_credit, Carfax2] The announcement also said Catherine and the baby are \"doing well.\"  The daughter of the royal couple was said to weigh 8TEMPLATE[w, pound (mass), lbs] 3TEMPLATE[w, ounce, oz].","Earlier in the day Catherine was admitted in labour into the Lindo Wing of TEMPLATE[w, St Mary\u0027s Hospital, London, St Mary\u0027s Hospital] in London.","Kensington Palace released a statement that the Duchess went to the hospital by car and was admitted into Saint Mary\u0027s at 6am TEMPLATE[w, UTC+1, local time].","The baby is the fourth in line to the throne. Australian Prime Minister Tony Abbott stated, \"On behalf of all Australians, Margie and I extend to the Duke and Duchess of Cambridge congratulations on the birth of a daughter [...] we wish the young Princess a long and happy life.\" UK Prime Minister David Cameron sent well wishes earlier via Twitter, saying, \"The whole country will wish her well.\"","TEMPLATE[w, Prince George of Cambridge, Prince George]\u0027s birth also took place in Saint Mary\u0027s in 2013, and Prince William\u0027s in 1982. Obstetrician Guy Thorpe-Beeston, along with TEMPLATE[w, Alan Farthing], surgeon gynaecologist to Queen Elizabeth II, were present for the second royal birth. The announcement of the birth also said, \"The Queen, TEMPLATE[w, Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh, The Duke of Edinburgh], TEMPLATE[w, Charles, Prince of Wales, The Prince of Wales], TEMPLATE[w, Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall, The Duchess of Cornwall], TEMPLATE[w, Prince Harry], and members of both families have been informed and are delighted with the news.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Royalty","description":"category:Royalty"},{"id":"category:London","description":"category:London"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Abbott","description":"Category:Tony Abbott"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 3, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Catherine, Duchess of Cambridge"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kensington Palace"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Carfax2"]},{"name":"w","description":["pound (mass)","lbs"]},{"name":"w","description":["ounce","oz"]},{"name":"w","description":["St Mary\u0027s Hospital, London","St Mary\u0027s Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+1","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prince George of Cambridge","Prince George"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alan Farthing"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prince Philip, Duke of Edinburgh","The Duke of Edinburgh"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles, Prince of Wales","The Prince of Wales"]},{"name":"w","description":["Camilla, Duchess of Cornwall","The Duchess of Cornwall"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prince Harry"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/lifestyle/celebrity/royal-baby-kate-middleton-duchess-of-cambridge-gives-birth-to-baby-girl-20150502-1mym0o.html","title\u003dRoyal Baby: Kate Middleton, Duchess of Cambridge, gives birth to baby girl","author\u003dNick Miller","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dMay 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/uk-32562117","title\u003dRoyal baby: Duchess of Cambridge gives birth to daughter","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMay 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-02/duchess-of-cambridge-taken-to-london-hospital-in-labour/6440060","title\u003dRoyal Baby: Catherine Duchess of Cambridge, take to London hospital in labour","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dMay 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.skynews.com.au/news/top-stories/2015/05/02/duchess-of-cambridge-in-labour.html","title\u003dRoyal Baby: Duchess of Cambridge in Labour","author\u003d","pub\u003dSky News","date\u003dMay 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"New Zealand begins process to consider changing national flag design","wikiTitle":"New_Zealand_begins_process_to_consider_changing_national_flag_design","wid":2117049,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-18T19:27:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.smh.com.au/world/new-zealand-flag-debate-begins-20150505-ggu62m.html, title\u003d New Zealand flag debate begins, author\u003d (TEMPLATE) with (TEMPLATE), pub\u003d The Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003d May 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id\u003d1\u0026objectid\u003d11443525, title\u003d New Zealanders encouraged to join flag discussions, author\u003d, pub\u003d The New Zealand Herald, date\u003d May 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.3news.co.nz/nznews/nz-flag-debate-set-to-open-to-public-2015050417#axzz3ZGE7BI8X, title\u003d NZ flag debate set to open to public, author\u003d Simon Wong, pub\u003d 3 News, date\u003d May 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/05/new-zealanders-asked-to-flag-ideas-for-a-new-design-online, title\u003d New Zealanders asked to flag ideas for a new design online, author\u003d (TEMPLATE), pub\u003d The Guardian, date\u003d May 4, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"New_Zealand","description":"New Zealand"},{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"United Kingdom"},{"id":"John_Key","description":"John Key"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[New_Zealand] On Tuesday, the New Zealand government announced the start of a public process to suggest designs for a new national flag, and determine whether their citizens would prefer a different national flag over the current one.","The current New Zealand flag is partially based on the United Kingdom\u0027s flag; the new one would be unique to New Zealand. The government\u0027s Flag Consideration Project has planned a number of conferences and roadshows as part of this process, with the first meeting set to take place in TEMPLATE[W, Christchurch] on May 16. According to the New Zealand Herald, Emeritus Professor John Burrows, the chairman of the project\u0027s panel of twelve, said New Zealand\u0027s flag has never before been open to public choice.","Professor Burrows also said resources and kits would be accessible for schools and communities, \"For example, schools can run their own flag discussions and referendums to mirror the formal process as part of their own learning exercise\". People were encouraged to submit their designs online at www.flag.govt.nz and suggest what the flag should mean on www.standfor.co.nz. Names of participants would be engraved, at their option, on a flag pole monument to be built in the nation\u0027s capital, TEMPLATE[w, Wellington].","New Zealand\u0027s Prime Minister John Key said he believes redesigning the flag now has a \"strong rationale\".  Mr Key promoted the campaign for a unique New Zealand flag on TEMPLATE[w, Waitangi Day] \u0026mdash; February 6 \u0026mdash; this year. Of the public process, he said, \"In the end I\u0027ll have one vote in each referendum just like every other New Zealander on the electoral roll\".","The New Zealand government intends to hold two referendums to reach a verdict on the flag, at an estimated cost of TEMPLATE[w, New Zealand dollar, NZ$]26 million, although a recent poll found only a quarter of citizens favoured changing the flag. This is a decrease from the year before, when it was forty percent. The first referendum is to be held from November 20 to December 11, selecting a single new flag design out of about four finalists. Voters would then choose between the new flag and their current flag early in 2016.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:_Oceania","description":"Category: Oceania"},{"id":"Category:_New_Zealand","description":"Category: New Zealand"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:John_Key","description":"Category:John Key"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 7, 2015"]},{"name":"New_Zealand","description":[]},{"name":"W","description":["Christchurch"]},{"name":"w","description":["Wellington"]},{"name":"w","description":["Waitangi Day"]},{"name":"w","description":["New Zealand dollar","NZ$"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.smh.com.au/world/new-zealand-flag-debate-begins-20150505-ggu62m.html","title\u003d New Zealand flag debate begins","author\u003d (TEMPLATE) with (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003d The Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003d May 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id\u003d1\u0026objectid\u003d11443525","title\u003d New Zealanders encouraged to join flag discussions","author\u003d","pub\u003d The New Zealand Herald","date\u003d May 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.3news.co.nz/nznews/nz-flag-debate-set-to-open-to-public-2015050417#axzz3ZGE7BI8X","title\u003d NZ flag debate set to open to public","author\u003d Simon Wong","pub\u003d 3 News","date\u003d May 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/05/new-zealanders-asked-to-flag-ideas-for-a-new-design-online","title\u003d New Zealanders asked to flag ideas for a new design online","author\u003d (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003d The Guardian","date\u003d May 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Copilot practiced putting plane into controlled descent prior to crash of Germanwings Flight 9525, French authorities say","wikiTitle":"Copilot_practiced_putting_plane_into_controlled_descent_prior_to_crash_of_Germanwings_Flight_9525,_French_authorities_say","wid":2120996,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-22T02:52:46Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, date\u003dMarch 29, 2015, title\u003dOfficials say co-pilot intentionally crashed Germanwings Airbus]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, date\u003dMarch 25, 2015, title\u003dGermanwings Flight 9525 crashes into French Alps, 150 on board]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/05/06/europe/france-germanwings-crash-report/, title\u003dReport: Germanwings crash co-pilot tested 100-foot descent setting, author\u003dLaura Smith-Spark, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMay 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/International/germanwings-crash-pilots-test-drops/story?id\u003d30841399, title\u003dGermanwings Crash: What We Know About the Co-Pilot\u0027s \u0027Test\u0027 Drops, author\u003dMeghan Keneally, pub\u003dABC News, date\u003dMay 6, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[disasters_and_accidents]  A report from TEMPLATE[w, France, French] TEMPLATE[w, Bureau of Enquiry and Analysis for Civil Aviation Safety, safety officials] released on Wednesday said the co-pilot, Andreas Lubitz, practiced putting a plane into a controlled descent earlier in the day of the March 24 crash of TEMPLATE[w, Germanwings Flight 9525], which officials allege the co-pilot caused by a controlled descent. The report was based on data from the plane\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, flight recorder, flight recorders].","According to the report, the TEMPLATE[w, flight data recorder] indicated the captain left the cockpit for a few minutes. During these few minutes, TEMPLATE[w, air traffic control] told the TEMPLATE[w, Airbus A320] to decend from 37,000 to 35,000 feet. But the co-pilot has set the altitude to a much lower than that before going back to 35,000 feet.","The co-pilot then set the altitude close to the ground again after air traffic control instructed descent to 21,000 feet. The plane remained on its flight path throughout, so there was no deviation from flight path for air traffic controllers to notice. The report does not say whether the pilot on the \"test\" flight also piloted the accident flight.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Barcelona","description":"Category:Barcelona"},{"id":"Category:Spain","description":"Category:Spain"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Bureau_of_Enquiry_and_Analysis_for_Civil_Aviation_Safety","description":"Category:Bureau of Enquiry and Analysis for Civil Aviation Safety"},{"id":"Category:Germanwings_Flight_9525","description":"Category:Germanwings Flight 9525"},{"id":"Category:Germanwings","description":"Category:Germanwings"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 9, 2015"]},{"name":"disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["France","French"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bureau of Enquiry and Analysis for Civil Aviation Safety","safety officials"]},{"name":"w","description":["Germanwings Flight 9525"]},{"name":"w","description":["flight recorder","flight recorders"]},{"name":"w","description":["flight data recorder"]},{"name":"w","description":["air traffic control"]},{"name":"w","description":["Airbus A320"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["date\u003dMarch 29, 2015","title\u003dOfficials say co-pilot intentionally crashed Germanwings Airbus"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["date\u003dMarch 25, 2015","title\u003dGermanwings Flight 9525 crashes into French Alps, 150 on board"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/05/06/europe/france-germanwings-crash-report/","title\u003dReport: Germanwings crash co-pilot tested 100-foot descent setting","author\u003dLaura Smith-Spark","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMay 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/International/germanwings-crash-pilots-test-drops/story?id\u003d30841399","title\u003dGermanwings Crash: What We Know About the Co-Pilot\u0027s \u0027Test\u0027 Drops","author\u003dMeghan Keneally","pub\u003dABC News","date\u003dMay 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["date","title","date","title","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Conservatives win majority in 2015 UK general election","wikiTitle":"Conservatives_win_majority_in_2015_UK_general_election","wid":2125560,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-04T00:09:05Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, date\u003dApril 10, 2015, title\u003dLabour grabs poll lead in UK General Election campaign]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dUK elections: Hung parliament, Cameron to negotiate with Liberal Democrats, date\u003dMay 7, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003d2010 UK general election results, date\u003dMay 6, 2010]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election/2015/results, title\u003dElection 2015 - Results, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 9, 2015 (access date)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1480319/inquiry-to-be-held-into-election-poll-accuracy, title\u003dInquiry To Be Held Into Election Poll Accuracy, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dMay 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-32659720, title\u003dUK election results: David Cameron pledges a \u0027greater Britain\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-scotland-32635871, title\u003dElection 2015: SNP wins 56 of 59 seats in Scots landslide, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.mirror.co.uk/news/uk-news/52-minutes-shook-britain-miliband-5661173, title\u003d52 minutes that shook Britain: Miliband, Clegg and Farage all resign in election bloodbath, author\u003dDan Bloom, pub\u003dDaily Mirror, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-wales-32610447, title\u003dElection 2015: Best Welsh Tory election for 30 years, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dEyEMw-P7Ie8, title\u003dPrime Minister David Cameron\u0027s arrival in Downing Street, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dYouTube, date\u003dMay 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[Video]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.itv.com/news/2015-05-08/prime-minister-reappoints-four-cabinet-members/, title\u003dPrime Minister reappoints four Cabinet members, author\u003d, pub\u003dITV News, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-scotland-32641832, title\u003dElection 2015: SNP wins all seven Glasgow seats, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/05/08/europe/uk-general-election/index.html, title\u003dUK election shock: David Cameron defies polls with clear victory, author\u003dLaura Smith-Spark and Paul Armstrong, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/politics/generalelection/ed-miliband-resigns-the-labour-leaders-resignation-speech--full-text-10236019.html, title\u003dEd Miliband resigns: The Labour leader\u0027s resignation speech - full text, author\u003dJon Stone, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-32633462, title\u003dElection results: Nick Clegg resigns after Lib Dem losses, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/health-32633388, title\u003dLabour election results: Ed Miliband resigns as leader, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"UK"},{"id":"Conservative_Party_(UK)","description":"Conservative Party"},{"id":"Liberal_Democrats_(UK)","description":"Liberal Democrats"},{"id":"Labour_Party_(UK)","description":"Labour Party"},{"id":"United_Kingdom_Independence_Party","description":"UKIP"},{"id":"Green_Party_(UK)","description":"Greens"},{"id":"England","description":"England"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scotland"},{"id":"Scottish_National_Party","description":"Scottish National Party"},{"id":"Wales","description":"Wales"},{"id":"Northern_Ireland","description":"Northern Ireland"},{"id":"Ed_Miliband","description":"Ed Miliband"},{"id":"Nigel_Farage","description":"Nigel Farage"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related articles","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] David Cameron is to continue being TEMPLATE[w, Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, Prime Minister] of the UK after his Conservative Party won a majority of seats in a general election on Thursday. Although the party led a Coalition government it formed alongside the Liberal Democrats after the previous general election in 2010, this is the first time the party has won an overall majority since 1992. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, Our manifesto is a manifesto for working people and as a majority government, we will be able to deliver all of it. Indeed, it is the reason why I think majority government is more accountable, source\u003d\u0027\u0027[[David Cameron]]\u0027\u0027]","Across the UK, Conservatives won 331 seats out of the 650 available, an increase of 24 on their 2010 total. The Labour Party, which won 258 seats in 2010, now has 232. The Liberal Democrats experienced the heaviest number of seat losses, dropping from 57 to eight. Amongst the Liberal Democrat figures to lose seats were TEMPLATE[w, David Laws], TEMPLATE[w, Charles Kennedy], TEMPLATE[w, Simon Hughes], TEMPLATE[w, Jo Swinson], TEMPLATE[w, Lynne Featherstone] and TEMPLATE[w, Jenny Willott]. Liberal Democrats leader TEMPLATE[w, Nick Clegg] said while \"fear and grievance have won, liberalism has lost\".","Although UKIP and the Greens each only won one seat, their national vote share increased by 9.5% to 12.6% and by 2.8% to 3.8%, respectively; this compares to 7.9% for the Liberal Democrats, 30.4% for Labour and 36.9% for Conservatives. Statistics reported by the BBC suggest the voting turnout was 66.1%, based on an electorate of approximately 46.4 million.","The bulk of Conservative seat increases occurred in England, where their seat total increased by 21 to 319 out of a possible 533. Labour\u0027s seat count here increased by 15 to 206, while the Liberal Democrats dropped from 43 seats to six. The final results defied opinion polls, which had broadly suggested Labour and Conservatives were tied for the lead. An independent inquiry is set to be conducted into opinion polling accuracy in the UK, given they had appeared to underestimate the Conservatives\u0027 success and/or overestimate Labour\u0027s results.","\"I truly believe we are on the brink of something special in our country\", David Cameron said in a speech yesterday. \"We can make Britain a place where a good life is in reach for everyone who is willing to work and do the right thing. Our manifesto is a manifesto for working people and as a majority government, we will be able to deliver all of it. Indeed, it is the reason why I think majority government is more accountable.\" In highlighting what a Conservative government would set out to achieve, he said it would include \"Three million apprenticeships, more help with childcare, helping 30 million people cope with the cost of living by cutting their taxes, building homes that people are able to buy and own, creating millions more jobs that give people the chance of a better future and yes, we will deliver that TEMPLATE[w, Proposed referendum on United Kingdom membership of the European Union, in-out referendum on our future in Europe].\" He went on to talk about new powers the UK Government had and would TEMPLATE[w, devolution, devolve] to regional administrations in Wales, Northern Ireland and Scotland. For the latter, he said, \"our plans are to create the strongest devolved government anywhere in the world with important powers over taxation.\"","In Scotland, the Scottish National Party (SNP) made the largest gains of any party in the UK, increasing from six seats to 56 seats out of a possible 59, the highest number they have ever had, based on a Scotland vote share of approximately 50%. The number of constituencies held by Labour and Liberal Democrats there decreased from 41 and 11, respectively, to one for each of them, with the Conservatives staying at one seat. SNP leader TEMPLATE[w, Nicola Sturgeon], who said this result had surpassed her expectations, said \"the tectonic plates of Scottish politics [have] shifted\".  Sturgeon also stated that the SNP would \"work with others across the UK, to try to get more progressive politics at the heart of Westminster\". One seat, TEMPLATE[w, Glasgow North East (UK Parliament constituency), Glasgow North East], experienced a record swing of 39% from Labour to the SNP. On top of that, 20-year-old student and SNP candidate TEMPLATE[w, Mhairi Black] became the youngest MP to be elected in the UK since 1667.","In Wales, Conservatives went up from eight to eleven of a possible 40 seats. Labour achieved 25, down one from 2010; the Liberal Democrats went down two to one seat and TEMPLATE[w, Plaid Cymru] remained at three seats. In Northern Ireland, most of the 18 constituencies did not change hands. However, TEMPLATE[w, Sinn FÃ©in] went down one to four seats, while the TEMPLATE[w, Alliance Party of Northern Ireland, Alliance Party] lost their one seat. The TEMPLATE[w, Ulster Unionist Party], who did not win any seats in the last general election, won two seats this time.","TEMPLATE[w, Shadow Chancellor] TEMPLATE[w, Ed Balls] was one of the high profile losses for Labour, having lost his seat to the Conservatives by a narrow 422-vote margin. Numerous Liberal Democrats who were previously government ministers, including TEMPLATE[w, Ed Davey], TEMPLATE[w, Vince Cable] and TEMPLATE[w, Danny Alexander], all lost their seats. In the wake of the results, Ed Miliband, Nick Clegg and Nigel Farage all announced they would resign from their roles as the leaders of Labour, Liberal Democrats and UKIP, respectively. Farage had said he would stand down as leader if he did not win the seat of TEMPLATE[w, Thanet South, Thanet South], which he did not, but said yesterday he was considering whether or not to stand in a leadership election for the party later this year. Clegg described the situation for his party as \"a very dark hour for our party\". He blamed the large loss of Liberal Democrat MPs on \"forces beyond their control\", describing the situation as \"simply heartbreaking\". Meanwhile, Miliband said \"I have done my best for nearly five years\" and that \"Britain needs a Labour Party that can rebuild after this defeat\". TEMPLATE[w, Harriet Harman] â the current deputy leader â is to serve as interim leader until a new Labour leader is selected. Harman also intends to resign the deputy leadership.","TEMPLATE[w, Tom Watson (politician), Tom Watson], Labour MP for TEMPLATE[w, West Bromwich East], said he is considering running for Labour deputy leader. \"I\u0027ve always thought that the deputy leader role is the campaigning role\", he said. \"We\u0027ve got a mayoral election in Tower Hamlets to fight in six weeks\u0027 time. Who knows, we might even have a by-election for London mayor. So this party has got to keep campaigning whilst we try and understand what\u0027s gone on in the general election.\"","Meanwhile, Cameron has begun to appoint members of his new cabinet, announcing TEMPLATE[w, George Osborne], TEMPLATE[w, Theresa May], TEMPLATE[w, Philip Hammond] and TEMPLATE[w, Michael Fallon] are to retain their posts as TEMPLATE[w, Chancellor of the Exchequer], TEMPLATE[w, Home Secretary], TEMPLATE[w, Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, Foreign Secretary] and TEMPLATE[w, Secretary of State for Defence, Defence Secretary], respectively.","TEMPLATE[picture_select, width\u003d240px, [[File:Davidcameron.jpg, 230px, center, David Cameron, Conservative Party leader and Prime Minister. (TEMPLATE)]]David Cameron, Conservative Party leader and Prime Minister. (TEMPLATE), [[File:Ed Miliband.jpg, 230px, center, Ed Miliband, outgoing Labour Party leader. (TEMPLATE)]]Ed Miliband, outgoing Labour Party leader. (TEMPLATE), [[File:Nick Clegg - World Economic Forum Annual Meeting 2011.jpg, 230px, center, Nick Clegg, outgoing Liberal Democrats leader. (TEMPLATE)]]Nick Clegg, outgoing Liberal Democrats leader. (TEMPLATE), [[File:Nigel Farage (2).jpg, 230px, center, Nigel Farage, outgoing UKIP leader. (TEMPLATE)]]Nigel Farage, outgoing UKIP leader. (TEMPLATE), [[File:Nicola Sturgeon, Deputy First Minister \u0026 Cabinet Secretary for Health \u0026 Wellbeing SMALL.JPG, 230px, center, Nicola Sturgeon, Scottish National Party leader and Scottish First Minister. (TEMPLATE)]]Nicola Sturgeon, Scottish National Party leader and Scottish First Minister. (TEMPLATE)]","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, United Kingdom general election, 2015, United Kingdom general election, 2010]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Conservative_Party_(UK)","description":"Category:Conservative Party (UK)"},{"id":"Category:Labour_Party_(UK)","description":"Category:Labour Party (UK)"},{"id":"Category:Liberal_Democrats_(UK)","description":"Category:Liberal Democrats (UK)"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Ed_Miliband","description":"Category:Ed Miliband"},{"id":"Category:Nick_Clegg","description":"Category:Nick Clegg"},{"id":"Category:Nigel_Farage","description":"Category:Nigel Farage"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_National_Party","description":"Category:Scottish National Party"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom_Independence_Party","description":"Category:United Kingdom Independence Party"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:Wales","description":"Category:Wales"},{"id":"Category:Northern_Ireland","description":"Category:Northern Ireland"},{"id":"Category:Simon_Hughes","description":"Category:Simon Hughes"},{"id":"Category:Green_Party_(UK)","description":"Category:Green Party (UK)"},{"id":"Category:Plaid_Cymru","description":"Category:Plaid Cymru"},{"id":"Category:Vince_Cable","description":"Category:Vince Cable"},{"id":"Category:George_Osborne","description":"Category:George Osborne"},{"id":"Category:Theresa_May","description":"Category:Theresa May"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_Liberal_Democrat_Party","description":"Category:Scottish Liberal Democrat Party"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_Labour_Party","description":"Category:Scottish Labour Party"},{"id":"Category:Tom_Morris_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Tom Morris (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Nicola_Sturgeon","description":"Category:Nicola Sturgeon"},{"id":"Category:2015_United_Kingdom_general_election","description":"Category:2015 United Kingdom general election"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 9, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Prime Minister of the United Kingdom","Prime Minister"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["Our manifesto is a manifesto for working people and as a majority government, we will be able to deliver all of it. Indeed, it is the reason why I think majority government is more accountable","source\u003d\u0027\u0027[[David Cameron]]\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["David Laws"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles Kennedy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Simon Hughes"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jo Swinson"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lynne Featherstone"]},{"name":"w","description":["J