{"title":"Fatalities, multiple injuries in Texas tornado","wikiTitle":"Fatalities,_multiple_injuries_in_Texas_tornado","wid":2132221,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-23T05:25:38Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/05/11/us/severe-weather-damage-injuries/, title\u003d5 dead, dozens injured after tornadoes blast central U.S., author\u003dAnn Colwell, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMay 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.kltv.com/story/29027194/van-fire-rotation-spotted-in-van-houses-damaged, title\u003dNWS confirms EF-3 hit Van area; dozens hospitalized, 2 dead, author\u003dJeff Wright, Gabby Sims, Ashley Slayton, pub\u003dKLTV, date\u003dMay 11, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[Disasters_and_accidents] A TEMPLATE[w, tornado] tore through much of the town of TEMPLATE[w, Van, Texas, Van], TEMPLATE[w, Texas] late Sunday evening. Officials said over 40 people were transported to local hospitals for treatment and reportedly two people died during the storm \u0026mdash; David Tapley, a retired TEMPLATE[w, Garland, Texas, Garland], Texas police officer, and his wife.","The TEMPLATE[w, National Weather Service] estimated winds over 130 TEMPLATE[w, miles per hour] (210 TEMPLATE[w, kilometres per hour]) during the tornado. Late Monday afternoon, debris was still scattered over much of the central portion of the town. An historic building which served as the town\u0027s first school suffered significant damage. Other school buildings were also damaged. All classes for students were cancelled for Monday.","Work crews and numerous utility trucks were on site Monday and the city\u0027s main street remained closed to thru traffic. A residential area on the town\u0027s eastern side was littered with debris and downed trees could be seen along the streets. Fifteen fire departments across five Texas counties responded following the storm, according to the county fire marshal. TEMPLATE[picture_select, width\u003d425px, [[File:Fence debris Van tornado.JPG, thumb, center, 400px, Debris hangs on a fence skirting an athletic field in the central part of the town. (TEMPLATE)]], [[File:Trailer debris Van.JPG, thumb, center, 400px, A trailer stacked with debris from the storm. An historic building (seen in background), located in the central part of the town, shows damage. (TEMPLATE)]], [[File:Workers debris Van.JPG, thumb, center, 400px, Workers clean up debris from a large field located near the central part of the town. Utility trucks are seen in the background. (TEMPLATE)]], [[File:Utility trucks leaving Van.JPG, thumb, center, 400px, Utility trucks seen leaving the town on Monday afternoon. (TEMPLATE)]], [[File:Van roadblock eastern edge.JPG, thumb, center, 400px, A police roadblock seen along the town\u0027s eastern edge on Monday afternoon. (TEMPLATE)]]] TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Weather","description":"Category:Weather"},{"id":"Category:Tornadoes","description":"Category:Tornadoes"},{"id":"Category:Texas","description":"Category:Texas"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["tornado"]},{"name":"w","description":["Van, Texas","Van"]},{"name":"w","description":["Texas"]},{"name":"w","description":["Garland, Texas","Garland"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Weather Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["miles per hour"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometres per hour"]},{"name":"picture_select","description":["width\u003d425px","[[File:Fence debris Van tornado.JPG","thumb","center","400px","Debris hangs on a fence skirting an athletic field in the central part of the town. (TEMPLATE)]]","[[File:Trailer debris Van.JPG","thumb","center","400px","A trailer stacked with debris from the storm. An historic building (seen in background), located in the central part of the town, shows damage. (TEMPLATE)]]","[[File:Workers debris Van.JPG","thumb","center","400px","Workers clean up debris from a large field located near the central part of the town. Utility trucks are seen in the background. (TEMPLATE)]]","[[File:Utility trucks leaving Van.JPG","thumb","center","400px","Utility trucks seen leaving the town on Monday afternoon. (TEMPLATE)]]","[[File:Van roadblock eastern edge.JPG","thumb","center","400px","A police roadblock seen along the town\u0027s eastern edge on Monday afternoon. (TEMPLATE)]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[User:Bddpaux","Paul Budd]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[User:Bddpaux","Paul Budd]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[User:Bddpaux","Paul Budd]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[User:Bddpaux","Paul Budd]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[User:Bddpaux","Paul Budd]]"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/05/11/us/severe-weather-damage-injuries/","title\u003d5 dead, dozens injured after tornadoes blast central U.S.","author\u003dAnn Colwell","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMay 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.kltv.com/story/29027194/van-fire-rotation-spotted-in-van-houses-damaged","title\u003dNWS confirms EF-3 hit Van area; dozens hospitalized, 2 dead","author\u003dJeff Wright, Gabby Sims, Ashley Slayton","pub\u003dKLTV","date\u003dMay 11, 2015"]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["width","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"UK Independence Party reject leader\u0027s resignation","wikiTitle":"UK_Independence_Party_reject_leader\u0027s_resignation","wid":2132251,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-05-21T15:40:47Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dConservatives win majority in 2015 UK general election, date\u003dMay 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/nigel-farage/11598007/Nigel-Farage-Why-I-decided-I-had-to-stay-on-as-Ukip-leader.html, title\u003dNigel Farage: Why I decided I had to stay on as Ukip leader, author\u003dNigel Farage, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dMay 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/UKIP/posts/945812968773927, title\u003dStatement from Steve Crowther, Chairman of UKIP, author\u003d[[United Kingdom Independence Party, UKIP]], pub\u003dFacebook, date\u003dMay 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election/2015/results, title\u003dElection 2015 - Results, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 11, 2015 (access date)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32633719, title\u003dNigel Farage resigns as UKIP leader as the party vote rises, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[Video]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32612295, title\u003dElection 2015: The Nigel Farage story, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 8, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Nigel_Farage","description":"Nigel Farage"},{"id":"United_Kingdom_Independence_Party","description":"UK Independence Party"},{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"UK"},{"id":"Conservatives_win_majority_in_2015_UK_general_election","description":"general election"},{"id":"Conservative_Party_(UK)","description":"Conservatives"},{"id":"Scottish_National_Party","description":"SNP"},{"id":"European_Union","description":"European Union"},{"id":"WWII","description":"WWII"},{"id":"Ed_Miliband","description":"Ed Miliband"},{"id":"Nick_Clegg","description":"Nick Clegg"},{"id":"Liberal_Democrats","description":"Liberal Democrats"},{"id":"Labour_Party_(UK)","description":"Labour"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related articles","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Politics_and_conflicts] Nigel Farage today reversed his decision to stand down as leader of the UK Independence Party (UKIP) after its National Executive Committee (NEC) rejected his resignation. Farage had previously said he would stand down as leader because he did not win the TEMPLATE[w, South Thanet (UK Parliament constituency), South Thanet] seat in last week\u0027s UK general election.","\"This offer was unanimously rejected by the NEC members who produced overwhelmingly evidence that the UKIP membership did not want Nigel to go\", UKIP chairman Steve Crowther said in a statement. \"The NEC also concluded that UKIP\u0027s general election campaign had been a great success. We have fought a positive campaign with a very good manifesto and despite relentless, negative attacks and an astonishing last minute swing to the Conservatives over fear of the SNP [Scottish National Party], that in these circumstances, 4 million votes was an extraordinary achievement. On that basis Mr Farage withdrew his resignation and will remain leader of UKIP. In addition the NEC recognised that the TEMPLATE[w, 2016 UK EU referendum, Proposed referendum on United Kingdom membership of the European Union, [in-out EU membership] referendum] campaign has already begun this week and we need our best team to fight that campaign led by Nigel.\" TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, I realise now that the party comes before me, and indeed, that this country comes before both, source\u003d\u0027\u0027Nigel Farage, UKIP leader\u0027\u0027]","In an article for TEMPLATE[w, The Daily Telegraph], Farage said he had been reluctant to continue being party leader but, in the face of evidence presented to him by the NEC, \"I breathed deep, and thought for as long as I possibly had, given the meeting was ongoing, and still is, at my time of writing this. I decided that as much as I had earned my holidays. As much as I wanted to spend the summer fishing, walking, and of course, in the European Parliament where all hell is currently breaking loose \u0026mdash; that I owed it to the party that got me here. There are some huge battles about to take place, and as much as I had thought that taking at least the summer off was in my best interests, I realise now that the party comes before me, and indeed, that this country comes before both.\"","Highlighting some issues UKIP supports, including UK withdrawal from the European Union and electoral reform, Farage said: \"I feel the need to stay involved for just a little bit longer, to add my voice to those who want Britain to be a country that trades and deals with the world, rather than ties itself to a post-WWII mind set about Europe and the political union.\" In concluding remarks, he wrote: \"Have I done the right thing by my party and my country? I think so. And Iâm sure many people will have their opinions on the matter. All I can say is that Iâm ready for the challenges ahead. The fight starts here.\" TEMPLATE[HYS_question_left, Did Nigel Farage make the right decision?]","Farage, who has lead the party since 2010, announced his resignation on Friday, with the recommendation that TEMPLATE[w, Suzanne Evans] serve as interim leader. \"I feel a huge weight has been lifted off my shoulders\", he commented at the time. After intending to \"take the summer off, enjoy meself a little bit, not do very much politics at all\", Farage said, a UKIP leadership election would happen in September; he would decide whether or not to stand again as leader at a later date. On the same day, Ed Miliband had announced he would stand down as Labour leader, while Nick Clegg said he would resign as leader of the Liberal Democrats.","UKIP achieved a 12.6% share of the vote at the general election, an increase of 9.5% on their 2010 performance, placing them third behind Labour and Conservatives in terms of popular vote. However, the party gained only one seat out of 650, taken by TEMPLATE[w, Douglas Carswell]. Farage has claimed these results illustrate how TEMPLATE[w, First-past-the-post voting, first-past-the-post], the electoral system used in UK general elections, is \"bankrupt because one party can get 50% of the vote in Scotland and nearly 100% of the seats, and our party can get 4 million votes and just one seat. [...] For those reasons there are a lot of angry UKIP people out there. They\u0027re not giving up on UKIP, but absolutely determined that we get a fairer, more reflective system.\"","Farage was once a Conservative Party member but left the party, objecting to the UK\u0027s decision to sign the TEMPLATE[w, Maastricht Treaty] creating the European Union, and became a founding member of UKIP in 1993. He was elected as an TEMPLATE[w, Member of the European Parliament, MEP] for TEMPLATE[w, South East England (European Parliament constituency), South East England] in 1999 and began his first stint as party leader in 2006. He stood down in 2009 in an attempt to challenge TEMPLATE[w, UK House of Commons, House of Commons] TEMPLATE[w, Speaker of the House of Commons (United Kingdom), Speaker] TEMPLATE[w, John Bercow] in the 2010 general election; after this challenge proved unsuccessful, he was re-elected as party leader.","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom_Independence_Party","description":"Category:United Kingdom Independence Party"},{"id":"Category:Nigel_Farage","description":"Category:Nigel Farage"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:2015_United_Kingdom_general_election","description":"Category:2015 United Kingdom general election"},{"id":"Category:Daily_Telegraph_(United_Kingdom)","description":"Category:Daily Telegraph (United Kingdom)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Politics_and_conflicts","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["South Thanet (UK Parliament constituency)","South Thanet"]},{"name":"w","description":["2016 UK EU referendum","Proposed referendum on United Kingdom membership of the European Union","[in-out EU membership] referendum"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["I realise now that the party comes before me, and indeed, that this country comes before both","source\u003d\u0027\u0027Nigel Farage, UKIP leader\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Daily Telegraph"]},{"name":"HYS_question_left","description":["Did Nigel Farage make the right decision?"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suzanne Evans"]},{"name":"w","description":["Douglas Carswell"]},{"name":"w","description":["First-past-the-post voting","first-past-the-post"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maastricht Treaty"]},{"name":"w","description":["Member of the European Parliament","MEP"]},{"name":"w","description":["South East England (European Parliament constituency)","South East England"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK House of Commons","House of Commons"]},{"name":"w","description":["Speaker of the House of Commons (United Kingdom)","Speaker"]},{"name":"w","description":["John Bercow"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dConservatives win majority in 2015 UK general election","date\u003dMay 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/nigel-farage/11598007/Nigel-Farage-Why-I-decided-I-had-to-stay-on-as-Ukip-leader.html","title\u003dNigel Farage: Why I decided I had to stay on as Ukip leader","author\u003dNigel Farage","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dMay 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/UKIP/posts/945812968773927","title\u003dStatement from Steve Crowther, Chairman of UKIP","author\u003d[[United Kingdom Independence Party","UKIP]]","pub\u003dFacebook","date\u003dMay 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election/2015/results","title\u003dElection 2015 - Results","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMay 11, 2015 (access date)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32633719","title\u003dNigel Farage resigns as UKIP leader as the party vote rises","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMay 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Video","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32612295","title\u003dElection 2015: The Nigel Farage story","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMay 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["source","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, The Daily Telegraph]"]}
{"title":"Over 900 asylum seekers rescued off Indonesian coast","wikiTitle":"Over_900_asylum_seekers_rescued_off_Indonesian_coast","wid":2144299,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-26T18:05:12Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theage.com.au/world/as-we-were-swimming-we-cried-for-help-over-900-migrants-rescued-as-pressure-grows-over-southeast-asia-crisis-20150515-gh30q2.html, title\u003d \u0027As we were swimming, we cried for help\u0027: Over 900 migrants rescued as pressure grows over South-East Asia crisis, author\u003d Nurdin Hasan ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003d The Age, date\u003d May 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/16/indonesian-navy-rescues-200-from-ocean-near-aceh-after-750-saved-earlier, title\u003d Indonesian navy rescues 200 from ocean near Aceh, after 750 saved earlier, author\u003d, pub\u003d The Guardian, date\u003d May 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-15/indonesia-rescues-200-asylum-seekers-off-aceh-coast/6474572, title\u003d Indonesia\u0027s navy rescues 200 more asylum seekers from waters of Aceh, author\u003d George Roberts, pub\u003d ABC News (Australia), date\u003d May 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-15/700-migrants-rescued-off-indonesia-police-say/6473352, title\u003d At least 750 migrants rescued off Indonesia by local fishermen after boat sinks, police say, author\u003d(TEMPLATE)/(TEMPLATE), pub\u003d ABC News (Australia), date\u003d May 15, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Indonesia","description":"Indonesia"},{"id":"Bangladesh","description":"Bangladesh"},{"id":"Myanmar","description":"Myanmar"},{"id":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysia"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"Thailand","description":"Thailand"},{"id":"John_Kerry","description":"John Kerry"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[Indonesia] On Friday, fishermen rescued over 700 asylum seekers whose boat sank, and the Indonesian Navy reportedly saved 200 more after they were found swimming along the coast of TEMPLATE[w, Aceh], Indonesia.","Major general Fuad Basya, spokesman for the Indonesian military, said fisherman first noticed the people and a warship was deployed to retrieve them. The rescued members included Bangladeshis and TEMPLATE[w, Rohingya], a stateless minority of TEMPLATE[w, Islam, Muslims] from Myanmar. Myanmar is mainly TEMPLATE[w, Buddhist] and the TEMPLATE[w, United Nations] rates the Rohingya among the world\u0027s most persecuted groups. According to ABC News, Basya also believes the asylum seekers found in the water may have left the boat on purpose to be rescued to avoid being sent away from Indonesia waters.","Malaysia and Indonesia have maintained a policy of turning away boats of migrants which, according to TEMPLATE[w, Agence France-Presse, AFP], the Untied Nations and United States have both criticised.","One Rohingya, Muhammad Amin, the first boat rescued on Friday was turned around twice, toward Malaysia by Indonesian navy and then toward Indonesia by Malaysian navy.","Discussing his concern in a public statement, Malaysia\u0027s Prime Minister, TEMPLATE[w, Najib Razak] said, \"We are in contact with all relevant parties, with whom we share the desire to find a solution to this crisis\".","Thailand has recently cracked down on TEMPLATE[w, human trafficking], which has affected the routes by which TEMPLATE[w, people smuggling, people-smugglers] transport migrants.","The US State Department said John Kerry, the Secretary of State, contacted Thailand\u0027s foreign minister over temporary housing for the Rohingya out at sea. Jeff Rathke, the State Department Spokesperson, said, \"We urge the governments of the region to work together quickly, first and foremost, to save the lives of migrants now at sea who are in need of an immediate rescue effort\". Rathke also asked the governments of South East Asia not to turn away boats of people seeking asylum.","Estimates suggest 8000 migrants may be currently at sea in the region.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia","description":"Category:Indonesia"},{"id":"Category:Bangladesh","description":"Category:Bangladesh"},{"id":"Category:Myanmar","description":"Category:Myanmar"},{"id":"Category:Thailand","description":"Category:Thailand"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:John_Kerry","description":"Category:John Kerry"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Indonesia","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Aceh"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rohingya"]},{"name":"w","description":["Islam","Muslims"]},{"name":"w","description":["Buddhist"]},{"name":"w","description":["United Nations"]},{"name":"w","description":["Agence France-Presse","AFP"]},{"name":"w","description":["Najib Razak"]},{"name":"w","description":["human trafficking"]},{"name":"w","description":["people smuggling","people-smugglers"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.theage.com.au/world/as-we-were-swimming-we-cried-for-help-over-900-migrants-rescued-as-pressure-grows-over-southeast-asia-crisis-20150515-gh30q2.html","title\u003d \u0027As we were swimming, we cried for help\u0027: Over 900 migrants rescued as pressure grows over South-East Asia crisis","author\u003d Nurdin Hasan ((TEMPLATE))","pub\u003d The Age","date\u003d May 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/16/indonesian-navy-rescues-200-from-ocean-near-aceh-after-750-saved-earlier","title\u003d Indonesian navy rescues 200 from ocean near Aceh, after 750 saved earlier","author\u003d","pub\u003d The Guardian","date\u003d May 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-15/indonesia-rescues-200-asylum-seekers-off-aceh-coast/6474572","title\u003d Indonesia\u0027s navy rescues 200 more asylum seekers from waters of Aceh","author\u003d George Roberts","pub\u003d ABC News (Australia)","date\u003d May 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-15/700-migrants-rescued-off-indonesia-police-say/6473352","title\u003d At least 750 migrants rescued off Indonesia by local fishermen after boat sinks, police say","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)/(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003d ABC News (Australia)","date\u003d May 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Jim Murphy announces resignation as Scottish Labour Party leader","wikiTitle":"Jim_Murphy_announces_resignation_as_Scottish_Labour_Party_leader","wid":2144646,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-04T00:09:10Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dUK Independence Party reject leader\u0027s resignation, date\u003dMay 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dConservatives win majority in 2015 UK general election, date\u003dMay 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-32760196, title\u003dScottish Labour leader Jim Murphy to resign, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://archive.is/RLWxF, title\u003dScotland needs a strong Labour party, author\u003d, pub\u003dScottish Labour Party, date\u003dMay 16, 2015 (access date)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.itv.com/news/2015-05-16/whoever-replaces-jim-murphy-faces-an-even-bigger-task/, title\u003dWhoever replaces Jim Murphy faces an even bigger task, author\u003dDebi Edward, pub\u003dITV News, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/NicolaSturgeon/status/599566155246903296, title\u003dI wish Jim Murphy all the very best for the future, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/RuthDavidsonMSP/status/599567822218522624, title\u003dJim Murphy announces a managed exit in order to help the party, which is to his credit, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/willie_rennie/status/599570564269871105, title\u003dCredit to @jimforscotland, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.itv.com/news/update/2015-05-16/murphy-led-scottish-labour-with-energy-and-dignity/, title\u003dMurphy led Scottish Labour with \u0027energy and dignity\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dITV News, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scottishgreens.org.uk/news/harvie-responds-to-murphy-resignation/, title\u003dHarvie responds to Murphy resignation, author\u003dPatrick Harvie, pub\u003dScottish Green Party, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/unitetheunion/status/599607983396519936, title\u003dPat Rafferty, leader of Unite in Scotland on the resignation of Jim Murphy (1/2), author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/unitetheunion/status/599608189022314496, title\u003d\"Scottish Labour needs to recover (2/2), author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dMay 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-32742516, title\u003dUnite boss McCluskey blames Tory win on Scottish Labour, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-32729492, title\u003dJim Murphy supporters asked to sign letter backing his leadership, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/election-2015-scotland-32703365, title\u003dAlex Rowley and Elaine Smith call for Jim Murphy to resign, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dMay 12, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Jim_Murphy","description":"Jim Murphy"},{"id":"Scottish_Labour_Party","description":"Scottish Labour Party"},{"id":"Scottish_Parliament","description":"Scottish Parliament"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scottish"},{"id":"Glasgow","description":"Glasgow"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scottish"},{"id":"Scottish_National_Party","description":"Scottish National Party"},{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"UK"},{"id":"Conservatives_win_majority_in_2015_UK_general_election","description":"general election"},{"id":"Ed_Miliband","description":"Ed Miliband"},{"id":"UK_Labour_Party","description":"UK Labour Party"},{"id":"trade_union","description":"trade union"},{"id":"Member_of_the_Scottish_Parliament","description":"MSP"},{"id":"Conservative_Party_(UK)","description":"Conservatives"},{"id":"Nicola_Sturgeon","description":"Nicola Sturgeon"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"},{"id":"Scottish_Liberal_Democrat_Party","description":"Scottish Liberal Democrats"},{"id":"Scottish_Green_Party","description":"Scottish Green Party"},{"id":"Scottish_Conservative_Party","description":"Scottish Conservative Party"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related articles","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[Politics_and_conflicts] Jim Murphy yesterday announced he intends to stand down as Scottish Labour Party leader next month, after narrowly surviving a TEMPLATE[w, Motion of no confidence, no confidence] vote. Murphy said he will present a list of suggested reforms to be made to the party, including changing the system for electing party leader to TEMPLATE[w, One member, one vote, one member, one vote], upon offering his resignation at the next meeting of its national executive in June. Murphy also said he will not stand for the Scottish Parliament TEMPLATE[w, Scottish Parliament general election, 2016, election in May 2016] and will \"do something else\".","At a meeting in the Scottish city Glasgow yesterday, the party\u0027s national executive held a vote of no confidence in Murphy; he won by 17 votes to 14. \"Today I received more support in the executive vote than I did from members of the executive when I stood for election five months ago\", Murphy said. Murphy became Scottish Labour leader in December 2014, following TEMPLATE[w, Johann Lamont]\u0027s resignation from the role. Until Scottish Labour holds a fresh leadership election \u0026mdash; its sixth in a span of eight years \u0026mdash; TEMPLATE[w, Kezia Dugdale], currently the party\u0027s deputy leader, is to assume the role of acting leader for the time being. Murphy cited concerns about Scottish Labour being divided as a contributory factor to his decision. \"Scotland needs a strong Labour party; Scotland needs a united Labour party\", he said yesterday. \"We have been the greatest force for change in our nationâs remarkable history. The Scottish Labour party will rise again. It will be under someone elseâs leadership and I am confident about my partyâs future.\"","The announcement came nine days after the party lost all but one of its 41 Scottish seats, including Murphy\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, East Renfrewshire (UK Parliament constituency), East Renfrewshire constituency], to the Scottish National Party (SNP) in a UK general election, and eight days after Ed Miliband said he would stand down as leader of the UK Labour Party.","There was controversy regarding whether Murphy should retain his role following this performance. Labour Party supporters were reportedly asked to sign a letter supporting Murphy\u0027s leadership, to be presented at the executive meeting yesterday. Calls for Murphy to resign came from multiple quarters, including trade unions TEMPLATE[w, Unite the Union, Unite] and TEMPLATE[w, Associated Society of Locomotive Engineers and Firemen, ASLEF], as well as Labour MSPs TEMPLATE[w, Alex Rowley] and TEMPLATE[w, Elaine Smith (Scottish politician), Elaine Smith]. Earlier in the week, Unite general secretary TEMPLATE[w, Len McCluskey] said \"the anti-Scottish card that was played by TEMPLATE[w, Lynton Crosby] and the Conservatives\" had caused them to win a majority in the general election, before going on to say: \"I lay the blame for that very squarely at the feet of Scottish Labour. Not only have they lost Scotland but I think they\u0027ve been responsible for making certain that the Conservatives were back in power in TEMPLATE[w, Government of the United Kingdom, Westminster].\" However, trade unions TEMPLATE[w, Union of Shop, Distributive and Allied Workers, USDAW] and TEMPLATE[w, Community (trade union), Community] were amongst those supporting Murphy\u0027s continued leadership. TEMPLATE[HYS_question_left, Did Jim Murphy make the right decision?]","In a speech, Murphy suggested he did he did not want the party to be divided as a result of his leadership. \"It is clear that the small minority who didnât accept my election as party leader by the majority five months ago also wonât accept the vote of the Executive today and will continue to divide the party if I remain\", he said. Murphy singled out McCluskey for criticism, claiming to have \"been at the centre of a campaign by the London leadership of the Unite union in blaming myself and the Scottish Labour party for the defeat of the UK Labour party in the general election. That is a grotesque insult to the Scottish Labour party.\" He went on to criticise what he called McCluskey\u0027s \"destructive behaviour\", commenting that: \"Whether in Scotland, or in the contest to come across the UK, we cannot have our leaders selected or deselected by the grudges and grievances of one prominent man. The leader of the Scottish Labour Party doesnât serve at the grace of Len McCluskey and the next leader of the UK Labour Party should not be picked by Len McCluskey.\"","Reacting to the news, SNP leader and Scottish TEMPLATE[w, First Minister of Scotland, First Minister] Nicola Sturgeon tweeted: \"I wish Jim Murphy all the very best for the future. Leadership is not easy and he deserves credit for standing up for what he believes in.\" Scottish Liberal Democrats leader TEMPLATE[w, Willie Rennie] said: \"Credit to [Murphy]. He stepped up and energetically campaigned for his beliefs. I wish him the best for the future.\" TEMPLATE[w, Harriet Harman], the acting leader of the UK Labour Party, said Murphy had been a \"hugely important figure\" for them, adding: \"Jim has given so much to the Labour Party over the last twenty years. He, I know reluctantly, took the responsibility for leading Scottish Labour at the most difficult election they have ever faced. He did so with incredible energy, purpose and dignity [...] He leaves with the best wishes and thanks of our movement.\"","Scottish Green Party TEMPLATE[wikt, convenor, co-convenor] TEMPLATE[w, Patrick Harvie] was more critical in his response, arguing the Greens should be the opposition of the Scottish Parliament instead. Harvie said Murphy\u0027s resignation was \"almost inevitable, but even as he announced it he promised to further weaken Labourâs relationship with the wider labour movement. People havenât left Labour because of the trade unions, but because the party itself long ago strayed from its principles. Without a clear sense of purpose, it has seemed to care only about holding office instead of creating new ideas for a better society. Itâs clear that the Scottish Parliament needs an opposition thatâs creative and challenging, but which can act constructively too.\"","Scottish Conservative Party leader TEMPLATE[w, Ruth Davidson] tweeted: \"Jim Murphy announces a managed exit in order to help the party, which is to his credit. But leaves a tough gig for whoever comes next.\"","Wikinews asked Unite the Union to comment on the story and has yet to receive a response. However, Pat Rafferty, Unite\u0027s Scotland leader, earlier stated: \"Jim has done the decent thing. Scottish Labour needs to recover, re-engage and reform. It can now begin that process.\"","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Labour_Party_(UK)","description":"Category:Labour Party (UK)"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_Labour_Party","description":"Category:Scottish Labour Party"},{"id":"Category:Nicola_Sturgeon","description":"Category:Nicola Sturgeon"},{"id":"Category:Jim_Murphy","description":"Category:Jim Murphy"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Glasgow","description":"Category:Glasgow"},{"id":"Category:Labor","description":"Category:Labor"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_Green_Party","description":"Category:Scottish Green Party"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_Parliament","description":"Category:Scottish Parliament"},{"id":"Category:2015_United_Kingdom_general_election","description":"Category:2015 United Kingdom general election"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Politics_and_conflicts","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Motion of no confidence","no confidence"]},{"name":"w","description":["One member, one vote","one member, one vote"]},{"name":"w","description":["Scottish Parliament general election, 2016","election in May 2016"]},{"name":"w","description":["Johann Lamont"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kezia Dugdale"]},{"name":"w","description":["East Renfrewshire (UK Parliament constituency)","East Renfrewshire constituency"]},{"name":"w","description":["Unite the Union","Unite"]},{"name":"w","description":["Associated Society of Locomotive Engineers and Firemen","ASLEF"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alex Rowley"]},{"name":"w","description":["Elaine Smith (Scottish politician)","Elaine Smith"]},{"name":"w","description":["Len McCluskey"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lynton Crosby"]},{"name":"w","description":["Government of the United Kingdom","Westminster"]},{"name":"w","description":["Union of Shop, Distributive and Allied Workers","USDAW"]},{"name":"w","description":["Community (trade union)","Community"]},{"name":"HYS_question_left","description":["Did Jim Murphy make the right decision?"]},{"name":"w","description":["First Minister of Scotland","First Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["Willie Rennie"]},{"name":"w","description":["Harriet Harman"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["convenor","co-convenor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Patrick Harvie"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ruth Davidson"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dUK Independence Party reject leader\u0027s resignation","date\u003dMay 11, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dConservatives win majority in 2015 UK general election","date\u003dMay 9, 2015"]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-32760196","title\u003dScottish Labour leader Jim Murphy to resign","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dMay 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://archive.is/RLWxF","title\u003dScotland needs a strong Labour party","author\u003d","pub\u003dScottish Labour Party","date\u003dMay 16, 2015 (access date)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.itv.com/news/2015-05-16/whoever-replaces-jim-murphy-faces-an-even-bigger-task/","title\u003dWhoever replaces Jim Murphy faces an even bigger task","author\u003dDebi Edward","pub\u003dITV News","date\u003dMay 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/NicolaSturgeon/status/599566155246903296","title\u003dI wish Jim Murphy all the very best for the future","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dTwitter","date\u003dMay 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/RuthDavidsonMSP/status/599567822218522624","title\u003dJim Murphy announces a managed exit in order to help the party, which is to his credit","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dTwitter","date\u003dMay 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/willie_rennie/status/599570564269871105","title\u003dCredit to @jimforscotland","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dTwitter","date\u003dMay 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp: