{"title":"Nine dead after biker gang feud in Texas","wikiTitle":"Nine_dead_after_biker_gang_feud_in_Texas","wid":2150189,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-25T02:05:36Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-18/nine-dead-several-injured-in-waco-bikie-shootout/6476708, title\u003d Nine dead in shootout between bikies at restaurant in Waco, Texas, author\u003d (TEMPLATE), pub\u003d ABC News (Australia), date\u003d May 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://news.yahoo.com/multiple-injuries-reported-texas-biker-gang-shooting-204703808.html, title\u003d Police: 9 dead in Texas shooting all members of biker gangs, author\u003d Nomaan Merchant ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003d Yahoo! News, date\u003d May 18, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Texas","description":"Texas"},{"id":"Waco,_Texas","description":"Waco"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[Texas] Nine people are dead and eighteen injured after a shootout among alleged rival biker gangs broke out inside a sports bar in Texas yesterday.","The violence erupted at TEMPLATE[w, Twin Peaks (restaurant chain), Twin Peaks] Sports Bar and Grill inside a shopping mall in Waco. The fight which included up to five biker gangs quickly escalated, resulting in a gunfire battle across two car parks. Waco Sergeant Patrick Swanton said an argument about a parking spot may have sparked the fight.","Restaurant customers said they waited out the fight with staff locked in a freezer room. Swanton said all but one of the deaths occurred at the scene, with the ninth in hospital.","Swanton said, \"This is probably one of the most gruesome crime scenes I\u0027ve ever seen in my 34 years of law enforcement\", and, \"I was amazed that we didn\u0027t have innocent civilians killed or injured.\"","Police officers were present and quick to intervene when the shooting broke out as they knew beforehand of a planned meeting.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Waco,_Texas","description":"Category:Waco, Texas"},{"id":"Category:Texas","description":"Category:Texas"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Texas","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Twin Peaks (restaurant chain)","Twin Peaks"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-18/nine-dead-several-injured-in-waco-bikie-shootout/6476708","title\u003d Nine dead in shootout between bikies at restaurant in Waco, Texas","author\u003d (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003d ABC News (Australia)","date\u003d May 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://news.yahoo.com/multiple-injuries-reported-texas-biker-gang-shooting-204703808.html","title\u003d Police: 9 dead in Texas shooting all members of biker gangs","author\u003d Nomaan Merchant ((TEMPLATE))","pub\u003d Yahoo! News","date\u003d May 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"France rejects European Union\u0027s asylum seeker quota initiative","wikiTitle":"France_rejects_European_Union\u0027s_asylum_seeker_quota_initiative","wid":2150662,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-25T02:05:29Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.worldbulletin.net/world/159257/ukraine-bans-soviet-era-symbols, title\u003d France opposes EU\u0027s plan on refugee quota, author\u003d, pub\u003d World Bulletin, date\u003d May 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.english.rfi.fr/europe/20150517-french-prime-minister-valls-opposes-binding-eu-migrant-quotas, title\u003d French Prime Minister Valls opposes binding EU migrant quotas, author\u003d, pub\u003d Radio France Internationale, date\u003d May 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.euronews.com/2015/05/16/french-pm-says-he-is-against-migrant-quotas/, title\u003d French PM says he is against migrant quotas, author\u003d, pub\u003d Euronews, date\u003d May 16, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"European_Commission","description":"European Commission"},{"id":"European_Union","description":"European Union"},{"id":"Germany","description":"Germany"},{"id":"Italy","description":"Italy"},{"id":"Middle_East","description":"Middle East"},{"id":"Niger","description":"Niger"},{"id":"Libya","description":"Libya"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[France] On Saturday, French Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Manuel Valls] stated his opposition to the European Commission\u0027s quota system for distributing TEMPLATE[w, asylum seekers] amongst member countries of the European Union (EU).","The quotas are determined by the TEMPLATE[w, gross domestic product], population, and unemployment levels of countries within the EU, and would mean that Germany, France, and Italy would receive the highest intake of migrants.","Valls did not approve of this scheme, instead suggesting asylum seekers be spread among the nations in a more \"fair distribution\". He said migrants should be denied access to Europe unless they are truly seeking TEMPLATE[w, asylum].","The quota scheme comes amidst a large influx of refugees from the Middle East and North TEMPLATE[w, Africa] who travel along the TEMPLATE[w, Mediterranean Sea]. Within the last week, almost 1000 migrants were seized in southern France near to TEMPLATE[w, Menton].","France has also suggested ways to stop migrants leaving their countries, including establishing a centre for migrants in TEMPLATE[w, Agadez], Niger. This centre, scheduled to be operational toward the end of 2015, is based in Niger as migrants travel through it to get to people smugglers in Libya who then transport them across the Mediterranean Sea.","The EU plans a naval unit to prevent people-smuggling boats from operating in Libyan territory, though it is yet to be approved by the TEMPLATE[w, United Nations Security Council].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:_France","description":"category: France"},{"id":"category:_Europe","description":"category: Europe"},{"id":"Category:European_Union","description":"Category:European Union"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:European_Commission","description":"Category:European Commission"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 18, 2015"]},{"name":"France","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Manuel Valls"]},{"name":"w","description":["asylum seekers"]},{"name":"w","description":["gross domestic product"]},{"name":"w","description":["asylum"]},{"name":"w","description":["Africa"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mediterranean Sea"]},{"name":"w","description":["Menton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Agadez"]},{"name":"w","description":["United Nations Security Council"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.worldbulletin.net/world/159257/ukraine-bans-soviet-era-symbols","title\u003d France opposes EU\u0027s plan on refugee quota","author\u003d","pub\u003d World Bulletin","date\u003d May 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.english.rfi.fr/europe/20150517-french-prime-minister-valls-opposes-binding-eu-migrant-quotas","title\u003d French Prime Minister Valls opposes binding EU migrant quotas","author\u003d","pub\u003d Radio France Internationale","date\u003d May 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.euronews.com/2015/05/16/french-pm-says-he-is-against-migrant-quotas/","title\u003d French PM says he is against migrant quotas","author\u003d","pub\u003d Euronews","date\u003d May 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Yingluck Shinawatra, former Thai prime minister, begins her trial in Bangkok over corruption allegations","wikiTitle":"Yingluck_Shinawatra,_former_Thai_prime_minister,_begins_her_trial_in_Bangkok_over_corruption_allegations","wid":2153130,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-07-21T19:32:51Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-19/former-thai-pm-yingluck-in-court-on-negligence-charges/6481182, title\u003d Thailand general election delayed six months, hours after former PM Yingluck Shinawatra fronts court, author\u003d(TEMPLATE)/(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dABC Australia, date\u003dMay 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-32790248, title\u003d Thai ex-PM Yingluck Shinawatra\u0027s negligence trial begins, author\u003dBBC News, pub\u003dBBC, date\u003dMay 19, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Thailand","description":"Thai"},{"id":"Bangkok","description":"Bangkok"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[image_credit, Gerd Seidel and Rob Irgendwer] Former Thai prime minister TEMPLATE[w, Yingluck Shinawatra] has begun her trial in Bangkok on Tuesday for alleged negligence in a rice subsidy scheme. If convicted she could face up to ten years in jail.","The subsidy scheme was designed to prop up rice prices by spending billions of dollars to acquire the crop at high rates over the market rates.","It has been alleged by her political opponents that this was a way to gain support from poor rice farmers.","\"I am confident that I am innocent and I hope the court will give me justice and allow everything to proceed in accordance with the law,\" Shinawatra told reporters outside the Bangkok courthouse.","12 months ago the former prime minister was removed from office by a military coup after weeks of protests in the Thai capital. The military stating that it had to restore order.","The court has forbidden Shinawatra to leave the country.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Thailand","description":"category:Thailand"},{"id":"category:Asia","description":"category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Bangkok","description":"Category:Bangkok"},{"id":"Category:Yingluck_Shinawatra","description":"Category:Yingluck Shinawatra"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 21, 2015"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Gerd Seidel and Rob Irgendwer"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yingluck Shinawatra"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-19/former-thai-pm-yingluck-in-court-on-negligence-charges/6481182","title\u003d Thailand general election delayed six months, hours after former PM Yingluck Shinawatra fronts court","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)/(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dABC Australia","date\u003dMay 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-32790248","title\u003d Thai ex-PM Yingluck Shinawatra\u0027s negligence trial begins","author\u003dBBC News","pub\u003dBBC","date\u003dMay 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"6.9 Magnitude Earthquake strikes Solomon Islands","wikiTitle":"6.9_Magnitude_Earthquake_strikes_Solomon_Islands","wid":2158423,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-05-30T04:51:37Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.9news.com.au/world/2015/05/21/09/02/strong-earthquake-strikes-off-solomon-islands, title\u003d Magnitude 6.9 earthquake strikes near Solomon Islands, author\u003d, pub\u003d nine news Australia, date\u003d May 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/05/earthquake-hits-solomon-islands-150521025037766.html, title\u003d Earthquake hits the Solomon Islands, author\u003d, pub\u003d Al Jazeera, date\u003d May 21, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 23, 2015] TEMPLATE[image, Tzzzpfff] An earthquake hit close to the TEMPLATE[w, Solomon Islands], in the early hours of Thursday morning. It was about 184 kilometres from Lata and 487 kilometres from the capital Honiara.  The US Geological Survey has stated that Tsunami warnings are yet to be released and that no major damage occurred.","The quake was 6.9 in magnitude and hit a depth of 19 kilometres. It was then followed by a smaller 4.9 magnitude aftershock.","The geographical position of the Solomon Islands places them in âthe ring of fireâ, an area of tectonic activity in the basin of the Pacific Ocean that is subject to frequent earthquakes and volcanic eruptions.","\"This is one of the most active seismic regions in the world -- in the last three years we have had 30 plus earthquakes of over 6.0 magnitude,\" Geoscience Australia Duty Seismologist Marco Maldoni told AFP.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Solomon_Islands","description":"Category:Solomon Islands"},{"id":"Category:Earthquakes","description":"Category:Earthquakes"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 23, 2015"]},{"name":"image","description":["Tzzzpfff"]},{"name":"w","description":["Solomon Islands"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.9news.com.au/world/2015/05/21/09/02/strong-earthquake-strikes-off-solomon-islands","title\u003d Magnitude 6.9 earthquake strikes near Solomon Islands","author\u003d","pub\u003d nine news Australia","date\u003d May 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/05/earthquake-hits-solomon-islands-150521025037766.html","title\u003d Earthquake hits the Solomon Islands","author\u003d","pub\u003d Al Jazeera","date\u003d May 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
