hours this past week. The artist took the title from TEMPLATE[w, Nicki Minaj] who had 19.6 million views for Anaconda in August 2014.","The country-turned-pop singer premiered the video at the Billboard Music Awards where she won several awards including Top Artist and the Billboard Achievement Award.","The video featured celebrities including Mariska Hargitay, Zendaya, Cindy Crawford, Ellen Pompeo, Lily Aldridge and more. Selena Gomez portrays the antagonist.","Victorias secret model Karlie Kloss believes the video could turn into a feature length film.","\"I think she should turn it into a movieâ¦ premiering next year at Cannes,\" she said.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Awards","description":"Category:Awards"},{"id":"Category:Music_videos","description":"Category:Music videos"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 24, 2015"]},{"name":"image","description":["[https://www.flickr.com/people/77979774@N05 Clarence Ji] from London, United Kingdom"]},{"name":"w","description":["Taylor Swift"]},{"name":"w","description":["Vevo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nicki Minaj"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.techtimes.com/articles/54820/20150523/taylor-swifts-bad-blood-breaks-vevos-record-for-most-views-in-24-hours.htm","title\u003dTaylor Swift\u0027s \u0027Bad Blood\u0027 Breaks Vevo\u0027s Record For Most Views In 24 Hours","author\u003d Menchie Mendoza","pub\u003dTech Times","date\u003dMay 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.heraldworldnews.com/taylor-swifts-bad-blood-gets-sets-vevo-record/","title\u003dTaylor Swiftâs âBad Bloodâ gets sets Vevo record","author\u003d","pub\u003d Herald World News","date\u003d May 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.gossipcop.com/karlie-kloss-taylor-swift-bad-blood-movie/","title\u003dKarlie Kloss: Taylor Swiftâs âBad Bloodâ Video Needs To Be a Full-Length Movie","author\u003d Minyvonne Burke","pub\u003d Gossip Cop","date\u003d May 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.billboard.com/articles/news/6575919/taylor-swift-bad-blood-video-karlie-kloss-interview","title\u003dTaylor Swift\u0027s \u0027Bad Blood\u0027 Video Should Be a Movie, Karlie Kloss Says","author\u003d Katie Atkinson","pub\u003dBillboard","date\u003dMay 22, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ew.com/article/2015/05/21/taylor-swift-bad-blood-vevo-record-selena-gomez-kendrick-lamar/article_2199188","title\u003dTaylor Swift\u0027s \u0027Bad Blood\u0027 breaks Vevo record","author\u003dMegan Daley","pub\u003d Entertainment Weekly","date\u003dMay 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Ireland legalises same-sex marriage","wikiTitle":"Ireland_legalises_same-sex_marriage","wid":2166682,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-02T01:12:18Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/05/23/europe/ireland-referendum-same-sex-marriage/, title\u003dIreland votes overwhelmingly in favor of same-sex marriage, author\u003dLaura Smith-Spark, Kevin Conlon and Phil Black, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dMay 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/yes-side-joyous-count-starts-irish-gay-marriage-090519559.html, title\u003dIreland gives resounding 62.1 percent \u0027yes\u0027 to gay marriage, author\u003dShawn Pogatchnik ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003dYahoo! News, date\u003dMay 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/23/gay-marriage-ireland-yes-vote, title\u003dIreland becomes first country to legalise gay marriage by popular vote, author\u003dHenry McDonald, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMay 23, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 24, 2015] TEMPLATE[LGBT] TEMPLATE[w, Ireland] by public vote on Friday legalised TEMPLATE[w, same-sex marriage]. This was the first time a country legalized same-sex marriage by popular vote.  The historic referendum resulted in a landslide sixty percent \"yes\".","Over sixty percent of the nation\u0027s electorate participated in the vote, with about two million counted on Saturday before the result was announced at TEMPLATE[w, Dublin Castle]. A total of 1,201,607 \u0026mdash; 62 percent \u0026mdash; of people voted \"yes\" to gay marriage, with only 734,300 \u0026mdash; 38 percent \u0026mdash; voting \"no\".","Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Enda Kenny] said, \"we have disclosed who we are. We are a generous, compassionate, bold and joyful people who say yes to inclusion, yes to generosity, yes to love, yes to gay marriage.\"","Other political leaders also took to the media to voice their support for the decision. Cabinet minister TEMPLATE[w, Leo Varadkar] remarked, \"We\u0027re the first country in the world to enshrine marriage equality in our constitution and do so by popular mandate. That makes us a beacon, a light to the rest of the world, of liberty and equality. So it\u0027s a very proud day to be Irish\".","Ireland is a majority TEMPLATE[w, Roman Catholicism, Catholic] country. The church opposes same-sex marriage. TEMPLATE[w, Dublin] archbishop TEMPLATE[w, Diarmuid Martin] said Ireland\u0027s vote is part of a \"social revolution\". \"If the referendum is an affirmation of the views of young people, the church has a huge task in front of it,\" he said.","About 2,000 TEMPLATE[w, LGBT] supporters celebrated in the Dublin Castle courtyard on Saturday. Drag queen TEMPLATE[w, Rory O\u0027Neill], publicly known as Panti Bliss, was among the crowd, and stated \"I am drunk on Yes [...] It\u0027s not that Ireland has changed today, but that Ireland has confirmed the change that we already knew had happened.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Ireland","description":"category:Ireland"},{"id":"category:Europe","description":"category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:Same-sex_marriage","description":"Category:Same-sex marriage"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Roman_Catholic_Church","description":"Category:Roman Catholic Church"},{"id":"Category:Christianity","description":"Category:Christianity"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 24, 2015"]},{"name":"LGBT","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Ireland"]},{"name":"w","description":["same-sex marriage"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dublin Castle"]},{"name":"w","description":["Enda Kenny"]},{"name":"w","description":["Leo Varadkar"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roman Catholicism","Catholic"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dublin"]},{"name":"w","description":["Diarmuid Martin"]},{"name":"w","description":["LGBT"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rory O\u0027Neill"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/05/23/europe/ireland-referendum-same-sex-marriage/","title\u003dIreland votes overwhelmingly in favor of same-sex marriage","author\u003dLaura Smith-Spark, Kevin Conlon and Phil Black","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dMay 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/yes-side-joyous-count-starts-irish-gay-marriage-090519559.html","title\u003dIreland gives resounding 62.1 percent \u0027yes\u0027 to gay marriage","author\u003dShawn Pogatchnik ((TEMPLATE))","pub\u003dYahoo! News","date\u003dMay 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/may/23/gay-marriage-ireland-yes-vote","title\u003dIreland becomes first country to legalise gay marriage by popular vote","author\u003dHenry McDonald","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMay 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Torrential rains cause deaths, wreak havoc across much of Texas","wikiTitle":"Torrential_rains_cause_deaths,_wreak_havoc_across_much_of_Texas","wid":2171616,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-04T04:55:39Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2015/05/25/409474791/more-heavy-rain-predicted-for-texas-oklahoma, title\u003dTexas Governor Calls Flood Damage \u0027Devastating\u0027, author\u003dKrishnadev Calamur, pub\u003dNPR, date\u003dMay 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/texas-oklahoma-set-more-flooding-two-families-still-missing-n364086, title\u003dTexas, Oklahoma Floods: 12 People Missing as More Rain Forecast, author\u003dElisha Fieldstadt, Alexander Smith and Gabe Gutierrez, pub\u003dNBC News, date\u003dMay 25, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Texas","description":"Texas"},{"id":"Dallas","description":"Dallas"},{"id":"Houston","description":"Houston"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Texas] TEMPLATE[date, May 27, 2015] Recently, record breaking rainfall has doled out severe destruction over much of the state of Texas, TEMPLATE[w, United States]. The state\u0027s governor called the effects of the storms \"absolutely devastating\". At least two people died over the weekend, while twelve more were reported missing.  TEMPLATE[image, Unknown U.S. Army official] Various rainfall records have been broken all over the state in recent days. On Sunday alone, over three inches of rain fell in the city of Dallas. In TEMPLATE[w, Hays County, Texas, Hays County], one official described the flooding as \"the largest flood in the history of this region\" \u0026mdash; at least 350 homes there were destroyed and an additional 1,000 homes suffered damage.","While both TEMPLATE[w, Oklahoma] and TEMPLATE[w, Mexico] have seen effects of the storms, the two killed in Texas were a girl returning from her TEMPLATE[w, prom] and a 14 year-old boy. A photo from TEMPLATE[w, The Weather Channel] showed flooding at TEMPLATE[w, The Galleria (Houston), The Galleria] shopping mall in Houston, preventing employees from leaving. In the eastern part of the state, heavy rains have struck nearly every day in May, washing out patches of roadways.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[original, left]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Texas","description":"Category:Texas"},{"id":"Category:Weather","description":"Category:Weather"},{"id":"Category:Dallas,_Texas","description":"Category:Dallas, Texas"},{"id":"Category:Houston","description":"Category:Houston"}],"templates":[{"name":"Texas","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["May 27, 2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States"]},{"name":"image","description":["Unknown U.S. Army official"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hays County, Texas","Hays County"]},{"name":"w","description":["Oklahoma"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mexico"]},{"name":"w","description":["prom"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Weather Channel"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Galleria (Houston)","The Galleria"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2015/05/25/409474791/more-heavy-rain-predicted-for-texas-oklahoma","title\u003dTexas Governor Calls Flood Damage \u0027Devastating\u0027","author\u003dKrishnadev Calamur","pub\u003dNPR","date\u003dMay 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/texas-oklahoma-set-more-flooding-two-families-still-missing-n364086","title\u003dTexas, Oklahoma Floods: 12 People Missing as More Rain Forecast","author\u003dElisha Fieldstadt, Alexander Smith and Gabe Gutierrez","pub\u003dNBC News","date\u003dMay 25, 2015"]},{"name":"original","description":["left"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Joe Hockey agrees to lobby states to ditch tampon tax","wikiTitle":"Joe_Hockey_agrees_to_lobby_states_to_ditch_tampon_tax","wid":2171764,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-10T12:35:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-26/tampon-tax-tony-abbottsays-no-federal-push-removing-gst/6498230, title\u003d Tampon tax: Tony Abbott says removing GST on sanitary items \u0027certainly not something Government plans to do\u0027, author\u003d Emma Griffiths, pub\u003d ABC News, date\u003d May 27, 12:50am]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.buzzfeed.com/alexlee/joe-hockey-says-he-supports-removing-the-tax-on-tampons#.qsvJJv80RK, title\u003d Joe Hockey Says He Supports Removing The Tax On Tampons, author\u003d Alex Lee, pub\u003d BuzzFeed News, date\u003d May 26, 6:00am]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-25/joe-hockey-says-he-will-put-tampon-tax-question-to-states/6496512, title\u003d Tampon tax: Joe Hockey agrees to lobby states to ditch GST on sanitary items after question from student on Q\u0026A, author\u003d Anna Henderson, pub\u003d ABC News, date\u003d May 26, 10:30am]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d https://www.communityrun.org/petitions/stop-taxing-my-period, title\u003d STOP TAXING MY PERIOD!, author\u003d Subeta Vimalarajah, pub\u003d CommunityRun and GetUp Australia, date\u003d May, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 28, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] TEMPLATE[W, Treasurer of Australia, Australian treasurer] TEMPLATE[W, Joe Hockey, Joe Hockey] has agreed to reconsider the TEMPLATE[W, Goods and Services Tax (Australia), Goods and Services Tax] (GST) on tampons and other hygiene products after being confronted about the issue on TEMPLATE[W, Q\u0026A (Australian talk show), Q\u0026A] Monday night. Mr Hockey was responding to a question from TEMPLATE[W, Student activism, student activist] Subeta Vimalarajah.","\"I started a petition against taxing the sanitary products under the GST. It now has over 86,000 signees and 11,000 submissions to the Better Tax Review. Mr Hockey, do you think that sanitary products are an essential health good for half the population?â she asked.","\"Do I think sanitary products are essential? I think so,\" Mr Hockey responded  \"Should the GST be taken off them? It probably should, yes. The answer is yes.â","He said that he will raise the issue with the next meeting of the state treasurers in July.","\"I understand there\u0027s long been a push to take the GST off goods, which are one way or another regarded as health products,\" Prime Minister Tony Abbott said. \"It\u0027s certainly not something that this Government has a plan to do.\"","He said he interpreted Joe Hockey\u0027s remarks as meaning it was a matter for the states.","Shadow Treasurer TEMPLATE[W, Chris Bowen, Chris Bowen] said the matter deserved serious consideration.","\"Why did it take till Mr Hockey was asked a question on live TV for him to acknowledge this was an issue?\" he asked.","\"I understand the concerns with taxing sanitary products â concerns that go back to the introduction of the GST by the TEMPLATE[W, Coalition (Australia), Coalition].","\"These are in effect health products and aren\u0027t simply a matter of choice for women.\"","The GST was introduced in Australia in 2000. The then Prime Minister TEMPLATE[W, John Howard, John Howard] said the tax on tampons was not a woman\u0027s issue.","\"I mean, of course if you look at tampons in isolation - just as you look at something else in isolation - you can mount an argument to take the tax off it,\" Mr Howard said at the time.","\"I could mount an argument to take the tax off children\u0027s clothes. I could mount an argument to take the tax off old people\u0027s clothes, I could mount an argument for a whole lot of things. But we\u0027ve had that argument and if you start doing that, you will have no GST in the end, and the whole system will begin to unravel.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Abbott","description":"Category:Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 28, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"W","description":["Treasurer of Australia","Australian treasurer"]},{"name":"W","description":["Joe Hockey","Joe Hockey"]},{"name":"W","description":["Goods and Services Tax (Australia)","Goods and Services Tax"]},{"name":"W","description":["Q\u0026A (Australian talk show)","Q\u0026A"]},{"name":"W","description":["Student activism","student activist"]},{"name":"W","description":["Chris Bowen","Chris Bowen"]},{"name":"W","description":["Coalition (Australia)","Coalition"]},{"name":"W","description":["John Howard","John Howard"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-26/tampon-tax-tony-abbottsays-no-federal-push-removing-gst/6498230","title\u003d Tampon tax: Tony Abbott says removing GST on sanitary items \u0027certainly not something Government plans to do\u0027","author\u003d Emma Griffiths","pub\u003d ABC News","date\u003d May 27, 12:50am"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.buzzfeed.com/alexlee/joe-hockey-says-he-supports-removing-the-tax-on-tampons#.qsvJJv80RK","title\u003d Joe Hockey Says He Supports Removing The Tax On Tampons","author\u003d Alex Lee","pub\u003d BuzzFeed News","date\u003d May 26, 6:00am"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-25/joe-hockey-says-he-will-put-tampon-tax-question-to-states/6496512","title\u003d Tampon tax: Joe Hockey agrees to lobby states to ditch GST on sanitary items after question from student on Q\u0026A","author\u003d Anna Henderson","pub\u003d ABC News","date\u003d May 26, 10:30am"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d https://www.communityrun.org/petitions/stop-taxing-my-period","title\u003d STOP TAXING MY PERIOD!","author\u003d Subeta Vimalarajah","pub\u003d CommunityRun and GetUp Australia","date\u003d May, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Western Australia police close in on murder suspect, arrest warrant issued","wikiTitle":"Western_Australia_police_close_in_on_murder_suspect,_arrest_warrant_issued","wid":2171912,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-24T19:07:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-25/warrant-issued-for-man-over-hayley-dodds-murder/6495762, title\u003dWarrant issued for man over Hayley Dodd\u0027s murder, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dMay 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/national/western-australia/hayley-dodd-murder-warrant-issued-for-arrest-of-man-for-1999-murder-of-missing-wa-teen/story-fnj4anv2-1227368808146, title\u003dHayley Dodd murder: arrest warrant issued for arrest of man for 1999 murder of missing WA teen, author\u003d, pub\u003dnews.com.au, date\u003dMay 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Western_Australia","description":"Western Australia"},{"id":"Queensland","description":"Queensland"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 28, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] TEMPLATE[image, Moondyne] Police in Western Australia revealed Monday they have reason to believe 59-year-old Francis John Wark was involved in the alleged murder of Hayley Marie Dodd. A TEMPLATE[wikt, warrant] was subsequently issued for his arrest, and it is likely that he will be charged.","Witnesses had seen 17-year-old Hayley walking and TEMPLATE[w, hitchhiking] in the TEMPLATE[w, Badgingarra] area July 29, 1999 \u0026mdash; the day she disappeared. She was believed to have been making her way to do some work at a family friend\u0027s home but concerns were raised when she never showed.","State Crime Commander Pryce Scanlan said that \"forensic advances\" led to the breakthrough during a review of the case.","\"It will be alleged the man abducted Hayley as she was walking on North West Road, Badgingarra,\" he said.","\"It is further alleged he murdered her and disposed of her body.\"","Police believe Wark, who is currently locked up in a Queensland prison for an un-related offence, was living in Badgingarra when Ms Dodd disappeared.","Relatives of Ms Dodd have been told about the anticipated arrest.","âIâm very pleased with the progress of the investigation but Iâm also more pleased that it does provide a degree of comfort to the family,â said Commander Scanlan.","There are plans to have Wark prosecuted for the crime in a court in Western Australia. Ms Dodd\u0027s body has yet to be found.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:_Australia","description":"category: Australia"},{"id":"category:_Western_Australia","description":"category: Western Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Missing_persons","description":"Category:Missing persons"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 28, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Moondyne"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["warrant"]},{"name":"w","description":["hitchhiking"]},{"name":"w","description":["Badgingarra"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-25/warrant-issued-for-man-over-hayley-dodds-murder/6495762","title\u003dWarrant issued for man over Hayley Dodd\u0027s murder","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dMay 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/national/western-australia/hayley-dodd-murder-warrant-issued-for-arrest-of-man-for-1999-murder-of-missing-wa-teen/story-fnj4anv2-1227368808146","title\u003dHayley Dodd murder: arrest warrant issued for arrest of man for 1999 murder of missing WA teen","author\u003d","pub\u003dnews.com.au","date\u003dMay 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"B.B. King\u0027s daughters allege blues musician was poisoned","wikiTitle":"B.B._King\u0027s_daughters_allege_blues_musician_was_poisoned","wid":2171982,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-06T14:21:28Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-26/bb-kings-death-to-be-investigated-as-homicide-coroner-says/6497688, title\u003d BB King\u0027s death to be investigated as homicide, Nevada coroner\u0027s office says, author\u003d, pub\u003d ABC News (Australia), date\u003d May 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/may/25/bb-king-may-have-been-poisoned-daughters-allege, title\u003d BB King: estate attorney dismisses claim that bluesman was poisoned, author\u003d, pub\u003d The Guardian, date\u003d May 26, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://time.com/3895784/bb-king-dead-poisoned-obit-death-blues-las-vegas/, title\u003d Allegations B.B. King Was Poisoned Are Ridiculous, Says Attorney, author\u003d Drew Mackie, pub\u003d TIME, date\u003d May 25, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"blues_music","description":"blues"},{"id":"Associated_Press","description":"Associated Press"},{"id":"Las_Vegas","description":"Las Vegas"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[music] TEMPLATE[date, May 28, 2015] TEMPLATE[image, Eric Draper] Two daughters of blues legend TEMPLATE[w, B.B. King] are claiming on Monday that he was poisoned by business manager LaVerne Toney and personal assistant Myron Johnson. The allegations were made by daughters Karen Williams and Patty King in affidavits provided by their lawyer to the Associated Press.","\"I believe my father was poisoned and that he was administered foreign substances,\" Williams and King said in identically worded sections of the affidavits. \"I believe my father was murdered.\"","Williams and King also allege that family members were prevented from visiting their father prior to his death. The lawyer for King\u0027s estate says the claims are ridiculous.","\"I hope they have a factual basis that they can demonstrate for their defamatory and libelous allegations,\" lawyer Brent Bryson said in a statement to the Associated Press.","Bryson says that King was appropriately cared for by medical professionals up until his death on May 14 in Las Vegas.","An autopsy of B.B. King\u0027s body was carried out on Sunday by the Clark County, Nevada coroner\u0027s office. The coroner\u0027s office said on Twitter that it would be a minimum of six to eight weeks before results of the autopsy are finalised.","The Las Vegas Police department said that a potential homicide investigation into the death of the blues legend will depend on autopsy findings.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Nevada","description":"Category:Nevada"},{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:Blues_music","description":"Category:Blues music"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"}],"templates":[{"name":"music","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["May 28, 2015"]},{"name":"image","description":["Eric Draper"]},{"name":"w","description":["B.B. King"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-26/bb-kings-death-to-be-investigated-as-homicide-coroner-says/6497688","title\u003d BB King\u0027s death to be investigated as homicide, Nevada coroner\u0027s office says","author\u003d","pub\u003d ABC News (Australia)","date\u003d May 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/music/2015/may/25/bb-king-may-have-been-poisoned-daughters-allege","title\u003d BB King: estate attorney dismisses claim that bluesman was poisoned","author\u003d","pub\u003d The Guardian","date\u003d May 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://time.com/3895784/bb-king-dead-poisoned-obit-death-blues-las-vegas/","title\u003d Allegations B.B. King Was Poisoned Are Ridiculous, Says Attorney","author\u003d Drew Mackie","pub\u003d TIME","date\u003d May 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Citizenship of Australian terrorists overseas under question","wikiTitle":"Citizenship_of_Australian_terrorists_overseas_under_question","wid":2175529,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-04T04:55:41Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-26/government-promises-laws-to-strip-citizenship-from-terrorists/6498300, title\u003dGovernment promises laws to strip citizenship from dual-nationality terrorists within weeks, amid debate within Cabinet, author\u003dJames Bennett, Eliza Borrello, Chris Uhlmann, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dMay 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/may/27/isis-fighter-khaled-sharroufs-family-want-to-return-to-australia, title\u003d\u0027No compromise\u0027 for Isis fighter Khaled Sharrouf\u0027s wife if she returns to Australia, author\u003d(TEMPLATE) and (TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMay 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/may/26/dual-national-jihadists-face-loss-of-citizenship-but-not-sole-nationals-yet, title\u003dDual-national jihadists face loss of Australian citizenship, but not sole nationals yet, author\u003dDaniel Hurst, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMay 26, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Nick-D, Nick-D]]] Yesterday, TEMPLATE[w, Australia]\u0027s TEMPLATE[W, Tony Abbott, Prime Minister] proposed his government might strip individuals of their Australian citizenship if authorities consider them involved in terrorist activity.","Prime Minister Tony Abbott stated, \"As flagged by me in my national security statement in February, we will be legislating within a few weeks to strip TEMPLATE[w, multiple citizenship, dual citizens] involved in terrorism of their Australian citizenship\".","The Coalition government\u0027s bill aims to empower the immigration minister to revoke Australian citizenship of dual nationals suspected of involvement in terrorist activity.","Speaking of procedural for stripping individual citizenship, immigration minister TEMPLATE[W, Peter Dutton] said he would take advice from intelligence agencies, such as the TEMPLATE[w, Australian Security Intelligence Organisation].","Dutton said, \"We would gather as much evidence as was possible and we would make a decision whether or not we thought somebody was captured by what is a tight definition in relation to somebody committing an act of terrorism, an act preparatory to, fundraising or supporting a terrorist organisation or providing financial support or indoctrinating young people into the ways of one of these cults.\"","This news comes as the Australian wife of TEMPLATE[w, Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant, Islamic State] fighter Khaled Sharrouf, Tara Nettleton, attempts to re-enter the country with her children. Khaled\u0027s seven-year-old son appeared in an internet image Khaled posted last year \u0026mdash; in which the boy was holding a severed human head.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Australia","description":"category:Australia"},{"id":"category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Australian_immigration_policies","description":"Category:Australian immigration policies"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Abbott","description":"Category:Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Nick-D","Nick-D]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australia"]},{"name":"W","description":["Tony Abbott","Prime Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["multiple citizenship","dual citizens"]},{"name":"W","description":["Peter Dutton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australian Security Intelligence Organisation"]},{"name":"w","description":["Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant","Islamic State"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-26/government-promises-laws-to-strip-citizenship-from-terrorists/6498300","title\u003dGovernment promises laws to strip citizenship from dual-nationality terrorists within weeks, amid debate within Cabinet","author\u003dJames Bennett, Eliza Borrello, Chris Uhlmann","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dMay 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/may/27/isis-fighter-khaled-sharroufs-family-want-to-return-to-australia","title\u003d\u0027No compromise\u0027 for Isis fighter Khaled Sharrouf\u0027s wife if she returns to Australia","author\u003d(TEMPLATE) and (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMay 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/australia-news/2015/may/26/dual-national-jihadists-face-loss-of-citizenship-but-not-sole-nationals-yet","title\u003dDual-national jihadists face loss of Australian citizenship, but not sole nationals yet","author\u003dDaniel Hurst","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMay 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Non-parole period extended to 43 years for Australian rapist and murderer","wikiTitle":"Non-parole_period_extended_to_43_years_for_Australian_rapist_and_murderer","wid":2180975,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-11T13:11:01Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/law-order/adrian-bayley-jill-meaghers-killer-to-serve-at-least-43-years-in-jail-after-18-year-rapes-sentence/story-fni0fee2-1227372763101, title\u003dAdrian Bayley, Jill MeagherÂs killer to serve at least 43 years in jail after 18-year rapes sentence, author\u003dWayne Flower, pub\u003dHerald Sun, date\u003dMay 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-28/adrian-bayley-minimum-prison-term-extended-10-years-over-rapes/6502986, title\u003dAdrian Bayley\u0027s minimum prison term extended by 10 years over three rape convictions, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dMay 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/05/28/13/17/adrian-bayley-sentenced-to-18-years-for-the-rape-of-three-more-women, title\u003dAdrian Bayley expected to appeal 18 year sentence for the rape of three more women, author\u003d, pub\u003dninemsn, date\u003dMay 28, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"rape","description":"rape"},{"id":"Melbourne","description":"Melbourne"},{"id":"Netherlands","description":"Dutch"},{"id":"death_penalty","description":"death penalty"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, May 30, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] Australian TEMPLATE[W, Adrian Ernest Bayley], 43, previously convicted of rape and murder, has been sentenced on Thursday to a further 18 years in prison for three more rapes.","Bayley had already been sentenced to life in prison with a minimum of 35 years, over the 2013 rape and murder of TEMPLATE[W, Australian Broadcasting Corporation, ABC] employee TEMPLATE[W, Jill Meagher]. The additional 18 year sentence means Bayley would not be eligible to apply for parole until the year 2058. He would then be age 86.","The judge presiding over the case, Judge Pullen said, \"Your repeated violent offending and gravity of that offending provides little to offer the faintest glimmer of hope\", as the sentence was handed down. Senior Crown Prosecutor Peter Rose QC supported the decision made by Judge Pullen saying, \"Given the history of the prisoner Bayley, the only finding available to the court is that the prisoner represents a serious danger to the community\".","Bayley committed rape and attempted rape at age 19. Later, in 2000, he raped six prostitutes in the Melbourne suburb of TEMPLATE[W, Saint Kilda, Victoria, Saint Kilda]. He was sentenced for these crimes to at least eight years in jail and was on parole in 2012 when he raped a Dutch backpacker and in 2013 raped and murdered Jill Meagher.","During the trial for the 2013 rape and murder of Jill Meagher, Bayley told the court \"They should have the death penalty for people like me [...] How many chances does a person need? They should never have let me out.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Sex_crimes","description":"Category:Sex crimes"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["May 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"W","description":["Adrian Ernest Bayley"]},{"name":"W","description":["Australian Broadcasting Corporation","ABC"]},{"name":"W","description":["Jill Meagher"]},{"name":"W","description":["Saint Kilda, Victoria","Saint Kilda"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.heraldsun.com.au/news/law-order/adrian-bayley-jill-meaghers-killer-to-serve-at-least-43-years-in-jail-after-18-year-rapes-sentence/story-fni0fee2-1227372763101","title\u003dAdrian Bayley, Jill MeagherÂs killer to serve at least 43 years in jail after 18-year rapes sentence","author\u003dWayne Flower","pub\u003dHerald Sun","date\u003dMay 28, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-05-28/adrian-bayley-minimum-prison-term-extended-10-years-over-rapes/6502986","title\u003dAdrian Bayley\u0027s minimum prison term extended by 10 years over three rape convictions","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dMay 28, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/05/28/13/17/adrian-bayley-sentenced-to-18-years-for-the-rape-of-three-more-women","title\u003dAdrian Bayley expected to appeal 18 year sentence for the rape of three more women","author\u003d","pub\u003dninemsn","date\u003dMay 28, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Kerry hospitalized after cycling accident","wikiTitle":"Kerry_hospitalized_after_cycling_accident","wid":2187955,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-20T20:40:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/may/31/john-kerry-injured-cycling-accident-france, title\u003dJohn Kerry breaks leg in cycling accident and scraps rest of four-stop Europe trip, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMay 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/secretary-john-kerry-hospitalized-switzerland-bike-crash/, title\u003dKerry hospitalized in Switzerland after bike crash, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dCBS News, date\u003dMay 31, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"John_Kerry","description":"John Kerry"},{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"Iran","description":"Iran"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] U.S. Secretary of State John Kerry had a cycling accident yesterday and as a result has broken his right leg. The accident happened near TEMPLATE[w, Scionzier], France; reportedly he may have hit a curb. TEMPLATE[image, US Department of State] Kerry was in TEMPLATE[w, Geneva] on Saturday for talks with the Iranian Foreign Minister, TEMPLATE[w, Mohammad Javad Zarif, Muhammad Javad Zarif], on the Iranian nuclear program. As a result of the accident Kerry has canceled his official trips, including an international conference on TEMPLATE[w, Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant, Islamic State] (ISIS).","Kerry was taken to Geneva\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, University Hospital of Geneva, HUG] medical centre by helicopter and after an X-ray examination it was confirmed his right femur is fractured. John Kirby, a State Department spokesman, said \"The secretary is stable and never lost consciousness, his injury is not life-threatening and he is expected to make a full recovery\".","Kerry is expected to receive further treatment in TEMPLATE[w, Boston] by a doctor there who operated on him for a previous hip injury located, Kirby said, near the current injury.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:John_Kerry","description":"Category:John Kerry"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Switzerland","description":"Category:Switzerland"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Iran","description":"Category:Iran"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 1, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Scionzier"]},{"name":"image","description":["US Department of State"]},{"name":"w","description":["Geneva"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mohammad Javad Zarif","Muhammad Javad Zarif"]},{"name":"w","description":["Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant","Islamic State"]},{"name":"w","description":["University Hospital of Geneva","HUG"]},{"name":"w","description":["Boston"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/may/31/john-kerry-injured-cycling-accident-france","title\u003dJohn Kerry breaks leg in cycling accident and scraps rest of four-stop Europe trip","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMay 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/secretary-john-kerry-hospitalized-switzerland-bike-crash/","title\u003dKerry hospitalized in Switzerland after bike crash","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dCBS News","date\u003dMay 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Beau Biden, son of US vice president, dies at 46","wikiTitle":"Beau_Biden,_son_of_US_vice_president,_dies_at_46","wid":2189492,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-25T20:18:56Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2015/05/30/e1ac5a2a-0731-11e5-a428-c984eb077d4e_story.html, title\u003dBeau Biden, vice presidentâs son, dies at 46 of brain cancer, author\u003d Paul Kane, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dMay 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://time.com/3902786/beau-biden-tragedy/, title\u003dVice President Joe Bidenâs Bond With Late Son Beau Was Forged by Tragedy, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTime (magazine), date\u003dMay 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/may/31/beau-biden-dies-of-brain-cancer, title\u003dBeau Biden, son of US vice-president Joe Biden, dies of brain cancer at 46, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dMay 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Joe_Biden","description":"Joe Biden"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 2, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_States] US Vice President Joe Biden\u0027s son TEMPLATE[w, Beau Biden, Beau] died of TEMPLATE[w, brain cancer] on Saturday.  He was 46. TEMPLATE[image, Doug Gansler] After being diagnosed less than two years ago, Beau underwent treatment and was considered recovered, but was recently admitted to TEMPLATE[w, Walter Reed National Military Medical Center] in TEMPLATE[w, Bethesda, Maryland, Bethesda], TEMPLATE[w, Maryland] due to return of the cancer.","Biden released a statement through the White House.  Noting the family was with Beau when he died, he said, \"It is with broken hearts that Hallie, Hunter, Ashley, TEMPLATE[w, Jill Biden, Jill] and I announce the passing of our husband, brother and son, Beau, after he battled brain cancer with the same integrity, courage and strength he demonstrated every day of his life.\"","President TEMPLATE[w, Barack Obama] and the first lady TEMPLATE[w, Michelle Obama] cancelled a scheduled White House reception to visit the Biden family and give their condolences.","The Obamas released a statement not long after receiving the news that states, âMichelle and I are grieving. Beau Biden was a friend of ours. His beloved family [...] are friends of ours. And Joe and Jill Biden are as good as friends get.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Joe_Biden","description":"Category:Joe Biden"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 2, 2015"]},{"name":"United_States","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Beau Biden","Beau"]},{"name":"w","description":["brain cancer"]},{"name":"image","description":["Doug Gansler"]},{"name":"w","description":["Walter Reed National Military Medical Center"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bethesda, Maryland","Bethesda"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maryland"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jill Biden","Jill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Barack Obama"]},{"name":"w","description":["Michelle Obama"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.washingtonpost.com/politics/2015/05/30/e1ac5a2a-0731-11e5-a428-c984eb077d4e_story.html","title\u003dBeau Biden, vice presidentâs son, dies at 46 of brain cancer","author\u003d Paul Kane","pub\u003dThe Washington Post","date\u003dMay 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://time.com/3902786/beau-biden-tragedy/","title\u003dVice President Joe Bidenâs Bond With Late Son Beau Was Forged by Tragedy","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dTime (magazine)","date\u003dMay 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/may/31/beau-biden-dies-of-brain-cancer","title\u003dBeau Biden, son of US vice-president Joe Biden, dies of brain cancer at 46","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dMay 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Charles Kennedy, former Liberal Democrats leader, dies aged 55","wikiTitle":"Charles_Kennedy,_former_Liberal_Democrats_leader,_dies_aged_55","wid":2194780,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-27T14:42:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32985571, title\u003dDavid Cameron leads Commons tributes to Charles Kennedy, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJune 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/charles-kennedy-tributes-pour-giant-5815955, title\u003dCharles Kennedy: Tributes pour in for \u0027giant of Scottish and UK politics\u0027 as MPs gather for special Commons session, author\u003d, pub\u003dDaily Record (Scotland), date\u003dJune 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/liberaldemocrats/11645189/charles-kennedy-dies-aged-55.html, title\u003dCharles Kennedy, former Lib Dem leader, dies aged 55, author\u003dSimon Johnson, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dJune 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jun/02/charles-kennedy-celia-munro-confidante-tragedies-alcoholism, title\u003dCharles Kennedy\u0027s friends tell of his struggle with alcohol, author\u003dLibby Brooks and Severin Carrell, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJune 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"British"},{"id":"Liberal_Democrats_(UK)","description":"Liberal Democrats"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scotland"},{"id":"Scottish_National_Party","description":"Scottish National Party"},{"id":"Iraq","description":"Iraq"},{"id":"Tony_Blair","description":"Tony Blair"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"Nick_Clegg","description":"Nick Clegg"},{"id":"Scottish_National_Party","description":"SNP"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] TEMPLATE[image, Moniker42] TEMPLATE[w, Charles Kennedy], British former TEMPLATE[w, UK House of Commons, Member of Parliament] who once led the Liberal Democrats, has died at age 55. He was found dead on Monday at his home in TEMPLATE[w, Fort William, Scotland, Fort William], Scotland by his partner, Carole Macdonald.","Kennedy was a Member of Parliament for 32 years, losing his seat in the TEMPLATE[w, United Kingdom general election, 2015, 2015 general election] to the Scottish National Party just under a month ago. He led the Liberal Democrats from 1999 until his resignation in 2006.","Kennedy first became a Member of Parliament in 1983 at age 23, becoming the youngest MP at the time. He was elected to represent the TEMPLATE[W, Ross, Cromarty and Skye (UK Parliament constituency), Ross, Cromarty and Skye] constituency under the TEMPLATE[w, Social Democratic Party (UK), Social Democratic Party] (SDP). Through this he helped the party eventually merge with the TEMPLATE[w, Liberal Party (UK), Liberal Party] to form the Liberal Democrats in 1988. He took over leadership of the party in 1999, replacing TEMPLATE[w, Paddy Ashdown].","During his time as party leader he won praise from critics for his opposition to the invasion of Iraq, which was being pushed through by then British Prime Minister Tony Blair. In the 2005 general election he saw his party record their highest ever electoral result, winning 62 seats. However his success wouldn\u0027t last, with Kennedy resigning the following year after going public with his alcohol abuse problem.","Tributes have come from politicians across a number of political parties. The first edition of Prime Minister\u0027s Questions since the general election took place in the TEMPLATE[w, UK House of Commons, House of Commons] yesterday and many offered their condolences to Kennedy\u0027s family.  Current Prime Minister David Cameron said \"Charles Kennedy played a pivotal role in bringing together two parties \u0026mdash; the SDP and the Liberals. As leader he took the Liberal Democrats to the best electoral result for a third party in British politics for nearly 100 years.\"","Nick Clegg, the outgoing leader of the Liberal Democrats, said Kennedy \"would have wanted to be remembered as a kind and loving father, brother and son first; and an accomplished politician second\".","TEMPLATE[W, Speaker of the House of Commons (United Kingdom), Speaker] of the House TEMPLATE[w, John Bercow] said to the House, \"Charles Kennedy spent almost his entire adult life as an MP. He was assuredly at home in this place, yet perhaps happiest beyond it. He was a man of deep progressive principle, but a man also blessed with the popular touch. He was a good talker but an even better listener. Above all, and perhaps most strikingly, Charles had the rare ability to reach out to millions of people of all political persuasions and of none across the country who were untouched by and in many cases actively hostile to politics. In this seminal sense, therefore, Charles was the boy next door of British public life \u0026mdash; we salute him. We honour his memory and we send today our sincere heartfelt and deepest condolences to his family and his friends.\"","The SNP\u0027s TEMPLATE[W, Ian Blackford], who defeated Kennedy in the general election, said \"So sorry to hear the dreadful news that Charles Kennedy had passed away. A man of such great ability, such [a] tragedy he has passed away. RIP.\"","The Liberal Democrats have set up an online condolence book on their website where anyone can post tributes and memories of the former MP.","Kennedy is survived by his partner Carole and 10 year-old son Donald, who he had with his ex-wife, Sarah Gurling. The couple married in 2002 but split in 2010. His mother died in 2013 and his father, Ian, died at the age of 88 in April of this year.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Liberal_Democrats_(UK)","description":"Category:Liberal Democrats (UK)"},{"id":"Category:Nick_Clegg","description":"Category:Nick Clegg"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_National_Party","description":"Category:Scottish National Party"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 4, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Moniker42"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles Kennedy"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK House of Commons","Member of Parliament"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fort William, Scotland","Fort William"]},{"name":"w","description":["United Kingdom general election, 2015","2015 general election"]},{"name":"W","description":["Ross, Cromarty and Skye (UK Parliament constituency)","Ross, Cromarty and Skye"]},{"name":"w","description":["Social Democratic Party (UK)","Social Democratic Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Liberal Party (UK)","Liberal Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Paddy Ashdown"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK House of Commons","House of Commons"]},{"name":"W","description":["Speaker of the House of Commons (United Kingdom)","Speaker"]},{"name":"w","description":["John Bercow"]},{"name":"W","description":["Ian Blackford"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-32985571","title\u003dDavid Cameron leads Commons tributes to Charles Kennedy","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJune 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/news/scottish-news/charles-kennedy-tributes-pour-giant-5815955","title\u003dCharles Kennedy: Tributes pour in for \u0027giant of Scottish and UK politics\u0027 as MPs gather for special Commons session","author\u003d","pub\u003dDaily Record (Scotland)","date\u003dJune 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/politics/liberaldemocrats/11645189/charles-kennedy-dies-aged-55.html","title\u003dCharles Kennedy, former Lib Dem leader, dies aged 55","author\u003dSimon Johnson","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dJune 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/politics/2015/jun/02/charles-kennedy-celia-munro-confidante-tragedies-alcoholism","title\u003dCharles Kennedy\u0027s friends tell of his struggle with alcohol","author\u003dLibby Brooks and Severin Carrell","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dJune 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Australian businessman Alan Bond dies aged 77","wikiTitle":"Australian_businessman_Alan_Bond_dies_aged_77","wid":2199048,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-28T19:53:31Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-05/alan-bond-dies-in-perth-after-heart-surgery-complications/6520630, title\u003dAlan Bond dies in Perth hospital after heart surgery complications, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dJune 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/06/05/03/35/businessman-alan-bond-dead-at-age-77, title\u003dMixed feelings on the end of Bondy\u0027s life, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dNine News, date\u003dJune 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/business/alan-bond-dead-businessman-dies-in-fiona-stanley-hospital-20150605-ghhi14.html, title\u003dAlan Bond dead: businessman dies in Fiona Stanley Hospital, author\u003dLeanne Nicholson, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dJune 5, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"Perth","description":"Perth"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 5, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] Australian business tycoon TEMPLATE[w, Alan Bond (businessman), Alan Bond] died today after complications from TEMPLATE[w, Cardiac surgery, open heart surgery]. He was 77.","Following open heart surgery to repair and replace TEMPLATE[w, heart valves], leading to complications, Bond was placed in an TEMPLATE[w, induced coma].  The family released a statement outside the Perth hospital where Bond died in intensive care following his operation on Tuesday.","His son John said, \"His body finally gave out after heroic efforts of everyone involved here at the intensive care unit at TEMPLATE[w, Fiona Stanley Hospital] [...] He never regained consciousness after his surgery on Tuesday.\"","In the 1980s Bond was one of the richest men in Australia; in 1992 he declared TEMPLATE[w, bankruptcy]. In 1997 he was convicted and jailed for his involvement in an TEMPLATE[w, Australian dollar, AU$]1.2 billion TEMPLATE[w, fraud] case. Bond was released in 2000.","In 2008 Australian magazine TEMPLATE[w, BRW (magazine), Business Review Weekly] estimated Bond was worth AU$265 million.","Bond leaves behind three children and eight grandchildren.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Perth,_Western_Australia","description":"Category:Perth, Western Australia"},{"id":"Category:Economy_and_business","description":"Category:Economy and business"},{"id":"Category:Western_Australia","description":"Category:Western Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 5, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Alan Bond (businessman)","Alan Bond"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cardiac surgery","open heart surgery"]},{"name":"w","description":["heart valves"]},{"name":"w","description":["induced coma"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fiona Stanley Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["bankruptcy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australian dollar","AU$"]},{"name":"w","description":["fraud"]},{"name":"w","description":["BRW (magazine)","Business Review Weekly"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-05/alan-bond-dies-in-perth-after-heart-surgery-complications/6520630","title\u003dAlan Bond dies in Perth hospital after heart surgery complications","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dJune 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.9news.com.au/national/2015/06/05/03/35/businessman-alan-bond-dead-at-age-77","title\u003dMixed feelings on the end of Bondy\u0027s life","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dNine News","date\u003dJune 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/business/alan-bond-dead-businessman-dies-in-fiona-stanley-hospital-20150605-ghhi14.html","title\u003dAlan Bond dead: businessman dies in Fiona Stanley Hospital","author\u003dLeanne Nicholson","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dJune 5, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Major haemorrhage linked to alcoholism announced as cause of Charles Kennedy\u0027s death","wikiTitle":"Major_haemorrhage_linked_to_alcoholism_announced_as_cause_of_Charles_Kennedy\u0027s_death","wid":2200669,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-06-29T22:01:11Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dCharles Kennedy, former Liberal Democrats leader, dies aged 55, date\u003dJune 4, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1496945/charles-kennedy-death-caused-by-alcoholism, title\u003dCharles Kennedy Death Caused By Alcoholism, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dJune 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-33027221, title\u003dCharles Kennedy: Family statement in full, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJune 5, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"UK","description":"UK"},{"id":"Liberal_Democrats","description":"Liberal Democrats"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scottish"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 6, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] TEMPLATE[image, catch21productions] TEMPLATE[w, Charles Kennedy], former UK Liberal Democrats leader, died of a major haemorrhage linked to his TEMPLATE[w, Alcoholism, alcohol addiction], his family announced in a statement yesterday. Kennedy, a Scottish former TEMPLATE[w, UK House of Commons, Member of Parliament], died unexpectedly on Monday at the age of 55.","His family said in the statement, \"Charles\u0027s death was caused by a major haemorrhage and the report makes clear this was a consequence of his battle with alcoholism. We are grateful to the many friends and also medical experts who sought to help down the years but ultimately this was an illness Charles could not conquer despite all the efforts he and others made.\"","They also spoke of the tributes that had been paid to the politician saying \"It has become all too apparent to us how much Charles meant to so many people and how many lives he touched. We were grateful that his young son Donald was able to attend the TEMPLATE[w, UK House of Commons, Commons] session where so many MPs spoke so warmly about his father. The words and images of that day, and of so many other tributes, will be there for us to look back on with pride in Charles, and Donald will always know what a special father he had.\"","On Wednesday, Members of Parliament from various political parties paid tribute to Kennedy. His ex-wife Sarah and 10-year-old son were in attendance to hear the tributes.","Despite a successful tenure as leader of the Liberal Democrats, Kennedy had to resign in 2006 as party leader due to his alcoholism. He was a Member of Parliament for 32 years until he lost his seat in last month\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, United Kingdom general election, 2015, General Election].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Liberal_Democrats_(UK)","description":"Category:Liberal Democrats (UK)"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Mike_Smith_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Mike Smith (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 6, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["catch21productions"]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles Kennedy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alcoholism","alcohol addiction"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK House of Commons","Member of Parliament"]},{"name":"w","description":["UK House of Commons","Commons"]},{"name":"w","description":["United Kingdom general election, 2015","General Election"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dCharles Kennedy, former Liberal Democrats leader, dies aged 55","date\u003dJune 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1496945/charles-kennedy-death-caused-by-alcoholism","title\u003dCharles Kennedy Death Caused By Alcoholism","author\u003d","pub\u003dSky News","date\u003dJune 5, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-politics-33027221","title\u003dCharles Kennedy: Family statement in full","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dJune 5, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"16-year-old girl charged with attempted murder in Melbourne, Australia","wikiTitle":"16-year-old_girl_charged_with_attempted_murder_in_Melbourne,_Australia","wid":2211051,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-07-02T15:50:12Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theage.com.au/victoria/teenage-girl-charged-after-stabbing-near-fountain-gate-shopping-centre-20150610-ghk98c, title\u003dTeenage girl charged after stabbing near Fountain Gate shopping centre, author\u003dAdam Cooper and Tom Cowie, pub\u003dThe Age, date\u003dJune 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/national/crime/teenage-girl-charged-over-melbourne-shopping-centre-stabbing/story-fns0kb1g-1227390779209, title\u003dTeenage girl charged over melbourne shopping centre stabbing, author\u003d, pub\u003dnews.com.au, date\u003dJune 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-10/fountain-gate-stabbing-teenager-attempted-murder-charge/6534046, title\u003dTeenage girl charged with attempted murder over stabbing of 16-year-old near Fountain Gate shopping centre, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dJune 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Melbourne","description":"Melbourne"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] Authorities arrested a 16-year-old girl on Tuesday on an attempted murder charge after the stabbing of another 16-year-old girl, Monica Hawkins, outside the TEMPLATE[w, Westfield Fountain Gate, Fountain Gate] shopping centre in Melbourne, Australia.","Hawkins was allegedly attacked last Friday and she was found injured around 1 p.m. TEMPLATE[w, UTC+10, local time] (0300 TEMPLATE[w, UTC]) on a footpath near the shopping centre. Hawkins was airlifted to TEMPLATE[w, The Alfred Hospital] where she was admitted in serious condition. Emergency surgery was performed on her and she was discharged on Monday from the hospital.","The suspect, not named by authorities, allegedly fled the crime scene but was arrested on Tuesday.","The suspect attended the children\u0027s court yesterday and has been charged with attempted murder and intentionally causing serious injury.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Melbourne","description":"Category:Melbourne"},{"id":"Category:Victoria","description":"Category:Victoria"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Westfield Fountain Gate","Fountain Gate"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+10","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Alfred Hospital"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theage.com.au/victoria/teenage-girl-charged-after-stabbing-near-fountain-gate-shopping-centre-20150610-ghk98c","title\u003dTeenage girl charged after stabbing near Fountain Gate shopping centre","author\u003dAdam Cooper and Tom Cowie","pub\u003dThe Age","date\u003dJune 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/national/crime/teenage-girl-charged-over-melbourne-shopping-centre-stabbing/story-fns0kb1g-1227390779209","title\u003dTeenage girl charged over melbourne shopping centre stabbing","author\u003d","pub\u003dnews.com.au","date\u003dJune 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-06-10/fountain-gate-stabbing-teenager-attempted-murder-charge/6534046","title\u003dTeenage girl charged with attempted murder over stabbing of 16-year-old near Fountain Gate shopping centre","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Aus