lling Stone","date\u003dJune 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.avclub.com/article/rip-christopher-lee-220716","title\u003dR.I.P. Christopher Lee","author\u003dLara Unnerstall","pub\u003dThe A.V. Club","date\u003dJune 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["anchor","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Dozens dead in Mumbai after consuming toxic alcohol","wikiTitle":"Dozens_dead_in_Mumbai_after_consuming_toxic_alcohol","wid":2239285,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-05T16:39:46Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/india-toxic-liquor-death-toll-rises-to-66/story-e6frfkui-1227407482000, title\u003dIndia toxic liquor toll rises to 84, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dNews.com.au, date\u003dJune 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/19/toxic-liquor-deaths-mumbai-india, title\u003d41 people die of alcohol poisoning in Mumbai, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJune 19, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Mumbai","description":"Mumbai"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 20, 2015] TEMPLATE[India] As of today, as many as 84 people are reported dead since Wednesday after drinking toxic homemade TEMPLATE[w, alcohol] sold in a slum in TEMPLATE[w, Malad] in northern Mumbai. More than twenty others are reported admitted to hospital for alcohol poisoning. TEMPLATE[image_source, Media House of Chief Ministers Office, Mantralaya, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India] Police said five people have been arrested for the transport and sale of the alcohol with three men ages 30 to 50 taken into police custody on Thursday night, and eight police suspended for failing to prevent the incident.","An investigation has been ordered by TEMPLATE[w, Devendra Fadnavis], the present chief minister of TEMPLATE[w, Maharashtra state].","Illicit alcohol is commonly sold in India usually in the poorer, more rural areas of the country and deaths from alcohol poisoning are not uncommon. However, this is the largest rash of deaths in Mumbai since the TEMPLATE[w, Vikhroli] hooch tragedy of 2004 where more than 100 people died due to low-cost alcohol.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:India","description":"Category:India"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Maharashtra","description":"Category:Maharashtra"},{"id":"Category:Mumbai","description":"Category:Mumbai"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 20, 2015"]},{"name":"India","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["alcohol"]},{"name":"w","description":["Malad"]},{"name":"image_source","description":["Media House of Chief Ministers Office, Mantralaya, Mumbai, Maharashtra, India"]},{"name":"w","description":["Devendra Fadnavis"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maharashtra state"]},{"name":"w","description":["Vikhroli"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/world/breaking-news/india-toxic-liquor-death-toll-rises-to-66/story-e6frfkui-1227407482000","title\u003dIndia toxic liquor toll rises to 84","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dNews.com.au","date\u003dJune 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/jun/19/toxic-liquor-deaths-mumbai-india","title\u003d41 people die of alcohol poisoning in Mumbai","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dJune 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Former Scottish Conservatives leader Annabel Goldie to stand down as MSP","wikiTitle":"Former_Scottish_Conservatives_leader_Annabel_Goldie_to_stand_down_as_MSP","wid":2257814,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-24T18:59:15Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scottishconservatives.com/2015/06/tributes-as-former-scottish-conservative-leader-announces-she-will-stand-down/, title\u003dTributes as former Scottish Conservative leader announces she will stand down, author\u003d, pub\u003dScottish Conservative Party, date\u003dJune 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.stv.tv/scotland-decides/news/1323574-annabel-goldie-former-scottish-tory-leader-to-retire-next-year/, title\u003dAnnabel Goldie: Former Scottish Tory leader to retire next year, author\u003d, pub\u003dSTV News, date\u003dJune 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-33173488, title\u003dCut in Scottish voting age passed unanimously, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dJune 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/politics/2005/nov/08/conservatives.uk1, title\u003dGoldie to lead Scottish Tories, author\u003dMatthew Tempest, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 8, 2005]"]],"links":[{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scottish"},{"id":"Scottish_Parliament","description":"Holyrood"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[Politics_and_conflicts] TEMPLATE[w, Annabel Goldie], Scottish Conservative Party leader from 2005 to 2011, has announced she will stand down as an TEMPLATE[w, Member of the Scottish Parliament, MSP] at the TEMPLATE[w, Scottish Parliament election, 2016, next elections in 2016]. Goldie, who has been an MSP for the TEMPLATE[w, West Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region), West Scotland] (previously TEMPLATE[w, West of Scotland (Scottish Parliament electoral region), West of Scotland]) electoral region since the Scottish Parliament\u0027s formation in 1999, said she intends to focus on her role in the TEMPLATE[w, House of Lords], where she has been a TEMPLATE[w, Life peer, peer] since 2013.","In a statement today, Goldie said leading the party was an \"enormous honour\" for her. She also said: \"It has afforded me both satisfaction and pleasure to serve my constituents and to serve the parliament and I will look back with great happiness at my time as an MSP. I am grateful to friends and colleagues from all parties for their support. Sometimes we found common ground, sometimes we disagreed but never I hope with rancour nor disrespect. Politics is a rough trade but we have built a strong parliament in Scotland of which we can all be rightly proud.\" She said because of TEMPLATE[w, Ruth Davidson], her successor as Scottish Conservative leader, the party is now \"in fine fettle and stands a great chance of making real progress in the years ahead,\" concluding by saying: \"I look forward to continuing to work as part of that effort in the House of Lords in the years to come.\"","Davidson responded to the news by calling Goldie an \"unstoppable force\", adding: \"She has been an inspiration to a whole generation of Scottish Conservatives, and she has been a tremendous mentor, support and friend to me. In Holyrood, she has fostered both affection and respect from all members â regardless of their political affiliation â and her retirement from the Scottish Parliament will leave an Annabel-sized hole which won\u0027t ever quite be filled. She is unique.\" Meanwhile, TEMPLATE[w, David Cameron], UK Conservative leader and UK TEMPLATE[w, Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, Prime Minister], said: \"Annabel is one of those rare breeds in Scottish politics, somebody known by her first name alone. When she was Scottish Conservative leader, I valued her sage advice. She has been a towering strength to our party in Scotland, a doughty debater in the TV studios and Scottish Parliament and has one of the sharpest wits around. I wish her a long and happy retirement after 17 years unstinting service at Holyrood â but look forward to seeing her on the red benches of the Lords for years to come.\" TEMPLATE[QuoteRight, In [[Scottish Parliament, Holyrood]], she has fostered both affection and respect from all members â regardless of their political affiliation â and her retirement from the Scottish Parliament will leave an Annabel-sized hole which won\u0027t ever quite be filled. She is unique., source\u003d\u0027\u0027Ruth Davidson, Scottish Conservative Party leader\u0027\u0027]","Goldie, the Scottish Conservatives\u0027 first ever female leader, was elected unopposed. She took up the role in the aftermath of TEMPLATE[w, David McLetchie]\u0027s resignation from the role in an expenses usage controversy and subsequent resignation of TEMPLATE[w, Brian Monteith] from his Conservative whip role in the Scottish Parliament for briefing the media against him. Meanwhile, as Scottish Conservatives won 18 seats in the Scottish Parliament in 1999 and 2003, the party had been less successful in UK general elections in Scotland; Conservatives went up from zero out of a possible 72 UK TEMPLATE[w, Member of Parliament, MP]s in Scotland in 1997 to one in 2001. This led to Goldie remarking in her inaugural speech in 2005 that: \"The wheels are back on the wagon - and I\u0027m the nag hitched up to tow it.\" She also said: \"The party is still way ahead of where it was in 1997. And my first task is to take it forward to 2007.\" However, under Goldie\u0027s leadership, the number of seats the Scottish Conservatives won in the Scottish Parliament slightly decreased from 18 in 2003 to 17 in 2007 and to 15 in 2011. At the same time, the number of Conservative MPs stood at one out of a possible 59 after the 2010 UK general election.","In the aforementioned 2005 speech, she also said the party could be trusted with TEMPLATE[w, Devolution, devolution] in Scotland, adding: \"making devolution work better means real devolution: not the lumbering and cripplingly expensive array of government departments, government advisers, consultants, quangos, quasi-quangos and agencies with all their expensive appendages, but devolving down to people and their communities, their right to make their own decisions about their lives, how for example they procure healthcare and how they educate their children.\" Goldie would go on to sit on the advisory board for the TEMPLATE[w, Smith Commission], which was set up to examine which further political powers should be devolved to Scotland following the 2014 TEMPLATE[w, Scottish independence referendum, 2014, Scottish independence referendum]. More recently, Goldie supported a reduction in the voting age for Scottish Parliament elections from 18 to 16 in a vote earlier this month, commenting: \"I think it is an opportunity for them to continue their high level of engagement in topical affairs that we saw with the independence referendum.\"","Goldie, a member of the TEMPLATE[w, Salvation Army]\u0027s West of Scotland Advisory Board and a TEMPLATE[w, Ministers and elders of the Church of Scotland, Church of Scotland elder], is not the only Scottish Conservative MSP intending to stand down in 2016. TEMPLATE[w, Mary Scanlon], TEMPLATE[w, Gavin Brown (politician), Gavin Brown], TEMPLATE[w, Alex Fergusson (politician), Alex Fergusson] and TEMPLATE[w, Nanette Milne] all reportedly intend to leave the Scottish Parliament next year.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Scottish_Parliament","description":"Category:Sco