{"title":"US Supreme Court declares same-sex marriage legal","wikiTitle":"US_Supreme_Court_declares_same-sex_marriage_legal","wid":2262768,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-02-14T02:29:05Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.forbes.com/sites/amitchowdhry/2015/06/27/facebook-celebrate-pride/, title\u003dFacebook Launches \u0027Celebrate Pride\u0027 Tool Which Puts A Rainbow Filter Over Profile Pictures, author\u003dAmit Chawdhary, pub\u003dForbes, date\u003dJune 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theatlantic.com/politics/archive/2015/06/9-angry-judges/396989/, title\u003dThe U.S. Supreme Court Is Acting Like Congress, author\u003dMegan Garber, pub\u003dThe Atlantic, date\u003dJune 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraphindia.com/1150627/jsp/frontpage/story_28185.jsp#.VY-i4_mqqkp, title\u003dJustice like a thunderbolt- Same-sex marriage in US, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dJune 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/society/2015/jun/26/gay-marriage-legal-supreme-court, title\u003dGay marriage declared legal across the US in historic supreme court ruling, author\u003dDan Roberts and Sabrina Siddiqui, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dJune 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nbcnews.com/news/us-news/supreme-court-gay-marriage-ruling-highlights-n382431, title\u003dSupreme Court Gay Marriage Ruling: The Highlights, author\u003dErin McClam, pub\u003dNBC News, date\u003dJune 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.politico.com/story/2015/06/white-house-set-aglow-with-rainbow-pride-119490.html, title\u003dWhite House set aglow with rainbow pride, author\u003dAdam B. Lerner, pub\u003dPolitico, date\u003dJune 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.npr.org/sections/thetwo-way/2015/06/26/417731614/obama-supreme-court-ruling-on-gay-marriage-a-victory-for-america, title\u003dObama: Supreme Court Same-Sex Marriage Ruling \u0027A Victory For America\u0027, author\u003dScott Neuman, pub\u003dNPR, date\u003dJune 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_States_Supreme_Court","description":"United States Supreme Court"},{"id":"same-sex_marriage","description":"same-sex marriage"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"gay","description":"gay"},{"id":"Barack_Obama","description":"Barack Obama"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"},{"id":"Mark_Zuckerberg","description":"Mark Zuckerberg"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, June 28, 2015]TEMPLATE[USA] TEMPLATE[image, Supreme Court of the United States] On Friday, the United States Supreme Court declared same-sex marriage legal in all fifty US states. More than 30 states already permitted gay marriage. The Supreme Court ruled by a five-to-four vote that bans on same-sex marriage were not constitutional. The majority decision was delivered by TEMPLATE[w, Anthony Kennedy, Justice Anthony Kennedy].","Same-sex marriage was banned in more than a dozen states. Justices TEMPLATE[w, Sonia Sotomayor, Sotomayor], TEMPLATE[w, Ruth Bader Ginsburg, Ginsburg], TEMPLATE[w, Elena Kagan, Kagan], TEMPLATE[w, Stephen Breyer, Breyer] and Kennedy voted in favour while Justices TEMPLATE[w, John Roberts, Roberts], TEMPLATE[w, Samuel Alito, Alito], TEMPLATE[w, Antonin Scalia, Scalia] and TEMPLATE[w, Clarence Thomas, Thomas] voted against.","Kennedy\u0027s decision brought tears to the eyes of some lawyers in the courtroom.  However, Justice Antonin Scalia in his dissenting opinion derided the majority decision: \"The opinion is couched in a style that is as pretentious as its content is egotistic. [...] Of course, the opinionâs showy profundities are often profoundly incoherent.\"","When the decision was made, police allowed people outside the court to wave the rainbow flag on the court plaza.  Demonstrators outside the court chanted \"Love has won\". This decision made the United States the 21st country to legalise same-sex marriage.","President Barack Obama responded to the decision: \"Today we can say, in no uncertain terms, that we have made our union a little more perfect.\"","After this decision, Facebook introduced a new tool to add rainbow coloring to one\u0027s profile picture to celebrate this victory. Mark Zuckerberg posted on Facebook \"I\u0027m so happy for all of my friends and everyone in our community who can finally celebrate their love and be recognized as equal couples under the law\".","Later, companies like TEMPLATE[w, Google], TEMPLATE[w, Yahoo], TEMPLATE[w, Tumblr] and TEMPLATE[w, Vine (service), Vine] TEMPLATE[w, twitter, tweeted] with hashtag \"#LoveWins\". That night, the TEMPLATE[w, White House] had the rainbow projected on the outside of the building to celebrate the decision.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Same-sex_marriage","description":"Category:Same-sex marriage"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:US_Supreme_Court","description":"Category:US Supreme Court"},{"id":"Category:Barack_Obama","description":"Category:Barack Obama"},{"id":"Category:Facebook","description":"Category:Facebook"},{"id":"Category:Mark_Zuckerberg","description":"Category:Mark Zuckerberg"},{"id":"Category:Antonin_Scalia","description":"Category:Antonin Scalia"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["June 28, 2015"]},{"name":"USA","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Supreme Court of the United States"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anthony Kennedy","Justice Anthony Kennedy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sonia Sotomayor","Sotomayor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ruth Bader Ginsburg","Ginsburg"]},{"name":"w","description":["Elena Kagan","Kagan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stephen Breyer","Breyer"]},{"name":"w