lish team were booked in the 77th, 83rd, and 90+2nd minutes respectively.","As the scores were 0\u0026ndash;0 at the end of 90 minutes of game play, the match proceeded in TEMPLATE[w, overtime (sports), extra time]. In the 108th minute, England won a penalty kick.  TEMPLATE[w, Fara Williams] netted the penalty which gave a lead to The three lionesses. The German team tried even in the dying moments but English goalkeeper TEMPLATE[w, Karen Bardsley] denied the Germans to claim the bronze medal.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]TEMPLATE[clear]","TEMPLATE[Footballbox, date\u003d4 July 2015\u003cbr\u003e14:00 (TEMPLATE) ((TEMPLATE)), time\u003d14:00 (TEMPLATE) ((TEMPLATE)), team1\u003d(TEMPLATE), score\u003d0â1, aet\u003dyes, report\u003d, team2\u003d(TEMPLATE), goals1\u003d, goals2\u003d(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE), stadium\u003d(TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE), attendance\u003d21,483, referee\u003dRi Hyang Ok (North Korea)]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Football_Match_Reports","description":"Category:Football Match Reports"},{"id":"Category:Alberta","description":"Category:Alberta"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["July 7, 2015"]},{"name":"football","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["England"]},{"name":"w","description":["Germany"]},{"name":"w","description":["third place playoff"]},{"name":"w","description":["2015 FIFA Women\u0027s World Cup","2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["FIFA Women\u0027s World Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["Commonwealth Stadium (Edmonton)","Commonwealth Stadium"]},{"name":"w","description":["Edmonton, Alberta","Edmonton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alberta"]},{"name":"w","descrip