{"title":"Djokovic defeats Federer to win 2015 Wimbledon Championship men\u0027s singles","wikiTitle":"Djokovic_defeats_Federer_to_win_2015_Wimbledon_Championship_men\u0027s_singles","wid":2306835,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-23T16:06:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/sport/0/tennis/33499557, title\u003dWimbledon 2015: Novak Djokovic beats Roger Federer in final, author\u003dPiers Newbery, pub\u003dBBC Sport, date\u003dJuly 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/news/articles/2015-07-12/how_the_final_was_won_and_lost.html, title\u003dHow the final was won and lost, author\u003dMatt Trollope, pub\u003dThe Championships, Wimbledon, date\u003dJuly 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/scores/stats/day21/1701ms.html, title\u003dMatch Statistics, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Championships, Wimbledon, date\u003dJuly 12, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, July 15, 2015] TEMPLATE[Sports]  On Sunday, TEMPLATE[w, Novak Djokovic] defeated seven-time champion TEMPLATE[w, Roger Federer] 7â6, 6â7, 6â4, 6â3 to win the TEMPLATE[w, 2015 Wimbledon Championships â Men\u0027s Singles, 2015 Wimbledon Championships] men\u0027s singles, which is overall his third Wimbledon trophy of his career. Djokovic, who is ranked world number one in men\u0027s tennis, has now won a total of nine TEMPLATE[w, Grand Slam (tennis), Grand Slam]Â titles.","Djokovic won the first set 7\u0026ndash;6 with 6 TEMPLATE[w, Ace (tennis), aces] in total. Federer snatched the second set 7\u0026ndash;6 in his favour, that too with 6 aces. The Serbian Djokovic had only 16 TEMPLATE[wikt, unforced error, unforced errors] as compared to Federer\u0027s 35 unforced errors. Completing the third and fourth sets 6\u0026ndash;4 and 6\u0026ndash;3, Djokovic ruined the chance of Federer winning the championship for an eighth time, a feat nobody has ever accomplished to date.","The match was completed in two hours and 56 minutes. After the match, Federer said \"I had my chances in the first set. I got lucky to win the second, had chances in the third. But he was better on the bigger points. He was rock solid, I didn\u0027t play badly myself. That\u0027s how it goes.\"","This was Djokovic\u0027s 48th victory in 2015.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, 2015 Wimbledon Championships â Men\u0027s Singles]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Tennis","description":"Category:Tennis"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Switzerland","description":"Category:Switzerland"},{"id":"Category:Serbia","description":"Category:Serbia"},{"id":"Category:Novak_Djokovic","description":"Category:Novak Djokovic"},{"id":"Category:Roger_Federer","description":"Category:Roger Federer"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["July 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Sports","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Novak Djokovic"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roger Federer"]},{"name":"w","description":["2015 Wimbledon Championships â Men\u0027s Singles","2015 Wimbledon Championships"]},{"name":"w","description":["Grand Slam (tennis)","Grand Slam"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ace (tennis)","aces"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["unforced error","unforced errors"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["2015 Wimbledon Championships â Men\u0027s Singles"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/sport/0/tennis/33499557","title\u003dWimbledon 2015: Novak Djokovic beats Roger Federer in final","author\u003dPiers Newbery","pub\u003dBBC Sport","date\u003dJuly 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/news/articles/2015-07-12/how_the_final_was_won_and_lost.html","title\u003dHow the final was won and lost","author\u003dMatt Trollope","pub\u003dThe Championships, Wimbledon","date\u003dJuly 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wimbledon.com/en_GB/scores/stats/day21/1701ms.html","title\u003dMatch Statistics","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Championships, Wimbledon","date\u003dJuly 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Formula One driver Jules Bianchi dies aged 25","wikiTitle":"Formula_One_driver_Jules_Bianchi_dies_aged_25","wid":2312656,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-24T18:56:31Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://espn.go.com/racing/f1/story/_/id/13276268/jules-bianchi-french-formula-one-driver-dies-injuries-sustained-2014-crash, title\u003dJules Bianchi dies from injuries suffered in 2014 Japanese GP crash, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dESPN, date\u003dJuly 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/120021, title\u003dJules Bianchi dies nine months after crash in Japanese F1 GP, author\u003d, pub\u003dAutosport, date\u003dJuly 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://motorsportstalk.nbcsports.com/2015/07/17/jules-bianchi-dies-at-age-25-his-family-confirms/, title\u003dJules Bianchi dies at age 25, his family confirms, author\u003dTony DiZinno, pub\u003dNBC Sports, date\u003dJuly 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/117246, title\u003dJules Bianchi begins rehabilitation therapy in French hospital, author\u003dPablo Elizalde, pub\u003dAutosport, date\u003dDecember 30, 2014]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.autosport.com/news/report.php/id/81893, title\u003dFerrari expands young driver academy, author\u003dMatt Beer, pub\u003dAutosport, date\u003dMarch 6, 2010]"]],"links":[{"id":"Formula_One","description":"Formula One"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, July 19, 2015] TEMPLATE[Formula_One] TEMPLATE[w, NÃ¼rburgring]TEMPLATE[w, World Series by Renault]TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Henry Mineur, Henry Mineur]]] French Formula One (F1) driver TEMPLATE[w, Jules Bianchi] died on Friday night at age 25, nine months after his serious accident at the TEMPLATE[w, 2014 Japanese Grand Prix]. News of his death was announced by his family the following morning:","TEMPLATE[cquote, It is with deep sadness that the parents of Jules Bianchi, Philippe and Christine, his brother Tom and sister MÃ©lanie, wish to make it known that Jules passed away last night at the Centre Hospitalier Universitaire (CHU) in Nice, (France) where he was admitted following the accident of 5th October 2014 at Suzuka Circuit during the Japanese Formula 1 Grand Prix.]","This is the first F1 race-related driver death since the TEMPLATE[w, 1994 San Marino Grand Prix], when TEMPLATE[w, Ayrton Senna] was killed.","On October 5, 2014, at the late portion of the Japanese Grand Prix at TEMPLATE[w, Suzuka Circuit], Bianchi collided with a tractor crane that had been attending to the crashed car of TEMPLATE[w, Adrian Sutil]. Bianchi\u0027s helmet became wedged underneath the tractor, causing a TEMPLATE[w, diffuse axonal injury], and he fell into a coma. After being treated at a Japanese medical centre, he was moved about two months after the accident to a hospital in TEMPLATE[w, Nice]. Placed in the TEMPLATE[w, intensive care unit], in December he began rehabilitation therapy. Bianchi\u0027s father, Philippe, described his non-progress as a \"daily torture\".","Bianchi, the 2007 TEMPLATE[w, Championnat de France Formula Renault 2.0, French Formula Renault] and 2009 TEMPLATE[w, Formula 3 Euro Series] champion, was the inaugural member of the TEMPLATE[w, Ferrari Driver Academy]. He joined F1 team TEMPLATE[w, Force India] in TEMPLATE[w, 2012 Formula One season, 2012]. In TEMPLATE[w, 2013 Formula One season, 2013], he joined TEMPLATE[w, Marussia F1]; the following year, at the TEMPLATE[w, 2014 Monaco Grand Prix], he scored his and Marussia\u0027s first points with a ninth-place finish.","After the accident, the TEMPLATE[w, FÃ©dÃ©ration Internationale de l\u0027Automobile, FIA], which sanctions Formula One racing, formed a panel to investigate the crash. Afterwards, the group revealed its findings: as Bianchi entered the TEMPLATE[w, run-off area] of the track, he disabled the failsafe mechanism by \"[applying] both throttle and brake together, using both feet\", while his front wheels were locked; the panel also stated he did not slow down enough to control his car. Eventually, F1 mandated the use of the \"virtual TEMPLATE[w, safety car]\", which requires drivers to enter the TEMPLATE[w, pit stop, pit lane] at slower speeds instead of proceeding around the track.","This is the Bianchi family\u0027s second driver death. TEMPLATE[w, Lucien Bianchi], the TEMPLATE[w, 1968 24 Hours of Le Mans] winner and Jules\u0027s great uncle, was killed in 1969 during testing at TEMPLATE[w, Circuit de la Sarthe], where the TEMPLATE[w, 24 Hours of Le Mans] race is held.","Upon the news of his death, many drivers sent their condolences through social media. Bianchi\u0027s Marussia team mate TEMPLATE[w, Max Chilton] tweeted, \"No words can describe what his family and the sport have lost. All I can say [is] it was a pleasure knowing and racing you.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Formula_One","description":"Category:Formula One"},{"id":"Category:Auto_racing","description":"Category:Auto racing"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:2014_Formula_One_season","description":"Category:2014 Formula One season"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["July 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Formula_One","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["NÃ¼rburgring"]},{"name":"w","description":["World Series by Renault"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Henry Mineur","Henry Mineur]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jules Bianchi"]},{"name":"w","description":["2014 Japanese Grand Prix"]},{"name":"cquote","description":["It is with deep sadness that the parents of Jules Bianchi, Philippe and Christine, his brother Tom and sister MÃ©lanie, wish to make it known that Jules passed away last night at the Centre Hospitalier Universitaire (CHU) in Nice, (France) where he was admitted following the accident of 5th October 2014 at Suzuka Circuit during the Japanese Formula 1 Grand Prix."]},{"name":"w","description":["1994 San Marino Grand Prix"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ayrton Senna"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suzuka Circuit"]},{"name":"w","description":["Adrian Sutil"]},{"name":"w","description":["diffuse axonal injury"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nice"]},{"name":"w","description":["intensive care unit"]},{"name":"w","description":["Championnat de France Formula Renault 2.0","French Formula Renault"]},{"name":"w","description":["Formula 3 Euro Series"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ferrari Driver Academy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Force India"]},{"name":"w","description":["2012 Formula One season","2012"]},{"name":"w","description":["2013 Formula One season","2013"]},{"name":"w","description":["Marussia F1"]},{"name":"w","description":["2014 Monaco Grand Prix"]},{"name":"w","description":["FÃ©dÃ©ration Internationale de l\u0027Automobile","FIA"]},{"name":"w","description":["run-off area"]},{"name":"w","description":["safety car"]},{"name":"w","description":["pit stop","pit lane"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lucien Bianchi"]},{"name":"w","description":["1968 24 Hours of Le Mans"]},{"name":"w","description":["Circuit de la Sarthe"]},{"name":"w","description":["24 Hours of Le Mans"]},{"name":"w","description":["Max Chilton"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://espn.go.com/racing/f1/story/_/id/13276268/jules-bianchi-french-formula-one-driver-dies-injuries-sustained-2014-crash","title\u003dJules Bianchi dies from injuries suffered in 2014 Japanese GP crash","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dESPN","date\u003dJuly 18, 2015"]},{"name":