{"title":"Arsenal defeats Chelsea 1-0 to win Community Shield 2015","wikiTitle":"Arsenal_defeats_Chelsea_1-0_to_win_Community_Shield_2015","wid":2339941,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-17T01:04:20Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3182844/Arsenal-vs-Chelsea-FA-Community-Shield-2015-LIVE-football-score-London-rivals-kick-new-season-Wembley.html, title\u003dArsenal 1-0 Chelsea Community Shield 2015 RESULT: Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain beats champions with fine goal at Wembley, author\u003dJonny Singer, pub\u003dDaily Mail, date\u003dAugust 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/sport/0/football/33667216, title\u003dArsenal 1-0 Chelsea, author\u003dAndy Cryer, pub\u003dBBC Sport, date\u003dAugust 2, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/football/teams/arsenal/11769945/Arsenal-1-0-Chelsea-Community-Shield-2015-as-it-happened.html, title\u003dArsenal 1-0 Chelsea, Community Shield 2015: as it happened, author\u003dAdam Hurrey, pub\u003dThe Sunday Telegraph, date\u003dAugust 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thefa.com/news/competitions/fa-community-shield/2015/aug/chelsea-v-arsenal-fa-community-shield-match-report, title\u003dArsenal brush aside Chelsea to lift Community Shield, author\u003dJamie Reid, pub\u003dThe FA, date\u003dAugust 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"football_(soccer)","description":"football"},{"id":"Arsenal_F.C.","description":"Arsenal"},{"id":"Chelsea_F.C.","description":"Chelsea"},{"id":"Belgium","description":"Belgian"},{"id":"ArsÃ¨ne_Wenger","description":"ArsÃ¨ne Wenger"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[football] On Sunday, London-based football club Arsenal, winners of the TEMPLATE[w, 2014â15 FA Cup, 2015 FA Cup], defeated TEMPLATE[w, 2014â15 Premier League, 2015] TEMPLATE[w, Premier League] Champions Chelsea 1\u0026ndash;0 in the TEMPLATE[w, 2015 FA Community Shield, 2015] TEMPLATE[w, FA Community Shield, Community Shield trophy] which was played in the TEMPLATE[w, Wembley Stadium]. TEMPLATE[image, Stanislav Vedmid] The match saw only two TEMPLATE[w, yellow card (association football), yellow cards], to one player from each club in the second half. Though Arsenal had lesser possession of the ball and fewer shots, they had more shots on target. A total of 23 fouls were committed.","It took fourteen attempts for The Gunners to win a game over the city rivals. TEMPLATE[w, Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain] scored the only goal of the match, for Arsenal in the 24th minute. Belgian TEMPLATE[w, Goalkeeper (association football), goalkeeper] TEMPLATE[w, Thibaut Courtois] could not save this left-footed shot in the top corner which gave Arsenal a lead. In the 80th minute, Chelsea won a free kick. TEMPLATE[w, Eden Hazard]\u0027s kick was denied by ex-Chelsea TEMPLATE[w, Petr Äech], who recently signed for Arsenal and this was his debut for Arsenal.","This was ArsÃ¨ne Wenger\u0027s first victory over the TEMPLATE[w, Portugual, Portuguese] Chelsea manager TEMPLATE[w, JosÃ© Mourinho]. Wenger did not even shake hands with Mourinho after the victory. This is back-to-back Community Shields for Arsenal. They defeated TEMPLATE[w, Manchester City] in the previous final.","\"We were the best team\", said Mourinho in remarks to TEMPLATE[w, BT Sport].  \"We had more initiative, we controlled the game by having ball possession. Arsenal defended with 10 players, they put everybody in front of their own line and they had good organisation, congratulations to them.\" TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]TEMPLATE[clear]","TEMPLATE[footballbox, date\u003dAugust 2, 2015 \u003cbr\u003e15:00 (TEMPLATE), time\u003d15:00 CET, team1\u003d[[Arsenal F.C., Arsenal]], score\u003d1â0, team2\u003d[[Chelsea F.C., Chelsea]], goals1\u003d(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE), goals2\u003d, stadium\u003d(TEMPLA