{"title":"U.S. presidential candidate Mark Everson challenges debate exclusion","wikiTitle":"U.S._presidential_candidate_Mark_Everson_challenges_debate_exclusion","wid":2342319,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-13T13:08:20Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.documentcloud.org/documents/2190707-fec-complaint-from-mark-everson.html#pages/p1, title\u003dComplaint to the FEC, author\u003dMark Everson, date\u003dAugust 3, 2015, pub\u003d]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2015/08/03/the-gops-18th-candidate-files-a-complaint-against-fox-newss-new-pre-debate-cutoff/, title\u003dCan Fox News exclude candidates just because they arenât mentioned in polls?, author\u003dPhilip Bump, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dAugust 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.businessinsider.com/mark-everson-launches-2016-campaign-with-emotional-letter-2015-3, title\u003dLong shot 2016 candidate launches campaign with emotional 16-page letter, author\u003dLeslie Larson, pub\u003dBusiness Insider, date\u003dMarch 5, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Republican Party"},{"id":"Indiana","description":"Indiana"},{"id":"New_York","description":"New York"},{"id":"Virginia","description":"Virginia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 5, 2015] TEMPLATE[2016_US_Presidential_Election] U.S. Republican Party TEMPLATE[w, President of the United States, presidential] candidate TEMPLATE[w, Mark Everson], former commissioner of the TEMPLATE[w, Internal Revenue Service] (IRS), filed a complaint on Monday with the TEMPLATE[w, Federal Election Commission] (FEC) to challenge his exclusion from Thursday\u0027s first TEMPLATE[w, Fox News] Republican Party presidential debate. Everson argues his exclusion violates Title 11 of the TEMPLATE[w, U.S. Code of Federal Regulations] in that debate hosts must not \"structure the debates to promote or advance one candidate over another\", and must \"use pre-established objective criteria to determine which candidates may participate in a debate.\" TEMPLATE[image, U.S. Government] Everson served as Commissioner of the IRS from 2003 to 2007, during the TEMPLATE[w, George W. Bush] administration. After his departure, he briefly served as CEO of the TEMPLATE[w, American Red Cross], worked in the cabinet of Indiana TEMPLATE[w, Governor of Indiana, governor] TEMPLATE[w, Mitch Daniels], and worked for the tax consulting firm TEMPLATE[w, alliantgroup]. He announced his candidacy this past March with a sixteen-page open letter in which he outlined the six pillars of his campaign: amnesty for TEMPLATE[w, Illegal immigration in the United States, illegal immigrants], reinstatement of the TEMPLATE[w, military draft], a promise to serve only a single presidential term, and calls for tax reform, deficit reduction, and corporate responsibility.","Fox News claims Everson fails to meet the criteria it established for Thursday\u0027s two debates. Only seventeen candidates meet the criteria, which require a candidate \"consistently\" be included in \"recognized\" opinion polls. The TEMPLATE[w, prime time, prime-time] event features the top ten candidates by average polling percentage. The other seven participate in a separate debate just before the prime time event.","In his complaint, Everson urges the FEC to compel Fox News to include him in the second tier debate as the eighth participant.","Everson argues Fox News, in violation of Title 11, \"structure[d] the debates to promote or advance one candidate over another\" through a July 27 change to its criteria that replaced a pre-existing one percent polling threshold with a threshold admitting those \"consistently\" included in \"recognized\" polls. He alleges this was done to ensure the inclusion of the low-polling candidates former TEMPLATE[w, Hewlett-Packard] CEO TEMPLATE[w, Carly Fiorina], former New York TEMPLATE[w, Governor of New York, governor] TEMPLATE[w, George Pataki], TEMPLATE[w, US Senate, Senator] TEMPLATE[w, Lindsey Graham], and former Virginia TEMPLATE[w, Governor of Virginia, governor] TEMPLATE[w, Jim Gilmore], because Fox News recognizes these candidates as \"major players.\"","Furthermore, Everson argues the Fox News criteria are not \"objective,\" as Title 11 requires, because they fail to define the terms \"consistently\" and \"recognized\" when referring to polls. He asserts he was included in the Republican Party\u0027s online straw poll in May and is the only candidate still listed on that poll who has been excluded from Thursday\u0027s debate.","TEMPLATE[w, Election law] expert TEMPLATE[w, Richard Winger], publisher of TEMPLATE[w, Ballot Access News], says Everson is \"completely correct\" in his challenge. However, he believes Everson only has a chance of success if he actually files a lawsuit rather than simply complaining to the FEC.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Election_Commission_of_the_United_States","description":"Category:Federal Election Commission of the United States"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:2016_United_States_presidential_election","description":"Category:2016 United States presidential election"},{"id":"Category:Carly_Fiorina","description":"Category:Carly Fiorina"},{"id":"Category:George_Pataki","description":"Category:George Pataki"},{"id":"Category:Lindsey_Graham","description":"Category:Lindsey Graham"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 5, 2015"]},{"name":"2016_US_Presidential_Election","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["President of the United States","presidential"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mark Everson"]},{"name":"w","description":["Internal Revenue Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["Federal Election Commission"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fox News"]},{"name":"w","description":["U.S. Code of Federal Regulations"]},{"name":"image","description":["U.S. Government"]},{"name":"w","description":["George W. Bush"]},{"name":"w","description":["American Red Cross"]},{"name":"w","description":["Governor of Indiana","governor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mitch Daniels"]},{"name":"w","description":["alliantgroup"]},{"name":"w","description":["Illegal immigration in the United States","illegal immigrants"]},{"name":"w","description":["military draft"]},{"name":"w","description":["prime time","prime-time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hewlett-Packard"]},{"name":"w","description":["Carly Fiorina"]},{"name":"w","description":["Governor of New York","governor"]},{"name":"w","description":["George Pataki"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Senate","Senator"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lindsey Graham"]},{"name":"w","description":["Governor of Virginia","governor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jim Gilmore"]},{"name":"w","description":["Election law"]},{"name":"w","description":["Richard Winger"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ballot Access News"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.documentcloud.org/documents/2190707-fec-complaint-from-mark-everson.html#pages/p1","title\u003dComplaint to the FEC","author\u003dMark Everson","date\u003dAugust 3, 2015","pub\u003d"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.washingtonpost.com/news/the-fix/wp/2015/08/03/the-gops-18th-candidate-files-a-complaint-against-fox-newss-new-pre-debate-cu