{"title":"Suspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands","wikiTitle":"Suspected_plane_debris_washes_ashore_on_several_Maldives_islands","wid":2348872,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-26T15:24:47Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/news/61447, title\u003dMore sightings of suspected plane debris reported across Maldives, author\u003dAli Naafiz, pub\u003dHaveeru Daily, date\u003dAugust 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://raajje.mv/45622, title\u003d\"Airline debris\" washed up in Maldives, author\u003d, pub\u003dRaajjÃ© Online, date\u003dAugust 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.sun.mv/english/31491, title\u003dA team from Police has gone to Banyan Tree resort to investigate the suspected plane debris found on the island, author\u003d, pub\u003dSunOnline, date\u003dAugust 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://syria-personally.beforeitsnews.com/alternative/2015/08/mh370-suspected-debris-strangely-being-secretly-disappeared-3196082.html, title\u003dMH370 Suspected Debris Strangely Being Secretly Disappeared (Photos), author\u003dDeborah DuprÃ©, pub\u003dBefore It\u0027s News, date\u003dAugust 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/news/61424, title\u003dMaldives Police probe plane debris claims, author\u003dMohamed Visham, pub\u003dHaveeru Daily, date\u003dAugust 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.maldivesfinest.com/mh370-possible-wing-part-found-on-maldives-island, title\u003dPossible wing part of MH370 found on Vabbinfaru Island Maldives, author\u003d, pub\u003dMaldivesfinest, date\u003dAugust 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/modrindo/posts/10152868169331503?pnref\u003dstory, title\u003dMohamed Wafir (Photo source), author\u003d, pub\u003dFacebook, date\u003dAugust 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.huffingtonpost.co.uk/2015/04/04/mh370-maldives-islanders-low-flying-missing-malaysia-airlines-flight_n_7003406.html, title\u003dMH370: Maldives Islanders Insist They Witnessed \u0027Low Flying\u0027 Missing Malaysia Airlines Flight, author\u003dSara C. Nelson, pub\u003dThe Huffington Post, date\u003dApril 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/missing-malaysia-airlines-plane-maldives-discounted-as-possible-location-for-mh370-20140319-hvkjq.html, title\u003dMissing Malaysia Airlines plane: Maldives discounted as possible location for MH370, author\u003dJason Koutsoukis, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dMarch 19, 2014]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] TEMPLATE[image, [[w:User:TUBS, TUBS]]] Authorities are investigating what\u0027s left of debris believed to belong to a plane, that washed ashore several small islands in the TEMPLATE[w, Maldives]. The investigation began as a result of photos of the debris being uploaded to the social networking TEMPLATE[w, website] TEMPLATE[w, Facebook]. Some of the debris is reported to have washed ashore as early as May 31 and was found on a beach owned by the Banyan Tree Vabbinfaru resort, located in TEMPLATE[w, Kaafu Atoll]. In the past few days, several other pieces of debris were recovered on at least three other islands. Authorities are trying to determine if it may be part of TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia Airlines Flight 370] (MH370). Last week, a piece of a wing known as a TEMPLATE[w, flaperon], reported to be from MH370, was found washed ashore on TEMPLATE[w, RÃ©union] Island.","Pictures taken of the objects recovered in the Maldives on, reportedly, May 31, were posted to Facebook by an employee of the resort. That prompted authorities to launch an investigation into the debris, but before it could be examined, it had already been sent away for disposal. The photographs show a large white object, possibly two, stained with TEMPLATE[w, algae] and appear to be made of a TEMPLATE[w, fiberglass] and honeycomb material. The objects appear to be several TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), feet] in length and width and in one photo where the paint is severely peeled, red letters \"IC\" can be seen.  Those pieces, along with others, were taken away and disposed of as trash. When authorities discovered the photographs, they returned to the site, but only found a small, five to seven TEMPLATE[w, inch] (about 13\u0026ndash;18\u0026nbsp;TEMPLATE[w, centimetre, cm]) piece of debris they say doesn\u0027t appear to be part of a plane.","According to the resort\u0027s manager Mr. Naseem, the bigger pieces of debris and other waste were taken away and disposed of in the usual way. He added other forms of debris and trash with no value, such as buoys and suspected military waste, wash up on the islands all the time, especially during TEMPLATE[w, monsoon] season. Local residents and resort workers regularly collect trash which is sent to the garbage island TEMPLATE[w, Thilafushi] where it\u0027s sorted, exported for recycling, or burned. Reports say at the time the debris was collected, no one suspected it could be from MH370.","\"Although some of it was taken to Thilafushi, there is still a five or a seven inch piece on the resort. It was left because it is small. The management has decided to hand it over to the Police\", said an unnamed official to SunOnline, who said authorities don\u0027t know if any of the debris taken away has been destroyed. The Serious and Organized Crime Unit of the TEMPLATE[w, Maldives Police Service] and experts from the TEMPLATE[w, Maldives Civil Aviation Authority] are heading the investigation.","Yesterday, reports stated several more pieces of debris, one piece measuring some eight feet by two feet (about 2.4 by 0.6\u0026nbsp;TEMPLATE[w, metre, m]), were found on TEMPLATE[w, Baa Atoll], TEMPLATE[w, Fehendhoo] and TEMPLATE[w, Fulhadhoo, Fulhahdhoo] and washed ashore sometime in the past few days. One piece appears to have a serial number on the side, possibly reading \u0027021411270507.\u0027 Initially residents who found the debris took it home. \"A resident had found the debris and taken it home. Nobody had thought twice about it then. When he heard about the discovery in Vabbinfaru resort we immediately called the Police,\" said Mohamed Ibrahim, a councilman for Fehendhoo Island, to Haveeru Daily.","MH370, while flying from TEMPLATE[w, Kuala Lumpur], TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia] to TEMPLATE[w, Beijing], TEMPLATE[w, China], vanished without a trace on March 8, 2014. All 239 passengers and crew are believed to be dead. On the day the plane went missing, residents on the small Maldive island of TEMPLATE[w, Kudahuvadhoo] claimed to have seen a very \"low flying jumbo jet\" crash into the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Ocean]. Some also noted the colors appeared to resemble that of a TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia Airlines] plane. \"Iâve never seen a jet flying so low over our island before. We\u0027ve seen seaplanes, but I\u0027m sure that this was not one of those. I could even make out the doors on the plane clearly\", one resident was quoted as saying to the newspaper TEMPLATE[w, Haveeru Daily]. Some claim the plane appeared to be headed in the direction of TEMPLATE[w, Diego Garcia].","According to TEMPLATE[w, The Huffington Post], Haveeru reported the witnesses were interviewed by authorities who deemed their statements to be truthful, but Maldive military officials along with TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia, Malaysian] officials say no such aircraft was in Maldive airspace at the time MH370 went missing. \"Based on the monitoring up to date, no indication of Flight MH370 has been observed on any military radars in the country [Maldives]. Furthermore, the data of radars at Maldives airports have also been analysed and shows no indication of the said flight\", said Malaysian Transport Minister Hishamuddin Hussein.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Maldives","description":"Category:Maldives"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:China","description":"Category:China"},{"id":"Category:RÃ©union","description":"Category:RÃ©union"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Category:British_Indian_Ocean_Territory","description":"Category:British Indian Ocean Territory"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[w:User:TUBS","TUBS]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maldives"]},{"name":"w","description":["website"]},{"name":"w","description":["Facebook"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaafu Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"]},{"name":"w","description":["flaperon"]},{"name":"w","description":["RÃ©union"]},{"name":"w","description":["algae"]},{"name":"w","description":["fiberglass"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","feet"]},{"name":"w","description":["inch"]},{"name":"w","description":["centimetre","cm"]},{"name":"w","description":["monsoon"]},{"name":"w","description":["Thilafushi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maldives Police Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maldives Civil Aviation Authority"]},{"name":"w","description":["metre","m"]},{"name":"w","description":["Baa Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fehendhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fulhadhoo","Fulhahdhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kuala Lumpur"]},{"name":"w","description":["Malaysia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Beijing"]},{"name":"w","description":["China"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kudahuvadhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Ocean"]},{