{"title":"Report: Vice-premier of North Korea executed","wikiTitle":"Report:_Vice-premier_of_North_Korea_executed","wid":2361631,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-24T20:46:03Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-33882799, title\u003dNorth Korea vice-premier Choe Yong-gon \u0027executed\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/north-korea-executes-vice-premier-for-discontent-with-leader-yonhap-20150812-gixwpd.html, title\u003dNorth Korea executes vice for discontent with leader: Yonhap, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"North_Korea","description":"North Korea"},{"id":"Wikinews","description":"Wikinews"},{"id":"Kim_Jong-un","description":"Kim Jong-un"},{"id":"BBC","description":"BBC"},{"id":"Kim_Jong-il","description":"Kim Jong-il"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[North_Korea] TEMPLATE[w, Supreme People\u0027s Assembly]TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Nicor, Nicor]]]A report published Wednesday by the TEMPLATE[w, Yonhap, Yonhap News Agency] claims vice premier Choe Yong-gon  of North Korea was executed in May.  The report, which cites an unnamed source, has not been confirmed by Wikinews or other agencies.  The government of North Korea rarely makes statements about its internal affairs.","According to the report, the 63-year-old Choe had disagreed with Supreme Leader Kim Jong-un\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, forestry] policies.  Choe, one of seven vice premiers, was in charge of construction and building material industries.  He was appointed to the position in June of 2014.  Choe was involved with trade talks between the two Koreas in the mid-2000s.  In 2004, he attended the opening of the TEMPLATE[w, Kaesong Industrial Region], a joint venture of the two nations.","South Korea\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Ministry of Unification] told both TEMPLATE[w, Reuters] and BBC it was monitoring the situation but Choe has not been seen publicly since December.  Back in April, South Korea\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, National Intelligence Service (South Korea), National Intelligence Service] said executions had been ordered for fifteen officials including a \"forestry official\".  Choe Yong-gon was not mentioned by name, nor is it known now if the report was referring to Choe.","Yonhap has attributed roughly 70 executions of officials to Kim Jong-un\u0027s rule which began after the death of his father Kim Jong-il in December 2011.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:North_Korea","description":"Category:North Korea"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Kim_Jong-un","description":"Category:Kim Jong-un"},{"id":"Category:Korean_Peninsula","description":"Category:Korean Peninsula"},{"id":"Category:Kaesong","description":"Category:Kaesong"},{"id":"Category:Kaesong_Industrial_Region","description":"Category:Kaesong Industrial Region"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 12, 2015"]},{"name":"North_Korea","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Supreme People\u0027s Assembly"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Nicor","Nicor]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yonhap","Yonhap News Agency"]},{"name":"w","description":["forestry"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaesong Industrial Region"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ministry of Unification"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reuters"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Intelligence Service (South Korea)","National Intelligence Service"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-33882799","title\u003dNorth Korea vice-premier Choe Yong-gon \u0027executed\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/north-korea-executes-vice-premier-for-discontent-with-leader-yonhap-20150812-gixwpd.html","title\u003dNorth Korea executes vice for discontent with leader: Yonhap","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Malaysia says debris found in Maldives could be from MH370","wikiTitle":"Malaysia_says_debris_found_in_Maldives_could_be_from_MH370","wid":2361901,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-26T16:14:23Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMalaysia to investigate suspected plane debris washed ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/news/61522, title\u003dMalaysia \u0027believes\u0027 debris in Maldives resort from MH370, author\u003dMohamed Visham, pub\u003dHaveeru Daily, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/suspected-plane-debris-found-in-maldives-to-be-brought-to-malaysia, title\u003dSuspected plane debris found in Maldives to be brought to Malaysia, author\u003dMelati A. Jalil, pub\u003dThe Malaysian Insider, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysian"},{"id":"Maldives","description":"Maldives"},{"id":"Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"},{"id":"Kuala_Lumpur","description":"Kuala Lumpur"},{"id":"Beijing","description":"Beijing"},{"id":"Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Malaysia Airlines"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[image, Mohamed Wafir (via Facebook)] TEMPLATE[image, [[w:User:AHeneen, AHeneen]]] Malaysian officials stated Wednesday, some of the debris found in the Maldives will be brought back to Malaysia to determine if they are from Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 (MH370) as they now believe. A team arrived Tuesday in Maldives to take charge of the debris, which had previously been disposed of as trash.","\"We [Malaysia] have an understanding with the authorities there [Maldives] ...we think the parts which were found about a month ago were parts of the aircraft,\" said Ab Aziz Kaprawi, the deputy transport minister for Malaysia as quoted by TEMPLATE[w, Bernama], a Malaysian government news agency. \"They have to be further analysed and will be brought back to Malaysia for verification,\" he added.","\"The parts are currently undergoing few processes before they can be released and brought to Malaysia for further identification and verification,\" said Seri Liow Tiong Lai, Malaysia\u0027s transport minister during a press conference today. \"If it belongs to Boeing 777 then we will have to carry out further analysis and verification,\" he added. Malaysia\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Department of Civil Aviation Malaysia, Department of Civil Aviation] will be in charge of examining the debris once it arrives in the country.","The debris washed ashore the TEMPLATE[w, Kaafu Atoll] reportedly around May 31 and was recovered by employees of the Banyan Tree Vabbinfaru Resort. However the debris had been disposed of as trash before authorities could examine it. An investigation into the debris was launched after photos of it were uploaded to the TEMPLATE[w, social networking service] Facebook, by an employee of the resort. The photographs show a large white object, possibly two, stained with TEMPLATE[w, algae] and appear to be made of a TEMPLATE[w, fiberglass] and honeycomb material.","Debris has since washed ashore on at least three other Maldives locations, the TEMPLATE[w, Baa Atoll], and the islands of TEMPLATE[w, Fehendhoo] and TEMPLATE[w, Fulhadhoo, Fulhahdhoo], but most of it isn\u0027t believed to be from an aircraft. Abdulla Rasheed, a captain of a cargo boat which recently capsized in the waters off the Maldives stated, \"From the pictures of the debris found on most of the islands, I can almost certainly say that they are from the cargo we were carrying.\" Despite this possibility, any debris located is being gathered up until Malaysian authorities can examine it.","\"We are collecting any unidentified debris and storing them in a warehouse so that the Malaysians can carry out tests and determine if it is from their plane or not,\" said the office of the Maldives President in a statement reported by TEMPLATE[w, Haveeru Daily] on Monday.","MH370, while flying from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia to Beijing, China, vanished on March 8, 2014. All 239 passengers and crew are believed to be dead. On the day the plane went missing, residents on the small Maldives island of TEMPLATE[w, Kudahuvadhoo] claimed to have seen a very \"low flying jumbo jet\" crash into the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Ocean]. Some also noted the colors appeared to resemble that of a Malaysia Airlines plane. \"Iâve never seen a jet flying so low over our island before. We\u0027ve seen seaplanes, but I\u0027m sure that this was not one of those. I could even make out the doors on the plane clearly\", one resident was quoted as saying to the newspaper Haveeru Daily. Some claim the plane appeared to be headed in the direction of TEMPLATE[w, Diego Garcia], but Malaysian authorities have discounted those claims.","\"Based on the monitoring up to date, no indication of Flight MH370 has been observed on any military radars in the country [Maldives]. Furthermore, the data of radars at Maldives airports have also been analysed and shows no indication of the said flight,\" said Malaysia\u0027s transport ministry at the time of the report.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:Maldives","description":"Category:Maldives"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Category:British_Indian_Ocean_Territory","description":"Category:British Indian Ocean Territory"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 12, 2015"]},{"name":"image","description":["Mohamed Wafir (via Facebook)"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[w:User:AHeneen","AHeneen]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bernama"]},{"name":"w","description":["Department of Civil Aviation Malaysia","Department of Civil Aviation"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaafu Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["social networking service"]},{"name":"w","description":["algae"]},{"name":"w","description":["fiberglass"]},{"name":"w","description":["Baa Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fehendhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fulhadhoo","Fulhahdhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Haveeru Daily"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kudahuvadhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Ocean"]},{"name":"w","description":["Diego Garcia"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMalaysia to investigate suspected plane debris washed ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 10, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/news/61522","title\u003dMalaysia \u0027believes\u0027 debris in Maldives resort from MH370","author\u003dMohamed Visham","pub\u003dHaveeru Daily","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.themalaysianinsider.com/malaysia/article/suspected-plane-debris-found-in-maldives-to-be-brought-to-malaysia","title\u003dSuspected plane debris found in Maldives to be brought to Malaysia","author\u003dMelati A. Jalil","pub\u003dThe Malaysian Insider","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Haveeru Daily]","Haveeru Daily"]}
{"title":"Huge explosions in Tianjin, China","wikiTitle":"Huge_explosions_in_Tianjin,_China","wid":2362527,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-24T20:38:06Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2015-08/13/c_134509489.htm, title\u003dWarehouse blast rocks N China port city, at least 50 wounded, author\u003dMu Xuequan, pub\u003dXinhua, date\u003dAugust 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-33896292, title\u003dChina blasts: Casualties as Tianjin warehouse blows up, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC, date\u003dAugust 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://reuters.com/article/idUSKCN0QH2B220150812?irpc\u003d932, title\u003dHuge explosions in China\u0027s Tianjin kill seven, injure 180: Xinhua, author\u003d Kazunori Takada, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url \u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/12/explosion-chinese-port-city-tianjin, title\u003dExplosions in Chinese city of Tianjin kill at least 17 and injure hundreds, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-33901206, title\u003dChina explosions: Tianjin blasts \u0027on seismic scale\u0027, author\u003dHeather Chen, pub\u003dBBC, date\u003d13 August 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"China","description":"Chinese"},{"id":"Beijing","description":"Beijing"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 13, 2015] TEMPLATE[China] TEMPLATE[image, [https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCj7wKsOBhRD9Jy4yahkMRMw CCTV America]] TEMPLATE[image, [[w:User:ASDFGH, ASDFGH]]] The Chinese news agency TEMPLATE[w, Xinhua News Agency, Xinhua] reports that there have been two massive explosions within seconds of each other, at about 11:30 p.m. local time, in a warehouse in the port of Dongjiang in TEMPLATE[w, Tianjin], a city of 15 million, near Beijing, in north-east China.","At least thirteen people have been killed and between 250 and 400 people injured. Two firefighters are also believed to be missing at the scene. Mobile phone footage taken by locals shows a large fireball in the Binhai New Area of the city. The warehouse is thought to belong RuiHai Logistics, and may have been storing explosives.","The two blasts were significant enough to register approximately magnitude 2.3 and 2.9 on the seismic scale as reported by the TEMPLATE[w, China Earthquake Administration].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Wikipedia, 2015 Tianjin explosion] TEMPLATE[broadcast_report, noimg\u003dtrue]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:China","description":"Category:China"},{"id":"Category:Beijing","description":"Category:Beijing"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Fires","description":"Category:Fires"},{"id":"Category:China_Earthquake_Administration","description":"Category:China Earthquake Administration"},{"id":"Category:Tianjin","description":"Category:Tianjin"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 13, 2015"]},{"name":"China","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCj7wKsOBhRD9Jy4yahkMRMw CCTV America]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[w:User:ASDFGH","ASDFGH]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Xinhua News Agency","Xinhua"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tianjin"]},{"name":"w","description":["China Earthquake Administration"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Wikipedia","description":["2015 Tianjin explosion"]},{"name":"broadcast_report","description":["noimg\u003dtrue"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2015-08/13/c_134509489.htm","title\u003dWarehouse blast rocks N China port city, at least 50 wounded","author\u003dMu Xuequan","pub\u003dXinhua","date\u003dAugust 13, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-33896292","title\u003dChina blasts: Casualties as Tianjin warehouse blows up","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC","date\u003dAugust 13, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://reuters.com/article/idUSKCN0QH2B220150812?irpc\u003d932","title\u003dHuge explosions in China\u0027s Tianjin kill seven, injure 180: Xinhua","author\u003d Kazunori Takada","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url \u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/12/explosion-chinese-port-city-tianjin","title\u003dExplosions in Chinese city of Tianjin kill at least 17 and injure hundreds","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-china-33901206","title\u003dChina explosions: Tianjin blasts \u0027on seismic scale\u0027","author\u003dHeather Chen","pub\u003dBBC","date\u003d13 August 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["noimg","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"More suspected plane debris washes ashore on Maldives island","wikiTitle":"More_suspected_plane_debris_washes_ashore_on_Maldives_island","wid":2364843,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-26T16:09:29Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMalaysia says debris found in Maldives could be from MH370, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMalaysia to investigate suspected plane debris washed ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://raajje.mv/46025, title\u003dSuspected plane parts found in Laamu atoll, author\u003dMohamed Junaid, pub\u003dRaajjÃ© Online, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/banyan_tree_vabbinfaru/61538, title\u003dSuspected plane wing fragment found in Maldives, author\u003dMohamed Visham, pub\u003dHaveeru Daily, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/banyan_tree_vabbinfaru/61522, title\u003dMalaysia \u0027believes\u0027 debris in Maldives resort from MH370, author\u003dMohamed Visham, pub\u003dHaveeru Daily, date\u003dAugust 12, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Maldives","description":"Maldives"},{"id":"Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysia"},{"id":"Kuala_Lumpur","description":"Kuala Lumpur"},{"id":"Beijing","description":"Beijing"},{"id":"China","description":"China"},{"id":"Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Malaysia Airlines"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 13, 2015]TEMPLATE[aviation] Debris believed to be part of an aircraft has washed ashore on an uninhabited island in the Maldives. The fragment, suspected to be from a wing, was found on Mendhoo island, within the TEMPLATE[w, Laamu Atoll]. The finding comes after several pieces of suspected plane debris washed ashore on the resort island Vabbinfaru, within the TEMPLATE[w, Kaafu Atoll], some of which could be from Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 (MH370).","The newest piece of debris is white and severely damaged and dented in places. Some of the paint also appears to be peeling off. Authorities have collected the debris, to be examined later. Malaysian officials are currently investigating other debris to determine if they came from an aircraft and if so \"discussions will be held to determine the next steps in terms of the process of analysis\", said the Malaysian transport ministry in a statement.","On Tuesday, a team of Malaysian investigators arrived in Maldives to take charge of debris washed ashore on Vabbinfaru on May 31, which had previously been disposed of as trash, and transport it back to Malaysia for further analysis. Malaysia said they believe the debris could be from MH370, but no official confirmation has been made.","\"We (Malaysia) have an understanding with the authorities there [the Maldives] [...] we think the parts which were found about a month ago were parts of the aircraft,\" said Ab Aziz Kaprawi, the deputy transport minister for Malaysia as quoted by TEMPLATE[w, Bernama], a Malaysian government news agency. \"They have to be further analysed and will be brought back to Malaysia for verification\", he added.","Since the Vabbinfaru incident, debris has washed ashore on at least three other Maldives locations, the TEMPLATE[w, Baa Atoll] and the islands of TEMPLATE[w, Fehendhoo] and TEMPLATE[w, Fulhadhoo, Fulhahdhoo], but much of it isn\u0027t believed to be from an aircraft. Abdulla Rasheed, a captain of a cargo boat which recently capsized in the waters off the Maldives, stated, \"From the pictures of the debris found on most of the islands, I can almost certainly say that they are from the cargo we were carrying.\" Despite this possibility, any debris located is being gathered up until Malaysian authorities can examine it.","\"We are collecting any unidentified debris and storing them in a warehouse so that the Malaysians can carry out tests and determine if it is from their plane or not,\" said the office of the Maldives President in a statement reported by TEMPLATE[w, Haveeru Daily] before the Malaysian investigators arrived.","MH370, while flying from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia to Beijing, China, vanished on March 8, 2014. All 239 passengers and crew are believed to be dead. On the day the plane went missing, residents on the small Maldives island of TEMPLATE[w, Kudahuvadhoo] claimed to have seen a very \"low flying jumbo jet\" crash into the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Ocean]. Some also noted the colors appeared to resemble that of a Malaysia Airlines plane. \"I\u0027ve never seen a jet flying so low over our island before. We\u0027ve seen seaplanes, but I\u0027m sure that this was not one of those. I could even make out the doors on the plane clearly\", one resident was quoted as saying to the newspaper Haveeru Daily. Some claim the plane appeared to be headed in the direction of TEMPLATE[w, Diego Garcia], but Malaysian authorities have discounted those claims.","\"Based on the monitoring up to date, no indication of Flight MH370 has been observed on any military radars in the country [Maldives]. Furthermore, the data of radars at Maldives airports have also been analysed and shows no indication of the said flight,\" said Malaysia\u0027s transport ministry at the time of the reports.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Maldives","description":"Category:Maldives"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Category:British_Indian_Ocean_Territory","description":"Category:British Indian Ocean Territory"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 13, 2015"]},{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Laamu Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaafu Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bernama"]},{"name":"w","description":["Baa Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fehendhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fulhadhoo","Fulhahdhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Haveeru Daily"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kudahuvadhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Ocean"]},{"name":"w","description":["Diego Garcia"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMalaysia says debris found in Maldives could be from MH370","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMalaysia to investigate suspected plane debris washed ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 10, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://raajje.mv/46025","title\u003dSuspected plane parts found in Laamu atoll","author\u003dMohamed Junaid","pub\u003dRaajjÃ© Online","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/banyan_tree_vabbinfaru/61538","title\u003dSuspected plane wing fragment found in Maldives","author\u003dMohamed Visham","pub\u003dHaveeru Daily","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/banyan_tree_vabbinfaru/61522","title\u003dMalaysia \u0027believes\u0027 debris in Maldives resort from MH370","author\u003dMohamed Visham","pub\u003dHaveeru Daily","date\u003dAugust 12, 2015"]},{"name":"Publi