{"title":"Malaysia: \u0027Most\u0027 debris found on Maldives islands not \u0027plane material\u0027","wikiTitle":"Malaysia:_\u0027Most\u0027_debris_found_on_Maldives_islands_not_\u0027plane_material\u0027","wid":2366251,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-26T16:16:03Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMore suspected plane debris washes ashore on Maldives island, date\u003dAugust 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2015/08/14/maldives-debris-not-mh370-malaysia, title\u003dReunion to end search for MH370 debris, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dSBS World News, date\u003dAugust 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thestar.com.my/News/Nation/2015/08/14/Liow-debris-Maldives-not-from-mh370/, title\u003dLiow: Debris found in Maldives not from MH370, author\u003dAdrian Chan, pub\u003dThe Star (Malaysia), date\u003dAugust 14, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysia"},{"id":"Maldives","description":"Maldives"},{"id":"Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"},{"id":"Kuala_Lumpur","description":"Kuala Lumpur"},{"id":"Beijing","description":"Beijing"},{"id":"China","description":"China"},{"id":"Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Malaysia Airlines"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[Maldives] According to the Malaysian transport ministry today, investigators sent to Maldives to examine suspected plane debris say \"most\" of the debris recovered from several Maldives islands are unrelated to Malaysia Airlines Flight 370 (MH370) and aren\u0027t part of an aircraft.","\"My team has witnessed the debris and most of them are negative. They are not related to MH370 and not even plane material,\" said Seri Liow, Malaysia\u0027s transport minister during a press conference today. He also stated investigators were still examining debris and if any of it was suspected of being from MH370, it would be taken for further analysis in Malaysia.","On Tuesday, the team of Malaysian investigators arrived in Maldives to take charge of the debris, which washed ashore on Vabbinfaru on May 31 and had been disposed of as trash. On Wednesday, the Malaysian government said they believed the debris could have been from MH370. \"We [Malaysia] have an understanding with the authorities there [Maldives] [...] we think the parts which were found about a month ago were parts of the aircraft,\" said Ab Aziz Kaprawi, the deputy transport minister for Malaysia.","The investigation in the Maldives began as a result of photos of suspected plane debris being uploaded to the social networking website Facebook. Some of the debris is reported to have washed ashore as early as May 31 and was found on a beach owned by the Banyan Tree Vabbinfaru resort, located on TEMPLATE[w, Kaafu Atoll]. In recent days, several other pieces of debris were recovered on at least three other islands, most of which was ruled out as belonging to a plane. In late July, a piece of a wing, a TEMPLATE[w, flaperon], reported to be from MH370 washed up on the French island of TEMPLATE[w, RÃ©union] in the southwest Indian Ocean.","MH370, while flying from Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia to Beijing, China, vanished without a trace on March 8, 2014. All 239 passengers and crew are believed to be dead. On the day the plane went missing, residents on the small Maldive island of TEMPLATE[w, Kudahuvadhoo] claimed to have seen a very \"low flying jumbo jet\" crash into the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Ocean]. Some also noted the colors appeared to resemble that of a Malaysia Airlines plane. \"Iâve never seen a jet flying so low over our island before. We\u0027ve seen seaplanes, but I\u0027m sure that this was not one of those. I could even make out the doors on the plane clearly\", one resident was quoted as saying to the newspaper Haveeru Daily. Some claim the plane appeared to be headed in the direction of TEMPLATE[w, Diego Garcia], but Malaysian authorities have discounted those claims.","\"No indication of Flight MH370 has been observed on any military radars in the country [Maldives]. Furthermore, the data of radars at Maldives airports have also been analysed and shows no indication of the said flight,\" said Malaysia\u0027s transport ministry at the time of the report.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370â","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines Flight 370â"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:Maldives","description":"Category:Maldives"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:China","description":"Category:China"},{"id":"Category:RÃ©union","description":"Category:RÃ©union"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:British_Indian_Ocean_Territory","description":"Category:British Indian Ocean Territory"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Maldives","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaafu Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["flaperon"]},{"name":"w","description":["RÃ©union"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kudahuvadhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Ocean"]},{"name":"w","description":["Diego Garcia"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMore suspected plane debris washes ashore on Maldives island","date\u003dAugust 13, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.sbs.com.au/news/article/2015/08/14/maldives-debris-not-mh370-malaysia","title\u003dReunion to end search for MH370 debris","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dSBS World News","date\u003dAugust 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thestar.com.my/News/Nation/2015/08/14/Liow-debris-Maldives-not-from-mh370/","title\u003dLiow: Debris found in Maldives not from MH370","author\u003dAdrian Chan","pub\u003dThe Star (Malaysia)","date\u003dAugust 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Haveeru Daily"]}
{"title":"\u0027Birther King\u0027 announces 2016 campaign for U.S. president","wikiTitle":"\u0027Birther_King\u0027_announces_2016_campaign_for_U.S._president","wid":2371484,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-10-11T10:53:23Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dU.S. presidential candidate Mark Everson challenges debate exclusion, date\u003dAugust 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMitt Romney wins the 2012 New Hampshire Republican primary, date\u003dJanuary 12, 2012]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dWikinews interviews Andy Martin, U.S. Republican Party presidential candidate, date\u003dAugust 8, 2011]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thegreenpapers.com/P12/R, title\u003dRepublican Convention 2012, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Green Papers, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015 (Accessed)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://fec.gov/press/press2013/presidential_form2nm.shtml, title\u003d2016 Presidential Form 2 Filers, author\u003d, pub\u003dFederal Election Commission, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015 (Last updated)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/882/201507169000246882/201507169000246882.pdf, title\u003dAndy Martin FEC Filing, author\u003d, pub\u003dFederal Election Commission, date\u003dJuly 16, 2015 (filed)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Politics/birther-king-andy-martin-seeks-gop-presidential-nomination/story?id\u003d12508838, title\u003d\u0027King of the Birthers\u0027 Launches Bid for Presidency, author\u003dDevin Dwyer, pub\u003dABC News (US), date\u003dDecember 30, 2010]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1999-12-21/news/9912210032_1_wmur-tv-andy-martin-palm-beach-lawyer, title\u003dFlorida Lawyer\u0027s Ad Says G.w. Bush Abused Drug, author\u003d, pub\u003dOrlando Sentinel, date\u003dDecember 21, 1999]"]],"links":[{"id":"Andy_Martin","description":"Andy Martin"},{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Republican Party"},{"id":"United_States_presidential_election,_2016","description":"2016 presidential nomination"},{"id":"US_White_House","description":"White House"},{"id":"Donald_Trump","description":"Donald Trump"},{"id":"Florida","description":"Florida"},{"id":"Jeb_Bush","description":"Jeb Bush"},{"id":"Barack_Obama","description":"Barack Obama"},{"id":"Democratic_Party_(United_States)","description":"Democratic Party"},{"id":"United_States_presidential_election,_2012","description":"2012"},{"id":"Wikinews","description":"Wikinews"},{"id":"George_W._Bush","description":"George W. Bush"},{"id":"cocaine","description":"cocaine"},{"id":"Greece","description":"Greece"},{"id":"Federal_Election_Commission","description":"Federal Election Commission"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 16, 2015] TEMPLATE[2016_US_Presidential_Election] Via press release on Friday, Andy Martin, a perennial candidate for political office and self-proclaimed \"Birther King\", announced he is seeking the U.S. Republican Party\u0027s 2016 presidential nomination, his fourth bid for the White House.  In his announcement and subsequent release, Martin expresses a desire to participate in TEMPLATE[w, Republican Party presidential debates, 2016, Republican presidential debates] and aligns himself with fellow Republican presidential candidate Donald Trump.  Additionally, he outlines six reasons for running, including degrading the candidacy of former Florida TEMPLATE[w, Governor of Florida, governor] Jeb Bush, who is also seeking the Republican nomination.","\"I have been a loyal Republican,\" says Martin in his announcement, \"loyal to the principles of our party but not necessarily loyal to some of its failed leaders.\"","Martin, best known for spreading multiple conspiracy theories concerning the TEMPLATE[w, Barack Obama citizenship conspiracy theories, birth] and TEMPLATE[w, Barack Obama religion conspiracy theories, religion] of U.S. TEMPLATE[w, President of the United States, President] Barack Obama, previously ran for the Democratic Party presidential nomination in TEMPLATE[w, United States presidential election, 1988, 1988], and unsuccessfully sought the backing of the Republican Party in TEMPLATE[w, United States presidential election, 2000, 2000] and 2012.  In 2012, he received a total of 19 votes in the TEMPLATE[w, New Hampshire Primary], the only primary ballot on which he appeared.","For 2016, Martin does not harbor high expectations of electoral success, though he hopes to receive an invitation to the debates.  In reference to the seventeen candidates invited to the two August 6 TEMPLATE[w, Fox News] debates, Martin casts himself as the \"eighteenth candidate,\" willing to participate in the second-tier debate.  Moreover, he declares himself as the \"second-most exciting\" candidate, reserving first place for Trump, whom Martin praises throughout his announcement.  Although he described Trump\u0027s previous foray into politics as a \"charade\" during a 2011 interview with Wikinews, Martin now sees himself as Trump\u0027s \"TEMPLATE[w, tag team]\" partner in attacking the Bush candidacy.","\"Trump has the raw media power to weaken Bush,\" says Martin, \"I have the negative information and hardball media tactics to make Bush a toxic candidate for the Republican base.\"","Martin adamantly opposes Bush because of the foreign policy of the candidate\u0027s brother, former President George W. Bush.  He also criticizes Bush for his alleged economic benefit from the collapse of TEMPLATE[w, Lehman Brothers], labeling Bush as a \"front man for a handful of corrupt TEMPLATE[w, Plutocracy, plutocrats] that have raped [the nation\u0027s] economy.\"  Martin has previously criticized the TEMPLATE[w, Bush family] during his 2000 campaign, when he ran television ads accusing then-presidential candidate George W. Bush of abusing cocaine and TEMPLATE[w, alcohol].","In addition to preventing Bush from gaining the Republican nomination, Martin intends to focus his campaign on protecting the prestige of the New Hampshire Primary and TEMPLATE[w, Iowa Caucus], defending the economic legacy of TEMPLATE[w, Founding Fathers of the United States, Founding Father] TEMPLATE[w, Alexander Hamilton], combating TEMPLATE[w, political correctness], emphasizing U.S. TEMPLATE[w, GreeceâUnited States relations, relations] with Greece, and fighting political corruption.","Martin filed paperwork with the Federal Election Commission last month to run for president in 2016 officially.  He joins 139 other Republican Party presidential candidates who have done likewise.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:Democratic_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Democratic Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Election_Commission_of_the_United_States","description":"Category:Federal Election Commission of the United States"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:Donald_Trump","description":"Category:Donald Trump"},{"id":"Category:George_W._Bush","description":"Category:George W. Bush"},{"id":"Category:Barack_Obama","description":"Category:Barack Obama"},{"id":"Category:2016_United_States_presidential_election","description":"Category:2016 United States presidential election"},{"id":"Category:Andy_Martin_(politician)","description":"Category:Andy Martin (politician)"},{"id":"Category:Jeb_Bush","description":"Category:Jeb Bush"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 16, 2015"]},{"name":"2016_US_Presidential_Election","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Republican Party presidential debates, 2016","Republican presidential debates"]},{"name":"w","description":["Governor of Florida","governor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Barack Obama citizenship conspiracy theories","birth"]},{"name":"w","description":["Barack Obama religion conspiracy theories","religion"]},{"name":"w","description":["President of the United States","President"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States presidential election, 1988","1988"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States presidential election, 2000","2000"]},{"name":"w","description":["New Hampshire Primary"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fox News"]},{"name":"w","description":["tag team"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lehman Brothers"]},{"name":"w","description":["Plutocracy","plutocrats"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bush family"]},{"name":"w","description":["alcohol"]},{"name":"w","description":["Iowa Caucus"]},{"name":"w","description":["Founding Fathers of the United States","Founding Father"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alexander Hamilton"]},{"name":"w","description":["political correctness"]},{"name":"w","description":["GreeceâUnited States relations","relations"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dU.S. presidential candidate Mark Everson challenges debate exclusion","date\u003dAugust 5, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMitt Romney wins the 2012 New Hampshire Republican primary","date\u003dJanuary 12, 2012"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dWikinews interviews Andy Martin, U.S. Republican Party presidential candidate","date\u003dAugust 8, 2011"]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thegreenpapers.com/P12/R","title\u003dRepublican Convention 2012","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Green Papers","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015 (Accessed)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://fec.gov/press/press2013/presidential_form2nm.shtml","title\u003d2016 Presidential Form 2 Filers","author\u003d","pub\u003dFederal Election Commission","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015 (Last updated)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://docquery.fec.gov/pdf/882/201507169000246882/201507169000246882.pdf","title\u003dAndy Martin FEC Filing","author\u003d","pub\u003dFederal Election Commission","date\u003dJuly 16, 2015 (filed)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Politics/birther-king-andy-martin-seeks-gop-presidential-nomination/story?id\u003d12508838","title\u003d\u0027King of the Birthers\u0027 Launches Bid for Presidency","author\u003dDevin Dwyer","pub\u003dABC News (US)","date\u003dDecember 30, 2010"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://articles.orlandosentinel.com/1999-12-21/news/9912210032_1_wmur-tv-andy-martin-palm-beach-lawyer","title\u003dFlorida Lawyer\u0027s Ad Says G.w. Bush Abused Drug","author\u003d","pub\u003dOrlando Sentinel","date\u003dDecember 21, 1999"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Wikinews"]}
{"title":"Two pieces of suspected plane debris from Maldives taken to Malaysia for analysis","wikiTitle":"Two_pieces_of_suspected_plane_debris_from_Maldives_taken_to_Malaysia_for_analysis","wid":2372151,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-26T16:08:41Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMalaysia: \u0027Most\u0027 debris found on Maldives islands not \u0027plane material\u0027, date\u003dAugust 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dMalaysia to investigate suspected plane debris washed ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands, date\u003dAugust 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ibtimes.com/flight-mh370-new-debris-found-maldives-be-examined-malaysia-links-missing-plane-2055760, title\u003dFlight MH370: New Debris Found On Maldives To Be Examined By Malaysia For Links To Missing Plane, author\u003dSuman Varandani, pub\u003dInternational Business Times, date\u003dAugust 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bernama.com/bernama/v8/ge/newsgeneral.php?id\u003d1162191, title\u003dTwo Small Objects Found In The Maldives Brought Home, author\u003d, pub\u003dBernama, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2015-08/16/c_134523531.htm, title\u003dMalaysia retrieves objects from Maldives to verify MH370 links, author\u003dEnglish.news.cn, pub\u003dXinhua, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/news/61609, title\u003dExperts to study new debris found in Maldives for MH370 links, Malaysia says, author\u003dMohamed Visham, pub\u003dHaveeru Daily, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.beritadaily.com/news/2015-08-16/19872/small-objects-found-in-maldives-brought-to-malaysia-says-liow, title\u003dSmall objects found in Maldives brought to Malaysia, says Liow, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dBerita Daily, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nationmultimedia.com/breakingnews/More-ocean-debris-to-be-tested-for-link-to-Malaysi-30266683.html?utm_source\u003dfeedburner\u0026utm_medium\u003dfeed\u0026utm_campaign\u003dFeed%3A+Nationmultimediacom-Breakingnews+%28NationMultimedia.com+-+Breakingnews%29, title\u003dMore ocean debris to be tested for link to Malaysian airliner, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Nation (Thailand), date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[Maldives] Two pieces of suspected plane debris found washed ashore  islands in the TEMPLATE[w, Maldives] have been taken back to TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia] for further analysis, Malaysia announced on Sunday. The pieces were found last Friday. Investigators are trying to determine if they\u0027re connected to TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia Airlines Flight 370] (MH370).","\"The first thing we have to do is to determine if it is actually of plane material\", said Liow Tiong Lai, Malaysia\u0027s transport minister, during a press conference on Sunday. \"The objects have been brought back and the investigation team will determine soon if they are debris of the MH370 plane [...] Our team here will confirm if they belong to a plane and if a confirmation is made, the pieces will be sent to the international investigation team to determine if they are from MH370,\" he added.","The surface of one of the pieces is flat while the other is constructed of \"honeycomb material.\" During the press conference, Liow described one the pieces as being \"very small, about the size of your hand\". TEMPLATE[image, Mohamed Wafir (via Facebook)] The debris was reportedly found while authorities were searching Maldives islands for other possible debris. Pieces of debris that resemble a honeycomb material were found on a beach owned by the Banyan Tree Vabbinfaru resort, located in the Maldives island chain TEMPLATE[w, Kaafu Atoll]. Those pieces are reported to have washed ashore onto the resort island around May 31. The investigation into the Maldives debris began as a result of photos of it being uploaded to the social networking website TEMPLATE[w, Facebook]. The photos show at least two pieces of debris, both appear to be flat, but at least one is made of a honeycomb material. Initially the debris was disposed of as trash and was reportedly sent to the garbage island TEMPLATE[w, Thilafushi], where trash is sorted, exported for recycling, or burned. Reports say at the time the debris was collected, no one suspected it could be from MH370.","Investigators examined several other pieces of debris that washed ashore onto other Maldives locations, the TEMPLATE[w, Baa Atoll] and the islands of TEMPLATE[w, Fehendhoo] and TEMPLATE[w, Fulhadhoo, Fulhahdhoo], and found none of it was related to an aircraft. \"My team has witnessed the debris and most of them are negative. They are not related to MH370 and not even plane material,\" said Liow on Friday. Around August 10, Abdulla Rasheed, a captain of a cargo boat which recently capsized in the waters off the Maldives, stated of debris then recently discovered, \"From the pictures of the debris found on most of the islands, I can almost certainly say that they are from the cargo we were carrying.\" In late July, a piece of a wing known as a TEMPLATE[w, flaperon] was found washed ashore on TEMPLATE[w, RÃ©union] Island. The Malaysian government stated it\u0027s from MH370, but according to TEMPLATE[w, China, Chinese] officials, the piece has yet to be confirmed to be from the aircraft.","MH370, while flying from TEMPLATE[w, Kuala Lumpur], Malaysia to TEMPLATE[w, Beijing], TEMPLATE[w, China], vanished without a trace on March 8, 2014. All 239 passengers and crew are believed to be dead. On the day the plane went missing, residents on the small Maldive island of TEMPLATE[w, Kudahuvadhoo] claimed to have seen a very \"low flying jumbo jet\" crash into the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Ocean]. Some also noted the colors appeared to resemble that of a TEMPLATE[w, Malaysia Airlines] plane. \"I\u0027ve never seen a jet flying so low over our island before. We\u0027ve seen seaplanes, but I\u0027m sure that this was not one of those. I could even make out the doors on the plane clearly\", one resident was quoted as saying to the newspaper Haveeru Daily. Some claim the plane appeared to he headed in the direction of TEMPLATE[w, Diego Garcia], but Malaysian authorities have discounted those claims.","\"Based on the monitoring up to date, no indication of Flight MH370 has been observed on any military radars in the country [Maldives]. Furthermore, the data of radars at Maldives airports have also been analysed and shows no indication of the said flight,\" said Malaysia\u0027s transport ministry at the time of the report.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines_Flight_370","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"},{"id":"Category:China","description":"Category:China"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia_Airlines","description":"Category:Malaysia Airlines"},{"id":"Category:British_Indian_Ocean_Territory","description":"Category:British Indian Ocean Territory"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Maldives","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Maldives"]},{"name":"w","description":["Malaysia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Malaysia Airlines Flight 370"]},{"name":"image","description":["Mohamed Wafir (via Facebook)"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kaafu Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Facebook"]},{"name":"w","description":["Thilafushi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Baa Atoll"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fehendhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fulhadhoo","Fulhahdhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["flaperon"]},{"name":"w","description":["RÃ©union"]},{"name":"w","description":["China","Chinese"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kuala Lumpur"]},{"name":"w","description":["Beijing"]},{"name":"w","description":["China"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kudahuvadhoo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Ocean"]},{"name":"w","description":["Malaysia Airlines"]},{"name":"w","description":["Diego Garcia"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMalaysia: \u0027Most\u0027 debris found on Maldives islands not \u0027plane material\u0027","date\u003dAugust 14, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dMalaysia to investigate suspected plane debris washed ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 10, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dSuspected plane debris washes ashore on several Maldives islands","date\u003dAugust 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ibtimes.com/flight-mh370-new-debris-found-maldives-be-examined-malaysia-links-missing-plane-2055760","title\u003dFlight MH370: New Debris Found On Maldives To Be Examined By Malaysia For Links To Missing Plane","author\u003dSuman Varandani","pub\u003dInternational Business Times","date\u003dAugust 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bernama.com/bernama/v8/ge/newsgeneral.php?id\u003d1162191","title\u003dTwo Small Objects Found In The Maldives Brought Home","author\u003d","pub\u003dBernama","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2015-08/16/c_134523531.htm","title\u003dMalaysia retrieves objects from Maldives to verify MH370 links","author\u003dEnglish.news.cn","pub\u003dXinhua","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.haveeru.com.mv/news/61609","title\u003dExperts to study new debris found in Maldives for MH370 links, Malaysia says","author\u003dMohamed Visham","pub\u003dHaveeru Daily","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.beritadaily.com/news/2015-08-16/19872/small-objects-found-in-maldives-brought-to-malaysia-says-liow","title\u003dSmall objects found in Maldives brought to Malaysia, says Liow","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dBerita Daily","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nationmultimedia.com/breakingnews/More-ocean-debris-to-be-tested-for-link-to-Malaysi-30266683.html?utm_source\u003dfeedburner\u0026utm_medium\u003dfeed\u0026utm_campaign\u003dFeed%3A+Nationmultimediacom-Breakingnews+%28NationMultimedia.com+-+Breakingnews%29","title\u003dMore ocean debris to be tested for link to Malaysian airliner","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Nation (Thailand)","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Haveeru Daily"]}
{"title":"Woman fined in Spain under new \u0027Gag Law\u0027","wikiTitle":"Woman_fined_in_Spain_under_new_\u0027Gag_Law\u0027","wid":2373669,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-25T17:53:33Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/16/spanish-woman-fined-gagging-law-photographing-police, title\u003dSpanish woman fined for posting picture of police parked in disabled bay, author\u003dStephen Burgen, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnet.com/news/woman-fined-for-facebook-pic-of-police-car-in-disabled-spot/, title\u003dWoman fined for Facebook pic of police car in disabled spot, author\u003dChris Matyszczyk, pub\u003dCNET, date\u003dAugust 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://petreraldia.com/reportajes/primera-aplicacion-de-la-ley-mordaza-en-petrer-y-primer-escandalo.html, title\u003dPrimera aplicaciÃ³n de la âLey Mordazaâ en Petrer y primera gran polÃ©mica, author\u003d, pub\u003dpetreraldia.com, date\u003dAugust 11, 2015, lang\u003des]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://euobserver.com/beyond-brussels/129459, title\u003dSpain\u0027s \u0027gag\u0027 law comes into force, author\u003dHelena Spongenberg, pub\u003dEUobserver, date\u003dJuly 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/24/spain-restricting-protest-fines-harassment-excessive-force, title\u003dSpain restricting people\u0027s right to protest, Amnesty report finds, author\u003dAshifa Kassam, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dApril 24, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Spain","description":"Spain"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] TEMPLATE[Image, [[Facebook]]] A woman in Spain has been fined TEMPLATE[w, Euro, â¬]800 after posting a photograph to her Facebook account of a police vehicle parked in space reserved for TEMPLATE[w, Disabled parking permit, disabled/handicapped] drivers.  She was located and fined within two days of posting the photograph.  The incident has now gained international attention.","The woman, who has not been named, saw the police vehicle parked in a reserved spot in TEMPLATE[w, Petrer] and snapped a photo.  She posted the photo with the caption: TEMPLATE[translated_quote, es, Spanish Language, Aparcas donde te sale de los cojones y encima no te multan..., Park where you bloody well please and you won\u0027t even be fined.]","Fernando Portillo, a local police spokesperson, told local media the vehicle was parked there because police were responding to an emergency.  After the story was reported on a local news website, it began to be reported internationally.","On July 1, the \"TEMPLATE[w, Anti-austerity movement in Spain, anchor\u003dCitizens\u0027 Security law, Citizens\u0027 Security law]\" went into effect.  The law was written in response to violent protests.  Even before its enactment it saw widespread criticism.  It was dubbed the TEMPLATE[translated_quote, es, Spanish language, ley mordaza, gag law] or the \"gagging law\".  The law prohibits TEMPLATE[translated_quote, es, Spanish language, El uso no autorizado de imÃ¡genes o datos personales o profesionales de autoridades o miembros de las Fuerzas y Cuerpos de Seguridad que pueda poner en peligro la seguridad personal o familiar de los agentes, de las instalaciones protegidas o en riesgo el Ã©xito de una operaciÃ³n, the unauthorized use of images of police officers that might jeopardize their or their family\u0027s safety or that of protected facilities or police operations].","Judge Joaquim Bosch, TEMPLATE[w, Judges for Democracy] spokesperson, said: \"It is not a law for citizens\u0027 security, but a law for the government to avoid citizensâ protests. All opinion polls indicate that the Spanish society is not at all preoccupied by security but by the economic situation and political corruption.\"","TEMPLATE[w, Amnesty International] condemned the law in a report: \"With threats of fines or threats of being beaten, the government is trying to stigmatize and criminalize people who are just practicing their rights.\" Virginia Ãlvarez, who wrote the report, noted, \"instead of listening to their demands, instead of starting a dialogue, authorities are doing everything they can to impede people from protesting\".","The part of the law which prohibits \"the unauthorized use of images of police officers that might jeopardize their or their family\u0027s safety\" is cited as the reason for the fine, however, police spokesperson Fernando Portillo said it was up to police officers involved and under the new law they could do this.  \"We would have preferred a different solution but they have the legal right to impose the fine,â Portillo said, but the public posting of the photo impugned the officers\u0027 sense of honor.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Spain","description":"Category:Spain"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Facebook","description":"Category:Facebook"},{"id":"Category:Free_speech","description":"Category:Free speech"},{"id":"Category:Protests","description":"Category:Protests"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"Image","description":["[[Facebook]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Euro","â¬"]},{"name":"w","description":["Disabled parking permit","disabled/handicapped"]},{"name":"w","description":["Petrer"]},{"name":"translated_quote","description":["es","Spanish Language","Aparcas donde te sale de los cojones y encima no te multan...","Park where you bloody well please and you won\u0027t even be fined."]},{"name":"w","description":["Anti-austerity movement in Spain","anchor\u003dCitizens\u0027 Security law","Citizens\u0027 Security law"]},{"name":"translated_quote","description":["es","Spanish language","ley mordaza","gag law"]},{"name":"translated_quote","description":["es","Spanish language","El uso no autorizado de imÃ¡genes o datos personales o profesionales de autoridades o miembros de las Fuerzas y Cuerpos de Seguridad que pueda poner en peligro la seguridad personal o familiar de los agentes, de las instalaciones protegidas o en riesgo el Ã©xito de una operaciÃ³n","the unauthorized use of images of police officers that might jeopardize their or their family\u0027s safety or that of protected facilities or police operations"]},{"name":"w","description":["Judges for Democracy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Amnesty International"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/16/spanish-woman-fined-gagging-law-photographing-police","title\u003dSpanish woman fined for posting picture of police parked in disabled bay","author\u003dStephen Burgen","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnet.com/news/woman-fined-for-facebook-pic-of-police-car-in-disabled-spot/","title\u003dWoman fined for Facebook pic of police car in disabled spot","author\u003dChris Matyszczyk","pub\u003dCNET","date\u003dAugust 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://petreraldia.com/reportajes/primera-aplicacion-de-la-ley-mordaza-en-petrer-y-primer-escandalo.html","title\u003dPrimera aplicaciÃ³n de la âLey Mordazaâ en Petrer y primera gran polÃ©mica","author\u003d","pub\u003dpetreraldia.com","date\u003dAugust 11, 2015","lang\u003des"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://euobserver.com/beyond-brussels/129459","title\u003dSpain\u0027s \u0027gag\u0027 law comes into force","author\u003dHelena Spongenberg","pub\u003dEUobserver","date\u003dJuly 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2014/apr/24/spain-restricting-protest-fines-harassment-excessive-force","title\u003dSpain restricting people\u0027s right to protest, Amnesty report finds","author\u003dAshifa Kassam","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dApril 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["anchor","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","lang","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Wikinews interviews Mark Everson, U.S. Republican Party presidential candidate","wikiTitle":"Wikinews_interviews_Mark_Everson,_U.S._Republican_Party_presidential_candidate","wid":2378969,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-27T15:23:18Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, William S. Saturn] Why run for president? Why not run for a lower office that you might be more likely to win and effect change?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] What qualifications do you have that will assist you in executing the duties of president?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] How much campaigning have you done so far?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] What are your thoughts on your fellow Republican presidential candidates?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Would you ever consider running as a third party or independent candidate?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Wikinews covered the complaint you filed with the FEC against Fox News in your attempt to be included in the August 6 Debate. In our report, Election Law expert TEMPLATE[w, Richard Winger] suggested you file a lawsuit rather than an FEC complaint. Do you have an update on your FEC complaint and might you consider filing a lawsuit if you are excluded from future debates?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Your exclusion from National presidential polls appears to be the biggest detriment to your campaign and effort to appear in debates. Is there anything your campaign can do to include your name in polls to qualify for future debates?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Are you surprised by your exclusion from presidential polls and events or did you expect this when you announced?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS]  What are your thoughts on the job Barack Obama has done as president? Specifically, what would you have done differently?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] If elected, what would constitute a successful presidency for you?"],["TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS]  Which individuals would you like to see in an Everson administration?"],["TEMPLATE[wikinews, U.S. presidential candidate Mark Everson challenges debate exclusion, date\u003dAugust 5, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.gop.com/presidential-straw-poll/, title\u003d2016 Presidential Straw Poll, pub\u003dU.S. Republican Party, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015 (accessed)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://time.com/3986183/republican-debate-mark-everson/, title\u003dMeet the Republican Candidate Who Wonât Be at the Debates, author\u003dAditya Agrawal, pub\u003dTime (magazine), date\u003dAugust 5, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"U.S.","description":"U.S."},{"id":"Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"U.S. Republican Party"},{"id":"United_States_presidential_election,_2016","description":"2016 presidential nomination"},{"id":"Indiana","description":"Indiana"},{"id":"Iowa","description":"Iowa"},{"id":"New_Hampshire","description":"New Hampshire"},{"id":"Barack_Obama","description":"Barack Obama"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Interview","Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 20, 2015] TEMPLATE[2016_US_Presidential_Election] TEMPLATE[image, U.S. Government] Former U.S. TEMPLATE[w, Commissioner of Internal Revenue] TEMPLATE[w, Mark Everson]  took some time to talk with Wikinews about his campaign for the U.S. Republican Party\u0027s 2016 presidential nomination.","Everson served as Commissioner of Internal Revenue, the administrative head of the TEMPLATE[w, Internal Revenue Service] (IRS) from 2003 to 2007, during the TEMPLATE[w, George W. Bush] administration. After his departure, he briefly served as CEO of the TEMPLATE[w, American Red Cross], worked in the cabinet of Indiana TEMPLATE[w, Governor of Indiana, governor] TEMPLATE[w, Mitch Daniels], and worked for the tax consulting firm TEMPLATE[w, alliantgroup]. He announced his candidacy this past March with a sixteen-page open letter in which he outlined the six pillars of his campaign: amnesty for TEMPLATE[w, Illegal immigration in the United States, illegal immigrants], reinstatement of the TEMPLATE[w, military draft], a promise to serve only a single presidential term, and calls for tax reform, deficit reduction, and corporate responsibility.","He was excluded from the August 6 TEMPLATE[w, Fox News] TEMPLATE[w, Republican Party presidential debates, 2016, Republican presidential debate] and has been excluded from most TEMPLATE[w, Nationwide opinion polling for the Republican Party 2016 presidential primaries, presidential polls].  However, he is listed on the Republican Party\u0027s website as one of 18 candidates and filed a TEMPLATE[w, Federal Election Commission] (FEC) complaint against Fox News for his exclusion from the August 6 debate.","With Wikinews reporter William S. Saturnâ, Everson discusses his 2016 campaign, the media blackout of his campaign, and his views on the presidency and the possible Everson administration.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Mark Everson] The electorate is very unsettled. Americans are fed up with politics as usual, so there is a clear path for a nontraditional candidate. I have extensive private sector experience and know the government inside out, but do not carry the political baggage of ties to special interest groups. I have lived in nine states. As a result, I have seen and know America well, but do not have the deep ties to a particular state or community that would traditionally be associated with seeking a different office.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] While I have not held elective office, my public service credentials meet or exceed those of many of the candidates in the race. My federal executive branch experience (at TEMPLATE[w, United States Information Agency, USIA], TEMPLATE[w, United States Department of Justice, DOJ], TEMPLATE[w, Office of Management and Budget, OMB], and the TEMPLATE[w, United States Department of Treasury, Treasury]) is greater than that of any candidate in the GOP contest. I managed the nation\u0027s immigration system under President TEMPLATE[w, Ronald Reagan, Reagan], and in the TEMPLATE[w, Presidency of George W. Bush, administration of President George W. Bush] was instrumental in the creation of the TEMPLATE[w, United States Department of Homeland Security, Department of Homeland Security] and directed the nation\u0027s tax system as Commissioner of Internal Revenue. Immigration, homeland security and taxes are issues of critical importance to the country and central to the 2016 election.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] I have campaigned in 26 counties across Iowa and also made campaign stops in New Hampshire.  I have been interviewed on radio shows across the country.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] I think it is a strong field and that the vigorous policy debate underway in the party is good for the country.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] I am running as a Republican and am not contemplating a third party or independent candidacy.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] We have received notice that the FEC has filed the complaint with Fox News, but nothing else. I have written to CNN and the Reagan Foundation requesting inclusion in their September debate. At this time I do not expect to file a lawsuit on this matter.","::TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] What is your response to Mr. Winger, who said you had a good case and may have had an opportunity to gain access to the debate if you filed a lawsuit instead of an FEC complaint?",":::TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] I did look into the possible filing of a law suit and was informed by a prominent election law expert that the chances were quite slim that the courts would intervene in a matter properly before the FEC.","::TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Are you saying that you do not expect to litigate the Fox News matter or do you not expect to file a lawsuit to gain access to future debates? If so, why?",":::TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] I expect to pursue the FOX matter with the FEC. I will assess future legal actions as events unfold.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] We have written the polling companies requesting that I be included in the polls.","::TEMPLATE[WNIQ, WSS] Have the polling companies responded to your requests?  If so, what have they said?",":::TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] We have not yet heard from the polling companies.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] At this still early stage of the race, I am surprised that participation has been limited to established politicians and individuals already enjoying significant name recognition. The process should be about surfacing issues of importance to the country and who can best tackle the challenges at hand.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] The president has failed to unite the nation, the government is not operating well in any number of areas, and the world is certainly a more dangerous place than when he took office. My main objection to his term in office extends beyond his policy choices to his unprecedented expansion of executive power. I have a track record of implementing the law as written, not as I might wish it to be. The powers of the presidency are significant, but limited under our constitution.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] The specifics include a rewrite of the tax code to take 150 million Americans off the income tax rolls; holding Wall Street and the big banks accountable to following the law, and taking regulatory actions to increase lending; institution of a program of national service; real, balanced reforms to our entitlement programs to assure their continued viability; rewriting our immigration laws to control our borders and reinforce our tradition of assimilation; and taking reelection politics out of Oval Office decision-making by serving only a single term. More broadly, I would consider an Everson presidency successful if we restore faith in our government at home and abroad, and Americans once again put national interests ahead of self-interest.",":TEMPLATE[WNIR, Everson] I know many qualified individuals who would do an excellent job serving the nation, but believe it serves no purpose to disclose particular names at this early date.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[interview]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Election_Commission_of_the_United_States","description":"Category:Federal Election Commission of the United States"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:2016_United_States_presidential_election","description":"Category:2016 United States presidential election"},{"id":"Category:Barack_Obama","description":"Category:Barack Obama"},{"id":"Category:George_W._Bush","description":"Category:George W. Bush"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 20, 2015"]},{"name":"2016_US_Presidential_Election","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["U.S. Government"]},{"name":"w","description":["Commissioner of Internal Revenue"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mark Everson"]},{"name":"w","description":["Internal Revenue Service"]},{"name":"w","description":["George W. Bush"]},{"name":"w","description":["American Red Cross"]},{"name":"w","description":["Governor of Indiana","governor"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mitch Daniels"]},{"name":"w","description":["alliantgroup"]},{"name":"w","description":["Illegal immigration in the United States","illegal immigrants"]},{"name":"w","description":["military draft"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fox News"]},{"name":"w","description":["Republican Party presidential debates, 2016","Republican presidential debate"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nationwide opinion polling for the Republican Party 2016 presidential primaries","presidential polls"]},{"name":"w","description":["Federal Election Commission"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["William S. Saturn"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Mark Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Information Agency","USIA"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Department of Justice","DOJ"]},{"name":"w","description":["Office of Management and Budget","OMB"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Department of Treasury","Treasury"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ronald Reagan","Reagan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Presidency of George W. Bush","administration of President George W. Bush"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Department of Homeland Security","Department of Homeland Security"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"w","description":["Richard Winger"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["WSS"]},{"name":"WNIR","description":["Everson"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["U.S. presidential candidate Mark Everson challenges debate exclusion","date\u003dAugust 5, 2015"]},{"name":"interview","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.gop.com/presidential-straw-pol