{"title":"Protesters in England call for change to cricket governance","wikiTitle":"Protesters_in_England_call_for_change_to_cricket_governance","wid":2383692,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-27T15:23:22Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.espncricinfo.com/ci/content/story/911337.html, title\u003dGiles Clarke is target of The Oval silent protest, author\u003dGeorge Dobell, pub\u003dESPN Cricinfo, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/cricket/article-3204554/England-vs-Australia-fifth-Ashes-Test-targeted-protesters-hold-three-minute-silence-bid-change-cricket.html, title\u003dEngland vs Australia fifth Ashes Test targeted as protesters hold three-minute silence outside The Oval, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Daily Mail, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/sport/cricket/international/theashes/11802350/Protest-planned-for-final-Ashes-Test-over-state-of-modern-cricket.html, title\u003dProtest planned for final Ashes Test over state of modern cricket, author\u003dScyld Berry, pub\u003dThe Telegraph, date\u003dAugust 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cricketcountry.com/articles/death-of-a-gentleman-mind-numbing-scary-317394, title\u003dDeath of a Gentleman: Numbing, scaryâ¦, author\u003dAbhishek Mukherjee, pub\u003dCricket Country, date\u003dAugust 14, 2015]"],["changecricket.com","Death of a Gentleman website"]],"links":[{"id":"India","description":"India"},{"id":"England","description":"England"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"http://www.changecricket.com/","description":"changecricket.com"},{"id":"http://deathofagentlemanfilm.com/","description":"Death of a Gentleman website"}],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 20, 2015] TEMPLATE[sports] A protest was held ahead of the start of the fifth TEMPLATE[W, The Ashes, Ashes] cricket TEMPLATE[w, test cricket, test] today, seeking a higher standard of cricket administration. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [http://www.geograph.org.uk/profile/34311 Richard Rogerson]] Around 100 protesters, which included writer TEMPLATE[W, Gideon Haigh], TEMPLATE[w, Wisden Cricketers\u0027 Almanack, Wisden] editor TEMPLATE[w, Lawrence Booth (cricket writer), Lawrence Booth], and TEMPLATE[W, Damian Collins], TEMPLATE[w, UK Parliament, MP] for TEMPLATE[w, Folkestone and Hythe], gathered outside the TEMPLATE[w, The Oval, Oval] cricket ground to observe three minutes of silence, a minute for each of the \"Big Three\" nations \u0026mdash; India, England, and Australia. Organisers claim these nations of controlling cricket\u0027s governance to benefit themselves.","Sam Collins and TEMPLATE[W, Jarrod Kimber], a pair of journalists and film-makers, organised the protest.","\"Now the Ashes have been decided, we feel the time is right to protest at the powerlessness of all other countries in the cricket world,\" Collins told TEMPLATE[w, The Telegraph]. \"Nobody has any power except for TEMPLATE[W, N. Srinivasan, Narayan Srinivasan], of India, TEMPLATE[W, Giles Clarke], of England, and Wally Edwards, of Australia.\"","Collins and Kimber recently released the film TEMPLATE[w, Death of a Gentleman]. The documentary was created by the pair to examine what the future holds for test match cricket whilst examining claims of corrupt administrators. The film-makers have launched changecricket.com, calling on cricket fans to advocate for better governance of the sport. \"We ask fans of all nations to stand with us and show their dissatisfaction about the way their game is being run,\" said Collins.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"category:Sports","description":"category:Sports"},{"id":"category:cricket","description":"category:cricket"},{"id":"category:England","description":"category:England"},{"id":"categor