{"title":"Cilla Black funeral held in Liverpool","wikiTitle":"Cilla_Black_funeral_held_in_Liverpool","wid":2384888,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-28T13:25:44Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33991635, title\u003dCilla Black funeral: Fans and stars say farewell in Liverpool, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2015/aug/20/cilla-black-funeral-fans-stars-farewell-liverpool, title\u003dCilla Black funeral: fans and Cliff Richard mourn a \u0027fabulous pop star\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/cilla-black-funeral-live-fans-line-streets--to-pay-final-respects-to-late-entertainer-10463527.html, title\u003dCilla Black funeral: Paul O\u0027Grady and Sir Cliff Richard lead tributes at Liverpool service, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[England] TEMPLATE[image, Joost Evers / (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, Anefo] Stars from the world of showbusiness joined fans and mourners yesterday at the funeral of the popular entertainer TEMPLATE[w, Cilla Black]. Her coffin was transported in a cortege in TEMPLATE[w, Liverpool] where she grew up, with hundreds of people paying their respects. Some were holding memorabilia related to Black\u0027s 50-year long career in entertainment, which included singing and presenting television programmes such as TEMPLATE[w, Blind Date].","TEMPLATE[w, Tom Williams (Auxiliary Bishop of Liverpool), Tom Williams], auxiliary bishop of Liverpool, conducted the TEMPLATE[w, Roman Catholicism, Roman Catholic] mass in St Mary\u0027s Roman Catholic Church in Liverpool\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Woolton] area. This is the same church that Black got married in 1969 to TEMPLATE[w, Bobby Willis], who died in 1999 after 30 years of marriage. TEMPLATE[wikt, eulogy, Eulogies] were delivered by TEMPLATE[w, Cliff Richard] and TEMPLATE[w, Paul O\u0027Grady] together with poems read by two of Black\u0027s sons. Further tributes were paid by TEMPLATE[w, Tom Jones], who flew in specially for the funeral.","After the service, Black was to be interred in a private ceremony, next to the graves of her parents at the Allerton cemetery. She died early this month, aged 72, after she fell at her home in Spain and suffered a stroke.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Liverpool","description":"Category:Liverpool"},{"id":"Category:Music","description":"Category:Music"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 21, 2015"]},{"name":"England","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Joost Evers / (TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["Anefo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cilla Black"]},{"name":"w","description":["Liverpool"]},{"name":"w","description":["Blind Date"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tom Williams (Auxiliary Bishop of Liverpool)","Tom Williams"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roman Catholicism","Roman Catholic"]},{"name":"w","description":["Woolton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bobby Willis"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["eulogy","Eulogies"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cliff Richard"]},{"name":"w","description":["Paul O\u0027Grady"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tom Jones"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/entertainment-arts-33991635","title\u003dCilla Black funeral: Fans and stars say farewell in Liverpool","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/tv-and-radio/2015/aug/20/cilla-black-funeral-fans-stars-farewell-liverpool","title\u003dCilla Black funeral: fans and Cliff Richard mourn a \u0027fabulous pop star\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/cilla-black-funeral-live-fans-line-streets--to-pay-final-respects-to-late-entertainer-10463527.html","title\u003dCilla Black funeral: Paul O\u0027Grady and Sir Cliff Richard lead tributes at Liverpool service","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"North Korea puts military in \u0027quasi-state of war\u0027","wikiTitle":"North_Korea_puts_military_in_\u0027quasi-state_of_war\u0027","wid":2385032,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-09T20:55:39Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/northkorea/2015/08/21/95/0401000000AEN20150821001551320F.html, title\u003dN. Korean leader orders military to have full combat readiness, author\u003d, pub\u003dYonhap, date\u003dAugust 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.kcna.kp/kcna.user.article.retrieveNewsViewInfoList.kcmsf;jsessionid\u003d2A83573FDAC1945F8ED8A4931D74BCB1, title\u003dKim Jong Un Guides Emergency Enlarged Meeting of WPK Central Military Commission, author\u003d, pub\u003dKorean Central News Agency, date\u003dAugust 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.kcna.kp/kcna.user.article.retrieveNewsViewInfoList.kcmsf;jsessionid\u003d2A83573FDAC1945F8ED8A4931D74BCB1, title\u003dKPA Supreme Command Warns S. Korean Military to Act with Discretion, author\u003d, pub\u003dKorean Central News Agency, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/20/south-korea-north-korea-border-attack-loudspeaker-retaliation, title\u003dSouth Korea fires at North Korea in retaliation for loudspeaker attack, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[North_Korea] According to TEMPLATE[w, Yonhap] news agency, quoting TEMPLATE[w, North Korea]\u0027s main news agency TEMPLATE[w, Korean Central News Agency] (KCNA), the country\u0027s military has been placed on high alert and has been told to prepare a \"quasi-state of war\". The report comes after North and TEMPLATE[w, South Korea] exchanged artillery fire yesterday.","\"War maniacs of the South Korean puppet military made another grave provocation to the DPRK in the central western sector of the front on Thursday afternoon. They perpetrated such reckless action as firing 36 shells at KPA civil police posts under the absurd pretext that the KPA fired one shell at the south side. Six shells of them hit the area near KPA civil police posts 542 and 543 and other 15 shells fell near KPA civil police posts 250 and 251,\" said KCNA. \"Foolhardy provocation deserves harsh punishment,\" it added; and, later, \"TEMPLATE[w, Kim Jong-un] issued an order of the supreme commander of the Korean Peopleâs Army [KPA] that the front-line large combined units of the KPA should enter a wartime state to be fully battle ready to launch surprise operations.\"","Yesterday, North Korea fired artillery rounds aimed at a loudspeaker in South Korea that broadcasts anti-TEMPLATE[w, Pyongyang] propaganda into the North. \"Commanders of the Korean People\u0027s Army were hastily dispatched to the front-line troops to command military operations to destroy psychological warfare tools if the enemy does not stop the propaganda broadcast within 48 hours and prepare against the enemy\u0027s possible counteractions,\" added KCNA.","No injuries or deaths were reported in the attacks from either side, but South Korea evacuated about 80 people in the town of TEMPLATE[w, Yeoncheon County, Yeoncheon] after at least one shell landed near the area. The South retaliated by firing dozens of rounds of artillery into the north.","South Korea had recently started to broadcast propaganda from loudspeakers after an 11-year lull. The broadcasts began on August 10 and South Korea says the broadcasts will continue. After the exchange of fire, North Korea stated it would attack any loudspeakers broadcasting propaganda and would respond, militarily, within 48 hours if the broadcasts do not stop.","Both countries have put their militaries on high levels of alert.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_Korea","description":"Category:North Korea"},{"id":"Category:Pyongyang","description":"Category:Pyongyang"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Kim_Jong-un","description":"Category:Kim Jong-un"},{"id":"Category:South_Korea","description":"Category:South Korea"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Korean_Peninsula","description":"Category:Korean Peninsula"},{"id":"Category:Korean_Central_News_Agency","description":"Category:Korean Central News Agency"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 21, 2015"]},{"name":"North_Korea","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Yonhap"]},{"name":"w","description":["North Korea"]},{"name":"w","description":["Korean Central News Agency"]},{"name":"w","description":["South Korea"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kim Jong-un"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pyongyang"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yeoncheon County","Yeoncheon"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/northkorea/2015/08/21/95/0401000000AEN20150821001551320F.html","title\u003dN. Korean leader orders military to have full combat readiness","author\u003d","pub\u003dYonhap","date\u003dAugust 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.kcna.kp/kcna.user.article.retrieveNewsViewInfoList.kcmsf;jsessionid\u003d2A83573FDAC1945F8ED8A4931D74BCB1","title\u003dKim Jong Un Guides Emergency Enlarged Meeting of WPK Central Military Commission","author\u003d","pub\u003dKorean Central News Agency","date\u003dAugust 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.kcna.kp/kcna.user.article.retrieveNewsViewInfoList.kcmsf;jsessionid\u003d2A83573FDAC1945F8ED8A4931D74BCB1","title\u003dKPA Supreme Command Warns S. Korean Military to Act with Discretion","author\u003d","pub\u003dKorean Central News Agency","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/20/south-korea-north-korea-border-attack-loudspeaker-retaliation","title\u003dSouth Korea fires at North Korea in retaliation for loudspeaker attack","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"\u0027Terror\u0027 shooting wounds three on international train in Belgium","wikiTitle":"\u0027Terror\u0027_shooting_wounds_three_on_international_train_in_Belgium","wid":2386647,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-24T20:22:42Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/ct-france-high-speed-train-shooting-20150821-story.html, title\u003d2 Marines subdue gunman who wounded 3 on high-speed train to Paris, author\u003d, pub\u003dChicago Tribune, date\u003dAugust 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/france/11817490/Gunman-injures-three-after-firing-Kalashnikov-on-train-in-France-latest.html, title\u003dGunman injures three after firing Kalashnikov on Amsterdam-Paris train: latest, author\u003d Barney Henderson, Andrew Marszal, James Rothwell, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph, date\u003dAugust 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/21/amsterdam-paris-train-gunman-france, title\u003dGunman opens fire on Amsterdam-Paris train, wounding two people, author\u003dAngelique Chrisafis, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34023361, title\u003dFrance train shooting: Americans overpower gunman, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 21, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Belgium","description":"Belgium"},{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"Morocco","description":"Moroccan"},{"id":"Amsterdam","description":"Amsterdam"},{"id":"Paris","description":"Paris"},{"id":"Francois_Hollande","description":"Francois Hollande"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[correction, label\u003d, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015, explanation\u003dThis article accurately records what was at the time widely reported by stating that two US Marines tackled the gunman. He was tackled by several passengers and train staff. These included a (TEMPLATE) Airman and a US (TEMPLATE) Specialist.] TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:T Houdijk, User:T Houdijk]]] TEMPLATE[France] A gunman yesterday wounded three people on an international train in Belgium, near the French border. Belgian Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Charles Michel] called the shooting a \"terrorist attack\" and French counterterrorism police are investigating.","Two United States TEMPLATE[w, US Marines, Marines] on the train heard a weapon being loaded in a bathroom. When the man exited the toilet, the unarmed Marines tackled him. One Marine was injured. French actor TEMPLATE[w, Jean-Hugues Anglade] was injured slightly by broken glass.","A man, believed to be a 26-year-old Moroccan, was arrested at the station in TEMPLATE[w, Arras], France. Some passengers reportedly leapt from the train as it passed through TEMPLATE[w, Henin-Beaumont]. The high-speed TEMPLATE[w, Thalys] service was headed from Amsterdam to Paris.","French Interior Minister TEMPLATE[w, Bernard Cazeneuve] travelled to Arras after the incident. He has met with passengers including Anglade. He said the two Marines are \"particularly courageous and showed great bravery in very difficult circumstances [...] Without their composure we could have been confronted with a terrible incident.\" French Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Manuel Valls] also expressed gratitude to the Marines.","The suspect is reported to have been carrying knives, a TEMPLATE[w, kalashnikov] rifle, and a handgun. Press reports suggest intelligence agencies were aware of him. Rail operator TEMPLATE[w, SNCF] say over 550 passengers were on board. Reports indicate the shooting was towards the rear.","Local prosecutors said counterterror resources were involved \"in view of the weaponry used, the way it happened and the context\". French President Francois Hollande promised \"Everything is being done to shed light on this tragedy.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive] TEMPLATE[DEFAULTSORT:Terror\u0027_shooting_wounds_three_on_international_train_in_Belgium]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Belgium","description":"Category:Belgium"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Morocco","description":"Category:Morocco"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Rail_transport","description":"Category:Rail transport"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:FranÃ§ois_Hollande","description":"Category:FranÃ§ois Hollande"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:SNCF","description":"Category:SNCF"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 22, 2015"]},{"name":"correction","description":["label\u003d","date\u003dAugust 24, 2015","explanation\u003dThis article accurately records what was at the time widely reported by stating that two US Marines tackled the gunman. He was tackled by several passengers and train staff. These included a (TEMPLATE) Airman and a US (TEMPLATE) Specialist."]},{"name":"w","description":["US Air Force"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Guard"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:T Houdijk","User:T Houdijk]]"]},{"name":"France","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Charles Michel"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Marines","Marines"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jean-Hugues Anglade"]},{"name":"w","description":["Arras"]},{"name":"w","description":["Henin-Beaumont"]},{"name":"w","description":["Thalys"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bernard Cazeneuve"]},{"name":"w","description":["Manuel Valls"]},{"name":"w","description":["kalashnikov"]},{"name":"w","description":["SNCF"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.chicagotribune.com/news/nationworld/ct-france-high-speed-train-shooting-20150821-story.html","title\u003d2 Marines subdue gunman who wounded 3 on high-speed train to Paris","author\u003d","pub\u003dChicago Tribune","date\u003dAugust 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/worldnews/europe/france/11817490/Gunman-injures-three-after-firing-Kalashnikov-on-train-in-France-latest.html","title\u003dGunman injures three after firing Kalashnikov on Amsterdam-Paris train: latest","author\u003d Barney Henderson, Andrew Marszal, James Rothwell","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph","date\u003dAugust 22, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/21/amsterdam-paris-train-gunman-france","title\u003dGunman opens fire on Amsterdam-Paris train, wounding two people","author\u003dAngelique Chrisafis","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34023361","title\u003dFrance train shooting: Americans overpower gunman","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]},{"name":"DEFAULTSORT:Terror\u0027_shooting_wounds_three_on_international_train_in_Belgium","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["label","date","explanation","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Vintage plane crashes into road during Shoreham Airshow in England","wikiTitle":"Vintage_plane_crashes_into_road_during_Shoreham_Airshow_in_England","wid":2389235,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-26T00:46:56Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAirshow collision kills one in Dittingen, Switzerland, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPlanes carrying parachutists collide, crash in Slovakia, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAircraft crashes during mock dogfight at Shoreham Airshow, United Kingdom, date\u003dSeptember 15, 2007]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/aug/22/shoreham-air-show-crash-sussex-police-bodies, title\u003dShoreham air crash: police warn more bodies may be found, author\u003dChris Johnston, Lin Jenkins, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/shoreham-plane-crash-live-wedding-limousine-caught-up-in-deadly-airshow-accident-10467686.html, title\u003dShoreham plane crash: Wedding limousine hit in deadly airshow accident, author\u003dDoug Bolton, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/aviation/11818912/Shoreham-air-show-plane-crash-LIVE.html, title\u003dShoreham Air Show plane crash: First three victims named as death toll of seven may rise - live, author\u003dDanny Boyle, Nicola Harley, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (UK), date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/aviation/11818767/Shoreham-air-show-crash-wedding-limousine-hit-as-jet-smashes-into-major-road-killing-sven-people.html, title\u003dShoreham air show crash: death toll \u0027may rise\u0027 past seven after jet smashes into major road hitting four cars including wedding limousine, author\u003dNicola Harley, Patrick Sawer, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (UK), date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/shoreham-airshow-crash-live-two-footballers-named-as-victims-10467744.html, title\u003dFootballers Matthew Grimstone and Jacob Schilt and personal trainer Matt Jones named as first victims of Shoreham Airshow crash, author\u003dDoug Bolton, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1540454/shoreham-airshow-crash-11-people-feared-dead, title\u003dShoreham Airshow Crash: 11 People Feared Dead, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"England","description":"England"},{"id":"British_Airways","description":"British Airways"},{"id":"association_football","description":"football"},{"id":"Air_Accidents_Investigation_Branch","description":"Air Accidents Investigation Branch"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"Europe","description":"Europe"},{"id":"Slovakia","description":"Slovakia"},{"id":"Switzerland","description":"Switzerland"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[aviation] TEMPLATE[date, August 23, 2015] TEMPLATE[image_credit, [https://www.flickr.com/people/65001151@N03 Alan Wilson]] Police warn more bodies may remain to be found after yesterday\u0027s crash of a vintage jet killed at least seven people. The TEMPLATE[w, Hawker Hunter] crashed into a busy road during the TEMPLATE[w, Shoreham Airshow] in England.","The plane failed to pull out of a large loop at around 1:20p.m. It hit the nearby TEMPLATE[w, A27 road], erupting into a fireball and leaving cars burned out and heavily damaged. The scene in TEMPLATE[w, West Sussex] is near the town of TEMPLATE[w, Shoreham].","Pilot Andy Hill is presently alive but critically injured in hospital. He has previously flown with British Airways and the TEMPLATE[w, Royal Air Force]. Two of the dead are TEMPLATE[w, Worthing United FC] football players, Matthew Grimstone and Jacob Schilt, who were on their way to a match.","Also killed was Matt Jones, 24, who worked as a TEMPLATE[w, personal trainer]. He came from TEMPLATE[w, Littlehampton] and was giving a friend a lift. A vintage TEMPLATE[w, Daimler] wedding limousine on its way to collect a bride was also caught up in the crash, but its owner Chariot Chauffeurs say they are unclear on if the driver was a fatality.","TEMPLATE[w, Sussex Police] and the Air Accidents Investigation Branch are investigating. Police Superintendent Jane Derrick said last night, \"At this time we are continuing to search[...] It is possible that tonight and tomorrow we are going to find more bodies at the scene.\" She said it is believed all casualties except the pilot were road users. At least fourteen were injured.  TEMPLATE[image_credit, [https://www.flickr.com/people/62787780@N06 John5199]] Assistant Chief Constable Steve Barry today said eleven people are \"highly likely to have died in this tragedy\", based upon \"our initial work at the site\" and \"inquiries following calls to the emergency services from worried families and friends\". He said officers currently remain at the \"incredibly large\" scene. There are plans to remove plane wreckage using a crane tomorrow.","The pilot, Hill, was experienced, with years of display flying under his belt and a military career that included flying TEMPLATE[w, Harrier jet, Harrier jump-jets]. David Wildridge, another pilot who took part yesterday, said Hill is \"well-known and well-loved\", \"very professional\", and that his Harrier experience made him \"the best of the best.\"","The 1950s jet was decommissioned from military service in 1996 and sold at auction. In 2012 English entrepreneur Graham Peacock bought it for around TEMPLATE[w, pound sterling, Â£]65,000. It is a regular at airshows.","Tina Tilley, head of the local chamber of commerce, was at the show and said \"From where we were we could see the jet came down very low and looked like it was going to scoop up \u0026mdash; but it didn\u0027t. There were flames and we knew it was right on the A27. Everyone was horrified and there were people crying.\" Motorist Dom Lawson, whose car was narrowly missed, said \"It was like something out of TEMPLATE[w, Die Hard]\". The road closure left thousands trapped at the scene as they could not remove their cars.","In a statement, Prime Minister David Cameron sent \"his heartfelt condolences to the families of the people who were so tragically killed [...] [his] thoughts and prayers are with the families and friends of the victims.\" The airshow is cancelled today.","It is one of three deadly European airshow crash in four days. On Thursday two planes carrying parachutists collided and crashed in West Slovakia. At least seven were killed. They had been practising for an airshow due to be held this weekend. Today two small planes collided during an airshow in TEMPLATE[w, Dittingen], Switzerland. One of the pilots escaped but the other was killed.","Earlier this year a pilot was killed when his plane crashed during an aerial display at TEMPLATE[w, CarFest] in England. In 2007 a Shoreham Airshow display recreating the TEMPLATE[w, Battle of Britain] ended with a pilot dead following a crash. TEMPLATE[PhoneContact, Those concerned about relatives can call police on 01273 470101] TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, 2015 Shoreham Airshow crash]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:British_Airways","description":"Category:British Airways"},{"id":"Category:Royal_Air_Force","description":"Category:Royal Air Force"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"},{"id":"Category:History","description":"Category:History"},{"id":"Category:Air_Accidents_Investigation_Branch","description":"Category:Air Accidents Investigation Branch"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Sussex_Police","description":"Category:Sussex Police"},{"id":"Category:Airshows","description":"Category:Airshows"},{"id":"Category:West_Sussex","description":"Category:West Sussex"},{"id":"Category:Shoreham","description":"Category:Shoreham"},{"id":"Category:Shoreham_Airshow","description":"Category:Shoreham Airshow"}],"templates":[{"name":"aviation","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["August 23, 2015"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[https://www.flickr.com/people/65001151@N03 Alan Wilson]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hawker Hunter"]},{"name":"w","description":["Shoreham Airshow"]},{"name":"w","description":["A27 road"]},{"name":"w","description":["West Sussex"]},{"name":"w","description":["Shoreham"]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal Air Force"]},{"name":"w","description":["Worthing United FC"]},{"name":"w","description":["personal trainer"]},{"name":"w","description":["Littlehampton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Daimler"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sussex Police"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[https://www.flickr.com/people/62787780@N06 John5199]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Harrier jet","Harrier jump-jets"]},{"name":"w","description":["pound sterling","Â£"]},{"name":"w","description":["Die Hard"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dittingen"]},{"name":"w","description":["CarFest"]},{"name":"w","description":["Battle of Britain"]},{"name":"PhoneContact","description":["Those concerned about relatives can call police on 01273 470101"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dAirshow collision kills one in Dittingen, Switzerland","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPlanes carrying parachutists collide, crash in Slovakia","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dAircraft crashes during mock dogfight at Shoreham Airshow, United Kingdom","date\u003dSeptember 15, 2007"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["2015 Shoreham Airshow crash"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/aug/22/shoreham-air-show-crash-sussex-police-bodies","title\u003dShoreham air crash: police warn more bodies may be found","author\u003dChris Johnston, Lin Jenkins","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/uk/home-news/shoreham-plane-crash-live-wedding-limousine-caught-up-in-deadly-airshow-accident-10467686.html","title\u003dShoreham plane crash: Wedding limousine hit in deadly airshow accident","author\u003dDoug Bolton","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/aviation/11818912/Shoreham-air-show-plane-crash-LIVE.html","title\u003dShoreham Air Show plane crash: First three victims named as death toll of seven may rise - live","author\u003dDanny Boyle, Nicola Harley","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (UK)","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/aviation/11818767/Shoreham-air-show-crash-wedding-limousine-hit-as-jet-smashes-into-major-road-killing-sven-people.html","title\u003dShoreham air show crash: death toll \u0027may rise\u0027 past seven after jet smashes into major road hitting four car