{"title":"Airshow collision kills one in Dittingen, Switzerland","wikiTitle":"Airshow_collision_kills_one_in_Dittingen,_Switzerland","wid":2389384,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-25T23:34:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dVintage plane crashes into road during Shoreham Airshow in England, date\u003d August 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPlanes carrying parachutists collide, crash in Slovakia, date\u003dAugust 20, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/one-dead-as-two-planes-collide-at-swiss-air-show-20150823-gj5x4c.html, title\u003dOne dead as two planes collide at Swiss air show, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/switzerland-airshow-crash-at-least-one-dead-after-two-planes-collide-in-dittingen-10467856.html, title\u003dSwitzerland airshow crash: At least one dead after two planes collide in Dittingen, author\u003dDoug Bolton, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ibtimes.co.in/switzerland-pilot-dies-after-two-small-planes-collide-mid-air-during-dittingen-air-show-643935, title\u003dSwitzerland: 2 Planes Collide Midair During Dittingen Airshow, Pilot Killed \u0026#91;Photos+Video\u0026#93;, author\u003dJohnlee Varghese, pub\u003dThe International Business Times, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"midair_collision","description":"midair collision"},{"id":"Switzerland","description":"Switzerland"},{"id":"Germany","description":"German"},{"id":"Europe","description":"Europe"},{"id":"Slovakia","description":"Slovakia"},{"id":"England","description":"England"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 23, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] A midair collision today killed a pilot during an airshow in the village of TEMPLATE[w, Dittingen] in Switzerland. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, Peter Bakema] The crash occurred as three TEMPLATE[w, Ikarus C42] planes from the German Grasshopper display team flew together in formation. Two collided and crashed, with one pilot ejecting and parachuting to safety and the other remaining on board and being killed. The third plane was not directly involved and landed successfully.","The northern Swiss village is near TEMPLATE[w, Basel]. Basel-TEMPLATE[w, Landschaft] police spokesman Meinrad Stoecklin put the time of the accident at 11:30a.m. The airshow was first halted as rescuers arrived, then cancelled altogether. It is unclear if there are any additional injuries.","Authorities have closed down access to the scene. The killed pilot\u0027s plane struck a barn. The display team reportedly was using amateur pilots.","It is the third deadly European airshow crash in four days. On Thursday two planes carrying parachutists collided and crashed in West Slovakia. At least seven were killed. They had been practising for an airshow due to be held this weekend. Yesterday a vintage warplane crashed onto a busy road by TEMPLATE[w, Shoreham] in England. Seven are confirmed dead, with the pilot critical and police continuing to search the scene for more bodies.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Midair_collisions","description":"Category:Midair collisions"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Switzerland","description":"Category:Switzerland"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Airshows","description":"Category:Airshows"},{"id":"Category:Aviation_accidents_and_incidents","description":"Category:Aviation accidents and incidents"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Dittingen"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["Peter Bakema"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ikarus C42"]},{"name":"w","description":["Basel"]},{"name":"w","description":["Landschaft"]},{"name":"w","description":["Shoreham"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dVintage plane crashes into road during Shoreham Airshow in England","date\u003d August 23, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPlanes carrying parachutists collide, crash in Slovakia","date\u003dAugust 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/one-dead-as-two-planes-collide-at-swiss-air-show-20150823-gj5x4c.html","title\u003dOne dead as two planes collide at Swiss air show","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/switzerland-airshow-crash-at-least-one-dead-after-two-planes-collide-in-dittingen-10467856.html","title\u003dSwitzerland airshow crash: At least one dead after two planes collide in Dittingen","author\u003dDoug Bolton","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ibtimes.co.in/switzerland-pilot-dies-after-two-small-planes-collide-mid-air-during-dittingen-air-show-643935","title\u003dSwitzerland: 2 Planes Collide Midair During Dittingen Airshow, Pilot Killed \u0026#91;Photos+Video\u0026#93;","author\u003dJohnlee Varghese","pub\u003dThe International Business Times","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"IndyCar driver Justin Wilson dies aged 37","wikiTitle":"IndyCar_driver_Justin_Wilson_dies_aged_37","wid":2390599,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-08-31T15:00:21Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://cbs4indy.com/2015/08/24/justin-wilson-passes-away-after-indycar-accident-at-pocono-raceway/, title\u003dJustin Wilson passes away after IndyCar accident at Pocono Raceway, author\u003dGreg Margason, pub\u003dWTTV, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://sports.usatoday.com/2015/08/24/justin-wilson-crash-indycar-canopies-safety-433304/, title\u003dJustin Wilson crash prompts canopy talk again in IndyCar, author\u003dJeff Olson, pub\u003dUSA Today, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.si.com/racing/2015/08/23/sage-karam-justin-wilson-crash-indycar-abc-supply, title\u003dDriver Justin Wilson in critical condition, coma after crash, author\u003dJermey Woo, pub\u003dSports Illustrated, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://espn.go.com/racing/story/_/id/13496744/justin-wilson-taken-hospital-accident-pocono-raceway, title\u003dJustin Wilson in coma after suffering severe head injury during race, author\u003d, pub\u003dESPN, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://sports.usatoday.com/2015/08/24/sage-karam-released-hospital-pocono-crash/, title\u003dSage Karam released from hospital, author\u003dBrant James, pub\u003dUSA Today, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://espn.go.com/racing/indycar/story/_/id/13498236/examining-indycar-safety-justin-wilson-accident, title\u003dHow can IndyCar be safer?, author\u003dBob Pockrass, pub\u003dESPN, date\u003dAugust 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://sports.usatoday.com/2015/08/23/indycar-justin-wilson-sage-karam-crash-at-pocono/, title\u003dIndyCar driver Justin Wilson in a coma after Pocono crash, author\u003dJeff Olson, pub\u003dUSA Today, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.indystar.com/story/sports/motor/2015/08/23/winner-hunter-reay-points-leader-montoya-somber-not-celebratory-after-race/32245171/, title\u003dWinner Hunter-Reay, points leader Montoya somber, not celebratory after race, author\u003dJeff Olson, pub\u003dUSA Today, date\u003dAugust 23, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Formula_One","description":"Formula One"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Sports] TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Midgrid, Midgrid]]] TEMPLATE[date, August 25, 2015]","Yesterday, 37-year old TEMPLATE[w, IndyCar Series] driver TEMPLATE[w, Justin Wilson (racing driver), Justin Wilson] died of injuries sustained on Sunday during the TEMPLATE[w, ABC Supply 500] at TEMPLATE[w, Pocono Raceway].","With about twenty laps remaining in the race, TEMPLATE[w, Sage Karam], who had been leading the event, crashed into the turn 1 wall. As Wilson approached the site of the crash, reportedly the nose cone from Karam\u0027s car that had been airborne struck Wilson in the helmet; Wilson\u0027s car steered to the left and collided with the inside TEMPLATE[w, SAFER barrier]. The event was placed under the TEMPLATE[w, Racing flags#Yellow flag, caution flag] as safety workers extracted Wilson from his car. Wilson was airlifted to TEMPLATE[w, Lehigh Valley Hospital] in TEMPLATE[w, Allentown, Pennsylvania]. At 9 P.M. TEMPLATE[w, Eastern Standard Time Zone, EST], TEMPLATE[w, INDYCAR] released a statement, announcing that Wilson had suffered a severe head injury, was in critical condition and had fallen into a TEMPLATE[w, coma]. The following day, TEMPLATE[w, Indianapolis Motor Speedway] president Doug Boles and TEMPLATE[w, Hulman \u0026 Company] Mark Miles officially announced Wilson\u0027s death.","Karam was able to walk away from the accident, and was evaluated for a right foot injury; he was released from the hospital the same day. Wilson\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Andretti Autosport] teammate TEMPLATE[w, Ryan Hunter-Reay] won the race, though he did not celebrate upon finding out about Wilson\u0027s accident. In Victory Lane, he stated, \"My first thoughts are with Justin, for sure[...] He\u0027s a friend, a teammate, and it\u0027s a bit hard not knowing anything.\"","Wilson, a former Formula One and TEMPLATE[w, Champ Car] driver, did not have a ride entering the TEMPLATE[w, 2015 IndyCar Series season, 2015 season], and joined Andretti on a seven-race deal. The contract had previously been for two races, but after acquiring sponsorship, the deal was increased by five events; earlier in August, Wilson recorded a best finish of second at TEMPLATE[w, Mid-Ohio Sports Car Course].","The accident led to discussions regarding the safety of the cars. A suggestion had been the addition of a TEMPLATE[w, Vehicle canopy, canopy] over the car\u0027s cockpit. The topic had been controversial: while some supported it for safety reasons, others opposed it because of history, possibly affecting the aerodynamics of the car, limiting one\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, peripheral vision] and movement inside the car, and worry about escaping an upside-down or burning car. Another had been to tether the nose cone to the car; Hunter-Reay mentioned renderings developed of a boomerang-like debris-deflector positioned in front of the driver. A further question raised had been regarding Wilson\u0027s height: at 6 TEMPLATE[w, foot (unit), feet], 3.5 TEMPLATE[w, inch, inches] (1.92 TEMPLATE[w, metre, m]) tall, Wilson was the tallest IndyCar Series driver; however, driver TEMPLATE[w, Josef Newgarden] refuted the statement, saying, \"They make a regulation for how tall you can be inside the car sitting compared to the TEMPLATE[w, roll cage, roll hoop] [...] It\u0027s safe for any height for any driver that gets in the car.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Pennsylvania","description":"Category:Pennsylvania"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Auto_racing","description":"Category:Auto racing"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"}],"templates":[{"name":"Sports","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Midgrid","Midgrid]]"]},{"name":"date","description":["August 25, 2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["IndyCar Series"]},{"name":"w","description":["Justin Wilson (racing driver)","Justin Wilson"]},{"name":"w","description":["ABC Supply 500"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pocono Raceway"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sage Karam"]},{"name":"w","description":["SAFER barrier"]},{"name":"w","description":["Racing flags#Yellow flag","caution flag"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lehigh Valley Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["Allentown, Pennsylvania"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eastern Standard Time Zone","EST"]},{"name":"w","description":["INDYCAR"]},{"name":"w","description":["coma"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indianapolis Motor Speedway"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hulman \u0026 Company"]},{"name":"w","description":["Andretti Autosport"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ryan Hunter-Reay"]},{"name":"w","description":["Champ Car"]},{"name":"w","description":["2015 IndyCar Series season","2015 season"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mid-Ohio Sports Car Course"]},{"name":"w","description":["Vehicle canopy","canopy"]},{"name":"w","description":["peripheral vision"]},{"name":"w","description":["foot (unit)","feet"]},{"name":"w","description":["inch","inches"]},{"name":"w","description":["metre","m"]},{"name":"w","description":["Josef Newgarden"]},{"name":"w","description":["roll cage","roll hoop"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://cbs4indy.com/2015/08/24/justin-wilson-passes-away-after-indycar-accident-at-pocono-raceway/","title\u003dJustin Wilson passes away after IndyCar accident at Pocono Raceway","author\u003dGreg Margason","pub\u003dWTTV","date\u003dAugust 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://sports.usatoday.com/2015/08/24/justin-wilson-crash-indycar-canopies-safety-433304/","title\u003dJustin Wilson crash prompts canopy talk again in IndyCar","author\u003dJeff Olson","pub\u003dUSA Today","date\u003dAugust 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.si.com/racing/2015/08/23/sage-karam-justin-wilson-crash-indycar-abc-supply","title\u003dDriver Justin Wilson in critical condition, coma after crash","author\u003dJermey Woo","pub\u003dSports Illustrated","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://espn.go.com/racing/story/_/id/13496744/justin-wilson-taken-hospital-accident-pocono-raceway","title\u003dJustin Wilson in coma after suffering severe head injury during race","author\u003d","pub\u003dESPN","date\u003dAugust 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://sports.usatoday.com/2015/08/24/sage-karam-released-hospital-pocono-crash/","title\u003dSage Karam released from hospital","author\u003dBrant James","pub\u003dUSA Today","date\u003dAugust 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://espn.go.com/racing/indycar/story/_/id/13498236/examining-indycar-safety-justin-wilson-accident","title\u003dHow can IndyCar be safer?","author\u003dBob Pockrass","pub\u003dESPN","date\u003dAugust 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://sports.usatoday.com/2015/08/23/indycar-justin-wilson-sage-karam-crash-at-pocono/","title\u003dIndyCar driver Justin Wilson in a coma after Pocono crash","author\u003dJeff Olson","pub\u003dUSA Today","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.indystar.com/story/sports/motor/2015/08/23/winner-hunter-reay-points-leader-montoya-somber-not-celebratory-after-race/32245171/","title\u003dWinner Hunter-Reay, points leader Montoya somber, not celebratory after race","author\u003dJeff Olson","pub\u003dUSA Today","date\u003dAugust 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"UK judge withholds report from Thai death penalty defendants","wikiTitle":"UK_judge_withholds_report_from_Thai_death_penalty_defendants","wid":2394485,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-14T16:51:00Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.judiciary.gov.uk/judgments/zaw-lin-and-wai-phyo-v-commissioner-of-police-for-the-metropolis/, title\u003dZaw Lin and Wai Phyo -v- Commissioner of Police for the Metropolis, author\u003dMr Justice Green, pub\u003dJudiciary of England and Wales, date\u003dAugust 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://home.bt.com/news/uk-news/thailand-tourist-murders-accused-mens-bid-to-access-met-report-rejected-11364000056860, title\u003dThailand tourist murders: Accused men\u0027s bid to access Met report rejected, author\u003d, pub\u003dBritish Telecom, date\u003dAugust 25, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"Thailand","description":"Thai"},{"id":"death_penalty","description":"death penalty"},{"id":"Metropolitan_Police","description":"Metropolitan Police"},{"id":"Burma","description":"Burmese"},{"id":"Jersey","description":"Jersey"},{"id":"England","description":"England"},{"id":"sex_crimes","description":"raped"},{"id":"right_to_a_fair_trial","description":"ongoing trial is unfair"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 25, 2015] TEMPLATE[crime_and_law] In a judgement released today Mr Justice Green, sitting in the TEMPLATE[w, High Court of Justice, High Court] in London, spoke of his \"very considerable unease\" as he rejected an application by two defendants in a Thai death penalty case. The pair sought a Metropolitan Police report they hoped could assist their defence. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, Wikivoyage] The court has expedited the case. Burmese nationals Zaw Lin and Wai Phyo, both 22, are currently on trial accused of murdering David Miller, 24, from Jersey, and Hannah Witheridge, 23, from England. With the defence case due to begin shortly and continue until mid- or late September the court has issued its judgement today following a hearing on Friday.","The case dates to September last year when the victims were found murdered on a TEMPLATE[w, Koh Tao] beach. Witheridge had been raped. The case attracted worldwide attention with Lin and Phyo confessing, before re-enacting the killing in front of the press.","The accused claim the confessions were tortured out of them and the ongoing trial is unfair. UK Prime Minister David Cameron intervened, speaking to Thai Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Prayut Chan-o-cha]. Cameron and Chan-o-cha arranged for an observer team from the Metropolitan Police to conduct an inspection of the Thai probe, based on powers in the TEMPLATE[w, Police Act 1996].","A team was duly dispatched and prepared a report with the intent to use it for assisting the victims\u0027 families. UK police were expressly forbidden, at a ministerial level, to provide any assistance to Thai authorities as the case involves the death penalty. Due to established UK policy on foreign death penalty cases, the report was also not shared with Thailand. It is this report that Lin and Phyo were seeking. TEMPLATE[w, Royal Courts of Justice]TEMPLATE[Image_credit, sjiong via (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, Flickr] Using the TEMPLATE[w, Data Protection Act 1998] the defendants asked police for this report to assist their defence, and were denied. That decision was the one challenged unsuccessfully in the High Court. The case pits the two accused trying to defend a death penalty case against the possibility of jeopardising international relations; Thai police co-operated, but only in light of an agreement the report would be confidential.","Legal charity TEMPLATE[w, Reprieve (organisation), Reprieve], who assisted the two men, said in a statement \"Concerns about the conduct of the Thai investigation and the safety of any convictions resulting have been raised from the very beginning[...]  only the defence lawyers in Thailand are in a position to judge whether the information could be of assistance.\" Mr Justice Green\u0027s judgement acknowledges he did not know \"how the accused might structure their defences\" or details about what evidence had been or would be involved. TEMPLATE[image_credit, D. Myles Cullen/(TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, United States armed forces, U.S. Military] Both men say they were starved, suffocated, stripped naked, exposed to cold temperatures, beaten, threatened, and denied legal representation. The TEMPLATE[w, Royal Thai Police] deny any misconduct. Mr Justice Green read the report himself and decided not to release it as it was of no assistance to the pair.","The report is known to contain some material disputed by Lin and Phyo. It says they repeated their confessions at various times, including in court with legal representation, before retracting them. It also says they have not backed up their torture claims with evidence, medical or otherwise. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, This is not a Report which contains, for instance, state secrets, 4\u003dMr Justice Green] Mr Justice Green said the report described \"in many respects [...] no more than the routine conduct of a serious crime investigation. This is not a Report which contains, for instance, state secrets.\" He also spoke of his distance from the ongoing trial, prompting him to remark of his \"very considerable unease\" and having to do \"the best I could\" \u0026mdash; not \"a comfortable process\".","Noting \"the issues of both law and fact are complex, novel and difficult\" Mr Justice Green\u0027s judgement notes that, before even hearing the case he promised permission to appeal would be granted, if requested, whatever the outcome. He also promised a swift Court of Appeal hearing to comply with Thai trial time constraints. \"The stakes are very high for both sides\", he added.","\"In my judgment the TEMPLATE[w, common law],\" the judgement reads, \"and in particular the principles of natural justice and fairness, would in a case such as this which involves the right to life, and the right to a fair trial, as well as powerful countervailing issues of public interest, compel the court to apply the most intense level of anxious scrutiny to the facts to ensure that the accused were not prejudiced.\"","Mr Justice Green also ruled the pair, in principal, \"have a perfectly proper right to seek access to the personal data for the purpose of using it subsequently in their defence in criminal proceedings\", calling the case one about \"fundamental rights\".","Rosa Curling, who represented both men in the London court, has said they would not appeal. She said Lin and Phyo are \"disappointed\" but \"are reassured that at least a British judge has now looked at the information held by the Metropolitan Police, applying anxious scrutiny, and determined that it would not assist them in their ongoing proceedings in Thailand.\"","Wikinews has contacted the Metropolitan Police, usually responsible for policing London, for a statement and is awaiting a response.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Thailand","description":"Category:Thailand"},{"id":"Category:Myanmar","description":"Category:Myanmar"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:Jersey","description":"Category:Jersey"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Sex_crimes","description":"Category:Sex crimes"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Right_to_a_fair_trial","description":"Category:Right to a fair trial"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Prayut_Chan-o-cha","description":"Category:Prayut Chan-o-cha"},{"id":"Category:Metropolitan_Police","description":"Category:Metropolitan Police"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 25, 2015"]},{"name":"crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["High Court of Justice","High Court"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["(TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["Wikivoyage"]},{"name":"w","description":["Koh Tao"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prayut Chan-o-cha"]},{"name":"w","description":["Police Act 1996"]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal Courts of Justice"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["sjiong via (TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["Flickr"]},{"name":"w","description":["Data Protection Act 1998"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reprieve (organisation)","Reprieve"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["D. Myles Cullen/(TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States armed forces","U.S. Military"]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal Thai Police"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["This is not a Report which contains, for instance, state secrets","4\u003dMr Justice Green"]},{"name":"w","description":["common law"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.judiciary.gov.uk/judgments/zaw-lin-and-wai-phyo-v-commissioner-of-police-for-the-metropolis/","title\u003dZaw Lin and Wai Phyo -v- Commissioner of Police for the Metropolis","author\u003dMr Justice Green","pub\u003dJudiciary of England and Wales","date\u003dAugust 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://home.bt.com/news/uk-news/thailand-tourist-