{"title":"Guatemalan Supreme Court approves impeachment of President Molina","wikiTitle":"Guatemalan_Supreme_Court_approves_impeachment_of_President_Molina","wid":2396448,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-27T18:28:03Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telesurtv.net/english/news/Guatemalan-Supreme-Court-Approves-Impeachment-of-President--20150826-0004.html, title\u003dGuatemalan Supreme Court Approves Impeachment of President, author\u003d, pub\u003dteleSUR, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.euronews.com/2015/08/26/guatemala-s-supreme-court-approves-bid-to-impeach-president/, title\u003dGuatemalaâs Supreme Court approves bid to impeach president, author\u003d, pub\u003deuronews, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Guatemala","description":"Guatemala"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[Guatemala] Yesterday in Guatemala, the TEMPLATE[w, sister\u003dw:es, Corte Suprema de Justicia de Guatemala, Supreme Court] approved the attorney general\u0027s request to impeach President TEMPLATE[w, Otto PÃ©rez Molina]. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[World Economic Forum]]] The final decision on lifting Presidential immunity now falls to TEMPLATE[w, Congress of Guatemala, Congress]. The case relates to a corruption scandal known locally as TEMPLATE[translation_note, \u0027\u0027La Linea\u0027\u0027, en, English language, The Line] which has seen Vice President TEMPLATE[w, Roxana Baldetti] arrested and charged with fraud and receiving bribes. Prosecutors allege Baldetti and Molina between them received half of all bribes in the case.","Congress previously refused to impeach Molina but the investigation has since broadened, with ministerial resignations. Molina, however, has stood firm in the face of widespread popular protests demanding he leave office. Elections are scheduled for September 6.","The Social and Popular Assembly, formed during protests in recent months, allege violations of electoral law by many parties, and want an electoral commission crackdown. One member organisation, the Committee for Campesino Unity, wants a delay until elections are reformed. They also seek a new constitution.","Molina is accused of conspiring to corruptly divert customs funds. He denies any misconduct.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Central_America","description":"Category:Central America"},{"id":"Category:Guatemala","description":"Category:Guatemala"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Otto_PÃ©rez_Molina","description":"Category:Otto PÃ©rez Molina"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Guatemala","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["sister\u003dw:es","Corte Suprema de Justicia de Guatemala","Supreme Court"]},{"name":"w","description":["Otto PÃ©rez Molina"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[World Economic Forum]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Congress of Guatemala","Congress"]},{"name":"translation_note","description":["\u0027\u0027La Linea\u0027\u0027","en","English language","The Line"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roxana Baldetti"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telesurtv.net/english/news/Guatemalan-Supreme-Court-Approves-Impeachment-of-President--20150826-0004.html","title\u003dGuatemalan Supreme Court Approves Impeachment of President","author\u003d","pub\u003dteleSUR","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.euronews.com/2015/08/26/guatemala-s-supreme-court-approves-bid-to-impeach-president/","title\u003dGuatemalaâs Supreme Court approves bid to impeach president","author\u003d","pub\u003deuronews","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["sister","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Virginia reporter, cameraman killed on live TV, alleged shooter commits suicide","wikiTitle":"Virginia_reporter,_cameraman_killed_on_live_TV,_alleged_shooter_commits_suicide","wid":2397497,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-03T20:39:03Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/virginia-police-shooting-live-television-news-report/, title\u003dGunman in deadly on-air attack dies after manhunt, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dCBS News, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/law-enforcement-investigating-incident-at-bridgewater-plaza/34923086, title\u003dTwo WDBJ7 employees shot and killed; suspected shooter kills himself, author\u003d, pub\u003dWDBJ, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Virginia","description":"Virginia"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] Two members of a news crew for TEMPLATE[w, Roanoke, Virginia, Roanoke], Virginia station TEMPLATE[w, WDBJ] were shot and killed on live television this morning. The suspect, a former reporter for the news station, later shot himself after a manhunt of several hours, authorities said.","Reporter Alison Parker, 24, and cameraman Adam Ward, 27, were conducting an interview at a local outdoor shopping mall when a gunman opened fire at approximately 6:45 AM TEMPLATE[w, UTC-4, local time] (1045 TEMPLATE[w, UTC]). Around fifteen shots were reported fired. Parker and Ward were killed, while the interviewee, Vicki Gardner, was transported to hospital and underwent surgery for her injuries, later listed in stable condition.","The gunman, later identified as 41 year-old Vester Lee Flanagan II, fled the scene. A brief police chase ensued several hours later when law enforcement attempted unsuccessfully to pull Flanagan over on TEMPLATE[w, Interstate 66] in TEMPLATE[w, Fauquier County, Virginia, Fauquier County]. Shortly after, Flanagan pulled off the road and shot himself. He was pronounced dead at a TEMPLATE[w, Fairfax, Virginia, Fairfax]-area hospital around 1:30 PM local time (1730 UTC).","Flanagan, who reported under the alias \"Bryce Williams\", was fired by the station in 2013. According to WDBJ president and general manager Jeffrey Marks, speaking to TEMPLATE[w, CBS News], Flanagan was \"an unhappy man\" and \"difficult to work with\". \"Eventually after many incidents of his anger coming to the fore, we dismissed him. He did not take that well\".","A video of the shooting, which appeared to have been captured from the point of view of the shooter, was posted on Bryce Williams\u0027 Twitter and Facebook pages several hours afterwards.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Virginia","description":"Category:Virginia"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Journalism","description":"Category:Journalism"},{"id":"Category:Media","description":"Category:Media"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Roanoke, Virginia","Roanoke"]},{"name":"w","description":["WDBJ"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC-4","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC"]},{"name":"w","description":["Interstate 66"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fauquier County, Virginia","Fauquier County"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fairfax, Virginia","Fairfax"]},{"name":"w","description":["CBS News"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/virginia-police-shooting-live-television-news-report/","title\u003dGunman in deadly on-air attack dies after manhunt","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dCBS News","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wdbj7.com/news/local/law-enforcement-investigating-incident-at-bridgewater-plaza/34923086","title\u003dTwo WDBJ7 employees shot and killed; suspected shooter kills himself","author\u003d","pub\u003dWDBJ","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Gujarat quota protests turn violent","wikiTitle":"Gujarat_quota_protests_turn_violent","wid":2398134,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-07T12:25:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dBJP\u0027s Narendra Modi elected new prime minister of India, date\u003dMay 17, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://hindustantimes.com/india/pm-modi-appeals-for-peace-in-violence-hit-gujarat/article1-1384375.aspx, title\u003dPatel stir: 7 killed, army called in to control Gujarat violence, author\u003d, pub\u003dHindustan Times, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-34059789, title\u003dNarendra Modi urges Gujarat calm after Patel caste protests, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://in.reuters.com/article/2015/08/26/india-protests-idINKCN0QV0IZ20150826, title\u003dThree killed in Gujarat as Modi urges calm, author\u003d, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"India","description":"India"},{"id":"Gujarat","description":"Gujarat"},{"id":"Narendra_Modi","description":"Narendra Modi"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[India] TEMPLATE[date, August 28, 2015] Parts of the Indian state of Gujarat have been under curfew since Tuesday. At least seven are reported dead, with over 100 buses and dozens of police stations burned, after protests over job quotas turned violent in several major cities including TEMPLATE[w, Ahmedabad], TEMPLATE[w, Surat], and TEMPLATE[w, Rajkot]. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, Each and every issue can be resolved through talks, 4\u003dNarendra Modi] The violence is thought to have started after a brief attempt by police to arrest protest leader Hardik Patel, 22 or 21. There have been weeks of protests by members of the TEMPLATE[w, Patel] caste, with the most recent involving an estimated half a million people.","Ahmedabad, the largest city in the state, has seen the closure of public transport, internet access, schools, and businesses. Ahmedabad is being patrolled by 400 military personnel. The national government has deployed several thousand paramilitary personnel to assist the state government.","The Patel caste, who form up to a fifth of the state population, are generally seen as being affluent businesspeople. However, they want their community to be given the status of TEMPLATE[w, Other Backward Class], which would result in eligibility for TEMPLATE[w, Reservation in India, reserved jobs]. They feel they are under-represented in higher education and are suffering in a regional economic downturn.","Amongst those calling for an end to the violence was Prime Minister Narendra Modi, who said \"each and every issue can be resolved through talks\" during a televised broadcast. He was elected last year and was previously the TEMPLATE[w, Chief Minister of Gujarat] for more than twelve years. He was in power in Gujurat during TEMPLATE[w, 2002 Gujarat riots, sectarian violence in 2002] which resulted in about a thousand deaths.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:India","description":"Category:India"},{"id":"Category:Gujarat","description":"Category:Gujarat"},{"id":"Category:Narendra_Modi","description":"Category:Narendra Modi"},{"id":"Category:Protests","description":"Category:Protests"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"}],"templates":[{"name":"India","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["August 28, 2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ahmedabad"]},{"name":"w","description":["Surat"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rajkot"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["Each and every issue can be resolved through talks","4\u003dNarendra Modi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Patel"]},{"name":"w","description":["Other Backward Class"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reservation in India","reserved jobs"]},{"name":"w","description":["Chief Minister of Gujarat"]},{"name":"w","description":["2002 Gujarat riots","sectarian violence in 2002"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dBJP\u0027s Narendra Modi elected new prime minister of India","date\u003dMay 17, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://hindustantimes.com/india/pm-modi-appeals-for-peace-in-violence-hit-gujarat/article1-1384375.aspx","title\u003dPatel stir: 7 killed, army called in to control Gujarat violence","author\u003d","pub\u003dHindustan Times","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-india-34059789","title\u003dNarendra Modi urges Gujarat calm after Patel caste protests","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://in.reuters.com/article/2015/08/26/india-protests-idINKCN0QV0IZ20150826","title\u003dThree killed in Gujarat as Modi urges calm","author\u003d","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Austrian police find dozens dead inside lorry","wikiTitle":"Austrian_police_find_dozens_dead_inside_lorry","wid":2398612,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-04T19:31:40Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/austria-lorry-migrants-eu-refugee-crisis-50-asylumseekers-found-dead-in-a-lorry-10474464.html, title\u003dEU migrant crisis: 50 refugees found \u0027suffocated\u0027 in the back of a single lorry in Austria, reports, author\u003dAdam Withnall, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34073534, title\u003dMigrant crisis: Grim find of bodies in Austria lorry, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/27/migrants-found-dead-inside-lorry-in-austria, title\u003dAt least 20 migrants found dead inside lorry in Austria, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.krone.at/Oesterreich/Bis_zu_50_Fluechtlinge_in_Schlepper-Lkw_erstickt-Asyl-Tragoedie_auf_A4-Story-469222, title\u003dBis zu 50 FlÃ¼chtlinge in Schlepper- Lkw erstickt, author\u003d, pub\u003dKronen Zeitung, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015, lang\u003dGerman]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bild.de/news/ausland/fluechtling/firma-hyza-wirbt-mit-fluechtlingsgeschichte-42351866.bild.html, title\u003dFirma wirbt mit FlÃ¼chtlingsgeschichte, author\u003d, pub\u003dBild Zeitung, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015, lang\u003dGerman]"]],"links":[{"id":"Austria","description":"Austria"},{"id":"Hungary","description":"Hungarian"},{"id":"Slovakia","description":"Slovakia"},{"id":"European_Union","description":"European Union"},{"id":"Serbia","description":"Serbia"},{"id":"Serbia","description":"Serbia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[Austria] TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:My Friend, My Friend]]] TEMPLATE[image_credit, Hyza] Austrian police today found an estimated 20\u0026ndash;50 decomposing corpses in an apparently abandoned lorry.","Roadworkers who spotted the vehicle, which had been there since yesterday at least, alerted police. Responding officers found it full of corpses. The lorry is on the so-called \"TEMPLATE[w, Eastern Motorway]\", the A4, close to the Hungarian border. It was on the TEMPLATE[w, hard shoulder] between TEMPLATE[w, Neusiedl] and TEMPLATE[w, Parndorf], closer to Parndorf.","The victims are thought to have suffocated. Police are seeking the driver. TEMPLATE[w, Kronen Zeitung, The Krone] published an image of a non-articulated food lorry on the hard shoulder, which they report is the vehicle in question. The photo shows a pool of dark liquid on the ground beside the vehicle.","Video from a passing motorist shows at least one helicopter on-scene. The truck, which has pictures of meat on the side, shows branding for Slovakian food firm Hyza. Earlier today the company\u0027s website sported an apparent anti-immigration graphic, which has since been removed.","Wikinews got in touch with Hyza. \"We are truly sorry about [the] tragedy\" they told us in a statement. They said they have checked GPS trackers on their fleet and all their vehicles remain in Slovakia. The statement says the lorry in question was one of 21 Hyza vehicles sold on last year. It was then sold again and exported to Hungary, where it is now registered. Hyza told us the new owners have not changed the branding on the vehicle. According to the TEMPLATE[w, Bild Zeitung, Bild] newspaper, TEMPLATE[W, Agrofert] -- the parent company of Hyza -- said in a statement the new owners were required to do so.","Hyza says they will \"actively cooperate with Slovak police\", and \"express [their] sincere condolences to the bereaved families.\"","Interior Minister TEMPLATE[w, Johanna Mikl-Leitner] called it \"a dark day\" and called for European Union-wide measures to protect immigrant refugees and tackle human traffickers. Neighbouring Hungary is constructing a border fence across its entire frontier with Serbia. Yesterday alone saw a record 3,241 attempts to enter Hungary illegally, according to authorities there.","Conflict in Syria and other parts of the world has led refugees to Europe. Once inside, they can move freely inside the TEMPLATE[w, Schengen Area], which covers most of the EU.","Austrian police earlier this week arrested three motorists suspected of people smuggling. One driver is accused of moving 34 people, ten of them children, into Austria from Serbia. The group were left by the roadside near TEMPLATE[w, Bruck an der Leitha] and reported struggling to breathe in the van.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"},{"id":"Category:Austria","description":"Category:Austria"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Human_trafficking","description":"Category:Human trafficking"},{"id":"Category:Hungary","description":"Category:Hungary"},{"id":"Category:Syria","description":"Category:Syria"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Slovakia","description":"Category:Slovakia"},{"id":"Category:Serbia","description":"Category:Serbia"},{"id":"Category:European_Union","description":"Category:European Union"},{"id":"Category:Refugees","description":"Category:Refugees"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Austria","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:My Friend","My Friend]]"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Hyza"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eastern Motorway"]},{"name":"w","description":["hard shoulder"]},{"name":"w","description":["Neusiedl"]},{"name":"w","description":["Parndorf"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kronen Zeitung","The Krone"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bild Zeitung","Bild"]},{"name":"W","description":["Agrofert"]},{"name":"w","description":["Johanna Mikl-Leitner"]},{"name":"w","description":["Schengen Area"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bruck an der Leitha"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/austria-lorry-migrants-eu-refugee-crisis-50-asylumseekers-found-dead-in-a-lorry-10474464.html","title\u003dEU migrant crisis: 50 refugees found \u0027suffocated\u0027 in the back of a single lorry in Austria, reports","author\u003dAdam Withnall","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34073534","title\u003dMigrant crisis: Grim find of bodies in Austria lorry","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/27/migrants-found-dead-inside-lorry-in-austria","title\u003dAt least 20 migrants found dead inside lorry in Austria","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.krone.at/Oesterreich/Bis_zu_50_Fluechtlinge_in_Schlepper-Lkw_erstickt-Asyl-Tragoedie_auf_A4-Story-469222","title\u003dBis zu 50 FlÃ¼chtlinge in Schlepper- Lkw erstickt","author\u003d","pub\u003dKronen Zeitung","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015","lang\u003dGerman"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bild.de/news/ausland/fluechtling/firma-hyza-wirbt-mit-fluechtlingsgeschichte-42351866.bild.html","title\u003dFirma wirbt mit FlÃ¼chtlingsgeschichte","author\u003d","pub\u003dBild Zeitung","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015","lang\u003dGerman"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","lang","url","title","author","pub","date","lang"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Kronen Zeitung, The Krone]","Wikinews","TEMPLATE[w, Bild Zeitung, Bild]"]}
{"title":"South Sudanese President Salva Kiir signs peace deal","wikiTitle":"South_Sudanese_President_Salva_Kiir_signs_peace_deal","wid":2398767,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-27T18:33:49Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/south-sudan-president-salva-kiir-reluctantly-signs-peace-deal-20150826-gj8orc.html, title\u003dSouth Sudan president Salva Kiir reluctantly signs peace deal, author\u003dDenis Dumo, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/27/south-sudan-president-salva-kiir-signs-peace-deal-despite-serious-reservations, title\u003dSouth Sudan\u0027s President Salva Kiir signs peace deal despite \u0027serious reservations\u0027, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-34066511, title\u003dSouth Sudan President Salva Kiir signs peace deal, author\u003dAlastair Leithead, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"South_Sudan","description":"South Sudan"},{"id":"Juba","description":"Juba"},{"id":"Ethiopia","description":"Ethiopia"},{"id":"United_Nations","description":"United Nations"},{"id":"Uganda","description":"Uganda"},{"id":"Ethiopia","description":"Ethiopia"},{"id":"Kenya","description":"Kenya"},{"id":"Ban_Ki-moon","description":"Ban Ki-moon"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[South_Sudan] TEMPLATE[image_credit, U.S. Department of State] TEMPLATE[w, Salva Kiir], the President of South Sudan, yesterday signed a deal designed to end a civil ethnic conflict that has killed thousands and displaced over two million.","Under the deal Kiir will share power with TEMPLATE[w, Riek Machar]. Machar was Vice President but Kiir sacked him in 2013. December that year saw the dispute turn to war. Kiir is a TEMPLATE[w, Dinka] while Machar is a TEMPLATE[w, Nuer people, Nuer], and the conflict has largely split along these racial lines.","Kiir spoke of \"serious reservations\" at the signing ceremony in Juba. He is concerned about a requirement to consult \"First Vice President\" Machar, as he will be under the deal, on policies. He is also concerned about demilitarisation of Juba.","The deal to close the 20-month conflict was negotiated in Ethiopia, where Machar signed the same deal last week. Several ceasefires have failed over months of talks. Kiir, the only leader in South Sudan since independence in 2011, sought an extension of a two-week deadline but signed yesterday after United Nations sanctions were threatened.","Both sides accused the other of continuing hostilities. The rebels claimed government forces attacked them south of Juba, but say they were victorious. Kiir claimed the rebels attacked a northern position. Kiir says international leaders were \"careless\" with negotiations and warned a flawed deal could do more harm.","Ugandan President TEMPLATE[w, Yoweri Museveni], Ethiopian Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Hailemariam Desalegn], Kenyan President TEMPLATE[w, Uhuru Kenyatta], and UN secretary-general Ban Ki-moon all expressed their approval of the deal\u0027s signing. Kenyatta called it a \"happy day for us in the region\". Earlier in the day he warned there was \"no such thing as a perfect agreement\" and Museveni said the conflict was \"the wrong war in the wrong place at the wrong time\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:South_Sudan","description":"Category:South Sudan"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Uganda","description":"Category:Uganda"},{"id":"Category:Ethiopia","description":"Category:Ethiopia"},{"id":"Category:Kenya","description":"Category:Kenya"},{"id":"Category:United_Nations","description":"Category:United Nations"},{"id":"Category:Ban_Ki-moon","description":"Category:Ban Ki-moon"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Juba","description":"Category:Juba"},{"id":"Category:Salva_Kiir","description":"Category:Salva Kiir"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 27, 2015"]},{"name":"South_Sudan","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["U.S. Department of State"]},{"name":"w","description":["Salva Kiir"]},{"name":"w","description":["Riek Machar"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dinka"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nuer people","Nuer"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yoweri Museveni"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hailemariam Desalegn"]},{"name":"w","description":["Uhuru Kenyatta"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/south-sudan-president-salva-kiir-reluctantly-signs-peace-deal-20150826-gj8orc.html","title\u003dSouth Sudan president Salva Kiir reluctantly signs peace deal","author\u003dDenis Dumo","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/aug/27/south-sudan-president-salva-kiir-signs-peace-deal-despite-serious-reservations","title\u003dSouth Sudan\u0027s President Salva Kiir signs peace deal despite \u0027serious reservations\u0027","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-34066511","title\u003dSouth Sudan President Salva Kiir signs peace deal","author\u003dAlastair Leithead","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Cairo court retrial: Al Jazeera journalists sentenced to three yearsâ jail","wikiTitle":"Cairo_court_retrial:_Al_Jazeera_journalists_sentenced_to_three_yearsâ_jail","wid":2402563,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-25T04:40:55Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dEgyptian court sends three Al-Jazeera journalists to jail, date\u003dJune 23, 2014]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/08/29/middleeast/egypt-al-jazeera-journalists-trial/, title\u003dEgyptian court sentences 3 Al Jazeera journalists to prison, author\u003dSarah Sirgany, Laura Smith-Spark, Ian Lee, pub\u003d CNN, date\u003dAugust 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d https://twitter.com/PeterGreste/status/637544694579249152, title\u003d Peter Greste Twitter status, author\u003d Peter Greste, pub\u003d Twitter, date\u003d August 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/world/australian-journalist-peter-greste-and-al-jazeera-colleagues-mohammed-fahmy-baher-mohammed-sentenced-to-three-years-jail/story-fnihsmjt-1227504189096, title\u003d Australian journalist Peter Greste and Al-Jazeera colleagues Mohammed Fahmy, Baher Mohammed sentenced to three years jail, author\u003dNews Corp Australia Network, pub\u003d The Courier-Mail, date\u003d August 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-08-29/al-jazeera-retrial-greste-fahmy-mohamed-await-verdict/6734946, title\u003dAl Jazeera retrial: Peter Greste, Mohammed Fahmy and Baher Mohamed due to learn verdict of retrial, author\u003dSophie McNeill, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dAugust 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/08/verdict-expected-egyptian-trial-al-jazeera-staff-150829041359781.html, title\u003dAl Jazeera staff sentenced to jail in Egypt, author\u003d, pub\u003dAl Jazeera, date\u003d August 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/03/faqs-al-jazeeras-journalists-trial-egypt-150317113935704.html#case, title\u003dFAQ: Al Jazeera\u0027s journalists on trial in Egypt, author\u003d, pub\u003dAl Jazeera, date\u003d August 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://foreignminister.gov.au/releases/Pages/2015/jb_mr_150829.aspx, title\u003dPeter Greste Verdict, author\u003dJulie Bishop, pub\u003dMinister for Foreign Affairs (Australia), date\u003dAugust 29, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Al_Jazeera","description":"Al Jazeera"},{"id":"Canada","description":"Canadian"},{"id":"Egypt","description":"Egypt"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"Cairo","description":"Cairo"},{"id":"Muslim_Brotherhood","description":"Muslim Brotherhood"},{"id":"Julie_Bishop","description":"Julie Bishop"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 30, 2015] TEMPLATE[Egypt] Al Jazeera journalists Canadian TEMPLATE[w, Mohamed Fahmy], Egyptian Baher Mohamed, and Australian TEMPLATE[w, Peter Greste] were sentenced yesterday to three years in prison by judge Hassan Farid following a retrial of the 2013 case in Cairo.","The three men were accused of and charged with aiding banned Egyptian organization the Muslim Brotherhood, broadcasting false information, and operating without a press license within Egypt. Fahmy and Mohamed were present at the courtroom in Cairo\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Tora Prison], while Greste was deported to Australia in February following an overturned conviction, and as a result was tried TEMPLATE[w, trial in absentia, in absentia] after an ordered re-trial.","TEMPLATE[w, Australian Minister for Foreign Affairs] Julie Bishop has commented on the court\u0027s decision, saying she would use all diplomatic means available with the Egyptian minister of foreign affairs to clear Grestse\u0027s name. Al Jazeera continue to deny the accusations.","\"The situation is a challenge to journalism as a whole. If this stands unchallenged, this formula will be repeated elsewhere. Journalists should not be imprisoned for doing their jobs. Journalism is not a crime\", stated Al Jazeera online.  They indicated intent to appeal the verdict to the TEMPLATE[w, Court of Cassation].","Peter Greste tweeted on the verdict: \"Shocked. Outraged. Angry. Upset. None of them convey how I feel right now. 3 yr sentences for @bahrooz, @MFFahmy11 and me is so wrong.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Cairo","description":"Category:Cairo"},{"id":"Category:Egypt","description":"Category:Egypt"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Media","description":"Category:Media"},{"id":"Category:Journalism","description":"Category:Journalism"},{"id":"Category:Al-Jazeera","description":"Category:Al-Jazeera"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Freedom_of_the_press","description":"Category:Freedom of the press"},{"id":"Category:Free_speech","description":"Category:Free speech"},{"id":"Category:Muslim_Brotherhood","description":"Category:Muslim Brotherhood"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Canada","description":"Category:Canada"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Julie_Bishop","description":"Category:Julie Bishop"},{"id":"Category:Trial_in_absentia","description":"Category:Trial in absentia"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Egypt","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Mohamed Fahmy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Peter Greste"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tora Prison"]},{"name":"w","description":["trial in absentia","in absentia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australian Minister for Foreign Affairs"]},{"name":"w","description":["Court of Cassation"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dEgyptian court sends three Al-Jazeera journalists to jail","date\u003dJune 23, 2014"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/08/29/middleeast/egypt-al-jazeera-journalists-trial/","title\u003dEgyptian court sentences 3 Al Jazeera journalists to prison","author\u003dSarah Sirgany, Laura Smith-Spark, Ian Lee","pub\u003d CNN","date\u003dAugust 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d https://twitter.com/PeterGreste/status/637544694579249152","title\u003d Peter Greste Twitter status","author\u003d Peter Greste","pub\u003d Twitter","date\u003d August 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.couriermail.com.au/news/world/australian-journalist-peter-greste-and-al-jazeera-colleagues-mohammed-fahmy-baher-mohammed-sentenced-to-three-years-jail/story-fnihsmjt-1227504189096","title\u003d Australian journalist Peter Greste and Al-Jazeera colleagues Mohammed Fahmy, Baher Mohammed sentenced to three years jail","author\u003dNews Corp Australia Network","pub\u003d The Courier-Mail","date\u003d August 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abc.net.au/news/2015-08-29/al-jazeera-retrial-greste-fahmy-mohamed-await-verdict/6734946","title\u003dAl Jazeera retrial: Peter Greste, Mohammed Fahmy and Baher Mohamed due to learn verdict of retrial","author\u003dSophie McNeill","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dAugust 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/08/verdict-expected-egyptian-trial-al-jazeera-staff-150829041359781.html","title\u003dAl Jazeera staff sentenced to jail in Egypt","author\u003d","pub\u003dAl Jazeera","date\u003d August 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/03/faqs-al-jazeeras-journalists-trial-egypt-150317113935704.html#case","title\u003dFAQ: Al Jazeera\u0027s journalists on trial in Egypt","author\u003d","pub\u003dAl Jazeera","date\u003d August 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://foreignminister.gov.au/releases/Pages/2015/jb_mr_150829.aspx","title\u003dPeter Greste Verdict","author\u003dJulie Bishop","pub\u003dMinister for Foreign Affairs (Australia)","date\u003dAugust 29, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Al Jazeera","TEMPLATE[w, trial in absentia, in absentia]","Al Jazeera"]}
{"title":"Four men go before Hungarian court after 71 found dead in lorry","wikiTitle":"Four_men_go_before_Hungarian_court_after_71_found_dead_in_lorry","wid":2402675,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-07T13:03:23Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAustrian police find dozens dead inside lorry, date\u003dAugust 27, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.kiiitv.com/story/29913094/4-men-in-court-in-hungary-over-migrant-truck-deaths, title\u003dHungary court orders arrest of 4 men in migrant truck deaths, author\u003dPablo Gorondi ([[Associated Press, AP]]), pub\u003dKIII, date\u003dAugust 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34096214, title\u003dAustria migrant lorry deaths: Suspects in Hungary court, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thelocal.at/20150829/more-migrants-risk-death-on-highway, title\u003dMore migrants risk lives on deadly journeys, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Local, date\u003dAugust 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thelocal.at/20150828/death-toll-in-truck-tragedy-exceeds-70, title\u003dTruck death toll 71 including 4 children, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Local, date\u003dAugust 28, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Hungary","description":"Hungary"},{"id":"Austria","description":"Austria"},{"id":"Bulgaria","description":"Bulgaria"},{"id":"Afghanistan","description":"Afghanistan"},{"id":"Syria","description":"Syria"},{"id":"Serbia","description":"Serbia"},{"id":"Slovakia","description":"Slovak"},{"id":"Romania","description":"Romania"},{"id":"Germany","description":"German"},{"id":"Bangladesh","description":"Bangladesh"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 29, 2015] TEMPLATE[Austria] Four foreign men have today gone before a court in Hungary on suspicion of people smuggling. Their detention relates to Thursday\u0027s discovery of a lorry full of corpses in Austria. The death toll was yesterday finalised at 71. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:talk:Tothsandor92, Tothsandor92]]] The lorry had been abandoned since Wednesday on the TEMPLATE[w, hard shoulder] of the \"TEMPLATE[w, Eastern Motorway]\", near the Hungarian border. Roadworkers became suspicious of dark liquid seeping from the vehicle, and responding police found the bodies. Initial police estimates were that 20\u0026ndash;50 were suffocated in the back of the lorry which was near TEMPLATE[w, Parndorf].","The arrested men are thought to include the vehicle\u0027s owner and at least two drivers. Three are Bulgarian and one is from Afghanistan. Criminal suspects in Hungary can generally be held for 72 hours before charge but prosecutors, citing the seriousness of the case, want the period extended. Extradition to Austria is possible.","Of the 71 dead, 59 are men, eight are women, and four are children. The children are thought to be aged three, eight, and ten years, alongside an eighteen-month-old baby. \"There was also a Syrian travel document found\" police spokesman Hans Peter Doskozil told journalists \"so of course our first assumption is that these people were migrants, and likely a group of Syrian migrants. We can rule out that they were Africans\".","The four accused were escorted into court in TEMPLATE[w, Kecskemet], central Hungary, by a police convoy. Reportedly the lorry traveled from Kecskemet. Hungary is presently building a border fence across the Serbian frontier, as migrants from war-torn Syria and other regions seek access to the TEMPLATE[w, Schengen Area] of free movement, which covers most of the EU. TEMPLATE[image_credit, Hyza] Slovak chicken meat company Hyza, a previous owner, previously told Wikinews the lorry has changed hands several times in roughly the last year. After they sold it they say it was exported to Hungary; it now bears Hungarian plates but still features Hyza branding including pictures of meat.","On the day of the discovery Hyza quickly removed a graphic from their homepage featuring cartoon chicken stowaways in a car being inspected at a customs post. The stowaways also appeared with a line through them alongside the word \"imigranti\" and the site www.imigranti.sk in one corner. On the other side was Hyza\u0027s logo. Imigranti.sk is also unavailable.","Police today found 26 migrants in a lorry near TEMPLATE[w, Braunau am Inn], Austria. The driver, from Romania, refused to stop for police and was arrested following a chase. Police said three children were hospitalised for \"severe dehydration\". Found near the German border, the migrants were from Afghanistan, Syria, and Bangladesh.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Hungary","description":"Category:Hungary"},{"id":"Category:Austria","description":"Category:Austria"},{"id":"Category:Syria","description":"Category:Syria"},{"id":"Category:Bulgaria","description":"Category:Bulgaria"},{"id":"Category:Afghanistan","description":"Category:Afghanistan"},{"id":"Category:Slovakia","description":"Category:Slovakia"},{"id":"Category:Romania","description":"Category:Romania"},{"id":"Category:Bangladesh","description":"Category:Bangladesh"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Refugees","description":"Category:Refugees"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 29, 2015"]},{"name":"Austria","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:talk:Tothsandor92","Tothsandor92]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["hard shoulder"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eastern Motorway"]},{"name":"w","description":["Parndorf"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kecskemet"]},{"name":"w","description":["Schengen Area"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Hyza"]},{"name":"w","description":["Braunau am Inn"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dAustrian police find dozens dead inside lorry","date\u003dAugust 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.kiiitv.com/story/29913094/4-men-in-court-in-hungary-over-migrant-truck-deaths","title\u003dHungary court orders arrest of 4 men in migrant truck deaths","author\u003dPablo Gorondi ([[Associated Press","AP]])","pub\u003dKIII","date\u003dAugust 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34096214","title\u003dAustria migrant lorry deaths: Suspects in Hungary court","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thelocal.at/20150829/more-migrants-risk-death-on-highway","title\u003dMore migrants risk lives on deadly journeys","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Local","date\u003dAugust 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thelocal.at/20150828/death-toll-in-truck-tragedy-exceeds-70","title\u003dTruck death toll 71 including 4 children","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Local","date\u003dAugust 28, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Wikinews"]}
{"title":"Fire kills eleven at oil worker housing in Alkhobar, Saudi Arabia","wikiTitle":"Fire_kills_eleven_at_oil_worker_housing_in_Alkhobar,_Saudi_Arabia","wid":2406229,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-27T18:36:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.arabnews.com/featured/news/799071, title\u003dFire at Alkhobar complex kills 11, injures over 200, author\u003dMohammed al-Sulami, pub\u003dArab News, date\u003dAugust 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.middleeasteye.net/news/fire-kills-11-saudi-aramco-compound-2013580819, title\u003dFire kills 11 in Saudi Aramco compound, author\u003d, pub\u003dMiddle East Eye, date\u003dAugust 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-34101228, title\u003dDeadly Saudi Arabia fire at Aramco complex in Khobar, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dAugust 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Saudi_Arabia","description":"Saudi"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, August 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[disasters_and_accidents] A fire in the eastern Saudi city of TEMPLATE[w, Alkhobar] tore through a housing complex for oil workers yesterday, killing eleven, according to civil officials. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [https://www.flickr.com/people/10345599@N03 Francisco Anzola]] The Radium complex is rented by oil firm TEMPLATE[w, Saudi Aramco, Aramco] for their employees. According to nearby resident Mohammed Siddique the fire broke out early in the morning. Siddique says the building contains locals, as well as Westerners and Asians. The cause is unclear but the civil defence ministry tweeted \"Cars and furniture caught fire in the basement of one of the towers\".","Over 200 people were injured. Firefighters scaled the burning tower on ladders, and helicopters were on-scene. Other towers in the complex were evacuated. Thick smoke from the blaze complicated rescue efforts.","Aramco CEO Amin H. Nasser said the firm is \"deeply saddened to learn of the fatalities and injuries. We offer heartfelt condolences to the families. Our immediate priority is to provide full support to those affected by this tragic incident.\" Aramco, which produces and exports more crude oil than any competitor worldwide, say the fire is under investigation.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Saudi_Arabia","description":"Category:Saudi Arabia"},{"id":"Category:Fires","description":"Category:Fires"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Saudi_Aramco","description":"Category:Saudi Aramco"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["August 31, 2015"]},{"name":"disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Alkhobar"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[https://www.flickr.com/people/10345599@N03 Francisco Anzola]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Saudi Aramco","Aramco"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.arabnews.com/featured/news/799071","title\u003dFire at Alkhobar complex kills 11, injures over 200","author\u003dMohammed al-Sulami","pub\u003dArab News","date\u003dAugust 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.middleeasteye.net/news/fire-kills-11-saudi-aramco-compound-2013580819","title\u003dFire kills 11 in Saudi Aramco compound","author\u003d","pub\u003dMiddle East Eye","date\u003dAugust 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-34101228","title\u003dDeadly Saudi Arabia fire at Aramco complex in Khobar","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dAugust 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Dedicated domestic violence court opens on Australian Gold Coast","wikiTitle":"Dedicated_domestic_violence_court_opens_on_Australian_Gold_Coast","wid":2408168,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-11T23:06:31Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.goldcoastbulletin.com.au/news/crime-court/domestic-violence-court-opens-doors-on-the-gold-coast/story-fnje8bkv-1227506772969, title\u003d Domestic violence court opens doors on the Gold Coast, author\u003d Emily MacDonald, pub\u003d Gold Coast Bulletin, date\u003d September 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://m.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/gold-coast-domestic-violence-court-means-timely-processing-of-cases/story-fntwpug1-1227508032472, title\u003d Gold Coast domestic violence court means timely processing of cases, author\u003d Alexandria Utting, pub\u003d The Courier-Mail, date\u003d September 1, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Queensland","description":"Queensland"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 3, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] Queensland, Australia on Tuesday opened a specialist court dedicated to dealing with TEMPLATE[w, domestic violence] cases. The TEMPLATE[w, Southport, Queensland, Southport] Court on the TEMPLATE[w, Gold Coast, Queensland, Gold Coast] is to undergo a six-month trial, after which domestic violence courts may be opened across the rest of the state. The court\u0027s motto is \"timeliness, access and resolution\"; it aims to see domestic violence cases lodged and heard on the same day.","Magistrate Colin Strofield, 57, highlighted the need for domestic violence cases to be heard as soon as possible: \"If you are in fear of domestic violence or being subjected to domestic violence why should you need to wait one minute longer than you need to?\"","Police statistics indicate domestic violence cases in Queensland have risen from 3349 in 2010, to 4683 in 2014; Magistrate Strofield is hopeful the dedicated court will help these figures decline by getting more people to act against domestic violence.","According to Strofield, Southport court gets more domestic violence applications than any other court in Queensland. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Queensland","description":"Category:Queensland"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 3, 2015"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["domestic violence"]},{"name":"w","description":["Southport, Queensland","Southport"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gold Coast, Queensland","Gold Coast"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.goldcoastbulletin.com.au/news/crime-court/domestic-violence-court-opens-doors-on-the-gold-coast/story-fnje8bkv-1227506772969","title\u003d Domestic violence court opens doors on the Gold Coast","author\u003d Emily MacDonald","pub\u003d Gold Coast Bulletin","date\u003d September 1, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://m.couriermail.com.au/news/queensland/gold-coast-domestic-violence-court-means-timely-processing-of-cases/story-fntwpug1-1227508032472","title\u003d Gold Coast domestic violence court means timely processing of cases","author\u003d Alexandria Utting","pub\u003d The Courier-Mail","date\u003d September 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Biologist Nick Bos tells Wikinews about \u0027self-medicating\u0027 ants","wikiTitle":"Biologist_Nick_Bos_tells_Wikinews_about_\u0027self-medicating\u0027_ants","wid":2408472,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-29T11:03:06Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bwars.com/index.php?q\u003dant/formicidae/formicinae/formica-fusca, title\u003dFormica fusca Linnaeus, 1758, author\u003d, pub\u003dBees, Wasps and Ants Recording Society, date\u003dAccessed September 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/science/ants-are-able-to-selfmedicate-by-changing-diet-when-they-are-unwell-in-first-for-insectkind-10467040.html, title\u003dAnts are able to \u0027self-medicate\u0027 by changing diet when they are unwell in first for insect-kind, author\u003dJessica Staufenberg, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dAugust 22, 2015]"],["AntyScience blog","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/evo.12752/abstract;jsessionid\u003d9681B97E6C714FA4EE18B3766F8C44CC.f01t01, title\u003dAnts medicate to fight disease, author\u003dNick Bos, Liselotte SundstrÃ¶m, Siiri Fuchs, Dalial Freitak, pub\u003dEvolution, pubtarget\u003dEvolution (journal), date\u003d2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.treehugger.com/cars/trillions-of-insects-killed-by-cars-every-year-says-study.html, title\u003dTrillions of Insects Killed by Cars Every Year, Says Study, author\u003dStephen Messenger, pub\u003dTreehugger.com, date\u003dJuly 10, 2011], link provided by Nick Bos for further reading"]],"links":[{"id":"ant","description":"ant"},{"id":"Bolivia","description":"Bolivia"},{"id":"Denmark","description":"Denmark"},{"id":"the_Netherlands","description":"the Netherlands"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"https://antyscience.wordpress.com/","description":"AntyScience blog"}],"sections":["Sister links","Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[commons:User:Leviathan1983, Mathias Krumbholz]]] Nick Bos, of the TEMPLATE[w, University of Helsinki], studies \"the amazing adaptations social insects have evolved in order to fight the extreme parasite pressure they experience\". In a recently-accepted TEMPLATE[w, Evolution (journal), Evolution] paper Bos and colleagues describe ants appearing to self-medicate. TEMPLATE[QuoteRight, I have no doubt that as time goes on, there will be more and more cases documented] The team used TEMPLATE[w, Formica fusca], an ant species that can form thousand-strong colonies. This common black ant eats other insects, and also TEMPLATE[w, honeydew (secretion), aphid honeydew]. It often nests in tree stumps or under rocks and foraging workers can sometimes be spotted climbing trees.","Some ants were infected with TEMPLATE[w, Beauveria bassiana], a TEMPLATE[w, fungus]. Infected ants chose food laced with toxic TEMPLATE[w, hydrogen peroxide], whereas healthy ants avoided it. Hydrogen peroxide reduced infected ant fatalities by 15%, and the ants varied their intake depending upon how high the peroxide concentration was.","In the wild, Formica fusca can encounter similar chemicals in aphids and dead ants. TEMPLATE[w, The Independent] reported self-medicating ants a first among insects.","Bos obtained his doctorate from the TEMPLATE[w, University of Copenhagen]. He began postdoctoral research at Helsinki in 2012. He also runs the AntyScience blog. The blog aims to help address \"a gap between scientists and \u0027the general public\u0027.\" The name is a pun referencing ants, its primary topic, science, and \"non-scientific\" jargon-free communication. He now discusses his work with Wikinews. TEMPLATE[w, cicada]TEMPLATE[image_credit, [http://www.mushroomobserver.org/observer/show_user/181 Danny Newman]] TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] What first attracted you to researching ants?",":Nick Bos Me and a studymate were keeping a lot of animals during our studies, from beetles, to butterflies and TEMPLATE[w, mantids], to ants. We had the ants in  an observation nest, and I could just look at them for hours, watching  them go about. This was in my third year of Biology study I think. After a while I needed to start thinking about an internship for my M.Sc. studies, and decided to write a couple of professors. I ended up going  to the Centre for Social Evolution at the University of Copenhagen where I did a project on learning in Ants under supervision of Prof. Patrizia d\u0027Ettorre. I liked it so much there I ended up doing a PhD and I\u0027ve been working on social insects ever since.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] What methods and equipment were used for this investigation?",":NB This is a fun one. I try to work on a very low budget, and like to  build most of the experimental setups myself (we actually have equipment in the lab nicknamed the \u0027Nickinator\u0027, \u0027i-Nick\u0027 and the \u0027Nicktendo64\u0027). There\u0027s not that much money in fundamental science at the moment, so I try to cut the costs wherever possible. We collected  wild colonies of Formica fusca by searching through old tree-trunks in old logging sites in southern Finland. We then housed the ants in nests I made using Y-tong [TEMPLATE[w, aerated concrete]]. It\u0027s  very soft stone that you can easily carve. We carved out little  squares for the ants to live in (covered with old CD covers to prevent  them escaping!). We then drilled a tunnel to a pot (the foraging  arena), where the ants got the choice between the food with medicine  and the food without.",":We infected the ants by preparing a solution of the fungus Beauveria bassiana. Afterwards, each ant was dipped in the solution for a couple  of seconds, dried on a cloth and put in the nest. After exposing the  ants to the fungus, we took pictures of each foraging arena three times per day, and counted how many ants were present on each food-source.",":This gave us the data that ants choose more medicine after they have  been infected.",":The result that healthy ants die sooner when ingesting ROS [TEMPLATE[w, Reactive oxygen species, Reactive Oxygen Species], the group of chemicals that includes hydrogen peroxide] but infected ants die less was obtained in another way (as you have to \u0027force feed\u0027 the ROS, as healthy ants, when given the choice, ignore  that food-source.)",":For this we basically put colonies on a diet of either food with medicine or without for a while. And afterwards either infected them  or not. Then for about two weeks we count every day how many ants  died. This gives us the data to do a so-called survival analysis.",":We measured the ROS-concentration in the bodies of ants after they ingested the food with the medicine using a TEMPLATE[w, spectrophotometry, spectrophotometer]. By  adding certain chemicals, the ROS can be measured using the emission of light of a certain wave-length.",":The detrimental effect of ROS on spores was easy to measure. We mixed  different concentrations of ROS with the spores, plated them out on TEMPLATE[w, petri dishes, petridishes] with an TEMPLATE[w, agar plate, agar-solution] where fungus can grow on. A day after, we counted how many spores were still alive.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] How TEMPLATE[w, Reliability (psychometrics), reliable] do you consider your results to be?",":NB The results we got are very reliable. We had a lot of colonies containing a lot of ants, and wherever possible we conducted the experiment blind. This means the experimenter doesn\u0027t know which ants belong to which treatment, so it\u0027s impossible to influence the results  with \u0027TEMPLATE[w, Observer-expectancy effect, observer bias]\u0027. However, of course this is proof in just one  species. It is hard to extrapolate to other ants, as different species  lead very different lives.","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, At the moment it seems that sick ants mostly take care of the problem themselves] TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] Where did the ants and fungus you used come from? How common are they in the wild?",":NB For ants, see above about the collection.",":This species of fungus does appear in Finland, but we chose to use a  different strain from Denmark (with thanks to Prof. J. Eilenberg and  the laboratory technician Louise Lee Munch Larsen from the University  of Copenhagen). Animals can adapt to local strains (\u0027local  adaptation\u0027), and just to make sure we thought it would be good to use  a strain of fungus that the ants definitely did not evolve specific resistances against. This means that the reaction of the ants (to self-medicate) is very likely to be a general response, and not just  against their local fungal enemies.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] Are there any ethical considerations around exposing ants to toxins and parasites?",":NB Legally, no. Insects do not have any \u0027rights\u0027 as such regarding  ethics. That said, we do take measures to not make them \u0027suffer  unnecessarily\u0027. For example, dissections are done when the ants are anesthetized (either by CO2 or Ice), and when ants need to be killed,  we do it in alcohol, which kills the ants in a matter of seconds. So while the ants do not have \u0027rights\u0027 as such, we still try to handle them with as much respect as possible (even though the experiment  involves infecting them with a deadly fungus).",":But even though the 12,000 ants in our study sounds like a lot (and it is), this is negligible in the \u0027grand scheme of things\u0027. It has been  calculated that in the Netherlands alone, nearly a trillion insects die against just the licence-plates of cars every six months. I don\u0027t own a car, so that means I\u0027m excused right? ;)","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] This is the first evidence for self-medicating insects. How widespread do you think this phenomenon could be in reality?",":NB It\u0027s not actually the first evidence for self-medication in insects. Moths and fruit flies definitely do it, and there\u0027s evidence in honey bees and bumble-bees as well. So it seems to be quite wide-spread in  the insect world. I have no doubt that as time goes on, there will be  more and more cases documented. Insects (and animals in general) seem  to be quite good at taking care of themselves.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] How might ants locate healing substances in the wild?",":NB Very good question. This is something that\u0027s important to know. If they would only do it in the lab, the behaviour wouldn\u0027t be very interesting. We have some guesses where they might get it from, but at the moment we don\u0027t know yet. That said, I plan to investigate this  question (among others) further [in] the next couple of years.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] For your PhD you researched ants\u0027 scent-based communications. Could healthy ants perhaps tell other ants are infected and encourage this behaviour?",":NB There\u0027s not much known about this. There\u0027s conflicting evidence about whether sick ants actually smell different from healthy ones or not. At the moment it seems that sick ants mostly take care of the problem themselves. Sick ants stop most interaction with nestmates and especially brood, and leave the nest to die in isolation. This is probably for reducing chance of infecting nestmates, but of course it  also reduces the work load of their nest-mates, as their corpse  doesn\u0027t have to be dragged out etc.",":So as an answer to the question, I would find it unlikely that such a  behaviour would evolve, but it\u0027s not known yet.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] Ants generally avoided the peroxide if they were healthy, but in some circumstances might they try to build resistance against infection in advance?",":NB Who knows? Also not known yet unfortunately. That said, there is a very interesting study about resin collection in ants. TEMPLATE[w, Wood ants] collect tree-resin, which has anti-microbial properties. They collect this even if not infected, and when you infect them, they don\u0027t collect more of the resin than normal. So basically it seems like they  collect it in order to keep diseases out of the nest, so they stop the disease before it can actually infect them.","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] Are there plans to follow this research up? Might you research other species? Other substances?",":NB I first want to find out where they get it from in nature. There might  be many sources of medicine (recent evidence suggests that tobacco  plays a similar role for bumble bees). Dalial Freitak, who is also on this paper is currently running tests with Ph.D. student Siiri Fuchs (who is also on the paper) with other substances to see if any have the same effect as H2O2 [hydrogen peroxide].",":Once the behaviour has been well described in this species of ant, I might do a comparison with other species. For example, once we find the source of the medicine in nature... would species without access to this source also have evolved the same behaviour in the lab? And if so... where would they get it from?",":Also... can ants medicate their friends? :)","TEMPLATE[WNIQ, Wikinews] What other research are you working on right now?",":NB Phew...lots! :)",":I still have some questions left unanswered from my Ph.D. work related to how ants recognize who is a friend and who isn\u0027t. I also started  collaborating with Prof. Michael Poulsen from the University of  Copenhagen on immunity in fungus-growing termites, as well as their  chemical recognition abilities. Furthermore we\u0027re working on social parasitism in wood-ants (ants have lots of animals exploiting the nest for shelter and resources, which all somehow have to get in to the fortress without getting killed).","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay] TEMPLATE[Science_and_technology_-_horizontal]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Entomopathogenic fungus, Zoopharmacognosy]","TEMPLATE[Interview]TEMPLATE[FA]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Biology","description":"Category:Biology"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Finland","description":"Category:Finland"},{"id":"Category:Denmark","description":"Category:Denmark"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Ants","description":"Category:Ants"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 1, 2015"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[commons:User:Leviathan1983","Mathias Krumbholz]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["University of Helsinki"]},{"name":"w","description":["Evolution (journal)","Evolution"]},{"name":"QuoteRight","description":["I have no doubt that as time goes on, there will be more and more cases documented"]},{"name":"w","description":["Formica fusca"]},{"name":"w","description":["honeydew (secretion)","aphid honeydew"]},{"name":"w","description":["Beauveria bassiana"]},{"name":"w","description":["fungus"]},{"name":"w","description":["hydrogen peroxide"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Independent"]},{"name":"w","description":["University of Copenhagen"]},{"name":"w","description":["cicada"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[http://www.mushroomobserver.org/observer/show_user/181 Danny Newman]"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["Wikinews"]},{"name":"w","description":["mantids"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["Wikinews"]},{"name":"w","description":["aerated concrete"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reactive oxygen species","Reactive Oxygen Species"]},{"name":"w","description":["spectrophotometry","spectrophotometer"]},{"name":"w","description":["petri dishes","petridishes"]},{"name":"w","description":["agar plate","agar-solution"]},{"name":"WNIQ","description":["Wikinews"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reliability (psychometrics)","reliable"]},{"name":"w","description":["Observer-expectancy effect","observer bias"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["