{"title":"Study estimates Earth has over three trillion trees","wikiTitle":"Study_estimates_Earth_has_over_three_trillion_trees","wid":2413050,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-10T14:54:48Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-34134366, title\u003dEarth\u0027s trees number \u0027three trillion\u0027, author\u003dJonathan Amos, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/environment/how-many-trees-are-there-on-earth-10483553.html, title\u003dThere are 3 trillion trees on Earth â but they\u0027re disappearing fast, author\u003dDoug Bolton, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dSeptember 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scotsman.com/news/environment/half-of-world-s-trees-wiped-out-by-mankind-1-3876168, title\u003dHalf of worldâs trees wiped out by mankind, author\u003dIlona Amos, pub\u003dThe Scotsman, date\u003dSeptember 2, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nature.com/articles/nature14967.epdf?referrer_access_token\u003d0P3bm4_MRo5dqUlysDi5ydRgN0jAjWel9jnR3ZoTv0PkYJmQ6VQcpxIB4Tt0SaQywsN0n2B7UMpxadfI0w_ofCZWbdodyrsedp3Bty2KGGMCWh8myOn7a26wiJer6LmhdB-jxtrAStb4FxX7zkme5uH5y5cOZl7ggCMW2oe2Dk1ZRU1arE5RQuGJ6EN16Zhy, title\u003dMapping tree density at a global scale, author\u003dCrowther et al, pub\u003dNature, pubtarget\u003dNature (journal), date\u003dSeptember 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Saudi_Arabia","description":"Saudi Arabia"},{"id":"Yale_University","description":"Yale University"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Russia","description":"Russia"},{"id":"North_America","description":"North America"},{"id":"United_Nations","description":"United Nations"},{"id":"BBC","description":"BBC"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources","External link"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 3, 2015] TEMPLATE[Biology] A study published yesterday by TEMPLATE[w, Nature (journal), Nature] estimates the global tree population at just over three trillion. Previous work estimated the total at 400 billion. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, [http://www.flickr.com/people/10345599@N03 Francisco Anzola]] The international research, led by Yale University in the US, used satellite images to examine over 400,000 plots of land for estimated tree density. Subarctic regions of TEMPLATE[w, Scandinavia], Russia, and North America had the highest densities but the largest forested areas were tropical. The study puts 43% of trees in the tropics, where deforestation is particularly common.","The study also claims the number has been cut by human activity from around six trillion 12,000 years ago. Lead researcher Thomas Crowther said \"We have nearly halved the number of trees on the planet, and we have seen the impacts on climate and human health as a result. This study highlights how much more effort is needed if we are to restore healthy forests worldwide.\" Crowther was \"surprised\" to come up with a number as high as the trillions.","The study was made at the request of a United Nations project which wanted an estimate on which to base reforestation targets. As well as numbers and distribution the study looks at what factors might control the density of trees in any given area, such as soil type. The study suggests trees outnumber humans by around 422 to one.","\"It\u0027s not like we\u0027ve discovered a load of new trees; it\u0027s not like we\u0027ve discovered a load of new carbon\", cautioned Crowther, speaking to the BBC. \"So, it\u0027s not good news for the world or bad news that we\u0027ve produced this new number.\" He says the estimate is valuable for lawmakers, academics, and the general public.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:World","description":"Category:World"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Environment","description":"Category:Environment"},{"id":"Category:Biology","description":"Category:Biology"},{"id":"Category:Yale_University","description":"Category:Yale University"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:United_Nations","description":"Category:United Nations"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 3, 2015"]},{"name":"Biology","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Nature (journal)","Nature"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["[http://www.flickr.com/people/10345599@N03 Francisco Anzola]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Scandinavia"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/science-environment-34134366","title\u003dEarth\u0027s trees number \u0027three trillion\u0027","author\u003dJonathan Amos","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dSeptember 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/environment/how-many-trees-are-there-on-earth-10483553.html","title\u003dThere are 3 trillion trees on Earth â but they\u0027re disappearing fast","author\u003dDoug Bolton","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dSeptember 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.scotsman.com/news/environment/half-of-world-s-trees-wiped-out-by-mankind-1-3876168","title\u003dHalf of worldâs trees wiped out by mankind","author\u003dIlona Amos","pub\u003dThe Scotsman","date\u003dSeptember 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nature.com/articles/nature14967.epdf?referrer_access_token\u003d0P3bm4_MRo5dqUlysDi5ydRgN0jAjWel9jnR3ZoTv0PkYJmQ6VQcpxIB4Tt0SaQywsN0n2B7UMpxadfI0w_ofCZWbdodyrsedp3Bty2KGGMCWh8myOn7a26wiJer6LmhdB-jxtrAStb4FxX7zkme5uH5y5cOZl7ggCMW2oe2Dk1ZRU1arE5RQuGJ6EN16Zhy","title\u003dMapping tree density at a global scale","author\u003dCrowther et al","pub\u003dNature","pubtarget\u003dNature (journal)","date\u003dSeptember 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","pubtarget","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Nature (journal), Nature]"]}
{"title":"Dutch sergeant may have gone to Syria to join ISIS, says Dutch Defence Ministry","wikiTitle":"Dutch_sergeant_may_have_gone_to_Syria_to_join_ISIS,_says_Dutch_Defence_Ministry","wid":2414520,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-01T23:55:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/09/03/middleeast/isis-dutch-airman/index.html, title\u003dDutch defense ministry: Airman likely left to join ISIS, author\u003dSteve Almasy, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dSeptember 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://news.yahoo.com/dutch-soldier-said-joined-islamic-militants-211727337.html, title\u003dDutch soldier said to have joined Islamic militants, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dYahoo! News, date\u003dSeptember 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.un.org/press/en/2013/sc11019.doc.htm, title\u003dSecurity Council Al-Qaida Sanctions Committee Amends Entry of One Entity on Its Sanctions List, author\u003d[[UN Security Council, Security Council]], pub\u003dUnited Nations, date\u003d May 30, 2013]"]],"links":[{"id":"Netherlands","description":"Dutch"},{"id":"Syria","description":"Syria"},{"id":"Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_Syria","description":"ISIS"},{"id":"United_Nations","description":"United Nations"},{"id":"Al-Qaida","description":"Al-Qaida"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[Syria] Yesterday the Dutch Defence Ministry said a Dutch sergeant, whose identity was not disclosed, may have gone to Syria from the Netherlands because he wanted to join extremist militant group ISIS. Prosecutors are investigating the sergeant. TEMPLATE[image, (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, US Department of Defense] Jeanie Hennis Plasschaer, Dutch Defence Minister, called the act of leaving one\u0027s country to join ISIS \"irresponsible\" and \"punishable\". \"Every case of radicalisation is one too many. It is disappointing if it appears that someone joins evil while colleagues risk their lives for the freedom of another.\"","The United Nations has imposed sanctions on ISIS under a resolution covering people and organisations associated with Al-Qaida.","The United States leads an international coalition against ISIS. The Netherlands, which has agreed to send six fighter jets to fight ISIS, is a part of the coalition.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Sunni_Islam","description":"Category:Sunni Islam"},{"id":"Category:Islam","description":"Category:Islam"},{"id":"Category:Syria","description":"Category:Syria"},{"id":"Category:Netherlands","description":"Category:Netherlands"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Syrian_Civil_War","description":"Category:Syrian Civil War"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Syria","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["(TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Department of Defense"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/09/03/middleeast/isis-dutch-airman/index.html","title\u003dDutch defense ministry: Airman likely left to join ISIS","author\u003dSteve Almasy","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dSeptember 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://news.yahoo.com/dutch-soldier-said-joined-islamic-militants-211727337.html","title\u003dDutch soldier said to have joined Islamic militants","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dYahoo! News","date\u003dSeptember 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.un.org/press/en/2013/sc11019.doc.htm","title\u003dSecurity Council Al-Qaida Sanctions Committee Amends Entry of One Entity on Its Sanctions List","author\u003d[[UN Security Council","Security Council]]","pub\u003dUnited Nations","date\u003d May 30, 2013"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"US adds 173,000 jobs in August; unemployment rate drops to seven year low","wikiTitle":"US_adds_173,000_jobs_in_August;_unemployment_rate_drops_to_seven_year_low","wid":2416425,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-01-20T03:55:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dUS economy adds 215,000 jobs in July; unemployment rate remains steady at 5.3%, date\u003dAugust 10, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bls.gov/news.release/empsit.nr0.htm, title\u003dEmployment Situation Summary, author\u003d, pub\u003dBureau of Labor Statistics, date\u003d4 September 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/employment-report-u-s-added-173k-jobs-in-august/, title\u003dEmployment report: U.S. added 173K jobs in August, author\u003dAssociated Press, pub\u003dCBS News, date\u003d4 September 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/09/04/us-usa-economy-idUSKCN0R40CT20150904, title\u003dU.S. labor market shows some muscle despite slower job growth, author\u003dLucia Mutikani, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003d4 September 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-09-04/drop-in-u-s-stock-futures-signals-anxiety-over-payrolls-report, title\u003dU.S. Stocks Decline as Jobs Report Brings Little Clarity on Fed, author\u003dOliver Renick and Anna-Louise Jackson, pub\u003dBloomberg, date\u003d4 September 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://fivethirtyeight.com/datalab/jobs-report-august-2015/, title\u003dAbout That âGame-Changingâ Jobs Report, author\u003dBen Casselman, pub\u003dFiveThirtyEight, date\u003d4 September 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://data.bls.gov/timeseries/CES3000000001, title\u003dEmployment, Hours, and Earnings from the Current Employment Statistics survey (National), author\u003d, pub\u003dBureau of Labor Statistics, date\u003d4 September 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"New_Jersey","description":"New Jersey"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[Economy_and_business] TEMPLATE[image_credit, Bureau of Labor Statistics] The US economy added 173,000 jobs in August, the TEMPLATE[w, Bureau of Labor Statistics] reported on Friday. The unemployment rate fell from 5.3 to 5.1 percent, the lowest since April 2008.","Although August job gains were lower than most economists forecast, job growth numbers for June and July were revised upwards by a combined 44,000. Average job gains over the past three months stand at 221,000, compared to March-May\u0027s 189,000 monthly average. Over the past twelve months, job growth has averaged 247,000 per month.","Average hourly earnings rose 0.3 percent, or 8 cents, marking the largest increase in earnings in seven months. Hourly earnings had risen by 6 cents in July. Wages have risen by 2.2 percent over the past year.","Job growth in August was primarily concentrated in the health care and social assistance, financial activities, and professional and business services sectors. Those three areas of the economy added a combined 108,000 jobs. Food service and drinking places employment increased by 26,000 over the month, and other economic sectors saw employment hold steady. Manufacturing, on the other hand, saw employment decline by 17,000 in August. A stronger TEMPLATE[w, United States dollar, dollar] and worldwide economic weakness make US exports less desirable, leading to a flattening in manufacturing employment so far this year after steadily rising in the early years of the US economic recovery.","The solid overall job gains led analysts to slightly raise expectations for a decision by the TEMPLATE[w, Federal Reserve] to raise interest rates this month. Investors raised the likelihood of a September rate increase from 26 percent before the jobs report to 30 percent, and stocks dropped by over one percent on Friday. \"The payrolls data is certainly good enough to allow for a Fed rate hike in September,\" said TEMPLATE[w, Deutsche Bank]\u0027s head of currency strategy, Alan Ruskin. \"The big question is still whether financial market volatility will scupper the plans.\"","\"This is the first time the market has looked at a Fed meeting and really has no idea what the Fed is going to do,\" said Mark Kepner, a New Jersey TEMPLATE[w, equity trader] with Themis Trading. \"Right now you\u0027re looking at the overall uncertainty and that\u0027s what\u0027s hanging on the market. I don\u0027t think this number in and of itself changes how somebody\u0027s going to vote.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Economy_and_business","description":"Category:Economy and business"},{"id":"Category:Labor","description":"Category:Labor"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Economy_and_business","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Bureau of Labor Statistics"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bureau of Labor Statistics"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States dollar","dollar"]},{"name":"w","description":["Federal Reserve"]},{"name":"w","description":["Deutsche Bank"]},{"name":"w","description":["equity trader"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dUS economy adds 215,000 jobs in July; unemployment rate remains steady at 5.3%","date\u003dAugust 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bls.gov/news.release/empsit.nr0.htm","title\u003dEmployment Situation Summary","author\u003d","pub\u003dBureau of Labor Statistics","date\u003d4 September 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbsnews.com/news/employment-report-u-s-added-173k-jobs-in-august/","title\u003dEmployment report: U.S. added 173K jobs in August","author\u003dAssociated Press","pub\u003dCBS News","date\u003d4 September 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/09/04/us-usa-economy-idUSKCN0R40CT20150904","title\u003dU.S. labor market shows some muscle despite slower job growth","author\u003dLucia Mutikani","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003d4 September 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2015-09-04/drop-in-u-s-stock-futures-signals-anxiety-over-payrolls-report","title\u003dU.S. Stocks Decline as Jobs Report Brings Little Clarity on Fed","author\u003dOliver Renick and Anna-Louise Jackson","pub\u003dBloomberg","date\u003d4 September 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://fivethirtyeight.com/datalab/jobs-report-august-2015/","title\u003dAbout That âGame-Changingâ Jobs Report","author\u003dBen Casselman","pub\u003dFiveThirtyEight","date\u003d4 September 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://data.bls.gov/timeseries/CES3000000001","title\u003dEmployment, Hours, and Earnings from the Current Employment Statistics survey (National)","author\u003d","pub\u003dBureau of Labor Statistics","date\u003d4 September 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Rwandan Supreme Court agrees to hear case on allowing third presidential term","wikiTitle":"Rwandan_Supreme_Court_agrees_to_hear_case_on_allowing_third_presidential_term","wid":2426493,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-18T14:44:04Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFKCN0R915V20150909?sp\u003dtrue, title\u003dRwanda court agrees to hear case to block president\u0027s third term, author\u003dClement Uwiringiyimana, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/09/rwanda-court-hear-case-president-term-150909104940132.html, title\u003dRwanda court to hear case on president\u0027s third term, author\u003d, pub\u003dAl-Jazeera, date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Rwanda","description":"Rwanda"},{"id":"Paul_Kagame","description":"Paul Kagame"},{"id":"Burundi","description":"Burundi"},{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"al-Jazeera","description":"al-Jazeera"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[Rwanda] The Rwandan TEMPLATE[w, Supreme Court of Rwanda, Supreme Court] today agreed to hear a case opposing a TEMPLATE[w, Rwandan Constitution, constitutional] amendment allowing President Paul Kagame to run for a third term. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:ÐÐµÐ½Ð¸ ÐÐ°ÑÐºÐ¾Ð²ÑÐºÐ¸, Veni Markovski]]] The government attorney had asked the court to throw the case, brought by the opposition TEMPLATE[w, Democratic Green Party], out. An eight-judge panel rejected that move. Kagame has grown popular at home and abroad following TEMPLATE[w, Rwandan genocide, post-genocide] reconstruction but the constitution does not allow a third term.","TEMPLATE[w, Rwandan Parliament, Parliament] voted to lift a limit of two seven-year terms after a petition for Kagame to stay garnered 3.8 million signatures. A referendum on constitutional change is required.  Neighbouring Burundi saw widespread unrest and ongoing political turmoil after a disputed election saw President TEMPLATE[w, Pierre Nkurunziza] gain a third term.","The move by the TEMPLATE[w, Rwandan Patriotic Front] has cooled Kagame\u0027s support abroad. Allies including major donor the United States expressed reservations on a third term in Rwanda. Rwanda and Burundi are just two nations of several in the region grappling with constitutional change to increase presidential term limits.","Kagame is yet to publicly decide on running again but has confirmed he is open to the idea of the constitutional amendment. \"There\u0027s international pressure for him not to do this\" MP TEMPLATE[w, Julianna Kantengwa] told al-Jazeera. \"Then there\u0027s pressure from Rwandans for him to run. Who should he listen to? I think the answer is obvious\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Rwanda","description":"Category:Rwanda"},{"id":"Category:Burundi","description":"Category:Burundi"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Al-Jazeera","description":"Category:Al-Jazeera"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Paul_Kagame","description":"Category:Paul Kagame"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Rwanda","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Supreme Court of Rwanda","Supreme Court"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rwandan Constitution","constitutional"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:ÐÐµÐ½Ð¸ ÐÐ°ÑÐºÐ¾Ð²ÑÐºÐ¸","Veni Markovski]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Democratic Green Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rwandan genocide","post-genocide"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rwandan Parliament","Parliament"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pierre Nkurunziza"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rwandan Patriotic Front"]},{"name":"w","description":["Julianna Kantengwa"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://af.reuters.com/article/topNews/idAFKCN0R915V20150909?sp\u003dtrue","title\u003dRwanda court agrees to hear case to block president\u0027s third term","author\u003dClement Uwiringiyimana","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/09/rwanda-court-hear-case-president-term-150909104940132.html","title\u003dRwanda court to hear case on president\u0027s third term","author\u003d","pub\u003dAl-Jazeera","date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["al-Jazeera"]}
{"title":"Investigators blame pilot error for deadly jet crash near Boston","wikiTitle":"Investigators_blame_pilot_error_for_deadly_jet_crash_near_Boston","wid":2427869,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-15T01:46:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/09/09/ntsb-bedford-crash-gulfstream-philadelphia-inquirer-lewis-katz/71922242/, title\u003dNTSB: Pilots left flaps locked in place in Gulfstream crash that killed 7, author\u003dBart Jansen, pub\u003dUSA Today, date\u003dSeptember 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/ntsb-crew-neglected-pre-flight-check-crash-killed-33627555, title\u003dNTSB: Crew Neglected Pre-Flight Check in Crash That Killed 7, author\u003dMark Pratt ([[Associated Press, AP]]), pub\u003dABC News (United States), date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.pressofatlanticcity.com/business/ntsb-pilots-skipped-safety-steps-in-crash-that-killed-longport/article_840447ba-5737-11e5-8747-2b903131d829.html, title\u003dPilots skipped safety steps in crash that killed Longport\u0027s Katz, Leeds, author\u003dMartin DeAngelis, pub\u003dThe Press of Atlantic City, date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ntsb.gov/news/press-releases/Pages/PR20150909.aspx, title\u003d Series of Errors by Flight Crew Caused Fatal Business Jet Crash, NTSB Says, author\u003dPress Release, pub\u003dNational Transportation Safety Board, date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"National Transportation Safety Board"},{"id":"Boston","description":"Boston"},{"id":"Massachusetts","description":"Massachusetts"},{"id":"Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Federal Aviation Administration"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 10, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] The US federal National Transportation Safety Board (NTSB) yesterday concluded a \"series of errors\" by flight crew caused a TEMPLATE[w, business jet] crash near Boston, Massachusetts last year. Seven were killed when the TEMPLATE[w, Gulfstream IV] overran a runway. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, I can\u0027t stop it, 4\u003dPilot de Vries, seconds from impact] The NTSB found the pilots failed to conduct preflight checks, mistakenly took off with flight control systems locked in position, and then failed to abort takeoff until too late. Manufacturer TEMPLATE[w, Gulfstream] was criticised for an inadequate safety system; the US Federal Aviation Administration (FAA) was accused of failing to properly check the system before certifying the aircraft.","On the evening of May 31 the passengers and crew were returning from TEMPLATE[w, Hanscom Field] to TEMPLATE[w, Atlanta International Airport]. Pilot Bauke \"Mike\" de Vries and co-pilot James McDowell each had thousands of hours\u0027 experience, and had flown together for years. They skipped over preflight checks; the NTSB found this was routine for the pair.","The plane set off with the TEMPLATE[w, gust lock] engaged. This system, which is intended to be disconnected before engine startup, locks various TEMPLATE[w, flight control surfaces] in position on the ground. Unable to takeoff, it overshot the runway, crashing through airport equipment and a fence, before landing in a watery ravine and bursting into flames. Nobody survived. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[US]] (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration] De Vries says several times \"lock is on\" on the TEMPLATE[w, cockpit voice recorder, voice recording], adding \"I can\u0027t stop it\" moments before the crash. Gulfstream had installed a mechanism to prevent the throttle fully moving when gust lock was engaged, to give pilots a clear early warning something was amiss.","The NTSB found the throttle could still be pushed far enough to reach takeoff speed. The FAA had certified the system based on technical drawings. The NTSB said the FAA process was \"inadequate\" because there were no \"engineering certification tests or analysis[...] to verify that the system had met its regulatory requirements.\" Gulfstream say they are working with the FAA to rectify the issue.","The NTSB says it took ten seconds from noticing the problem before the crew began braking and another four seconds to power down the engines. The NTSB believes doing both within eleven seconds would have brought the flight to a halt on the runway.","The lock was applied upon landing six hours earlier. The flight was carrying four passengers, including entrepreneur and philanthropist TEMPLATE[w, Lewis Katz], back from a fundraiser. The seventh fatality was a flight attendant. Katz had co-engineered an TEMPLATE[w, united States dollar, $]88 million takeover deal for the TEMPLATE[w, Philadelphia Inquirer] four days earlier.","The Katz family later sold his stake in the paper to a business partner. Katz had hoped to boost the paper\u0027s reputation.","\"Complacency does not have a place in the cockpit of any aircraft\", NTSB Vice Chairman Bella Dinh-Zarr said. The probe found skipped checks on 98% of the prior 175 flights the pilots undertook together. \"If you\u0027re acting that way, you are just fooling yourself,\" said NTSB member Robert Sumwalt, who has 32 years of commercial flight experience. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Massachusetts","description":"Category:Massachusetts"},{"id":"Category:Boston,_Massachusetts","description":"Category:Boston, Massachusetts"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:National_Transportation_Safety_Board","description":"Category:National Transportation Safety Board"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Aviation_Administration","description":"Category:Federal Aviation Administration"},{"id":"Category:Journalism","description":"Category:Journalism"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Philadelphia_Inquirer","description":"Category:Philadelphia Inquirer"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["business jet"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gulfstream IV"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["I can\u0027t stop it","4\u003dPilot de Vries, seconds from impact"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gulfstream"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hanscom Field"]},{"name":"w","description":["Atlanta International Airport"]},{"name":"w","description":["gust lock"]},{"name":"w","description":["flight control surfaces"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[US]] (TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Oceanic and Atmospheric Administration"]},{"name":"w","description":["cockpit voice recorder","voice recording"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lewis Katz"]},{"name":"w","description":["united States dollar","$"]},{"name":"w","description":["Philadelphia Inquirer"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.usatoday.com/story/news/2015/09/09/ntsb-bedford-crash-gulfstream-philadelphia-inquirer-lewis-katz/71922242/","title\u003dNTSB: Pilots left flaps locked in place in Gulfstream crash that killed 7","author\u003dBart Jansen","pub\u003dUSA Today","date\u003dSeptember 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/wireStory/ntsb-crew-neglected-pre-flight-check-crash-killed-33627555","title\u003dNTSB: Crew Neglected Pre-Flight Check in Crash That Killed 7","author\u003dMark Pratt ([[Associated Press","AP]])","pub\u003dABC News (United States)","date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.pressofatlanticcity.com/business/ntsb-pilots-skipped-safety-steps-in-crash-that-killed-longport/article_840447ba-5737-11e5-8747-2b903131d829.html","title\u003dPilots skipped safety steps in crash that killed Longport\u0027s Katz, Leeds","author\u003dMartin DeAngelis","pub\u003dThe Press of Atlantic City","date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ntsb.gov/news/press-releases/Pages/PR20150909.aspx","title\u003d Series of Errors by Flight Crew Caused Fatal Business Jet Crash, NTSB Says","author\u003dPress Release","pub\u003dNational Transportation Safety Board","date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Philadelphia Inquirer]"]}
{"title":"Typhoon Etau causes more leakage at Fukushima","wikiTitle":"Typhoon_Etau_causes_more_leakage_at_Fukushima","wid":2429916,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-24T12:31:16Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPower outage at Fukushima poses radioactive risk, date\u003dApril 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dExplosion at earthquake-damaged Fukushima nuclear power plant, date\u003dMarch 12, 2011]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-34217327, title\u003dJapan floods: Rescue work continues amid deadly floods, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News, date\u003dSeptember 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.efe.com/efe/english/world/contaminated-water-from-fukushima-leaks-into-sea-due-to-typhoon-etau/50000262-2708892, title\u003dContaminated water from Fukushima leaks into sea due to typhoon Etau, author\u003d, pub\u003dAgencia EFE, S.A., pubtarget\u003dEFE, date\u003dSeptember 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/10/japan-floods-spark-evacuations-of-thousands-from-towns, title\u003dTyphoon Etau: thousands evacuated as severe flooding hits Japan, author\u003dJustin McCurry, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Fukushima_Daiichi_Nuclear_Power_Plant","description":"Fukushima nuclear plant"},{"id":"Japan","description":"Japan"},{"id":"TEPCO","description":"TEPCO"},{"id":"earthquake","description":"earthquake"},{"id":"tsunami","description":"tsunami"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Japan] TEMPLATE[image_credit, Digital Globe] TEMPLATE[date, September 11, 2015] Radioactive water has been leaking from the damaged Fukushima nuclear plant following damage caused by TEMPLATE[w, Tropical Storm Etau (2015), Typhoon Etau]. The plant\u0027s drainage system has been inundated by a surge of sea water brought in by the typhoon, which reached Japan on Wednesday. A spokesperson for TEPCO, the company that runs the plant, yesterday said they were investigating the leaked water but it did not present a significant danger.","This comes after authorities in eastern Japan ordered over 100,000 people to leave the area as a precautionary measure as the typhoon proceeded to flood the town of TEMPLATE[w, Joso]. Up to 25 people are still missing and at least three are dead as a consequence of the flooding. Hundreds of thousands more people in the region have been encouraged to evacuate as well. Rescue efforts are being hampered by the floods, with some people being plucked from roofs and cars by teams in helicopters.","The Fukushima nuclear plant was damaged after a huge earthquake and tsunami in March 2011. As recently as April this year there were concerns about leakages as a result of electrical problems with water pumps that caused contaminated water to escape into the TEMPLATE[w, Pacific Ocean]. A large volume of water used as part of the cooling mechanism before the reactors were damaged has since been stored in numerous steel drums.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Fukushima_Daiichi_Nuclear_Power_Plant","description":"Category:Fukushima Daiichi Nuclear Power Plant"},{"id":"Category:Fukushima_Prefecture","description":"Category:Fukushima Prefecture"},{"id":"Category:Nuclear_accidents","description":"Category:Nuclear accidents"},{"id":"Category:Nuclear_power","description":"Category:Nuclear power"},{"id":"Category:Tokyo_Electric_Power_Company","description":"Category:Tokyo Electric Power Company"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Nuclear_technology","description":"Category:Nuclear technology"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Weather","description":"Category:Weather"},{"id":"Category:Tropical_cyclones","description":"Category:Tropical cyclones"},{"id":"Category:Japan","description":"Category:Japan"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"}],"templates":[{"name":"Japan","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Digital Globe"]},{"name":"date","description":["September 11, 2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tropical Storm Etau (2015)","Typhoon Etau"]},{"name":"w","description":["Joso"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pacific Ocean"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPower outage at Fukushima poses radioactive risk","date\u003dApril 24, 2015"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dExplosion at earthquake-damaged Fukushima nuclear power plant","date\u003dMarch 12, 2011"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-34217327","title\u003dJapan floods: Rescue work continues amid deadly floods","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News","date\u003dSeptember 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.efe.com/efe/english/world/contaminated-water-from-fukushima-leaks-into-sea-due-to-typhoon-etau/50000262-2708892","title\u003dContaminated water from Fukushima leaks into sea due to typhoon Etau","author\u003d","pub\u003dAgencia EFE, S.A.","pubtarget\u003dEFE","date\u003dSeptember 10, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/10/japan-floods-spark-evacuations-of-thousands-from-towns","title\u003dTyphoon Etau: thousands evacuated as severe flooding hits Japan","author\u003dJustin McCurry","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dSeptember 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","pubtarget","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Australian Liberal party change leader, Prime Minister: Turnbull replaces Abbott","wikiTitle":"Australian_Liberal_party_change_leader,_Prime_Minister:_Turnbull_replaces_Abbott","wid":2436308,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-25T03:55:16Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Source, url\u003dhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dspcILZnxavQ, title\u003dIn Full: Malcolm Turnbull to challenge Tony Abbott, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/finance/work/malcolm-turnbull-wins-liberal-leadership/story-fn5tas5k-1227527262266, title\u003dMalcolm Turnbull wins Liberal leadership, author\u003dMalcolm Farr and James Law, pub\u003dNews.com.au, date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://theconversation.com/turnbull-defeats-abbott-set-to-become-prime-minister-experts-respond-47499, title\u003dTurnbull defeats Abbott, set to become prime minister: experts respond, author\u003dNatalie Mast, Flavio Menezes, Todd Winther and Zareh Ghazarian, pub\u003dThe Conversation (website), date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Source, url\u003dhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dW5q8isyVjNs\u0026feature\u003dyoutu.be, title\u003d\nMalcolm Turnbull, Julie Bishop speak after winning leadership ballot, author\u003d, pub\u003dABC News (Australia), date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Malcolm_Turnbull","description":"Malcolm Turnbull"},{"id":"Tony_Abbott","description":"Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Monash_University","description":"Monash University"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 14, 2015] TEMPLATE[Australia] TEMPLATE[image, Eva Rinaldi]  The federal party room of the TEMPLATE[w, Liberal Party of Australia] has voted to change its leader this evening local time (TEMPLATE[w, UTC+10]). Malcolm Turnbull has been elected over incumbent Prime Minister Tony Abbott 54 votes to 44.","\"This has been a very important sobering event\", Turnbull told the media an hour after the ballot. Turnbull had requested a leadership ballot at about 4:30pm. The meeting, in which the ballot was held, started about 9:15pm with the announcement of the result at about 9:55pm.","\"Malcolm Turnbull has been like the TEMPLATE[w, Damocles, sword of Damocles] hanging over Tony Abbott\u0027s head ever since he was defeated by Abbott in the leadership ballot in 2009 by just one vote\", Zareh Ghazarian, Social Sciences Lecturer at Monash University, wrote in reaction to the result. \"Tonight the two Liberal Party heavyweights faced off again and Turnbull exacted revenge.\"","The leadership spill came just under a week before the TEMPLATE[w, Canning by-election, 2015, Canning by-election].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[broadcast_report]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Malcolm_Turnbull","description":"Category:Malcolm Turnbull"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Abbott","description":"Category:Tony Abbott"},{"id":"Category:Monash_University","description":"Category:Monash University"},{"id":"Category:Liberal_Party_(Australia)","description":"Category:Liberal Party (Australia)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Australia","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Eva Rinaldi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Liberal Party of Australia"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+10"]},{"name":"w","description":["Damocles","sword of Damocles"]},{"name":"w","description":["Canning by-election, 2015","Canning by-election"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dspcILZnxavQ","title\u003dIn Full: Malcolm Turnbull to challenge Tony Abbott","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news.com.au/finance/work/malcolm-turnbull-wins-liberal-leadership/story-fn5tas5k-1227527262266","title\u003dMalcolm Turnbull wins Liberal leadership","author\u003dMalcolm Farr and James Law","pub\u003dNews.com.au","date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://theconversation.com/turnbull-defeats-abbott-set-to-become-prime-minister-experts-respond-47499","title\u003dTurnbull defeats Abbott, set to become prime minister: experts respond","author\u003dNatalie Mast, Flavio Menezes, Todd Winther and Zareh Ghazarian","pub\u003dThe Conversation (website)","date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015"]},{"name":"Source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dW5q8isyVjNs\u0026feature\u003dyoutu.be","title\u003d\nMalcolm Turnbull, Julie Bishop speak after winning leadership ballot","author\u003d","pub\u003dABC News (Australia)","date\u003dSeptember 14, 2015"]},{"name":"broadcast_report","description":[]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Kuwaiti court sentences seven to death for June mosque bombing","wikiTitle":"Kuwaiti_court_sentences_seven_to_death_for_June_mosque_bombing","wid":2441108,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-25T04:37:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scotsman.com/news/world/7-sentenced-to-death-over-is-bomb-at-kuwait-mosque-1-3887460, title\u003d7 sentenced to death over IS bomb at Kuwait mosque, author\u003dHussain al-Qatari, pub\u003dThe Scotsman, date\u003dSeptember 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/15/kuwait-sentences-seven-men-to-death-for-shia-mosque-bombing, title\u003dKuwait sentences seven men to death for Shia mosque bombing, author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse, AFP]], pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://thehimalayantimes.com/world/seven-sentenced-to-death-over-kuwaiti-mosque-bombing/, title\u003dSeven sentenced to death over Kuwaiti mosque bombing, author\u003d[[Reuters]], pub\u003dThe Himalayan Times, date\u003dSeptember 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2015/09/kuwait-overturn-death-sentences-in-mosque-bombing-case/, title\u003dKuwait: Overturn death sentences in mosque bombing case, author\u003d, pub\u003dAmnesty International, date\u003dSeptember 15, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Kuwait","description":"Kuwait"},{"id":"Kuwait_City","description":"Kuwait City"},{"id":"Sunni_Islam","description":"Sunni"},{"id":"Islamic_State","description":"Islamic State"},{"id":"Shia_Islam","description":"Shi\u0027ites"},{"id":"Ramadan","description":"Ramadan"},{"id":"Iraq","description":"Iraq"},{"id":"Syria","description":"Syria"},{"id":"Saudi_Arabia","description":"Saudi"},{"id":"Pakistan","description":"Pakistan"},{"id":"Amnesty_International","description":"Amnesty International"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister link","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 16, 2015] TEMPLATE[Kuwait] TEMPLATE[missing_image, File:12306354.jpg, thumb, left, 200px, A file photo of the mosque.(TEMPLATE)] A court in Kuwait yesterday sentenced fifteen people for involvement in June\u0027s bombing of the Imam Sadiq Mosque. Seven were sentenced to death.","The suicide attack in Kuwait City killed 26 and injured 227. The trial of seven women and 22 men before Judge Mohammad al-Duaij produced fourteen acquittals. All those sentenced to death were men; prison terms from two to fifteen years were imposed on the remaining convicts. A number were tried TEMPLATE[w, trial in absentia, in absentia].","Sunni militants Islamic State (IS) claimed responsibility for the attack. IS view Shi\u0027ites as enemies. Conducted in the Shi\u0027ite mosque during Friday prayers, the attack came during Ramadan. IS hold a large swathe of Iraq and Syria. Sunnis and Shi\u0027ites live together peacefully in Kuwait. It was amongst the worst attacks to hit the nation in decades.","The accused include Kuwaiti, Saudi, and Pakistani citizens, as well as stateless individuals. Abdul Rahman Sabah Saud, stateless, admitted driving bomber Fahad Suleiman Abdulmohsen al-Gabbaa, Saudi, to the mosque. Saud, also accused of handling explosives, denied intending to harm any people.  TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, The court draws attention to the dangers of this extremist ideology, 4\u003dJudge Mohammad al-Duaij] Judge al-Duaij found Fahad Farraj Muhareb to be an IS leader and sentenced him to death. Muhareb and Saud are in Kuwaiti custody. Saudi brothers Mohammad and Majed al-Zahrani, who have been detained in their homeland but were tried in absentia, were held to have transported the explosives used out of Saudi Arabia. Two stateless men convicted of being IS soldiers and a man whose identity is unclear were also sentenced to death in their absence.","Of the eight given prison terms, three were men and five women. They were convicted of offences such as assisting the attack, training IS fighters, and withholding knowledge about the bombing. The death row convicts faced more serious charges such as premeditated murder.","Appeals are possible. The prosecution had sought death sentences for eleven defendents.","Amnesty International acknowledged the bombing was \"an utterly heinous and callous criminal act\" but said the death sentences are \"misguided\" and \"must be overturned\". The group, which is categorically opposed to the death penalty, said Kuwait conducted five executions in 2013 and none at all last year.","Judge al-Duaij said in delivering his judgement \"The court draws attention to the dangers of this extremist ideology that resorts to terrorism for its implementation.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, 2015 Kuwait mosque bombing]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Kuwait","description":"Category:Kuwait"},{"id":"Category:Saudi_Arabia","description":"Category:Saudi Arabia"},{"id":"Category:Pakistan","description":"Category:Pakistan"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Islam","description":"Category:Islam"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Sunni_Islam","description":"Category:Sunni Islam"},{"id":"Category:Shia_Islam","description":"Category:Shia Islam"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"},{"id":"Category:Amnesty_International","description":"Category:Amnesty International"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Ramadan","description":"Category:Ramadan"},{"id":"Category:Kuwait_City","description":"Category:Kuwait City"},{"id":"Category:Trial_in_absentia","description":"Category:Trial in absentia"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Kuwait","description":[]},{"name":"missing_image","description":["File:12306354.jpg","thumb","left","200px","A file photo of the mosque.(TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[w:ar:User:Abza","Abza]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["trial in absentia","in absentia"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["The court draws attention to the dangers of this extremist ideology","4\u003dJudge Mohammad al-Duaij"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["2015 Kuwait mosque bombing"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.scotsman.com/news/world/7-sentenced-to-death-over-is-bomb-at-kuwait-mosque-1-3887460","title\u003d7 sentenced to death over IS bomb at Kuwait mosque","author\u003dHussain al-Qatari","pub\u003dThe Scotsman","date\u003dSeptember 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/15/kuwait-sentences-seven-men-to-death-for-shia-mosque-bombing","title\u003dKuwait sentences seven men to death for Shia mosque bombing","author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse","AFP]]","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dSeptember 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://thehimalayantimes.com/world/seven-sentenced-to-death-over-kuwaiti-mosque-bombing/","title\u003dSeven sentenced to death over Kuwaiti mosque bombing","author\u003d[[Reuters]]","pub\u003dThe Himalayan Times","date\u003dSeptember 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.amnesty.org/en/latest/news/2015/09/kuwait-overturn-death-sentences-in-mosque-bombing-case/","title\u003dKuwait: Overturn death sentences in mosque bombing case","author\u003d","pub\u003dAmnesty International","date\u003dSeptember 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, trial in absentia, in absentia]","in absentia"]}
{"title":"Subway sandwich empire co-founder Fred DeLuca dies","wikiTitle":"Subway_sandwich_empire_co-founder_Fred_DeLuca_dies","wid":2441316,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-27T19:52:37Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.abqjournal.com/644970/news/subway-cofounder-dies-of-cancer-at-67.html, title\u003dSubway co-founder dies of cancer at 67, author\u003dCandice Choi ([[The Associated Press, AP]]), pub\u003dThe Albuquerque Journal, date\u003dSeptember 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/business/subway-co-founder-deluca/2129172.html, title\u003dSubway co-founder DeLuca dies after battling leukemia, author\u003d[[Reuters]], pub\u003dChannel NewsAsia, date\u003dSeptember 16, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"cancer","description":"cancer"},{"id":"Edinburgh","description":"Edinburgh"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scotland"},{"id":"Connecticut","description":"Connecticut"},{"id":"child_pornography","description":"child pornography"},{"id":"Bronx","description":"The Bronx"},{"id":"New_York_City","description":"New York City"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 16, 2015] TEMPLATE[obituaries] Fifty years after starting his first sandwich shop as a teenager, TEMPLATE[w, Subway (restaurant), Subway] CEO and co-founder TEMPLATE[w, Fred DeLuca] died on Monday. He was 67 and suffering from cancer. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [http://www.geograph.org.uk/profile/23411 Ian Thomson]] Subway yesterday announced his death, but not the location. He had developed TEMPLATE[w, leukaemia], which the company announced in 2013. The business was founded with friend Peter Buck who lent DeLuca TEMPLATE[w, United States dollar, $]1,000 to open Pete\u0027s Super Submarines in TEMPLATE[w, Bridgeport, Connecticut, Bridgeport], Connecticut. The company remains based in the state.","By 1968 the business was renamed Subway and the two young entrepreneurs began looking at franchising as a method of expansion. It worked: With over 44,000 locations Subway is the world\u0027s largest fast food franchise. The company has locations in 110 countries.","Subway brands itself as a healthy alternative on the fast food market. It has faced various controversies: ingredients, contracts with franchisees, and longtime advertiser Jared Fogle have all come under scrutiny. Fogle left the company this year after admitting underage sex and child pornography offences.","\"I knew nothing about making sandwiches, nor the food industry,\" DeLuca would later write of his 1965 startup. Growing up he lived in state-owned housing in The Bronx, New York City. Forbes estimated his 2015 wealth at around $3.5 billion.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Economy_and_business","description":"Category:Economy and business"},{"id":"Category:Food","description":"Category:Food"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:World_records","description":"Category:World records"},{"id":"Category:Connecticut","description":"Category:Connecticut"},{"id":"Category:New_York,_New_York","description":"Category:New York, New York"},{"id":"Category:Bronx","description":"Category:Bronx"},{"id":"Category:New_York","description":"Category:New York"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 16, 2015"]},{"name":"obituaries","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Subway (restaurant)","Subway"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fred DeLuca"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[http://www.geograph.org.uk/profile/23411 Ian Thomson]"]},{"name":"w","description":["leukaemia"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States dollar","$"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bridgeport, Connecticut","Bridgeport"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.abqjournal.com/644970/news/subway-cofounder-dies-of-cancer-at-67.html","title\u003dSubway co-founder dies of cancer at 67","author\u003dCandice Choi ([[The Associated Press","AP]])","pub\u003dThe Albuquerque Journal","date\u003dSeptember 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/business/subway-co-founder-deluca/2129172.html","title\u003dSubway co-founder DeLuca dies after battling leukemia","author\u003d[[Reuters]]","pub\u003dChannel NewsAsia","date\u003dSeptember 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Forbes"]}
{"title":"South Sudan fuel tanker explosion kills dozens","wikiTitle":"South_Sudan_fuel_tanker_explosion_kills_dozens","wid":2443845,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-09-28T19:52:56Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/85-reported-dead-afte-fuel-tank-explosion-in-south-sudan-live-10505698.html, title\u003d\u0027More than 100\u0027 reported dead after fuel tank explosion in South Sudan, author\u003dCaroline Mortimer, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/17/south-sudan-oil-tanker-crash, title\u003dDozens killed in South Sudan after oil tanker crash, author\u003d[[Reuters]], pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"South_Sudan","description":"South Sudan"},{"id":"BBC","description":"BBC"},{"id":"Red_Cross","description":"Red Cross"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[South_Sudan] An overturned tanker exploded in TEMPLATE[w, Western Equatoria], South Sudan yesterday, killing dozens. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, [[Commons:User talk:JennaCB123, JennaCB123]]] The death toll is unclear. At least 85 died according to presidential spokesman Ateny Wek Ateny, citing \"local authorities\". Charles Kisagna of the local government said at least 100 died. County commissioner Wilson Thomas Yanga in remarks to the BBC put the toll at a minimum of 176.","The Red Cross said it had sent two burn kits to local rescuers in TEMPLATE[w, Maridi] with provisions for 100 patients. Kisanga warns the toll may increase \"because we do not have the facilities to treat the highly burnt people.\" TEMPLATE[w, Radio Tamazuj] spoke to a doctor who reported reserves of painkillers, oxygen, and other consumables were being exhausted.","Some casualties may have fled the scene. Reportedly, after the driver walked away from the crash to seek assistance, local residents began stealing petrol. South Sudan has few paved roads. Mass casualty fuel explosions are common in poor regions of East Africa.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:South_Sudan","description":"Category:South Sudan"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Red_Cross_and_Red_Crescent","description":"Category:Red Cross and Red Crescent"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 17, 2015"]},{"name":"South_Sudan","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Western Equatoria"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User talk:JennaCB123","JennaCB123]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maridi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Radio Tamazuj"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/africa/85-reported-dead-afte-fuel-tank-explosion-in-south-sudan-live-10505698.html","title\u003d\u0027More than 100\u0027 reported dead after fuel tank explosion in South Sudan","author\u003dCaroline Mortimer","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/17/south-sudan-oil-tanker-crash","title\u003dDozens killed in South Sudan after oil tanker crash","author\u003d[[Reuters]]","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Romanian PM Victor Ponta indicted in fraud case","wikiTitle":"Romanian_PM_Victor_Ponta_indicted_in_fraud_case","wid":2443938,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-06T15:55:28Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bangkokpost.com/news/world/697140/romanian-pm-victor-ponta-facing-graft-trial-prosecutors, title\u003dRomanian PM Victor Ponta facing graft trial: prosecutors, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dBangkok Post, date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34279002, title\u003dRomania PM Victor Ponta to face corruption trial, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/09/17/us-romania-ponta-idUSKCN0RH17E20150917, title\u003dRomanian PM Ponta faces trial in corruption case, author\u003dRadu-Sorin Marinas and Luiza Ilie, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dw.com/en/romanian-prime-minister-ponta-indicted-for-corruption/a-18720431, title\u003dRomanian Prime Minister Ponta indicted for corruption, author\u003d, pub\u003dDeutsche Welle, date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Romania","description":"Romania"},{"id":"Victor_Ponta","description":"Victor Ponta"},{"id":"Europe","description":"Europe"},{"id":"Soviet_Union","description":"Soviet Union"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[Romania] Romanian Prime Minister Victor Ponta was today indicted for fraud offences. TEMPLATE[image_credit, Social Democratic Party] The move follows a previous charging, which sees Ponta accused of forgery, TEMPLATE[w, tax evasion], TEMPLATE[w, money laundering], and having a conflict of interest. He is set to become the nation\u0027s first Prime Minister to face trial while in power.","His party, the left-wing TEMPLATE[w, Social Democrats (Romania), Social Democrats], support him. Ponta denies the accusations which emerged months ago, and has refused to resign. The Social Democrats lost the Presidential election last year and face a general election next year.","Ponta has thrice resisted censures proposed by the opposition. He has resigned the Social Democratic leadership and prosecutors say they have frozen some of his assets. President TEMPLATE[w, Klaus Iohannis] has asked Ponta to leave office, saying TEMPLATE[translated_quote, ro, Romanian language, Trebuie sÄ recunoaÈtem cÄ imaginea RomÃ¢niei are foarte mult de suferit de pe urma acestei chestiuni., we must admit that Romania\u0027s image has the most to suffer from this issue.]","The alleged misconduct predates Ponta\u0027s time in office and therefore avoids presidential immunity. The indictment indicates prosecutors have finished investigations and are ready to try Ponta and four others involved in the case. Ponta was a lawyer and TEMPLATE[w, Romanian Parliament, member of parliament] in 2008\u0026ndash;09, the period covered by the indictment. He was elected Prime Minister in 2012. TEMPLATE[image_credit, (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, European People\u0027s Party] The case alleges Ponta forged expenses claims for 39,750 TEMPLATE[w, euro, euros] while working for political ally TEMPLATE[w, Dan Sova]\u0027s law firm. Ponta gave Sova three different ministerial roles, the foundation for the conflict of interest allegations. The case is now sent to the country\u0027s highest court.","Ponta accused anti-corruption prosecutors of  \"manipulating public opinion\" and withholding information. Romania is amongst Europe\u0027s poorest nations and has been grappling with corruption and political instability since independence from the Soviet Union in 1989. In recent years the rich and powerful have come under scrutiny by the nation\u0027s anti-corruption investigators, often claiming the cases against them are political. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Romania","description":"Category:Romania"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Victor_Ponta","description":"Category:Victor Ponta"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Romania","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Social Democratic Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["tax evasion"]},{"name":"w","description":["money laundering"]},{"name":"w","description":["Social Democrats (Romania)","Social Democrats"]},{"name":"w","description":["Klaus Iohannis"]},{"name":"translated_quote","description":["ro","Romanian language","Trebuie sÄ recunoaÈtem cÄ imaginea RomÃ¢niei are foarte mult de suferit de pe urma acestei chestiuni.","we must admit that Romania\u0027s image has the most to suffer from this issue."]},{"name":"w","description":["Romanian Parliament","member of parliament"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["(TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["European People\u0027s Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["euro","euros"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dan Sova"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bangkokpost.com/news/world/697140/romanian-pm-victor-ponta-facing-graft-trial-prosecutors","title\u003dRomanian PM Victor Ponta facing graft trial: prosecutors","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dBangkok Post","date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34279002","title\u003dRomania PM Victor Ponta to face corruption trial","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/09/17/us-romania-ponta-idUSKCN0RH17E20150917","title\u003dRomanian PM Ponta faces trial in corruption case","author\u003dRadu-Sorin Marinas and Luiza Ilie","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dw.com/en/romanian-prime-minister-ponta-indicted-for-corruption/a-18720431","title\u003dRomanian Prime Minister Ponta indicted for corruption","author\u003d","pub\u003dDeutsche Welle","date\u003dSeptember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"London court jails man after Dark Web ricin sting","wikiTitle":"London_court_jails_man_after_Dark_Web_ricin_sting","wid":2445671,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-02T11:22:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/sep/18/breaking-bad-fan-jailed-over-ricin-plot, title\u003dBreaking Bad fan jailed for trying to buy ricin, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34288380, title\u003dBreaking Bad fan jailed over Dark Web ricin plot, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/GtrManchesterPolice/photos/a.229258947144132.55414.166857596717601/975939575809395/?type\u003d1, title\u003dPress Release, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dFacebook, date\u003dSeptember 18, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"FBI","description":"FBI"},{"id":"Liverpool","description":"Liverpool"},{"id":"chemical_weapon","description":"chemical weapon"},{"id":"Internet","description":"Internet"},{"id":"UK","description":"UK"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 18, 2015] TEMPLATE[United_Kingdom] Mr Justice Saunders today imprisoned a man for eight years at the TEMPLATE[w, Old Bailey] in London after an FBI sting in which he tried to buy TEMPLATE[w, ricin] on the TEMPLATE[w, Dark Web]. TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, Everyone needs to know that the possession of a chemical weapon is extremely serious and long prison sentences will follow, 4\u003dMr Justice Saunders] Mohammed Ali, 31, from Liverpool, was convicted at trial of attempting to possess a chemical weapon. He told the jury he was \"curious\" about the Dark Web, which is a largely hidden and difficult to police section of the Internet. Ali said he didn\u0027t realise he had done anything illegal.","Ali was prosecuted under the TEMPLATE[w, Chemical Weapons Act 1996] after sending an undercover agent a message reading  \"Hi, would you be able to make me some ricin and send it to the UK?\" He bought 500mg, which has the potential to kill about 1,400, but was sent a dummy package. Counter-terror police in the UK liaised with the FBI. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[w:User:AzaToth, AzaToth]]] The powder, which Ali paid for in TEMPLATE[w, BitCoin], was actually harmless. Hidden inside a toy car, the package was treated with markers and his face glowed under ultraviolet light, indicating he had handled it. The judge said today there was \"real risk\" involved.","Ali told his trial he had discovered drugs and guns for sale. Computer analysis showed he had looked up ricin and other poisons; he said he went for ricin simply because it had appeared in TEMPLATE[w, Breaking Bad]. He also searched for small animals after being advised to test it on a rodent; a to-do list on his computer included \"paid ricin guy\" and \"get pet to murder\".","Mr Justice Saunders said the case called for \"a deterrent sentence\", which \"will appear harsh to the defendant and his family.\" \"Everyone needs to know that the possession of a chemical weapon is extremely serious and long prison sentences will follow.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Weapons_of_mass_destruction","description":"Category:Weapons of mass destruction"},{"id":"Category:Chemical_weapons","description":"Category:Chemical weapons"},{"id":"Category:FBI","description":"Category:FBI"},{"id":"Category:Computing","description":"Category:Computing"},{"id":"Category:Internet","description":"Category:Internet"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Liverpool","description":"Category:Liverpool"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 18, 2015"]},{"name":"United_Kingdom","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Old Bailey"]},{"name":"w","description":["ricin"]},{"name":"w","description":["Dark Web"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["Everyone needs to know that the possession of a chemical weapon is extremely serious and long prison sentences will follow","4\u003dMr Justice Saunders"]},{"name":"w","description":["Chemical Weapons Act 1996"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[w:User:AzaToth","AzaToth]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["BitCoin"]},{"name":"w","description":["Breaking Bad"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/sep/18/breaking-bad-fan-jailed-over-ricin-plot","title\u003dBreaking Bad fan jailed for trying to buy ricin","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dSeptember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-34288380","title\u003dBreaking Bad fan jailed over Dark Web ricin plot","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dSeptember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.facebook.com/GtrManchesterPolice/photos/a.229258947144132.55414.166857596717601/975939575809395/?type\u003d1","title\u003dPress Release","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dFacebook","date\u003dSeptember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Breaking Bad]"]}
{"title":"Civilian government restored as Burkina Faso coup ends","wikiTitle":"Civilian_government_restored_as_Burkina_Faso_coup_ends","wid":2454042,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-09T19:57:41Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-34365564, title\u003dBurkina Faso coup guards unit to be disbanded, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/25/burkina-faso-foiled-military-coup, title\u003dHow the people of Burkina Faso foiled a military coup, author\u003dSimon Allison, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-34340704, title\u003dMogho Naba: Burkina Faso\u0027s mediator monarch, author\u003dLamine Konkobo, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-africa-34321961, title\u003dBurkina Faso coup leader Gen Diendere defies ultimatum, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/09/protests-burkina-faso-army-moves-disarm-junta-150921150344686.html, title\u003dBurkina Faso coup leader to \u0027hand over power\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dAl Jazeera, date\u003dSeptember 22, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Burkina_Faso","description":"Burkina Faso"},{"id":"Economic_Community_of_West_African_States","description":"Economic Community of West African States"},{"id":"Abuja","description":"Abuja"},{"id":"African_Union","description":"African Union"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[Burkina_Faso] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, Jeremiah Erickson, (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, US Air Force, USAF] The week-long TEMPLATE[w, coup d\u0027Ã©tat] in Burkina Faso ended on Wednesday with the restoration of interim President TEMPLATE[w, Michel Kafando] and the civilian government. By yesterday the government announced that the presidential guard unit involved in the coup, the TEMPLATE[w, Regiment of Presidential Security], would be dissolved.","This follows the intercession of regional leaders and the regular TEMPLATE[w, Military of Burkina Faso, Army], which sent soldiers to the capital on Monday.","The leaders of the Economic Community of West African States met on Tuesday in the Nigerian capital Abuja and helped with negotiations. A prominent mediation role was also played by the TEMPLATE[w, Mogho Naba], the traditional king of the TEMPLATE[w, Mossi people, Mossi], who are the country\u0027s largest ethnic group. Civilian protests against the coup resulted in the deaths of at least ten people with more than a hundred injured. The attempt to overthrow the government was criticized by the international community, with the African Union suspending the country\u0027s membership and describing the coup as \"null and void\".","The President and Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Yacouba Isaac Zida] were detained by the presidential guards at a ministerial meeting on September 16. The guards installed their former commander, TEMPLATE[w, Gilbert DiendÃ©rÃ©], as head of state and demanded the lifting of a ban on electoral participation by anybody who had tried to help exiled former President TEMPLATE[w, Blaise CompaorÃ©] to extend his 27-year rule in October 2014. DiendÃ©rÃ© was previously CompaorÃ©\u0027s chief of staff.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, 2015 Burkinabe coup d\u0027Ã©tat]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Abuja","description":"Category:Abuja"},{"id":"Category:Nigeria","description":"Category:Nigeria"},{"id":"Category:Burkina_Faso","description":"Category:Burkina Faso"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and confli