{"title":"Independence debate as Catalonia holds regional elections","wikiTitle":"Independence_debate_as_Catalonia_holds_regional_elections","wid":2465939,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-02-14T23:21:52Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://elpais.com/elpais/2015/09/27/inenglish/1443342268_544226.html, title\u003dCatalonia goes to the polls at elections that could decide regionâs future, author\u003dMiquel Noguer, pub\u003dEl PaÃ­s, date\u003dSeptember 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://reuters.com/article/idUSKCN0RQ0RN20150926, title\u003dCatalan separatists see election boost as step towards independence, author\u003dJulien Toyer, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dSeptember 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/27/catalans-cast-votes-in-unofficial-independence-referendum, title\u003dCatalans cast votes in unofficial independence referendum, author\u003dAshifa Kassam, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 27, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, September 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[Spain]  Regional elections are taking place today in TEMPLATE[w, Catalonia], TEMPLATE[w, Spain], in which the biggest talking point is whether the TEMPLATE[w, Autonomous communities of Spain, autonomous region] should become an independent country. The polls are being held early as the national government has not allowed an official referendum on independence. Opinion polls, according to TEMPLATE[w, Reuters], suggest the secessionists will win more than half of the 135 TEMPLATE[w, Parliament of Catalonia, regional Parliament] seats but less than half of the popular vote.","The pro-independence parties include the TEMPLATE[w, Together for Yes, Junts pel SÃ­] (Together for Yes) coalition and the left-wing TEMPLATE[w, Popular Unity Candidacy] (CUP). If they win a clear majority, the Junts pel SÃ­ hopes to hold further elections in eighteen months after developing future state institutions such as a separate tax office. However, they might have to find a compromise candidate for regional president because CUP does not support the incumbent, TEMPLATE[w, Artur Mas i GavarrÃ³, Artur Mas]. The CUP is also campaigning for Catalonia to leave the TEMPLATE[w, European Union].","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, 1\u003dUnited we will win, 4\u003d(TEMPLATE)\u003cbr/\u003ePrime Minister of Spain] In contrast, the TEMPLATE[w, People\u0027s Party (Spain), People\u0027s Party], led by Spanish Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Mariano Rajoy], has called for Catalonia to remain within Spain. Rajoy took part in a campaign video on Friday in which he says \"united we will win\".","Other parties in the election include the TEMPLATE[w, Socialists\u0027 Party of Catalonia], which has called for a federal solution, and the TEMPLATE[w, Citizens (Spanish political party), Ciutadans (Citizens)], which is proposing a reform of the financial balance between the national and regional governments.","Voting was due to finish at 8pm TEMPLATE[w, Central European Summer Time, local time] (1800 TEMPLATE[w, UTC]) today and more than 5 million people are eligible to participate.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, Catalonian parliamentary election, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Catalonia"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:Spain","description":"Category:Spain"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["September 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Spain","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Catalonia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Spain"]},{"name":"w","description":["Autonomous communities of Spain","autonomous region"]},{"name":"w","description":["Reuters"]},{"name":"w","description":["Parliament of Catalonia","regional Parliament"]},{"name":"w","description":["Together for Yes","Junts pel SÃ­"]},{"name":"w","description":["Popular Unity Candidacy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Artur Mas i GavarrÃ³","Artur Mas"]},{"name":"w","description":["European Union"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["1\u003dUnited we will win","4\u003d(TEMPLATE)\u003cbr/\u003ePrime Minister of Spain"]},{"name":"w","description":["People\u0027s Party (Spain)","People\u0027s Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mariano Rajoy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Socialists\u0027 Party of Catalonia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Citizens (Spanish political party)","Ciutadans (Citizens)"]},{"name":"w","description":["Central European Summer Time","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["Catalonian parliamentary election, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://elpais.com/elpais/2015/09/27/inenglish/1443342268_544226.html","title\u003dCatalonia goes to the polls at elections that could decide regionâs future","author\u003dMiquel Noguer","pub\u003dEl PaÃ­s","date\u003dSeptember 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://reuters.com/article/idUSKCN0RQ0RN20150926","title\u003dCatalan separatists see election boost as step towards independence","author\u003dJulien Toyer","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dSeptember 27, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/sep/27/catalans-cast-votes-in-unofficial-independence-referendum","title\u003dCatalans cast votes in unofficial independence referendum","author\u003dAshifa Kassam","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dSeptember 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["1","4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"NASA announces water on Mars","wikiTitle":"NASA_announces_water_on_Mars","wid":2468551,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-12-25T04:50:33Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.google.com/doodles/evidence-of-water-found-on-mars, title\u003dEvidence of water found on Mars, author\u003d, pub\u003dGoogle Doodle, date\u003dSeptember 29, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/sep/28/nasa-scientists-find-evidence-flowing-water-mars, title\u003dNasa scientists find evidence of flowing water on Mars, author\u003dIan Sample, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dSeptember 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Technology/nasa-reveals-mars-frozen-liquid-water/story?id\u003d34100372, title\u003dMars: NASA Reveals Red Planet Contains Both Frozen, Liquid Water, author\u003dAlyssa Newcomb, pub\u003dABC News (US), date\u003dSeptember 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.aljazeera.com/news/2015/09/nasa-water-mars-150928111344570.html, title\u003dNASA: Water found on Mars, author\u003dAli Younes, pub\u003dAljazeera, date\u003dSeptember 28, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/SciAstro/status/648518371487690753, title\u003dWater on Mars, not just frozen. Is anything drinking it? Someday we will find out on our #JourneyToMars, author\u003dJohn Grunsfeld, pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dSeptember 28, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"NASA","description":"NASA"},{"id":"Mars","description":"Mars"},{"id":"University_of_Arizona","description":"University of Arizona"},{"id":"Google","description":"Google"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dNASA announces water on Mars audio wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-11] TEMPLATE[Space] TEMPLATE[w, Viking Orbiter]TEMPLATE[image, [[NASA]]/(TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, USGS] TEMPLATE[w, Newton (Martian crater), Newton Crater]TEMPLATE[image, NASA/JPL-Caltech/Univ. of Arizona] On Monday, NASA announced that signs of liquid water have been found on Mars. The TEMPLATE[w, Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter] spacecraft found evidence of the liquid on the Martian surface, in long dark spots on the Red Planet thought to be formed because of water flow.","In a news conference, NASA\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, planetary science] director, TEMPLATE[w, James L. Green, Jim Green] said, \"We now know Mars was once a planet very much like Earth with warm salty seas and fresh water lakes [...] but something has happened to Mars, it lost its water.\"","Water is thought to flow down slopes in the warm summer months and dry up as the temperature drops seasonally. Scientists have different theories about the water\u0027s origin, as perhaps from the Martian atmosphere or from ice below the surface.","In 2011, Lujendra Ojha proposed the theory of water on the Martian surface, after studying salt samples from Martian soil. The temperature of Mars is close to the freezing point of water, but the presence of salt lowers the freezing point. Alfred McEwen, professor of TEMPLATE[w, planetary geology] at the University of Arizona, described the water as \"briny\". Moreover, the TEMPLATE[w, Seasonal flows on warm Martian slopes, recurring slope lineae] (RSL) on the surface of Mars are found to slide down the slope in the hotter season indicating the presence of water.","NASA\u0027s associate administrator John Grunsfeld said those observations gave a better picture about the planet\u0027s resources that could be helpful in the future. Grunsfeld tweeted Water on Mars, not just frozen. Is anything drinking it? Someday we wil find out on our #JourneyToMars.","To mark this discovery, Google created a TEMPLATE[w, Google Doodle, doodle] in which Mars is sipping water.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Sisters, w, Water on Mars, commons, Water on Mars]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Physics"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Space","description":"Category:Space"},{"id":"Category:Mars","description":"Category:Mars"},{"id":"Category:NASA","description":"Category:NASA"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Geology","description":"Category:Geology"},{"id":"Category:Google","description":"Category:Google"},{"id":"Category:University_of_Arizona","description":"Category:University of Arizona"},{"id":"Category:Mars_Reconnaissance_Orbiter","description":"Category:Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dNASA announces water on Mars audio wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-11"]},{"name":"Space","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Viking Orbiter"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[NASA]]/(TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["USGS"]},{"name":"w","description":["Newton (Martian crater)","Newton Crater"]},{"name":"image","description":["NASA/JPL-Caltech/Univ. of Arizona"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mars Reconnaissance Orbiter"]},{"name":"w","description":["planetary science"]},{"name":"w","description":["James L. Green","Jim Green"]},{"name":"w","description":["planetary geology"]},{"name":"w","description":["Seasonal flows on warm Martian slopes","recurring slope lineae"]},{"name":"w","description":["Google Doodle","doodle"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Sisters","description":["w","Water on Mars","commons","Water on Mars"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.google.com/doodles/evidence-of-water-found-on-mars","title\u003dEvidence of water found on Mars","author\u003d","pub\u003dGoogle Doodle","date\u003dSeptember 29, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":