{"title":"Russian jets carry out strikes in Syria","wikiTitle":"Russian_jets_carry_out_strikes_in_Syria","wid":2474158,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-10T12:41:47Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/09/30/politics/russia-syria-airstrikes-isis/, title\u003dRussia conducts first airstrikes in Syria, author\u003dEd Payne and Barbara Starr, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dOctober 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-34399164, title\u003dSyria crisis: Russian air strikes against Assad enemies, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dSeptember 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://sana.sy/en/?p\u003d56330, title\u003dUpdated-Russian airstrikes against ISIS sites in Syria begin, author\u003dManar al-Freih / Hazem al-Sabbagh/ Barry, pub\u003dSyrian Arab News Agency, date\u003dSeptember 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Russia","description":"Russian"},{"id":"Syria","description":"Syrian"},{"id":"Bashar_al-Assad","description":"Bashar al-Assad"},{"id":"Vladimir_Putin","description":"Vladimir Putin"},{"id":"Sergey_Lavrov","description":"Sergey Lavrov"},{"id":"John_Kerry","description":"John Kerry"},{"id":"Syrian_Observatory_for_Human_Rights","description":"Syrian Observatory for Human Rights"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 1, 2015] TEMPLATE[Syria] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, Oleg V. Belyakov - AirTeamImages] Russian jets stationed reportedly in the Syrian city of TEMPLATE[w, Latakia] have been carrying out air strikes since yesterday, in support of Syrian President Bashar al-Assad, having notified the United States an hour before.","Russian President Vladimir Putin announced the strikes against TEMPLATE[w, Islamism, Islamist] militants who \"if they succeed in Syria [...] will come to Russia, too\", and clarified he would not be sending ground troops to participate in the TEMPLATE[w, Syrian Civil War]. He called on Assad to engage in dialogue with \"healthy\" opposition groups.","The TEMPLATE[w, ITAR-Tass] news agency reported earlier yesterday Putin had been given the green light for the air raids by the TEMPLATE[w, Russian Federation Council, upper chamber, foreign\u003dsuppress] of TEMPLATE[w, Russian Parliament, Russia\u0027s legislature]. The TEMPLATE[w, Syrian Arab News Agency] (SANA) said Russia responded after Assad had sent a letter seeking assistance from Putin. SANA also reported the strikes were carried out in conjunction with the Syrian Air Force and had focussed on ISIS facilities in a number of locations.","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, 1\u003destablish channels of communications to avoid any unintended incidents, 4\u003dSergey Lavrov, Russian Foreign Minister] The US State Department said US aircraft would continue to operate throughout the region. An agreement to hold military talks was announced by Russian Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov and US Secretary of State John Kerry. Lavrov said it was necessary to \"establish channels of communications to avoid any unintended incidents\". However, US officials questioned the purpose of the Russian strikes, stating the targeted areas were unlikely to be under ISIS control.","Syrian opposition groups claimed there have been civilian casualties as a direct consequence of the strikes. The TEMPLATE[w, Syrian National Coalition] said several children were amongst 36 people who died after planes struck several towns, whilst the Syrian Observatory for Human Rights claimed there had been 28 deaths.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, Russian-led military intervention in Syria]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Syrian_Civil_War","description":"Category:Syrian Civil War"},{"id":"Category:Russia","description":"Category:Russia"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Russian_Federal_Assembly","description":"Category:Russian Federal Assembly"},{"id":"Category:Russian_Federation_Council","description":"Category:Russian Federation Council"},{"id":"Category:Syria","description":"Category:Syria"},{"id":"Category:Syrian_Observatory_for_Human_Rights","description":"Category:Syrian Observatory for Human Rights"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 1, 2015"]},{"name":"Syria","description":[]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["Oleg V. Belyakov - AirTeamImages"]},{"name":"w","description":["Latakia"]},{"name":"w","description":["Islamism","Islamist"]},{"name":"w","description":["Syrian Civil War"]},{"name":"w","description":["ITAR-Tass"]},{"name":"w","description":["Russian Federation Council","upper chamber","foreign\u003dsuppress"]},{"name":"w","description":["Russian Parliament","Russia\u0027s legislature"]},{"name":"w","description":["Syrian Arab News Agency"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["1\u003destablish channels of communications to avoid any unintended incidents","4\u003dSergey Lavrov, Russian Foreign Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["Syrian National Coalition"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["Russian-led military intervention in Syria"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/09/30/politics/russia-syria-airstrikes-isis/","title\u003dRussia conducts first airstrikes in Syria","author\u003dEd Payne and Barbara Starr","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dOctober 1, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-middle-east-34399164","title\u003dSyria crisis: Russian air strikes against Assad enemies","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dSeptember 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://sana.sy/en/?p\u003d56330","title\u003dUpdated-Russian airstrikes against ISIS sites in Syria begin","author\u003dManar al-Freih / Hazem al-Sabbagh/ Barry","pub\u003dSyrian Arab News Agency","date\u003dSeptember 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["foreign","1","4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Several dead in Oregon college shootings","wikiTitle":"Several_dead_in_Oregon_college_shootings","wid":2477399,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-14T13:47:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dEight people found slain inside Houston-area home, date\u003dAugust 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dNine dead after biker gang feud in Texas, date\u003dMay 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dDozens dead in Connecticut school shooting, date\u003dDecember 14, 2012]","TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dThree students killed in Ohio school shooting, others injured, date\u003dFebruary 29, 2012]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-34436373, title\u003dOregon shooting: Gunman killed himself, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dOctober 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/survivor-recalls-terrifying-moments-oregon-campus-shooting/story?id\u003d34219240, title\u003dSurvivor Recalls Terrifying Moments During Oregon Campus Shooting, author\u003dNeil Karlinsky, pub\u003dABC News (US), date\u003dOctober 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/10/01/us/oregon-college-shooting/, title\u003dOregon shooting: Gunman dead after college rampage, author\u003dDana Ford, Ed Payne, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dOctober 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-34419802, title\u003dOregon college shooting: Nine dead in Roseburg attack, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dOctober 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/10/01/politics/oregon-shooting-obama-response/index.html, title\u003dObama on Oregon shooting: \u0027Somehow this has become routine\u0027, author\u003dStephen Collinson, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dOctober 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/oregon-shooting-weapons_560ec25be4b0dd85030bd1f9, title\u003dAuthorities: Weapons Recovered In Oregon Shooting Purchased Legally, author\u003dDana Liebelson, pub\u003dHuffington Post, date\u003dOctober 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Oregon","description":"Oregon"},{"id":"Barack_Obama","description":"Barack Obama"},{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"United Kingdom"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[Oregon] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, US Geological Survey] Nine people were killed on Thursday by 26-year-old Chris Harper Mercer on the campus of TEMPLATE[w, Umpqua Community College] in TEMPLATE[w, Roseburg, Oregon, Roseburg], Oregon. By various reports seven or nine people were also injured. Officials said Mercer killed himself during the subsequent shootout with police.","Mercer began the killing spree in a class where he was a student by shooting the class teacher, and killed eight students in that and at least one other classroom. In the next classroom, a student nurse unsuccessfully tried to save the life of her friend who was wounded by the gunman. Another student, ex-soldier Chris Mintz, was shot seven times after coming to help.","The reasons for the attack are not known but TEMPLATE[w, CNN] reports he singled out people who identified themselves as TEMPLATE[w, Christianity, Christian]. The TEMPLATE[w, BBC] noted Mercer may have revealed his plans via social media and possibly left a written statement. He briefly served in the TEMPLATE[w, US Army] in 2008.","An ATF (TEMPLATE[w, Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives]) agent said authorities found six weapons at the college and a further seven weapons from the gunman\u0027s home, including a shotgun, all of which appear to have been obtained lawfully by Mercer and members of his family. State laws permit people to carry concealed weapons in higher education institutions and at least one other person at the college was armed. Oregon recently passed a new gun law in response to a shooting incident in 2012, in which a man used a stolen rifle to murder two other people in a TEMPLATE[w, Portland] shopping center.","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, 1\u003dSomehow this has become routine. The reporting is routine. My response here at this podium ends up being routine, the conversation in the aftermath of it, 4\u003dBarack Obama] Later on Thursday, President Barack Obama spoke for twelve minutes about the incident and called for stricter gun controls in line with other countries like Australia and the United Kingdom. Referring to earlier similar shootings, he said \"Somehow this has become routine. The reporting is routine. My response here at this podium ends up being routine, the conversation in the aftermath of it. We have become numb to this\". This is reportedly the fifteenth occasion Obama has spoken out after such a killing spree. He expressed his belief that there would soon be a \"press release\" from the pro-gun lobby, who would call for a reduction of gun controls. He also predicted there would be criticism levelled at him about his politicization of the matter, but he said \"this is something we should politicize.\" Although no new initiative was outlined, Obama highlighted TEMPLATE[w, US Congress, Congressional] opposition which had stopped \"the collection of data on shooting incidents\" and stated \"this is not something I can do myself.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, Umpqua Community College shooting]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Oregon","description":"Category:Oregon"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Education","description":"Category:Education"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Gun_politics","description":"Category:Gun politics"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Oregon","description":[]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["US Geological Survey"]},{"name":"w","description":["Umpqua Community College"]},{"name":"w","description":["Roseburg, Oregon","Roseburg"]},{"name":"w","description":["CNN"]},{"name":"w","description":["Christianity","Christian"]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Army"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bureau of Alcohol, Tobacco, Firearms and Explosives"]},{"name":"w","description":["Portland"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["1\u003dSomehow this has become routine. The reporting is routine. My response here at this podium ends up being routine, the conversation in the aftermath of it","4\u003dBarack Obama"]},{"name":"w","description":["US Congress","Congressional"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dEight people found slain inside Houston-area home","date\u003dAugust 13, 2015"]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dNine dead after biker gang feud in Texas","date\u003dMay 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dDozens dead in Connecticut school shooting","date\u003dDecember 14, 2012"]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dThree students killed in Ohio school shooting, others injured","date\u003dFebruary 29, 2012"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["Umpqua Community College shooting"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-34436373","title\u003dOregon shooting: Gunman killed himself","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dOctober 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/US/survivor-recalls-terrifying-moments-oregon-campus-shooting/story?id\u003d34219240","title\u003dSurvivor Recalls Terrifying Moments During Oregon Campus Shooting","author\u003dNeil Karlinsky","pub\u003dABC News (US)","date\u003dOctober 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/10/01/us/oregon-college-shooting/","title\u003dOregon shooting: Gunman dead after college rampage","author\u003dDana Ford, Ed Payne","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dOctober 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-34419802","title\u003dOregon college shooting: Nine dead in Roseburg attack","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dOctober 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edition.cnn.com/2015/10/01/politics/oregon-shooting-obama-response/index.html","title\u003dObama on Oregon shooting: \u0027Somehow this has become routine\u0027","author\u003dStephen Collinson","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dOctober 2, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.huffingtonpost.com/entry/oregon-shooting-weapons_560ec25be4b0dd85030bd1f9","title\u003dAuthorities: Weapons Recovered In Oregon Shooting Purchased Legally","author\u003dDana Liebelson","pub\u003dHuffington Post","date\u003dOctober 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["1","4","title","date","title","date","title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Civilian deaths as U.S. bombs hospital in Afghanistan","wikiTitle":"Civilian_deaths_as_U.S._bombs_hospital_in_Afghanistan","wid":2483801,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-14T13:47:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dAfghan provincial governor killed in mosque bomb attack, date\u003dOctober 9, 2010]","TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dNATO: 130 militants killed in Afghanistan, date\u003dNovember 10, 2009]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://reuters.com/article/idUSKCN0RZ1FX20151005, title\u003dAfghan forces called for air strike in Kunduz: U.S. general, author\u003dYeganeh Torbati, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dOctober 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.msf.org/topics/kunduz-hospital-airstrike, title\u003dKunduz Hospital Airstrike, author\u003d, pub\u003dMÃ©decins Sans FrontiÃ¨res, date\u003dOctober 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.sky.com/story/1563203/nato-deeply-saddened-after-us-bombs-hospital, title\u003dNATO \u0027Deeply Saddened\u0027 After US Bombs Hospital, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky News, date\u003dOctober 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/world-asia-34433302, title\u003dAfghan hospital attack: MSF condemns Kunduz air strikes, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dOctober 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.icrc.org/en/document/afghanistan-icrc-condemns-bombing-msf-hospital-kunduz, title\u003dAfghanistan: ICRC condemns bombing of MSF hospital in Kunduz, author\u003d, pub\u003dInternational Committee of the Red Cross, date\u003dOctober 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ohchr.org/EN/NewsEvents/Pages/DisplayNews.aspx?NewsID\u003d16564\u0026LangID\u003dE, title\u003dKunduz hospital airstrikes âinexcusableâ -- Zeid, author\u003d, pub\u003dUN High Commissioner for Human Rights, date\u003dOctober 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.stripes.com/news/middle-east/afghan-forces-to-counterattack-as-district-falls-to-taliban-1.353634?utm_medium\u003dtwitter\u0026utm_source\u003dtwitterfeed, title\u003dAfghan forces to counterattack as district falls to Taliban, author\u003dSlobodan Lekic, pub\u003dStars \u0026 Stripes, date\u003dJune 21, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_States","description":"United States"},{"id":"Afghanistan","description":"Afghanistan"},{"id":"Taliban","description":"Taliban"},{"id":"International_Committee_of_the_Red_Cross","description":"International Committee of the Red Cross"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Afghanistan] TEMPLATE[date, October 6, 2015] TEMPLATE[picture_select_R, noborder\u003d1, width\u003d205px, [[File:Kunduz in Afghanistan.svg, 190px, center, thumb, Kunduz province in Afghanistan. (TEMPLATE)]], [[File:Kunduz MSF Trauma Center - location map - 01.png, 190px, center, thumb, The location of the hospital in Kunduz. (TEMPLATE)]]] Twenty two civilians, including three children, died, TEMPLATE[w, MÃ©decins Sans FrontiÃ¨res] (MSF) reported, on Saturday after a United States airstrike hit a hospital in the city of TEMPLATE[w, Kunduz] in northern Afghanistan. Amongst the fatalities were twelve charity staff working for MSF. MSF said there were about two hundred people in the building.","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, Under the clear presumption that a war crime has been committed, MSF demands that a full and transparent investigation into the event be conducted by an independent international body., source\u003dMÃ©decins Sans FrontiÃ¨res]","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, The strike may have resulted in collateral damage to a nearby medical facility., source\u003dUnited States military] A statement was issued on the MSF website criticising the attack and stating \"Under the clear presumption that a war crime has been committed, MSF demands that a full and transparent investigation into the event be conducted by an independent international body.\" The US military released a statement saying they had struck \"against individuals threatening the force\" and \"The strike may have resulted in collateral damage to a nearby medical facility.\" The US Government announced there would be three separate investigations, carried out by the Afghan forces, the US military, and TEMPLATE[w, NATO]. The Afghan interior ministry claimed there had been a Taliban presence in the hospital although this was denied by the insurgent organization.","The attack was also condemned by the International Committee of the Red Cross, whilst the UN TEMPLATE[w, Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights, High Commissioner for Human Rights], TEMPLATE[w, Prince Zeid bin Ra\u0027ad, Zeid Ra\u0027ad Al Hussein], described the strike as \"inexcusable\" and called for a full investigation.","On September 28, the Taliban launched an assault on Kunduz. The US has been carrying out air strikes to support Afghan government forces attempting to recover the city. MSF said it had often provided the Afghan and US governments with details of the location of the hospital, particularly on September 29. The Taliban had unsuccessfully tried to capture Kunduz in April this year, but they were pushed back by government forces.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Kunduz hospital airstrike, w, Battle of Kunduz]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Red_Cross_and_Red_Crescent","description":"Category:Red Cross and Red Crescent"},{"id":"Category:MÃ©decins_Sans_FrontiÃ¨res","description":"Category:MÃ©decins Sans FrontiÃ¨res"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:United_Nations","description":"Category:United Nations"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Taliban","description":"Category:Taliban"},{"id":"Category:War_crimes","description":"Category:War crimes"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Afghanistan","description":"Category:Afghanistan"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"}],"templates":[{"name":"Afghanistan","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["October 6, 2015"]},{"name":"picture_select_R","description":["noborder\u003d1","width\u003d205px","[[File:Kunduz in Afghanistan.svg","190px","center","thumb","Kunduz province in Afghanistan. (TEMPLATE)]]","[[File:Kunduz MSF Trauma Center - location map - 01.png","190px","center","thumb","The location of the hospital in Kunduz. (TEMPLATE)]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[:c:User:TUBS","User:TUBS]]"]},{"name":"image","description":["Â© OpenStreetMap contributors"]},{"name":"w","description":["MÃ©decins Sans FrontiÃ¨res"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kunduz"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["Under the clear presumption that a war crime has been committed, MSF demands that a full and transparent investigation into the event be conducted by an independent international body.","source\u003dMÃ©decins Sans FrontiÃ¨res"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["The strike may have resulted in collateral damage to a nearby medical facility.","source\u003dUnited States military"]},{"name":"w","description":["NATO"]},{"name":"w","description":["Office of the United Nations High Commissioner for Human Rights","High Commissioner for Human Rights"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prince Zeid bin Ra\u0027ad","Zeid Ra\u0027ad Al Hussein"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dAfghan provincial governor killed in mosque bomb attack","date\u003dOctober 9, 2010"]},{"name":