{"title":"Three scientists share 2015 Chemistry Nobel Prize for DNA repair research","wikiTitle":"Three_scientists_share_2015_Chemistry_Nobel_Prize_for_DNA_repair_research","wid":2492371,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-15T21:53:34Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003d2006 Nobel Prize in chemistry for insight into cells, date\u003dOctober 4, 2006]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/announcement.html, title\u003dThe Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - Prize Announcement, author\u003d, pub\u003dNobel Media, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015 (date of access)]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/, title\u003dThe Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - Tomas Lindahl, Paul Modrich, Aziz Sancar, author\u003d, pub\u003dNobel Media, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/press.html, title\u003dThe Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - Press Release, author\u003d, pub\u003dNobel Media, date\u003dOctober 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.wired.com/2015/10/dna-repair-mechanisms-get-nobel-prize-chemistry/?mbid\u003dsocial_twitter, title\u003dDNA Repair Discoveries Get the Nobel Prize in Chemistry, author\u003dKatie M. Palmer, pub\u003dWired (website), date\u003dOctober 7, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/advanced-chemistryprize2015.pdf, title\u003dScientific Background on the Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - mechanistic studies of DNA repair -, author\u003dClass for Chemistry, pub\u003dRoyal Swedish Academy of Sciences, date\u003dOctober 7, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry","description":"Nobel Prize in Chemistry"},{"id":"Sweden","description":"Swedish"},{"id":"Turkey","description":"Turkish"},{"id":"US","description":"US"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources","External link"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dThree scientists share 2015 Chemistry Nobel Prize for DNA repair research Audio Wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-11] TEMPLATE[date, October 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[Nobel_Prize] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, Tom Ellenberger] Yesterday, TEMPLATE[w, GÃ¶ran K. Hansson], permanent secretary of the TEMPLATE[w, Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences], announced this year\u0027s Nobel Prize in Chemistry is awarded to three scientists for their work on TEMPLATE[w, DNA repair].","TEMPLATE[w, Tomas Lindahl], TEMPLATE[w, Paul L. Modrich, Paul Modrich] and TEMPLATE[w, Aziz Sancar] showed how damaged TEMPLATE[w, DNA] is repaired and TEMPLATE[w, genetics, genetic information] is safeguarded by the cells at the TEMPLATE[w, molecule, molecular] level.","Swedish scientist Tomas Lindahl found that DNA molecules decay too quickly for life, or evolution, to be sustainable. This led to the discovery of TEMPLATE[w, base excision repair], a cellular mechanism that repairs damaged DNA by removing erroneous sections and replacing them.","Turkish TEMPLATE[w, molecular biology, molecular biologist] Aziz Sancar mapped TEMPLATE[w, nucleotide excision repair], a DNA repair mechanism that targets larger-scale damage caused by TEMPLATE[w, mutagen, mutagens] and TEMPLATE[w, ultraviolet radiation].","US professor of TEMPLATE[w, biochemistry] Paul Modrich showed how errors caused during TEMPLATE[w, DNA replication] are usually rectified. TEMPLATE[w, DNA mismatch repair] increases the precision of DNA replication when TEMPLATE[w, cell (biology), cells] divide.","The prize is shared 1/3rd to each scientist. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Sweden CAT:Nobel Prize CAT:Chemistry CAT:Biology CAT:Science and technology CAT:Genetics CAT:United States CAT:Turkey"],"categories":[],"templates":[{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dThree scientists share 2015 Chemistry Nobel Prize for DNA repair research Audio Wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-11"]},{"name":"date","description":["October 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Nobel_Prize","description":[]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["Tom Ellenberger"]},{"name":"w","description":["GÃ¶ran K. Hansson"]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal Swedish Academy of Sciences"]},{"name":"w","description":["DNA repair"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tomas Lindahl"]},{"name":"w","description":["Paul L. Modrich","Paul Modrich"]},{"name":"w","description":["Aziz Sancar"]},{"name":"w","description":["DNA"]},{"name":"w","description":["genetics","genetic information"]},{"name":"w","description":["molecule","molecular"]},{"name":"w","description":["base excision repair"]},{"name":"w","description":["molecular biology","molecular biologist"]},{"name":"w","description":["nucleotide excision repair"]},{"name":"w","description":["mutagen","mutagens"]},{"name":"w","description":["ultraviolet radiation"]},{"name":"w","description":["biochemistry"]},{"name":"w","description":["DNA replication"]},{"name":"w","description":["DNA mismatch repair"]},{"name":"w","description":["cell (biology)","cells"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003d2006 Nobel Prize in chemistry for insight into cells","date\u003dOctober 4, 2006"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/announcement.html","title\u003dThe Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - Prize Announcement","author\u003d","pub\u003dNobel Media","date\u003dOctober 8, 2015 (date of access)"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/","title\u003dThe Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - Tomas Lindahl, Paul Modrich, Aziz Sancar","author\u003d","pub\u003dNobel Media","date\u003dOctober 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/press.html","title\u003dThe Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - Press Release","author\u003d","pub\u003dNobel Media","date\u003dOctober 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.wired.com/2015/10/dna-repair-mechanisms-get-nobel-prize-chemistry/?mbid\u003dsocial_twitter","title\u003dDNA Repair Discoveries Get the Nobel Prize in Chemistry","author\u003dKatie M. Palmer","pub\u003dWired (website)","date\u003dOctober 7, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/chemistry/laureates/2015/advanced-chemistryprize2015.pdf","title\u003dScientific Background on the Nobel Prize in Chemistry 2015 - mechanistic studies of DNA repair -","author\u003dClass for Chemistry","pub\u003dRoyal Swedish Academy of Sciences","date\u003dOctober 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"After Mars, NASA announces water ice on Pluto","wikiTitle":"After_Mars,_NASA_announces_water_ice_on_Pluto","wid":2493652,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-19T14:08:56Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dNASA announces water on Mars, date\u003dOctober 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dNASA\u0027s New Horizons space probe performs first close planetary flyby of Pluto, date\u003dJuly 17, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.express.co.uk/news/science/610802/ICE-ON-PLUTO-Frozen-water-and-blue-skies-found-on-dwarf-planet, title\u003dICE ON PLUTO: Now frozen water and BLUE SKY found on dwarf planet giving more hope of life, author\u003dJon Austin, pub\u003dDaily Express, date\u003dOctober 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.nasa.gov/nh/nh-finds-blue-skies-and-water-ice-on-pluto, title\u003dNew Horizons Finds Blue Skies and Water Ice on Pluto, author\u003d, pub\u003dNASA, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.com/news/science-environment-34481347, title\u003dNew Horizons: Probe captures Pluto\u0027s blue hazes, author\u003dJonathan Amos, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/science/2015/oct/06/pluto-charon-photos-nasa-new-horizons-data, title\u003dImages of Pluto and Charon continue to captivate Nasa: \u0027This world is alive\u0027, author\u003d Alan Yuhas, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dOctober 6, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"NASA","description":"NASA"},{"id":"Pluto","description":"Pluto"},{"id":"New_Horizons","description":"New Horizons"},{"id":"Titan","description":"Titan"},{"id":"Saturn","description":"Saturn"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dAfter Mars, NASA announces water ice on Pluto Audio Wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-11] TEMPLATE[space] TEMPLATE[image, NASA] NASA released yesterday the first coloured pictures of Pluto\u0027s blue atmosphere and water ice on the surface taken by the space probe New Horizons.","NASA said the haze particles may be grey or red in colour, but the TEMPLATE[w, Light scattering, scattering of light] producing blue colour indicates the size of the particles. Smaller particles results in the scattering of the blue light. Scientists calls those soot like grey-red particles TEMPLATE[w, tholin, tholins].","The scientists suggest nitrogen and methane in the upper atmosphere, exposed to the Sun\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, ultraviolet radiation], break and combine to form more complex TEMPLATE[w, macromolecule, macromolecules] similar to a  process first observed on Titan, Saturn\u0027s satellite.  Some of them grow to tholins. Eventually they are coated with volatile gas frost and fall to the surface, contributing to its red color.","The data collected from the probe\u0027s Ralph spectral composition mapper shows several small zones of water ice on Pluto. Alex Parker from TEMPLATE[w, Southwest Research institute] (SwRI) tweeted, \"We expected water-ice to be there, but we\u0027ve searched for water-ice in Pluto\u0027s spectrum for decades and not seen it before now\".","\"Who would have expected a blue sky in the Kuiper Belt?\", New Horizons principal investigator Alan Stern of SwRI remarked; \"It\u0027s gorgeous.\"  \"This world is alive [...] It has weather, it has hazes in the atmosphere, active geology.\"","The space probe has traveled over 100 million TEMPLATE[w, kilometre, km] (over 60 million TEMPLATE[w, mile, miles]) further since gathering the data on its Pluto flyby of July 14. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Atmosphere of Pluto]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Space CAT:Pluto CAT:NASA CAT:Physics CAT:United States CAT:North America CAT:Science and technology CAT:Geology"],