{"title":"Three FIFA officials suspended for ninety days","wikiTitle":"Three_FIFA_officials_suspended_for_ninety_days","wid":2493859,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-19T01:04:53Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dFIFA announce Russia to host 2018 World Cup, Qatar to host 2022 World Cup, date\u003dDecember 2, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dFormer F.A. chairman alleges FIFA 2018 World Cup vote was riddled with bribes, corruption, date\u003dMay 11, 2011]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://fifa.com/governance/news/y\u003d2015/m\u003d10/news\u003dofficial-statement-regarding-fifa-s-independent-ethics-committee-decis-2709923.html?intcmp\u003dfifacom_hp_module_news, title\u003dOfficial statement regarding FIFAâs Independent Ethics Committee decisions, author\u003d, pub\u003dFIFA, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34474231, title\u003dFifa: Sepp Blatter, Michel Platini \u0026 Jerome Valcke suspended, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC Sport, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/oct/08/sepp-blatter-suspended-fifa, title\u003dSepp Blatter, Michel Platini and JÃ©rÃ´me Valcke suspended for 90 days, author\u003dOwen Gibson, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dOctober 8, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"FIFA","description":"FIFA"},{"id":"Sepp_Blatter","description":"Sepp Blatter"},{"id":"soccer","description":"football"},{"id":"Switzerland","description":"Swiss"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Sports] TEMPLATE[date, October 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, Press Service of the President of Russia] TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, Enough is enough, source\u003dThomas Bach, IOC President] Three top FIFA (International Federation of Association Football) officials have been suspended from their jobs yesterday for a period of ninety days pending an internal inquiry into alleged corruption. The three are FIFA President Sepp Blatter, Vice President TEMPLATE[w, Michel Platini] and Secretary General TEMPLATE[w, JÃ©rÃ´me Valcke]. They aren\u0027t allowed to participate in football-related activities during their suspensions.","Blatter was going to serve as president until February 2016, although he was elected to a five year term on May 29 this year.","The suspensions have been issued by FIFA\u0027s Independent Ethics Committee, in the wake of the decision of Swiss authorities to investigate possible criminal charges against Blatter. The authorities are looking into an \"unfavourable\" contract signed by Blatter and a \"disloyal payment\" involving Platini. Valcke was already suspended from his job, allegedly involved in a controversy about TEMPLATE[w, FIFA World Cup] tickets. These followed a US investigation in May 2015, which implicated fourteen FIFA employees in bribery and racketeering, and a Swiss inquiry about the conduct of the TEMPLATE[w, 2018 FIFA World Cup, 2018] and TEMPLATE[w, 2022 FIFA World Cup] bidding process.","The ethics committee has the power to increase the length of the suspensions by a further forty five days if it deems this necessary. The suspensions would then end just days before FIFA holds elections for a new president, for which Platini is a possible candidate. However, there have been calls for the reform of FIFA, by major sponsors and the TEMPLATE[w, International Olympic Committee], whose president, TEMPLATE[w, Thomas Bach], said \"enough is enough\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:FIFA","description":"Category:FIFA"},{"id":"Category:Football_(soccer)","description":"Category:Football (soccer)"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Sepp_Blatter","description":"Category:Sepp Blatter"},{"id":"Category:Switzerland","description":"Category:Switzerland"},{"id":"Category:Olympics","description":"Category:Olympics"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"}],"templates":[{"name":"Sports","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["October 9, 2015"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["Press Service of the President of Russia"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["Enough is enough","source\u003dThomas Bach, IOC President"]},{"name":"w","description":["Michel Platini"]},{"name":"w","description":["JÃ©rÃ´me Valcke"]},{"name":"w","description":["FIFA World Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["2018 FIFA World Cup","2018"]},{"name":"w","description":["2022 FIFA World Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["International Olympic Committee"]},{"name":"w","description":["Thomas Bach"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dFIFA announce Russia to host 2018 World Cup, Qatar to host 2022 World Cup","date\u003dDecember 2, 2010"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dFormer F.A. chairman alleges FIFA 2018 World Cup vote was riddled with bribes, corruption","date\u003dMay 11, 2011"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://fifa.com/governance/news/y\u003d2015/m\u003d10/news\u003dofficial-statement-regarding-fifa-s-independent-ethics-committee-decis-2709923.html?intcmp\u003dfifacom_hp_module_news","title\u003dOfficial statement regarding FIFAâs Independent Ethics Committee decisions","author\u003d","pub\u003dFIFA","date\u003dOctober 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/34474231","title\u003dFifa: Sepp Blatter, Michel Platini \u0026 Jerome Valcke suspended","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC Sport","date\u003dOctober 8, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/oct/08/sepp-blatter-suspended-fifa","title\u003dSepp Blatter, Michel Platini and JÃ©rÃ´me Valcke suspended for 90 days","author\u003dOwen Gibson","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dOctober 8, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive"