{"title":"Scottish Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey \u0027critically ill\u0027 says Royal Free Hospital","wikiTitle":"Scottish_Ebola_nurse_Pauline_Cafferkey_\u0027critically_ill\u0027_says_Royal_Free_Hospital","wid":2506784,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-23T20:06:19Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3272304/Ebola-nurse-Pauline-Cafferkey-CRITICALLY-ill.html, title\u003d Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey is CRITICALLY ill as her condition deteriorates, the London isolation unit treating her has revealed, author\u003d Anthony Jospeh, pub\u003d Mail Online, date\u003d October 15, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/14/ebola-nurse-pauline-cafferkey-critically-ill, title\u003d Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey critically ill in deterioration that shocks experts, author\u003d Sarah Boseley, pub\u003d The Guardian, date\u003d October 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-34529575, title\u003d Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey now \u0027critically ill\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003d BBC News Online, date\u003d October 14, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-34499608, title\u003d Family of Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey says she was \u0027let down\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003d BBC News Online, date\u003d October 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Ebola","description":"Ebola"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 15, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dScottish Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey \u0027critically ill\u0027 says Royal Free Hospital Audio Wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-15] TEMPLATE[Health] The TEMPLATE[w, Royal Free Hospital] in TEMPLATE[w, London] yesterday said a nurse suffering with complications after Ebola, Pauline Cafferkey, is \"critically ill\" after her condition deteriorated. Cafferkey, 39, was readmitted to an isolation unit at the Royal Free on the night of October 8\u0026ndash;9 where she had spent time earlier in the year after contracting Ebola in TEMPLATE[w, Sierra Leone] whilst treating patients with the infection.","The hospital said in a statement: \"We are sad to announce that Pauline Cafferkey\u0027s condition has deteriorated and she is now critically ill. She is being treated for Ebola in the high level isolation unit at the Royal Free Hospital.\" TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Ryan4314~commonswiki, User:Ryan4314]]] Cafferkey visited an TEMPLATE[w, out-of-hours service, out of hours GP] clinic on October 5 where her symptoms were not linked to Ebola, before deciding to go to the TEMPLATE[w, Queen Elizabeth University Hospital] in TEMPLATE[w, Glasgow] on October 6 where she was treated at the hospital\u0027s infectious diseases unit. Two days later, she was flown by plane to the Royal Free. She is the only person known to suffer with Ebola in this way for a second time, which can remain in the body after an initial recovery.","Jonathan Ball of the TEMPLATE[w, University of Nottingham] said he\u0027d heard of nothing like this. \"I am not aware from the scientific literature of a case where Ebola has been associated with what we can only assume as life-threatening complications after someone has initially recovered, and certainly not so many months after.\"","Pauline\u0027s sister Toni Cafferkey was critical of the wrong diagnosis, telling the TEMPLATE[w, Sunday Mail (Scotland), Sunday Mail] newspaper, \"At that point me and my family believe they missed a big opportunity to give the right diagnosis and we feel she was let down. Instead of being taken into hospital, she spent the whole of Tuesday very ill\".","A spokesperson for NHS Glasgow and Clyde said Pauline Cafferkey did receive a diagnosis from an out of hours clinic and said: \"Her management and the clinical decisions taken based on the symptoms she was displaying at the time were entirely appropriate.  All appropriate infection control procedures were carried out as part of this episode of care.\"","Experts say they do not believe the infection recurring within Pauline Cafferkey is contagious despite monitoring 58 people she has been in contact with. This is said to be a precaution as Ebola can only be spread through body fluids and the infection is not creating the same symptoms associated with a one-off diagnosis of Ebola.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Ebola virus"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:_October_14,_2015","description":"Category: October 14, 2015"},{"id":"Category:_Europe","description":"Category: Europe"},{"id":"Category:_Scotland","description":"Category: Scotland"},{"id":"Category:_United_Kingdom","description":"Category: United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Infectious_disease","description":"Category:Infectious disease"},{"id":"Category:Health","description":"Category:Health"},{"id":"Category:Disease","description":"Category:Disease"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 15, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dScottish Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey \u0027critically ill\u0027 says Royal Free Hospital Audio Wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-15"]},{"name":"Health","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Royal Free Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["London"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sierra Leone"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Ryan4314~commonswiki","User:Ryan4314]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["out-of-hours service","out of hours GP"]},{"name":"w","description":["Queen Elizabeth University Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["Glasgow"]},{"name":"w","description":["University of Nottingham"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sunday Mail (Scotland)","Sunday Mail"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.dailymail.co.uk/news/article-3272304/Ebola-nurse-Pauline-Cafferkey-CRITICALLY-ill.html","title\u003d Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey is CRITICALLY ill as her condition deteriorates, the London isolation unit treating her has revealed","author\u003d Anthony Jospeh","pub\u003d Mail Online","date\u003d October 15, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/14/ebola-nurse-pauline-cafferkey-critically-ill","title\u003d Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey critically ill in deterioration that shocks experts","author\u003d Sarah Boseley","pub\u003d The Guardian","date\u003d October 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-34529575","title\u003d Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey now \u0027critically ill\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003d BBC News Online","date\u003d October 14, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-34499608","title\u003d Family of Ebola nurse Pauline Cafferkey says she was \u0027let down\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003d BBC News Online","date\u003d October 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Sunday Mail (Scotland), Sunday Mail]"]}
{"title":"Police shut down Edmonton pizza restaurant for illegally delivering alcohol","wikiTitle":"Police_shut_down_Edmonton_pizza_restaurant_for_illegally_delivering_alcohol","wid":2512907,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-09T02:18:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/edmonton-restaurant-caught-delivering-booze-in-pizza-boxes-1.3275512, title\u003dEdmonton restaurant caught delivering booze in pizza boxes, author\u003d, pub\u003dCBC News, date\u003dOctober 16, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://edmonton.ctvnews.ca/pizza-shop-caught-delivering-booze-in-boxes-1.2613848, title\u003dPizza shop caught delivering booze in boxes, author\u003dKim Smith, pub\u003dCTV, date\u003d October 16, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Alberta","description":"Alberta"},{"id":"Canada","description":"Canada"},{"id":"CBC_News","description":"CBC"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dPolice shut down Edmonton pizza restaurant for illegally delivering alcohol audio wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-17] TEMPLATE[Canada]TEMPLATE[w, Edmonton Police Service, Edmonton police] have closed down an TEMPLATE[w, Edmonton], Alberta, Canada pizza restaurant for a single day for delivering TEMPLATE[w, alcoholic beverages] despite not being licensed to do so. It is unclear when this incident occurred, but the CBC reported that it occurred \"recently\", after police searched the shop in September.","The alcohol was being delivered in paper bags and pizza boxes, with the same delivery vehicles used to deliver pizza. Curtis Hoople, a Sergeant in the Edmonton Police Service, says that alcohol was also being sold within the restaurant\u0027s premises.","It is estimated that the seized alcohol was worth around TEMPLATE[w, Canadian dollar, CAD$]4,000, Hoople said.","Four of the restaurant\u0027s employees were issued a summons, and were accused of violating the Gaming and Liquor Act.","Police have not named the restaurant in question.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Alberta","description":"Category:Alberta"},{"id":"Category:Food","description":"Category:Food"},{"id":"Category:Drink","description":"Category:Drink"},{"id":"Category:Culture_and_entertainment","description":"Category:Culture and entertainment"},{"id":"Category:Canada","description":"Category:Canada"},{"id":"Category:Local_only","description":"Category:Local only"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dPolice shut down Edmonton pizza restaurant for illegally delivering alcohol audio wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-17"]},{"name":"Canada","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Edmonton Police Service","Edmonton police"]},{"name":"w","description":["Edmonton"]},{"name":"w","description":["alcoholic beverages"]},{"name":"w","description":["Canadian dollar","CAD$"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/edmonton/edmonton-restaurant-caught-delivering-booze-in-pizza-boxes-1.3275512","title\u003dEdmonton restaurant caught delivering booze in pizza boxes","author\u003d","pub\u003dCBC News","date\u003dOctober 16, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://edmonton.ctvnews.ca/pizza-shop-caught-delivering-booze-in-boxes-1.2613848","title\u003dPizza shop caught delivering booze in boxes","author\u003dKim Smith","pub\u003dCTV","date\u003d October 16, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
