{"title":"Searchers find wreckage of New Zealand fishing boat \u0027Jubilee\u0027","wikiTitle":"Searchers_find_wreckage_of_New_Zealand_fishing_boat_\u0027Jubilee\u0027","wid":2516838,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-27T22:19:07Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.stuff.co.nz/the-press/news/mid-canterbury-selwyn/73135401/search-continues-for-missing-fishermen, title\u003dMissing fishermen presumed drowned after lifeboat found empty, author\u003dGeorgina Campbell, pub\u003dStuff.co.nz, date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://m.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id\u003d1\u0026objectid\u003d11531232, title\u003dSearch continues for fishermen, author\u003dVaimoana Tapaleao; John Weekes, pub\u003dThe New Zealand Herald, date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.radionz.co.nz/news/regional/287361/boat%27s-sinking-is-a-%27mystery%27,-says-owner, title\u003dBoat\u0027s owner says sudden sinking a \u0027mystery\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dRadio New Zealand, date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"New_Zealand","description":"New Zealand"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 19, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dSearchers find wreckage of New Zealand fishing boat \u0027Jubilee\u0027 spoken wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-19] TEMPLATE[New_Zealand] TEMPLATE[image_credit, [http://www.flickr.com/people/42033648@N00 Phillip Capper]] Searchers looking for New Zealand fishing boat FV Jubilee found the vessel on the sea floor overnight local time (TEMPLATE[w, UTC+13]).","The search was sparked by a mayday call from the three-man crew early yesterday morning. The three fishermen said they were abandoning ship in favour of a lifeboat. The search, which covered roughly 170 TEMPLATE[w, square kilometre, square km], earlier located an empty lifeboat from FV Jubilee.","A police dive team was sent today to look for bodies. Police and owner-operator Ocean Fisheries believe the missing men are deceased. Weather conditions at the site, around 40 TEMPLATE[w, metre, m] deep and 22 TEMPLATE[w, kilometre, km] from the TEMPLATE[w, Rakaia River] mouth, are reported with dropping wind and swells of 1.5 m.","\"The sea conditions were rough,\" said Ocean Fisheries boss Andrew Stark; \"without knowing what was going wrong with the vessel we really can\u0027t speculate, whether the sea was a cause or a contributing factor. Rough conditions are usual at sea, so we don\u0027t believe the weather was severe enough to be the main contributing factor. There must have been something involved prior to that which caused the vessel to sink.\"","Stark said the accident is \"a mystery\". He said the company had trawled the area with other ships in the hope of retrieving corpses from the sea bed. In addition to Ocean Fisheries boats FV Legacy and FV Frontier, which used technology designed for locating fish to search for the wreck, search vehicles included a helicopter, a plane, and two Coastguard vessels. An emergency beacon, oil, fishing bins, and documentation are among the floating debris found.","Launched in January 2008, FV Jubilee is 16 m long and weighs 100 TEMPLATE[w, tonne, t].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:New_Zealand","description":"Category:New Zealand"},{"id":"Category:Merchant_shipping","description":"Category:Merchant shipping"},{"id":"Category:Missing_persons","description":"Category:Missing persons"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dSearchers find wreckage of New Zealand fishing boat \u0027Jubilee\u0027 spoken wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-19"]},{"name":"New_Zealand","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[http://www.flickr.com/people/42033648@N00 Phillip Capper]"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+13"]},{"name":"w","description":["square kilometre","square km"]},{"name":"w","description":["metre","m"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometre","km"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rakaia River"]},{"name":"w","description":["tonne","t"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.stuff.co.nz/the-press/news/mid-canterbury-selwyn/73135401/search-continues-for-missing-fishermen","title\u003dMissing fishermen presumed drowned after lifeboat found empty","author\u003dGeorgina Campbell","pub\u003dStuff.co.nz","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://m.nzherald.co.nz/nz/news/article.cfm?c_id\u003d1\u0026objectid\u003d11531232","title\u003dSearch continues for fishermen","author\u003dVaimoana Tapaleao; John Weekes","pub\u003dThe New Zealand Herald","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.radionz.co.nz/news/regional/287361/boat%27s-sinking-is-a-%27mystery%27,-says-owner","title\u003dBoat\u0027s owner says sudden sinking a \u0027mystery\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dRadio New Zealand","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Jubilee","Jubilee","Legacy","Frontier","Jubilee"]}
{"title":"Typhoon Koppu makes landfall in the Philippines, displacing at least 16,000","wikiTitle":"Typhoon_Koppu_makes_landfall_in_the_Philippines,_displacing_at_least_16,000","wid":2516970,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-10-28T15:30:36Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/world/philippines-typhoon-koppu-1.3276871?cmp\u003drss, title\u003dTyphoon Koppu kills at least 2 in Philippines, author\u003d[[Associated Press]], pub\u003dCBC News, date\u003dOctober 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/10/18/asia/typhoon-koppu-lando-philippines/index.html?eref\u003drss_world, title\u003dThousands displaced as Typhoon Koppu pummels northern Philippines, author\u003dJethro Mullen and Chieu Luu, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dOctober 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.pna.gov.ph/index.php?idn\u003d\u0026sid\u003d\u0026nid\u003d\u0026rid\u003d816605, title\u003d1 killed, four others hurt as \u0027Lando\u0027 toppled trees in QC, author\u003d, pub\u003dPhilippines News Agency, date\u003dOctober 18, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Philippines","description":"Philippines"},{"id":"Manila","description":"Manila"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 19, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dTyphoon Koppu makes landfall in the Philippines, displacing at least 16,000 audio wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-20] TEMPLATE[Disasters_and_accidents]TEMPLATE[w, Typhoon Koppu (2015), Typhoon Koppu], known additionally as Lando, made landfall in the northern Philippines on Sunday, killing at least two and displacing at least 16,000 people.","The deadly storm caused a concrete wall in a home in TEMPLATE[w, Subic, Zambales] to topple over, killing a 62-year-old woman and injuring her husband. A 14-year-old teenager was killed after being fatally pinned down in Manila by a tree which got knocked over. The same fallen tree injured four others, including a three-year-old. The tree additionally damaged three nearby houses.","The injured people were sent to the East Avenue Medical Centre for treatment.","The typhoon made landfall in the town of TEMPLATE[w, Casiguran, Aurora, Casiguran], a town with a population of 25,000 in the province of TEMPLATE[w, Aurora (province), Aurora]. Subsequently it ripped roofs off of houses, uprooted trees, and knocked down power lines. Nine provinces were left without electricity. Flash floods and landslides heavily damaged roads, and as a result 25 roads were made impassable.","The army attempted to clear routes leading to Casiguran, according to the state-owned Philippines News Agency. Nigel Lontoc, an employee of the TEMPLATE[w, Office of Civil Defense (Philippines), Office of Civil Defense] said that some residents were trapped on rooftops in the province of TEMPLATE[w, Nueva Ecija]. Troops were sent to that location as a part of a rescue operation.","The typhoon weakened as it moved over land, and weather improved in some regions. Officials urged residents to be cautious since Koppu may still cause landslides and flash floods.","Alexander Pama, Executive Director of the TEMPLATE[w, National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council], said that they were asking their countrymen \"not to become complacent.\"","The typhoon is expected to move slowly over the Philippines, causing large amounts of rainfall.","This year, Koppu is the twelfth typhoon to hit the Philippines, where around 20 typhoons make landfall per year.","Bob Henson, weather blogger from TEMPLATE[w, Weather Underground (weather service), Weather Underground], said that the Philippines is considered to be \"the most vulnerable large nation on earth for tropical cyclones.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Weather","description":"Category:Weather"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Philippines","description":"Category:Philippines"},{"id":"Category:Natural_disasters","description":"Category:Natural disasters"},{"id":"Category:Hurricane","description":"Category:Hurricane"},{"id":"Category:Manila","description":"Category:Manila"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dTyphoon Koppu makes landfall in the Philippines, displacing at least 16,000 audio wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-20"]},{"name":"Disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Typhoon Koppu (2015)","Typhoon Koppu"]},{"name":"w","description":["Subic, Zambales"]},{"name":"w","description":["Casiguran, Aurora","Casiguran"]},{"name":"w","description":["Aurora (province)","Aurora"]},{"name":"w","description":["Office of Civil Defense (Philippines)","Office of Civil Defense"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nueva Ecija"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Disaster Risk Reduction and Management Council"]},{"name":"w","description":["Weather Underground (weather service)","Weather Underground"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cbc.ca/news/world/philippines-typhoon-koppu-1.3276871?cmp\u003drss","title\u003dTyphoon Koppu kills at least 2 in Philippines","author\u003d[[Associated Press]]","pub\u003dCBC News","date\u003dOctober 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/10/18/asia/typhoon-koppu-lando-philippines/index.html?eref\u003drss_world","title\u003dThousands displaced as Typhoon Koppu pummels northern Philippines","author\u003dJethro Mullen and Chieu Luu","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dOctober 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.pna.gov.ph/index.php?idn\u003d\u0026sid\u003d\u0026nid\u003d\u0026rid\u003d816605","title\u003d1 killed, four others hurt as \u0027Lando\u0027 toppled trees in QC","author\u003d","pub\u003dPhilippines News Agency","date\u003dOctober 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Indian cricketer Sehwag announces international retirement","wikiTitle":"Indian_cricketer_Sehwag_announces_international_retirement","wid":2520008,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-04T17:12:15Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.firstpost.com/sports/for-virender-sehwag-cricket-was-all-about-joy-and-being-in-the-moment-2475926.html, title\u003dFor Sehwag, the only ball that mattered was the one he was about to face, author\u003dTariq Engineer, pub\u003dFirstpost, date\u003dOctober 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/virendersehwag/status/656402033289904128, title\u003dVirender Sehwag on Twitter, author\u003dVirender Sehwag, pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dOctober 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.skysports.com/cricket/news/12344/10035950/virender-sehwag-will-not-play-in-indian-premier-league, title\u003dIndia legend Virender Sehwag retires from international cricket, author\u003d, pub\u003dSky Sports, date\u003dOctober 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bangaloremirror.com/sports/cricket/Cricketing-fraternity-congratulates-Sehwag-on-his-career/articleshow/49470276.cms?, title\u003dCricketing fraternity congratulates Sehwag on his career, author\u003d, pub\u003dBangalore Mirror, date\u003dOctober 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/cricket/34579839, title\u003dVirender Sehwag: India opener retires from international cricket, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC Sport, date\u003dOctober 20, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"India","description":"Indian"},{"id":"cricket","description":"cricketer"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[cricket] TEMPLATE[Image, Flying Cloud]  Indian cricketer TEMPLATE[w, Virender Sehwag] yesterday announced his retirement from TEMPLATE[w, International cricket, international cricket matches] and the next TEMPLATE[w, Indian Premier League] season. TEMPLATE[w, Batting order (cricket), Opener] Sehwag played his last TEMPLATE[w, Test cricket, test match] in March 2013 against TEMPLATE[w, Australia national cricket team, Australia]. He scored 8,586 runs, including 23 TEMPLATE[w, century (cricket), centuries], in 104 test matches, with a TEMPLATE[w, Batting average (Cricket), batting average] of 49.34.","Sehwag, who turned 37 yesterday, said on Twitter \"I hereby retire from all forms of international cricket and from the Indian Premier League. A statement will follow.\" He stated he has not retired from TEMPLATE[w, first-class cricket] matches, and he is also scheduled to appear in the TEMPLATE[w, Masters Champions League] in February 2016.","Also known as the Nawab of Najafgarh, Sehwag is the only Indian cricketer to score a triple century in test matches, making 309 runs against TEMPLATE[w, Pakistan national cricket team, Pakistan] in 2004 and 319 against TEMPLATE[w, South Africa national cricket team, South Africa] in 2008.","Sehwag stated, \"I have always done what I felt was right and not what conformists thought to be right [...] God has been kind and I have done what I wanted to do, on the field and in my life, and I had decided some time back that I will retire on my 37th birthday.\"","Fellow Indian cricketers praised Sehwag when news of his retirement broke.  TEMPLATE[w, Sachin Tendulkar] referred to Sehwag\u0027s \"tremendous achievements\" and \"superlative performances\", TEMPLATE[w, V. V. S. Laxman] called him \"a pure entertainer\", and TEMPLATE[w, Ajinkya Rahane] described him as \"an inspiration to billions of cricket fans across the world.\"","TEMPLATE[clear]TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Cricket CAT:Sports CAT:India CAT:Asia"],"categories":[],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 21, 2015"]},{"name":"cricket","description":[]},{"name":"Image","description":["Flying Cloud"]},{"name":"w","description":["Virender Sehwag"]},{"name":"w","description":["International cricket","international cricket matches"]},{"name":"w","description":["Indian Premier League"]},{"name":"w","description":["Batting order (cricket)","Opener"]},{"name":"w","description":["Test cricket","test match"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australia national cricket team","Australia"]},{"name":"w","description":["century (cricket)","centuries"]},{"name":"w","description":["Batting average (Cricket)","batting average"]},{"name":"w","description":["first-class cricket"]},{"name":"w","description":["Masters Champions League"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pakistan national cricket team","Pakistan"]},{"name":"w","description":["South Africa national cricket team","South Africa"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sachin Tendulkar"]},{"name":"w","description":["V. V. S. Laxman"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ajinkya Rahane"]},{"name":"clear","description":[]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.firstpost.com/sports/for-virender-sehwag-cricket-was-all-about-joy-and-being-in-the-moment-2475926.html","title\u003dFor Sehwag, the only ball that mattered was the one he was about to face","author\u003dTariq Engineer","pub\u003dFirstpost","date\u003dOctober 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/virendersehwag/status/656402033289904128","title\u003dVirender Sehwag on Twitter","author\u003dVirender Sehwag","pub\u003dTwitter","date\u003dOctober 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.skysports.com/cricket/news/12344/10035950/virender-sehwag-will-not-play-in-indian-premier-league","title\u003dIndia legend Virender Sehwag retires from international cricket","author\u003d","pub\u003dSky Sports","date\u003dOctober 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bangaloremirror.com/sports/cricket/Cricketing-fraternity-congratulates-Sehwag-on-his-career/articleshow/49470276.cms?","title\u003dCricketing fraternity congratulates Sehwag on his career","author\u003d","pub\u003dBangalore Mirror","date\u003dOctober 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/cricket/34579839","title\u003dVirender Sehwag: India opener retires from international cricket","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC Sport","date\u003dOctober 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"London serial murder accused Stephen Port makes first court appearance","wikiTitle":"London_serial_murder_accused_Stephen_Port_makes_first_court_appearance","wid":2520381,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-11-25T11:08:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/11939792/Barking-man-charged-with-murdering-four-young-men-by-poisoning.html, title\u003dMan appears in court charged with four poison murders, author\u003dMartin Evans, pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (United Kingdom), date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/oct/19/man-charged-with-by-poisoning-of-four-men-in-east-london, title\u003dMan charged with murder and poisoning of four men in east London, author\u003dVikram Dodd, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/10/19/man-charged-with-murder-of-four-men-he-met-on-gay-dating-sites/, title\u003dMan charged with murder of four men he âmet on gay dating sitesâ, author\u003dNick Duffy, pub\u003dPinkNews, date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-34568485, title\u003dSerial killer suspect Stephen Port \u0027drugged victims\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dOctober 19, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"Stephen_Port","description":"Stephen Port"},{"id":"Metropolitan_Police","description":"Metropolitan Police"},{"id":"Independent_Police_Complaints_Commission","description":"Independent Police Complaints Commission"},{"id":"Mental_health","description":"Special needs"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 20, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dLondon serial murder accused Stephen Port makes first court appearance audio wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-20] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] A London man charged on Sunday with drugging and murdering four men made his first court appearance yesterday. Stephen Port, 40, was remanded to appear before a higher court tomorrow. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[commons:User:Man vyi, \"Man vyi\"]]] Port faces four counts of murder and four counts of \"administering a poison with intent to endanger life or inflict TEMPLATE[w, grievous bodily harm]\". He is alleged to have administered overdoses of recreational drug TEMPLATE[w, gamma-Hydroxybutyric acid, GHB]. He allegedly murdered the men at his home before dumping the bodies, after finding victims online using TEMPLATE[w, homosexual, gay] dating services.","Three of the deaths were last year. Anthony Patrick Walgate, 23, was found dead on June 19, 2014 in Cooke Street. Port lives in Cooke Street. The other three alleged victims were found in the vicinity of St Margaret\u0027s Church on North Street. Gabriel Kovari, 22, was discovered dead on August 28. Daniel Whitworth, 21, was found dead the following month on September 20. Fourth alleged victim Jack Taylor, 25, was found a year later on September 14.","Whitworth and Kovari were known to each other, according to testimony at inquest. The Metropolitan Police has referred itself to the Independent Police Complaints Commission concerning what police called \"potential vulnerabilities in [our response] to the four deaths.\" Police did not initially link the deaths.","Special needs teacher Port, who was guarded by three officers in the dock, spoke in court to confirm his identity. He did not indicate if he will deny the offences. He was arrested following a police appeal to trace a man seen with Taylor shortly before his death.","Police at the time released security footage of Taylor\u0027s movements, with an officer telling the press \"the man captured on TEMPLATE[w, CCTV] may well be the last person to talk to Jack.\" The four deaths were finally linked and passed to the Metropolitan Police\u0027s serious crime investigators on Wednesday last week.","The Magistrates\u0027 Court ordered Taylor to appear at the TEMPLATE[w, Old Bailey], a famed London courthouse, tomorrow. He spent the hearing holding one arm, and repeatedly looking at the floor, whilst clad in a grey tracksuit given to him by the authorities holding him. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:Metropolitan_Police","description":"Category:Metropolitan Police"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Drugs","description":"Category:Drugs"},{"id":"Category:Serial_killers","description":"Category:Serial killers"},{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Independent_Police_Complaints_Commission","description":"Category:Independent Police Complaints Commission"},{"id":"Category:Stephen_Port","description":"Category:Stephen Port"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dLondon serial murder accused Stephen Port makes first court appearance audio wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-20"]},{"name":"Crime_and_law","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[commons:User:Man vyi","\"Man vyi\"]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["grievous bodily harm"]},{"name":"w","description":["gamma-Hydroxybutyric acid","GHB"]},{"name":"w","description":["homosexual","gay"]},{"name":"w","description":["CCTV"]},{"name":"w","description":["Old Bailey"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/uknews/crime/11939792/Barking-man-charged-with-murdering-four-young-men-by-poisoning.html","title\u003dMan appears in court charged with four poison murders","author\u003dMartin Evans","pub\u003dThe Daily Telegraph (United Kingdom)","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/uk-news/2015/oct/19/man-charged-with-by-poisoning-of-four-men-in-east-london","title\u003dMan charged with murder and poisoning of four men in east London","author\u003dVikram Dodd","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.pinknews.co.uk/2015/10/19/man-charged-with-murder-of-four-men-he-met-on-gay-dating-sites/","title\u003dMan charged with murder of four men he âmet on gay dating sitesâ","author\u003dNick Duffy","pub\u003dPinkNews","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-34568485","title\u003dSerial killer suspect Stephen Port \u0027drugged victims\u0027","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dOctober 19, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Former Miss Austria Ena Kadic dies after mountain fall","wikiTitle":"Former_Miss_Austria_Ena_Kadic_dies_after_mountain_fall","wid":2526406,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-05T14:18:17Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thelocal.at/20151020/beauty-queen-dies-after-jogging-fall, title\u003dBeauty queen dies after mountain fall, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Local, date\u003dOctober 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/miss-austria-winner-ena-kadic-dies-after-falling-from-the-side-of-a-mountain-a6701441.html, title\u003dMiss Austria winner Ena Kadic dies after falling from the side of a mountain, author\u003dHeather Saul, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dOctober 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.miss-austria.at/index.php?id\u003d48\u0026(TEMPLATE)\u003d587\u0026cHash\u003d70c04ff7ec1fb0aff41796b8d6a28ff3, title\u003dMiss Ãsterreich 2013, author\u003d, pub\u003dMiss Austria, date\u003dJuly 24, 2013, lang\u003dGerman]"]],"links":[{"id":"Austria","description":"Austria"},{"id":"sports","description":"sports"},{"id":"Indonesia","description":"Indonesia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dFormer Miss Austria Ena KadiÄ dies after mountain fall spoken wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-22] TEMPLATE[Austria] TEMPLATE[w, Ena KadiÄ], an Austrian woman who won the 2013 TEMPLATE[w, Miss Austria] crown, died early this week in hospital. She was 26 and fell whilst jogging in the Austrian TEMPLATE[w, Alps] on Friday. TEMPLATE[image_credit, Miss Austria Corp] KadiÄ fell roughly 30TEMPLATE[w, metre, m] down the TEMPLATE[w, Bergisel] mountain in TEMPLATE[w, Tyrol], near TEMPLATE[w, Innsbruck] where she worked. She was taken to TEMPLATE[w, Innsbruck University Hospital] with injuries to her head, pelvis, and lung. Remaining conscious after the fall, she had alerted her family via telephone who in turn contacted emergency services.","She was found near the Drachenfelsen platform, which overlooks the TEMPLATE[w, River Sill]. Police said she knew the area and enjoyed running; a profile on the Miss Austria website said she was into sports and nature.","The brown-haired, green-eyed beauty\u0027s looks took her to compete in TEMPLATE[w, Bali], Indonesia in 2013. Thereafter she shunned publicity and worked in a fashion store. \"The media, the events, the parties \u0026mdash; that life made me so unhappy,\" she said this year in a TEMPLATE[w, Seitenblicke] interview.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Sports","description":"Category:Sports"},{"id":"Category:Obituaries","description":"Category:Obituaries"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Austria","description":"Category:Austria"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia","description":"Category:Indonesia"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 22, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dFormer Miss Austria Ena KadiÄ dies after mountain fall spoken wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-22"]},{"name":"Austria","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Ena KadiÄ"]},{"name":"w","description":["Miss Austria"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alps"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["Miss Austria Corp"]},{"name":"w","description":["metre","m"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bergisel"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tyrol"]},{"name":"w","description":["Innsbruck"]},{"name":"w","description":["Innsbruck University Hospital"]},{"name":"w","description":["River Sill"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bali"]},{"name":"w","description":["Seitenblicke"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.thelocal.at/20151020/beauty-queen-dies-after-jogging-fall","title\u003dBeauty queen dies after mountain fall","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Local","date\u003dOctober 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/miss-austria-winner-ena-kadic-dies-after-falling-from-the-side-of-a-mountain-a6701441.html","title\u003dMiss Austria winner Ena Kadic dies after falling from the side of a mountain","author\u003dHeather Saul","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dOctober 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttps://www.miss-austria.at/index.php?id\u003d48\u0026(TEMPLATE)\u003d587\u0026cHash\u003d70c04ff7ec1fb0aff41796b8d6a28ff3","title\u003dMiss Ãsterreich 2013","author\u003d","pub\u003dMiss Austria","date\u003dJuly 24, 2013","lang\u003dGerman"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","lang"],"highlights":["TEMPLATE[w, Seitenblicke]"]}
{"title":"Masked man kills two in sword attack at Swedish school","wikiTitle":"Masked_man_kills_two_in_sword_attack_at_Swedish_school","wid":2527020,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-23T23:23:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/sweden-school-attack-sword-wielding-man-posed-for-pictures-with-pupils-before-killing-child-and-a6704566.html, title\u003dSweden school attack: Sword-wielding man \u0027posed for pictures with pupils\u0027 before killing child and teacher, author\u003dLizzie Dearden, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dOctober 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/22/pupils-wounded-in-sword-attack-at-swedish-school, title\u003dSweden school attack: horror as sword attacker kills teacher and pupil, author\u003dDavid Crouch, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dOctober 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://expo.se/2015/school-killer-showed-far-right-sympathies-on-social-media_6955.html, title\u003dSchool killer showed far-right sympathies on social media, author\u003d Maria-Pia Cabero, Jonathan Leman, and Alex Bengtsson; translation: Morgan FinnsiÃ¶, pub\u003dExpo (magazine), date\u003dOctober 22, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"The_Guardian","description":"The Guardian"},{"id":"YouTube","description":"YouTube"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 23, 2015] TEMPLATE[Audio_box_2, filename\u003dMasked man kills two in sword attack at Swedish school spoken wikinews.wav, text\u003dListen to this article, date\u003d2015-10-23] TEMPLATE[Sweden]A masked man killed a teacher and an 11 year old student in a sword attack at a school in TEMPLATE[w, TrollhÃ¤ttan, Sweden] yesterday, before police who arrived at the scene fatally shot him.","The teacher died on the scene, while the student was sent to a hospital before he died.","In addition, three others have been injured in the sword attacks. The injured, who are hovering \"between life and death\" according to Doctor Lars Spetz, have been sent to the TEMPLATE[w, Norra Ãlvsborgs LÃ¤nssjukhus] hospital for treatment.","TEMPLATE[QuoteRight, It is a black day for Sweden., 4\u003d(TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE)] \"It is a black day for Sweden,\" TEMPLATE[w, Stefan LÃ¶fven], TEMPLATE[w, Prime Minister of Sweden], who later visited the school, said in response to the attack.","Bo Johansson, head of the TEMPLATE[w, Swedish Teachers\u0027 Union], expressed concern that schools are too open. Johansson said that schools should not be so open that \"anyone can walk in,\" even though \"of course schools should be open to society.\"","The school in question, Kronan, had a high immigrant population, The Guardian reported. Expo, a non-profit anti-racist organization which publishes the TEMPLATE[w, Expo (magazine), Expo magazine], said online that authorities are \"investigating a possible political motive,\" citing unspecified sources. Expo adds that the attacker may have held TEMPLATE[w, racist] views, stating that he had shown \"clear sympathies for extreme right-wing and anti-immigrant movements,\" and that the attacker has \"\u0027liked\u0027 videos glorifying TEMPLATE[w, Nazi Germany]\" on the online video sharing site YouTube.","The man, dressed like the TEMPLATE[w, Star Wars, \u0027\u0027Star Wars\u0027\u0027] character TEMPLATE[w, Darth Vader], posed for a photo with students, who believed that he was pulling an early Halloween prank, before he started attacking others with a sword. A student who attends the school said that fellow students \"initially thought it was a joke.\" The photo showed the man holding a sword and wearing a helmet.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, TrollhÃ¤ttan school attack]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Sweden","description":"Category:Sweden"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Education","description":"Category:Education"},{"id":"Category:Halloween","description":"Category:Halloween"},{"id":"Category:Star_Wars","description":"Category:Star Wars"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Audio_box_2","description":["filename\u003dMasked man kills two in sword attack at Swedish school spoken wikinews.wav","text\u003dListen to this article","date\u003d2015-10-23"]},{"name":"Sweden","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["TrollhÃ¤ttan, Sweden"]},{"name":"w","description":["Norra Ãlvsborgs LÃ¤nssjukhus"]},{"name":"QuoteRight","description":["It is a black day for Sweden.","4\u003d(TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE)"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prime Minister of Sweden"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stefan LÃ¶fven"]},{"name":"w","description":["Prime Minister of Sweden"]},{"name":"w","description":["Swedish Teachers\u0027 Union"]},{"name":"w","description":["Expo (magazine)","Expo magazine"]},{"name":"w","description":["racist"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nazi Germany"]},{"name":"w","description":["Star Wars","\u0027\u0027Star Wars\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["Darth Vader"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","TrollhÃ¤ttan school attack"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/sweden-school-attack-sword-wielding-man-posed-for-pictures-with-pupils-before-killing-child-and-a6704566.html","title\u003dSweden school attack: Sword-wielding man \u0027posed for pictures with pupils\u0027 before killing child and teacher","author\u003dLizzie Dearden","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dOctober 22, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/22/pupils-wounded-in-sword-attack-at-swedish-school","title\u003dSweden school attack: horror as sword attacker kills teacher and pupil","author\u003dDavid Crouch","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dOctober 22, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://expo.se/2015/school-killer-showed-far-right-sympathies-on-social-media_6955.html","title\u003dSchool killer showed far-right sympathies on social media","author\u003d Maria-Pia Cabero, Jonathan Leman, and Alex Bengtsson; translation: Morgan FinnsiÃ¶","pub\u003dExpo (magazine)","date\u003dOctober 22, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["filename","text","date","4","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["The Guardian","TEMPLATE[w, Expo (magazine), Expo magazine]"]}
{"title":"Magnitude 7.5 earthquake hits Afghanistan","wikiTitle":"Magnitude_7.5_earthquake_hits_Afghanistan","wid":2535767,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-02-21T12:02:29Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://indianexpress.com/article/india/india-news-india/earthquake-rocks-north-india/, title\u003dDeath toll rises to 311 in quake-hit Pakistan, Afghanistan areas, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Indian Express, date\u003dOctober 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.huffingtonpost.in/2015/10/26/earthquake-pakistan-india_n_8388054.html, title\u003dEarthquake Strikes Afghanistan; Tremors Felt In Pakistan, Northern India, author\u003dIndrani Basu, pub\u003dThe Huffington Post, date\u003dOctober 26, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/International/wireStory/latest-strong-afghan-earthquake-felt-south-asia-34730075, title\u003dThe Latest: UN Mobilizing to Aid Quake Victims, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dABC News (United States), date\u003dOctober 26, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Afghanistan","description":"Afghanistan"},{"id":"Pakistan","description":"Pakistan"},{"id":"Rajasthan","description":"Rajasthan"},{"id":"United_States_Geological_Survey","description":"United States Geological Survey"},{"id":"Punjab_(India)","description":"Punjab"},{"id":"Jammu_and_Kashmir","description":"Jammu and Kashmir"},{"id":"Narendra_Modi","description":"Narendra Modi"},{"id":"Nawaz_Sharif","description":"Nawaz Sharif"},{"id":"twitter","description":"tweeted"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Effects in Behror and nearby areas","Sister link","Realted news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 27, 2015] TEMPLATE[Disasters_and_accidents] Early yesterday afternoon local time, a 7.5 magnitude earthquake hit Afghanistan, Pakistan and TEMPLATE[w, North India], with its TEMPLATE[wikt, epicenter] in the TEMPLATE[w, Hindu Kush] mountain range which stretches from Afghanistan to North Pakistan, causing damage to life and buildings. A Wikinews correspondent felt the shock waves in TEMPLATE[w, Behror], Rajasthan at 2:50 PM TEMPLATE[w, India Standard Time, IST] (0920 TEMPLATE[w, UTC]).","Hundreds of people died in this disaster. The death toll is highest in Pakistan. Pakistani officials yesterday afternoon declared over 145 people were found dead. United States Geological Survey reported the earthquake occurred at 212TEMPLATE[w, kilometre, km] depth due to TEMPLATE[w, reverse fault, reverse faulting]. Twelve students died in the rush due to trembles, in an Afghani girls\u0027 school in TEMPLATE[w, Takhar Province, Takhar], near TEMPLATE[w, Badakhshan]. Two elderly women in Kashmir died due to TEMPLATE[wikt, heart attack]. Some people in Pakistan died by crushing by roof collapse.","Indian states Punjab, Jammu and Kashmir, Rajasthan, TEMPLATE[W, Uttar Pradesh] and Delhi TEMPLATE[w, National Capital Region (India), National Capital Region] were affected. TEMPLATE[w, Srinagar] experienced a power cutoff after the earthquake.","During yesterday afternoon, Indian Prime minister Narendra Modi communicated with Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif, volunteering help. He also tweeted \"Heard about strong earthquake in Afghanistan-Pakistan region whose tremors have been felt in parts of India. I pray for everyone\u0027s safety.\"","Yesterday evening, TEMPLATE[w, Pervez Rashid], TEMPLATE[w, Minister of Information and Broadcasting (Pakistan), Pakistani Information Minister], declared Pakistan would not ask for help for resources and rescue work and thanked India for offering help.  \"We have enough resources to handle the situation. Our top priority is to help those affected because of the earthquake\".","As of earlier today, officials in Pakistan and Afghanistan came up with statistics of 237 deaths in Pakistan and a total rising to 311.","Almost a decade ago, this region suffered an earthquake with a magnitude of 7.6.","A Wikinews correspondent reports the tremors were felt in Behror, Rajasthan at 2:50 PM IST. In the boys hostel on NIIT University, the students felt the vibrations of cupboards, tables and beds which lasted over a minute. Nobody was harmed because of the shock-waves, but many students came out of their rooms, asking others whether they felt the vibrations or not.","Our correspondent contacted other students in affected areas of India.  According to one student the projectors used for delivering lectures in TEMPLATE[w, BITS Pilani] university in TEMPLATE[W, Pilani], Rajasthan started shaking. The students asked the professor to cancel the lecture. A first year B. Tech student said he was in the library, listening to music, when suddenly everyone ran out. Later, when he got out of the library, he came to know it was an earthquake.","Students in TEMPLATE[w, ITM University, Gurgaon, Haryana, ITM Gurgaon] in TEMPLATE[w, Gurgaon], TEMPLATE[w, Haryana] were asked to shelter themselves in an open space of the sports ground and return after few minutes. Many of the students left for their home.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, 2015 Hindu Kush earthquake]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, Strong earthquake hits Pakistan, north India, Afghanistan, October 8, 2005]","TEMPLATE[original]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Earthquakes","description":"Category:Earthquakes"},{"id":"Category:Afghanistan","description":"Category:Afghanistan"},{"id":"Category:India","description":"Category:India"},{"id":"Category:Pakistan","description":"Category:Pakistan"},{"id":"Category:Tajikistan","description":"Category:Tajikistan"},{"id":"Category:Punjab_(India)","description":"Category:Punjab (India)"},{"id":"Category:Punjab_(Pakistan)","description":"Category:Punjab (Pakistan)"},{"id":"Category:Rajasthan","description":"Category:Rajasthan"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Delhi","description":"Category:Delhi"},{"id":"Category:Jammu_and_Kashmir","description":"Category:Jammu and Kashmir"},{"id":"Category:Kabul,_Afghanistan","description":"Category:Kabul, Afghanistan"},{"id":"Category:Islamabad","description":"Category:Islamabad"},{"id":"Category:Narendra_Modi","description":"Category:Narendra Modi"},{"id":"Category:Nawaz_Sharif","description":"Category:Nawaz Sharif"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Haryana","description":"Category:Haryana"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 27, 2015"]},{"name":"Disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["North India"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["epicenter"]},{"name":"w","description":["Hindu Kush"]},{"name":"w","description":["Behror"]},{"name":"w","description":["India Standard Time","IST"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometre","km"]},{"name":"w","description":["reverse fault","reverse faulting"]},{"name":"w","description":["Takhar Province","Takhar"]},{"name":"w","description":["Badakhshan"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["heart attack"]},{"name":"W","description":["Uttar Pradesh"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Capital Region (India)","National Capital Region"]},{"name":"w","description":["Srinagar"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pervez Rashid"]},{"name":"w","description":["Minister of Information and Broadcasting (Pakistan)","Pakistani Information Minister"]},{"name":"w","description":["BITS Pilani"]},{"name":"W","description":["Pilani"]},{"name":"w","description":["ITM University, Gurgaon, Haryana","ITM Gurgaon"]},{"name":"w","description":["Gurgaon"]},{"name":"w","description":["Haryana"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","2015 Hindu Kush earthquake"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["Strong earthquake hits Pakistan, north India, Afghanistan","October 8, 2005"]},{"name":"original","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://indianexpress.com/article/india/in