{"title":"Romanian nightclub fire kills over two dozen","wikiTitle":"Romanian_nightclub_fire_kills_over_two_dozen","wid":2546044,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-25T01:47:09Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34684973, title\u003dBucharest nightclub fire leaves Romania stunned, pub\u003dBBC News, date\u003dOctober 31, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/bucharest-nightclub-fire-deaths-killed-injured-colectiv-strada-tabacarilor-a6715846.html, title\u003dBucharest nightclub fire: At least 26 killed and over 150 injured in fire at Colectiv nightclub in Romania, author\u003dDoug Bolton, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dOctober 30, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/30/dozens-killed-explosion-bucharest-nightclub, title\u003dDozens killed after explosion at Bucharest nightclub, author\u003dKit Gillet, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dOctober 30, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Bucharest,_Romania","description":"Bucharest"},{"id":"Romania","description":"Romania"},{"id":"Facebook","description":"Facebook"},{"id":"Reuters","description":"Reuters"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, October 31, 2015] TEMPLATE[Romania] Officials said at least 27 people are dead and 155 injured after TEMPLATE[w, pyrotechnic] effects used at the Colectiv TEMPLATE[w, nightclub] in Bucharest, Romania reportedly malfunctioned yesterday, sparking a fire.","The club was hosting an album launch party which attracted hundreds of attendees at the time of the fire. As of this morning, some people thought to be attending the nightclub were still unaccounted for.","A witness told local media that pyrotechnics used in the club ignited nearby objects. The Facebook page for the album launch event said \"customized light show and pyrotechnic effects\" were to be used at the scene.","A TEMPLATE[wikt, stampede, crush] occurred as people flocked to exits in an attempt to flee from the nightclub. A witness interviewed by Reuters said \"there was a stampede of people running out of the club.\"","On the Facebook page for the album launch event, users who believed people they knew may have been attending the event posted questions asking about where their friends or family members were. Many victims of the fire did not carry any form of identification with them. The Government has set up a hotline for those whose friends or family members are believed to have been at the club.","President of Romania TEMPLATE[w, Klaus Iohannis] said on Facebook he was TEMPLATE[translated_quote, ro, Romanian language, cutremurat Èi profund Ã®ndurerat, shocked and deeply saddened] by the incident. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Romania","description":"Category:Romania"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Fires","description":"Category:Fires"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Bucharest","description":"Category:Bucharest"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["October 31, 2015"]},{"name":"Romania","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["pyrotechnic"]},{"name":"w","description":["nightclub"]},{"name":"wikt","description":["stampede","crush"]},{"name":"w","description":["Klaus Iohannis"]},{"name":"translated_quote","description":["ro","Romanian language","cutremurat Èi profund Ã®ndurerat","shocked and deeply saddened"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34684973","title\u003dBucharest nightclub fire leaves Romania stunned","pub\u003dBBC News","date\u003dOctober 31, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/europe/bucharest-nightclub-fire-deaths-killed-injured-colectiv-strada-tabacarilor-a6715846.html","title\u003dBucharest nightclub fire: At least 26 killed and over 150 injured in fire at Colectiv nightclub in Romania","author\u003dDoug Bolton","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dOctober 30, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/oct/30/dozens-killed-explosion-bucharest-nightclub","title\u003dDozens killed after explosion at Bucharest nightclub","author\u003dKit Gillet","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dOctober 30, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Volkswagen emissions scandal may affect thousands more cars","wikiTitle":"Volkswagen_emissions_scandal_may_affect_thousands_more_cars","wid":2555307,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-24T04:29:44Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dVolkswagen CEO resigns after emissions scandal, date\u003dSeptember 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Wikinews, title\u003dVolkswagen engulfed by diesel emissions scandal, date\u003dSeptember 22, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34712435, title\u003dVolkswagen says 800,000 cars may have false CO2 levels, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dNovember 4, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34705604, title\u003dVW emissions scandal: US regulators find more cars with cheat tests, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dNovember 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/nov/03/vw-c02-emmission-problems-800000-vehicles, title\u003dVW admission suggests cheats went much further than emissions, author\u003dGraham Ruddick, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 3, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/nov/02/vw-emissions-scandal-widens-to-include-porsche-claims-epa, title\u003dVW emissions scandal widens to include Porsche claims, author\u003dGraham Ruddick, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Volkswagen_emissions_scandal","description":"Volkswagen emissions scandal"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[Economy_and_business] TEMPLATE[date, November 4, 2015] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, [[:c:User:Mariordo, Mariordo Mario Roberto Duran Ortiz]]] The Volkswagen emissions scandal continued yesterday with the company announcing 800,000 mainly diesel vehicles may also be affected by TEMPLATE[w, carbon dioxide] emissions problems.","The company stated \"the safety of the vehicles is in no way compromised\". They estimated potentially this could cost them TEMPLATE[w, euro, â¬]2bn on top of the â¬6.7bn set aside to pay for the cost of correcting 11 million cars affected when the scandal broke, in addition to fines by regulators.","TEMPLATE[QuoteRight, 1\u003dthe safety of the vehicles is in no way compromised, 4\u003dVolkswagen]This follows Monday\u0027s revelation that the emissions scandal has affected up to 10,000 vehicles sold in the USA by brands in the Volkswagen group, although the company refutes the allegation. The TEMPLATE[w, United States Environmental Protection Agency] (EPA), the regulatory body which has been investigating Volkswagen, claims the company fitted a number of recent TEMPLATE[w, Audi], TEMPLATE[w, Porsche], and TEMPLATE[w, Volkswagen] models with technology that initiates secret components during emission tests to ensure the results are favourable.","The scandal began with damaging revelations that the car manufacturer has been using illegal software to enable diesel cars to cheat on mandatory emissions tests. This lead to a public apology on September 20 by then-chief executive TEMPLATE[w, Martin Winterkorn] and the promise of an outside inquiry. He then resigned on September 23, and was replaced by TEMPLATE[w, Matthias MÃ¼ller]. The new allegation about Porsche is of particular concern for MÃ¼ller, because he had previously been in charge of Porsche.","The company is expected to foot the bill for the recall of close to 500,000 VW and Audi cars affected at the time. There is also the possibility of Volkswagen having to pay federal fines of up to TEMPLATE[w, US$]18 billion dollars because the US TEMPLATE[w, Clean Air Act (United States), Clean Air Act] sets a maximum fine of US$37,500 for each vehicle that contravenes the requirements of the Act.","An investigation into alleged breaches of environmental law was originally initiated on the advice of the TEMPLATE[w, International Council on Clean Transportation], a European non-governmental organisation. The EPA requested tests be carried out by TEMPLATE[w, West Virginia University], where the secret software was discovered.","The software, known as a \"defeat device\", enabled cars to identify when they were being tested and to switch on the emission control system. The devices may have been adding TEMPLATE[w, urea] to the car exhaust because that would reduce the amount of nitrogen dioxide. The car would release a fraction of the TEMPLATE[w, nitrogen oxide] compared to when they were being driven normally. Emissions of nitrogen oxide contribute to TEMPLATE[w, smog] and are thought to have caused a rise in TEMPLATE[w, respiratory illnesses] like TEMPLATE[w, asthma].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Volkswagen emissions scandal]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Volkswagen_emissions_scandal","description":"Category:Volkswagen emissions scandal"},{"id":"Category:Economy_and_business","description":"Category:Economy and business"},{"id":"Category:Germany","description":"Category:Germany"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Environment","description":"Category:Environment"},{"id":"Category:Science_and_technology","description":"Category:Science and technology"},{"id":"Category:Computing","description":"Category:Computing"},{"id":"Category:Software","description":"Category:Software"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Roads","description":"Category:Roads"}],"templates":[{"name":"Economy_and_business","description":[]},{"name":"date","description":["November 4, 2015"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["[[:c:User:Mariordo","Mariordo Mario Roberto Duran Ortiz]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["carbon dioxide"]},{"name":"w","description":["euro","â¬"]},{"name":"QuoteRight","description":["1\u003dthe safety of the vehicles is in no way compromised","4\u003dVolkswagen"]},{"name":"w","description":["United States Environmental Protection Agency"]},{"name":"w","description":["Audi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Porsche"]},{"name":"w","description":["Volkswagen"]},{"name":"w","description":["Martin Winterkorn"]},{"name":"w","description":["Matthias MÃ¼ller"]},{"name":"w","description":["US$"]},{"name":"w","description":["Clean Air Act (United States)","Clean Air Act"]},{"name":"w","description":["International Council on Clean Transportation"]},{"name":"w","description":["West Virginia University"]},{"name":"w","description":["urea"]},{"name":"w","description":["nitrogen oxide"]},{"name":"w","description":["smog"]},{"name":"w","description":["respiratory illnesses"]},{"name":"w","description":["asthma"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dVolkswagen CEO resigns after emissions scandal","date\u003dSeptember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Wikinews","description":["title\u003dVolkswagen engulfed by diesel emissions scandal","date\u003dSeptember 22, 2015"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","Volkswagen emissions scandal"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34712435","title\u003dVolkswagen says 800,000 cars may have false CO2 levels","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dNovember 4, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/business-34705604","title\u003dVW emissions scandal: US regulators find more cars with cheat tests","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dNovember 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/nov/03/vw-c02-emmission-problems-800000-vehicles","title\u003dVW admission suggests cheats went much further than emissions","author\u003dGraham Ruddick","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dNovember 3, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/business/2015/nov/02/vw-emissions-scandal-widens-to-include-porsche-claims-epa","title\u003dVW emissions scandal widens to include Porsche claims","author\u003dGraham Ruddick","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dNovember 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["1","4","title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Maldives President Abdulla Yameen lifts state of emergency","wikiTitle":"Maldives_President_Abdulla_Yameen_lifts_state_of_emergency","wid":2573121,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-25T02:22:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/maldives-sacks-chief-prosecutor-after-lifting-emergency/, title\u003dMaldives sacks chief prosecutor a day after lifting emergency, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Indian Express, date\u003dNovember 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.arabnews.com/world/news/833681, title\u003dMaldives lifts emergency, author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse, AFP]], pub\u003dArab News, date\u003dNovember 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/10/maldives-revokes-state-of-emergency, title\u003dMaldives revokes state of emergency amid global outcry and tourism worries, author\u003d[[Associated Press, AP]], pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 10, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Maldives","description":"Maldives"},{"id":"US","description":"US"},{"id":"Sri_Lanka","description":"Sri Lanka"},{"id":"UK","description":"UK"},{"id":"EU","description":"EU"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 11, 2015] TEMPLATE[Maldives] TEMPLATE[w, Abdullah Yameen], President of the Maldives, yesterday lifted the state of emergency he imposed on his nation last week. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, [http://www.flickr.com/people/19935963@N00 Timo Newton-Syms]] Attorney General TEMPLATE[w, Mohamed Anil] cited progress in an investigation into the bombing of Yameen\u0027s speedboat in September. The state of emergency was imposed last Wednesday with Yameen reporting security concerns.","The move proved controversial. The opposition TEMPLATE[w, Maldivian Democratic Party, Democrats] accused the President of political motivations and using the powers to block a rally planned to demand ex-President TEMPLATE[w, Mohamed Nasheed], Democratic leader\u0027s, release. A Democrat statement said \"It appears that Yameen is willing to make up threats about the nation\u0027s security in order to settle political scores[...] He has failed and should step down.\"","Vice President TEMPLATE[w, Ahmed Adeeb] was impeached and removed from office during the state of emergency. He is accused of involvement in the attack. After the ending of emergency rule a midnight vote in Parliament last night saw Prosecutor General Muhthaz Muhsin dismissed by a heavy majority. The reasons for the vote have not been publicised. The opposition refused to attend.","Yameen also came under international pressure, including from the US, Sri Lanka, UK, and EU. The emergency provisions included the ability for authorities to search homes and people without formalities, restrictions on travelling around the nation of islands, and restrictions on the TEMPLATE[w, freedom of assembly, right to assemble].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Maldives","description":"Category:Maldives"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Maldives","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Abdullah Yameen"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["[http://www.flickr.com/people/19935963@N00 Timo Newton-Syms]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mohamed Anil"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maldivian Democratic Party","Democrats"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mohamed Nasheed"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ahmed Adeeb"]},{"name":"w","description":["freedom of assembly","right to assemble"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://indianexpress.com/article/world/world-news/maldives-sacks-chief-prosecutor-after-lifting-emergency/","title\u003dMaldives sacks chief prosecutor a day after lifting emergency","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Indian Express","date\u003dNovember 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.arabnews.com/world/news/833681","title\u003dMaldives lifts emergency","author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse","AFP]]","pub\u003dArab News","date\u003dNovember 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/10/maldives-revokes-state-of-emergency","title\u003dMaldives revokes state of emergency amid global outcry and tourism worries","author\u003d[[Associated Press","AP]]","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dNovember 10, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"South African judge jails eight police for Mido Macia\u0027s \u0027barbaric\u0027 murder","wikiTitle":"South_African_judge_jails_eight_police_for_Mido_Macia\u0027s_\u0027barbaric\u0027_murder","wid":2575168,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-25T17:55:52Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/former-south-african-police-jailed-for-barbaric-dragging-murder-20151112-gkx38y.html, title\u003dFormer South African police jailed for \u0027barbaric\u0027 dragging murder, author\u003dZandi Shabalala, pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald, date\u003dNovember 13, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/12/world/africa/south-africa-police-murder-mozambique-immigrant.html?_r\u003d0, title\u003dSouth Africa Court Sentences 8 Ex-Policemen in Immigrantâs Murder, author\u003dSewell Chan, pub\u003dThe New York Times, date\u003dNovember 11, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.dw.com/en/south-african-policemen-sentenced-for-taxi-driver-murder/a-18843316, title\u003dSouth African policemen sentenced for taxi driver murder, author\u003dChrispin Mwakideu, pub\u003dDeutsche Welle, date\u003dNovember 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Pretoria","description":"Pretoria"},{"id":"South_Africa","description":"South Africa"},{"id":"Mozambique","description":"Mozambican"},{"id":"Cape_Town","description":"Cape Town"},{"id":"Johannesburg","description":"Johannesburg"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[South_Africa] A judge in Pretoria, South Africa yesterday sentenced eight police officers to fifteen years\u0027 imprisonment each for the 2013 murder of TEMPLATE[w, Mido Macia]. Mozambican immigrant Macia was dragged behind a police van and beaten in what the judge called a \"barbaric\" attack. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [http://flickr.com/photos/64535987@N00 Shi Zhao]] Judge Bert Bam rejected the 25-year maximum sentence, citing a lack of premeditation and the otherwise good records of the officers involved. Judge Bam said he could not be more lenient owing to a lack of remorse.","Officers confronted Macia, whose illegally parked taxi was obstructing traffic in TEMPLATE[w, Daveyton], near Johannesburg. Macia remonstrated; an angry crowd formed. Police responded by binding the cuffed Macia to their van and dragging him through the streets. Video footage of this sparked worldwide media attention, but the assault continued out of public view in a holding cell where Macia was beaten.","Macia succumbed to head trauma and internal bleeding. His attackers were detained when the footage emerged; President TEMPLATE[w, Jacob Zuma] called the film \"horrific, disturbing and unacceptable\".","The sentence, which follows an August conviction, was welcomed by the TEMPLATE[w, Independent Police Investigative Directorate] which says over 900 die annually either in police custody or from police action. Prosecutors and Macia\u0027s family were also welcoming; the prosecution hope the sentence has a deterrent effect although the family had hoped for stiffer punishment.","The defence has indicated an appeal is likely. The convicted officers are Meshack Malele, Thamsanqa Ngema, Percy Mnisi, Bongamusa Mdluli, Sipho Ngobeni, Lungisa Gwababa, Bongani Kolisi, and Linda Sololo.","Macia had left his girlfriend Biuda Mazive, their young son Sergio, and other family including his parents in Mozambique. He headed to South Africa to join around five million immigrant workers and support his relatives, who are suing the South African government. They seek 6.5 million TEMPLATE[w, South African rand, rand]. The government say they intend to pay but are negotiating the value. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Mozambique","description":"Category:Mozambique"},{"id":"Category:South_Africa","description":"Category:South Africa"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Immigration","description":"Category:Immigration"},{"id":"Category:Pretoria","description":"Category:Pretoria"},{"id":"Category:Johannesburg","description":"Category:Johannesburg"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 12, 2015"]},{"name":"South_Africa","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Mido Macia"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[http://flickr.com/photos/64535987@N00 Shi Zhao]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Daveyton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jacob Zuma"]},{"name":"w","description":["Independent Police Investigative Directorate"]},{"name":"w","description":["South African rand","rand"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.smh.com.au/world/former-south-african-police-jailed-for-barbaric-dragging-murder-20151112-gkx38y.html","title\u003dFormer South African police jailed for \u0027barbaric\u0027 dragging murder","author\u003dZandi Shabalala","pub\u003dThe Sydney Morning Herald","date\u003dNovember 13, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.nytimes.com/2015/11/12/world/africa/south-africa-police-murder-mozambique-immigrant.html?_r\u003d0","title\u003dSouth Africa Court Sentences 8 Ex-Policemen in Immigrantâs Murder","author\u003dSewell Chan","pub\u003dThe New York Times","date\u003dNovember 11, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.dw.com/en/south-african-policemen-sentenced-for-taxi-driver-murder/a-18843316","title\u003dSouth African policemen sentenced for taxi driver murder","author\u003dChrispin Mwakideu","pub\u003dDeutsche Welle","date\u003dNovember 11, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templa