{"title":"Rwandan Senate approves constitutional change allowing third term for Kagame","wikiTitle":"Rwandan_Senate_approves_constitutional_change_allowing_third_term_for_Kagame","wid":2586790,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-26T04:11:32Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dRwandan Supreme Court agrees to hear case on allowing third presidential term, date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.news24.com/Africa/News/kagame-may-rule-until-2034-20151117, title\u003dKagame may rule until 2034, author\u003d, pub\u003dNews24, date\u003dNovember 17, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/11/17/rwanda-politics-idUSL8N13C2QQ20151117, title\u003dUPDATE 1-Rwandan senate votes to allow President Kagame more time in office, author\u003dClement Uwiringiyimana, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dNovember 17, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Rwanda","description":"Rwanda"},{"id":"Paul_Kagame","description":"Paul Kagame"},{"id":"Rwandan_genocide","description":"Rwanda\u0027s genocide"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 17, 2015] TEMPLATE[Rwanda] The TEMPLATE[w, Senate (Rwanda), Senate] of Rwanda today voted to amend the TEMPLATE[w, Constitution of Rwanda, country\u0027s constitution] to allow a third term for President Paul Kagame. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:ÐÐµÐ½Ð¸ ÐÐ°ÑÐºÐ¾Ð²ÑÐºÐ¸, Veni Markovski]]] The changes, which require a referendum before becoming law, reduce the current limit of two seven-year Presidential terms to two five-year terms. Kagame receives an exemption allowing another seven-year term before starting to count his five-year terms. If approved the amendments can keep him in power until 2034.","Following Rwanda\u0027s genocide Kagame grew popular at home and abroad, leading to over three million petitioners demanding he be allowed to run again. The ruling TEMPLATE[w, Rwandan Patriotic Front] has already gained approval from TEMPLATE[w, Parliament of Rwanda, Parliament] and seen off a TEMPLATE[w, Supreme Court of Rwanda, Supreme Court] challenge by the opposition TEMPLATE[w, Democratic Green Party of Rwanda, Democratic Green Party].","Kagame has yet to decide if he will run again. Opposition leader TEMPLATE[w, Frank Habineza] says his party will continue to oppose the change. Senate leader TEMPLATE[w, Bernard Makuza] says he expects the referendum, the date of which is not yet set, to succeed.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Africa","description":"Category:Africa"},{"id":"Category:Rwanda","description":"Category:Rwanda"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Paul_Kagame","description":"Category:Paul Kagame"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Rwanda","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Senate (Rwanda)","Senate"]},{"name":"w","description":["Constitution of Rwanda","country\u0027s constitution"]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:ÐÐµÐ½Ð¸ ÐÐ°ÑÐºÐ¾Ð²ÑÐºÐ¸","Veni Markovski]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rwandan Patriotic Front"]},{"name":"w","description":["Parliament of Rwanda","Parliament"]},{"name":"w","description":["Supreme Court of Rwanda","Supreme Court"]},{"name":"w","description":["Democratic Green Party of Rwanda","Democratic Green Party"]},{"name":"w","description":["Frank Habineza"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bernard Makuza"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dRwandan Supreme Court agrees to hear case on allowing third presidential term","date\u003dSeptember 9, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.news24.com/Africa/News/kagame-may-rule-until-2034-20151117","title\u003dKagame may rule until 2034","author\u003d","pub\u003dNews24","date\u003dNovember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/11/17/rwanda-politics-idUSL8N13C2QQ20151117","title\u003dUPDATE 1-Rwandan senate votes to allow President Kagame more time in office","author\u003dClement Uwiringiyimana","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dNovember 17, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Germaine Greer gives Cardiff University oration despite campaign to prevent lecture","wikiTitle":"Germaine_Greer_gives_Cardiff_University_oration_despite_campaign_to_prevent_lecture","wid":2591007,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-27T13:21:09Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dCardiff student union calls for cancellation of lecture by Germaine Greer, date\u003dOctober 25, 2015]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/germaine-greer-author-gives-cardiff-university-speech-despite-protests-against-her-comments-on-a6739746.html, title\u003dGermaine Greer: Author gives Cardiff University speech despite protests against her comments on transgender people, author\u003dIan Johnston, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dNovember 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/germaine-greers-cardiff-university-lecture-10465912, title\u003dGermaine Greer\u0027s Cardiff University lecture goes ahead despite petition to have event cancelled, author\u003dHarry Yorke, pub\u003dWestern Mail (Wales), date\u003dNovember 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/books/2015/nov/18/transgender-activists-protest-germaine-greer-lecture-cardiff-university, title\u003dGermaine Greer gives university lecture despite campaign to silence her, author\u003dSteven Morris, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 18, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/protests-planned-germaine-greers-controversial-10462483, title\u003dProtests planned as Germaine Greer\u0027s controversial lecture is set to go ahead in Cardiff, author\u003dKhalan Rosenblatt, pub\u003dWestern Mail (Wales), date\u003dNovember 18, 2015]"],["the petition"]],"links":[{"id":"Cardiff_University","description":"Cardiff University"},{"id":"LGBTQ","description":"LGBTQ"},{"id":"transgender","description":"transgender"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"https://www.change.org/p/cardiff-university-do-not-host-germaine-greer","description":"the petition"}],"sections":["Related news","Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 20, 2015] TEMPLATE[infobox, Free speech] Feminist author and academic TEMPLATE[w, Germaine Greer] gave a lecture at Cardiff University on Wednesday despite a petition with over 3,000 signatures calling for its cancellation.","TEMPLATE[QuoteLeft, I feel like the words Germaine Greer has spouted in recent years has no place in our movement, source\u003dEmily Cotterill, LGBTQ rights activist]","Australian Greer gave the Hayden Ellis Lecture entitled \"Women and Power: The Lessons of the 20th Century\" under security with uniformed police officers and university security guards.  The lecture covered equal pay for women, and TEMPLATE[w, Emmeline Pankhurst] and the TEMPLATE[w, Suffragettes].","Ms Greer had been criticised by LGBTQ rights activists for comments made about transgender reality television star TEMPLATE[w, Caitlyn Jenner], and her belief that \u0027post-operative\u0027 trans women aren\u0027t \u0027real women\u0027.  The women\u0027s officer of the Cardiff University Student Union called for cancelling the lecture in a TEMPLATE[w, Change.org] petition which has received over 3,000 signatures. \"I\u0027m 76,\" Greer said in a TEMPLATE[w, BBC Newsnight] interview, \"I don\u0027t want to go down there and be screamed at and have things thrown at me.\" However, ultimately she did give the lecture.","The Independent reported a group of around two dozen protestors outside the lecture. LGBTQ rights activist Emily Cotterill, who was at the protest, said she believed transphobia had no place in modern feminism. \"I feel like the words Germaine Greer has spouted in recent years has no place in our movement\", Ms Cotterill said.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Feminism","description":"Category:Feminism"},{"id":"Category:University_of_Cardiff","description":"Category:University of Cardiff"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 20, 2015"]},{"name":"w","description":["Germaine Greer"]},{"name":"QuoteLeft","description":["I feel like the words Germaine Greer has spouted in recent years has no place in our movement","source\u003dEmily Cotterill, LGBTQ rights activist"]},{"name":"w","description":["Emmeline Pankhurst"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suffragettes"]},{"name":"w","description":["Caitlyn Jenner"]},{"name":"w","description":["Change.org"]},{"name":"w","description":["BBC Newsnight"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dCardiff student union calls for cancellation of lecture by Germaine Greer","date\u003dOctober 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/people/germaine-greer-author-gives-cardiff-university-speech-despite-protests-against-her-comments-on-a6739746.html","title\u003dGermaine Greer: Author gives Cardiff University speech despite protests against her comments on transgender people","author\u003dIan Johnston","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dNovember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/germaine-greers-cardiff-university-lecture-10465912","title\u003dGermaine Greer\u0027s Cardiff University lecture goes ahead despite petition to have event cancelled","author\u003dHarry Yorke","pub\u003dWestern Mail (Wales)","date\u003dNovember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/books/2015/nov/18/transgender-activists-protest-germaine-greer-lecture-cardiff-university","title\u003dGermaine Greer gives university lecture despite campaign to silence her","author\u003dSteven Morris","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dNovember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.walesonline.co.uk/news/wales-news/protests-planned-germaine-greers-controversial-10462483","title\u003dProtests planned as Germaine Greer\u0027s controversial lecture is set to go ahead in Cardiff","author\u003dKhalan Rosenblatt","pub\u003dWestern Mail (Wales)","date\u003dNovember 18, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["source","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["The Independent"],"infobox":{"name":"infobox","description":["Free speech"]}}
{"title":"Australian Eddie Jones named as England\u0027s rugby union head coach","wikiTitle":"Australian_Eddie_Jones_named_as_England\u0027s_rugby_union_head_coach","wid":2594623,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-29T12:31:47Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-union/34875741, title\u003d Eddie Jones: Australian appointed England head coach, author\u003d, pub\u003d BBC Sport, date\u003d November 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/sport/2015/nov/20/eddie-jones-appointed-england-coach-rfu, title\u003d Eddie Jones appointed England head coach by RFU, author\u003d, pub\u003d The Guardian, date\u003d November 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/11/20/uk-rugby-union-england-jones-idUKKCN0T90M120151120, title\u003d Australian Jones named England\u0027s first foreign coach, author\u003d Mitch Phillips, pub\u003d Reuters, date\u003d November 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.independent.co.uk/sport/rugby/rugby-union/international/stuart-lancaster-resigns-england-head-coach-quits-after-rugby-world-cup-failure-a6729986.html, title\u003d Stuart Lancaster resigns: England head coach quits after Rugby World Cup failure, author\u003d Jack de Menezes, pub\u003d The Independent, date\u003d November 11, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Australia","description":"Australia"},{"id":"rugby_union","description":"rugby union"},{"id":"Cape_Town","description":"Cape Town"},{"id":"South_Africa","description":"South Africa"},{"id":"New_Zealand","description":"New Zealand"},{"id":"Edinburgh","description":"Edinburgh"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 22, 2015]  TEMPLATE[sports] TEMPLATE[image, [https://www.flickr.com/people/35355786@N05 Belinda Lester]] Australian TEMPLATE[w, Eddie Jones (rugby union), Eddie Jones] was named on Friday as TEMPLATE[w, England national rugby union team, England]\u0027s new rugby union head coach by the TEMPLATE[w, Rugby Football Union] (RFU), making him the first foreign coach to be appointed to the role. Jones has signed a four year contract after TEMPLATE[w, Stuart Lancaster (rugby union), Stuart Lancaster] resigned from the post in early November following England\u0027s disappointing performance at this year\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Rugby World Cup].","Jones, 55, is to leave a position he was appointed to only two months ago as coach of Cape Town\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Stormers] in South Africa. Jones said: \"The opportunity to take the reins in possibly the worldâs most high-profile international rugby job doesnât come along every day however, and I feel fortunate to be given the opportunity.\"","Jones led Australian side TEMPLATE[w, Brumbies] to the first TEMPLATE[w, Super Rugby, Super 12] win by a non-New Zealand team. While he was head coach of TEMPLATE[w, Australia national rugby union side, Australia] they won the TEMPLATE[w, The Rugby Championship, Tri Nations] and were finalists against England at the 2003 Rugby World Cup.","He was also assistant to TEMPLATE[w, South Africa national rugby union team, South Africa] the year of their 2007 World Cup win. His TEMPLATE[w, Japan national rugby union team, Japan] side, with ten consecutive victories, broke the record for the number of successive wins for a second tier rugby union team. His first game as England head coach is to be against TEMPLATE[w, Scotland national rugby union team, Scotland] in the TEMPLATE[w, Six Nations Championship] at TEMPLATE[w, Murrayfield Stadium, Murrayfield Stadium] in Edinburgh on February 6.","Chief Executive of the RFU Ian Ritchie said he is confident Jones has the right credentials for the role. \"We promised to recruit a coach with proven international experience and we have done that. Eddie is a world-class coach, with extensive experience at the highest level with Australia, South Africa and Japan.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:_November_20,_2015","description":"Category: November 20, 2015"},{"id":"Category:_England","description":"Category: England"},{"id":"Category:_Rugby","description":"Category: Rugby"},{"id":"Category:_Sports","description":"Category: Sports"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Australia","description":"Category:Australia"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 22, 2015"]},{"name":"sports","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["[https://www.flickr.com/people/35355786@N05 Belinda Lester]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eddie Jones (rugby union)","Eddie Jones"]},{"name":"w","description":["England national rugby union team","England"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rugby Football Union"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stuart Lancaster (rugby union)","Stuart Lancaster"]},{"name":"w","description":["Rugby World Cup"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stormers"]},{"name":"w","description":["Brumbies"]},{"name":"w","description":["Super Rugby","Super 12"]},{"name":"w","description":["Australia national rugby union side","Australia"]},{"name":"w","description":["The Rugby Championship","Tri Nations"]},{"name":"w","description":["South Africa national rugby union team","South Africa"]},{"name":"w","description":["Japan national rugby union team","Japan"]},{"name":"w","description":["Scotland national rugby union team","Scotland"]},{"name":"w","description":["Six Nations Championship"]},{"name":"w","description":["Murrayfield Stadium","Murrayfield Stadium"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/rugby-union/34875741","title\u003d Eddie Jones: Australian appointed England head coach","author\u003d","pub\u003d BBC Sport","date\u003d November 20, 201