{"title":"Saudi Arabian court convicts poet of apostasy, sentences to death","wikiTitle":"Saudi_Arabian_court_convicts_poet_of_apostasy,_sentences_to_death","wid":2595745,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-11-28T16:41:54Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/saudi-arabian-court-sentences-palestinian-poet-ashraf-fayadh-to-death-for-apostasy-a6742161.html, title\u003dSaudi Arabian court sentences Palestinian poet Ashraf Fayadh to death for apostasy, author\u003dAngus McDowall, pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dNovember 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/20/saudi-court-sentences-poet-to-death-for-renouncing-islam, title\u003dSaudi court sentences poet to death for renouncing Islam, author\u003dDavid Batty, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 20, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Saudi_Arabia","description":"Saudi Arabia"},{"id":"Palestine","description":"Palestinian"},{"id":"death_penalty","description":"death"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 21, 2015] TEMPLATE[Saudi_Arabia] A court in Saudi Arabia sentenced Saudi-born Palestinian poet TEMPLATE[w, Ashraf Fayadh] to death on Tuesday for allegedly committing TEMPLATE[w, apostasy in Islam, apostasy], a crime punishable by death under Saudi Arabia\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Law in Saudi Arabia, interpretation] of TEMPLATE[w, Sharia Law]. The court decision was brought to light yesterday by Adam Coogle, a researcher working for TEMPLATE[w, Human Rights Watch].","Fayadh has previously posted a video online of a public lashing by TEMPLATE[w, mutaween, religious police]. Mona Kareem, an activist from TEMPLATE[w, Kuwait] calling for Fayadh\u0027s release, said \"some Saudis think this was revenge by the morality police.\"","Fayadh was detained by police in August 2013, accused of TEMPLATE[w, Blasphemy in Islam, blasphemy] and promoting TEMPLATE[w, atheism] through his poems. According to Fayadh, this stemmed from a dispute with a fellow artist. He was soon released under bail.","Fayadh was again arrested in January 2014. He was tried at a court in TEMPLATE[w, Abha] in February under allegations of committing blasphemy, promoting atheism, and having illegal relationships with women. He was sentenced in May that year to four years of jail and 800 lashes. Fayadh appealed the decision, and the case was retried by another judge, who sentenced him to death.","Activist Mona Kareem said the judge for Fayadh\u0027s retrial \"didn\u0027t even talk to [Fayadh], he just made the verdict.\"","Fayadh was given 30 days to appeal the court ruling, but according to Kareem, Fayadh \"was unable to assign a lawyer because his ID was confiscated when he was arrested\" in January 2014.","Human Rights Watch researcher Adam Coogle called the court ruling an example of Saudi Arabia\u0027s \"complete intolerance for anyone who may not share government-mandated religious, political, and social views.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:_Human_Rights_Watch","description":"Category: Human Rights Watch"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Death_penalty","description":"Category:Death penalty"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Saudi_Arabia","description":"Category:Saudi Arabia"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Palestine","description":"Category:Palestine"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Islam","description":"Category:Islam"},{"id":"Category:Atheism","description":"Category:Atheism"},{"id":"Category:Poetry","description":"Category:Poetry"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 21, 2015"]},{"name":"Saudi_Arabia","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Ashraf Fayadh"]},{"name":"w","description":["apostasy in Islam","apostasy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Law in Saudi Arabia","interpretation"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sharia Law"]},{"name":"w","description":["Human Rights Watch"]},{"name":"w","description":["mutaween","religious police"]},{"name":"w","description":["Kuwait"]},{"name":"w","description":["Blasphemy in Islam","blasphemy"]},{"name":"w","description":["atheism"]},{"name":"w","description":["Abha"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/saudi-arabian-court-sentences-palestinian-poet-ashraf-fayadh-to-death-for-apostasy-a6742161.html","title\u003dSaudi Arabian court sentences Palestinian poet Ashraf Fayadh to death for apostasy","author\u003dAngus McDowall","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dNovember 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/20/saudi-court-sentences-poet-to-death-for-renouncing-islam","title\u003dSaudi court sentences poet to death for renouncing Islam","author\u003dDavid Batty","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dNovember 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
