{"title":"Pakistani female fighter pilot Marium Mukhtiar dies in jet crash","wikiTitle":"Pakistani_female_fighter_pilot_Marium_Mukhtiar_dies_in_jet_crash","wid":2604142,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-05T22:43:13Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/24/marium-mukhtiar-pakistan-female-fighter-pilot-dies-crash-training-exercise, title\u003dFemale Pakistani fighter pilot dies in crash during training exercise, author\u003dJon Boone, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/asia/2015/11/24/Pakistan-female-fighter-pilot-dies-in-jet-crash-.html, title\u003dPakistan female fighter pilot dies in jet crash, author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse, AFP]], pub\u003dal-Arabiya, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-34910278, title\u003dMarium Mukhtiar, Pakistani female fighter pilot, dies in crash, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Pakistan","description":"Pakistan"},{"id":"Punjab_(Pakistan)","description":"Punjab"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 25, 2015] TEMPLATE[Pakistan] Marium Mukhtiar yesterday became the first Pakistani female fighter pilot to die on duty when a jet aircraft crashed near TEMPLATE[w, Kundian], in Punjab\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Mianwali] district. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, 1\u003d[http://www.airliners.net/search/photo.search?photographersearch\u003dAsuspine\u0026distinct_entry\u003dtrue Asuspine]] The TEMPLATE[w, Pakistan Air Force] (PAF) said Flying Officer Mukhtiar and male colleague Squadron Leader Saqib Abbasi faced a \"serious in-flight emergency\" while training in an TEMPLATE[w, Chengdu J-7, F7-PG] fighter. After taking evasive action to avoid a residential area the pilots were left with insufficient altitude to safely eject. Both ejected and were injured; Mukhtiar died in hospital whilst Abbasi sustained minor injuries.","The PAF said Mukhtiar \"embraced shahadat [martyrdom] and became the first lady pilot from PAF to attain this great honour,\" crediting Abbasi\u0027s survival as possibly down to his escaping several seconds prior to Mukhtiar. The duo \"handled the serious emergency with professionalism and courage and tried to save the ill-fated aircraft till the very last minute,\" according to the PAF.","The PAF estimates it has around 30 female fighter pilots. The force began recruiting women in 2003 and in 2006 the nation\u0027s first seven female fighter pilots began service.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Pakistan","description":"Category:Pakistan"},{"id":"Category:Punjab_(Pakistan)","description":"Category:Punjab (Pakistan)"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Military","description":"Category:Military"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Women","description":"Category:Women"},{"id":"Category:Women\u0027s_rights","description":"Category:Women\u0027s rights"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Pakistan","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Kundian"]},{"name":"w","description":["Mianwali"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["1\u003d[http://www.airliners.net/search/photo.search?photographersearch\u003dAsuspine\u0026distinct_entry\u003dtrue Asuspine]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Pakistan Air Force"]},{"name":"w","description":["Chengdu J-7","F7-PG"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/nov/24/marium-mukhtiar-pakistan-female-fighter-pilot-dies-crash-training-exercise","title\u003dFemale Pakistani fighter pilot dies in crash during training exercise","author\u003dJon Boone","pub\u003dThe Guardian","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://english.alarabiya.net/en/News/asia/2015/11/24/Pakistan-female-fighter-pilot-dies-in-jet-crash-.html","title\u003dPakistan female fighter pilot dies in jet crash","author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse","AFP]]","pub\u003dal-Arabiya","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-asia-34910278","title\u003dMarium Mukhtiar, Pakistani female fighter pilot, dies in crash","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["1","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["shahadat"]}
{"title":"Ferry MV Suilven sinks in Suva, Fiji","wikiTitle":"Ferry_MV_Suilven_sinks_in_Suva,_Fiji","wid":2604410,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-04T05:12:56Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.odt.co.nz/news/world/364502/ferry-capsizes-fiji, title\u003dFerry capsizes off Fiji, author\u003d\u0027\u0027(TEMPLATE)\u0027\u0027, pub\u003dOtago Daily Times, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.scotsman.com/news/transport/former-cal-mac-ferry-capsizes-in-fiji-harbour-1-3956988, title\u003dFormer Cal Mac ferry capsizes in Fiji harbour, author\u003d, pub\u003dThe Scotsman, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scotland"},{"id":"Fiji","description":"Fiji"},{"id":"Scotland","description":"Scotland"},{"id":"New_Zealand","description":"New Zealand"},{"id":"Norway","description":"Norway"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 24, 2015] TEMPLATE[disasters_and_accidents] TEMPLATE[Image_credit, 1\u003d[http://www.geograph.org.uk/profile/796?expand\u003d1 Dr Neil Clifton]] TEMPLATE[w, MV Suilven, MV \u0027\u0027Suilven\u0027\u0027], a ferry in service in Fiji, capsized and sank in TEMPLATE[w, Suva] Harbour today.","Around thirty people, all crewmembers, were on board. Local media report all were rescued. The 41-year-old vessel previously saw service in Scotland and New Zealand.","The ship capsized early this afternoon and sank within an hour. It had been converted from passenger to cargo use following its most recent sale, to Venu Shipping in 2012 or 2011. Local reports indicated police, the TEMPLATE[w, Fijian Navy, Navy], local tug boats, and volunteer rescuers all attended the accident.","The converted ferry reportedly began to list on entering the harbour. It was working a route carrying cargo between TEMPLATE[w, Suva] and the TEMPLATE[w, Northern Division, Fiji, Northern Division].","Built in Norway, in service from 1974, the ship served with Scottish ferry firm TEMPLATE[w, Caledonian MacBrayne] until 1995, connecting the mainland town of TEMPLATE[w, Ullapool] to TEMPLATE[w, Stornoway] on the TEMPLATE[w, Isle of Lewis]. It was ultimately replaced by a larger, faster vessel and was sold to TEMPLATE[w, Strait Shipping] who used it until 2004 to ply New Zealand\u0027s seas, connecting TEMPLATE[w, Wellington, New Zealand, Wellington] to TEMPLATE[w, Picton, New Zealand, Picton] and to TEMPLATE[w, Nelson, New Zealand, Nelson].","The name MV Suilven is in reference to the TEMPLATE[w, Suilven] mountain in Scotland\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Sutherland] region.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Merchant_shipping","description":"Category:Merchant shipping"},{"id":"Category:Oceania","description":"Category:Oceania"},{"id":"Category:Fiji","description":"Category:Fiji"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:New_Zealand","description":"Category:New Zealand"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 24, 2015"]},{"name":"disasters_and_accidents","description":[]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["1\u003d[http://www.geograph.org.uk/profile/796?expand\u003d1 Dr Neil Clifton]"]},{"name":"w","description":["MV Suilven","MV \u0027\u0027Suilven\u0027\u0027"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suva"]},{"name":"w","description":["Fijian Navy","Navy"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suva"]},{"name":"w","description":["Northern Division, Fiji","Northern Division"]},{"name":"w","description":["Caledonian MacBrayne"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ullapool"]},{"name":"w","description":["Stornoway"]},{"name":"w","description":["Isle of Lewis"]},{"name":"w","description":["Strait Shipping"]},{"name":"w","description":["Wellington, New Zealand","Wellington"]},{"name":"w","description":["Picton, New Zealand","Picton"]},{"name":"w","description":["Nelson, New Zealand","Nelson"]},{"name":"w","description":["Suilven"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sutherland"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.odt.co.nz/news/world/364502/ferry-capsizes-fiji","title\u003dFerry capsizes off Fiji","author\u003d\u0027\u0027(TEMPLATE)\u0027\u0027","pub\u003dOtago Daily Times","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.scotsman.com/news/transport/former-cal-mac-ferry-capsizes-in-fiji-harbour-1-3956988","title\u003dFormer Cal Mac ferry capsizes in Fiji harbour","author\u003d","pub\u003dThe Scotsman","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["1","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["","Suilven"]}
{"title":"Athens bomb targets business group, damages Cypriot embassy","wikiTitle":"Athens_bomb_targets_business_group,_damages_Cypriot_embassy","wid":2606509,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-08T17:49:47Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.ekathimerini.com/203747/article/ekathimerini/news/police-seek-perpetrators-of-athens-bomb-blast, title\u003dPolice seek perpetrators of Athens bomb blast, author\u003d, pub\u003dKathimerini, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34907489, title\u003dAthens bomb explodes near Greek parliament, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/11/24/us-eurozone-greece-blast-idUSKBN0TD06T20151124, title\u003dBomb blast in central Athens damages Cypriot Embassy, author\u003d, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dNovember 24, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Athens","description":"Athens"},{"id":"Greece","description":"Greece"},{"id":"Cyprus","description":"Cypriot"},{"id":"Reuters","description":"Reuters"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 25, 2015] TEMPLATE[Athens,_Greece] A bombing outside the TEMPLATE[w, sister\u003dw:el, Î£ÏÎ½Î´ÎµÏÎ¼Î¿Ï ÎÏÎ¹ÏÎµÎ¹ÏÎ®ÏÎµÏÎ½ ÎºÎ±Î¹ ÎÎ¹Î¿Î¼Î·ÏÎ±Î½Î¹ÏÎ½, Hellenic Federation of Enterprises] in central Athens, Greece early yesterday morning caused heavy damage to the Cypriot embassy across the street. TEMPLATE[Image_credit, [[Commons:User:Athenswalk, Athenswalk]]] The explosion hit Xenofontos Street around 3.30 a.m. TEMPLATE[w, Eastern European Time, local time] (0130 TEMPLATE[w, UTC]). Police had cordoned off the area after two local newspapers received calls warning of the impending blast 30\u0026ndash;40 minutes before the blast. Unconfirmed reports state the bomb as being 3TEMPLATE[w, kilogram, kg] of explosives left in a backpack outside the office and detonated by a timer.","Police evacuated a hotel near the scene and warned kiosk vendors in the vicinity. Nobody was injured. The site is close to the city\u0027s famed TEMPLATE[w, Syntagma Square]. Witnesses report two individuals leaving the bag and police told Reuters a CCTV camera recorded two dark-clad men speeding off on a motorcycle.","Kyriakos Kenevezos, the Cypriot Ambassador, said to state media conglomerate TEMPLATE[w, Cyprus News Agency, CNA] \"Our embassy absorbed the full impact of the blast[...] there is incalculable damage to the interior from the ground floor to the sixth floor.\"","Domestic anarchist and extreme left militants have been carrying out bombings and starting fires since 2010 saw the introduction of widespread austerity. Attacks have however decreased since left-wingers TEMPLATE[w, Syriza] took power in January under Prime Minister TEMPLATE[w, Alexis Tsipras]. The government condemned the attacks, as did conservative opposition party TEMPLATE[w, New Democracy (Greece), New Democracy].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Greece","description":"Category:Greece"},{"id":"Category:Cyprus","description":"Category:Cyprus"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Athens,_Greece","description":"Category:Athens, Greece"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Athens,_Greece","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["sister\u003dw:el","Î£ÏÎ½Î´ÎµÏÎ¼Î¿Ï ÎÏÎ¹ÏÎµÎ¹ÏÎ®ÏÎµÏÎ½ ÎºÎ±Î¹ ÎÎ¹Î¿Î¼Î·ÏÎ±Î½Î¹ÏÎ½","Hellenic Federation of Enterprises"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:Athenswalk","Athenswalk]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Eastern European Time","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilogram","kg"]},{"name":"w","description":["Syntagma Square"]},{"name":"w","description":["Cyprus News Agency","CNA"]},{"name":"w","description":["Syriza"]},{"name":"w","description":["Alexis Tsipras"]},{"name":"w","description":["New Democracy (Greece)","New Democracy"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.ekathimerini.com/203747/article/ekathimerini/news/police-seek-perpetrators-of-athens-bomb-blast","title\u003dPolice seek perpetrators of Athens bomb blast","author\u003d","pub\u003dKathimerini","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34907489","title\u003dAthens bomb explodes near Greek parliament","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/2015/11/24/us-eurozone-greece-blast-idUSKBN0TD06T20151124","title\u003dBomb blast in central Athens damages Cypriot Embassy","author\u003d","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dNovember 24, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["sister","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["Reuters"]}
{"title":"New Polish government takes down findings on Russian air disaster","wikiTitle":"New_Polish_government_takes_down_findings_on_Russian_air_disaster","wid":2607102,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2017-01-14T16:26:18Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003d\u0027Unacceptable\u0027 and \u0027without foundation\u0027: Poland rejects Russian air crash report, date\u003dDecember 20, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dBronislaw Komorowski sworn in as president of Poland, date\u003dAugust 10, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dInvestigation into Polish air crash reveals passengers in cockpit, date\u003dMay 19, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPoland: Around 100,000 people attend public memorial for victims of plane crash, date\u003dApril 18, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPolish president and first lady lie in state ahead of funeral, date\u003dApril 13, 2010]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dPolish President Lech KaczyÅski dies as his plane crashes in Russia, date\u003dApril 10, 2010]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34922787, title\u003dSmolensk air crash: Poland\u0027s Tusk targeted by new government, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dNovember 25, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory/polish-govt-reopens-questions-2010-plane-crash-35412039, title\u003dNew Polish Gov\u0027t Reopens Questions About 2010 Plane Crash, author\u003dVanessa Gera ([[Associated Press, AP]]), pub\u003dABC News (US), date\u003dNovember 25, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Law_and_Justice_Party","description":"Law and Justice Party"},{"id":"Poland","description":"Poland"},{"id":"Russia","description":"Russia"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, November 26, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] TEMPLATE[w, Warsaw]TEMPLATE[Image_credit, Chancellery of the President of the Republic of Poland] The Law and Justice Party of Poland, which took power last week, this week removed web pages featuring the results of an investigation into the TEMPLATE[w, 2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash, Smolensk air disaster] in Russia in 2010. The cause of the crash, which killed Polish President TEMPLATE[w, Lech Kaczynski], is disputed.","The flight was carrying high-profile political figures to attend a ceremony commemorating the 70th anniversary of the TEMPLATE[w, Katyn massacre], when thousands of Polish prisoners of war and civilians were killed by the TEMPLATE[w, Soviet Union, Soviets]. All 96 on board died. Amongst the dead were First Lady TEMPLATE[w, Maria KaczyÅska], several members of the lower parliamentary house known as the TEMPLATE[w, Sejm], Deputy Foreign Minister TEMPLATE[w, Andrzej Kremer], TEMPLATE[w, National Security Bureau (Poland), National Security Bureau] head TEMPLATE[w, Aleksander SzczygÅo], and TEMPLATE[w, Ryszard Kaczorowski], the last President of the TEMPLATE[w, Polish government-in-exile].","The Law and Justice Party was in power at the time, led then as now by Lech Kaczynski\u0027s identical twin brother TEMPLATE[w, Jaroslaw Kaczynski]. Jaroslaw was himself Prime Minister of Poland from 2006 to 2007. Jaroslaw contested the vacated Presidency later that year but was defeated by TEMPLATE[w, Bronislaw Komorowski] of the TEMPLATE[w, Civic Platform Party]. Lech and Jaroslaw co-founded Law and Justice. TEMPLATE[image, [[Commons:User:Staszewski, Bartosz Staszewski]]] Russian and Polish investigations deemed the crash an accident. Edmund Klich, head of the Polish air accident investigatory body, said in 2010 the Polish military pilots of the TEMPLATE[w, Tupolev Tu-154] were determined to get the dignitaries through dense fog so they could attend the ceremony. He said the pilots were insufficiently trained and put safety second, whilst Russian TEMPLATE[w, air traffic controller, air traffic controllers] should have diverted the aircraft away from TEMPLATE[w, Smolensk]. Passengers entered the cockpit during the final stages of the flight.","Government spokesman Elzbieta Witek yesterday said TEMPLATE[w, Donald Tusk], a former Prime Minister, should be prosecuted before the TEMPLATE[w, State Tribunal (Poland), State Tribunal], although Witek said this was a personal view and not government policy. Jaroslaw and allies have insinuated Russia purposefully brought the plane down.","Law and Justice accuse Tusk, Prime Minister from 2007 to 2014, of failings before and after the crash. He is accused of not ensuring the President was safe, of not establishing an international investigation, and of allowing Russia to maintain possession of the wreckage.","Russia\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Interstate Aviation Committee] performed its own investigation blaming solely Poland\u0027s pilots and exonerating the controllers. Upon receiving the first draft of their report in 2010 Tusk branded the contents \"unacceptable\", the findings \"without foundation\", and the overall result a breach of the TEMPLATE[w, Convention on International Civil Aviation, Chicago Convention], an international regulatory document on air travel.","Tusk resigned last year to take the TEMPLATE[w, European Council] Presidency until 2017. Witek said he had \"given away\" investigative control. Polish minister TEMPLATE[w, Adam Lipinski] has previously called for Tusk\u0027s prosecution after his European duties conclude, saying he has \"a lot to answer for\" over the disaster.","Polish conspiracy theorists have been spurred on by Russian refusal to accede to Polish requests to return wreckage, which the Russians claim to still be investigating.","The new Prime Minister is Law and Justice\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Beata Szydlo]. Asked on Tuesday about one disappearing website containing investigative findings, Szydlo told press \"the website has been closed and will simply remain closed.\"","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, wikipedia, 2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash, commons, Category:2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Russia","description":"Category:Russia"},{"id":"Category:Poland","description":"Category:Poland"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Law_and_Justice_Party","description":"Category:Law and Justice Party"},{"id":"Category:Beata_SzydÅo","description":"Category:Beata SzydÅo"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["November 26, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Warsaw"]},{"name":"Image_credit","description":["Chancellery of the President of the Republic of Poland"]},{"name":"w","description":["2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash","Smolensk air disaster"]},{"name":"w","description":["Lech Kaczynski"]},{"name":"w","description":["Katyn massacre"]},{"name":"w","description":["Soviet Union","Soviets"]},{"name":"w","description":["Maria KaczyÅska"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sejm"]},{"name":"w","description":["Andrzej Kremer"]},{"name":"w","description":["National Security Bureau (Poland)","National Security Bureau"]},{"name":"w","description":["Aleksander SzczygÅo"]},{"name":"w","description":["Ryszard Kaczorowski"]},{"name":"w","description":["Polish government-in-exile"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jaroslaw Kaczynski"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bronislaw Komorowski"]},{"name":"w","description":["Civic Platform Party"]},{"name":"image","description":["[[Commons:User:Staszewski","Bartosz Staszewski]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Tupolev Tu-154"]},{"name":"w","description":["air traffic controller","air traffic controllers"]},{"name":"w","description":["Smolensk"]},{"name":"w","description":["Donald Tusk"]},{"name":"w","description":["State Tribunal (Poland)","State Tribunal"]},{"name":"w","description":["Interstate Aviation Committee"]},{"name":"w","description":["Convention on International Civil Aviation","Chicago Convention"]},{"name":"w","description":["European Council"]},{"name":"w","description":["Adam Lipinski"]},{"name":"w","description":["Beata Szydlo"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003d\u0027Unacceptable\u0027 and \u0027without foundation\u0027: Poland rejects Russian air crash report","date\u003dDecember 20, 2010"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dBronislaw Komorowski sworn in as president of Poland","date\u003dAugust 10, 2010"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dInvestigation into Polish air crash reveals passengers in cockpit","date\u003dMay 19, 2010"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPoland: Around 100,000 people attend public memorial for victims of plane crash","date\u003dApril 18, 2010"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPolish president and first lady lie in state ahead of funeral","date\u003dApril 13, 2010"]},{"name":"wikinews","description":["title\u003dPolish President Lech KaczyÅski dies as his plane crashes in Russia","date\u003dApril 10, 2010"]},{"name":"sisters","description":["wikipedia","2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash","commons","Category:2010 Polish Air Force Tu-154 crash"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-europe-34922787","title\u003dSmolensk air crash: Poland\u0027s Tusk targeted by new government","author\u003d","pub\u003dBBC News Online","date\u003dNovember 25, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://abcnews.go.com/Technology/wireStory/polish-govt-reopens-questions-2010-plane-crash-35412039","title\u003dNew Polish Gov\u0027t Reopens Questions About 2010 Plane Crash","author\u003dVanessa Gera ([[Associated Press","AP]])","pub\u003dABC News (US)","date\u003dNovember 25, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["title","date","title","date","title","date","title","date","title","date","title","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"Investigators blame pilot error for AirAsia crash into Java Sea","wikiTitle":"Investigators_blame_pilot_error_for_AirAsia_crash_into_Java_Sea","wid":2623481,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-14T23:03:44Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dDivers retrieve 100th corpse from Java Sea jet crash, date\u003dFebruary 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAirAsia disaster: Bodies, wreckage found, date\u003dDecember 30, 2014]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAirAsia jet vanishes over Indonesia, 162 missing, date\u003dDecember 28, 2014]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dAir France, pilots union, victims group criticise transatlantic disaster probe, date\u003dAugust 5, 2011]","TEMPLATE[wikinews, title\u003dFinal report blames instrument failure for Adam Air Flight 574 disaster, date\u003dMarch 25, 2008]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.thejakartapost.com/news/2015/12/02/broken-component-pilot-error-led-airasia-crash-knkt.html, title\u003dBroken component, pilot error led to AirAsia crash, author\u003dHans Nicholas Jong, pub\u003dThe Jakarta Post, date\u003dDecember 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bangkokpost.com/news/asia/782829/poor-pilot-emergency-training-behind-airasia-crash-analysts, title\u003dPoor pilot emergency training behind AirAsia crash: analysts, author\u003d[[Agence France-Presse, AFP]], pub\u003dThe Bangkok Post, date\u003dDecember 2, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/dec/01/airasia-crew-actions-caused-jet-to-lose-control-say-crash-investigators, title\u003dAirAsia crash: crew lost control of plane after apparent misunderstanding, author\u003dKate Lamb, pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dDecember 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://kemhubri.dephub.go.id/knkt/ntsc_home/Media_Release/English%20-%20Media%20Release%20Final%20Report%20PK-AXC.pdf, title\u003dMedia Release, author\u003d, pub\u003dNational Transportation Safety Committee, date\u003dDecember 1, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://uk.reuters.com/article/2015/01/27/uk-indonesia-airplane-computer-pilots-ex-idUKKBN0L00X720150127, title\u003dExclusive - AirAsia probe vets possible computer glitch, crew response, author\u003dSiva Govindasamy, Tim Hepher, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dJanuary 27, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.atsb.gov.au/media/24500/final_adamair_pk_kkw_17032008.pdf, title\u003dAircraft Accident Investigation Report KNKT/07.01/08.01.36, author\u003d National Transportation Safety Committee, pub\u003dAustralian Transportation Safety Bureau, date\u003d2008]"],["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://kemhubri.dephub.go.id/knkt/ntsc_aviation/baru/Final%20Report%20PK-AXC.pdf, title\u003dAircraft Accident Investigation Report, PT. Indonesia Air Asia, Airbus A320-216; PK-AXC, Karimata Strait, Coordinate 3Â°37â19âS - 109Â°42â41âE, Republic of Indonesia, 28 December 2014, author\u003d, pub\u003dNational Transportation Safety Committee, date\u003dDecember 1, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Indonesia","description":"Indonesia"},{"id":"National_Transportation_Safety_Committee","description":"National Transportation Safety Committee"},{"id":"Indonesia_AirAsia_Flight_8501","description":"Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501"},{"id":"Java_Sea","description":"Java Sea"},{"id":"Surabaya","description":"Surabaya"},{"id":"Singapore","description":"Singapore"},{"id":"National_Search_and_Rescue_Agency","description":"National Search and Rescue Agency"},{"id":"France","description":"French"},{"id":"South_Korea","description":"South Korea"},{"id":"Malaysia","description":"Malaysia"},{"id":"UK","description":"Brit"},{"id":"AirAsia","description":"AirAsia"},{"id":"Tony_Fernandes","description":"Tony Fernandes"},{"id":"Airbus","description":"the manufacturer"},{"id":"weather","description":"weather"},{"id":"Sulawesi","description":"Sulawesi"},{"id":"Agence_France-Presse","description":"AFP"},{"id":"Air_France_Flight_447","description":"Air France Flight 447"},{"id":"Bureau_of_Enquiry_and_Analysis_for_Civil_Aviation_Safety","description":"BEA"},{"id":"Adam_Air_Flight_574","description":"Adam Air Flight 574"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Related news","Sister links","Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 2, 2015] TEMPLATE[Aviation] Indonesia\u0027s National Transportation Safety Committee yesterday declared pilot error to be behind the crash of Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501. All 162 passengers and crew died when the plane crashed into the Java Sea a year ago. TEMPLATE[image_credit, [[Commons:User:Sabung.hamster, Oka Sudiatmika]]] The TEMPLATE[w, Airbus A320-200] was around 40 minutes from Surabaya\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Juanda International Airport] to Singapore\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Changi International Airport] when it vanished on December 28. Wreckage and bodies were found floating two days later; National Search and Rescue Agency divers led an international recovery effort but over 50 bodies remain lost.","The pilots were facing a fault with the TEMPLATE[w, rudder travel limiter], a part involved in rudder control. They repeatedly received warnings on their TEMPLATE[w, Electronic Centralised Aircraft Monitor, Electronic Centralized Aircraft Monitoring (ECAM) system]. The first three times Indonesian Pilot Iriyanto and French co-pilot Remi Emmanuel Plesel followed correct procedure only for the fault to recur. The fourth time, they tried something else \u0026mdash; based on TEMPLATE[w, Flight Data Recorder] readouts, investigators believe they reset power to their Flight Augmentation Computers.","The computers are principally responsible for rudder control and aircraft stability. With both computers switched off, the entire TEMPLATE[w, fly-by-wire] system of semi-automation disconnected, as did the TEMPLATE[w, autopilot] and TEMPLATE[w, autothrust] systems. The pilots were now left to fly entirely manually, without automation that protects the aircraft from entering unusual and dangerous positions.","A miscommunication followed. Iriyanto asked Plesel, who was flying, to \"pull down\". Plesel pulled the controls down, which pitched the nose up; Iriyanto had wanted to descend. The flight ascended without permission through 36,000ft with a TEMPLATE[w, ground speed] of 353TEMPLATE[w, knot (unit), knts]. The aircraft would normally be travelling faster, with a nearby TEMPLATE[w, Emirates (airline), Emirates] jet at a ground speed of 503knts at 36,000ft. The aircraft also banked as the disengagement of automation left the rudder off-centre. TEMPLATE[image_credit, Antonio P. Turretto Ramos, (TEMPLATE)]TEMPLATE[w, US Navy] The AirAsia flight reached 38,000ft and entered a TEMPLATE[w, aerodynamic stall, stall]. The crew did not manage to regain control. The 155 passengers and seven crew died when the plane hit the sea. Most were Indonesians, but for three South Koreans, one Malaysian, one Brit, and French national Plesel.","The fault was traced to cracked TEMPLATE[w, solder] on a circuit board. It had repeatedly occurred in the weeks before the crash. The investigation concluded maintenance failings contributed to the disaster, but Muhammad Alwi of the Indonesian Transportation Ministry said \"Repeated trouble in maintenance is a normal thing[...] If the trouble is fixed in accordance with the manual maintenance procedures, then it\u0027s alright\".","Investigators believe the solder crack is attributable to extreme temperature changes in the unprotected compartment near the tail that houses the component.","The investigation further found the flight crew were untrained in recovering from extreme events. AirAsia boss Tony Fernandes said yesterday \"there is much to be learned here for AirAsia, the manufacturer and the aviation industry... We will not leave any stone unturned to make sure the industry learns from this tragic incident\".","The report also dismisses weather as a contributory factor. The flight was diverting around storms in the area.","Iriyanto and Plessel had over 8,000 hours experience between them. Iriyanto had a decade of experience training other pilots, and previous employers include the air force. They spent three minutes struggling to regain control as the pane fell to the sea. Some bodies were recovered around 1,000km away near Sulawesi.","AFP spoke to Terence Fan, an air industry expert from TEMPLATE[w, Singapore Management University], who said \"It\u0027s a scenario that has played out in air accidents in the past[...] Pilots are either distracted by a faulty equipment or cannot properly solve the issue and something else is brewing in the background.\"","One such accident was the loss of Air France Flight 447 in 2009 into the Atlantic. It was investigated by the BEA of France, which also assisted the AirAsia probe. The BEA issued recommendations on how to train pilots after the Air France crash. Ex-BEA boss Jean-Paul Troadec said to AFP \"Several recommendations of the (BEA) on the subject of pilot training were clearly not implemented by [AirAsia].\"","Indonesia saw such an accident on New Years\u0027 Day 2007 when Adam Air Flight 574 crashed into the Makasser Strait near Sulawesi. The plane suffered a failure on a navigational instrument. While pilots were troubleshooting for this navigational system they first unintentionally disconnected the autopilot, then lost control and crashed into the sea.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501] TEMPLATE[sisters, commons, Category:Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia","description":"Category:Indonesia"},{"id":"Category:Disasters_and_accidents","description":"Category:Disasters and accidents"},{"id":"Category:Transport","description":"Category:Transport"},{"id":"Category:Aviation","description":"Category:Aviation"},{"id":"Category:Indonesia_AirAsia_Flight_8501","description":"Category:Indonesia AirAsia Flight 8501"},{"id":"Category:Java_Sea","description":"Category:Java Sea"},{"id":"Category:National_Search_and_Rescue_Agency","description":"Category:National Search and Rescue Agency"},{"id":"Category:National_Transportation_Safety_Committee","description":"Category:National Transportation Safety Committee"},{"id":"Category:Weather","description":"Category:Weather"},{"id":"Category:Iain_Macdonald_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Iain Macdonald (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:Sulawesi","description":"Category:Sulawesi"},{"id":"Category:Singapore","description":"Category:Singapore"},{"id":"Category:Juanda_International_Airport","description":"Category:Juanda International Airport"},{"id":"Category:Changi_International_Airport","description":"Category:Changi International Airport"},{"id":"Category:South_Korea","description":"Category:South Korea"},{"id":"Category:Korean_Peninsula","description":"Category:Korean Peninsula"},{"id":"Category:Malaysia","description":"Category:Malaysia"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:France","description":"Category:France"},{"id":"Category:Aerodynamic_stalls","description":"Category:Aerodynamic stalls"},{"id":"Category:AirAsia","description":"Category:AirAsia"},{"id":"Category:Tony_Fernandes","description":"Category:Tony Fernandes"},{"id":"Category:Bureau_of_Enquiry_and_Analysis_for_Civil_Aviation_Safety","description":"Category:Bureau of Enquiry and Analysis for Civil Aviation Safety"},{"id":"Category:Air_France_Flight_447","description":"Category:Air France Flight 447"},{"id":"Category:Adam_Air_Flight_574","description":"Category:Adam Air Flight 574"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["December 2, 2015"]},{"name":"Aviation","description":[]},{"name":"image_credit","description":["[[Commons:User:Sabung.hamster","Oka Sudiatmika]]"]},{"name":"w","description":["Airbus A320-200"]},{"name":"w","description":["Juanda International 