{"title":"Car bombing kills Yemen government official; ISIS claims responsibility","wikiTitle":"Car_bombing_kills_Yemen_government_official;_ISIS_claims_responsibility","wid":2633626,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-18T20:00:50Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/yemen-governor-killed-in-suicide-car-bombing-a6762116.html, title\u003dYemen governor killed in Isis-claimed \u0027car bombing\u0027, author\u003dSamuel Osborne and (TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Independent, date\u003dDecember 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/yemens-aden-governor-killed-suicide-car-bombing-sources-075933897.html, title\u003dYemen\u0027s Aden governor killed in car bombing claimed by Islamic State, author\u003dMohammed Mukhashaf ((TEMPLATE)), pub\u003dYahoo! News, date\u003dDecember 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.jordantimes.com/news/region/governor-yemen%E2%80%99s-aden-killed-car-bomb-claimed-daesh, title\u003dGovernor of Yemenâs Aden killed in car bomb claimed by Daesh, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Jordan Times, date\u003dDecember 6, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[Yemen] TEMPLATE[image, Brian Harrington Spier] Yesterday, at least seven people including TEMPLATE[w, Aden, Yemen, Aden], TEMPLATE[w, Yemen] governor TEMPLATE[w, Jaafar Mohammed Saad] died in a car bomb attack on their convoy in the city of Aden, according to local officials. An online claim of responsibility on behalf of militant group TEMPLATE[w, ISIS] called Saad a \"tyrant\".","An online post purportedly from the group claimed they detonated the bomb as Saad\u0027s convoy passed where the car was parked.  The post shared photos purporting to show Saad\u0027s vehicle passing the parked car, and the following explosion.","People as much as 10TEMPLATE[w, kilometre, km] away reported hearing the explosion, and medics said it left victims\u0027 bodies unrecognizable. Photos supposedly of the attack showed a burning, wrecked car. Aden\u0027s Jumhoriya Hospital treated the victims.","The online statement threatened to \"chop off\" the \"rotten heads\" of Yemen\u0027s \"infidels\", and said more attacks are coming.","TEMPLATE[w, Iran]-backed TEMPLATE[w, Houthi] rebels, who follow TEMPLATE[w, Shia Islam], have taken over Yemen\u0027s capital of TEMPLATE[w, Sanaa]. Until just recently, President TEMPLATE[w, Abed Rabbo Mansour Hadi, Abed Rabbo Mansour Hadi\u0027s] government operated for several months in TEMPLATE[w, Saudi Arabia], which has led a coalition involving air strikes against the rebels.","Yemeni fatalities in ISIS-claimed bombings this year number reportedly around 159. Yemeni fatalities since March, when Saudi Arabia\u0027s pro-Hadi airstrikes began, number at least 5,700 according to the United Nations.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:Aden,_Yemen","description":"Category:Aden, Yemen"},{"id":"Category:Yemen","description":"Category:Yemen"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["December 7, 2015"]},{"name":"Yemen","description":[]},{"name":"image","description":["Brian Harrington Spier"]},{"name":"w","description":["Aden, Yemen","Aden"]},{"name":"w","description":["Yemen"]},{"name":"w","description":["Jaafar Mohammed Saad"]},{"name":"w","description":["ISIS"]},{"name":"w","description":["kilometre","km"]},{"name":"w","description":["Iran"]},{"name":"w","description":["Houthi"]},{"name":"w","description":["Shia Islam"]},{"name":"w","description":["Sanaa"]},{"name":"w","description":["Abed Rabbo Mansour Hadi","Abed Rabbo Mansour Hadi\u0027s"]},{"name":"w","description":["Saudi Arabia"]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/middle-east/yemen-governor-killed-in-suicide-car-bombing-a6762116.html","title\u003dYemen governor killed in Isis-claimed \u0027car bombing\u0027","author\u003dSamuel Osborne and (TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Independent","date\u003dDecember 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://news.yahoo.com/yemens-aden-governor-killed-suicide-car-bombing-sources-075933897.html","title\u003dYemen\u0027s Aden governor killed in car bombing claimed by Islamic State","author\u003dMohammed Mukhashaf ((TEMPLATE))","pub\u003dYahoo! News","date\u003dDecember 6, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.jordantimes.com/news/region/governor-yemen%E2%80%99s-aden-killed-car-bomb-claimed-daesh","title\u003dGovernor of Yemenâs Aden killed in car bomb claimed by Daesh","author\u003d(TEMPLATE)","pub\u003dThe Jordan Times","date\u003dDecember 6, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":[]}
{"title":"UK court remands man in custody over Leytonstone knife attack","wikiTitle":"UK_court_remands_man_in_custody_over_Leytonstone_knife_attack","wid":2634914,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-06-28T19:31:10Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.middleeasteye.net/news/uk-charges-man-attempted-murder-over-leytonstone-knife-attack-1723738817, title\u003dUK charges man with attempted murder over Leytonstone attack, author\u003d, pub\u003dMiddle East Eye, date\u003dDecember 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-england-london-35023517, title\u003dLeytonstone Tube stabbings: Man appears in court, author\u003d, pub\u003dBBC News Online, date\u003dDecember 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v\u003dHX7aVeA-IFg, title\u003dDavid Cameron says \u0027You ain\u0027t no Muslim bruv\u0027, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dYouTube, date\u003dDecember 7, 2015] TEMPLATE[Video]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/SadiqKhan/status/673465076620402688, title\u003dTo defeat extremism we must directly challenge their poisonous ideology, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dDecember 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.newstatesman.com/politics/uk/2015/12/attacker-leytonstone-tube-reportedly-said-syria-during-knife-assault, title\u003dAn attacker at Leytonstone tube reportedly said \"this is for Syria\" during knife assault, author\u003d, pub\u003dNew Statesman, date\u003dDecember 6, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/metpoliceuk/status/673274282898800641, title\u003dCmdr Walton re #Leytonstone, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dDecember 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://twitter.com/jeremycorbyn/status/673270606264160256, title\u003dThe stabbing in Leytonstone is absolutely shocking, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dTwitter, date\u003dDecember 5, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.publications.parliament.uk/pa/cm201516/cmhansrd/cm151202/debtext/151202-0005.htm#1512032000001, title\u003dHouse of Commons Hansard Debates for 02 Dec 2015 (pt 0005), author\u003d, pub\u003dparliament.uk, date\u003dDecember 2, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"United_Kingdom","description":"UK"},{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"Twitter","description":"Twitter"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 8, 2015] TEMPLATE[Crime_and_law] A UK court has remanded a man in custody after he appeared in court over a stabbing incident in the capital London. Muhaydin Mire, a 29-year-old from east London, was charged with attempted murder after reportedly at least two people were injured, one seriously, in TEMPLATE[w, Leytonstone tube station] on Saturday. The suspect, who spoke only to confirm personal details in yesterday\u0027s hearing at TEMPLATE[w, Westminster Magistrates\u0027 Court], is also set to appear at the TEMPLATE[w, Old Bailey] on Friday.","The motivation for the attack is not yet clear, although prosecutors told yesterday\u0027s hearing imagery associated with TEMPLATE[w, Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant, Daesh] was thought to be on the suspect\u0027s phone. Witnesses reportedly heard the suspect shout the words \"this is for Syria\" when the attack occurred. The TEMPLATE[w, UK House of Commons, House of Commons] voted in favour of UK military action against Daesh in Syria three days earlier. The TEMPLATE[w, Metropolitan Police] have said they are treating this attack as a terrorist incident.","TEMPLATE[w, Prime Minister of the United Kingdom, Prime Minister] David Cameron yesterday condemned the attack as \"hideous\" and praised the public and police response. \"It\u0027s obviously a hideous attack,\" he said, \"and we\u0027ve all seen pictures of it and read about it and first of all, full credit to the person and people who took on this attacker, and full credit to the very brave police officers who managed to subdue him [...] I think this event simply showed again what brilliant and brave and dedicated people there are when it comes to our police officers.\" Earlier, TEMPLATE[w, Labour Party (UK), Labour Party] leader TEMPLATE[w, Jeremy Corbyn] said: \"The stabbing in Leytonstone is absolutely shocking. My thoughts are with the victim and his family.\"","The Prime Minister also endorsed the sentiment of the phrase \u0027You ain\u0027t no Muslim, bruv\u0027, which one man is heard to shout in video of the suspect\u0027s arrest, and which subsequently became a Twitter trend. \"Some of us have dedicated speeches and media appearances and soundbites and everything to this subject,\" Cameron said, \"but \u0027you ain\u0027t no Muslim, bruv\u0027 said it all much better than I ever could and thank you because that will be applauded around the country.\" Additionally, TEMPLATE[w, Sadiq Khan], Labour Party candidate for TEMPLATE[w, Mayor of London], used the hashtag in a tweet in which he added: \"To defeat extremism we must directly challenge their poisonous ideology\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, December 2015 Leytonstone tube station attack]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Crime_and_law","description":"Category:Crime and law"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:England","description":"Category:England"},{"id":"Category:United_Kingdom","description":"Category:United Kingdom"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Ryan_Peteranna_(Wikinewsie)","description":"Category:Ryan Peteranna (Wikinewsie)"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Jeremy_Corbyn","description":"Category:Jeremy Corbyn"}],"templates":[