{"title":"Petition calls for Trump UK ban","wikiTitle":"Petition_calls_for_Trump_UK_ban","wid":2640205,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-20T21:09:47Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-35052505, title\u003d Trump UK ban petition passes 300,000 signatures, author\u003d, pub\u003d BBC News Online, date\u003d December 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/uk-scotland-scotland-politics-35054360, title\u003d Donald Trump: Robert Gordon University strips honorary degree, author\u003d, pub\u003d BBC News Online, date\u003d December 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://uk.reuters.com/article/us-usa-election-trump-defense-idUKKBN0TR1KY20151209, title\u003d Muslim proposal prompts calls to ban Trump from UK, Israel, author\u003d  John Whitesides, pub\u003d Reuters, date\u003d December 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.theguardian.com/us-news/2015/dec/08/donald-trump-muslim-ban-republican-party-chaos, title\u003d Donald Trump\u0027s Muslim ban plan plunges Republican party into chaos, author\u003d  Tom McCarthy, Ben Jacobs, Sabrina Siddiqui, Ryan Felton, Kate Lamb, pub\u003d The Guardian, date\u003d December 9, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-35047105, title\u003d Trumpâs Muslim ban call \u0027endangers US security\u0027, author\u003d, pub\u003d BBC News Online, date\u003d December 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://www.bbc.co.uk/news/world-us-canada-35033747, title\u003d Is Donald Trump destroying the Republican Party?, author\u003d Anthony Zurcher, pub\u003d BBC News Online, date\u003d December 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://edition.cnn.com/2015/12/07/us/san-bernardino-shooting/, title\u003d San Bernardino shooters were radicalized \u0027for quite some time,\u0027 FBI says, author\u003d  Faith Karimi, Catherine E. Shoichet, Dana Ford, pub\u003d CNN, date\u003d December 8, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d http://edition.cnn.com/2015/12/06/politics/obama-oval-office-address-isis-terror/index.html, title\u003d Obama: \u0027This was an act of terrorism\u0027, author\u003d  Stephen Collinson, pub\u003d CNN, date\u003d December 7, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003d https://www.donaldjtrump.com/press-releases/donald-j.-trump-statement-on-preventing-muslim-immigration, title\u003d Donald J. Trump Statement on Preventing Muslim Immigration, author\u003d Press release, pub\u003d Donald J. Trump, date\u003d December 7, 2015]"],["Petition \u0026mdash; Block Donald J Trump from UK entry"]],"links":[{"id":"Donald_Trump","description":"Donald Trump"},{"id":"Paul_Ryan","description":"Paul Ryan"},{"id":"Hillary_Clinton","description":"Hillary Clinton"},{"id":"John_Kerry","description":"John Kerry"},{"id":"Islamic_State","description":"Islamic State"},{"id":"London","description":"London"},{"id":"David_Cameron","description":"David Cameron"},{"id":"Boris_Johnson","description":"Boris Johnson"}],"externalLinks":[{"id":"https://petition.parliament.uk/petitions/114003","description":"Petition \u0026mdash; Block Donald J Trump from UK entry"}],"sections":["Sources","External links"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 9, 2015] TEMPLATE[2016_US_Presidential_Election] A petition reached over 300,000 signatures today urging Donald Trump, considered the front runner to become the TEMPLATE[w, Republican Party (United States), Republican Party]\u0027s candidate for President of the TEMPLATE[w, United States], be banned from entering the TEMPLATE[w, United Kingdom]. This follows Mr Trump\u0027s comments that TEMPLATE[w, Islam, Muslims] should be blocked from entering the US.","Also, TEMPLATE[w, Scotland]\u0027s First Minister, TEMPLATE[w, Nicola Sturgeon], removed Trump from his role as business ambassador for Scotland.","On Monday, Mr Trump said he wants a \"total and complete shutdown of Muslims entering the US\" until the country can understand \"what the hell is going on\" with regard to terrorism. He said in a statement that a large number of Muslims show \"great hatred towards Americans\".","Trump\u0027s comments on Monday came days after a shooting in TEMPLATE[w, San Bernardino, California, San Bernardino], TEMPLATE[w, California] by Syed Rizwan Farook and his wife Tashfeen Malik, in which fourteen people were killed. US President TEMPLATE[w, Barack Obama] said in an address from the TEMPLATE[w, Oval Office] on Sunday the attack was an act of terrorism.","Donald Trump\u0027s statement has been widely criticised, including by members of his own political party. Republican TEMPLATE[w, Matt Moore (politician), Matt Moore] said the policy is a \"bad idea\" and Speaker of the TEMPLATE[w, United States House of Representatives, House] Paul Ryan said \"this is not Conservatism\".","TEMPLATE[w, Democratic Party (United States), Democrat] candidate for President Hillary Clinton described Trump\u0027s comments as \"shameful\". Secretary of State John Kerry argued Trump\u0027s statement would not help in the ongoing fight against Islamic State (IS), saying his remarks were \"not constructive\".","Trump argued that his policy idea is \"no different\" to that of former President TEMPLATE[w, Franklin D. Roosevelt\u0027s] policy which saw large-scale confinement of Japanese US citizens in internment camps following Japan\u0027s attacks on TEMPLATE[w, Pearl Harbor] in 1941. Mr Trump also said the policy should not be implemented on Muslims currently living within the US.","Kassem Allie from the TEMPLATE[w, Islamic Center of America], accused Trump of evoking fear \"reminiscent of TEMPLATE[w, Nazi Germany, Nazi Germany] and TEMPLATE[w, Joseph Stalin, Stalin]\". TEMPLATE[w, The Pentagon] expressed concern Trump\u0027s demands could be counterproductive in the fight against IS, saying it \"bolsters Isil\u0027s narrative\".","Mr Trump also said on Tuesday that police in London are \"afraid for their lives\" in some areas because of radicalisation in the city. These comments were rebuffed by the United Kingdom Prime Minister David Cameron who said Trump was \"simply wrong\" and Mayor of London Boris Johnson said the claim was \"ridiculous\".","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"},{"id":"Category:Middle_East","description":"Category:Middle East"},{"id":"Category:Islamic_State_of_Iraq_and_the_Levant","description":"Category:Islamic State of Iraq and the Levant"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:Islam","description":"Category:Islam"},{"id":"Category:Donald_Trump","description":"Category:Donald Trump"},{"id":"Category:Republican_Party_(United_States)","description":"Category:Republican Party (United States)"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:Federal_Election_Commission_of_the_United_States","description":"Category:Federal Election Commission of the United States"},{"id":"Category:Elections","description":"Category:Elections"},{"id":"Category:2016_United_States_presidential_election","description":"Category:2016 United States presidential election"},{"id":"Category:Religion","description":"Category:Religion"},{"id":"Category:Scotland","description":"Category:Scotland"},{"id":"Category:Nicola_Sturgeon","description":"Category:Nicola Sturgeon"},{"id":"Category:Paul_Ryan","description":"Category:Paul Ryan"},{"id":"Category:Hillary_Clinton","description":"Category:Hillary Clinton"},{"id":"Category:John_Kerry","description":"Category:John Kerry"},{"id":"Category:London","description":"Category:London"},{"id":"Category:David_Cameron","description":"Category:David Cameron"},{"id":"Category:Boris_Johnson","description":"Category:Boris Johnson"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["December 9, 2015"]},{"