s the first man to be booked in the 9th minute. In the 18th minute, TEMPLATE[w, Aaron Ramsey] was yellow carded. Later, in the 29th minute, Ramsey assisted TEMPLATE[w, Olivier Giroud] and the Frenchman scored the first goal of the match. The Gunners needed a win bigger than 0\u0026ndash;1 in order to advance to the Last 16 knockout round of TEMPLATE[w, 2015â16 UEFA Champions League]. The first half ended in 0\u0026ndash;1.","In the 49th minute, Giroud scored the second goal, assisted by TEMPLATE[w, Joel Campbell]. Giroud was booked for his foul in the 63rd minute. TEMPLATE[w, Omar Elabdellaoui] committed a TEMPLATE[w, Fouls and misconduct (association football), handball] in the penalty area and was yellow carded in the 66th minute. Arsenal was awarded a penalty kick. Giroud successfully converted the penalty into a goal, completing a hat-trick for his first time for Arsenal. The match ended 0\u0026ndash;3 and Arsenal qualified for the Last 16. Olympiakos, standing third in the group table, qualified for the TEMPLATE[w, UEFA Europa League].","Giroud was awarded the man of the match.","TEMPLATE[clear] TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[footballbox, date\u003d December 9, 2015, team1\u003d (TEMPLATE), score\u003d 0\u0026ndash;3, report\u003d(0\u0026ndash;1) \u0027\u0027\u0027HT\u0027\u0027\u0027, team2\u003d (TEMPLATE), goals1\u003d (TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE), goals2\u003d (TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) Olivier Giroud\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) Olivier Giroud\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) Olivier Giroud, stadium\u003d (TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE), attendance\u003d 31,388, referee\u003d [[File:Flag of Italy.svg, 30px, link\u003d, border]] (TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE)]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:England CAT:Europe CAT:Football (soccer) CAT:Sports CAT:Greece CAT:Arsenal F.C. CAT:ArsÃ¨ne Wenger CAT:Football Match Reports"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:UEFA_Champions_League_Match_Reports","descrip