{"title":"UEFA Champions League 2015-2016: Lewandowski scores twice in group stage match against Dinamo Zagreb","wikiTitle":"UEFA_Champions_League_2015-2016:_Lewandowski_scores_twice_in_group_stage_match_against_Dinamo_Zagreb","wid":2642549,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2015-12-21T18:35:15Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.goal.com/en-india/match/dinamo-zagreb-vs-bayern-m%C3%BCnchen/2146839/live-commentary?ICID\u003dMP_MS_3, title\u003dDinamo Zagreb 0 - 2 Bayern MÃ¼nichen LIVE Commentary, author\u003d, pub\u003dGoal.com, date\u003dDecember 10, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.theguardian.com/football/2015/dec/09/dinamo-zagreb-bayern-munich-champions-league-match-report, title\u003dRobert Lewandowski helps Bayern Munich ease past Dinamo Zagreb, author\u003d(TEMPLATE), pub\u003dThe Guardian, date\u003dDecember 9, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Germany","description":"German"},{"id":"Bayern_Munich","description":"Bayern Munich"},{"id":"Croatia","description":"Croatian"},{"id":"Arsenal_F.C.","description":"Arsenal"},{"id":"Greece","description":"Greek"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 12, 2015] TEMPLATE[football] On Wednesday, German football club Bayern Munich defeated Croatian football club TEMPLATE[w, GNK Dinamo Zagreb, Dinamo Zagreb] in a TEMPLATE[w, UEFA Champions League] group stage match played TEMPLATE[w, Stadion Maksimir], TEMPLATE[w, Zagreb].","Bayern had a greater ball possession. The match saw three TEMPLATE[w, yellow card (association football), yellow cards], all for the home side. A total of 16 fouls were committed in the match. Zagreb defender TEMPLATE[w, GonÃ§alo Santos] was the first man to be booked for committing a foul on Lewandowski in the 31st minute and Munich won a free kick. TEMPLATE[w, Xabi Alonso] took the kick but it was just wide. First half ended in 0\u0026ndash;0.","In the second half, TEMPLATE[w, Thomas MÃ¼ller] was substituted in for TEMPLATE[w, Franck RibÃ©ry] in the 47th minute. Later, in the 61th minute, Thomas MÃ¼ller assisted TEMPLATE[w, Robert Lewandowski] and he scored a header, making it 1\u0026ndash;0 lead for the visitors. Lewandowski doubled the lead in the 64th minute, assisted by TEMPLATE[w, Sebastian Rode].","TEMPLATE[w, Josip PivariÄ] was yellow carded in the 73th minute. In the 87th minute, TEMPLATE[w, Eduardo Carvalho] was yellow carded for bringing down Arturo Vidal in the penalty area. Bayern won a penalty kick, but MÃ¼ller hit the woodwork. The match ended 0\u0026ndash;2  while Bayern had already qualified for the next stage.","Bayern Munich and Arsenal advanced to the Last 16 knockout stage of TEMPLATE[w, 2015â16 UEFA Champions League].","Zagreb ended fourth in the table and their European journey for this season ended. Greek TEMPLATE[w, Olympiacos F.C., Olympiacos], being third in the table after 3\u0026ndash;0 defeat at home by Arsenal moved to TEMPLATE[w, UEFA Europa League].","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay] TEMPLATE[clear]","TEMPLATE[footballbox, date\u003d December 9, 2015, team1\u003d (TEMPLATE), score\u003d 0\u0026ndash;2, report\u003d(0\u0026ndash;0) \u0027\u0027\u0027HT\u0027\u0027\u0027, team2\u003d [[Bayern Munich, Bayern MÃ¼nich]], goals1\u003d (TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE), goals2\u003d (TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE), stadium\u003d (TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE), attendance\u003d 19,681, referee\u003d [[File:Flag of Sweden.svg, 30px, link\u003d, border]] (TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE)]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Germany CAT:Football (soccer) CAT:Sports CAT:Europe CAT:Croatia CAT:FC Bayern MÃ¼nchen"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Football_Match_Reports","description":"Category:Football Match Reports"},{"id":"Category:UEFA_Champions_League_Match_Reports","description":"Category:UEFA Champions League Match Reports"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["December 12, 2015"]},{"name":"