{"title":"Chennaiyin FC score late goal, beat Goa 3-2 to win Indian Super League 2015","wikiTitle":"Chennaiyin_FC_score_late_goal,_beat_Goa_3-2_to_win_Indian_Super_League_2015","wid":2669969,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-09-12T12:07:02Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.indiansuperleague.com/news/3495-chennai-beat-goa-in-a-3-2-thriller-to-become-hero-isl-2015-champions, title\u003dChennai beat Goa in a 3-2 thriller to become Hero ISL 2015 champions, author\u003d, pub\u003dIndian Super League, date\u003dDecember 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.goal.com/en-india/match/goa-vs-chennaiyin-fc/2177113/live-commentary?ICID\u003dMP_MS_3, title\u003dGoa 2 - 3 Chennaiyin FC, author\u003d, pub\u003dGoal.com, date\u003dDecember 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.goal.com/en-india/match/goa-vs-chennaiyin-fc/2177113/report?ICID\u003dMP_MS_5, title\u003dGoa 2 - 3 Chennaiyin FC, author\u003dRahul Bali, pub\u003dGoal.com, date\u003dDecember 20, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 20, 2015] TEMPLATE[football] Today, TEMPLATE[w, Chennai]-based football club TEMPLATE[w, Chennaiyin FC] defeated TEMPLATE[w, FC Goa] 3\u0026ndash;2 at TEMPLATE[w, Fatorda Stadium] in TEMPLATE[w, Margao] in the TEMPLATE[w, Indian Super League] final.","The match saw five TEMPLATE[w, yellow card (association football), yellow cards], two for the home side. Chennai\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Mehrajuddin Wadoo] was the first one to be booked in the 18th minute. In the 33rd minute, Goa\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Leonardo da Silva Moura, Moura]\u0027s shot was deflected by Wadoo. With a single booking, the first half ended 0\u0026ndash;0.","In the second half, in the 53rd minute, TEMPLATE[w, Pronay Halder] committed a foul on Chennai\u0027s TEMPLATE[w, Stiven Mendoza] in the penalty area, and the visitors were awarded a penalty kick. Stepping forward for the kick, TEMPLATE[w, Bruno Pelissari]\u0027s kick was saved by TEMPLATE[w, Laxmikant Kattimani] but the ball bounced back, and Pelissari made no mistake, scoring. Chennai got a 1\u0026ndash;0 lead.","TEMPLATE[w, Thoi Singh] was booked in the 57th minute. Halder, in the 58th minute, assisted TEMPLATE[w, Thongkhosiem Haokip] and the Indian footballer scored an equaliser for the home side. TEMPLATE[w, GrÃ©gory Arnolin] received a yellow card in the 60th minute for protesting the referee\u0027s decision. Chennai was awarded another penalty kick. TEMPLATE[w, Stiven Mendoza] stood up for the penalty, but missed.","Table-turning events took place in the dying moments of the game. TEMPLATE[w, Jofre] scored a goal in the 87th minute. A minute later, he was yellow-carded; but, Goa had a 2\u0026ndash;1 lead. Goa\u0027s goalie Laxmikant Kattimani scored an TEMPLATE[wikt, own goal] for a 2\u0026ndash;2 equaliser and in the additional time, Mendoza netted a goal assisted by TEMPLATE[w, Jayesh Rane]. Next minute, Mendoza was yellow-carded, but the final whistle blew a few moments later, and Chennaiyin FC won the second edition of the Indian Super League in the 3\u0026ndash;2 goal tally. TEMPLATE[haveyoursay] TEMPLATE[clear]","TEMPLATE[footballbox, date\u003d December 20, 2015\u003cbr\u003e19:00 (TEMPLATE) (1330 (TEMPLATE)), team1\u003d(TEMPLATE), score\u003d 2\u0026ndash;3, team2\u003d (TEMPLATE), report\u003d (0\u0026ndash;0) \u0027\u0027\u0027HT\u0027\u0027\u0027, goals1\u003d (TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) Jofre\u003cbr\u003e, goals2\u003d (TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) (TEMPLATE)\u003cbr\u003e(TEMPLATE) Stiven Mendoza, stadium\u003d (TEMPLATE), (TEMPLATE), attendance\u003d, referee\u003d]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]","CAT:Football (soccer) CAT:Sports CAT:India CAT:Fo