{"title":"Slovenians reject referendum to recognize same-sex marriage","wikiTitle":"Slovenians_reject_referendum_to_recognize_same-sex_marriage","wid":2670669,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-01-12T19:09:23Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/12/21/europe/slovenia-rejects-same-sex-marriage/index.html, title\u003dSlovenia rejects same-sex marriage by large margin in referendum, author\u003dTim Hume, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dDecember 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/21/world/social-issues-world/mainly-catholic-slovenia-rejects-gay-marriage-in-referendum/, title\u003dMainly-Catholic Slovenia rejects gay marriage in referendum, pub\u003dAgence France-Presse, date\u003dDecember 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/us-slovenia-rights-idUSKBN0U30BS20151220, title\u003dSlovenia rejects same-sex marriages in a referendum, author\u003dMarja Novak, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dDecember 20, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://bigstory.ap.org/article/16d15856e6fb48c2b836bee331fdd33d/slovenians-vote-whether-uphold-same-sex-marriage-law, title\u003dPreliminary results: Slovenians reject same-sex marriage law, author\u003dAli Zerdin, pub\u003dAssociated Press, date\u003dDecember 20, 2015]"]],"links":[{"id":"Slovenia","description":"Slovenians"},{"id":"same-sex_marriage","description":"same-sex marriage"},{"id":"Roman_Catholicism","description":"Roman Catholicism"},{"id":"European_Union","description":"European Union"},{"id":"France","description":"France"},{"id":"Spain","description":"Spain"}],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 22, 2015] TEMPLATE[Slovenia] On Sunday, Slovenians voted on a referendum to legalize same-sex marriage. The referendum failed to pass, with opposing majority.","Slovenia, whose population largely practice Roman Catholicism, neither recognizes marriage between nor allows full child adoption by two persons of the same sex. Even as a member of the European Union, its position has not changed.","The issue has been still debated in the country. In 2012, a majority of participating voters opposed a referendum to legalize same-sex marriage.","The government earlier this year passed a law to legally recognize same-sex marriage. However, the law had not been enforced; a civil group translated as For Children or Children Are at Stake demanded a referendum to the top court. The group\u0027s petition for a referendum collected at least 40,000 signatures.","In preliminary results from this year\u0027s elections, around 36.18% out of more than 1.7 million registered voters voted on the referendum. 63.5% voted to oppose the referendum, while 36.5% voted in favor.","Meanwhile, Slovenia allows civil union registration by same-sex couples since 2006. Also it allows them to adopt children of either partner\u0027s previous marriage(s). Thirteen European Countries, such as France and Spain, and five non-European countries legally recognize same-sex marriages.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, Slovenian same-sex marriage referendum, 2015]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Slovenia","description":"Category:Slovenia"},{"id":"Category:Europe","description":"Category:Europe"},{"id":"Category:Same-sex_marriage","description":"Category:Same-sex marriage"},{"id":"Category:LGBT","description":"Category:LGBT"},{"id":"Category:Human_rights","description":"Category:Human rights"},{"id":"Category:Politics_and_conflicts","description":"Category:Politics and conflicts"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["December 22, 2015"]},{"name":"Slovenia","description":[]},{"name":"haveyoursay","description":[]},{"name":"sisters","description":["w","Slovenian same-sex marriage referendum, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/12/21/europe/slovenia-rejects-same-sex-marriage/index.html","title\u003dSlovenia rejects same-sex marriage by large margin in referendum","author\u003dTim Hume","pub\u003dCNN","date\u003dDecember 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.japantimes.co.jp/news/2015/12/21/world/social-issues-world/mainly-catholic-slovenia-rejects-gay-marriage-in-referendum/","title\u003dMainly-Catholic Slovenia rejects gay marriage in referendum","pub\u003dAgence France-Presse","date\u003dDecember 21, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/us-slovenia-rights-idUSKBN0U30BS20151220","title\u003dSlovenia rejects same-sex marriages in a referendum","author\u003dMarja Novak","pub\u003dReuters","date\u003dDecember 20, 2015"]},{"name":"source","description":["url\u003dhttp://bigstory.ap.org/article/16d15856e6fb48c2b836bee331fdd33d/slovenians-vote-whether-uphold-same-sex-marriage-law","title\u003dPreliminary results: Slovenians reject same-sex marriage law","author\u003dAli Zerdin","pub\u003dAssociated Press","date\u003dDecember 20, 2015"]},{"name":"Publish","description":[]},{"name":"Archive","description":[]}],"templatesSchema":["url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date","url","title","author","pub","date"],"highlights":["For Children","Children Are at Stake"]}
{"title":"Suicide bombing in Afghanistan kills six US NATO members","wikiTitle":"Suicide_bombing_in_Afghanistan_kills_six_US_NATO_members","wid":2673380,"lang":"en","namespace":"","integerNamespace":0,"timestamp":"2016-01-14T19:41:37Z","type":"ARTICLE","tables":[],"lists":[["TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.reuters.com/article/us-afghanistan-attack-victims-idUSKBN0U51NJ20151222, title\u003dIdentities revealed for all six U.S. troops killed in Afghanistan attack, author\u003dBarbara Goldberg, pub\u003dReuters, date\u003dDecember 23, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.people.com/article/nypd-detective-joseph-lemm-killed-afghanistan, title\u003dNYPD Detective Is Among 6 Americans Killed in Afghanistan Suicide Bombing: \u0027We Will Miss Him Very Much\u0027, author\u003dTim Nudd, pub\u003dPeople (magazine), date\u003dDecember 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.advocate.com/military/2015/12/22/lesbian-air-force-major-dadt-repeal-advocate-killed-action, title\u003dBREAKING: Lesbian Air Force Major, DADT Repeal Advocate Killed in Action, author\u003dSunnivie Brydum, pub\u003dThe Advocate, date\u003dDecember 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.krgv.com/news/local-news/rio-grande-valley-service-member-killed-in-afghanistan/37085324, title\u003dRio Grande Valley Service Member Killed in Afghanistan, pub\u003dKRGV-TV, date\u003dDecember 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://pix11.com/2015/12/22/second-airman-among-6-killed-in-afghanistan-bombing-identified-as-long-island-man/, title\u003dSecond airman among 6 killed in Afghanistan bombing identified as Long Island man, author\u003dAndrea Cavallier, pub\u003dWPIX-TV, date\u003dDecember 22, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://www.cnn.com/2015/12/21/asia/nato-members-killed-bagram-afghanistan/, title\u003d6 U.S. troops killed in motorcycle bomb attack in Afghanistan, officials say, author\u003dMasoud Popalzai and Barbara Starr, pub\u003dCNN, date\u003dDecember 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttps://www.washingtonpost.com/news/checkpoint/wp/2015/12/21/mass-casualty-in-afghanistan-six-u-s-troops-dead-others-wounded/, title\u003dSix U.S. troops dead, others wounded in apparent suicide attack in Afghanistan, author\u003dDan Lamothe and Pamela Constable, pub\u003dThe Washington Post, date\u003dDecember 21, 2015]","TEMPLATE[source, url\u003dhttp://bigstory.ap.org/article/4ecb0b2938a5456482d12da29ad3a841/afghan-official-taliban-overrun-district-helmand, title\u003dUS troops killed near Bagram, Taliban insurgency intensifies, author\u003dLynne O\u0027Donnell, pub\u003dAssociated Press, date\u003dDecember 21, 2015]"]],"links":[],"externalLinks":[],"sections":["Sister links","Sources"],"paragraphs":["TEMPLATE[date, December 23, 2015] TEMPLATE[Afghanistan] On Monday, a suicide bomber blew himself up on a motorcycle in TEMPLATE[w, Bagram District], TEMPLATE[w, Afghanistan]. The bombing killed six TEMPLATE[w, US] TEMPLATE[w, NATO] service members and injured several others.","According to NATO and Afghan officials, the bombing occurred at 1:30pm TEMPLATE[w, UTC+04:30, local time] in a village near TEMPLATE[w, Bagram Airfield]. Bagram Airfield is located about TEMPLATE[km_to_mi, 40, abbr\u003dyes] north of TEMPLATE[w, Kabul], the Afghan capital.","The bombing killed six US NATO soldiers. The TEMPLATE[w, United States Department of Defense, US Department of Defense] delayed officially releasing their names, following policy, but all the victims have been identified.","One of them is Joseph Lemm, aged 45. Lemm served fifteen years as an officer of the TEMPLATE[w, New York City Police Department] and has a wife and two children.","Another is Adrianna Vorderbruggen, an openly TEMPLATE[w, lesbian] TEMPLATE[w, US Air Force] major. Vorderbruggen advocated repealing TEMPLATE[w, Don\u0027t Ask, Don\u0027t Tell] and is now married to her same-sex partner. The couple has a son.","The others are Peter Taub from TEMPLATE[w, Philadelphia], TEMPLATE[w, Pennsylvania]; Michael Anthony Cinco from TEMPLATE[w, Rio Grande Valley, Texas, Rio Grande Valley], TEMPLATE[w, Texas], age 28; Chester McBride Jr., TEMPLATE[w, Statesboro, Georgia, Statesboro], TEMPLATE[w, Georgia (U.S. state), Georgia]; and Louis Bonacasa, TEMPLATE[w, Coram, New York, Coram], TEMPLATE[w, New York].","The bombing also injured others, including two US military personnel  and, according to an Afghan official, three local police officers.","Via email and TEMPLATE[w, Twitter], the TEMPLATE[w, Taliban], whose regime the US overthrew after invading the country in 2001, claimed responsibility to the bombing.","Currently, about 10,000 US, and less than half as many NATO, military personnel remain in Afghanistan.","TEMPLATE[haveyoursay]","TEMPLATE[sisters, w, 2015 Bagram suicide bombing]","TEMPLATE[Publish] TEMPLATE[Archive]"],"categories":[{"id":"Category:Afghanistan","description":"Category:Afghanistan"},{"id":"Category:NATO","description":"Category:NATO"},{"id":"Category:Asia","description":"Category:Asia"},{"id":"Category:United_States","description":"Category:United States"},{"id":"Category:North_America","description":"Category:North America"},{"id":"Category:New_York,_New_York","description":"Category:New York, New York"},{"id":"Category:New_York","description":"Category:New York"},{"id":"Category:Washington,_D.C.","description":"Category:Washington, D.C."},{"id":"Category:Texas","description":"Category:Texas"},{"id":"Category:Georgia_(U.S._state)","description":"Category:Georgia (U.S. state)"},{"id":"Category:Taliban","description":"Category:Taliban"}],"templates":[{"name":"date","description":["December 23, 2015"]},{"name":"Afghanistan","description":[]},{"name":"w","description":["Bagram District"]},{"name":"w","description":["Afghanistan"]},{"name":"w","description":["US"]},{"name":"w","description":["NATO"]},{"name":"w","description":["UTC+04:30","local time"]},{"name":"w","description":["Bagram Airfield"]},{"name":"km_to_mi","description":["40","abbr\